example: When someone is afraid, they feel fear.
type: The woman was afraid of what she saw.
example_tr: Biror kishi qo'rqqanida, u qo'rquvni his qiladi.
column14: Ayol ko'rgan narsasidan qo'rqib ketdi.

example: To agree is to say “yes” or to think the same way.
type: A: The food is very good in that restaurant. B: I agree with you.
example_tr: Rozi bo'lish - "ha" deb aytish yoki xuddi shunday o'ylash.
column14: Javob: Bu restoranda taomlar juda yaxshi. B: Men siz bilan roziman.

example: When someone is angry, they may want to speak loudly or fight.
type: She didn’t do her homework, so her father is angry.
example_tr: Biror kishi g'azablansa, u baland ovozda gapirishni yoki urishishni xohlaydi.
column14: U uy vazifasini bajarmadi, shuning uchun otasi g'azablangan.

example: To arrive is to get to or reach some place.
type: The bus always arrives at the corner of my street at 4:00.
example_tr: Yetib kelish - biror joyga borish yoki yetib borish.
column14: Avtobus har doim mening ko'chamning burchagiga soat 4:00 da keladi.

example: To attack is to try to fight or to hurt.
type: The man with the sword attacked the other man first.
example_tr: Hujum - jang qilish yoki xafa qilish.
column14: Qilichli odam birinchi bo'lib boshqa odamga hujum qildi.

example: The bottom is the lowest part.
type: The bottom of my shoe has a hole in it.
example_tr: Pastki qismi eng pastki qismidir.
column14: Oyoq kiyimimning tagida teshik bor.

example: When someone is clever, they can solve a hard puzzle or problem.
type: The clever boy thought of a good idea.
example_tr: Agar kimdir aqlli bo'lsa, u qiyin jumboq yoki muammoni hal qilishi mumkin.
column14: Aqlli bola yaxshi fikr o‘ylab topdi.

example: When someone is cruel, they do bad things to hurt others.
type: The cruel man yelled at his sister.
example_tr: Agar kimdir shafqatsiz bo'lsa, u boshqalarga zarar etkazish uchun yomon ishlarni qiladi.
column14: Zolim odam singlisiga baqirdi.

example: If something happens finally, it happens after a long time or at the end.
type: He finally crossed the finish line after five hours of running.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa nihoyat sodir bo'lsa, u uzoq vaqtdan keyin yoki oxirida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Nihoyat u besh soatlik yugurishdan so‘ng marraga yetib keldi.

example: To hide is to try not to let others see you.
type: The other children will hide while you count to 200.
example_tr: Yashirish - boshqalar sizni ko'rmaslikka harakat qilishdir.
column14: 200 ga qadar hisoblaganingizda, qolgan bolalar yashirinadi.

example: To hunt is to look for or search for an animal to kill.
type: Long ago, people hunted with bows and arrows.
example_tr: Ov - o'ldirish uchun hayvonni qidirish yoki qidirish.
column14: Qadim zamonlarda odamlar o'q va kamon bilan ov qilishgan.

example: A lot means a large number or amount of people, animals, things, etc.
type: There are a lot of apples in the basket.
example_tr: Ko'p odamlar, hayvonlar, narsalar va boshqalarning ko'p yoki miqdorini anglatadi.
column14: Savatda juda ko'p olma bor.

example: The middle of something is the center or halfway point.
type: The Canadian flag has a maple leaf in the middle of it.
example_tr: Biror narsaning o'rtasi - markaz yoki yarim nuqta.
column14: Kanada bayrog‘ining o‘rtasida chinor bargi bor.

example: A moment is a second or a very short time.
type: I was only a few moments late for the meeting.
example_tr: Bir lahza - bu soniya yoki juda qisqa vaqt.
column14: Uchrashuvga bir necha daqiqa kechikdim.

example: When someone is pleased, they are happy.
type: She was pleased with the phone call she received.
example_tr: Biror kishi xursand bo'lsa, u xursand bo'ladi.
column14: Qabul qilingan telefon qo'ng'irog'idan mamnun edi.

example: To promise is to say you will do something for sure.
type: He promised to return my key by tomorrow.
example_tr: Va'da berish, albatta, biror narsa qilishingni aytishdir.
column14: U ertaga kalitimni qaytarib berishga va'da berdi.

example: To reply is to give an answer or say back to someone.
type: She asked him what time his meeting was. He replied, “at three.”
example_tr: Javob berish - kimgadir javob berish yoki javob berish.
column14: U undan uchrashuv vaqti nechada bo'lganini so'radi. U "uchda" deb javob berdi.

example: When a person is safe, they are not in danger.
type: Put on your seat belt in the car to be safe.
example_tr: Biror kishi xavfsiz bo'lsa, u xavf ostida emas.
column14: Xavfsiz bo'lish uchun mashinada xavfsizlik kamarini taqing.

example: A trick is something you do to fool another person.
type: His card trick really surprised us.
example_tr: Hiyla - bu boshqa odamni aldash uchun qiladigan narsa.
column14: Uning karta hiylasi bizni chindan ham hayratda qoldirdi.

example: You use well to say that something was done in a good way.
type: The couple can dance quite well.
example_tr: Biror narsa yaxshi yo'l bilan amalga oshirildi deb aytish uchun yaxshi foydalanasiz.
column14: Er-xotin juda yaxshi raqsga tushishi mumkin.

example: An adventure is a fun or exciting thing that you do.
type: Riding in the rough water was an adventure.
example_tr: Sarguzasht - bu siz qiladigan qiziqarli yoki hayajonli narsa.
column14: Qattiq suvda sayr qilish sarguzasht edi.

example: To approach something means to move close to it.
type: The boy approached his school.
example_tr: Biror narsaga yaqinlashish, unga yaqinlashishni anglatadi.
column14: Bola maktabiga yaqinlashdi.

example: Carefully means with great attention, especially to detail or safety.
type: The baby carefully climbed down the Stairs.
example_tr: Ehtiyotkorlik, ayniqsa, tafsilotlarga yoki xavfsizlikka katta e'tibor berishni anglatadi.
column14: Chaqaloq ehtiyotkorlik bilan zinapoyadan pastga tushdi.

example: A chemical is something that scientists use in chemistry.
type: The scientist mixed the chemicals.
example_tr: Kimyoviy olimlar kimyoda foydalanadigan narsadir.
column14: Olim kimyoviy moddalarni aralashtirib yubordi.

example: To create means to make something new.
type: She created an igloo from blocks of snow.
example_tr: Yaratmoq yangi narsa yasamoq demakdir.
column14: U qor bloklaridan iglo yaratdi.

example: Evil describes something or someone bad or cruel, not good.
type: The evil figure scared us all.
example_tr: Yovuzlik yaxshi emas, biror narsani yoki kimnidir yomon yoki shafqatsiz tasvirlaydi.
column14: Yovuz figura barchamizni qo'rqitdi.

example: An experiment is a test that you do to see what will happen.
type: The student did an experiment in science class.
example_tr: Tajriba - bu nima bo'lishini ko'rish uchun qiladigan sinov.
column14: Talaba fan darsida tajriba o'tkazdi.

example: To kill someone or something is to make them die.
type: I killed the fly with a fly swatter.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani o'ldirish, uni o'ldirishdir.
column14: Men chivinni chivin bilan o'ldirdim.

example: A laboratory is a room where a scientist works.
type: My mother works in a laboratory.
example_tr: Laboratoriya - bu olim ishlaydigan xona.
column14: Onam laboratoriyada ishlaydi.

example: Laugh is the sound made when someone is happy or a funny thing occurs.
type: The sound of their laugh filled the room.
example_tr: Kulgi - bu kimdir xursand bo'lganida yoki kulgili voqea sodir bo'lganda chiqarilgan ovoz.
column14: Ularning kulgi ovozi xonani to‘ldirdi.

example: If a sound is loud, it is strong and very easy to hear.
type: The man’s voice was so loud that we all could hear him.
example_tr: Agar tovush baland bo'lsa, u kuchli va eshitish juda oson.
column14: Bu odamning ovozi shunchalik baland ediki, biz hammamiz uni eshitdik.

example: When a person is nervous, they think something bad will happen.
type: The boy became nervous when he heard the news.
example_tr: Inson asabiylashganda, biror yomon narsa yuz beradi deb o'ylaydi.
column14: Bu xabarni eshitgan bola asabiylashdi.

example: A noise is an unpleasant sound.
type: The crying baby made a loud noise.
example_tr: Shovqin - bu yoqimsiz ovoz.
column14: Yig'layotgan go'dak qattiq ovoz chiqardi.

example: A project is a type of work that you do for school or a job.
type: His afternoon work project was to paint the room green.
example_tr: Loyiha - bu maktab yoki ish uchun qiladigan ish turi.
column14: Uning tushdan keyingi ish loyihasi xonani yashil rangga bo'yash edi.

example: To scare someone is to make them feel afraid.
type: My uncle was scared by what he saw in the room.
example_tr: Biror kishini qo'rqitish - uni qo'rqitish.
column14: Amakim xonada ko‘rgan narsasidan qo‘rqib ketdi.

example: A secret is something that you do not tell other people.
type: The two boys were sharing a secret.
example_tr: Sir - bu siz boshqalarga aytmaydigan narsadir.
column14: Ikki yigit bir sirni baham ko'rishdi.

example: To shout is to say something loudly.
type: My boss shouted at me because I was late for work.
example_tr: Baqirmoq - baland ovozda gapirmoq.
column14: Ishga kech qolganim uchun xo‘jayinim menga baqirdi.

example: To smell something means to use your nose to sense it.
type: The two friends smelled the flower.
example_tr: Biror narsani hidlash, uni his qilish uchun burnidan foydalanishni anglatadi.
column14: Ikki do‘st gulni hidladi.

example: If something is terrible, it is very bad.
type: The way he treated his classmate was terrible.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, bu juda yomon.
column14: Uning sinfdoshiga munosabati dahshatli edi.

example: If something is worse, it is of poorer quality than another thing.
type: Business was worse this month than last month.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomonroq bo'lsa, u boshqa narsaga qaraganda sifatsizroqdir.
column14: Bu oyda biznes o'tgan oyga qaraganda yomonroq bo'ldi.

example: An alien is a creature from a different world.
type: The alien came in peace.
example_tr: O'zga sayyoralik - bu boshqa dunyodan kelgan mavjudot.
column14: O'zga sayyoralik tinchlik bilan keldi.

example: If you are among certain things, they are all around you.
type: There was a red apple among the green ones.
example_tr: Agar siz ba'zi narsalar orasida bo'lsangiz, ular sizning atrofingizda.
column14: Yashillar orasida qizil olma ham bor edi.

example: A chart is a list of information.
type: We used a chart to see how we had improved.
example_tr: Diagramma - bu ma'lumotlar ro'yxati.
column14: Biz qanday yaxshilanganimizni ko'rish uchun jadvaldan foydalandik.

example: A cloud is a group of water drops in the sky.
type: The sky was filled with white clouds.
example_tr: Bulut - osmondagi suv tomchilari guruhi.
column14: Osmon oq bulutlarga to'lib ketdi.

example: To comprehend something is to understand it.
type: Henry could not comprehend the message.
example_tr: Biror narsani tushunish - uni tushunish.
column14: Genri bu xabarni tushuna olmadi.

example: To describe is to say or write what someone or something is like.
type: They described their tree as colorful with gold ribbon and a star.
example_tr: Ta'riflash - kimningdir yoki biror narsaning qanday ekanligini aytish yoki yozish.
column14: Ular o'z daraxtini oltin lenta va yulduz bilan rang-barang deb ta'rifladilar.

example: Ever means at any time.
type: Going skiing last winter was the most fun I’ve ever had.
example_tr: Har doim istalgan vaqtda degani.
column14: O'tgan qishda chang'i uchish men uchun eng qiziqarli bo'ldi.

example: To fail means you do not succeed in what you try to do.
type: Since he failed to get the job, he was sad.
example_tr: Muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lish, siz qilmoqchi bo'lgan ishingizda muvaffaqiyat qozonmasligingizni anglatadi.
column14: Ishga kira olmagani uchun u g'amgin edi.

example: Friendly is behaving in a pleasant, kind way toward someone.
type: The friendly animals came up to the girl.
example_tr: Do'stona - bu kimgadir yoqimli, yaxshi munosabatda bo'lish.
column14: Do'stona hayvonlar qizning oldiga kelishdi.

example: A grade is a score or mark given to someone’s work.
type: I managed to get good grades on my report cards.
example_tr: Baho - bu birovning ishiga berilgan ball yoki baho.
column14: Hisobot kartochkalarimdan yaxshi baho olishga muvaffaq bo‘ldim.

example: Instead means in place of.
type: He ate the carrot instead of the ice cream.
example_tr: Buning o'rniga o'rnida degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Muzqaymoq o‘rniga sabzi yedi.

example: A library is a place where you go to read books.
type: The library at school is full of books.
example_tr: Kutubxona - bu kitob o'qish uchun boradigan joy.
column14: Maktab kutubxonasi kitoblar bilan to'la.

example: A planet is a large round thing in space.
type: Saturn is the planet with the ring around it.
example_tr: Sayyora kosmosdagi katta dumaloq narsadir.
column14: Saturn - bu uning atrofida halqasi bo'lgan sayyora.

example: A report is something students write for school.
type: Karen had trouble writing her report.
example_tr: Hisobot - bu o'quvchilar maktab uchun yozadigan narsadir.
column14: Karen hisobot yozishda qiynaldi.

example: Several is more than two but not many.
type: He had to read several books for class.
example_tr: Bir nechta ikkitadan ko'p, lekin ko'p emas.
column14: U dars uchun bir nechta kitoblarni o'qishi kerak edi.

example: To solve something is to find an answer to it.
type: All the students could easily solve the math problem.
example_tr: Biror narsani hal qilish - unga javob topish.
column14: Barcha talabalar matematika muammosini osongina echishlari mumkin edi.

example: If something happens suddenly, it happens quickly and unexpectedly.
type: I was suddenly surprised by the cake my friends brought me.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'satdan sodir bo'lsa, u tez va kutilmaganda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Do'stlarim olib kelgan tort meni birdan hayratda qoldirdi.

example: To suppose is to guess.
type: I suppose I should go home now.
example_tr: Taxmin qilish - taxmin qilish.
column14: Menimcha, hozir uyga borishim kerak.

example: The universe is the known or supposed objects in space.
type: The universe is so large that it cannot be measured.
example_tr: Koinot kosmosdagi ma'lum yoki taxmin qilingan ob'ektlardir.
column14: Koinot shunchalik kattaki, uni o'lchash mumkin emas.

example: To view is to look at something.
type: Michael likes to view himself in the mirror.
example_tr: Ko'rish - biror narsaga qarash.
column14: Maykl o'zini ko'zguda ko'rishni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: When a thing is appropriate, it is right or normal.
type: It’s appropriate to wear a suit when you go to the office.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mos bo'lsa, u to'g'ri yoki normaldir.
column14: Ofisga borganingizda kostyum kiyish o'rinli.

example: To avoid something is to stay away from it.
type: Avoid the broken bottle on the floor.
example_tr: Biror narsadan qochish - undan uzoqlashish.
column14: Erdagi singan shishadan saqlaning.

example: To behave is to act in a particular way, especially to be good.
type: She always behaves well when her father is around.
example_tr: O'zini tutish - muayyan tarzda harakat qilish, ayniqsa yaxshi bo'lish.
column14: Otasi yonida bo'lsa, u doimo o'zini yaxshi tutadi.

example: When someone is calm, they do not get excited or upset.
type: A nice warm bath makes me feel so calm.
example_tr: Biror kishi xotirjam bo'lsa, u hayajonlanmaydi va xafa bo'lmaydi.
column14: Chiroyli iliq vanna meni juda xotirjam his qiladi.

example: Concern is a feeling of worry.
type: I was filled with concern after reading the newspaper.
example_tr: Xavotir - tashvish hissi.
column14: Gazetani o'qib chiqqanimdan keyin tashvishga tushdim.

example: To be content is to be happy and not want more.
type: The baby looked very content sitting on the floor.
example_tr: Qoniqish - bu baxtli bo'lish va ko'proq narsani xohlamaslikdir.
column14: Chaqaloq yerda o‘tirganidan juda mamnun ko‘rindi.

example: If you expect something to happen, you believe it will happen.
type: I expect the bus to be here very soon.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lishini kutsangiz, bu sodir bo'lishiga ishonasiz.
column14: Tez orada avtobus shu yerda bo'lishini kutaman.

example: When something happens frequently, it happens often.
type: We meet frequently, either at the beginning or ending of the week.
example_tr: Biror narsa tez-tez sodir bo'lganda, u tez-tez sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Biz haftaning boshida yoki oxirida tez-tez uchrashamiz.

example: A habit is a thing that you do often.
type: Smoking is a bad habit that can kill you.
example_tr: Odat - bu siz tez-tez qiladigan narsadir.
column14: Chekish sizni o'ldirishi mumkin bo'lgan yomon odatdir.

example: To instruct is to teach.
type: My teacher instructs us in several subjects.
example_tr: Ta'lim berish - o'rgatish.
column14: Ustozim bizga bir nechta fanlardan dars beradi.

example: An issue is an important topic.
type: The men spoke about issues that were important to the people.
example_tr: Muammo muhim mavzu.
column14: Erkaklar xalq uchun muhim bo'lgan masalalar haqida gapirdilar.

example: None means not any of someone or something.
type: He spent all his money. There is none left.
example_tr: Hech kim hech kimni yoki biror narsani anglatmaydi.
column14: U bor pulini sarfladi. Hech kim qolmadi.

example: If a person is patient, they don’t become angry or upset easily.
type: I had to be patient and wait until 5 o’clock to leave.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi sabrli bo'lsa, u tezda g'azablanmaydi yoki xafa bo'lmaydi.
column14: Men sabrli bo'lishim va ketish uchun soat 5 ga qadar kutishim kerak edi.

example: If something is positive, it is good.
type: She has a positive future ahead of her after finishing college.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ijobiy bo'lsa, bu yaxshi.
column14: Kollejni tugatgandan keyin uni ijobiy kelajak kutmoqda.

example: To punish means to make someone suffer for breaking the rules or laws.
type: To punish me, my teacher had me stand in the corner.
example_tr: Jazolash - bu qoidalar yoki qonunlarni buzganlik uchun kimnidir azoblash demakdir.
column14: Meni jazolash uchun o‘qituvchim meni burchakda turishga majbur qildi.

example: To represent is to speak or act for a person or group.
type: My lawyer will represent me in court.
example_tr: Vakillik - bu shaxs yoki guruh uchun gapirish yoki harakat qilish.
column14: Advokatim sudda meni himoya qiladi.

example: To shake is to move back and forth or up and down quickly.
type: When people shake hands, it usually means they agree.
example_tr: Tebranish - tez oldinga va orqaga yoki yuqoriga va pastga harakat qilish.
column14: Odamlar qo'l silkitganda, bu odatda rozi bo'lishlarini anglatadi.

example: To spread is to move quickly to more places.
type: I like to spread butter on my toast.
example_tr: Tarqalish - tezroq ko'proq joylarga ko'chib o'tishdir.
column14: Men tostimga sariyog‘ surishni yaxshi ko‘raman.

example: To stroll means to walk slowly and calmly.
type: My dog and I strolled through the park today.
example_tr: Sayr qilish sekin va xotirjam yurishni anglatadi.
column14: Bugun men itim bilan parkda sayr qildik.

example: A village is a very small town.
type: There are only a few houses in my village.
example_tr: Qishloq juda kichik shaharcha.
column14: Qishlog‘imda bir nechta uy bor.

example: If you are aware of something, you know about it.
type: I was not aware of the ringing phone.
example_tr: Agar biror narsadan xabardor bo'lsangiz, bu haqda bilasiz.
column14: Telefon jiringlaganidan bexabar edim.

example: Badly means in a severe or harmful way.
type: He hurt his arm badly playing with friends.
example_tr: Yomon og'ir yoki zararli ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: U do'stlari bilan o'ynab, qo'lini qattiq jarohatlagan.

example: If something belongs to you, you own it.
type: The blue suit belongs to Paul.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sizga tegishli bo'lsa, siz unga egalik qilasiz.
column14: Moviy kostyum Polga tegishli.

example: To continue something is to keep doing it.
type: She stood under her umbrella as the rain continued to fall.
example_tr: Biror narsani davom ettirish - uni davom ettirish.
column14: Yomg'ir davom etar ekan, u soyabon ostida turdi.

example: An error is something you do wrong.
type: I made an error on my report, so my boss was angry.
example_tr: Xato - bu siz noto'g'ri qilgan narsadir.
column14: Men hisobotimda xato qildim, shuning uchun xo'jayinim g'azablandi.

example: An experience is something you have seen or done.
type: Rock climbing was a fun experience.
example_tr: Tajriba - bu siz ko'rgan yoki qilgan narsadir.
column14: Qoyaga ko'tarilish qiziqarli tajriba edi.

example: A field is a big area of land.
type: The field of flowers looked so pretty.
example_tr: Dala - bu katta er maydoni.
column14: Gullar maydoni juda chiroyli ko'rinardi.

example: To hurt is to do something that makes you feel pain.
type: She hurt her leg falling down the stairs.
example_tr: Ozor berish - bu sizni og'riqli his qiladigan narsani qilishdir.
column14: U zinapoyadan yiqilib, oyog'ini shikastladi.

example: Judgment is the ability to form opinions or decisions.
type: It's good judgment to recycle your aluminum cans.
example_tr: Hukm - bu fikr yoki qaror qabul qilish qobiliyati.
column14: Alyuminiy qutilaringizni qayta ishlash yaxshi qaror.

example: If something likely happens, it will probably happen.
type: I will likely stay at home and watch TV tonight.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, ehtimol bu sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Men bugun kechqurun uyda qolib, televizor ko'raman.

example: If something is normal, it is not strange nor surprising to you.
type: It is normal for me to bathe every night.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa normal bo'lsa, bu siz uchun g'alati va ajablanarli emas.
column14: Men uchun har kecha yuvinish odatiy hol.

example: If something is rare, you do not see it very often.
type: It is rare for him to miss his flight.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kamdan-kam bo'lsa, uni tez-tez ko'rmaysiz.
column14: Uning parvozini o'tkazib yuborishi kamdan-kam uchraydi.

example: To relax is to rest.
type: The frog relaxed in the warm sun.
example_tr: Dam olish - dam olish.
column14: Qurbaqa issiq quyoshda bo'shashdi.

example: To request something is to ask for it.
type: The little girl requested a special gift from Santa Claus.
example_tr: Biror narsani so'rash, uni so'rashdir.
column14: Kichkina qiz Santa Klausdan maxsus sovg'a so'radi.

example: To reside means to live somewhere permanently or for a long time.
type: My brother and his family reside in a lovely house on the beach.
example_tr: Yashash, biror joyda doimiy yoki uzoq vaqt yashashni anglatadi.
column14: Akam va uning oilasi sohildagi go'zal uyda yashaydi.

example: A result is something that happens because of something else.
type: As a result of all the rain, the man had to climb on the roof.
example_tr: Natija - bu boshqa narsa tufayli sodir bo'ladigan narsa.
column14: Butun yomg'ir natijasida odam tomga chiqishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: To roll is to move by turning over and over.
type: You must roll the ball into the pins when you bowl.
example_tr: Dumalamoq - teskari aylanib harakat qilish.
column14: Piyola olayotganda to'pni pinlarga aylantirishingiz kerak.

example: Since is used to talk about a past event still happening now.
type: Since 1992, he has been driving that car.
example_tr: Chunki hozir ham sodir bo'layotgan o'tmishdagi voqea haqida gapirish uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: 1992 yildan beri u ushbu mashinani boshqaradi.

example: If something is visible, it can be seen.
type: The moon and stars were visible in the night sky.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ko'rinadigan bo'lsa, uni ko'rish mumkin.
column14: Kechasi osmonda oy va yulduzlar ko'rindi.

example: If something is wild, it is found in nature.
type: You should be careful around a fox, because it is a wild animal.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yovvoyi bo'lsa, u tabiatda topiladi.
column14: Siz tulki atrofida ehtiyot bo'lishingiz kerak, chunki u yovvoyi hayvon.

example: An advantage is something that helps you.
type: Being tall is an advantage to a basketball player.
example_tr: Afzallik - bu sizga yordam beradigan narsa.
column14: Uzun bo'yli bo'lish basketbolchi uchun afzallikdir.

example: To cause is to make something happen.
type: The cold weather caused her to get sick.
example_tr: Sabab berish - biror narsa sodir bo'lish.
column14: Sovuq havo uning kasallanishiga sabab bo'ldi.

example: A choice is the act or possibility of picking something.
type: I had my choice of five doors to open.
example_tr: Tanlov - biror narsani tanlash harakati yoki imkoniyati.
column14: Men ochadigan beshta eshikni tanladim.

example: A community is a group of people who live together.
type: The kids from my community usually play together.
example_tr: Jamiyat - bu birga yashaydigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Mening mahallamdagi bolalar odatda birga o'ynashadi.

example: To be dead is to not be alive.
type: A dead person is usually buried in the ground.
example_tr: O'lgan bo'lish - tirik bo'lmaslik.
column14: O'lgan odam odatda erga ko'miladi.

example: The distance between two things is how far it is between them.
type: The distance between the Earth and the Moon is 384,400 kilometers.
example_tr: Ikki narsa orasidagi masofa ular orasidagi masofani anglatadi.
column14: Yer va Oy orasidagi masofa 384 400 kilometrni tashkil qiladi.

example: To escape is to run away from something bad.
type: The butterfly could not escape from the cage.
example_tr: Qochish - yomon narsadan qochish.
column14: Kapalak qafasdan qochib qutula olmadi.

example: If you face a problem, you deal with it.
type: My sister and I have to find a better way to face our differences.
example_tr: Agar muammoga duch kelsangiz, uni hal qilasiz.
column14: Singlim va men kelishmovchiliklarga qarshi turishning yaxshiroq yo'lini topishimiz kerak.

example: To follow means to go behind someone and go where they go.
type: The little boy followed his mother home.
example_tr: Tuzatish, birovning orqasidan borish va u borsa, borishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkina bola onasining orqasidan uyga ketdi.

example: Fright is the feeling of being scared.
type: She was filled with fright.
example_tr: Qo'rquv - qo'rquv hissi.
column14: U qo'rquvga to'ldi.

example: A ghost is the spirit of a dead person.
type: Many people are afraid of ghosts.
example_tr: Arvoh - o'lgan odamning ruhi.
column14: Ko'p odamlar arvohlardan qo'rqishadi.

example: An individual is one person.
type: Only one individual could win the bicycle race.
example_tr: Shaxs - bu bir shaxs.
column14: Velosiped poygasida faqat bir kishi g'olib bo'lishi mumkin edi.

example: A pet is an animal that lives with people.
type: Out of all my pets, the dog is my favorite.
example_tr: Uy hayvonlari - bu odamlar bilan yashaydigan hayvon.
column14: Mening barcha uy hayvonlarim orasida it mening eng sevimlisidir.

example: To reach means to arrive at a place.
type: I was happy to finally reach my destination.
example_tr: Yetib kelmoq, bir joyga yetib kelmoq degan ma’noni anglatadi.
column14: Nihoyat manzilimga yetganimdan xursand bo‘ldim.

example: To return is to go back to a place.
type: I was happy to return home to my mom after school.
example_tr: Qaytish - biror joyga qaytish.
column14: Men maktabdan keyin uyga onamning oldiga qaytganimdan xursand bo'ldim.

example: To survive is to stay alive.
type: My dog survived her fall into the water.
example_tr: Omon qolish - tirik qolishdir.
column14: Mening itim suvga tushishidan omon qoldi.

example: To be upset is to be unhappy about something.
type: She was upset because she broke her toy.
example_tr: Xafa bo'lish - biror narsadan norozi bo'lish.
column14: U o'yinchog'ini sindirib tashlaganidan xafa bo'ldi.

example: A voice is the sound a person makes when they talk or sing.
type: He used a microphone, so everyone could hear his voice.
example_tr: Ovoz - bu odamning gapirganda yoki qo'shiq aytganda chiqaradigan ovozi.
column14: U mikrofondan foydalangan, shuning uchun hamma uning ovozini eshitishi mumkin edi.

example: The weather is the condition of the air: hot, rainy, windy, etc.
type: The weather can be sunny, rainy, or cold.
example_tr: Ob-havo - havoning holati: issiq, yomg'irli, shamolli va hokazo.
column14: Ob-havo quyoshli, yomg'irli yoki sovuq bo'lishi mumkin.

example: To be wise is to use experience and intelligence to make good choices.
type: Many people believe that owls are very wise animals.
example_tr: Dono bo'lish - tajriba va aqlni to'g'ri tanlash uchun ishlatishdir.
column14: Ko'pchilik boyqushlarning juda dono hayvonlar ekanligiga ishonishadi.

example: To allow something to happen means to let it happen.
type: Having a ticket will allow you to enter the show.
example_tr: Biror narsaning sodir bo'lishiga yo'l qo'yish, uning sodir bo'lishiga yo'l qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Chiptaga ega bo'lish shouga kirish imkonini beradi.

example: To announce something is to make it known.
type: He announced to everyone his new idea for the company.
example_tr: Biror narsani e'lon qilish - uni ma'lum qilish.
column14: U barchaga kompaniya uchun yangi g'oyasini e'lon qildi.

example: When someone or something is beside you, they are next to you.
type: The two brothers stood beside each other.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa sizning yoningizda bo'lsa, ular sizning yoningizda.
column14: Ikki aka-uka bir-birining yonida turishdi.

example: A challenge is something difficult to complete.
type: It was a challenge to climb to the top of the mountain.
example_tr: Qiyinchilik - bu bajarish qiyin narsa.
column14: Tog'ning cho'qqisiga chiqish qiyin edi.

example: To claim means to say that something is true.
type: He claimed to know why the country’s laws were weak.
example_tr: Da'vo qilish, biror narsaning haqiqat ekanligini aytishni anglatadi.
column14: U mamlakat qonunlari nima uchun zaif ekanligini bilishini da'vo qildi.

example: The condition of someone or something is the state that they are in.
type: The patient’s condition was very good.
example_tr: Biror kishining yoki biror narsaning holati - bu ularning holati.
column14: Bemorning ahvoli juda yaxshi edi.

example: To contribute to something means to do something to make it successful.
type: We decided to contribute money to the new hospital.
example_tr: Biror narsaga hissa qo'shish, uni muvaffaqiyatli qilish uchun biror narsa qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Biz yangi shifoxonaga pul ajratishga qaror qildik.

example: A difference is a way that something is not like other things.
type: The biggest difference between the birds is the color of their feathers.
example_tr: Farq - bu narsaning boshqa narsalarga o'xshamasligi.
column14: Qushlar orasidagi eng katta farq ularning patlarining rangidir.

example: To divide something is to make it into smaller parts.
type: We divided the pizza.
example_tr: Biror narsani bo'lish - uni kichikroq qismlarga bo'lish.
column14: Biz pizzani bo'laklarga ajratdik.

example: An expert is someone who is very good at doing something.
type: The wizard was an expert at magic.
example_tr: Mutaxassis - bu biror narsa qilishda juda yaxshi odam.
column14: Sehrgar sehrgar edi.

example: If someone or something is famous, they are known to many people.
type: The Eiffel Tower in Paris is very famous.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa mashhur bo'lsa, ular ko'pchilikka ma'lum.
column14: Parijdagi Eyfel minorasi juda mashhur.

example: Force is a person’s strength or power.
type: He used all his force to try and open the door.
example_tr: Kuch - bu insonning kuchi yoki kuchi.
column14: U bor kuchini ishga solib eshikni ochishga harakat qildi.

example: Harm is hurt or problems caused to someone or something.
type: A hot iron can cause great harm if you are not careful.
example_tr: Zarar - bu kimgadir yoki biror narsaga etkazilgan zarar yoki muammolar.
column14: Ehtiyot bo'lmasangiz, issiq dazmol katta zarar etkazishi mumkin.

example: To lay means to put or place in a horizontal or flat position.
type: Don’t lay your socks on the floor.
example_tr: Yotish - gorizontal yoki tekis holatga qo'yish yoki joylashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Paypoqlaringizni erga qo'ymang.

example: Peace is a time without war.
type: A white dove is a symbol for peace.
example_tr: Tinchlik - urushsiz vaqt.
column14: Oq kaptar tinchlik ramzidir.

example: A prince is the son of a king.
type: The prince and the princess were married.
example_tr: Shahzoda - podshohning o'g'li.
column14: Shahzoda va malika turmush qurishdi.

example: To protect someone is to stop them from getting hurt.
type: Firemen protect us from fires.
example_tr: Biror kishini himoya qilish, uni xafa qilishdan to'xtatishdir.
column14: O't o'chiruvchilar bizni yong'inlardan himoya qiladi.

example: To sense something is to know about it without being told.
type: I could sense that he was watching me.
example_tr: Biror narsani his qilish - bu haqda aytmasdan bilishdir.
column14: U meni kuzatib turganini sezdim.

example: When something is sudden, it happens very quickly.
type: He felt a sudden pain in his chest.
example_tr: Biror narsa to'satdan sodir bo'lganda, u juda tez sodir bo'ladi.
column14: U to'satdan ko'kragida og'riqni his qildi.

example: Therefore means for this reason.
type: He is fat. Therefore, he will go on a diet.
example_tr: Shuning uchun bu sababni anglatadi.
column14: U semiz. Shuning uchun u dietaga o'tadi.

example: To accept something that is offered is to take it.
type: I accepted the girl’s very nice gift.
example_tr: Taklif qilingan narsani qabul qilish, uni qabul qilishdir.
column14: Men qizning juda yaxshi sovg'asini qabul qildim.

example: To arrange things is to put them in the right place.
type: Please arrange the bowling pins in order so we can play.
example_tr: Ishlarni tartibga solish - ularni to'g'ri joyga qo'yishdir.
column14: Iltimos, biz o'ynashimiz uchun bouling pinlarini tartibda joylashtiring.

example: To attend something is to go to it.
type: My sister and I attend the same school.
example_tr: Biror narsada qatnashish - unga borish.
column14: Singlim bilan bir maktabda o‘qiymiz.

example: To balance something is to keep it from falling.
type: We saw an elephant balance itself on a ball.
example_tr: Biror narsani muvozanatlash - uni yiqilib tushmaslik.
column14: Biz to'pda filning muvozanatini ko'rdik.

example: A contrast is the sharp difference between two things.
type: The contrast between my parents is very noticeable.
example_tr: Kontrast - bu ikki narsa o'rtasidagi keskin farq.
column14: Ota-onam o'rtasidagi kontrast juda sezilarli.

example: To encourage someone is to make them want to do something.
type: My football coach will encourage us when we are losing.
example_tr: Biror kishini rag'batlantirish, uni biror narsa qilishni xohlashdir.
column14: Mag'lubiyatga uchraganimizda futbol murabbiyim bizga dalda beradi.

example: If someone or something is familiar to you, you know them well.
type: The two friends were very familiar with each other.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa sizga tanish bo'lsa, siz uni yaxshi bilasiz.
column14: Ikki do'st bir-biriga juda tanish edi.

example: To grab is to take a hold of someone or something suddenly.
type: I grabbed a pear from the tree.
example_tr: Qo‘lga olish – birdaniga kimnidir yoki biror narsani ushlab olish.
column14: Men daraxtdan nok oldim.

example: To hang something is to keep it above the ground.
type: I drew a picture of my family, and my mother hung it on the wall.
example_tr: Biror narsani osib qo'yish - uni erdan yuqorida saqlash.
column14: Men oilamning rasmini chizdim, onam uni devorga osib qo'ydi.

example: If something is huge, it is very big.
type: At work, my father drives a huge truck.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa juda katta bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Ishda otam katta yuk mashinasini boshqaradi.

example: If something is necessary, you must do it.
type: It is necessary to have a passport when you travel to a foreign country.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kerak bo'lsa, buni qilishingiz kerak.
column14: Xorijiy davlatga sayohat qilishda pasport bo'lishi shart.

example: A pattern is a way in which something is done or organized.
type: My pattern of brushing my teeth is the same as most people’s.
example_tr: Naqsh - bu biror narsa qilish yoki tartibga solish usuli.
column14: Mening tishlarimni cho'tkalash uslubi ko'pchiliknikiga o'xshaydi.

example: To propose something is to say that it should be done.
type: Santa Claus proposed that I try to be a good boy all year.
example_tr: Biror narsani taklif qilish, buni qilish kerakligini aytishdir.
column14: Santa Klaus menga yil bo'yi yaxshi bola bo'lishga harakat qilishni taklif qildi.

example: A purpose is the reason that you do something.
type: The purpose of exercising is to get into shape.
example_tr: Maqsad - bu biror narsa qilishning sababi.
column14: Mashq qilishning maqsadi - shaklga kirish.

example: To release something is to stop holding it.
type: She released the bird from her hands.
example_tr: Biror narsani ozod qilish - uni ushlab turishni to'xtatish.
column14: U qushni qo'lidan qo'yib yubordi.

example: To require something is to say that it is necessary.
type: We require teachers to have a university degree.
example_tr: Biror narsani talab qilish, zarurligini aytishdir.
column14: Biz o‘qituvchilardan oliy ma’lumotli bo‘lishini talab qilamiz.

example: If something is single, then there is only one.
type: I have a single key in my hand.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yolg'iz bo'lsa, unda faqat bittasi bor.
column14: Mening qo'limda bitta kalit bor.

example: Success is doing something well that you choose to do.
type: My daughter was a big success at school.
example_tr: Muvaffaqiyat bu siz tanlagan ishni yaxshi bajarishdir.
column14: Qizim maktabda katta muvaffaqiyatga erishdi.

example: To tear something means to pull it apart.
type: It is easy to tear paper.
example_tr: Biror narsani yirtib tashlash, uni tortib olish demakdir.
column14: Qog'ozni yirtib tashlash oson.

example: A theory is an idea about how something works.
type: We talked about Einstein’s theory of relativity in class
example_tr: Nazariya - biror narsaning qanday ishlashi haqidagi g'oya.
column14: Biz sinfda Eynshteynning nisbiylik nazariyasi haqida gaplashdik

example: To be against something is to be touching it or opposed to it.
type: They both leaned against the wall.
example_tr: Biror narsaga qarshi bo'lish - unga tegish yoki unga qarshi bo'lish.
column14: Ikkalasi ham devorga suyanib turishdi.

example: The beach is a sandy or rocky place by the ocean.
type: The little girl built a sandcastle on the beach.
example_tr: Plyaj - okean bo'yidagi qumli yoki toshloq joy.
column14: Qizcha sohilda qumdan qasr qurdi.

example: To damage something is to break it.
type: The car was damaged in the accident.
example_tr: Biror narsaga zarar etkazish - uni buzish.
column14: Hodisa oqibatida mashina shikastlangan.

example: To discover something is to find it for the first time.
type: I discovered some new information in this book!
example_tr: Biror narsani kashf qilish uni birinchi marta topishdir.
column14: Men ushbu kitobda yangi ma'lumotlarni topdim!

example: An emotion is how you feel.
type: Anger is a common emotion that we all feel.
example_tr: Tuyg'u - bu sizning his-tuyg'ularingiz.
column14: G'azab - bu barchamiz his qiladigan umumiy tuyg'u.

example: To fix something is to make it work.
type: My dad has many tools to help him fix broken things.
example_tr: Biror narsani tuzatish - uni amalga oshirish.
column14: Dadamning buzilgan narsalarni tuzatishga yordam beradigan ko'plab vositalari bor.

example: If you are frank, you are being very honest.
type: The teacher had a frank discussion with her students.
example_tr: Agar siz ochiqchasiga gapirsangiz, siz juda halolsiz.
column14: O‘qituvchi shogirdlari bilan ochiq suhbatlashdi.

example: To identify something is to be able to name it.
type: I used the file to identify his name.
example_tr: Biror narsani aniqlash, uni nomlay olishdir.
column14: Men uning ismini aniqlash uchun fayldan foydalandim.

example: An island is land in the middle of water.
type: Japan is a group of islands.
example_tr: Orol suv o'rtasida joylashgan quruqlikdir.
column14: Yaponiya orollar guruhidir.

example: The ocean is all of the salt water that surrounds lands.
type: The ocean can make powerful waves.
example_tr: Okean quruqliklarni o'rab turgan barcha sho'r suvdir.
column14: Okean kuchli to'lqinlarni keltirib chiqarishi mumkin.

example: Perhaps is used when you say that something could happen.
type: Perhaps I will eat an apple for lunch.
example_tr: Ehtimol, biror narsa sodir bo'lishi mumkin deganda ishlatiladi.
column14: Balki tushlikda olma yeyman.

example: If something is pleasant, you enjoy it.
type: The character had a pleasant look on its face.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoqimli bo'lsa, siz undan zavqlanasiz.
column14: Qahramonning yuzida yoqimli ko'rinish bor edi.

example: To prevent something is to stop it from happening.
type: The handcuffs prevented me from moving my hands.
example_tr: Biror narsaning oldini olish uning sodir bo'lishini to'xtatishdir.
column14: Qo‘llarimni qimirlatishimga qo‘l kishanlari to‘sqinlik qildi.

example: A rock is a hard thing in the dirt.
type: I stacked rocks on top of one another.
example_tr: Tosh - tuproqdagi qattiq narsa.
column14: Men toshlarni bir-birining ustiga qo'ydim.

example: To save something is to keep it from being hurt.
type: I want to help save the world.
example_tr: Biror narsani qutqarish - uni xafa qilishdan saqlashdir.
column14: Men dunyoni qutqarishga yordam bermoqchiman.

example: To step is to walk.
type: Be careful where you step.
example_tr: Qadam - yurish.
column14: Qaerga qadam qo'yganingizda ehtiyot bo'ling.

example: Still is used when you say that a situation keeps going on.
type: They are still waiting in line to get tickets.
example_tr: Vaziyat davom etayotganini aytganda hali ham ishlatiladi.
column14: Ular hamon chipta olish uchun navbat kutishmoqda.

example: A taste is the flavor something makes in your mouth.
type: The taste of the fruit was sweet.
example_tr: Ta'm - bu sizning og'zingizdagi narsaning lazzatidir.
column14: Mevaning ta'mi shirin edi.

example: To throw something is to use your hand to make it go through the air.
type: The pitcher can throw the baseball very fast.
example_tr: Biror narsani otish - qo'lingiz bilan uni havodan o'tkazish.
column14: Ko'za beysbolni juda tez tashlay oladi.

example: A wave is a line of water that moves higher than the rest of the water.
type: The water was filled with large blue waves.
example_tr: To'lqin - bu suvning qolgan qismidan balandroq harakatlanadigan suv chizig'i.
column14: Suv katta ko'k to'lqinlar bilan to'ldirilgan edi.

example: A benefit is a good thing.
type: Being able to fly is a good benefit to birds.
example_tr: Foyda - bu yaxshi narsa.
column14: Uchish qobiliyati qushlar uchun yaxshi foyda.

example: If you are certain about something, you know it is true.
type: I am certain that zebras have stripes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsaga ishonchingiz komil bo'lsa, bu haqiqat ekanligini bilasiz.
column14: Ishonchim komilki, zebralarda chiziqlar bor.

example: A chance is an opportunity to do something.
type: I had a chance to see the Roman Coliseum last summer.
example_tr: Imkoniyat - bu biror narsa qilish imkoniyati.
column14: O'tgan yozda Rim Kolizeyini ko'rish imkoniga ega bo'ldim.

example: An effect is a change made by something else.
type: The medicine had a good effect on the boy.
example_tr: Effekt - bu boshqa narsa tomonidan qilingan o'zgarish.
column14: Dori bolaga yaxshi ta'sir qildi.

example: If something is essential, it is very important and necessary.
type: It is essential to have oxygen when you scuba dive.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u juda muhim va zarurdir.
column14: Suvga sho'ng'ish paytida kislorodga ega bo'lish juda muhimdir.

example: If something is far, it is not close.
type: It’s far going from the east coast to the west coast of America.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa uzoq bo'lsa, u yaqin emas.
column14: U Amerikaning sharqiy qirg'og'idan g'arbiy sohilgacha uzoqda.

example: To focus on something is to think about it and pay attention to it.
type: My mom always helps me to focus on my school work.
example_tr: Biror narsaga e'tibor berish - bu haqda o'ylash va unga e'tibor berishdir.
column14: Onam har doim diqqatimni maktab ishlariga qaratishimga yordam beradi.

example: The function of something is what it does.
type: The function of a flashlight is to help you see in the dark.
example_tr: Biror narsaning vazifasi uning bajaradigan vazifasidir.
column14: Chiroqning vazifasi qorong'uda ko'rishga yordam berishdir.

example: Grass is the green leaves that cover the ground.
type: The grass looked so soft and green.
example_tr: O't - bu yerni qoplaydigan yashil barglar.
column14: Maysa juda yumshoq va yashil ko'rinardi.

example: To guard something is to take care of it.
type: The police officer will guard us from any harm.
example_tr: Biror narsani qo'riqlash - unga g'amxo'rlik qilish.
column14: Politsiya xodimi bizni har qanday yomonlikdan himoya qiladi.

example: The image of something is a picture of it.
type: The image of her eye was very clear.
example_tr: Biror narsaning tasviri uning suratidir.
column14: Uning ko'zining tasviri juda aniq edi.

example: If something is immediate, it happens quickly.
type: An immediate response came from the pizza place.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa darhol bo'lsa, u tezda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Pitssa joyidan darhol javob keldi.

example: If something is primary, it is the most important thing.
type: His primary thoughts are about money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa asosiy bo'lsa, u eng muhimi.
column14: Uning asosiy fikrlari pul haqida.

example: If someone feels proud, they are happy about what they have done.
type: She is proud of the picture she drew of her house.
example_tr: Agar kimdir faxrlansa, u qilgan ishidan xursand bo'ladi.
column14: U uyini chizgan rasmidan faxrlanadi.

example: To remain somewhere is to stay there.
type: My sister had to remain home since she was sick.
example_tr: Biror joyda qolish - u erda qolish.
column14: Singlim kasal bo'lgani uchun uyda qolishi kerak edi.

example: To rest is to stop being active while the body gets back its strength.
type: I rested on the couch after work.
example_tr: Dam olish - bu tana kuchini tiklaganda faollikni to'xtatishdir.
column14: Ishdan keyin divanda dam oldim.

example: If two things are separate, they are not together.
type: New York and Los Angeles are in two separate parts of America.
example_tr: Ikki narsa alohida bo'lsa, ular birga emas.
column14: Nyu-York va Los-Anjeles Amerikaning ikki alohida qismida joylashgan.

example: A site is a place.
type: We found the perfect site for our picnic.
example_tr: Sayt - bu joy.
column14: Piknikimiz uchun mukammal sayt topdik.

example: A tail is a part of an animal’s body, sticking out from its rear or bags
type: Our dog wags its tail when it’s happy.
example_tr: Quyruq - bu hayvon tanasining orqa qismidan yoki sumkasidan tashqariga chiqadigan qismi
column14: Bizning itimiz baxtli bo'lganda dumini qimirlatadi.

example: Trouble is a problem or a difficulty.
type: I have trouble working with my boss.
example_tr: Muammo - bu muammo yoki qiyinchilik.
column14: Men xo'jayin bilan ishlashda muammoga duch keldim.

example: Anymore means any longer.
type: Her old pants don’t fit her anymore.
example_tr: Anymore bu endi uzoq degani.
column14: Uning eski shimlari endi unga mos kelmaydi.

example: When a person is asleep, they are not awake.
type: The baby has been asleep for hours.
example_tr: Biror kishi uxlab yotganida, u uyg'oq emas.
column14: Chaqaloq bir necha soat davomida uxlab qoldi.

example: A berry is a small round fruit that grows on certain plants and trees.
type: The berry looked delicious.
example_tr: Berry - bu ma'lum o'simliklar va daraxtlarda o'sadigan kichik yumaloq meva.
column14: Berry mazali ko'rindi.

example: To collect things is to group them together all in one place.
type: I collected shells when I was younger.
example_tr: Narsalarni yig'ish - bu ularning barchasini bir joyda to'plashdir.
column14: Men yoshligimda qobiqlarni yig'ganman.

example: To compete is to try to be better than someone.
type: He will compete with very good athletes.
example_tr: Raqobat - bu kimdandir yaxshiroq bo'lishga harakat qilishdir.
column14: U juda yaxshi sportchilar bilan bellashadi.

example: A conversation is a talk between people.
type: There were two conversations going on at once.
example_tr: Suhbat - bu odamlar o'rtasidagi suhbat.
column14: Bir vaqtning o'zida ikkita suhbat bo'lib o'tdi.

example: A creature is any living thing.
type: The creature we saw today was either a dolphin or a porpoise.
example_tr: Jonivor har qanday tirik mavjudotdir.
column14: Bugun biz ko‘rgan jonzot yo delfin yoki cho‘chqa edi.

example: A decision is a choice.
type: He made the wrong decision.
example_tr: Qaror - bu tanlov.
column14: U noto'g'ri qaror qildi.

example: Either is used with “or” to say there are two or more possibilities.
type: You can choose to be either white or black when you play chess.
example_tr: Yoki ikki yoki undan ortiq imkoniyat borligini aytish uchun “yoki” bilan ishlatiladi.
column14: Shaxmat o'ynaganingizda oq yoki qora bo'lishni tanlashingiz mumkin.

example: A forest is a place with lots of trees and animals.
type: I love to go walking in the forest.
example_tr: O'rmon - bu daraxtlar va hayvonlar ko'p bo'lgan joy.
column14: Men o'rmonda sayr qilishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: The ground is the top part of the Earth that we walk on.
type: The ground under our feet was dry and brown.
example_tr: Er - biz yuradigan Yerning eng yuqori qismi.
column14: Oyog'imiz ostidagi yer quruq va jigarrang edi.

example: To introduce someone or something is to say who they are.
type: I introduced myself to our newest co-worker today.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani tanishtirish uning kimligini aytishdir.
column14: Bugun men o'zimni eng yangi hamkasbimiz bilan tanishtirdim.

example: To marry is to legally become husband and wife.
type: Rose and Henry were married, and they lived happily.
example_tr: Turmush qurish qonuniy ravishda er va xotin bo'lishdir.
column14: Rose va Genri turmush qurishdi va ular baxtli yashashdi.

example: To prepare is to get ready for something.
type: I prepared my speech to the class.
example_tr: Tayyorlanish - biror narsaga tayyorlanish.
column14: Men sinfga nutqimni tayyorladim.

example: To sail is to move a boat on the water.
type: I love to sail my boat on the lake.
example_tr: Suzib yurish - qayiqni suv ustida harakatlantirish.
column14: Men ko'lda qayiqda suzib yurishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: When something is serious, it is bad or unsafe.
type: The accident was very serious.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jiddiy bo'lsa, u yomon yoki xavflidir.
column14: Baxtsiz hodisa juda jiddiy edi.

example: To spend is to use time doing something or being somewhere.
type: I like to spend my free time fishing.
example_tr: Sarflash - biror narsa qilish yoki biror joyda bo'lish uchun vaqtdan foydalanish.
column14: Men bo'sh vaqtimni baliq ovlashda o'tkazishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: When something is strange, it is not normal.
type: Joe had a strange look on his face after he saw what happened.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'alati bo'lsa, bu normal emas.
column14: Nima bo'lganini ko'rgan Joning yuzida g'alati nigoh paydo bo'ldi.

example: The truth is a fact or something that is right.
type: He was telling the truth about seeing a large green snake.
example_tr: Haqiqat haqiqat yoki to'g'ri narsadir.
column14: U katta yashil ilonni ko'rgani haqida haqiqatni aytdi.

example: To wake is to not be sleeping anymore.
type: He is always full of energy when he wakes in the morning.
example_tr: Uyg'onish - endi uxlamaslik.
column14: Ertalab uyg'onganida u doimo energiyaga to'la.

example: If someone is alone, they are not with another person.
type: The boy wanted to be alone to think.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yolg'iz bo'lsa, u boshqa odam bilan emas.
column14: Bola o'ylash uchun yolg'iz qolishni xohladi.

example: An apartment is a set of rooms in a building where people live.
type: She has a nice apartment in the city.
example_tr: Kvartira - bu odamlar yashaydigan binodagi xonalar to'plami.
column14: Uning shaharda yaxshi kvartirasi bor.

example: An article is a story in a newspaper or magazine.
type: Did you read the article in the newspaper about the soccer game?
example_tr: Maqola gazeta yoki jurnaldagi hikoyadir.
column14: Gazetadagi futbol o'yini haqidagi maqolani o'qidingizmi?

example: An artist is a person who paints, draws, or makes sculptures.
type: He went to Paris to become an artist.
example_tr: Rassom - rasm chizadigan, chizadigan yoki haykaltaroshlik qiladigan shaxs.
column14: U rassom bo'lish uchun Parijga bordi.

example: Someone’s attitude is the way they feel and think.
type: John has a bad attitude. He’s always angry.
example_tr: Biror kishining munosabati uning his qilish va fikrlash tarzidir.
column14: Jon yomon munosabatda. U har doim g'azablangan.

example: To compare means to say how two things are the same and different.
type: If you compare cats and dogs, you'll see that they’re both good pets.
example_tr: Taqqoslash ikki narsaning bir xil va farqli ekanligini aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Agar siz mushuk va itlarni solishtirsangiz, ularning ikkalasi ham yaxshi uy hayvonlari ekanligini ko'rasiz.

example: To judge something is to say if it is good or bad.
type: The boy was going to judge how his mother’s turkey tasted.
example_tr: Biror narsani hukm qilish, uning yaxshi yoki yomonligini aytishdir.
column14: O'g'il onasining kurka go'shti qanday ta'mga ega ekanligini baholamoqchi edi.

example: A magazine is a regular publication with news, stories, and articles.
type: She likes to read fashion magazines.
example_tr: Jurnal - yangiliklar, hikoyalar va maqolalardan iborat muntazam nashr.
column14: U moda jurnallarini o'qishni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: A material is what is used to make something.
type: Brick is a good material for building houses.
example_tr: Material - bu biror narsa qilish uchun ishlatiladigan narsa.
column14: G'isht uylarni qurish uchun yaxshi materialdir.

example: A meal is a time when food is eaten like breakfast, lunch, or dinner.
type: Breakfast is my favorite meal because I enjoy breakfast foods.
example_tr: Ovqatlanish - bu nonushta, tushlik yoki kechki ovqat kabi ovqat iste'mol qilinadigan vaqt.
column14: Nonushta mening sevimli taomim, chunki men nonushta qilishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: A method is the way to do something.
type: One method to remember things is to tie a string around your finger.
example_tr: Usul - biror narsa qilish usuli.
column14: Biror narsani eslab qolishning bir usuli - barmog'ingizga ipni bog'lash.

example: A neighbor is a person who lives near you.
type: I like my neighbor because he’s very friendly.
example_tr: Qo'shni - bu sizga yaqin yashaydigan odam.
column14: Men qo'shnimni yaxshi ko'raman, chunki u juda do'stona.

example: If something is professional, it deals with work that uses special skills.
type: If you want to be a pilot, you must have professional training.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa professional bo'lsa, u maxsus ko'nikmalardan foydalanadigan ish bilan shug'ullanadi.
column14: Agar siz uchuvchi bo'lishni istasangiz, professional tayyorgarlikka ega bo'lishingiz kerak.

example: A profit is the extra money you make when you sell something.
type: I made a small profit from selling my old clothes.
example_tr: Foyda - bu siz biror narsani sotganingizda qo'shimcha pul topasiz.
column14: Eski kiyimlarimni sotishdan ozgina daromad oldim.

example: The quality of something is how good it is.
type: The quality of his car is very good.
example_tr: Biror narsaning sifati uning qanchalik yaxshi ekanligidir.
column14: Uning mashinasining sifati juda yaxshi.

example: A shape is a simple form like a square or circle.
type: The triangle is my favorite shape.
example_tr: Shakl - bu kvadrat yoki doira kabi oddiy shakl.
column14: Uchburchak mening eng sevimli shaklim.

example: A space is an empty area.
type: I don’t have much space for things in my small house.
example_tr: Bo'sh joy - bu bo'sh joy.
column14: Mening kichkina uyimda narsalar uchun ko'p joy yo'q.

example: Stairs are the things that are used to go up in a building.
type: You can take the stairs to the second floor.
example_tr: Zinapoya - bu binoda ko'tarilish uchun ishlatiladigan narsalar.
column14: Zinadan ikkinchi qavatga chiqishingiz mumkin.

example: A symbol is a thing that stands for something else.
type: This symbol tells us that we cannot smoke in this area.
example_tr: Ramz - bu boshqa narsani anglatadigan narsa.
column14: Bu belgi bizga bu hududda chekishimiz mumkin emasligini aytadi.

example: If someone or something is thin, they are not fat.
type: The man was thin because he didn’t eat much.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa nozik bo'lsa, ular semiz emas.
column14: Odam ozg'in edi, chunki u ko'p ovqatlanmadi.

example: Blood is the red liquid in your body.
type: I cut my finger and got blood on my shirt.
example_tr: Qon tanadagi qizil suyuqlikdir.
column14: Barmog‘imni kesib, ko‘ylagimga qon tushdi.

example: To burn something is to set it on fire.
type: I burned some wood in the camp fire.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoqish - uni yoqish.
column14: Men lager olovida o‘tin yoqib yubordim.

example: A cell is a small room where a person is locked in.
type: The jail cell was very small.
example_tr: Hujayra - bu odam qulflangan kichik xona.
column14: Qamoqxona kamerasi juda kichik edi.

example: To contain something is to have it inside.
type: The mailbox contained a letter.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'z ichiga olish - uning ichida bo'lish.
column14: Pochta qutisida xat bor edi.

example: To be correct is to be right.
type: All of my answers on the test were correct.
example_tr: To'g'ri bo'lish - to'g'ri bo'lish.
column14: Testdagi barcha javoblarim to'g'ri edi.

example: A crop is something that a farmer grows.
type: Wheat is a crop that is made into bread.
example_tr: Ekin - bu dehqon yetishtiradigan narsa.
column14: Bug'doy - bu non ishlab chiqariladigan ekin.

example: To demand something is to say strongly that you want it.
type: The workers demanded to be paid more money.
example_tr: Biror narsani talab qilish, buni xohlayotganingizni qattiq aytishdir.
column14: Ishchilar ko'proq pul to'lashni talab qilishdi.

example: To be equal is to be the same.
type: Both students are equal in age.
example_tr: Teng bo'lish - bir xil bo'lish.
column14: Ikkala o'quvchining yoshi teng.

example: To feed is to give food.
type: Mother feeds my baby brother everyday.
example_tr: Oziqlantirish - ovqat berishdir.
column14: Onam har kuni ukamni ovqatlantiradi.

example: A hole is an opening in something.
type: The man was going to jump into the hole in the ice.
example_tr: Teshik - biror narsaning ochilishi.
column14: Erkak muzning teshigiga sakrab tushmoqchi edi.

example: To increase something is to make it larger or more.
type: They’ve increased the price of gas by 15 cents!
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'paytirish - uni katta yoki ko'proq qilishdir.
column14: Gaz narxini 15 sentga oshirib yuborishdi!

example: Long ago, a lord was a man in charge of a town.
type: The lord of the town was not kind.
example_tr: Qadim zamonlarda lord bir shaharni boshqargan odam edi.
column14: Shahar xo'jayini mehribon emas edi.

example: To owe is to have to pay or give back something received from another.
type: I owed him twenty dollars, so I paid him back.
example_tr: Qarzdorlik - bu boshqasidan olingan narsani to'lash yoki qaytarish.
column14: Unga yigirma dollar qarzim bor edi, shuning uchun uni qaytarib berdim.

example: A position is the way something is placed.
type: How can you sit in that position?
example_tr: Lavozim - bu biror narsaning joylashishi.
column14: Qanday qilib bu holatda o'tirish mumkin?

example: To raise something is to lift it up.
type: We had to work together to raise the last piece.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'tarish - uni ko'tarish.
column14: Oxirgi qismni ko'tarish uchun birgalikda ishlashimiz kerak edi.

example: If a person is responsible, they do the right things.
type: I try to be responsible and save money.
example_tr: Agar inson mas'uliyatli bo'lsa, u to'g'ri ishlarni qiladi.
column14: Men mas'uliyatli bo'lishga va pulni tejashga harakat qilaman.

example: A sight is something interesting to see.
type: I saw the pyramids of Egypt. What a sight!
example_tr: Ko'rish - bu ko'rish uchun qiziqarli narsa.
column14: Men Misr piramidalarini ko'rdim. Qanday manzara!

example: A spot is a place where something happens.
type: The kitchen is a good spot to eat meals.
example_tr: Nuqta - bu biror narsa sodir bo'ladigan joy.
column14: Oshxona - ovqatlanish uchun yaxshi joy.

example: A structure is a building.
type: They just built a beautiful new structure downtown.
example_tr: Inshoot - bu bino.
column14: Ular endigina shahar markazida chiroyli yangi inshoot qurdilar.

example: Whole means all of something.
type: I ate the whole pie. We don’t have any more.
example_tr: Butun bir narsaning hammasini anglatadi.
column14: Men butun pirogni yedim. Bizda boshqasi yo'q.

example: A coach is a person who teaches sports.
type: My coach gets very excited during games.
example_tr: Murabbiy - bu sportni o'rgatuvchi shaxs.
column14: Murabbiyim o'yinlarda juda hayajonlanadi.

example: To control something is to make it do what you want.
type: To control the TV, just push the buttons.
example_tr: Biror narsani nazorat qilish - uni o'zingiz xohlagan narsani qilishdir.
column14: Televizorni boshqarish uchun tugmalarni bosish kifoya.

example: A description of someone or something says what they are like.
type: I gave a description of the man with the gun and hat to the police.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsaning tavsifi ularning qanday ekanligini aytadi.
column14: Men politsiyaga qurol va qalpoqli odamning tavsifini berdim.

example: If something is direct, it goes straight between two places.
type: The green path is a direct route to my house.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ridan-to'g'ri bo'lsa, u to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ikki joy o'rtasida ketadi.
column14: Yashil yo'l mening uyimga to'g'ridan-to'g'ri yo'l.

example: An exam is a test.
type: I did some practice questions for the math exam on the board.
example_tr: Imtihon - bu sinov.
column14: Doskada matematika imtihoniga bir nechta mashq savollarini berdim.

example: An example of something is a thing that is typical of it.
type: Cola is an example of a soft drink.
example_tr: Biror narsaning namunasi - unga xos bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Kola salqin ichimlikning namunasidir.

example: A limit is the largest or smallest amount of something that you allow.
type: My mother put a limit on how much I could use the phone.
example_tr: Limit - bu siz ruxsat bergan narsaning eng katta yoki eng kichik miqdori.
column14: Onam telefondan foydalanishimga chek qo'ygan.

example: If something is local, it is nearby.
type: The local market in my neighborhood sells all the food we need.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mahalliy bo'lsa, u yaqin joyda.
column14: Mahallamizdagi mahalliy bozorda barcha zarur oziq-ovqatlar sotiladi.

example: Magical describes a quality that makes someone or something special.
type: The fireworks made the night sky look so magical.
example_tr: Sehrli kimnidir yoki biror narsani o'ziga xos qiladigan sifatni tasvirlaydi.
column14: Pirotexnika tungi osmonni juda sehrli qilib ko'rsatdi.

example: Mail is letters and other things sent to people.
type: I get a lot of mail because I have friends all over the world.
example_tr: Pochta - bu odamlarga yuboriladigan xatlar va boshqa narsalar.
column14: Menga ko'p xatlar keladi, chunki butun dunyoda do'stlarim bor.

example: A novel is a book that tells a story.
type: He wrote a great novel about ancient China.
example_tr: Roman - bu voqeani hikoya qiluvchi kitob.
column14: U qadimgi Xitoy haqida ajoyib roman yozgan.

example: An outline is the plan for a story or essay.
type: Before I wrote my essay, I made an outline.
example_tr: Reja - bu hikoya yoki inshoning rejasi.
column14: Insho yozishdan oldin men konturni tuzdim.

example: A poet is a person who writes poems.
type: William Shakespeare was one of the greatest poets.
example_tr: Shoir - she'r yozadigan odam.
column14: Uilyam Shekspir eng buyuk shoirlardan biri edi.

example: To print something is to put it onto paper.
type: Make sure that you print your name clearly.
example_tr: Biror narsani chop etish uni qog'ozga tushirishdir.
column14: Ismingizni aniq chop etishingizga ishonch hosil qiling.

example: A scene is one part of a book or movie.
type: A movie is made up of many short pieces or scenes.
example_tr: Sahna kitob yoki filmning bir qismidir.
column14: Film ko'plab qisqa qismlar yoki sahnalardan iborat.

example: A sheet is a thin flat piece of paper.
type: I only needed a single sheet of paper to do my homework.
example_tr: Varaq - bu yupqa tekis qog'oz.
column14: Menga uy vazifamni bajarish uchun faqat bitta varaq kerak edi.

example: If someone or something is silly, they show a lack of thought.
type: I made a silly mistake of dropping mom’s vase.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa ahmoq bo'lsa, ular o'ylashning etishmasligini ko'rsatadi.
column14: Men onamning vazasini tashlab, ahmoqona xatoga yo'l qo'ydim.

example: A store is a place where you can buy things.
type: I picked up a few things at the grocery store.
example_tr: Do'kon - bu narsalarni sotib olish mumkin bo'lgan joy.
column14: Men oziq-ovqat do'konida bir nechta narsalarni oldim.

example: To suffer is to feel pain.
type: Her headache made her suffer all day.
example_tr: Azob chekmoq og'riqni his qilmoq.
column14: Bosh og‘rig‘i uni kun bo‘yi qiynalardi.

example: Technology is new things made by using science.
type: He loves technology such as laptop computers.
example_tr: Texnologiya ilm-fan yordamida yaratilgan yangi narsalardir.
column14: U noutbuklar kabi texnologiyani yaxshi ko'radi.

example: To go across something is to go to the other side of it.
type: He walked across the board to the other side.
example_tr: Biror narsani bo'ylab o'tish - uning boshqa tomoniga o'tish.
column14: U taxtaning narigi tomoniga o'tdi.

example: To breathe means to let air go in and out of your body.
type: We need strong healthy lungs to help us breathe well.
example_tr: Nafas olish, tanangizga havo kirishi va chiqishini anglatadi.
column14: Bizga yaxshi nafas olishimizga yordam beradigan kuchli sog'lom o'pka kerak.

example: A characteristic is something that shows what a person or a thing is like
type: One characteristic of tigers is their black stripes.
example_tr: Xususiyat - bu shaxs yoki narsaning qanday ekanligini ko'rsatadigan narsa
column14: Yo'lbarslarning o'ziga xos xususiyatlaridan biri ularning qora chiziqlaridir.

example: To consume something means to eat or drink it.
type: Jack consumed a whole plate of spaghetti.
example_tr: Biror narsani iste'mol qilish, uni yeyish yoki ichish demakdir.
column14: Jek butun bir plastinka spagetti iste'mol qildi.

example: To excite someone means to make them happy and interested.
type: I heard about the school dance on Friday. This excited me.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayajonlantirish, uni xursand qilish va qiziqtirish demakdir.
column14: Juma kuni maktab raqsi haqida eshitdim. Bu meni hayajonga soldi.

example: If something is extreme, it is in a large amount or degree.
type: His workout was so extreme that he was sweating heavily.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ekstremal bo'lsa, u katta miqdorda yoki darajada.
column14: Uning mashg'ulotlari shu qadar qattiq ediki, u qattiq terlagan edi.

example: Fear is the feeling of being afraid.
type: I have a great fear of skateboarding.
example_tr: Qo'rquv - qo'rquv hissi.
column14: Men skeytbordda uchishdan juda qo'rqaman.

example: If you are fortunate, you are lucky.
type: I was fortunate to get a seat.
example_tr: Agar omadingiz bo'lsa, omadingiz bor.
column14: Menga joy olish nasib qildi.

example: If someone happens to do something, they do it by chance.
type: I happened to meet some new friends at school today.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsaga duch kelsa, u buni tasodifan qiladi.
column14: Bugun maktabda yangi do'stlar bilan uchrashdim.

example: The length of something is how long it is from one end to the other.
type: The length of the floor is three meters.
example_tr: Biror narsaning uzunligi uning bir chetidan ikkinchi chetigacha bo'lgan uzunligidir.
column14: Zaminning uzunligi uch metrni tashkil qiladi.

example: A mistake is something you do wrong.
type: My boss always yells at me when I make a mistake.
example_tr: Xato - bu siz noto'g'ri qilgan narsadir.
column14: Xo'jayinim xato qilsam doim menga baqiradi.

example: To consider something means to think about it.
type: Pete didn’t like his job. He considered getting a new one.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rib chiqish, bu haqda o'ylashni anglatadi.
column14: Pit uning ishini yoqtirmasdi. U yangisini olishni o'ylardi.

example: To destroy means to damage something so badly that it cannot be used.
type: The glass was destroyed.
example_tr: Yo'q qilish - biror narsaga shunchalik zarar etkazish, uni ishlatib bo'lmaydi.
column14: Shisha vayron bo'ldi.

example: To entertain someone is to do something that they enjoy.
type: The clown entertained the kids at the party.
example_tr: Biror kishini ko'ngil ochish - ular zavqlanadigan narsani qilishdir.
column14: Bayramda masxaraboz bolalarni xushnud etdi.

example: If something is extra, it is more than what is needed.
type: The squirrel had extra nuts for the winter.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ortiqcha bo'lsa, u zarur bo'lganidan ko'proqdir.
column14: Sincapning qish uchun qo'shimcha yong'oqlari bor edi.

example: A goal is something you work toward.
type: Her goal was to become a doctor.
example_tr: Maqsad - bu siz harakat qiladigan narsa.
column14: Uning maqsadi shifokor bo'lish edi.

example: To lie is to say or write something untrue to deceive someone.
type: Whenever Pinocchio lied to his father, his nose grew.
example_tr: Yolg'on gapirish - kimnidir aldash uchun yolg'on gapirish yoki yozish.
column14: Qachonki Pinokkio otasiga yolg‘on gapirsa, uning burni o‘sib borardi.

example: Meat is food made of animals.
type: This piece of meat I’m eating tastes very good.
example_tr: Go'sht hayvonlardan tayyorlangan oziq-ovqat.
column14: Men yeyayotgan bu go'sht bo'lagi juda mazali.

example: An opinion is a thought about a person or a thing.
type: Meg told me her opinion of my story. She said it was not funny.
example_tr: Fikr - bu shaxs yoki narsa haqidagi fikr.
column14: Meg mening hikoyam haqidagi fikrini aytdi. U bu kulgili emasligini aytdi.

example: If something is real, it actually exists.
type: The handbag has a stamp on it, so it’s real.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa haqiqat bo'lsa, u haqiqatda mavjud.
column14: Qo'l sumkasida muhr bor, shuning uchun u haqiqiydir.

example: To reflect is when a surface sends back light, heat, sound or an image.
type: Her face was reflected on the smooth glass.
example_tr: Aks ettirish - bu sirt yorug'lik, issiqlik, tovush yoki tasvirni orqaga yuboradi.
column14: Uning yuzi silliq oynada aks etdi.

example: To regard someone or something is to think of them in a certain way.
type: The boy regarded the girl as a good friend.
example_tr: Biror kishiga yoki biror narsaga qarash - ular haqida ma'lum bir tarzda o'ylash.
column14: Yigit qizni yaxshi do'st deb bilardi.

example: To serve someone is to give them food or drinks.
type: He served us our drinks quickly.
example_tr: Biror kishiga xizmat qilish, unga ovqat yoki ichimliklar berishdir.
column14: U bizga tezda ichimliklarimizni berdi.

example: A vegetable is a plant used as food.
type: Carrots are my favorite vegetable.
example_tr: Sabzavot - bu oziq-ovqat sifatida ishlatiladigan o'simlik.
column14: Sabzi mening sevimli sabzavotlarim.

example: A war is a big fight between two groups of people.
type: Many young men died in the war.
example_tr: Urush - bu ikki guruh odamlar o'rtasidagi katta kurash.
column14: Urushda ko‘plab yigitlar halok bo‘ldi.

example: If something is worth an amount of money, it costs that amount.
type: Our house is worth a lot of money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa katta miqdordagi pulga arziydigan bo'lsa, u shunchalik qimmatga tushadi.
column14: Bizning uyimiz katta pulga arziydi.

example: To appear is to seem.
type: She appeared to be sad. She was crying.
example_tr: Ko'rinish - ko'rinish.
column14: U g'amgin bo'lib ko'rindi. U yig'lardi.

example: The base is the bottom of something.
type: The base of the table has three legs.
example_tr: Baza biror narsaning pastki qismidir.
column14: Stolning tagida uchta oyoq bor.

example: The brain is the organ in your head that lets you think.
type: You must use your brain to solve the problem.
example_tr: Miya - bu sizning fikrlashingizga imkon beradigan boshingizdagi organ.
column14: Muammoni hal qilish uchun siz miyangizni ishlatishingiz kerak.

example: A career is a job that you do for a large part of your life.
type: He was in the hospitality business for most of his career.
example_tr: Karyera - bu hayotingizning ko'p qismini bajaradigan ish.
column14: U faoliyatining ko'p qismini mehmondo'stlik biznesida o'tkazgan.

example: A clerk is a type of worker. Clerks in a store help customers.
type: The clerk added up her bill for the groceries.
example_tr: Kotib - bu ishchining bir turi. Do'kondagi sotuvchilar xaridorlarga yordam berishadi.
column14: Kotib oziq-ovqat uchun hisobini qo‘shib qo‘ydi.

example: Effort is hard work or an attempt to do something.
type: He always puts a lot of effort into his studies.
example_tr: Harakat - bu mashaqqatli ish yoki biror narsa qilishga urinish.
column14: U har doim o'qishga juda ko'p kuch sarflaydi.

example: To enter a place is to go into it.
type: Two guards greeted me as I entered the front door.
example_tr: Biror joyga kirish - unga kirish.
column14: Eshikdan kirganimda ikki qo‘riqchi kutib oldi.

example: When something is excellent, it is very good.
type: I got an excellent score on my school test.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa zo'r bo'lsa, u juda yaxshi.
column14: Men maktab imtihonida juda yaxshi ball oldim.

example: A hero is a brave person who does things to help others.
type: To children, the man in the blue and red costume was the hero.
example_tr: Qahramon - boshqalarga yordam berish uchun narsalarni qiladigan jasur odam.
column14: Bolalar uchun ko'k va qizil kostyumdagi odam qahramon edi.

example: To hurry is to do something quickly.
type: I hurried home on my bike.
example_tr: Shoshilmoq — biror narsani tez qilmoq.
column14: Velosipedda uyga shoshildim.

example: To inform someone is to tell them about something.
type: I called and informed her about my idea.
example_tr: Biror kishiga xabar berish - unga biror narsa haqida gapirish.
column14: Men unga qo'ng'iroq qildim va fikrimni aytdim.

example: Later means after the present, expected, or usual time.
type: She missed the train, so she’ll arrive a little later than expected.
example_tr: Keyinchalik hozirgi, kutilgan yoki odatiy vaqtdan keyin degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: U poezdni o'tkazib yubordi, shuning uchun u kutilganidan biroz kechroq keladi.

example: To leave means to go away from someone or something.
type: He packed his bag and was ready to leave for home.
example_tr: Ketish, kimdandir yoki biror narsadan uzoqlashishni anglatadi.
column14: U sumkasini yig'di va uyga ketishga tayyor edi.

example: To locate something is to find it.
type: I could not locate my keys in the house.
example_tr: Biror narsani topish - uni topish.
column14: Uyda kalitlarimni topa olmadim.

example: A nurse is a person who helps sick people in the hospital.
type: A nurse helped me get better.
example_tr: Hamshira - kasalxonada kasallarga yordam beradigan odam.
column14: Bir hamshira yaxshilanishimga yordam berdi.

example: An operation is when a doctor replaces or removes something in the body.
type: The operation on my arm was a success.
example_tr: Operatsiya - bu shifokorning tanadagi biror narsani almashtirishi yoki olib tashlashi.
column14: Qo‘limdagi operatsiya muvaffaqiyatli o‘tdi.

example: Pain is the feeling that you have when you are hurt.
type: His head was full of pain.
example_tr: Og'riq - bu sizni xafa qilganda paydo bo'ladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Uning boshi og'riq bilan to'la edi.

example: To refuse something is to say “no” to it.
type: The dog refused to play with the cat.
example_tr: Biror narsani rad qilish, unga "yo'q" deyishdir.
column14: It mushuk bilan o'ynashdan bosh tortdi.

example: Though is used when the second idea makes the first seem surprising.
type: Though he was overweight, he liked to be active.
example_tr: Garchi ikkinchi fikr birinchisini hayratlanarli qilib ko'rsatsa ishlatiladi.
column14: U ortiqcha vaznga ega bo'lsa-da, u faol bo'lishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: If something is various, there are many types of it.
type: She owned shoes of various styles.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa har xil bo'lsa, uning ko'p turlari mavjud.
column14: U turli xil uslubdagi poyabzallarga ega edi.

example: Actual means that something is real or true.
type: This is the actual sword that the King owned, not a fake one.
example_tr: Haqiqiy narsa haqiqat yoki haqiqat ekanligini anglatadi.
column14: Bu qirolga tegishli bo'lgan haqiqiy qilich, soxta emas.

example: To amaze someone is to surprise them very much.
type: The news in the paper amazed Jack.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayratda qoldirish, uni juda hayratda qoldirishdir.
column14: Gazetadagi yangiliklar Jekni hayratda qoldirdi.

example: A charge is the price to pay for something.
type: The charge for the shirts was $15.00.
example_tr: To'lov - bu biror narsa uchun to'lanadigan narx.
column14: Ko'ylaklarning narxi 15,00 dollarni tashkil etdi.

example: To comfort someone means to make them feel better.
type: I wanted to comfort my friend after I heard the bad news.
example_tr: Biror kishiga tasalli berish, uni yaxshi his qilish demakdir.
column14: Yomon xabarni eshitganimdan keyin dugonamga tasalli bermoqchi edim.

example: To contact someone is to speak or write to them.
type: I contacted Sue about my party.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan bog'lanish - u bilan gaplashish yoki yozish.
column14: Men Sue bilan partiyam haqida bog'landim.

example: A customer is a person who buys something at a store.
type: The customer put a few items in a bag.
example_tr: Xaridor - bu do'konda biror narsa sotib oladigan odam.
column14: Xaridor sumkaga bir nechta narsalarni qo'ydi.

example: To deliver something is to take it from one place to another.
type: The man delivered Chinese food to my house.
example_tr: Biror narsani yetkazib berish, uni bir joydan ikkinchi joyga olib borishdir.
column14: U kishi mening uyimga xitoy taomlarini yetkazib berdi.

example: To earn means to get money for the work you do.
type: He earns his living as a chef in a great restaurant.
example_tr: Pul topish, qilgan ishingiz uchun pul olishni anglatadi.
column14: U zo'r restoranda oshpaz bo'lib tirikchilik qiladi.

example: A gate is a type of door. Gates are usually made of metal or wood.
type: We want to put up a wooden gate around our house.
example_tr: Darvoza - eshikning bir turi. Darvozalar odatda metall yoki yog'ochdan yasalgan.
column14: Biz uyimiz atrofida yog'och darvoza o'rnatmoqchimiz.

example: To include something means to have it as part of something.
type: Does this meal include a soft drink?
example_tr: Biror narsani o'z ichiga olish, uni biror narsaning bir qismi sifatida qabul qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Bu taomga alkogolsiz ichimlik kiradimi?

example: To manage something means to control or be in charge of it.
