type: I had to manage the meeting myself.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshqarish, uni boshqarish yoki boshqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Uchrashuvni o'zim boshqarishim kerak edi.

example: A mystery is something that is difficult to understand or explain.
type: The path on the map was a complete mystery to me.
example_tr: Sir - bu tushunish yoki tushuntirish qiyin bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Xaritadagi yo'l men uchun to'liq sir edi.

example: To occur means to happen.
type: When did the thunderstorm occur?
example_tr: Voqea sodir bo'lmoq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Momaqaldiroq qachon sodir bo'lgan?

example: If A is the opposite of B, A is completely different from B.
type: The opposite of black is white.
example_tr: Agar A B ga qarama-qarshi bo'lsa, A B dan butunlay farq qiladi.
column14: Qora rangning aksi oq.

example: A plate is a flat round thing that you put food on.
type: I put my plate down so I could put some food on it.
example_tr: Plastinka - bu siz ovqat qo'yadigan tekis yumaloq narsa.
column14: Men ovqat qo'yishim uchun likopamni qo'ydim.

example: To receive something is to get it.
type: I received a present on my birthday.
example_tr: Biror narsani olish - uni olish.
column14: Men tug'ilgan kunimda sovg'a oldim.

example: A reward is something given in exchange for good behavior or work.
type: He was given a reward for his excellent performance.
example_tr: Mukofot - bu yaxshi xulq-atvor yoki ish evaziga beriladigan narsa.
column14: Unga o'zining ajoyib ishlashi uchun mukofot berildi.

example: To set something is to put it somewhere.
type: Please set the dice down on the table.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rnatish, uni biror joyga qo'yishdir.
column14: Iltimos, zarlarni stol ustiga qo'ying.

example: To steal is to take something that is not yours.
type: The men tried to steal money from the bank.
example_tr: O'g'irlik - sizniki bo'lmagan narsani olish.
column14: Erkaklar bankdan pul o‘g‘irlamoqchi bo‘lgan.

example: A thief is someone who quietly takes things that do not belong to them.
type: A thief broke into our home and took my mother’s jewelry.
example_tr: O'g'ri - o'ziga tegishli bo'lmagan narsalarni jimgina oladigan kishi.
column14: Uyimizga o'g'ri kirib, onamning taqinchoqlarini olib ketdi.

example: To advance is to go forward.
type: He advanced up the ladder slowly.
example_tr: Oldinga borish - oldinga borish.
column14: U sekin zinapoyaga ko'tarildi.

example: An athlete is a person who plays sports.
type: Some athletes can play many sports very well.
example_tr: Sportchi - bu sport bilan shug'ullanadigan odam.
column14: Ba'zi sportchilar ko'plab sport turlarini juda yaxshi o'ynashlari mumkin.

example: If something is average, it is at a normal level.
type: I’m not rich or poor; I’m average.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'rtacha bo'lsa, u normal darajada.
column14: Men boy yoki kambag'al emasman; Men o'rtachaman.

example: Your behavior is the way you act.
type: Their behavior was good this semester. They didn’t cause trouble.
example_tr: Sizning xatti-harakatingiz sizning harakatingizdir.
column14: Ularning xatti-harakatlari bu semestrda yaxshi edi. Ular muammo tug'dirmadi.

example: Behind means to be at the back of something.
type: The little girl was hiding behind a tree.
example_tr: Orqada biror narsaning orqasida bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Qizcha daraxt orqasiga yashiringan edi.

example: A course is a class in school.
type: I took a PE course in school this year.
example_tr: Kurs - bu maktabdagi dars.
column14: Bu yil maktabda jismoniy tarbiya kursini oldim.

example: To lower something is to make it go down.
type: The chart shows how his production has lowered over the year.
example_tr: Biror narsani tushirish - uni pastga tushirish.
column14: Grafikda uning ishlab chiqarishi yil davomida qanday pasayganligi ko'rsatilgan.

example: To match is to be the same or similar.
type: The two shoes matched. They looked the same.
example_tr: Mos kelmoq - bir xil yoki o'xshash bo'lish.
column14: Ikki tufli mos tushdi. Ular bir xil ko'rinishga ega edilar.

example: A member is a person who is part of a group.
type: Julie is the newest member of our team.
example_tr: A'zo - bu guruhning bir qismi bo'lgan shaxs.
column14: Juli - jamoamizning eng yangi a'zosi.

example: If something is mental, it has to do with your mind.
type: I made a mental picture of the room.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aqliy bo'lsa, bu sizning ongingiz bilan bog'liq.
column14: Men xonaning aqliy rasmini yaratdim.

example: A passenger is a person who rides in a car, train, or airplane.
type: One passenger was standing in the subway train.
example_tr: Yo'lovchi - bu mashinada, poezdda yoki samolyotda minadigan odam.
column14: Bir yo‘lovchi metro poyezdida turgan.

example: Your personality is what you are like and how you behave.
type: John has a bad personality.
example_tr: Sizning shaxsiyatingiz - bu siz qanday ekanligingiz va o'zingizni qanday tutishingiz.
column14: Jon yomon xarakterga ega.

example: A poem is a short kind of writing.
type: William Shakespeare wrote many poems.
example_tr: She'r - bu qisqa yozish turi.
column14: Uilyam Shekspir ko'plab she'rlar yozgan.

example: A pole is a long thin stick made of wood or metal that supports things.
type: The flag was hanging from the flag pole.
example_tr: Ustun - bu narsalarni qo'llab-quvvatlaydigan yog'och yoki metalldan yasalgan uzun ingichka tayoq.
column14: Bayroq bayroq ustuniga osilib turardi.

example: To remove something is to take it away.
type: I removed the nail from the board.
example_tr: Biror narsani olib tashlash - uni olib tashlash.
column14: Men tirnoqni taxtadan olib tashladim.

example: Safety means to be the condition of being safe and free from danger.
type: For his own safety, he was placed in a car seat.
example_tr: Xavfsizlik - bu xavfsiz va xavfdan xoli bo'lish sharti.
column14: O'zining xavfsizligi uchun uni avtomobil o'rindig'iga qo'yishdi.

example: To shoot is to fire something like a bullet at someone or something.
type: The hunter raised his gun to shoot at the target.
example_tr: Otish - kimgadir yoki biror narsaga o'q kabi narsalarni otishdir.
column14: Ovchi nishonga otish uchun miltig‘ini ko‘tardi.

example: To sound means to make a noise.
type: The alarm clock sounded and woke us all up.
example_tr: Ovoz berish shovqin qilish demakdir.
column14: Budilnik yangradi va hammamizni uyg'otdi.

example: To swim is to move through water.
type: I love to swim in the ocean.
example_tr: Suzish - suvda harakat qilish.
column14: Men okeanda suzishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: A web is a home made by a spider.
type: Mom cleaned the spider webs out of the garage.
example_tr: To'r - bu o'rgimchak tomonidan yaratilgan uy.
column14: Onam garajdan o'rgimchak to'rlarini tozaladi.

example: A block is a solid piece of wood, stone or ice.
type: I saw a block of ice on the floor.
example_tr: Blok - bu yog'och, tosh yoki muzning qattiq qismi.
column14: Men polda muz bo'lagini ko'rdim.

example: To cheer is to give a loud shout of approval or encouragement.
type: The crowd all cheered when the home team won.
example_tr: Quvontirish - bu ma'qullash yoki dalda berishni baland ovozda baqirish.
column14: Mezbonlar g‘alaba qozonganida, yig‘ilganlarning hammasi olqishladi.

example: If something is complex, it has many small parts. It is hard to understand.
type: A jig-saw puzzle can be complex because it has so many pieces.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa murakkab bo'lsa, unda juda ko'p kichik qismlar mavjud. Buni tushunish qiyin.
column14: Jig-arra boshqotirmasi murakkab bo'lishi mumkin, chunki u juda ko'p qismlarga ega.

example: A critic is someone who gives their opinions about movies, books, plays, etc.
type: The wine critic tasted the wine so he could give his opinion.
example_tr: Tanqidchi - bu filmlar, kitoblar, spektakllar va hokazolar haqida o'z fikrini bildiradigan odam.
column14: Sharob tanqidchisi o'z fikrini bildirishi uchun sharobni tatib ko'rdi.

example: An event is something that happens, especially something important.
type: Finishing high school was a major event in his life.
example_tr: Voqea - bu sodir bo'ladigan narsa, ayniqsa muhim narsa.
column14: O'rta maktabni tugatish uning hayotidagi muhim voqea edi.

example: To exercise is to run or play sports so that you can be healthy.
type: You should exercise every day.
example_tr: Jismoniy mashqlar qilish - sog'lom bo'lishingiz uchun yugurish yoki sport bilan shug'ullanish.
column14: Har kuni mashq qilishingiz kerak.

example: If something fits, it is small enough or the right size to go there.
type: The colorful eggs fit into the box.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mos bo'lsa, u erga borish uchun etarlicha kichik yoki to'g'ri o'lchamdir.
column14: Rangli tuxumlar qutiga mos keladi.

example: Friendship is the relationship between people who are friends.
type: Michael and Lisa have a very strong friendship with each other.
example_tr: Do'stlik - bu do'st bo'lgan odamlar o'rtasidagi munosabatlar.
column14: Maykl va Liza bir-birlari bilan juda kuchli do'stlikka ega.

example: A guide is someone who shows you where to go.
type: We followed a guide at the park.
example_tr: Yo'lboshchi - bu sizga qaerga borishni ko'rsatadigan odam.
column14: Biz parkdagi gidga ergashdik.

example: If there is a lack of something, there is not enough of it.
type: His only problem is a lack of money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa etishmasa, u etarli emas.
column14: Uning yagona muammosi - pul etishmasligi.

example: A passage is a long area with walls that goes from one place to another.
type: The long passage led us to the other side of the field.
example_tr: O'tish joyi - bu bir joydan ikkinchi joyga o'tadigan devorlari bo'lgan uzun maydon.
column14: Uzun yo‘lak bizni maydonning narigi tomoniga olib bordi.

example: To perform is to do something in front of people who watch.
type: He will perform a song for the class.
example_tr: Ijro qilish - tomosha qilayotgan odamlar oldida biror narsa qilish.
column14: U sinf uchun qo'shiq ijro etadi.

example: Pressure is what you apply to make someone do something.
type: They put pressure on him to change his mind.
example_tr: Bosim - bu kimnidir biror narsa qilishga majburlash uchun qo'llagan narsangiz.
column14: Fikrini o'zgartirish uchun unga bosim o'tkazishdi.

example: If something is probable, it is likely to happen.
type: It is probable that you will get a good grade if you study for the test.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ehtimoli bo'lsa, bu sodir bo'lishi mumkin.
column14: Agar siz imtihonga o'qisangiz, yaxshi baho olishingiz ehtimoldan yiroq.

example: If something is public, it is meant for everyone to use.
type: I went to the public park to play with my friends.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ommaviy bo'lsa, u hamma foydalanishi uchun mo'ljallangan.
column14: Men do'stlarim bilan o'ynash uchun jamoat bog'iga bordim.

example: To strike someone or something is to hit them.
type: She struck the other girl in the face.
example_tr: Birovni yoki biror narsani urish - uni urish.
column14: U boshqa qizning yuziga urdi.

example: To support something is to like it and help it be successful.
type: Everyone at work supports the new plan.
example_tr: Biror narsani qo'llab-quvvatlash - uni yoqtirish va muvaffaqiyatli bo'lishiga yordam berishdir.
column14: Ishdagi hamma yangi rejani qo'llab-quvvatlaydi.

example: A task is work that someone has to do.
type: Who has the task of building the brick wall?
example_tr: Vazifa - bu kimdir bajarishi kerak bo'lgan ish.
column14: G'isht devorini qurish vazifasi kimga yuklangan?

example: A term is a word for something.
type: I often use the term “oops” when I make a mistake.
example_tr: Termin - bu biror narsa uchun so'z.
column14: Men xatoga yo'l qo'yganimda tez-tez "oh" atamasini ishlataman.

example: To unite is to get together to do something.
type: If we unite, we can finish our project faster.
example_tr: Birlashish - biror narsa qilish uchun birlashish.
column14: Agar biz birlashsak, loyihamizni tezroq yakunlashimiz mumkin.

example: To associate means to connect something with a person or thing.
type: Most people associate birthday parties with having fun.
example_tr: Birlashma, biror narsani shaxs yoki narsa bilan bog'lashni anglatadi.
column14: Ko'pchilik tug'ilgan kunlarni dam olish bilan bog'laydi.

example: The environment is the place where people work or live.
type: Keeping our environment clean is important to our health.
example_tr: Atrof-muhit - bu odamlar ishlaydigan yoki yashaydigan joy.
column14: Atrof-muhitni toza saqlash bizning salomatligimiz uchun muhimdir.

example: A factory is a building where things are made or put together.
type: We have only one factory in our town.
example_tr: Zavod - bu narsalar ishlab chiqariladigan yoki birlashtiriladigan bino.
column14: Bizning shahrimizda faqat bitta zavod bor.

example: A feature is an important part of something.
type: The cell phone has many features.
example_tr: Xususiyat biror narsaning muhim qismidir.
column14: Mobil telefon juda ko'p xususiyatlarga ega.

example: An instance is an example of something.
type: I have never experienced an instance of hate. Have you?
example_tr: Biror narsaning misoli misoldir.
column14: Men hech qachon nafratlanishni boshdan kechirmaganman. Sizda bormi?

example: To involve means to be actively taking part in something.
type: The whole family was involved in playing the game.
example_tr: Ishtirok etish, biror narsada faol ishtirok etishni anglatadi.
column14: O'yinda butun oila ishtirok etdi.

example: Medicine is something you take to feel better or treat an illness.
type: The doctor gave me medicine for my cold.
example_tr: Dori - bu o'zingizni yaxshi his qilish yoki kasallikni davolash uchun qabul qiladigan narsa.
column14: Doktor shamollashim uchun dori berdi.

example: A mix is different things put together.
type: The green mix we made in science class spilled onto the table.
example_tr: Aralash - bu birlashtirilgan turli xil narsalar.
column14: Tabiatshunoslik darsida tayyorlagan yashil aralash dasturxonga to‘kildi.

example: To organize is to plan or get ready for an event.
type: Make a list to help you organize the things you need.
example_tr: Tashkilot qilish - bu tadbirni rejalashtirish yoki unga tayyorgarlik ko'rish.
column14: Sizga kerak bo'lgan narsalarni tartibga solishga yordam beradigan ro'yxat tuzing.

example: A period is an amount of time when something happens.
type: In one period in Europe, there were many NRO.
example_tr: Davr - bu biror narsa sodir bo'ladigan vaqt miqdori.
column14: Evropada bir davrda ko'plab NRO mavjud edi.

example: If people populate an area, they live there.
type: Billions of people populate the Earth.
example_tr: Agar odamlar biror hududda yashasa, u erda yashaydi.
column14: Yer yuzida milliardlab odamlar yashaydi.

example: To produce something is to make or grow it.
type: This tree produces apples every year.
example_tr: Biror narsani ishlab chiqarish - uni ishlab chiqarish yoki etishtirishdir.
column14: Bu daraxt har yili olma beradi.

example: A range is a number or a set of similar things.
type: I saw a range of cars to choose from.
example_tr: Diapazon - bu raqam yoki shunga o'xshash narsalar to'plami.
column14: Men tanlash uchun bir qator mashinalarni ko'rdim.

example: To recognize something is to know it because you have seen it before.
type: I recognized an old friend from many years ago.
example_tr: Biror narsani tan olish - uni bilish, chunki siz uni ilgari ko'rgansiz.
column14: Men ko'p yillar oldin eski do'stimni tanidim.

example: If something is regular, it happens often and in equal amounts of time.
type: Our regular lunch time is around noon.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muntazam bo'lsa, u tez-tez va teng miqdorda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Bizning odatiy tushlik vaqtimiz tushga yaqin.

example: A sign is a notice giving information, directions, a warning, etc.
type: The sign indicated that today would be a bad day.
example_tr: Belgi - bu ma'lumot, yo'l-yo'riq, ogohlantirish va hk.
column14: Belgi bugun yomon kun bo'lishini ko'rsatdi.

example: A tip is a pointed end of something.
type: The tip of his pen was very sharp.
example_tr: Maslahat - biror narsaning uchi uchi.
column14: Qalamining uchi juda o‘tkir edi.

example: A tradition is something people have been doing for a long time.
type: Marriage is a tradition all over the world.
example_tr: An'ana - bu odamlar uzoq vaqtdan beri qiladigan narsa.
column14: Nikoh butun dunyoda an'anaga aylangan.

example: Trash is waste material or unwanted or worthless things.
type: Please take out the trash; it smells bad.
example_tr: Axlat - bu chiqindi material yoki keraksiz yoki keraksiz narsalar.
column14: Iltimos, axlatni olib tashlang; yomon hid keladi.

example: If something is wide, it is large from side to side.
type: The door was as wide as my arms.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keng bo'lsa, u yon tomondan katta.
column14: Eshik mening qo‘llarimdek keng edi.

example: Advice is an opinion about what to do.
type: I don’t know how to study for my exams. Can you give me some advice!
example_tr: Maslahat - bu nima qilish kerakligi haqidagi fikr.
column14: Men imtihonlarimga qanday o'qishni bilmayman. Menga maslahat bera olasizmi!

example: Along means to move from one part of a road, river, etc. to another.
type: Walk along this tunnel for ten minutes, and you'll see a door on the left
example_tr: Boʻylab yoʻlning, daryoning va hokazolarning bir qismidan ikkinchisiga oʻtish maʼnosini bildiradi.
column14: Ushbu tunnel bo'ylab o'n daqiqa yuring va chap tomonda eshikni ko'rasiz

example: Attention is the notice, thought, or consideration of someone.
type: His work got the attention of two of his co-workers.
example_tr: Diqqat - bu kimnidir ogohlantirishi, fikri yoki e'tibori.
column14: Uning ishi ikki hamkasbining e'tiborini tortdi.

example: To attract means to make a person or thing come closer or be interested.
type: The magnet attracted the metal.
example_tr: O'ziga jalb qilish, odamni yoki narsalarni yaqinlashtirish yoki qiziqtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Magnit metallni o'ziga tortdi.

example: To climb means to use your hands and feet to go up on something.
type: The girls climbed to the top of the mountain.
example_tr: Ko'tarilish - bu biror narsaga ko'tarilish uchun qo'l va oyoqlaringizni ishlatishni anglatadi.
column14: Qizlar tog‘ cho‘qqisiga chiqishdi.

example: To drop is to fall or allow something to fall.
type: A small amount of water dropped from the bottle.
example_tr: Yiqilish - yiqilish yoki biror narsaning tushishiga ruxsat berish.
column14: Shishadan oz miqdorda suv tushdi.

example: If something is final, it is the last part.
type: In the final part of the film, the man and the woman got married.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yakuniy bo'lsa, bu oxirgi qismdir.
column14: Filmning yakuniy qismida erkak va ayol turmush qurishdi.

example: Further is used to say something is from a distance or time.
type: The escalator is further along than I thought.
example_tr: Keyinchalik biror narsa uzoqdan yoki vaqtdan ekanligini aytish uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: Eskalator men o'ylagandan uzoqroqda.

example: To imply something is to suggest it without saying it.
type: The man implied that he wanted the job, but he
example_tr: Biror narsani nazarda tutmoq, uni aytmasdan taklif qilishdir.
column14: Erkak ishni xohlayotganini aytdi, lekin u

example: To maintain means to make something stay the same.
type: The balls maintain constant movement.
example_tr: Saqlash, biror narsani o'zgarishsiz qoldirishni anglatadi.
column14: To'plar doimiy harakatni saqlaydi.

example: You use neither to connect two negative statements.
type: Neither the pass on the left nor the pass on the right will lead us home.
example_tr: Ikkita salbiy iborani ulash uchun hech birini ishlatmaysiz.
column14: Chapdagi dovon ham, o'ngdagi dovon ham bizni uyga olib bormaydi.

example: Otherwise means different or in another way.
type: It’s good to stay active; otherwise, you’ll gain weight.
example_tr: Aks holda, boshqacha yoki boshqa ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Faol bo'lish yaxshi; aks holda siz kilogramm olasiz.

example: If something is physical, it is related to your body and not your mind.
type: Biking is good for your physical health.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jismoniy bo'lsa, bu sizning ongingiz bilan emas, balki tanangiz bilan bog'liq.
column14: Velosiped haydash jismoniy salomatligingiz uchun foydalidir.

example: To prove something is to show that it is true.
type: My teacher proved the answer on the board.
example_tr: Biror narsani isbotlash - bu haqiqat ekanligini ko'rsatish.
column14: O‘qituvchim doskada javobni isbotlab berdi.

example: To react is to act in a certain way because of something that happened.
type: James reacted badly to the news.
example_tr: Reaksiya qilish - sodir bo'lgan narsa tufayli ma'lum bir tarzda harakat qilish.
column14: Jeyms bu xabarga yomon munosabatda bo'ldi.

example: To ride something is to travel on it. You can ride an animal, a bike, etc.
type: I will ride a roller-coaster for the first time today.
example_tr: Biror narsaga minish - bu uning ustida sayohat qilish. Siz hayvon, velosiped va boshqalarni minishingiz mumkin.
column14: Men bugun birinchi marta roller-coaster minaman.

example: If something is situated somewhere, it is in that place.
type: The white board is situated between the two men.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa biror joyda joylashgan bo'lsa, u o'sha joyda.
column14: Oq taxta ikki erkak o'rtasida joylashgan.

example: Society is people and the way that they live.
type: Society expects people to be good and honest.
example_tr: Jamiyat - bu odamlar va ularning yashash tarzi.
column14: Jamiyat odamlardan yaxshi va halol bo'lishini kutadi.

example: A standard is what people consider normal or good.
type: This older model TV is below our store’s standards.
example_tr: Standart - bu odamlar normal yoki yaxshi deb hisoblaydigan narsa.
column14: Ushbu eski modeldagi televizor do'konimiz standartlaridan past.

example: To suggest means to give an idea or plan about something.
type: He suggested that we go to see his boss.
example_tr: Taklif qilish, biror narsa haqida fikr yoki reja berishni anglatadi.
column14: U boshlig‘ining oldiga borishimizni taklif qildi.

example: Actually means in fact or really.
type: My dad looks a little mean, but actually he’s very kind.
example_tr: Aslida haqiqatda yoki haqiqatda degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Dadam biroz yomon ko'rinadi, lekin aslida u juda mehribon.

example: Bite is the act of using your teeth to cut and tear into something.
type: The boy took a big bite out of his hamburger.
example_tr: Tishlash - biror narsani kesish va yirtish uchun tishlarni ishlatish harakati.
column14: Bola gamburgeridan katta tishlab oldi.

example: The coast is the land by an ocean.
type: I stayed on the southern coast of Australia.
example_tr: Sohil - bu okean bo'yidagi quruqlik.
column14: Men Avstraliyaning janubiy qirg'og'ida qoldim.

example: A deal is an agreement that you have with another person.
type: I made a deal with the other company to give us some money.
example_tr: Bitim - bu boshqa shaxs bilan tuzilgan shartnoma.
column14: Bizga pul berish uchun boshqa kompaniya bilan shartnoma tuzdim.

example: The desert is an area of land without many plants or water.
type: Not many plants grow in the desert.
example_tr: Cho'l - ko'p o'simlik va suvsiz quruqlik maydoni.
column14: Cho'lda ko'p o'simliklar o'smaydi.

example: An earthquake is a shaking movement of the ground.
type: The building shook during the earthquake.
example_tr: Zilzila - yerning silkinishi.
column14: Zilzila paytida bino silkindi.

example: If something is effective, it works well.
type: Swimming is an effective way to stay healthy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa samarali bo'lsa, u yaxshi ishlaydi.
column14: Suzish - sog'lom bo'lishning samarali usuli.

example: To examine something is to look at it carefully.
type: The doctor examined my eyes today.
example_tr: Biror narsani tekshirish - unga diqqat bilan qarash.
column14: Bugun shifokor ko'zlarimni tekshirdi.

example: If something is false, it is not correct.
type: If you think the answer is false, press the red button.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noto'g'ri bo'lsa, u to'g'ri emas.
column14: Agar javob noto'g'ri deb hisoblasangiz, qizil tugmani bosing.

example: A gift is something you give someone.
type: Dave received many gifts for Christmas.
example_tr: Sovg'a - bu siz kimgadir beradigan narsadir.
column14: Deyv Rojdestvo uchun ko'plab sovg'alar oldi.

example: Hunger is the feeling that you get when you need to eat.
type: After playing all day long, he was filled with hunger.
example_tr: Ochlik - bu ovqatlanish kerak bo'lganda paydo bo'ladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Kun bo'yi o'ynab, ochlikdan to'lib ketdi.

example: To imagine something is to think of it in your mind.
type: Sally imagined herself winning lots of money.
example_tr: Biror narsani tasavvur qilish, uni miyangizda o'ylashdir.
column14: Sally o'zini juda ko'p pul yutganini tasavvur qildi.

example: A journey is a long trip.
type: I went on a journey across the country with my parents.
example_tr: Sayohat - bu uzoq safar.
column14: Men ota-onam bilan mamlakat bo'ylab sayohatga chiqdim.

example: A puzzle is something that is hard to understand.
type: The question was a puzzle to him.
example_tr: Jumboq - bu tushunish qiyin bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Bu savol uning uchun boshqotirma edi.

example: Quite is used to say that something is complete or very much.
type: I think typing on a keyboard is quite easy.
example_tr: Quite biror narsa to'liq yoki juda ko'p ekanligini aytish uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: Menimcha, klaviaturada yozish juda oson.

example: Rather is used when you want to do one thing but not the other.
type: I would rather have the red one than the blue one.
example_tr: To'g'rirog'i, siz bir narsani qilmoqchi bo'lsangiz, boshqasini qilmasangiz ishlatiladi.
column14: Men ko'kdan ko'ra qizilni afzal ko'raman.

example: If something is specific, it is precise or exact.
type: Please choose a specific place on the map.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u aniq yoki aniq.
column14: Iltimos, xaritada aniq joyni tanlang.

example: A tour is a short trip in which you see many sights.
type: I took a tour of Asia and Europe.
example_tr: Ekskursiya - bu ko'plab diqqatga sazovor joylarni ko'radigan qisqa sayohat.
column14: Men Osiyo va Yevropa bo‘ylab sayohat qildim.

example: A trip is a journey to a certain place.
type: Ken took a trip to the city yesterday.
example_tr: Sayohat - bu ma'lum bir joyga sayohat.
column14: Ken kecha shaharga sayohat qildi.

example: If something has value, it is worth a lot of money.
type: Matthew found a treasure of very high value.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qimmatga ega bo'lsa, u juda ko'p pulga arziydi.
column14: Metyu juda qimmatli xazinani topdi.

example: A band is a group of people who play music.
type: My brother is in a rock band.
example_tr: Guruh - bu musiqa ijro etadigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Akam rok guruhida.

example: Barely means by the smallest amount, almost not.
type: I barely had enough money to pay for my bus ticket.
example_tr: Zo'rg'a eng kichik miqdorni anglatadi, deyarli yo'q.
column14: Avtobus chiptasini to‘lashga zo‘rg‘a pulim bor edi.

example: If something is boring, it is not fun.
type: I think the internet is boring.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa zerikarli bo'lsa, bu qiziq emas.
column14: Menimcha, internet zerikarli.

example: To cancel means to decide that an event or a request will not happen.
type: She cancelled the rest of her plans because of the rain.
example_tr: Bekor qilish, biror voqea yoki so'rov sodir bo'lmasligi haqida qaror qabul qilishni anglatadi.
column14: U yomg'ir tufayli qolgan rejalarini bekor qildi.

example: A driveway is a short private road that leads to a person’s home.
type: The long driveway led us to their new house.
example_tr: Avtomobil yo'li - bu odamning uyiga olib boradigan qisqa shaxsiy yo'l.
column14: Uzoq yo'l bizni ularning yangi uyiga olib bordi.

example: Garbage is waste material like unwanted or spoiled food, bottles, paper, etc.
type: The boy cleaned up the garbage around his house.
example_tr: Axlat - bu keraksiz yoki buzilgan oziq-ovqat, shisha, qog'oz va boshqalar kabi chiqindilar.
column14: Bola uyi atrofidagi axlatlarni tozaladi.

example: An instrument is a tool designed to do a certain task like music.
type: My favorite musical instrument is the piano.
example_tr: Asbob musiqa kabi ma'lum bir vazifani bajarish uchun mo'ljallangan asbobdir.
column14: Mening sevimli musiqa asbobim - pianino.

example: A list is a record of information printed with an item on each line.
type: My mom makes a list of groceries to buy.
example_tr: Ro'yxat - bu har bir satrda bir element bilan chop etilgan ma'lumotlarning yozuvi.
column14: Onam xarid qilish uchun oziq-ovqat ro'yxatini tuzadi.

example: Magic is the power to do impossible things.
type: The magician used magic to pull a rabbit out of his hat.
example_tr: Sehr - imkonsiz narsalarni qilish kuchi.
column14: Sehrgar shlyapasidan quyonni tortib olish uchun sehr ishlatgan.

example: A message is a set of words that you send to someone.
type: I left a message for you in the envelope.
example_tr: Xabar - bu kimgadir yuboradigan so'zlar to'plami.
column14: Men sizga konvertda xabar qoldirdim.

example: To notice something is to see it for the first time.
type: Did you notice the view?
example_tr: Biror narsani payqash, uni birinchi marta ko'rishdir.
column14: Ko'rinishga e'tibor berdingizmi?

example: To own something means to have it. That thing belongs to you.
type: My grandfather owns that house.
example_tr: Biror narsaga egalik qilish, unga ega bo'lishni anglatadi. Bu narsa sizga tegishli.
column14: Bu uy mening bobomga tegishli.

example: To predict something is to say that it will happen.
type: She predicted that I would get married next year.
example_tr: Biror narsani bashorat qilish - bu sodir bo'lishini aytish.
column14: U kelasi yil turmush qurishimni bashorat qilgan edi.

example: A professor is a person who teaches in college.
type: Mike’s science professor knows a lot about physics.
example_tr: Professor - bu kollejda dars beradigan shaxs.
column14: Maykning fan professori fizika haqida ko'p narsani biladi.

example: To rush is to go somewhere or do something very quickly.
type: Nancy rushed to finish her homework.
example_tr: Shoshilish - biror joyga borish yoki biror narsani juda tez qilish.
column14: Nensi uy vazifasini bajarishga shoshildi.

example: A schedule is a plan that tells you when to do things.
type: What is your class schedule for today?
example_tr: Jadval - bu ishlarni qachon qilish kerakligini aytadigan reja.
column14: Bugungi dars jadvalingiz qanday?

example: To share something is to give some of it to another person.
type: Jimmy shared his apple with me.
example_tr: Biror narsani bo'lishish, uning bir qismini boshqa odamga berishdir.
column14: Jimmi men bilan olmasini baham ko'rdi.

example: A stage is a place where actors or musicians act or sing.
type: A large screen was on the stage.
example_tr: Sahna - bu aktyorlar yoki musiqachilar harakat qiladigan yoki qo'shiq aytadigan joy.
column14: Sahnada katta ekran bor edi.

example: A storm is very bad weather. There is a lot of rain or snow.
type: Did that storm wake you up last night?
example_tr: Bo'ron - bu juda yomon ob-havo. Yomg'ir yoki qor ko'p.
column14: Kecha sizni bo'ron uyg'otdimi?

example: You use within to say that something is inside.
type: Within the box, there was a pizza.
example_tr: Siz ichkarida biror narsa borligini aytish uchun foydalanasiz.
column14: Qutida pitsa bor edi.

example: To advertise is to tell people about something on TV, radio, etc.
type: They used a rabbit to help them advertise their product.
example_tr: Reklama - bu odamlarga televizor, radio va hokazolarda biror narsa haqida aytib berishdir.
column14: Ular o'z mahsulotlarini reklama qilishda yordam berish uchun quyondan foydalanganlar.

example: To assign something to someone is to tell them to do it.
type: I assigned the worker an important task.
example_tr: Biror kishiga biror narsani tayinlash, uni bajarishni aytishdir.
column14: Men ishchiga muhim vazifani topshirdim.

example: An audience is a group of people who watch something together.
type: There was a large audience at the game.
example_tr: Tomoshabinlar - bu birgalikda biror narsani tomosha qiladigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: O'yinda tomoshabinlar ko'p edi.

example: Breakfast is the first meal of the day.
type: I eat breakfast at 8:00 every morning.
example_tr: Nonushta kunning birinchi taomidir.
column14: Men har kuni ertalab soat 8:00 da nonushta qilaman.

example: A competition is a contest to see who is the best at something.
type: He won the running competition over the weekend.
example_tr: Raqobat - bu kimning eng zo'r ekanligini aniqlash uchun musobaqa.
column14: U dam olish kunlari yugurish musobaqasida g'olib chiqdi.

example: If the weather is cool, it is a little bit cold.
type: The weather is cool in the fall.
example_tr: Havo salqin bo'lsa, biroz sovuq.
column14: Kuzda havo salqin.

example: If you gain something, you get more of it.
type: I gained some weight over the summer.
example_tr: Agar biror narsaga erishsangiz, undan ko'proq narsani olasiz.
column14: Men yozda biroz vazn oldim.

example: Importance means the quality or condition of being needed or valued.
type: VIPs are people of great importance.
example_tr: Muhimlik, zarur yoki qadrli bo'lish sifati yoki holatini anglatadi.
column14: VIPlar katta ahamiyatga ega odamlardir.

example: Knowledge is information that you have about something.
type: A music teacher should have good knowledge of music.
example_tr: Bilim - bu sizda biror narsa haqida mavjud bo'lgan ma'lumot.
column14: Musiqa o'qituvchisi musiqani yaxshi bilishi kerak.

example: If something is major, it is big or important.
type: I have a major problem. My boss wants me to do my project!
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u katta yoki muhim.
column14: Menda katta muammo bor. Xo'jayinim loyihamni bajarishimni xohlaydi!

example: Mean describes someone who is unkind or cruel.
type: My co-worker is a very mean person. He gets angry very quickly.
example_tr: Mean shafqatsiz yoki shafqatsiz odamni tasvirlaydi.
column14: Mening hamkasbim juda yomon odam. U juda tez jahli chiqadi.

example: If you prefer something, you want it more than something else.
type: I prefer to take the path that will lead me to a bright future.
example_tr: Agar biror narsani afzal ko'rsangiz, uni boshqa narsadan ko'ra ko'proq xohlaysiz.
column14: Meni yorug‘ kelajak sari yetaklaydigan yo‘ldan borishni afzal ko‘raman.

example: A president is the leader of a country.
type: The president of our country made an important announcement.
example_tr: Prezident mamlakat rahbaridir.
column14: Davlatimiz rahbari muhim bayonot berdi.

example: Progress is the act of getting closer to doing or finishing something.
type: Our company made financial progress this year.
example_tr: Taraqqiyot - bu biror narsani bajarish yoki tugatishga yaqinlashish harakati.
column14: Bu yil kompaniyamiz moliyaviy muvaffaqiyatga erishdi.

example: Respect is a good opinion of someone because they are good.
type: I have great respect for firemen.
example_tr: Hurmat - bu kimdir haqida yaxshi fikr, chunki ular yaxshi.
column14: Men o't o'chiruvchilarni juda hurmat qilaman.

example: If you are rich, you have a lot of money.
type: He’s rich, He can buy anything he wants.
example_tr: Agar siz boy bo'lsangiz, pulingiz juda ko'p.
column14: U boy, xohlagan narsasini sotib olishi mumkin.

example: A skill is the knowledge and ability that allows you to do something well.
type: A snowboarder must have the right skills to do well.
example_tr: Ko'nikma - bu biror narsani yaxshi bajarishga imkon beradigan bilim va qobiliyatdir.
column14: Snoubordchi yaxshi ishlash uchun to'g'ri ko'nikmalarga ega bo'lishi kerak.

example: Somehow means in a way or by some means which is not known.
type: He somehow had to find a way to reach the life preserver.
example_tr: Qaysidir ma'noda ma'lum bo'lmagan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: U qandaydir tarzda qutqaruvchiga erishish yo'lini topishi kerak edi.

example: Strength is the physical power that you have.
type: Exercising will increase your strength and give you more power.
example_tr: Kuch - bu sizda mavjud bo'lgan jismoniy kuch.
column14: Mashq qilish kuchingizni oshiradi va sizga ko'proq kuch beradi.

example: To vote is to officially choose between two or more things.
type: I voted for Billy to be our class president.
example_tr: Ovoz berish - bu ikki yoki undan ortiq narsadan rasman tanlash.
column14: Men Billini sinfimiz prezidenti bo'lishi uchun ovoz berdim.

example: If Something is above, it is at a higher level than something else.
type: He straightened the sign that was above the crowd.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yuqorida bo'lsa, u boshqa narsadan yuqori darajada.
column14: Olomon tepasida turgan belgini tuzatdi.

example: If something is ahead of something else, it is in front of it.
type: The blue car drove on ahead of us.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsadan oldinda bo'lsa, u oldinda.
column14: Ko‘k mashina oldimizda yurdi.

example: An amount is how much there is of something.
type: Can I use my card to pay for the entire amount?
example_tr: Miqdor - bu narsaning qancha miqdori.
column14: To'liq summani to'lash uchun kartamdan foydalana olamanmi?

example: A belief is a strong feeling that something is correct or true.
type: A preacher or priest should have a strong belief in God.
example_tr: E'tiqod - bu biror narsaning to'g'ri yoki haqiqat ekanligini kuchli his qilish.
column14: Voiz yoki ruhoniy Xudoga qattiq ishonishi kerak.

example: The center of something is the middle of it.
type: The center of a dart board is the most important spot.
example_tr: Biror narsaning markazi uning o'rtasidir.
column14: Dart taxtasining markazi eng muhim joy.

example: If something is common, it happens often or there is much of it.
type: It is common for snow to fall in the winter.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keng tarqalgan bo'lsa, u tez-tez sodir bo'ladi yoki uning ko'pi bor.
column14: Qishda qor yog'ishi odatiy holdir.

example: To cost is to require expenditure or payment.
type: These designer shoes cost more than the regular ones.
example_tr: Xarajat - bu xarajatlar yoki to'lovni talab qilish.
column14: Ushbu dizaynerlik poyafzallari odatdagidan qimmatroq.

example: To demonstrate something is to show how it is done.
type: She demonstrated her plan to her co-workers.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rsatish - bu qanday amalga oshirilganligini ko'rsatish.
column14: U o'z rejasini hamkasblariga namoyish etdi.

example: Different describes someone or something that is not the same as something else.
type: Each of my sisters has a different hair style from one another.
example_tr: Different kimnidir yoki boshqa narsa bilan bir xil bo'lmagan narsani tasvirlaydi.
column14: Opalarimning har birining soch turmagi bir-biridan farq qiladi.

example: Evidence is a fact or thing that you use to prove something.
type: He used the pictures as evidence that UFOs are real.
example_tr: Dalil - bu biror narsani isbotlash uchun foydalanadigan fakt yoki narsa.
column14: U suratlardan NUJlarning haqiqiy ekanligiga dalil sifatida foydalangan.

example: Honesty means the quality of being truthful or honest.
type: A courtroom should be a place of honesty.
example_tr: Halollik rostgo'ylik yoki halollik sifatini anglatadi.
column14: Sud zali halollik joyi bo'lishi kerak.

example: An idiom is a phrase with a meaning different from its words.
type: The idiom “when pigs fly” means that something will never happen.
example_tr: Idioma - so'zlaridan farqli ma'noga ega bo'lgan ibora.
column14: "cho'chqalar uchganda" idiomasi hech qachon biror narsa sodir bo'lmasligini anglatadi.

example: If something is independent, it is not controlled by something else.
type: She chose to live an independent life in the country.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mustaqil bo'lsa, u boshqa narsa tomonidan boshqarilmaydi.
column14: U mamlakatda mustaqil hayot kechirishni tanladi.

example: Inside means the inner part, space or side of something.
type: The inside of the box was empty.
example_tr: Ichkarida biror narsaning ichki qismi, bo'sh joyi yoki tomoni ma'nosini bildiradi.
column14: Qutining ichki qismi bo'sh edi.

example: A master is a person who is very good at something.
type: My brother is a master of taekwondo.
example_tr: Usta - biror narsaga juda usta odam.
column14: Akam taekvondo ustasi.

example: A memory is something you remember.
type: The memory of my first time in the city will always be the best.
example_tr: Xotira - bu siz eslagan narsadir.
column14: Shaharga birinchi marta kelganim xotirasi har doim eng yaxshisi bo'lib qoladi.

example: If something is proper, it is right.
type: It is not proper to throw your garbage on the road.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ri bo'lsa, u to'g'ri.
column14: Axlatni yo'lga tashlash to'g'ri emas.

example: To scan something is to look at it very carefully.
type: You must scan each person closely.
example_tr: Biror narsani skanerlash - unga juda ehtiyotkorlik bilan qarash.
column14: Har bir odamni diqqat bilan tekshirishingiz kerak.

example: A section is a part of something larger.
type: The green section of the graph is the most important part.
example_tr: Bo'lim kattaroq narsaning bir qismidir.
column14: Grafikning yashil qismi eng muhim qismdir.

example: The surface of something is the top part or outside of it.
type: The surface of the moon is very rough.
example_tr: Biror narsaning sirti uning yuqori qismi yoki tashqi qismidir.
column14: Oyning yuzasi juda qo'pol.

example: When a person is anxious, they worry that something bad will happen.
type: She was anxious about not making her appointment on time.
example_tr: Inson tashvishlansa, biror yomon narsa yuz berishidan xavotirlanadi.
column14: U uchrashuvni o‘z vaqtida bajara olmaslikdan xavotirda edi.

example: When something is awful, it is very bad.
type: Her performance last night was awful.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, bu juda yomon.
column14: Uning kechagi chiqishi dahshatli edi.

example: To consist of is to be made of parts or things.
type: Today's choices for lunch consisted of pizza, hamburgers, and hot dogs.
example_tr: Tarkib bo'lmoq qismlar yoki narsalardan iborat bo'lmoq.
column14: Tushlik uchun bugungi tanlovlar pizza, gamburger va hot-doglardan iborat edi.

example: To desire is to want something.
type: My sister desires a big house and lots of money.
example_tr: Hohish - biror narsani xohlash.
column14: Opam katta uy va ko'p pulni orzu qiladi.

example: When a person is eager about something, they are excited about it.
type: The man was eager to talk about the good news.
example_tr: Biror kishi biror narsaga ishtiyoqli bo'lsa, u bundan hayajonlanadi.
column14: U kishi xushxabar haqida gapirishga intilardi.

example: A household is all the people who live in one house.
type: Our household is made up of my father, my mother and me.
example_tr: Uy xo'jaligi - bu bir uyda yashovchi barcha odamlar.
column14: Bizning xonadonimiz otam, onam va mendan iborat.

example: An intent is a plan to do something.
type: Her intent is to visit Italy next summer.
example_tr: Niyat - bu biror narsa qilish rejasi.
column14: Uning niyati kelasi yozda Italiyaga borish.

example: A landscape is how an area of land looks.
type: The landscape of the country is very green.
example_tr: Landshaft - bu yerning qanday ko'rinishi.
column14: Mamlakat landshafti juda yashil.

example: To lift something is to move it higher.
type: The man tried to lift the box.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'tarish - uni yuqoriga ko'tarish.
column14: Erkak qutini ko‘tarmoqchi bo‘ldi.

example: To load is to put objects into something.
type: The man loaded the boxes into a truck.
example_tr: Yuklash - biror narsaga narsalarni qo'yish.
column14: Erkak qutilarni yuk mashinasiga ortdi.

example: A lung is the organ in the body that fills with air when breathing.
type: Having strong lungs is necessary for a healthy life.
example_tr: O'pka - bu nafas olayotganda havo bilan to'ldiriladigan tanadagi organ.
column14: Sog'lom hayot uchun kuchli o'pkaga ega bo'lish kerak.

example: A motion is a movement that someone makes.
type: The police officer made a motion with his hand.
example_tr: Harakat - bu kimdir qiladigan harakat.
column14: Politsiya xodimi qo'li bilan harakat qildi.

example: The pace of something is the speed at which it happens.
type: I ran the race at a slower pace than my friend.
example_tr: Biror narsaning tezligi - bu sodir bo'ladigan tezlik.
column14: Men poygada do'stimga qaraganda sekinroq yugurdim.

example: When someone is polite, they are acting in a thoughtful way.
type: The boy was very polite: he behaved very thoughtfully.
example_tr: Biror kishi muloyim bo'lsa, u o'ylangan tarzda harakat qiladi.
column14: Bola juda muloyim edi: u o'zini juda o'ychan tutdi.

example: To possess something is to have it or own it.
type: My uncle possesses three sheep, a chicken, a cow and a dog.
example_tr: Biror narsaga egalik qilish - unga egalik qilish yoki unga egalik qilish.
column14: Amakimning uchta qo'yi, tovuqi, sigiri va iti bor.

example: When something happens rapidly, it happens very fast.
type: The train moved rapidly on the tracks.
example_tr: Biror narsa tez sodir bo'lganda, u juda tez sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Poyezd relslarda tez harakat qildi.

example: To remark is to say something.
type: The teacher remarked on how quickly the students were learning.
example_tr: Qayd etish - biror narsani aytish.
column14: O'qituvchi o'quvchilar qanchalik tez o'zlashayotganini ta'kidladi.

example: To seek is to look for something.
type: If I have a problem, I seek my sister’s advice.
example_tr: Izlash - biror narsani izlash.
column14: Agar menda muammo bo'lsa, men singlimdan maslahat so'rayman.

example: To shine is to make a bright light.
type: The candles are shining in the dark room.
example_tr: Yorqinlik - yorqin nur qilish.
column14: Qorong'i xonada shamlar porlaydi.

example: To spill is to have something fall out of its container.
type: I spilled the coffee on the table.
example_tr: To'kish - idishidan biror narsa tushib ketishi.
column14: Men qahvani stolga to'kib tashladim.

example: To bring means to take someone or something to a person or place.
type: Oscar will bring in all the boxes.
example_tr: Olib keltirmoq kimnidir yoki biror narsani biror kishiga yoki joyga olib borishni anglatadi.
column14: Oskar barcha qutilarni olib keladi.

example: A castle is a building with strong walls where royalty usually lives.
type: The castle was built many years ago.
example_tr: Qal'a - bu odatda qirollik oilasi yashaydigan mustahkam devorlarga ega bino.
column14: Qal'a ko'p yillar oldin qurilgan.

example: To command someone is to tell them to do something.
type: The general commanded his army to attack.
example_tr: Biror kishiga buyruq berish, unga biror narsa qilishni aytishdir.
column14: General o‘z qo‘shiniga hujum qilishni buyurdi.

example: To counsel someone is to listen and give advice about a problem.
type: The teacher counseled the girl about her troubles.
example_tr: Biror kishiga maslahat berish - tinglash va muammo haqida maslahat berishdir.
column14: O'qituvchi qizga uning muammolari haqida maslahat berdi.

example: To ensure is to make certain that something happens.
type: Eating good food ensures that we stay healthy.
example_tr: Ta'minlash - biror narsa sodir bo'lishiga ishonch hosil qilish.
column14: To'g'ri ovqatlanish sog'lom bo'lishimizni ta'minlaydi.

example: An explosion is a violent burst, usually with a loud sound.
type: A nuclear explosion can cause great damage.
example_tr: Portlash - bu kuchli portlash, odatda baland ovoz bilan.
column14: Yadro portlashi katta zarar keltirishi mumkin.

example: Jewelry is something that people wear like earrings or necklaces.
type: The woman looked beautiful with her nice dress and jewelry.
example_tr: Zargarlik - bu odamlar sirg'a yoki marjonlarni kiyadigan narsadir.
column14: Ayol chiroyli ko'ylagi va taqinchoqlari bilan chiroyli ko'rinardi.

example: To land means to come to the ground usually from a ship or aircraft.
type: The parachutist landed safely on the ground.
example_tr: Qo'nish odatda kema yoki samolyotdan erga kelishni anglatadi.
column14: Parashyutchi yerga eson-omon tushdi.

example: A meteor is a rock from outer space that falls to Earth.
type: We saw a meteor in the sky last night.
example_tr: Meteor - bu koinotdan Yerga tushadigan tosh.
column14: Kecha biz osmonda meteoritni ko'rdik.

example: A monster is any imaginary frightening creature that looks strange.
type: The monster scared everyone in the village.
example_tr: Yirtqich hayvon g'alati ko'rinadigan har qanday hayoliy qo'rqinchli mavjudotdir.
column14: Yirtqich hayvon qishloqdagi hammani qo‘rqitdi.

example: If something is northern, it is in the direction of north.
type: It is much colder in northern countries than it is here.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa shimoliy bo'lsa, u shimol tomonda.
column14: Shimoliy mamlakatlarda bu yerga qaraganda ancha sovuqroq.

example: If something is remote, it is very far away and difficult to get to.
type: It took many days to get to the remote island.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa uzoqda bo'lsa, u juda uzoq va borish qiyin.
column14: Olis orolga yetib borish uchun ko‘p kunlar ketdi.

example: If something is southern, it is in the direction of south.
type: Taegu is located in the southern part of the Korean peninsula.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa janubiy bo'lsa, u janub tomonda.
column14: Taegu Koreya yarim orolining janubiy qismida joylashgan.

example: A statue is an image of a person or animal made of stone or metal.
type: I saw a beautiful statue of a lion today.
example_tr: Haykal - tosh yoki metalldan yasalgan odam yoki hayvonning tasviri.
column14: Men bugun go‘zal sher haykalini ko‘rdim.

example: Steam is water that has become hot and has turned into a misty gas.
type: We could see the steam rise from the boiling water.
example_tr: Bug 'issiq bo'lib, tumanli gazga aylangan suvdir.
column14: Qaynayotgan suvdan bug‘ ko‘tarilishini ko‘rdik.

example: To submit to someone is to agree to do what they tell you to do.
type: She submitted to her mother’s wishes and did her homework.
example_tr: Biror kishiga bo'ysunish - u sizga buyurgan narsaga rozi bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U onasining xohishiga bo'ysundi va uy vazifasini bajardi.

example: A temple is a building that is used for religious purposes.
type: The people visited the temple to pray.
example_tr: Ma'bad - diniy maqsadlarda foydalaniladigan bino.
column14: Odamlar ibodat qilish uchun ma'badga tashrif buyurishdi.

example: Upper means higher in position or place.
type: A home’s attic is at the upper part of the structure.
example_tr: Yuqori mavqe yoki joyda yuqoriroq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Uyning chodiri strukturaning yuqori qismida joylashgan.

example: A weed is a plant, especially one that is not useful or wanted.
type: The yard of the house was full of ugly weeds.
example_tr: Yovvoyi o't - bu o'simlik, ayniqsa foydali yoki kerakli bo'lmagan o'simlik.
column14: Uyning hovlisi xunuk o‘tlar bilan to‘la edi.

example: A wing is the part of an animal that lets it fly.
type: The bird used its wings to fly across the water.
example_tr: Qanot - bu hayvonning uchib ketishiga imkon beradigan qismi.
column14: Qush qanotlarini suv bo'ylab uchib o'tish uchun ishlatgan.

example: An arrow is a thin, straight stick shot from a bow.
type: The arrow flew through the air and hit the target.
example_tr: O'q - kamondan otilgan ingichka, tekis tayoq.
column14: O‘q havoda uchib, nishonga tegdi.

example: A battle is a fight between two armies during a war.
type: The battle lasted for many days.
example_tr: Jang - bu urush paytida ikki qo'shin o'rtasidagi jang.
column14: Jang ko'p kunlar davom etdi.

example: A bow is a weapon made of curved wood and string that shoots arrows
type: He went hunting with a bow and arrow.
example_tr: Yoy - egilgan yog'och va ipdan yasalgan qurol, o'q otadi
column14: O‘q-yoy bilan ovga chiqdi.

example: When people are brave, they are not afraid to face pain or danger.
type: The brave firefighter saved the girl from the burning building.
example_tr: Odamlar jasur bo'lsa, ular og'riq yoki xavfga duch kelishdan qo'rqmaydilar.
column14: Jasur o‘t o‘chiruvchi qizni yonayotgan binodan qutqarib qoldi.

example: A chief is the leader of a group of people.
type: The chief led the people through the mountains.
example_tr: Boshliq - bir guruh odamlarning rahbari.
column14: Boshliq odamlarni tog‘lardan o‘tkazdi.

example: A disadvantage is a situation where someone is likely to lose.
type: Mike had a disadvantage in the race since he hurt his knee,
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu kimdir yo'qotishi mumkin bo'lgan vaziyat.
column14: Mayk poygada kamchilikka duch keldi, chunki u tizzasini shikastladi,

example: An enemy is a country that is fighting another country during a war.
type: The enemy prepared to attack the kingdom.
example_tr: Urush paytida boshqa davlatga qarshi kurashayotgan davlat dushmandir.
column14: Dushman saltanatga hujum qilishga tayyorlandi.

example: An entrance is a place where someone can enter an area.
type: The gate was locked, so Bill had to find a different entrance.
example_tr: Kirish - bu biror kishining hududga kirishi mumkin bo'lgan joy.
column14: Darvoza qulflangan edi, shuning uchun Bill boshqa kirish yo'lini topishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: If something hardly happens, it almost does not happen at all.
type: I hardly saw the concert since I had to leave early.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa deyarli sodir bo'lmasa, u deyarli sodir bo'lmaydi.
column14: Erta ketishga majbur bo'lganim uchun kontsertni deyarli ko'rmadim.

example: To intend to do something means to plan to do it.
type: I intend to finish college in three years.
example_tr: Biror narsani qilishni niyat qilish, uni amalga oshirishni rejalashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kollejni uch yilda tamomlamoqchiman.

example: Laughter is the sound produced by laughing about something funny.
type: Susan’s joke made her classmates burst into laughter.
example_tr: Kulgi - bu kulgili narsa haqida kulish natijasida hosil bo'lgan ovoz.
column14: Syuzanning hazilidan sinfdoshlari kulib yuborishdi.

example: A log is a thick piece of wood that is cut from a tree.
type: The fire was too small, so we added another log to it.
example_tr: Kundalik - bu daraxtdan kesilgan qalin yog'och.
column14: Olov juda kichik edi, shuning uchun biz unga yana bir log qo'shdik.

example: The military is the armed forces of a country.
type: I joined the military after I finished high school.
example_tr: Harbiy - bu mamlakatning qurolli kuchlari.
column14: O‘rta maktabni tugatgach, harbiy xizmatga bordim.

example: To obey means to follow what a law or a person says you must do.
type: My little sister did not obey my mother. Now she is in trouble.
example_tr: Itoat qilish, qonun yoki shaxsning aytganiga rioya qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkina singlim onamga bo'ysunmadi. Endi u muammoga duch keldi.

example: To secure something means to get it after a lot of effort.
type: I was able to secure a good grade on my test after weeks of studying.
example_tr: Biror narsani ta'minlash, uni ko'p harakatlardan keyin olish demakdir.
column14: Men haftalar davomida o'qiganimdan so'ng testdan yaxshi baho olishga muvaffaq bo'ldim.

example: When someone or something is steady, they are under control.
type: The problem was hard but she remained steady and solved it.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa barqaror bo'lsa, ular nazorat ostida.
column14: Muammo qiyin edi, lekin u barqaror bo'lib, uni hal qildi.

example: To trust is to believe that someone is honest and will do what is right.
type: I trust my friends; they don’t tell my secrets to other people.
example_tr: Ishonish - bu kimdir halol ekanligiga va to'g'ri ish qilishiga ishonishdir.
column14: Men do'stlarimga ishonaman; ular mening sirlarimni boshqalarga aytmaydilar.

example: To twist something is to wrap it around itself or another thing.
type: She twisted the spaghetti around her fork.
example_tr: Biror narsani burish - uni o'ziga yoki boshqa narsaga o'rash.
column14: U spagettini sanchqisiga aylantirdi.

example: Unless means if not or except when.
type: Unless you clean your room, you cannot play with your friends.
example_tr: Agar bo'lmasa yoki qachondan tashqari degan ma'noni bildirmasa.
column14: Xonangizni tozalamaguningizcha, do'stlaringiz bilan o'ynay olmaysiz.

example: A weapon is an object that can be used to hurt people.
type: Swords have been used as weapons for thousands of years.
example_tr: Qurol - bu odamlarga zarar etkazish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Qilichlar ming yillar davomida qurol sifatida ishlatilgan.

example: The chest is the front part of a person’s body under the neck.
type: The water in the lake was as high as my chest.
example_tr: Ko'krak - bo'yin ostidagi odam tanasining old qismi.
column14: Ko‘ldagi suv ko‘ksimdek baland edi.

example: If you have confidence about something, you are sure of it.
type: I have confidence that I did well on the test.
example_tr: Agar biror narsaga ishonchingiz komil bo'lsa, bunga ishonchingiz komil.
column14: Imtihondan yaxshi o'tganimga ishonchim komil.

example: A consequence is a result of a choice or action.
type: As a consequence of missing my bus, I had to find another way to get home.
example_tr: Natija tanlov yoki harakat natijasidir.
column14: Avtobusni o'tkazib yuborganim sababli, uyga borishning boshqa yo'lini topishga majbur bo'ldim.

example: A disaster is a really bad thing that happens.
type: When the car crashed, it was a disaster.
example_tr: Falokat - bu sodir bo'ladigan juda yomon narsa.
column14: Mashina halokatga uchraganida, bu falokat edi.

example: To disturb someone means to upset them.
type: The loud noise disturbed me while I was working.
example_tr: Birovni bezovta qilish, uni xafa qilish demakdir.
column14: Ishlayotganimda qattiq shovqin meni bezovta qildi.

example: To estimate something means to make a guess about it.
type: The boy estimated that he was one meter tall.
example_tr: Biror narsani taxmin qilish, u haqida taxmin qilish demakdir.
column14: Bolaning bo'yi bir metrga teng deb hisoblagan.

example: When you honor people or things, you show respect for them.
type: I honor my science teacher by working hard in class.
example_tr: Odamlarni yoki narsalarni hurmat qilsangiz, ularga hurmat ko'rsatasiz.
column14: Darsda qattiq mehnat qilib, fan o‘qituvchimni hurmat qilaman.

example: To impress someone means to make that person proud.
type: He was able to impress the girls with his new dance.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayratda qoldirish, bu odamni mag'rur qilish demakdir.
column14: U yangi raqsi bilan qizlarni hayratga sola oldi.

example: A marathon is a very long foot race just over 42 kilometers.
type: I ran a marathon, and now my legs are tired.
example_tr: Marafon - bu 42 kilometrdan sal ko'proq masofaga yugurish bo'yicha juda uzun poyga.
column14: Men marafonda yugurdim, endi oyoqlarim charchagan.

example: When something is narrow, it is very thin.
type: The bridge is too narrow for a car to drive over.
example_tr: Biror narsa tor bo'lsa, u juda nozik bo'ladi.
column14: Ko‘prik juda tor bo‘lib, mashina o‘ta olmaydi.

example: When something is pale, it does not have a bright color.
type: The girl’s skin was very pale.
example_tr: Biror narsa oqargan bo'lsa, u yorqin rangga ega bo'lmaydi.
column14: Qizning terisi juda oqarib ketgan edi.

example: When something is rough, it is not even or smooth.
type: The rough ground hurt my feet.
example_tr: Biror narsa qo'pol bo'lsa, u tekis yoki silliq emas.
column14: Dag‘al zamin oyoqlarimni og‘ritdi.

example: To satisfy someone means to make them happy.
type: It will satisfy my teacher if I finish all my homework.
example_tr: Biror kishini qondirish, uni baxtli qilish demakdir.
column14: Barcha uy vazifalarimni tugatsam, o'qituvchimni qoniqtiradi.

example: To scream means to make a loud noise with your mouth.
type: The girl saw a spider and screamed.
example_tr: Qichqirish og'iz bilan baland ovozda ovoz chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Qiz o'rgimchakni ko'rdi va qichqirdi.

example: When someone or something is sensitive, they are easily hurt.
type: My teeth are sensitive to cold things.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa sezgir bo'lsa, ular osonlikcha xafa bo'lishadi.
column14: Mening tishlarim sovuq narsalarga sezgir.

example: The shade is a dark area that something makes when it blocks the sun.
type: It was hot outside, so the boy sat in the shade of a tree.
example_tr: Soya - bu quyoshni to'sib qo'yganda paydo bo'ladigan qorong'i joy.
column14: Tashqarida havo issiq edi, shuning uchun bola daraxt soyasida o'tirdi.

example: To supplement something is to add something else to it in a good way.
type: He supplements his diet with fresh fruits.
example_tr: Biror narsani to'ldirish, unga boshqa narsani yaxshi ma'noda qo'shishdir.
column14: U o'z dietasini yangi mevalar bilan to'ldiradi.

example: When someone feels terror, they are scared.
type: I felt a sense of terror when the tiger chased me.
example_tr: Biror kishi qo'rquvni his qilsa, u qo'rqib ketadi.
column14: Yo‘lbars meni ta’qib qilganida qo‘rquvni his qildim.

example: A threat is something bad that might happen.
type: Due to the dark clouds, there was a threat of a bad storm.
example_tr: Tahdid - bu sodir bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan yomon narsa.
column14: Qora bulutlar tufayli yomon bo'ron xavfi bor edi.

example: A victim is a person that had something bad happen to them.
type: I was a victim of a robbery.
example_tr: Jabrlanuvchi - ular bilan yomon narsa sodir bo'lgan odam.
column14: Men talonchilik qurboni bo‘ldim.

example: An ancestor is a family member from the past.
type: My ancestors came from Germany.
example_tr: Ajdod - bu o'tmishdagi oila a'zosi.
column14: Mening ota-bobolarim Germaniyadan kelgan.

example: An angle is the direction from which you look at something.
type: The giraffe turned its head to see from another angle.
example_tr: Burchak - bu biror narsaga qaraydigan yo'nalish.
column14: Jirafa boshqa tomondan ko'rish uchun boshini burdi.

example: A boot is a heavy shoe that goes over your ankle.
type: He wore boots so that his feet wouldn’t get wet.
example_tr: Etik - to'pig'ingizdan o'tib ketadigan og'ir poyabzal.
column14: Oyoqlari ho'l bo'lmasligi uchun etik kiyib olgan.

example: A border is the edge of an area.
type: The postcard had a pretty green border of pine needles.
example_tr: Chegara - bu hududning chekkasi.
column14: Pochta kartochkasida qarag'ay ignalarining juda yashil chegarasi bor edi.

example: To congratulate someone is to tell them that you are happy for them.
type: Bill and Angela congratulated each other on a job well done.
example_tr: Biror kishini tabriklash, u uchun baxtli ekanligingizni aytishdir.
column14: Bill va Anjela bir-birlarini yaxshi bajarilgan ish bilan tabriklashdi.

example: A frame is a border for a picture or mirror.
type: I have to get a frame for my friend's picture.
example_tr: Ramka - bu rasm yoki oyna uchun chegara.
column14: Do'stimning surati uchun ramka olishim kerak.

example: Heaven is the place that some people believe people go when they die.
type: When I die, I hope that I go to heaven.
example_tr: Jannat, ba'zi odamlar odamlar o'lganlarida borishlariga ishonadigan joy.
column14: O‘lsam, jannatga kirishimni umid qilaman.

example: If someone or something is incredible, it is hard to believe they are true.
type: I have an incredible story to tell you about my vacation.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa aql bovar qilmaydigan bo'lsa, ularning haqiqat ekanligiga ishonish qiyin.
column14: Mening ta'tilim haqida sizga aytib beradigan ajoyib hikoyam bor.

example: A legend is a story from the past.
type: There is a well-known legend about a king and his queen.
example_tr: Afsona - bu o'tmishdagi voqea.
column14: Shoh va uning malikasi haqida mashhur afsona bor.

example: To praise is to show that you like someone or something.
type: The coach praised both athletes after a good practice.
example_tr: Maqtov - kimnidir yoki biror narsani yoqtirishingizni ko'rsatish.
column14: Murabbiy yaxshi mashg‘ulotlardan so‘ng har ikki sportchini ham olqishladi.

example: To proceed is to go in a certain direction.
type: My son and I proceeded to the beach so we could go fishing.
example_tr: Davom etish - ma'lum bir yo'nalishda borish.
column14: O'g'lim bilan men baliq ovlash uchun sohilga bordik.

example: If something is pure, it is very clear and beautiful.
type: The rose was pure. It had no dirt or imperfections.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sof bo'lsa, u juda aniq va chiroyli.
column14: Atirgul toza edi. Unda axloqsizlik va kamchiliklar yo'q edi.

example: A relative is a family member.
type: My relatives came by to see the new baby.
example_tr: Qarindosh - bu oila a'zosi.
column14: Qarindoshlarim yangi chaqaloqni ko'rgani kelishdi.

example: If one is senior, they are the oldest or have been there the longest.
type: Because he got his job first, Bob is the senior chef.
example_tr: Agar ulardan biri katta bo'lsa, ular eng keksa yoki u erda eng uzoq vaqt bo'lgan.
column14: U birinchi bo'lib ishlagani uchun Bob katta oshpaz.

example: If someone or something is silent, they make no sound.
type: Since no one was home, the house was silent.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa jim bo'lsa, ular hech qanday ovoz chiqarmaydi.
column14: Uyda hech kim bo'lmagani uchun uy jimjit edi.

example: To sink into something is to slowly fall into it.
type: The boat had a hole in it, and it sank into the ocean.
example_tr: Biror narsaga botish - asta-sekin unga tushish.
column14: Qayiqda teshik bor edi va u okeanga cho'kib ketdi.

example: If someone or something is superior, they are better than another.
type: I think cooking outdoors is superior to cooking indoors.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa ustun bo'lsa, ular boshqasidan yaxshiroqdir.
column14: Menimcha, ochiq havoda pishirish uyda pishirishdan ustundir.

example: To surround something is to close in on it from all sides.
type: We surrounded the suspect on all four sides.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rab olish - uni har tomondan yopish.
column14: Gumonlanuvchini to‘rt tomondan o‘rab oldik.

example: If something is thick, it is wide and solid.
type: The fog was so thick that I couldn’t see through it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qalin bo'lsa, u keng va mustahkamdir.
column14: Tuman shunchalik qalin ediki, men uni ko'ra olmadim.

example: To wrap is to cover something on all sides.
type: I wrapped his gift and put a bow on it.
example_tr: O'rash - biror narsani har tomondan yopish.
column14: Men uning sovg'asini o'rab, ustiga kamon qo'ydim.

example: If Someone goes or travels abroad, they go to another country.
type: My brother wants to go abroad next year,
example_tr: Kimdir chet elga ketsa yoki sayohat qilsa, boshqa davlatga ketadi.
column14: Akam kelasi yil chet elga ketmoqchi

example: To anger someone is to make them mad.
type: It angers me when people are rude.
example_tr: Birovni g'azablantirish, uni aqldan ozdirishdir.
column14: Odamlar qo'pol bo'lsa, bu meni g'azablantiradi.

example: A bride is a woman who is getting married or has just gotten married.
type: The bride looked beautiful in her wedding dress.
example_tr: Kelin - turmushga chiqayotgan yoki endigina turmushga chiqqan ayol.
column14: Kelin ko'ylagida chiroyli ko'rinardi.

example: If something is brief, it only lasts for a short time.
type: The meeting this afternoon was very brief.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qisqa bo'lsa, u faqat qisqa vaqt davom etadi.
column14: Bugun tushdan keyingi uchrashuv juda qisqa bo'ldi.

example: To chase someone or something is to follow them in order to catch them.
type: I was chased by an angry native.
example_tr: Kimnidir yoki biror narsani ta'qib qilish, uni qo'lga olish uchun unga ergashishdir.
column14: Meni g‘azablangan vatandoshim quvdi.

example: To disappoint is to make one feel sad or unsatisfied.
type: I do not want to disappoint my family, so I try to do well at school.
example_tr: Ko'ngli qoldirish - odamni qayg'uga solish yoki qoniqishsizlik hissini uyg'otish.
column14: Men oilamni xafa qilishni xohlamayman, shuning uchun maktabda yaxshi o'qishga harakat qilaman.

example: To dive is to jump into water.
type: I will dive into the lake once we get there.
example_tr: Sho'ng'ish - suvga sakrash.
column14: U erga etib borganimizdan keyin men ko'lga sho'ng'aman.

example: To exchange means to give something for another thing in return.
type: I exchanged my foreign money for American dollars.
example_tr: Almashtirish evaziga biror narsani boshqa narsaga berish demakdir.
column14: Men chet eldagi pulimni Amerika dollariga almashtirdim.

example: A favor is something you do for someone to help them.
type: Can you do me a favor and turn off the lights?
example_tr: Yaxshilik - bu kimgadir ularga yordam berish uchun qiladigan narsadir.
column14: Menga bir yaxshilik qilib, chiroqlarni o'chira olasizmi?

example: A fee is an amount of money that a person or company asks for a service.
type: I had to pay an hourly fee to speak with my lawyer.
example_tr: To'lov - bu shaxs yoki kompaniya xizmat uchun so'ragan pul miqdori.
column14: Advokatim bilan gaplashish uchun soatiga pul to'lashim kerak edi.

example: If something lasts forever, it means it lasts for all time.
type: The young couple promised that they would love each other forever.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa abadiy davom etsa, demak u hamma vaqt davom etadi.
column14: Yosh er-xotin bir-birlarini abadiy sevishlarini va'da qilishdi.

example: A guy is an informal way to call a man.
type: The guy at the flower shop was really helpful today.
example_tr: Yigit - bu erkakni chaqirishning norasmiy usuli.
column14: Gul do'konidagi yigit bugun juda foydali bo'ldi.

example: If people or things are lovely, they are good-looking or beautiful.
type: The trees look lovely in the fall.
example_tr: Agar odamlar yoki narsalar yoqimli bo'lsa, ular chiroyli yoki chiroyli.
column14: Daraxtlar kuzda chiroyli ko'rinadi.

example: A mood is the way someone is feeling.
type: I am in a good mood because I did well on my math test.
example_tr: Kayfiyat - bu kimnidir his qilish usuli.
column14: Kayfiyatim yaxshi, chunki matematika imtihonini yaxshi o‘tkazdim.

example: A palace is a very large building. It is often the home of a royal family.
type: The king and queen live in a beautiful palace.
example_tr: Saroy juda katta bino. Bu ko'pincha qirollik oilasining uyidir.
column14: Qirol va malika chiroyli saroyda yashaydi.

example: To permit something is to let someone do it.
type: I was sick, so my mother permitted me to stay home from school.
example_tr: Biror narsaga ruxsat berish, kimdir buni qilishga ruxsat berishdir.
column14: Men kasal edim, shuning uchun onam maktabdan uyda qolishimga ruxsat berdi.

example: To protest something is to argue about it with someone.
type: The people protested the decision of the president.
example_tr: Biror narsaga e'tiroz bildirish - bu haqda kimdir bilan bahslashish.
column14: Xalq prezident qaroriga norozilik bildirdi.

example: A sculpture is a piece of art that is made from wood, clay, or stone.
type: We saw an old sculpture of Buddha at the museum.
example_tr: Haykal - bu yog'och, loy yoki toshdan yasalgan san'at asari.
column14: Biz muzeyda Buddaning eski haykalini ko'rdik.

example: A tribe is a group of people who live in the same culture.
type: There’s a small tribe of people who live in the mountains of Spain.
example_tr: Qabila - bir xil madaniyatda yashaydigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Ispaniyaning tog'larida yashaydigan kichik bir qabilasi bor.

example: Youth is a time in people’s lives when they are young.
type: My mother wanted to be a nurse in her youth.
example_tr: Yoshlik - bu odamlar hayotidagi yoshlik davri.
column14: Onam yoshligida hamshira bo'lishni orzu qilgan.

example: To do something on time’s basis is how often you do it.
type: My grandfather gets his hearing checked on a yearly basis.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'z vaqtida qilish - bu uni qanchalik tez-tez qilishdir.
column14: Mening bobom har yili eshitish qobiliyatini tekshiradi.

example: Biology is the study of living things.
type: We learned about the human heart in biology class.
example_tr: Biologiya tirik mavjudotlarni o'rganadi.
column14: Biz biologiya darsida inson qalbi haqida bilib oldik.

example: A cage is something that holds an animal so it cannot leave.
type: We put the parrots in their cage at night.
example_tr: Qafas - bu hayvonni tark eta olmaydigan narsadir.
column14: Kechasi to'tiqushlarni qafasga solamiz.

example: A colleague is somebody you work with.
type: My colleague helped me finish the job.
example_tr: Hamkasb - bu siz bilan birga ishlaydigan odam.
column14: Ishni tugatishimga hamkasbim yordam berdi.

example: A colony is a country controlled by another country.
type: The USA was at one time a colony of Great Britain.
example_tr: Koloniya - bu boshqa davlat tomonidan boshqariladigan davlat.
column14: AQSh bir vaqtlar Buyuk Britaniyaning mustamlakasi edi.

example: To debate is to seriously discuss something with someone.
type: The husband and wife debated over which TV to buy.
example_tr: Munozara - kimdir bilan biror narsani jiddiy muhokama qilish.
column14: Er va xotin qaysi televizor sotib olishni muhokama qilishdi.

example: To depart is to leave some place so you can go to another place.
type: The plane departed for Italy at 3:00 this afternoon.
example_tr: Ketish - bu boshqa joyga borishingiz uchun biror joyni tark etishdir.
column14: Samolyot bugun tushdan keyin soat 3:00da Italiyaga jo'nab ketdi.

example: To depress someone is to make them sad.
type: The bad news from work depressed the man.
example_tr: Biror kishini tushkunlikka tushirish, uni xafa qilishdir.
column14: Ishdan kelgan yomon xabar odamni tushkunlikka soldi.

example: When something is factual, it is true.
type: John learns about history from factual books.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa haqiqat bo'lsa, u haqiqatdir.
column14: Jon tarixni faktik kitoblardan bilib oladi.

example: To fascinate someone is to make them really like something.
type: The kitten was fascinated by the ball of yarn.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayratda qoldirish, unga haqiqatan ham biror narsani yoqtirishdir.
column14: Mushukcha ipning to'pi bilan hayratga tushdi.

example: A mission is an important job that is sometimes far away.
type: The woman’s mission was to help sick people.
example_tr: Missiya ba'zan uzoqda bo'lgan muhim ishdir.
column14: Ayolning vazifasi kasallarga yordam berish edi.

example: You use nevertheless to show that something goes against a fact.
type: He is usually friendly. Nevertheless, he wasn’t this afternoon.
example_tr: Shunga qaramay, biror narsa haqiqatga zid ekanligini ko'rsatish uchun foydalanasiz.
column14: U odatda do'stona. Shunga qaramay, u bugun tushdan keyin emas edi.

example: An occupation is a person’s job.
type: My father’s occupation is a dentist.
example_tr: Kasb - bu insonning ishi.
column14: Otamning kasbi tish shifokori.

example: IF you go Overseas, you go to a country on the other side of an ocean.
type: John often goes overseas for vacations.
example_tr: Agar siz xorijga chiqsangiz, okeanning narigi tomonidagi mamlakatga borasiz.
column14: Jon tez-tez ta'til uchun chet elga boradi.

example: To persuade someone is to make them agree to do something.
type: The children persuaded their parents to buy them gifts.
example_tr: Biror kishini ishontirish, uni biror narsa qilishga rozi qilishdir.
column14: Bolalar ota-onalarini sovg'a sotib olishga ko'ndirdilar.

example: A route is the way you go from one place to another.
type: I saw many new houses along the route to the city.
example_tr: Marshrut - bu bir joydan ikkinchi joyga boradigan yo'l.
column14: Men shaharga boradigan yo'lda ko'plab yangi uylarni ko'rdim.

example: Ruins are old buildings that are not used anymore.
type: I visited some interesting ruins in Greece.
example_tr: Xarobalar endi foydalanilmayotgan eski binolardir.
column14: Men Gretsiyadagi qiziqarli xarobalarni ziyorat qildim.

example: Ascholar is a person who studies something and knows much about it.
type: The scholar knew much about art history.
example_tr: Olim - biror narsani o'rganadigan va u haqida ko'p narsani biladigan odam.
column14: Olim san’at tarixi haqida ko‘p ma’lumotga ega edi.

example: When someone or something is significant, they are important.
type: I read many significant novels as a literature major in university.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, ular muhim.
column14: Universitetda adabiyot mutaxassisligi sifatida ko'plab muhim romanlarni o'qidim.

example: A volcano is a mountain with a hole on top where hot liquid comes out.
type: When the volcano erupted, smoke and heat filled the air.
example_tr: Vulkan - tepasida issiq suyuqlik chiqadigan teshikli tog'.
column14: Vulqon otilishi bilan havoni tutun va issiqlik to'ldirdi.

example: If something is broad, it is wide.
type: The river is very long and broad.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keng bo'lsa, u kengdir.
column14: Daryo juda uzun va keng.

example: A bush is a plant with many thin branches. It is smaller than a tree.
type: My dad and I planted some small bushes around the house.
example_tr: Buta - ko'p ingichka shoxlari bo'lgan o'simlik. U daraxtdan kichikroq.
column14: Dadam bilan men uy atrofiga mayda butalar ekdik.

example: If someone or something is capable of something, they can do it.
type: The Olympic athlete is capable of lifting a lot of weight.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa biror narsaga qodir bo'lsa, ular buni qila oladilar.
column14: Olimpiya sportchisi juda ko'p og'irliklarni ko'tarishga qodir.

example: To cheat is to be dishonest so that you can win or do well.
type: They cheated on the test by sharing answers.
example_tr: Aldash, g'alaba qozonish yoki yaxshi ish qilish uchun insofsiz bo'lishdir.
column14: Ular javoblarni almashish orqali testda aldashdi.

example: To concentrate on someone or something is to give your full attention.
type: I could not concentrate on my homework because the room was so loud.
example_tr: Biror kishiga yoki biror narsaga diqqatni jamlash - bu butun e'tiboringizni berishdir.
column14: Uy vazifamga diqqatimni jamlay olmadim, chunki xona juda baland edi.

example: To conclude is to arrive at a logical end by looking at evidence.
type: I saw crumbs on my dog’s face, so I concluded that he ate my cookie.
example_tr: Xulosa qilish - dalillarni ko'rib chiqish orqali mantiqiy natijaga erishish.
column14: Men itimning yuzida maydalanganlarni ko'rdim, shuning uchun u mening pecheneimni yeydi, degan xulosaga keldim.

example: Confident means that one believes they can do something without failing.
type: She was confident she could climb the mountain due to her training.
example_tr: Ishonchlilik insonning biror narsani muvaffaqiyatsiz bajara olishiga ishonishini anglatadi.
column14: U mashg‘ulotlari tufayli toqqa chiqishga ishonchi komil edi.

example: If something is considerable, it is large in size, amount or extent.
type: They paid a considerable amount of money for that car.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sezilarli bo'lsa, u hajmi, miqdori yoki hajmi bo'yicha katta.
column14: Ular bu mashina uchun katta miqdorda pul to'lashdi.

example: To convey is to communicate or make ideas known.
type: That picture of a crying child conveys a feeling of sadness.
