example_tr: Etkazish - bu muloqot qilish yoki fikrlarni ma'lum qilishdir.
column14: Yig'layotgan bolaning surati qayg'u tuyg'usini bildiradi.

example: If something is definite, it is certain or sure to be true.
type: There is a definite connection between hard work and success.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u aniq yoki haqiqatdir.
column14: Qattiq mehnat va muvaffaqiyat o'rtasida aniq bog'liqlik bor.

example: Delight is a feeling of being very happy with something.
type: He felt such delight after getting a promotion at work.
example_tr: Xursandchilik - biror narsadan juda xursand bo'lish hissi.
column14: Ishda ko'tarilganidan keyin u shunday zavqni his qildi.

example: A destination is the place where someone or something is going to.
type: The destination of this plane is Munich, Germany.
example_tr: Belgilangan joy - bu kimdir yoki biror narsa boradigan joy.
column14: Ushbu samolyotning manzili Germaniyaning Myunxen shahri.

example: To dictate something is to read it aloud so it can be written down.
type: He dictated his speech so his secretary could write it down.
example_tr: Biror narsani diktatsiya qilish, uni yozib olish uchun uni ovoz chiqarib o'qishdir.
column14: U nutqini kotibi yozib olishi uchun diktant qildi.

example: The edge of something is the part of it that is farthest from the center.
type: He ran to the edge of the cliff.
example_tr: Biror narsaning cheti uning markazdan eng uzoqda joylashgan qismidir.
column14: U qoya chetiga yugurdi.

example: A path is a way from one place to another that people can walk along.
type: We followed a path through the woods.
example_tr: Yo'l - bu bir joydan ikkinchi joyga odamlar boradigan yo'l.
column14: Biz o'rmon bo'ylab yo'l bo'ylab yurdik.

example: To resort to something is to depend on it in order to solve a problem.
type: I hope they don’t resort to violence to end the argument.
example_tr: Biror narsaga murojaat qilish - muammoni hal qilish uchun unga bog'liq bo'lish.
column14: Umid qilamanki, ular bahsni tugatish uchun zo'ravonlikka murojaat qilishmaydi.

example: A shadow is the dark area that is made when something blocks light.
type: The man’s shadow was taller than he was.
example_tr: Soya - bu biror narsa yorug'likni to'sib qo'yganda hosil bo'ladigan qorong'u joy.
column14: Odamning soyasi undan balandroq edi.

example: To succeed is to complete something that you planned or tried to do.
type: He will continue to work on the robot until he succeeds.
example_tr: Muvaffaqiyatga erishish - bu siz rejalashtirgan yoki qilishga harakat qilgan narsani bajarishdir.
column14: U muvaffaqiyatga erishmaguncha robot ustida ishlashda davom etadi.

example: To suspect something is to believe that it is true.
type: I suspect that those kids stole the money.
example_tr: Biror narsadan shubhalanish - bu haqiqat ekanligiga ishonish.
column14: Men o'sha bolalar pulni o'g'irlagan deb gumon qilaman.

example: A valley is a low area of land between two mountains or hills.
type: We looked at the valley below from the top of the mountain.
example_tr: Vodiy - ikki tog' yoki tepalik orasidagi pasttekislikdagi yer.
column14: Tog‘ tepasidan pastdagi vodiyga qaradik.

example: To admire someone is to like them for what they do.
type: I admire my brother for his hard work.
example_tr: Biror kishiga qoyil qolish, uni qilgan ishi uchun yoqtirishdir.
column14: Men akamni mehnatsevarligi uchun qadrlayman.

example: To aid someone is to help them when they need something.
type: The doctor aided the boy after his accident.
example_tr: Biror kishiga yordam berish, unga biror narsa kerak bo'lganda yordam berishdir.
column14: Voqea sodir bo'lganidan keyin shifokor bolaga yordam berdi.

example: To attempt something is to try to do that thing.
type: I am attempting to learn English.
example_tr: Biror narsaga urinish - bu ishni qilishga urinish.
column14: Men ingliz tilini o'rganishga harakat qilaman.

example: Authority is the power that someone has because of their position.
type: The policeman has authority on the streets.
example_tr: Vakolat - bu kimningdir o'z mavqei tufayli ega bo'lgan kuchdir.
column14: Politsiyachi ko'chada hokimiyatga ega.

example: A capital is an important city where a country’s leaders live and work.
type: We will visit the capital to learn about our government.
example_tr: Poytaxt - bu mamlakat rahbarlari yashaydigan va ishlaydigan muhim shahar.
column14: Hukumatimiz bilan tanishish uchun poytaxtga boramiz.

example: To cooperate is to work together to do something.
type: The students cooperated to clean up the classroom.
example_tr: Hamkorlik - biror narsa qilish uchun birgalikda harakat qilishdir.
column14: Talabalar sinfni tozalashda hamkorlik qilishdi.

example: To defend someone or something is to protect them from attack.
type: The soldiers defended the town from the invaders.
example_tr: Kimnidir yoki biror narsani himoya qilish, uni hujumdan himoya qilishdir.
column14: Askarlar shaharni bosqinchilardan himoya qildilar.

example: Destruction is damage to something so bad that it can’t be fixed.
type: After the big fire, there was much destruction in the city.
example_tr: Vayronagarchilik - bu shunchalik yomon narsaning shikastlanishi, uni tuzatib bo'lmaydi.
column14: Katta yong'indan keyin shaharda ko'plab vayronagarchiliklar yuz berdi.

example: Disorder is a lack of order or a complete mess.
type: The teacher’s desk had many papers in disorder.
example_tr: Tartibsizlik - tartibsizlik yoki to'liq tartibsizlik.
column14: O'qituvchining stolida ko'plab qog'ozlar tartibsiz edi.

example: A division is the act of making smaller groups out of a larger one.
type: The chart had six divisions which all had different colors.
example_tr: Bo'linish - bu kattaroq guruhlardan kichikroq guruhlarni yaratish harakati.
column14: Jadvalda oltita bo'lim bor edi, ularning barchasi turli xil ranglarga ega edi.

example: To enable a person is to make it possible for them to do something.
type: Having the key enabled us to open the door.
example_tr: Biror kishiga imkon berish, unga biror narsa qilish imkoniyatini berishdir.
column14: Kalitning mavjudligi bizga eshikni ochishga imkon berdi.

example: To frustrate is to prevent someone from fulfilling their desire.
type: The machine frustrated me because I could not fix it.
example_tr: Xafa bo'lish - kimningdir istagini amalga oshirishga to'sqinlik qilish.
column14: Mashina meni xafa qildi, chunki men uni tuzata olmadim.

example: To govern is to control the public business of a country, state, or city.
type: The United States is governed from the White House.
example_tr: Boshqarish - bu mamlakat, shtat yoki shaharning davlat biznesini nazorat qilish.
column14: Qo'shma Shtatlar Oq uydan boshqariladi.

example: To have plenty of something is to have more than you need.
type: The school had plenty of books for the students to read.
example_tr: Ko'p narsaga ega bo'lish - bu sizga kerak bo'lgandan ko'proq narsaga ega bo'lishdir.
column14: Maktabda o'quvchilar o'qishi uchun juda ko'p kitoblar bor edi.

example: To relieve someone is to make them feel less pain.
type: The medicine relieved the sick boy.
example_tr: Biror kishini engillashtirish, unga kamroq og'riqni his qilishdir.
column14: Dori bemor bolani yengil qildi.

example: Reputation is the opinion that people have about someone.
type: The doctor had a reputation for helping people.
example_tr: Obro' - bu odamlarning kimdir haqida bo'lgan fikri.
column14: Shifokor odamlarga yordam berish uchun obro'ga ega edi.

example: Royal describes something that belongs to a king or queen.
type: The king sat upon the royal throne.
example_tr: Royal qirol yoki malikaga tegishli narsalarni tasvirlaydi.
column14: Shoh shoh taxtiga o'tirdi.

example: A slave is a person who is not free and must work for someone else.
type: The slave worked very hard all day long.
example_tr: Qul - ozod bo'lmagan va boshqa birov uchun ishlashi kerak bo'lgan odam.
column14: Qul kun bo‘yi juda qattiq mehnat qildi.

example: To struggle is to fight against someone or something.
type: The kids struggled with each other for the toy.
example_tr: Kurash - kimgadir yoki biror narsaga qarshi kurashish.
column14: Bolalar o'yinchoq uchun bir-birlari bilan kurashdilar.

example: When someone is stupid, they lack intelligence.
type: He said something stupid that made everyone angry at him.
example_tr: Biror kishi ahmoq bo'lsa, unga aql yetishmaydi.
column14: U hammaning jahlini chiqargan ahmoqona gap aytdi.

example: A citizen is someone who lives in a certain town or city.
type: Carlos was born in Spain, He is a Spanish citizen.
example_tr: Fuqaro - bu ma'lum bir shahar yoki shaharda yashovchi shaxs.
column14: Karlos Ispaniyada tug'ilgan, u Ispaniya fuqarosi.

example: A council is a group of people who run a city or town.
type: The council met to discuss the new laws for the city.
example_tr: Kengash - bu shahar yoki shaharchani boshqaradigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Kengash shahar uchun yangi qonunlarni muhokama qilish uchun yig'ildi.

example: To declare is to say something officially.
type: I declared my love for him.
example_tr: E'lon qilish - biror narsani rasmiy ravishda aytish.
column14: Men unga muhabbatimni izhor qildim.

example: When people or things are enormous, they are very large.
type: My dog looks enormous next to yours.
example_tr: Odamlar yoki narsalar juda katta bo'lsa, ular juda katta.
column14: Sizning itingiz yonida mening itim juda katta ko'rinadi.

example: When someone or something are extraordinary, they are amazing.
type: The fireman who rescued the girl was extraordinary.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa g'ayrioddiy bo'lsa, ular hayratlanarli.
column14: Qizni qutqargan o't o'chiruvchi g'ayrioddiy edi.

example: Fog is a thick cloud that is near the ground or water.
type: I did not want to drive in the thick fog.
example_tr: Tuman - bu yer yoki suv yaqinida joylashgan qalin bulut.
column14: Men quyuq tumanda haydashni xohlamadim.

example: A funeral is a ceremony that takes place after a person dies.
type: They had a funeral for the soldier who died during the war.
example_tr: Dafn marosimi - bu odam vafot etganidan keyin o'tkaziladigan marosim.
column14: Urush paytida halok bo‘lgan askarni dafn qilishdi.

example: When people or things are giant, they are very big.
type: The giant truck got in my way.
example_tr: Odamlar yoki narsalar gigant bo'lsa, ular juda katta.
column14: Katta yuk mashinasi yo‘limga to‘g‘ri keldi.

example: An impression is the way of thinking about someone or something.
type: Most people’s first impression of Dr. Giani is that he is mean.
example_tr: Taassurot - bu kimdir yoki biror narsa haqida fikrlash usuli.
column14: Ko'pchilikning doktor Giani haqidagi birinchi taassurotlari uning yomonligidir.

example: Income is how much money a person or business makes.
type: Her company pays her a fairly good income.
example_tr: Daromad - bu odam yoki biznes qancha pul topsa.
column14: Uning kompaniyasi unga juda yaxshi daromad to'laydi.

example: When someone is mad, they are angry.
type: Mother got mad when I didn’t listen to her.
example_tr: Biror kishi jinni bo'lsa, u g'azablanadi.
column14: Men unga quloq solmaganimdan, onam jahli chiqdi.

example: If someone ought to do something, then it is the right thing to do.
type: I ought to take my library books back.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsa qilishi kerak bo'lsa, bu to'g'ri ishdir.
column14: Kutubxonadagi kitoblarimni qaytarib olishim kerak.

example: To resist something is to fight against it.
type: He resisted the treatment at the hospital.
example_tr: Biror narsaga qarshilik ko'rsatish - unga qarshi kurashish.
column14: U kasalxonada davolanishga qarshilik ko'rsatdi.

example: To reveal is to show something.
type: I will reveal where I hid the candy bar.
example_tr: Oshkora qilish - biror narsani ko'rsatish.
column14: Men konfetni qaerga yashirganimni oshkor qilaman.

example: To rid is to make a place free from something or someone.
type: We rid our home of mice by using traps.
example_tr: Qutilish - biror joyni biror narsadan yoki kimdandir ozod qilish.
column14: Tuzoqlar yordamida uyimizni sichqonlardan tozalaymiz.

example: Asword is a long sharp weapon.
type: They used to use swords in battles in ancient times.
example_tr: Asword - uzun o'tkir qurol.
column14: Qadimda janglarda qilichdan foydalanishgan.

example: A tale is a story.
type: She told her two friends about the wild tale of her day.
example_tr: Ertak - bu hikoya.
column14: U ikki do'stiga o'z davrining yovvoyi ertaklarini aytib berdi.

example: To trap people or animals is to capture them so they cannot get away.
type: We trapped butterflies in a net.
example_tr: Odamlarni yoki hayvonlarni tuzoqqa tushirish, qochib ketmasliklari uchun ularni qo'lga olishdir.
column14: Biz kapalaklarni to'rga tutdik.

example: A trial is the way a court discovers if a person is guilty or innocent.
type: He went on trial for robbing the bank.
example_tr: Sud muhokamasi - bu sud shaxsning aybdor yoki aybsizligini aniqlash usuli.
column14: U bankni talon-taroj qilgani uchun sudga tortildi.

example: When people are violent, they want to hurt someone.
type: The man was put into jail because he was violent.
example_tr: Odamlar zo'ravonlik qilsa, ular kimnidir xafa qilishni xohlashadi.
column14: Erkak zo'ravonlik qilgani uchun qamoqqa tashlangan.

example: Admission is the act of allowing to enter a place.
type: The admission ticket to the movie was $5.
example_tr: Qabul qilish - bu joyga kirishga ruxsat berish harakati.
column14: Filmga kirish chiptasi 5 dollar edi.

example: Astronomy is the study of the stars and planets.
type: Harotd loved watching the stars, so he decided to study astronomy.
example_tr: Astronomiya yulduzlar va sayyoralarni o'rganadigan fandir.
column14: Harotd yulduzlarni tomosha qilishni yaxshi ko'rardi, shuning uchun u astronomiyani o'rganishga qaror qildi.

example: To blame someone for something bad is to say they did it.
type: My mom blamed me for something I didn’t do.
example_tr: Birovni yomon narsada ayblash, u buni qilganini aytishdir.
column14: Onam men qilmagan narsam uchun meni aybladi.

example: Chemistry is the study of and reaction to substances.
type: In chemistry class, the professor taught us about chemical reactions.
example_tr: Kimyo - bu moddalarni o'rganish va ularga reaktsiya.
column14: Kimyo darsida professor bizga kimyoviy reaksiyalar haqida dars berdi.

example: If something happens despite what you do, it happens anyway.
type: We still played the game despite the cold weather.
example_tr: Agar nima qilsangiz ham, nimadir sodir bo'lsa, baribir sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Havo sovuq bo'lishiga qaramay, o'yin o'ynadik.

example: A dinosaur is a very big animal that lived millions of years ago.
type: I like to see the dinosaur bones at the museum.
example_tr: Dinozavr millionlab yillar oldin yashagan juda katta hayvondir.
column14: Men muzeyda dinozavr suyaklarini ko'rishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: An exhibit is a display of interesting things.
type: There was an animal exhibit at the fair.
example_tr: Ko'rgazma - bu qiziqarli narsalarning namoyishi.
column14: Yarmarkada hayvonlar ko'rgazmasi tashkil etildi.

example: Fame is reputation one has gained among the public.
type: He had fame and fortune, but he was not happy.
example_tr: Shon-shuhrat - bu xalq orasida erishilgan obro'.
column14: Unda shon-shuhrat va boylik bor edi, lekin u baxtli emas edi.

example: A forecast is an idea about what the weather will be like in the future.
type: The forecast says that it will rain all week.
example_tr: Prognoz - bu kelajakda ob-havo qanday bo'lishi haqida fikr.
column14: Prognozga ko'ra, butun hafta yomg'ir yog'adi.

example: A genius is a very smart person.
type: Since she was a genius, she easily passed all of her school exams.
example_tr: Daho juda aqlli odam.
column14: U daho bo'lganligi sababli, u maktabdagi barcha imtihonlarni osongina topshirdi.

example: Someone who is gentle is kind and calm.
type: He is very gentle with the baby.
example_tr: Yumshoq odam mehribon va xotirjam bo'ladi.
column14: U chaqaloq bilan juda yumshoq.

example: Geography is the study of where things are.
type: I had to draw a map for geography class.
example_tr: Geografiya narsalarning qaerdaligini o'rganadi.
column14: Geografiya darsi uchun xarita chizishim kerak edi.

example: To interfere is to cause problems and keep something from happening.
type: My little sister always interferes when I’m trying to study.
example_tr: Xalaqit qilish - muammo tug'dirish va biror narsa sodir bo'lishiga yo'l qo'ymaslik.
column14: Men o'qishga harakat qilsam, singlim doim xalaqit beradi.

example: To do something lightly is to not push very hard.
type: Draw lightly so you do not tear your paper.
example_tr: Biror narsani engil qilish - juda qattiq bosmaslikdir.
column14: Qog'ozingizni yirtmaslik uchun engil chizing.

example: A principal is a person in charge of a school.
type: My school’s principal can be very strict with the rules.
example_tr: Direktor - bu maktab uchun mas'ul shaxs.
column14: Mening maktabimning direktori qoidalarga juda qattiq munosabatda bo'lishi mumkin.

example: A row is a line of things.
type: James put all of his toy soldiers into neat rows.
example_tr: Qator - bu narsalar qatori.
column14: Jeyms barcha o'yinchoq askarlarini toza qatorlarga qo'ydi.

example: A shelf is a place on a wall where you put things.
type: I keep my clothes on a shelf in my closet.
example_tr: Raf - bu narsalarni qo'yadigan devordagi joy.
column14: Kiyimlarimni shkafimdagi javonda saqlayman.

example: If you do something out of spite, you want to be mean.
type: He snuck into his sister’s room and stole her bag out of spite.
example_tr: Agar siz g'azablanib biror narsa qilsangiz, siz yomon bo'lishni xohlaysiz.
column14: U singlisining xonasiga yashirincha kirib, uning sumkasini o'g'irlab ketdi.

example: Super means really good.
type: My dad said I did a super job cleaning the house.
example_tr: Super, albatta, yaxshi degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Dadamning aytishicha, men uyni tozalashni juda yaxshi bajarganman.

example: If something is wet, it has water on it.
type: Since my dog was wet, he tried to shake all the water off his body.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa nam bo'lsa, unda suv bor.
column14: Mening itim ho'l bo'lganligi sababli, u butun suvni tanasidan silkitmoqchi bo'ldi.

example: To abuse someone or something means to hurt them on purpose.
type: The mean man abused his dog when it barked too loudly.
example_tr: Birovni yoki biror narsani haqorat qilish, uni ataylab xafa qilish demakdir.
column14: Qashshoq odam itini qattiq hurlaganida uni haqorat qildi.

example: To afford something means you have enough money to pay for it.
type: I’ve been saving my money, so I can afford to buy a new bike.
example_tr: Biror narsani sotib olish, uni to'lash uchun etarli pulingiz borligini anglatadi.
column14: Men pulimni tejaganman, shuning uchun yangi velosiped sotib olishim mumkin.

example: To bake means to cook food with heat.
type: My sister is a good cook. She bakes delicious cakes.
example_tr: Pishirish ovqatni issiqlik bilan pishirishni anglatadi.
column14: Mening singlim yaxshi oshpaz. U mazali tortlar pishiradi.

example: A bean is a plant seed that is good to eat.
type: There are many different kinds of beans to eat.
example_tr: Fasol - yeyish uchun yaxshi bo'lgan o'simlik urug'idir.
column14: Ovqatlanish uchun juda ko'p turli xil loviya mavjud.

example: A candle is a stick of wax that is lit on fire for light or heat.
type: When the lights went out, we lit some candles.
example_tr: Sham - yorug'lik yoki issiqlik uchun olovda yoqilgan mum tayoqchasi.
column14: Chiroqlar o'chganida, biz sham yoqdik.

example: To convert something means to change it into something else.
type: The man converted his messy field into a garden of flowers.
example_tr: Biror narsani aylantirish, uni boshqa narsaga aylantirish demakdir.
column14: Erkak o'zining tartibsiz dalasini gullar bog'iga aylantirdi.

example: A debt is an amount of money that a person owes.
type: I have not paid my gas bill. I owe a debt to the gas company.
example_tr: Qarz - bu odamning qarzi bo'lgan pul miqdori.
column14: Men gaz to'lovini to'lamadim. Gaz kompaniyasidan qarzim bor.

example: To decrease something is to make it less than it was before.
type: Hiring more police officers has decreased crime in the city.
example_tr: Biror narsani kamaytirish, uni avvalgisidan kamroq qilishdir.
column14: Ko'proq politsiya xodimlarini yollash shaharda jinoyatchilikni kamaytirdi.

example: A fault is a mistake.
type: It is my fault that the cat ran away. I left the door open.
example_tr: Xato - bu xato.
column14: Mushuk qochib ketganiga men aybdorman. Men eshikni ochiq qoldirdim.

example: A fund is an amount of money that people have.
type: We all put money into our club’s fund.
example_tr: Jamg'arma - bu odamlarda mavjud bo'lgan pul miqdori.
column14: Hammamiz klubimiz fondiga pul kiritamiz.

example: When someone is generous, they like to give things to people.
type: The generous man donated several new computers to our school.
example_tr: Agar kimdir saxiy bo'lsa, u odamlarga narsalarni berishni yaxshi ko'radi.
column14: Saxovatpesha inson maktabimizga bir nechta yangi kompyuter sovg‘a qildi.

example: An ingredient is something that is part of a food dish.
type: The main ingredients in cake are eggs, sugar and flour.
example_tr: Ingredient - bu taomning bir qismi bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Kekning asosiy tarkibiy qismlari tuxum, shakar va undir.

example: To insist means to be firm in telling people what to do.
type: I insist that you try some of these cookies.
example_tr: Qat'iylik qilish, odamlarga nima qilish kerakligini aytishda qat'iy bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Men ushbu cookie-fayllardan ba'zilarini sinab ko'rishingizni talab qilaman.

example: A mess is a condition that is not clean or neat.
type: Heather’s room was a complete mess.
example_tr: Tartibsizlik - bu toza yoki toza bo'lmagan holat.
column14: Xezerning xonasi butunlay tartibsiz edi.

example: Metal is a strong material people use to build things.
type: Steel is a common metal that is used to build buildings.
example_tr: Metall - bu odamlar narsalarni qurish uchun foydalanadigan kuchli material.
column14: Chelik - binolarni qurish uchun ishlatiladigan keng tarqalgan metall.

example: To monitor people or things is to watch them closely.
type: The teacher monitors the students when they take tests.
example_tr: Odamlarni yoki narsalarni kuzatish ularni diqqat bilan kuzatishdir.
column14: O'qituvchi o'quvchilarni test topshirayotganda kuzatib boradi.

example: To oppose something means to dislike it or act against it.
type: I want to be a police officer because I oppose crime.
example_tr: Biror narsaga qarshi chiqish, uni yoqtirmaslik yoki unga qarshi harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Men politsiyachi bo'lishni xohlayman, chunki men jinoyatga qarshiman.

example: If a person is passive, they do not take action to solve problems.
type: Marcie is so passive that she never solves her own problems.
example_tr: Agar odam passiv bo'lsa, u muammolarni hal qilish uchun harakat qilmaydi.
column14: Marsi shunchalik passivki, u hech qachon o'z muammolarini hal qilmaydi.

example: A quantity is a certain amount of something.
type: I have a small quantity of milk in my glass.
example_tr: Miqdor - biror narsaning ma'lum miqdori.
column14: Stakanda oz miqdorda sut bor.

example: To sue someone is to take them to court for something wrong they did.
type: I sued the company after I slipped on a banana peel in their hallway.
example_tr: Biror kishini sudga berish, uni noto'g'ri qilgan ish uchun sudga berishdir.
column14: Koridorda banan po‘stlog‘ini kiyib olganimdan keyin men kompaniyani sudga berdim.

example: When someone has anxiety, they have a lot of worries and fear.
type: When I have to climb to high places, I’m filled with anxiety.
example_tr: Biror kishi tashvishlansa, u juda ko'p tashvish va qo'rquvga ega.
column14: Men baland joylarga ko'tarilishim kerak bo'lsa, men tashvishga to'laman.

example: An army is a large group of people who fight in wars.
type: The army protects all the people in the country.
example_tr: Armiya - bu urushlarda qatnashadigan odamlarning katta guruhi.
column14: Armiya mamlakatdagi barcha odamlarni himoya qiladi.

example: A billion is a very large number; 1,000,000,000.
type: There are billions of stars in outer space.
example_tr: Bir milliard juda katta raqam; 1 000 000 000.
column14: Kosmosda milliardlab yulduzlar mavjud.

example: To carve means to cut into something.
type: My father usually carves the turkey for Thanksgiving.
example_tr: O‘yib yasamoq, bir narsani kesib olmoq degan ma’noni anglatadi.
column14: Otam odatda kurkani Shukrona kuni uchun o‘yib yasaydi.

example: To consult someone means to ask them for help.
type: I will consult my accountant to find a way to pay for my bills.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan maslahatlashish, undan yordam so'rash demakdir.
column14: To‘lovlarimni to‘lash yo‘lini topish uchun buxgalterim bilan maslahatlashaman.

example: An emergency is a time when someone needs help right away.
type: There is a huge fire in my house! This is an emergency!
example_tr: Favqulodda vaziyat - bu kimdir darhol yordamga muhtoj bo'lgan vaqt.
column14: Mening uyimda katta olov bor! Bu favqulodda holat!

example: When someone has good fortune, it means they have luck.
type: I have good fortune when I play cards.
example_tr: Agar kimdir omadga ega bo'lsa, bu uning omadli ekanligini anglatadi.
column14: Men karta o'ynaganimda omadim bor.

example: To guarantee means to know something will happen.
type: I guarantee that the sun will come up in the morning.
example_tr: Kafolat qilish, biror narsa sodir bo'lishini bilishni anglatadi.
column14: Ertalab quyosh chiqishiga kafolat beraman.

example: To hike means to walk in the mountains or forest.
type: I always bring plenty of equipment with me when I hike.
example_tr: Piyoda yurish tog'larda yoki o'rmonda yurishni anglatadi.
column14: Men har doim o'zim bilan ko'p jihozlarni olib yuraman.

example: When something is initial, it is the first thing.
type: The initial step when writing a paper is to find a good topic.
example_tr: Biror narsa boshlang'ich bo'lsa, bu birinchi narsa.
column14: Maqolani yozishning dastlabki bosqichi yaxshi mavzuni topishdir.

example: If something is intense, it is very strong.
type: The skunk made an intense odor that filled the air.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kuchli bo'lsa, u juda kuchli.
column14: Skunk havoni to'ldirgan kuchli hid chiqardi.

example: To lend something is to give it to someone for a short time.
type: My sister lost her pen, so I will lend her mine.
example_tr: Biror narsani qarzga berish - uni birovga qisqa muddatga berish.
column14: Singlim qalamini yo‘qotib qo‘ydi, men unga o‘zimnikini qarzga beraman.

example: The peak is the very top of a mountain.
type: There is snow on the peaks of those mountains.
example_tr: Cho'qqi - tog'ning eng tepasi.
column14: O‘sha tog‘larning cho‘qqilarida qor bor.

example: Potential means capable of being but not yet in existence.
type: I’ve thought of some potential problems with your idea.
example_tr: Potentsial mavjud bo'lishga qodir, lekin hali mavjud emas degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Men sizning fikringiz bilan bog'liq ba'zi muammolar haqida o'yladim.

example: When you have pride, you are happy with yourself.
type: I take pride in getting good grades.
example_tr: Agar sizda mag'rurlik bo'lsa, siz o'zingizdan xursand bo'lasiz.
column14: Men yaxshi baho olganimdan faxrlanaman.

example: Proof is a fact that shows something is real.
type: They used his fingerprint as proof for the crime he committed.
example_tr: Isbot - biror narsaning haqiqat ekanligini ko'rsatadigan haqiqat.
column14: Ular uning sodir etgan jinoyatiga dalil sifatida uning barmoq izini ishlatgan.

example: To quit something means to stop doing it.
type: I quit running because I got tired.
example_tr: Biror narsadan voz kechish, uni qilishni to'xtatishni anglatadi.
column14: Men charchaganim uchun yugurishni tashladim.

example: To spin is to turn around in circles.
type: The boy kept spinning until he fell down.
example_tr: Aylanmoq - aylana bo'ylab aylanish.
column14: Bola yiqilguncha aylanardi.

example: When people or things are tiny, they are very small.
type: A baby’s hand is tiny.
example_tr: Odamlar yoki narsalar kichik bo'lsa, ular juda kichikdir.
column14: Bolaning qo'li juda kichik.

example: A tutor is someone who gives lessons in a certain subject.
type: My sister is bad at math. So my mother hired a tutor to help her.
example_tr: Repetitor - bu ma'lum bir mavzu bo'yicha dars beradigan kishi.
column14: Mening singlim matematikadan yomon. Shuning uchun onam unga yordam berish uchun repetitor yolladi.

example: If something is apparent, it is easy to see.
type: Her happiness was apparent from the smile on her face.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, uni ko'rish oson.
column14: Uning baxti yuzidagi tabassumdan bilinib turardi.

example: When people are blind, they cannot see.
type: The blind man didn’t see the hole and almost fell in.
example_tr: Odamlar ko'r bo'lsa, ular ko'ra olmaydilar.
column14: Ko'r odam teshikni ko'rmadi va deyarli tushib ketdi.

example: To calculate is to find an answer using math.
type: I calculated how much money I would need to buy the car.
example_tr: Hisoblash matematika yordamida javob topishdir.
column14: Men mashina sotib olishim uchun qancha pul kerakligini hisoblab chiqdim.

example: To chat is to talk with someone.
type: Even though they were far apart, the couple chatted every day.
example_tr: Suhbat - bu kimdir bilan gaplashish.
column14: Ular bir-biridan uzoq bo'lsa ham, er-xotin har kuni suhbatlashishdi.

example: To commit to something is to promise to do it.
type: Seth wanted to go home, but he had committed to finishing the job.
example_tr: Biror narsaga va'da berish - uni bajarishga va'da berish.
column14: Set uyga qaytmoqchi edi, lekin u ishni tugatishga va'da bergan edi.

example: To compose something is to make it from smaller parts.
type: Tonya composed her report using many sources of information.
example_tr: Biror narsani yaratish - uni kichikroq qismlardan yasash.
column14: Tonya o'z hisobotini ko'plab ma'lumot manbalaridan foydalangan holda tuzdi.

example: A dormitory is a school building where students live.
type: I will move into the dormitory at the beginning of the school year.
example_tr: Yotoqxona - bu talabalar yashaydigan maktab binosi.
column14: O‘quv yili boshida yotoqxonaga ko‘chib o‘taman.

example: To exhaust someone is to make them tired.
type: John exhausted himself by swimming all day.
example_tr: Birovni charchatish, uni charchatishdir.
column14: Jon kun bo'yi suzish bilan charchagan.

example: A greenhouse is a small glass building that is used to grow plants.
type: We have a small greenhouse in our backyard where we grow plants.
example_tr: Issiqxona - bu o'simliklar etishtirish uchun ishlatiladigan kichik shisha bino.
column14: Hovlimizda kichik issiqxonamiz bor, u yerda o‘simliklar yetishtiramiz.

example: To ignore something is to act like you do not see or hear it.
type: I ignored the message he was making and kept studying.
example_tr: Biror narsani e'tiborsiz qoldirish - uni ko'rmagan yoki eshitmagandek tutishdir.
column14: Men uning xabariga e'tibor bermay, o'qishni davom ettirdim.

example: If something is obvious, it is clear and easily seen.
type: It was obvious that he was tired. He kept falling asleep.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u aniq va oson ko'rinadi.
column14: Uning charchagani aniq edi. U uxlab qolishda davom etdi.

example: Physics is a science that deals with energy and how it affects things.
type: In physics class, we used Newton’s Cradle to learn about energy.
example_tr: Fizika - bu energiya va u narsalarga qanday ta'sir qilish bilan shug'ullanadigan fan.
column14: Fizika darsida biz energiya haqida bilish uchun Nyuton beshigidan foydalandik.

example: A portion of something is a part of it.
type: I only ate a small portion of the pizza.
example_tr: Biror narsaning bir qismi uning bir qismidir.
column14: Men pitsaning ozgina qismini yedim.

example: To remind someone is to tell them to remember to do something.
type: Nick’s dad reminded him to do his homework.
example_tr: Biror kishini eslatish, unga biror narsa qilishni unutmang.
column14: Nikning otasi unga uy vazifasini bajarishni eslatdi.

example: A secretary is a person who works in an office.
type: Rebecca asked her secretary to type a report.
example_tr: Kotib - bu ofisda ishlaydigan odam.
column14: Rebekka kotibidan hisobot yozishni so'radi.

example: If something is severe, it is very bad or serious.
type: After hitting his hand with the hammer, Sam was in severe pain.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jiddiy bo'lsa, bu juda yomon yoki jiddiy.
column14: Qo'lini bolg'a bilan urgandan keyin Sem qattiq og'riydi.

example: If someone has a talent, they are naturally able to do it well.
type: Maria has a talent for playing the piano.
example_tr: Agar kimdir iste'dodga ega bo'lsa, u buni tabiiy ravishda yaxshi qila oladi.
column14: Mariyada pianino chalish qobiliyati bor.

example: A thesis is an idea that needs to be proved.
type: She did not support her thesis very well.
example_tr: Tezis - bu isbotlanishi kerak bo'lgan g'oya.
column14: U o'z dissertatsiyasini unchalik qo'llab-quvvatlamadi.

example: A uniform is a piece of clothing worn by people of the same group.
type: All the members of our marching band wear matching uniforms.
example_tr: Forma - bu bir guruh odamlari kiyadigan kiyim.
column14: Bizning orkestrimizning barcha a'zolari bir-biriga mos libos kiyishadi.

example: Vision is the act of seeing.
type: The eye doctor tested my vision.
example_tr: Ko'rish - bu ko'rish harakati.
column14: Ko'z shifokori mening ko'rishimni sinab ko'rdi.

example: To absorb a liquid means to take it inside.
type: He used a sponge to absorb the water on the floor.
example_tr: Suyuqlikni singdirish uni ichkariga olish demakdir.
column14: U shimgich yordamida poldagi suvni shimib oldi.

example: A HOES is a person in charge of other people at work.
type: My boss is a nice person.
example_tr: HOES - bu ishdagi boshqa odamlar uchun javobgar shaxs.
column14: Mening xo'jayinim yaxshi odam.

example: A committee is a group of people who meet together to make decisions.
type: The school’s committee agreed on a new dress code for students.
example_tr: Qo'mita - bu qaror qabul qilish uchun yig'iladigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Maktab qo'mitasi o'quvchilar uchun yangi kiyinish qoidalarini kelishib oldi.

example: A contract is a written agreement between two people.
type: The woman signed a contract when she bought the house.
example_tr: Shartnoma - bu ikki kishi o'rtasidagi yozma kelishuv.
column14: Ayol uyni sotib olayotganda shartnoma imzolagan.

example: A crew is a group of workers.
type: My father has a crew. They help him build houses.
example_tr: Brigada - bu ishchilar guruhi.
column14: Dadamning ekipaji bor. Ular unga uy qurishda yordam berishadi.

example: To devote time to something means to spend a lot of time doing it.
type: She devotes two hours a day to playing the piano.
example_tr: Biror narsaga vaqt ajratish, uni bajarish uchun ko'p vaqt sarflashni anglatadi.
column14: U kuniga ikki soatni pianino chalishga bag'ishlaydi.

example: To dig is to make a hole in the ground.
type: My dog digs in the yard so he can hide his bones.
example_tr: Qazish - yerga teshik ochish.
column14: Itim suyaklarini yashirish uchun hovlida qazishadi.

example: To dine means to eat dinner.
type: The young couple dined at their home.
example_tr: Ovqatlanish kechki ovqatni iste'mol qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Yosh er-xotin o'z uylarida tushlik qilishdi.

example: To donate is to give something to a charity or organization.
type: We donate money to Christmas charities every year.
example_tr: Xayriya qilish - xayriya yoki tashkilotga biror narsa berish.
column14: Biz har yili Rojdestvo xayriya tashkilotlariga pul ajratamiz.

example: If something is double, it is twice as much, or twice as many.
type: I paid almost double the amount for that shirt.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ikki barobar bo'lsa, u ikki barobar ko'p yoki ikki barobar ko'p bo'ladi.
column14: Men bu ko‘ylak uchun deyarli ikki baravar pul to‘laganman.

example: To elevate something is to put it at a higher level.
type: The man elevated the picture so he could see it better.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'tarish - uni yuqori darajaga qo'yishdir.
column14: Erkak rasmni yaxshiroq ko'rish uchun ko'tardi.

example: A flavor is the taste of food or drinks.
type: The flavor of the ice cream was very good.
example_tr: Lazzat - bu taom yoki ichimliklarning ta'mi.
column14: Muzqaymoqning ta'mi juda yaxshi edi.

example: A foundation is a group that provides money for research.
type: The foundation raised money to give scholarships to students.
example_tr: Jamg'arma - bu tadqiqot uchun pul beradigan guruh.
column14: Jamg'arma talabalarga stipendiya berish uchun pul yig'di.

example: A generation is a group of people who live at the same time.
type: My grandparents are from a different generation than me.
example_tr: Avlod - bu bir vaqtning o'zida yashaydigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Mening bobom va buvim mendan boshqa avlod vakillari.

example: A handle is the part of an object people hold while using it.
type: The pot is very hot. So pick it up by the handle.
example_tr: Tutqich - bu foydalanish paytida odamlar ushlab turadigan ob'ektning bir qismi.
column14: Idish juda issiq. Shunday qilib, uni dastagidan oling.

example: A layer covers over something or is between two things.
type: There was a layer of snow on the tops of the houses this morning.
example_tr: Qatlam biror narsani qoplaydi yoki ikki narsa orasida joylashgan.
column14: Bugun ertalab uylarning tepasida qor qatlami bor edi.

example: Mud is soft, wet dirt.
type: My brother played rugby in the mud. Now he’s dirty.
example_tr: Loy yumshoq, nam axloqsizlikdir.
column14: Akam loyda regbi o'ynadi. Endi u iflos.

example: If something is smooth, it has no bumps.
type: The baby's skin felt very smooth.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa silliq bo'lsa, unda hech qanday zarba yo'q.
column14: Bolaning terisi juda silliq edi.

example: Soil is the top layer of land on the Earth.
type: The boy planted flowers in the soil and watered them every day.
example_tr: Tuproq - Yerdagi quruqlikning yuqori qatlami.
column14: Bola tuproqqa gul ekib, har kuni sug‘orardi.

example: If people or things are unique, they are not like the others.
type: Her dog is unique. I’ve never seen one quite like it.
example_tr: Agar odamlar yoki narsalar noyob bo'lsa, ular boshqalarga o'xshamaydi.
column14: Uning iti o'ziga xosdir. Men hech qachon bunday odamni ko'rmaganman.

example: A chamber is an old word for a bedroom.
type: The girl was tired. She went to her chamber for a nap.
example_tr: Palata - yotoqxona uchun eski so'z.
column14: Qiz charchagan edi. U uxlash uchun xonasiga bordi.

example: To deny something is to say it is not true.
type: The boy denied that he broke the window.
example_tr: Biror narsani inkor etish - bu haqiqat emasligini aytish.
column14: Bola derazani sindirganini rad etdi.

example: A document is an official piece of writing.
type: He was given an official document proving he was a citizen.
example_tr: Hujjat rasmiy yozuvdir.
column14: Unga fuqaroligini tasdiqlovchi rasmiy hujjat berildi.

example: To emphasize is to give importance or attention to something.
type: She emphasized the key points by circling them in red ink.
example_tr: Ta'kidlash - biror narsaga ahamiyat berish yoki e'tibor berish.
column14: U asosiy fikrlarni qizil siyoh bilan aylantirib ta'kidladi.

example: A fever is a high body temperature that people get when they are sick
type: Lydia had a high fever so she didn’t go to school.
example_tr: Isitma - bu odamlar kasal bo'lganda paydo bo'ladigan yuqori tana harorati
column14: Lidiyaning isitmasi baland edi, shuning uchun u maktabga bormadi.

example: The flu is a type of sickness that makes you feel weak or your body hurt.
type: Since he had the flu, he felt miserable.
example_tr: Gripp - bu o'zingizni zaif his qiladigan yoki tanangiz og'riydigan kasallikning bir turi.
column14: Grippga chalingani uchun u o'zini baxtsiz his qildi.

example: To freeze is to become very cold.
type: If you don’t wear your coat in winter, you will freeze.
example_tr: Muzlash - juda sovuq bo'lish.
column14: Agar siz qishda palto kiymasangiz, muzlab qolasiz.

example: A gesture is a movement of the hands or body.
type: My teacher makes a lot of gestures when she speaks.
example_tr: Imo-ishora - bu qo'llar yoki tananing harakati.
column14: O‘qituvchim gapirganda ko‘p imo-ishoralar qiladi.

example: To interrupt is to briefly stop someone when they are doing something.
type: My mother interrupted me when I was trying to listen to music.
example_tr: To'xtatib turish - kimdir biror narsa qilayotganda uni qisqa vaqt ichida to'xtatib qo'yishdir.
column14: Musiqa tinglamoqchi bo‘lganimda onam gapimni to‘xtatdi.

example: To last is to continue or go on for an amount of time.
type: The football match lasted for nearly two hours.
example_tr: Davom etish - bu ma'lum vaqt davom etish yoki davom ettirishdir.
column14: Futbol bahsi qariyb ikki soat davom etdi.

example: Likeness means the state of being like, or resemblance.
type: Michelle bears a strong likeness to her older sister Kate.
example_tr: O'xshashlik o'xshashlik yoki o'xshashlik holatini anglatadi.
column14: Mishel katta singlisi Keytga juda o'xshaydi.

example: Moreover means besides or in addition to something.
type: It’s cold outside, Moreover, the wind is very strong.
example_tr: Bundan tashqari, biror narsadan tashqari yoki qo'shimcha ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Tashqarida sovuq, Bundan tashqari, shamol juda kuchli.

example: A perspective is the way you think about something.
type: The man’s speech gave me a new perspective on our country.
example_tr: Perspektiv - bu sizning biror narsa haqida o'ylash usuli.
column14: Bu odamning nutqi menga mamlakatimizga yangicha qarashni berdi.

example: When something is rational, it is normal or practical.
type: It is hard to think in a rational way when you are scared.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oqilona bo'lsa, u normal yoki amaliydir.
column14: Qo'rqqaningizda oqilona fikr yuritish qiyin.

example: To recover is to go back to normal after something bad happens.
type: I hope the city will recover soon after the flood.
example_tr: Qayta tiklash - yomon narsa sodir bo'lgandan keyin normal holatga qaytish.
column14: Umid qilamanki, shahar toshqindan keyin tez orada tiklanadi.

example: To rely on something or someone is to trust or depend on them.
type: The boy relied on his older brother to help him.
example_tr: Biror narsaga yoki kimgadir tayanish - ularga ishonish yoki unga bog'liqlik.
column14: Bola unga yordam berish uchun katta akasiga ishondi.

example: To shock people is to surprise them.
type: The man was shocked by the news.
example_tr: Odamlarni hayratda qoldirish, ularni hayratda qoldirishdir.
column14: Erkak bu xabardan hayratda qoldi.

example: When people are shy, they are nervous around people strange to them.
type: The girl was too shy to try out for the play.
example_tr: Odamlar uyatchan bo'lsa, ular o'zlariga begona odamlar atrofida asabiylashadilar.
column14: Qiz spektaklni sinab ko'rish uchun juda uyatchan edi.

example: To stare at something is to look at it for a long time.
type: The young couple stared into each other's eyes.
example_tr: Biror narsaga tikilish - unga uzoq vaqt qarash.
column14: Yosh er-xotin bir-birlarining ko‘zlariga tikilishdi.

example: Thus means as a result or for that reason.
type: The sun was shining. Thus, I wore my sunglasses.
example_tr: Shunday qilib, natijada yoki shu sababdan anglatadi.
column14: Quyosh porlab turardi. Shunday qilib, men quyoshdan saqlaydigan ko'zoynak taqdim.

example: An aim is a goal someone wants to make happen.
type: My aim is to become a helicopter pilot.
example_tr: Maqsad - bu kimdir amalga oshirishni istagan maqsad.
column14: Mening maqsadim vertolyot uchuvchisi bo'lish.

example: To attach is to put two things together.
type: I attached the socks to the clothesline to dry.
example_tr: Biriktirmoq ikki narsani birlashtirmoqdir.
column14: Men paypoqlarni quritish uchun kiyim ipiga bog'lab qo'ydim.

example: To bet is to risk money on the result of a game or a business.
type: How much will you bet that your horse will win?
example_tr: Tikish - bu o'yin yoki biznes natijasi uchun pulni xavf ostiga qo'yishdir.
column14: Sizning otingiz g'alaba qozonishiga qancha pul tikasiz?

example: A carriage is a vehicle pulled by a horse.
type: We took a carriage ride in the park.
example_tr: Arava - ot tortadigan transport vositasi.
column14: Biz parkda aravada sayr qildik.

example: If something is classic, it is typical.
type: The athlete made a classic mistake - he started running too soon.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa klassik bo'lsa, u odatiy.
column14: Sportchi klassik xatoga yo'l qo'ydi - u juda tez yugurishni boshladi.

example: To commute is to travel a long distance to get to work.
type: I usually commute to work on the train.
example_tr: Ishga borish - ishga borish uchun uzoq masofani bosib o'tish.
column14: Men odatda ishga poyezdda boraman.

example: To confirm is to make sure something is correct.
type: Winning the game confirmed that James was a good player.
example_tr: Tasdiqlash - biror narsa to'g'ri ekanligiga ishonch hosil qilish.
column14: O'yindagi g'alaba Jeymsning yaxshi futbolchi ekanligini tasdiqladi.

example: To criticize is to say you do not like someone or something.
type: He criticized his wife for spending too much money.
example_tr: Tanqid qilish - kimnidir yoki biror narsani yoqtirmasligingizni aytishdir.
column14: U xotinini juda ko'p pul sarflagani uchun tanqid qildi.

example: To differ is to not be the same as another person or thing.
type: I differ from my brother: he is short, while I am tall.
example_tr: Farqlanish boshqa shaxs yoki narsa bilan bir xil bo'lmaslikdir.
column14: Men akamdan farq qilaman: u past, men esa balandman.

example: An expense is the money that people spend on something.
type: She wrote down all the expenses for her trip.
example_tr: Xarajat - bu odamlarning biror narsaga sarflagan pullari.
column14: U sayohati uchun barcha xarajatlarni yozib oldi.

example: If something is formal, it is done in an official way.
type: It was a formal dinner, so we wore our best clothes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa rasmiy bo'lsa, u rasmiy tarzda amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Bu rasmiy kechki ovqat edi, shuning uchun biz eng yaxshi kiyimlarimizni kiyib oldik.

example: Height is how tall someone or something is.
type: My height is 168 centimeters.
example_tr: Balandlik - bu kimningdir yoki biror narsaning balandligi.
column14: Mening bo'yim 168 santimetr.

example: To invent something is to create something that never existed before.
type: My grandfather has invented some interesting things.
example_tr: Biror narsani ixtiro qilish - ilgari mavjud bo'lmagan narsani yaratish.
column14: Mening bobom qiziqarli narsalarni ixtiro qilgan.

example: If someone is junior in their job, they do not have a lot of power.
type: When she started at the company, she was only a junior manager.
example_tr: Agar kimdir o'z ishida kichik bo'lsa, unda unchalik katta kuch yo'q.
column14: U kompaniyada ish boshlaganida, u faqat kichik menejer edi.

example: Labor is the act of doing or making something.
type: Building the house took a lot of labor.
example_tr: Mehnat - bu biror narsa qilish yoki qilish harakati.
column14: Uyni qurish juda ko'p mehnat talab qildi.

example: A mechanic is someone who fixes vehicles or machines.
type: We took the car to the mechanic to be fixed.
example_tr: Mexanik - bu transport vositalari yoki mashinalarni tuzatuvchi kishi.
column14: Biz mashinani tuzatish uchun ustaga olib bordik.

example: If something is prime, it is the most important one.
type: Dirty air is a prime cause of illness.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa asosiy bo'lsa, u eng muhimi.
column14: Nopok havo kasallikning asosiy sababidir.

example: To shift to something is to move into a new place or direction.
type: He shifted to the other side of the table to eat his breakfast.
example_tr: Biror narsaga o'tish - yangi joyga yoki yo'nalishga o'tish.
column14: U nonushta qilish uchun stolning narigi tomoniga o'tdi.

example: A signal is a sound or action that tells someone to do something.
type: The coach blew his whistle as a signal to begin the game.
example_tr: Signal - bu kimgadir biror narsa qilishni buyuradigan tovush yoki harakat.
column14: Murabbiy o'yinni boshlashga ishora sifatida hushtagi chaldi.

example: When people are sincere, they tell the truth.
type: He sounded sincere when he apologized to me.
example_tr: Odamlar samimiy bo'lsa, ular haqiqatni aytadilar.
column14: U mendan kechirim so‘raganda samimiy gapirdi.

example: Ability is the quality of a person being able to do something well.
type: His swimming abilities let him cross the entire lake.
example_tr: Qobiliyat - bu odamning biror narsani yaxshi qila olish sifati.
column14: Uning suzish qobiliyati unga butun ko'lni kesib o'tishga imkon beradi.

example: Agriculture is the growing of food and animals.
type: The farmer studied agriculture in college.
example_tr: Qishloq xoʻjaligi oziq-ovqat va hayvonlar yetishtirishdir.
column14: Fermer kollejda qishloq xo‘jaligi yo‘nalishida tahsil olgan.

example: A cartoon is a funny drawing.
type: Sometimes, people draw cartoons for the newspaper.
example_tr: Multfilm - bu kulgili rasm.
column14: Ba'zida odamlar gazeta uchun multfilmlar chizishadi.

example: The ceiling is the top of a room.
type: He painted the ceiling with a special roller.
example_tr: Shift xonaning yuqori qismidir.
column14: Shiftni maxsus rolik bilan bo'yadi.

example: To convince someone means to make them sure of something.
type: She convinced me to buy the house.
example_tr: Biror kishini ishontirish, uni biror narsaga ishonch hosil qilishni anglatadi.
column14: U meni uyni sotib olishga ishontirdi.

example: When you are curious about something, you want to know more about it.
type: I opened up the clock because I was curious about how it worked.
example_tr: Agar biror narsaga qiziqsangiz, u haqida ko'proq bilishni xohlaysiz.
column14: Men soatni ochdim, chunki u qanday ishlashiga qiziqdim.

example: To delay means to wait to do something.
type: I was delayed at the airport for over two hours.
example_tr: Kechiktirish, biror narsa qilishni kutishni anglatadi.
column14: Aeroportda ikki soatdan ko'proq kechikdim.

example: A diary is a book in which people write their personal experiences.
type: I do not let anybody read my diary.
example_tr: Kundalik - bu odamlar o'zlarining shaxsiy tajribalarini yozadigan kitob.
column14: Men hech kimga kundaligimni o'qishiga ruxsat bermayman.

example: An element of something is a particular part of it.
type: Tackling an opponent is Johnny’s favorite element of American football.
example_tr: Biror narsaning elementi uning alohida qismidir.
column14: Raqib bilan kurashish - Jonnining Amerika futbolidagi eng sevimli elementi.

example: When people have faith in something, they believe in it and trust it.
type: The sick girl had faith in doctors. She knew they would make her better.
example_tr: Odamlar biror narsaga ishonsa, unga ishonadi va ishonadi.
column14: Kasal qiz shifokorlarga ishonardi. U ular uni yaxshiroq qilishlarini bilar edi.

example: Grain is food crops such as wheat, corn, rice or oats.
type: The farmer planted two fields of grain this year.
example_tr: Don - bug'doy, makkajo'xori, guruch yoki jo'xori kabi oziq-ovqat ekinlari.
column14: Fermer bu yil ikki maydonga g‘alla ekdi.

example: To greet someone means to meet and welcome them.
type: When my friend came over, I greeted him at the door.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan salomlashish, u bilan uchrashish va kutib olish demakdir.
column14: Do'stim kelganida, men uni eshik oldida kutib oldim.

example: To investigate means to search for something or learn about it.
type: The detective went to investigate the crime.
example_tr: Tekshiruv nimanidir izlash yoki u haqda bilishni anglatadi.
column14: Tergovchi jinoyatni tergov qilish uchun ketdi.

example: Joy is a feeling you get when you are really happy.
type: I love baseball. I feel joy when I play.
example_tr: Quvonch - bu haqiqatan ham baxtli bo'lganingizda paydo bo'ladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Men beysbolni yaxshi ko'raman. O'ynaganimda quvonchni his qilaman.

example: A label is a tag that tells about something.
type: The label on the back of your shirt will tell you what size it is.
example_tr: Yorliq - bu biror narsa haqida gapiradigan teg.
column14: Ko'ylakning orqa tomonidagi yorliq sizga uning o'lchamini ko'rsatadi.

example: A monk is a religious person who lives a simple life.
type: The monks knew a lot about religion.
example_tr: Rohib oddiy hayot kechiradigan dindor odam.
column14: Rohiblar din haqida ko'p narsalarni bilishgan.

example: When something is odd, it is unusual.
type: Her cat is odd. It walks on two feet.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'alati bo'lsa, u g'ayrioddiy.
column14: Uning mushuki g'alati. Ikki oyoqda yuradi.

example: To pause means to stop doing something for a while.
type: Since she was so hungry, she paused to make a snack.
example_tr: Pauza qilish, biror ishni bir muddat to'xtatishni anglatadi.
column14: U juda och bo'lgani uchun, u gazak qilish uchun to'xtab qoldi.

example: A priest is a person trained to perform religious duties.
type: The priest taught us about God.
example_tr: Ruhoniy - diniy vazifalarni bajarishga o'rgatilgan shaxs.
column14: Ruhoniy bizga Xudo haqida o'rgatdi.

example: A profession is a person’s job.
type: He loved sailing, so he chose to work on ships as a profession.
example_tr: Kasb - bu insonning ishi.
column14: U suzib yurishni yaxshi ko'rardi, shuning uchun u kemalarda ishlashni kasb sifatida tanladi.

example: To adopt someone is to make them as a part of one’s own family.
type: The girl was adopted by the couple when she was three.
example_tr: Biror kishini asrab olish, uni o'z oilasining bir qismiga aylantirishdir.
column14: Qiz uch yoshida er-xotin tomonidan asrab olingan.

example: To beg is to ask for something one really wants.
type: The man begged for some money.
example_tr: Yalinish - chindan ham xohlagan narsani so'rash.
column14: Erkak bir oz pul so'radi.

example: If A is beyond B, A is farther away from a certain point than B.
type: John’s house is beyond that lake.
example_tr: Agar A B dan tashqarida bo'lsa, A ma'lum bir nuqtadan B ga qaraganda uzoqroqdir.
column14: Jonning uyi ko'lning narigi tomonida.

example: A costume is a set of clothes people wear for a particular occasion.
type: The woman wore a mask with her costume.
example_tr: Kostyum - bu odamlarning ma'lum bir voqea uchun kiyadigan kiyimlari to'plami.
column14: Ayol o'zining kostyumi bilan niqob kiygan.

example: To exclaim is to say something loudly, usually due to being excited.
type: “Look at her dress!” Sara exclaimed.
example_tr: Xitob qilish - odatda hayajonlanish tufayli baland ovozda gapirish.
column14: "Uning kiyimiga qarang!" — xitob qildi Sara.

example: To extend is to stretch out or reach.
type: The boy extended his hand to catch the ball.
example_tr: Uzatmoq — cho‘zmoq yoki cho‘zmoq.
column14: Bola to'pni ushlab olish uchun qo'lini uzatdi.

example: A fool is someone who makes unwise choices.
type: The girl was a fool for playing too close to the water.
example_tr: Axmoq - bu noto'g'ri tanlov qiladigan odam.
column14: Qiz suvga juda yaqin o'ynagani uchun ahmoq edi.

example: To forbid is to tell someone they cannot do something.
type: My father forbids watching TV while we're eating dinner.
example_tr: Taqiqlash kimgadir biror narsa qila olmasligini aytishdir.
column14: Kechki ovqatlanayotganimizda otam televizor ko'rishni taqiqlaydi.

example: To illustrate is to show something by drawing a picture.
type: The executive illustrated the decreasing profits of the company.
example_tr: Tasvirlash - biror narsani rasm chizish orqali ko'rsatish.
column14: Ijrochi kompaniyaning daromadlari pasayib borayotganini tasvirlab berdi.

example: Indeed means truly or really.
type: The birthday party was indeed fun last night.
example_tr: Haqiqatan ham, haqiqatdan ham, haqiqatdan ham.
column14: Tug'ilgan kun kechasi haqiqatan ham qiziqarli bo'ldi.

example: To interpret is to explain what something means.
type: The woman interpreted what her co-worker was trying to say.
example_tr: Talqin qilish - biror narsa nimani anglatishini tushuntirish.
column14: Ayol hamkasbining aytmoqchi bo‘lgan gaplarini talqin qildi.

example: If people do something kindly, they do it in a nice way.
type: The stranger kindly cared for the hurt man.
example_tr: Agar odamlar biron bir ishni mehribonlik bilan qilsalar, ular buni chiroyli tarzda qilishadi.
column14: Notanish odam xafa bo'lgan odamga mehribonlik bilan g'amxo'rlik qildi.

example: A motive is the reason someone does something.
type: His motive for studying so hard is to get into a good college.
example_tr: Motiv - bu kimdir biror narsa qilishining sababi.
column14: Uning juda qattiq o'qish maqsadi - yaxshi kollejga kirish.

example: A nest is a place where a bird lays its eggs.
type: The bird laid her eggs in the nest that she made.
example_tr: Uya - bu qush tuxum qo'yadigan joy.
column14: Qush o‘zi yasagan iniga tuxum qo‘ydi.

example: The origin of someone or something is where they come from.
type: The origin of the honey that we eat is from a beehive.
example_tr: Kimningdir yoki biror narsaning kelib chiqishi, ular qaerdan kelganligi.
column14: Biz iste'mol qiladigan asalning kelib chiqishi asalari uyasidan.

example: A reception is a party to welcome a person or celebrate an event.
type: We all danced and had a good time at the wedding reception.
example_tr: Ziyofat - bu odamni kutib olish yoki biron bir voqeani nishonlash uchun ziyofat.
column14: To‘yxonada hammamiz raqsga tushdik va maroqli vaqt o‘tkazdik.

example: To reject is to refuse something because you do not want it.
type: The girl rejected the broken cup.
example_tr: Rad etish - biror narsani xohlamaganingiz uchun rad etishdir.
column14: Qiz singan kosani rad etdi.

example: Silence is complete quiet.
type: The man asked for silence while he worked on the problem.
example_tr: Sukunat butunlay jim.
column14: Erkak muammo ustida ishlayotganda jim bo'lishni so'radi.

example: A stream is a small river.
type: The boy caught a fish in the stream.
example_tr: Oqim - bu kichik daryo.
column14: Bola ariqdan baliq tutdi.

example: Tone is the sound of someone’s voice. It shows how they feel.
type: My father’s tone told me I had broken the rule.
example_tr: Ohang - bu birovning ovozi. Bu ularning his-tuyg'ularini ko'rsatadi.
column14: Otamning ohangi menga qoidani buzganimni aytdi.

example: To accomplish something means to finish it.
type: He accomplished his goal of running ten miles.
example_tr: Biror ishni bajarish, uni tugatish demakdir.
column14: U o'n mil yugurish maqsadini amalga oshirdi.

example: To approve of something means you like it or are happy about it.
type: Her co-workers approved her new plan.
example_tr: Biror narsani ma'qullash, uni yoqtirish yoki undan xursand bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Hamkasblari uning yangi rejasini ma’qullashdi.

example: Approximate means to be close to an exact amount, number or time.
type: My approximate height is two meters.
example_tr: Taxminan aniq miqdor, raqam yoki vaqtga yaqin bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Mening bo'yim taxminan ikki metr.

example: A barrier is something that is in your way.
type: The Great Wall was a barrier between China and its enemies.
example_tr: To'siq - bu sizning yo'lingizda bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Buyuk devor Xitoy va uning dushmanlari o'rtasida to'siq edi.

example: To detect something means to notice or find something.
type: The boy ran to the kitchen when he detected the smell of cookies.
example_tr: Biror narsani aniqlash, biror narsani payqash yoki topish demakdir.
column14: Pechene hidini sezgan bola oshxonaga yugurdi.

example: A duty is something that a person has to do.
type: It is parents’ duty to take care of their children.
example_tr: Majburiyat - bu inson bajarishi kerak bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Farzandlariga g'amxo'rlik qilish ota-onalarning burchidir.

example: When something is elementary, it is the first or most simple thing.
type: Children go to elementary school before high school.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa elementar bo'lsa, u birinchi yoki eng oddiy narsadir.
column14: Bolalar o'rta maktabgacha boshlang'ich maktabga boradilar.

example: A failure — when you do not do something right.
type: My cooking ended in failure because I burned the food.
example_tr: Muvaffaqiyatsizlik - biror narsani to'g'ri qilmasangiz.
column14: Ovqatni yoqib yuborganim uchun pishirishim muvaffaqiyatsiz tugadi.

example: When something is gradual, it happens slowly.
type: Children learn to read at a gradual pace. They do not learn right away.
example_tr: Biror narsa asta-sekin bo'lsa, u asta-sekin sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Bolalar asta-sekin o'qishni o'rganadilar. Ular darhol o'rganishmaydi.

example: An immigrant is a person who moves to a different country.
type: My parents were immigrants. They came from Poland.
example_tr: Immigrant - bu boshqa davlatga ko'chib o'tgan shaxs.
column14: Ota-onam muhojirlar edi. Ular Polshadan kelgan.

example: To insert something means to put it in something else.
type: The mailman inserted the letter into the mailbox.
example_tr: Biror narsani kiritish, uni boshqa narsaga qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Pochtachi xatni pochta qutisiga soldi.

example: An instant is a very short amount of time.
type: A microwave oven cooks food in an instant.
example_tr: Bir lahza - bu juda qisqa vaqt.
column14: Mikroto'lqinli pech bir zumda ovqat pishiradi.

example: Poverty is the state of being poor.
type: Poverty is a problem in many countries around the world.
example_tr: Qashshoqlik - bu kambag'allik holati.
column14: Dunyoning ko'plab mamlakatlarida qashshoqlik muammosi.

example: To pretend means to make believe something is real.
type: The boy liked to pretend he was a king.
example_tr: O'zini ko'rsatish, biror narsaning haqiqat ekanligiga ishonishni anglatadi.
column14: Bola o'zini podshoh qilib ko'rsatishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: A person’s rank is their place in an order of people.
type: The man got to the rank of captain in the navy.
example_tr: Insonning martabasi - bu odamlar qatoridagi o'rni.
column14: Bu odam dengiz flotida kapitan unvoniga ega bo'ldi.

example: Recognition is getting praise from other people.
type: The hero got recognition for his brave deed.
example_tr: Tan olish - bu boshqa odamlarning maqtoviga sazovor bo'lish.
column14: Qahramon o'zining jasur harakati uchun e'tirofga sazovor bo'ldi.

example: To refrigerate something means to make it cold.
type: Grocery stores refrigerate fruit to make it last long.
example_tr: Biror narsani sovutib qo'yish, uni sovuq qilish demakdir.
column14: Oziq-ovqat do'konlari mevalarni uzoqroq saqlash uchun muzlatgichda saqlashadi.

example: Rent is the money people pay to someone to live in a certain place.
type: To live in this house, I have to pay rent at the start of each month.
example_tr: Ijara - bu ma'lum bir joyda yashash uchun odamlarga to'laydigan pul.
column14: Bu uyda yashash uchun har oy boshida ijara haqini toʻlashim kerak.

example: To retire is to leave a job, usually because of old age.
type: My father is sixty-five years old. He is about to retire from work.
example_tr: Pensiyaga chiqish, odatda keksalik tufayli ishdan ketishdir.
column14: Otam oltmish besh yoshda. U ishdan nafaqaga chiqmoqchi.

example: A statistic is a number that tells a fact about something.
type: The statistics showed that we did just as well this year as last year.
example_tr: Statistika - bu biror narsa haqida haqiqatni aytadigan raqam.
column14: Statistik ma’lumotlar shuni ko‘rsatdiki, biz bu yil ham o‘tgan yilgidek yaxshi natijalarga erishdik.

example: An astronaut is a person that goes into outer space.
type: The astronaut was walking on the moon.
example_tr: Kosmonavt - bu kosmosga chiqadigan odam.
column14: Kosmonavt oyda yurgan edi.

example: When you are awake, you are not asleep.
type: Sometimes I lay awake in bed because I am not tired.
example_tr: Siz uyg'oq bo'lganingizda, siz uxlamaysiz.
column14: Ba'zida to'shakda bedor yotaman, chunki charchamaganman.

example: When you have courage, you are not afraid.
type: The man had the courage to touch the lion.
example_tr: Jasorat bo'lsa, qo'rqmaysiz.
column14: Erkak sherga tegishga jur'at etdi.

example: To float is to move on top of water without sinking.
type: The boy’s toy boat floated in the pool.
example_tr: Suzish - suv ustida cho'kmasdan harakat qilish.
column14: Bolaning o'yinchoq qayig'i hovuzda suzib yurdi.

example: To grant something is to allow someone to have it.
type: The teacher granted us a break after studying hard all day.
example_tr: Biror narsani berish - bu kimgadir unga ega bo'lishiga ruxsat berishdir.
column14: Domla kun bo'yi o'qiganimizdan so'ng bizga tanaffus berdi.

example: Gravity is the force that makes things fall to Earth.
type: There is no gravity in space.
example_tr: Gravitatsiya - bu narsalarni Yerga tushirishga majbur qiluvchi kuch.
column14: Kosmosda tortishish kuchi yo'q.

example: A jewel is a beautiful stone that is worth a lot of money.
type: A diamond is one of the most expensive jewels in the world.
example_tr: Javohir - bu juda ko'p pulga arziydigan chiroyli tosh.
column14: Olmos dunyodagi eng qimmat marvaridlardan biridir.

example: A miner is a person who works in a mine.
type: The miner was looking for gold.
example_tr: Konchi - shaxtada ishlaydigan odam.
column14: Konchi oltin qidirayotgan edi.

example: A mineral is a type of substance found in the Earth.
type: Rocks are made up of different kinds of minerals.
example_tr: Mineral Yerda topilgan moddaning bir turi.
column14: Tog' jinslari turli xil minerallardan iborat.

example: To participate is to take part in something.
type: The students participated in the school play.
example_tr: Ishtirok etish - biror narsada ishtirok etish.
column14: O'quvchilar maktab o'yinida ishtirok etishdi.

example: Permission means the act of allowing the doing of something.
type: I have permission to drive my mom’s car.
example_tr: Ruxsat biror narsa qilishga ruxsat berishni anglatadi.
column14: Onamning mashinasini haydashga ruxsatim bor.

example: To pour a liquid means to make it come out of a container.
type: I poured some milk into my sister’s cup.
example_tr: Suyuqlikni quyish, uni idishdan chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Men opamning kosasiga bir oz sut quydim.

example: Someone or something’s presence is the fact they are there.
type: The presence of dark clouds meant it would rain.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsaning mavjudligi ularning u erda ekanligidir.
column14: Qora bulutlarning mavjudligi yomg'ir yog'ishini anglatardi.

example: If a material is raw, it is natural and has not been processed.
type: The company dumped raw sewage into the river.
example_tr: Agar material xom bo'lsa, u tabiiy va qayta ishlanmagan.
column14: Korxona xomashyo oqava suvlarni daryoga to‘kdi.

example: A satellite is something that is sent into space to get information.
type: The satellite was traveling around the earth.
example_tr: Sun'iy yo'ldosh - bu ma'lumot olish uchun kosmosga yuboriladigan narsa.
column14: Sun'iy yo'ldosh Yer atrofida aylanib yurgan.

example: The scale of something is its size, especially when it is very large.
type: I was surprised by the scale of the buildings in the downtown area.
example_tr: Biror narsaning miqyosi uning o'lchamidir, ayniqsa u juda katta bo'lsa.
column14: Shahar markazidagi binolarning ko'lami meni hayratda qoldirdi.

example: To skip something is to not do it.
type: He skipped work to get more sleep.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'tkazib yuborish - buni qilmaslik.
column14: U ko'proq uxlash uchun ishni tashlab ketdi.

example: To stretch is to make your arms or legs reach out.
type: She stretched her body before exercising.
example_tr: Cho'zish - bu qo'llaringizni yoki oyoqlaringizni cho'zishdir.
column14: Mashq qilishdan oldin u tanasini cho'zdi.

example: A telescope is a tool people use to look at the stars.
type: With a telescope, you can see the moon and stars easily.
example_tr: Teleskop - bu odamlar yulduzlarga qarash uchun foydalanadigan asbob.
column14: Teleskop yordamida siz oy va yulduzlarni osongina ko'rishingiz mumkin.

example: When something is underground, it is below the surface of the Earth.
type: Subway trains travel underground.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa er ostida bo'lsa, u Yer yuzasi ostidadir.
column14: Metro poyezdlari yer ostida harakatlanadi.

example: An alarm is something that warns people of danger.
type: When the students heard the fire alarm, they left the building.
example_tr: Signal - bu odamlarni xavf haqida ogohlantiruvchi narsa.
column14: Yong'in signalini eshitgan talabalar binoni tark etishdi.

example: When people or things are apart, they are not close together.
type: The couple decided to live apart from each other.
example_tr: Odamlar yoki narsalar bir-biridan uzoqlashganda, ular bir-biriga yaqin emas.
column14: Er-xotin bir-biridan alohida yashashga qaror qilishdi.

example: To arrest someone means to catch them for doing something bad.
type: The man was arrested for breaking the law.
example_tr: Biror kishini hibsga olish, uni yomon ish qilgani uchun qo'lga olishni anglatadi.
column14: Erkak qonunni buzgani uchun hibsga olingan.

example: An award is a prize someone gets for doing something well.
type: He got an award for having the best grades in class.
example_tr: Mukofot - bu yaxshi ish qilgani uchun oladigan mukofot.
column14: U sinfdagi eng yaxshi baholar uchun mukofot oldi.

example: A breed is a group of animals within a species.
type: like small dog breeds, such as terriers.
example_tr: Zot - bu tur ichidagi hayvonlar guruhi.
column14: kichik it zotlari kabi, masalan, teriyerlar.

example: A bucket is a round container to put things in.
type: I filled the bucket with water.
example_tr: Chelak - bu narsalarni qo'yish uchun dumaloq idish.
column14: Men chelakni suv bilan to'ldirdim.

example: A contest is a game or a race.
type: The girls had a contest to see who could jump higher.
example_tr: Bellashuv - bu o'yin yoki poyga.
column14: Qizlar o'rtasida kim balandroq sakrash uchun musobaqa o'tkazildi.

example: To convict someone means to prove that they did a bad thing.
type: He was convicted of the crime and sent to jail.
example_tr: Biror kishini ayblash uning yomon ish qilganligini isbotlashni anglatadi.
column14: U jinoyatda ayblanib, qamoqqa jo'natilgan.

example: A garage is the part of a house where people put their cars.
type: My car does not get dirty because I keep it in the garage.
example_tr: Garaj - bu odamlar o'z mashinalarini qo'yadigan uyning bir qismi.
column14: Mashinam kirlanmaydi, chunki men uni garajda saqlayapman.

example: A journalist is a person who writes news stories.
type: The journalist took notes for a story he was writing.
example_tr: Jurnalist - bu yangiliklar yozadigan odam.
column14: Jurnalist yozayotgan hikoyasi uchun eslatma oldi.

example: A pup is a young dog.
type: All the girl wanted for her birthday was a pup.
example_tr: Kuchuk - yosh it.
column14: Qizning tug'ilgan kunida xohlagan narsasi kuchukcha edi.

example: To qualify is to get, or to be declared, adequate or good enough.
type: He qualified to go to the final match by beating the opponent.
example_tr: Mavjud bo'lish - bu etarli yoki etarlicha yaxshi bo'lish yoki e'lon qilish.
column14: U raqibni mag'lub etib, final bahsiga yo'l olish huquqini qo'lga kiritdi.

example: To repair something is to fix it.
type: I repaired the flat tire on my car.
example_tr: Biror narsani tuzatish - uni tuzatish.
column14: Men mashinamning shinasini ta'mirladim.

example: To resume something means to start it again after taking a break.
type: I put the newspaper down to eat breakfast. Then I resumed reading.
example_tr: Biror narsani davom ettirish, tanaffusdan keyin uni qayta boshlashni anglatadi.
column14: Men nonushta qilish uchun gazetani qo'ydim. Keyin men o'qishni davom ettirdim.

example: To rob a person or place is to take their property by using force.
type: A thief has robbed me of my passport.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki joyni talon-taroj qilish uning mulkini kuch ishlatib tortib olishdir.
column14: O'g'ri mening pasportimni o'g'irlab ketdi.

example: To slip means to slide and fall down.
type: The man slipped on the wet floor.
example_tr: Sirpanmoq sirg‘alib yiqilmoq degan ma’noni anglatadi.
column14: Erkak nam polda sirpanib ketdi.

example: Somewhat means to some degree, but not to a large degree.
type: James was somewhat upset when he had to move some boxes.
example_tr: Qaysidir ma'noni anglatadi, lekin katta darajada emas.
column14: Jeyms ba'zi qutilarni ko'chirishga majbur bo'lganida biroz xafa bo'ldi.

example: When something is stable, it will not fall over.
type: The chair is stable, Its legs are strong.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa barqaror bo'lsa, u yiqilmaydi.
column14: Kreslo barqaror, oyoqlari kuchli.

example: A tissue is a soft piece of paper people use to wipe their noses.
type: There was a box of tissue on the table.
example_tr: Ro'molcha - bu odamlar burunlarini artish uchun ishlatadigan yumshoq qog'oz.
column14: Stol ustida bir quti ro'molcha bor edi.

example: A yard is the ground just outside of a person’s house.
type: The girls jumped rope in the yard.
example_tr: Hovli - bu odamning uyi tashqarisidagi zamin.
column14: Qizlar hovlida arqon bilan sakrashdi.

example: If two things or people are alike, they are similar in some way.
type: People often think my sister and I look alike.
example_tr: Agar ikkita narsa yoki odamlar bir-biriga o'xshash bo'lsa, ular qandaydir tarzda o'xshashdir.
column14: Odamlar ko'pincha singlim va men bir-biriga o'xshaymiz deb o'ylashadi.

example: To annoy someone means to bother them.
type: The flies buzzing around John’s head annoyed him very much.
example_tr: Birovni bezovta qilish, uni bezovta qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Jonning boshi atrofida g'uvillab yurgan pashshalar uni juda bezovta qildi.

example: Architecture is the style or way a building is made.
type: The architecture of the church is amazing.
example_tr: Arxitektura - bu binoning uslubi yoki uslubi.
column14: Cherkovning arxitekturasi hayratlanarli.

example: If something is artificial, it is made to look like something natural.
type: That soccer field has artificial grass, but it looks real.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sun'iy bo'lsa, u tabiiy narsaga o'xshaydi.
column14: O'sha futbol maydonida sun'iy o't bor, lekin u haqiqiy ko'rinadi.

example: A chain is a series of connected loops often used to keep things in place.
type: The scary dog was secured with a chain.
example_tr: Zanjir - bu narsalarni joyida ushlab turish uchun ko'pincha ishlatiladigan bir-biriga bog'langan halqalar seriyasidir.
column14: Qo'rqinchli it zanjir bilan mahkamlangan.

example: If something is distinct, it is easily noticed or different from other things.
type: That girl has distinct pink hair.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u osongina seziladi yoki boshqa narsalardan farq qiladi.
column14: Bu qizning aniq pushti sochlari bor.

example: To distinguish is to recognize differences between things.
type: The twins look exactly the same. It is hard to distinguish between them.
example_tr: Farqlash - bu narsalar orasidagi farqni tan olishdir.
column14: Egizaklar bir xil ko'rinishga ega. Ularni farqlash qiyin.

example: Dust is very tiny pieces of dirt or other matter.
type: In the old house, the dust was thick on the floor and chairs.
example_tr: Chang - bu juda kichik axloqsizlik yoki boshqa moddalar.
column14: Qadimgi uyda pol va stullarda chang qalin edi.

example: Excitement means to feel a lot of happiness about something.
type: Did you see the excitement in her when the team scored?
example_tr: Hayajon, biror narsadan juda ko'p baxtni his qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Jamoa gol urganida undagi hayajonni ko'rdingizmi?

example: To heal means to make a part of the body healthy again after injury.
type: After my broken arm heals, I can play baseball again.
example_tr: Sog'ayish, jarohatdan keyin tananing bir qismini yana sog'lom qilish demakdir.
column14: Singan qo‘lim tuzalgach, yana beysbol o‘ynashim mumkin.

example: To inherit is to get something from someone who has died.
type: She inherited her mother’s gold earrings.
example_tr: Meros olish - o'lgan kishidan biror narsa olish.
column14: U onasining tilla sirg'alarini meros qilib oldi.

example: A manner is the way someone does something.
type: His manner of not looking at someone while speaking, is a bit rude.
example_tr: Xulq - bu birovning biror narsa qilish usuli.
column14: Gapirayotganda birovga qaramasligi biroz qo'pol.

example: Something mounts when it becomes stronger over time.
type: His fear mounted as the monster crawled out from under his bed.
example_tr: Biror narsa vaqt o'tishi bilan kuchayib borsa, kuchayadi.
column14: Yirtqich hayvon karavoti ostidan sudralib chiqqanida uning qo‘rquvi kuchaydi.

example: A roof is the outside top part of a building.
type: The roof was covered with snow.
example_tr: Tom - bu binoning tashqi ustki qismi.
column14: Tom qor bilan qoplangan edi.

example: A shortage is a lack of something you need or want.
type: Since there was a shortage of food, people were hungry.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu sizga kerakli yoki xohlagan narsaning etishmasligi.
column14: Oziq-ovqat tanqisligi sababli odamlar och edi.

example: If something is solid, it is made of firm material.
type: The safe looked to be quite solid.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qattiq bo'lsa, u qattiq materialdan qilingan.
column14: Seyf ancha mustahkam ko'rinardi.

example: A stock is a stored amount of something.
type: They keep a stock of rice so they'll always have something to eat.
example_tr: Qimmatli qog'ozlar - bu biror narsaning saqlangan miqdori.
column14: Ular har doim ovqatlanadigan narsaga ega bo'lishlari uchun guruch zaxirasini saqlashadi.

example: A substance is any specific material or mixture of materials.
type: Water is an important substance for all living things.
example_tr: Modda - har qanday o'ziga xos material yoki materiallar aralashmasi.
column14: Suv barcha tirik mavjudotlar uchun muhim moddadir.

example: A tomb is a grave where a dead person is buried.
type: Their whole family is buried inside the tomb.
example_tr: Qabr - o'lgan odam ko'miladigan qabr.
column14: Ularning butun oilasi qabr ichiga dafn etilgan.

example: A wound is an injury to the body.
type: He had many wounds after the car accident.
example_tr: Yara - bu tanadagi shikastlanish.
column14: Avtohalokatdan keyin uning ko'p jarohatlari bor edi.

example: A bath is water in a tub. People take a bath to get clean.
type: After playing in the dirt, the boy took a bath.
example_tr: Hammom - bu vannadagi suv. Odamlar tozalanish uchun vanna qabul qilishadi.
column14: Tuproqda o‘ynagach, bola cho‘mildi.

example: To bend is to move something so it is not straight.
type: Lee bent over and picked up the paper on the ground.
example_tr: Egilish - biror narsani tekis bo'lmasligi uchun harakatlantirish.
column14: Li egilib, yerda turgan qog‘ozni oldi.

example: To chew is to move your mouth to break up food.
