type: I always chew my food carefully before swallowing it.
example_tr: Chaynash - ovqatni parchalash uchun og'zingizni harakatlantirishdir.
column14: Men har doim ovqatni yutishdan oldin ehtiyotkorlik bilan chaynayman.

example: When a person is disabled, they cannot do what a normal person can do
type: The disabled man used a wheelchair to move around.
example_tr: Biror kishi nogiron bo'lsa, u oddiy odam qila oladigan narsani qila olmaydi
column14: Nogiron odam harakatlanish uchun aravachadan foydalangan.

example: If something is fantastic, it is really good.
type: The student did a fantastic job on his project and got an award.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa fantastik bo'lsa, u haqiqatan ham yaxshi.
column14: Talaba o'z loyihasida ajoyib ish qildi va mukofot oldi.

example: Fiction is a story that is not true.
type: I enjoy reading works of fiction because they are very entertaining.
example_tr: Badiiy adabiyot haqiqatga to'g'ri kelmaydigan hikoyadir.
column14: Badiiy asarlarni o‘qishni yoqtiraman, chunki ular juda qiziqarli.

example: A flag is a piece of colored cloth that represents something.
type: Our country has a beautiful flag.
example_tr: Bayroq - biror narsani ifodalovchi rangli mato bo'lagi.
column14: Mamlakatimizning go‘zal bayrog‘i bor.

example: To inspect is to look at something carefully.
type: The mechanic inspected our car to see if it had any problems.
example_tr: Tekshirish - biror narsani diqqat bilan ko'rib chiqish.
column14: Mexanizator mashinamizni ko‘zdan kechirdi, unda muammo bor-yo‘qmi.

example: A journal is a type of magazine that deals with an academic subject.
type: Mi-young was busy working on an article for an art journal.
example_tr: Jurnal - ilmiy mavzu bilan shug'ullanadigan jurnalning bir turi.
column14: Mi-young badiiy jurnal uchun maqola ustida ishlash bilan band edi.

example: A liquid is a substance that is neither solid nor gas.
type: Water is the most important liquid for life.
example_tr: Suyuqlik qattiq ham, gaz ham bo'lmagan moddadir.
column14: Suv hayot uchun eng muhim suyuqlikdir.

example: To marvel at something is to feel surprise and interest in it.
type: We marveled at her excellent piano playing.
example_tr: Biror narsaga hayron bo'lish - unga hayrat va qiziqishni his qilish.
column14: Biz uning ajoyib pianino chalishidan hayratda qoldik.

example: A nutrient is something that a living thing needs to keep it alive.
type: Vegetables are full of important nutrients.
example_tr: Ozuqa moddasi tirik mavjudotning yashashi uchun zarur bo'lgan narsadir.
column14: Sabzavotlar muhim oziq moddalar bilan to'la.

example: To overcome a problem is to successfully fix it.
type: She overcame her shyness and spoke in front of the class.
example_tr: Muammoni bartaraf etish uni muvaffaqiyatli hal qilishdir.
column14: U uyatchanligini yengib, sinf oldida gapirdi.

example: To recall something is to remember it.
type: She was trying to recall what she had told her friend.
example_tr: Biror narsani eslash - uni eslash.
column14: U dugonasiga aytgan gaplarini eslashga urinardi.

example: To regret something is to wish that it didn’t happen.
type: I regret that I was mean to my sister.
example_tr: Biror narsadan afsuslanish - bu sodir bo'lmasligini orzu qilish.
column14: Opamga yomon munosabatda bo‘lganimdan afsusdaman.

example: A soul is a person’s spirit.
type: Some people believe that the soul lives after the body dies.
example_tr: Ruh - bu insonning ruhi.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar tana o'lgandan keyin ruh yashaydi, deb hisoblashadi.

example: When something is sufficient, you have enough of it.
type: After eating a sufficient amount of food, I left the table.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa etarli bo'lsa, sizda etarli bo'ladi.
column14: Etarli miqdorda ovqat yegach, stoldan chiqib ketdim.

example: Surgery is medical treatment when the doctor cuts open your body.
type: I needed surgery to repair my leg after the accident.
example_tr: Jarrohlik - bu shifokor tanangizni kesib tashlaganida tibbiy davolanish.
column14: Baxtsiz hodisadan keyin oyog'imni tiklash uchun operatsiya qilishim kerak edi.

example: If something is tough, it is difficult.
type: The man passed his driving test even though it was very tough.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qiyin bo'lsa, bu qiyin.
column14: Erkak haydovchilik imtihonidan o'tdi, garchi bu juda qiyin bo'lsa ham.

example: A tube is a pipe through which water or air passes.
type: The pile of tubes was going to be put in the ground.
example_tr: Quvur - suv yoki havo o'tadigan quvur.
column14: Quvurlar uyumini erga qo'yish kerak edi.

example: To admit something means to say that it is true.
type: I had to admit that I stole his idea.
example_tr: Biror narsani tan olish bu haqiqat ekanligini aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Men uning fikrini o'g'irlaganimni tan olishim kerak edi.

example: A bin is a container that holds things.
type: He put his trash in the bin.
example_tr: Axlat qutisi - bu narsalarni saqlaydigan idish.
column14: U axlat qutisiga tashladi.

example: A bowl is a deep, round dish that holds food or liquid.
type: I ate a bowl of cereal for breakfast.
example_tr: Piyola - bu oziq-ovqat yoki suyuqlikni saqlaydigan chuqur, yumaloq idish.
column14: Nonushtaga bir piyola yorma yedim.

example: A cabin is a small house made of wood.
type: My grandfather owns a small cabin in the country.
example_tr: Kabina - bu yog'ochdan yasalgan kichik uy.
column14: Mening bobomning mamlakatda kichkina kabinasi bor.

example: Cash is money in the form of paper or coins.
type: I was able to save up enough cash to buy my mother a gift.
example_tr: Naqd pul - bu qog'oz yoki tanga shaklidagi pul.
column14: Men onamga sovg'a sotib olish uchun etarli miqdorda pul yig'ishga muvaffaq bo'ldim.

example: A criminal is a person who does something against the law.
type: The police made sure the criminal couldn’t move his hands.
example_tr: Jinoyatchi qonunga zid ish qilgan shaxsdir.
column14: Politsiya jinoyatchi qo'llarini qimirlata olmasligiga ishonch hosil qildi.

example: A dozen is a group of twelve things.
type: Mom brought home a dozen donuts for us as a treat.
example_tr: O'nlab - o'n ikki narsadan iborat guruh.
column14: Onam bizga sovg'a sifatida uyga o'nlab donut olib keldi.

example: An elder is a person who is older than the people around them.
type: Uncle Ray is my elder so I always try to be respectful.
example_tr: Oqsoqol - bu atrofidagi odamlardan kattaroq odam.
column14: Rey amaki mening oqsoqol, shuning uchun men har doim hurmatli bo'lishga harakat qilaman.

example: If something is facial, it is related to a person’s face.
type: I could tell from his facial features that he was angry.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yuz bo'lsa, u odamning yuziga bog'liq.
column14: Uning jahli chiqqanini yuz xususiyatlaridan bildim.

example: A fence is a structure around a house or field.
type: The farmer put up a fence so that no one could walk on her field.
example_tr: Devor - bu uy yoki dala atrofidagi inshoot.
column14: Fermer uning dalasida hech kim yura olmasligi uchun panjara o'rnatdi.

example: To inspire means to make a person want to do something.
type: I was inspired to write a poem after watching the sunrise.
example_tr: Ilhomlantirish, odamni biror narsa qilishga intilishni anglatadi.
column14: Quyosh chiqishini ko‘rib, she’r yozishga ruhlandim.

example: When something is mere, it is small or not important.
type: We lost the game by a mere two points.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oddiy bo'lsa, u kichik yoki muhim emas.
column14: O'yinda atigi ikki ochkoga yutqazdik.

example: If something is neat, it is very clean or organized well.
type: My sister always keeps her bedroom very neat.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa toza bo'lsa, u juda toza yoki yaxshi tashkil etilgan.
column14: Opam yotoqxonani doim toza tutadi.

example: An occasion is a time when something important happens.
type: Her graduation was an occasion to have a good time.
example_tr: Voqea - bu muhim narsa sodir bo'ladigan vaqt.
column14: Uning bitiruvi yaxshi vaqt o'tkazish uchun imkoniyat bo'ldi.

example: A penalty is a punishment, given when someone breaks a rule or law.
type: I had to pay a $100 penalty for parking in the wrong spot.
example_tr: Jazo - bu kimdir qoida yoki qonunni buzganida beriladigan jazo.
column14: Men noto'g'ri joyda to'xtab qolganim uchun 100 dollar jarima to'lashim kerak edi.

example: When someone is rude, they are mean and not polite.
type: The children at the bus stop were very rude.
example_tr: Biror kishi qo'pol bo'lsa, u odobli emas, yomon.
column14: Avtobus bekatidagi bolalar juda qo'pol edi.

example: To settle a problem means to end it by finding a solution.
type: It took three of our best executives all day to settle the problem.
example_tr: Muammoni hal qilish, uni yechim topish orqali tugatish demakdir.
column14: Muammoni hal qilish uchun kun bo'yi uchta eng yaxshi menejerimiz kerak bo'ldi.

example: A vehicle is a thing that moves people or things to another place.
type: A ferry is a vehicle that takes people from one island to another.
example_tr: Avtotransport - bu odamlarni yoki narsalarni boshqa joyga ko'chiradigan narsa.
column14: Parom - bu odamlarni bir oroldan boshqasiga olib boradigan transport vositasi.

example: A wallet is a thing that holds money and fits in a pocket.
type: I keep my money in a wallet.
example_tr: Hamyon - bu pulni saqlaydigan va cho'ntagiga sig'adigan narsa.
column14: Men pulimni hamyonda saqlayman.

example: To yell is to say something very loudly.
type: The coach yelled at his team for their poor performance.
example_tr: Qichqirmoq - bir narsani juda baland ovozda aytish.
column14: Murabbiy o'z jamoasiga yomon o'yin ko'rsatgani uchun baqirdi.

example: To accuse someone of something is to blame them for doing it.
type: She accused her brother of breaking her computer.
example_tr: Biror kishini biror narsada ayblash, uni bu ishni qilganlikda ayblashdir.
column14: U akasini kompyuterini sindirishda aybladi.

example: To adjust something means to change it so it is better.
type: He adjusted the old guitar to make it sound better.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'zgartirish, uni yaxshiroq qilish uchun o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: U eski gitarani yaxshi ovoz berish uchun sozladi.

example: To amuse someone means to do something that is funny or entertaining.
type: The singer was very good. She amused the crowd.
example_tr: Biror kishini qiziqtirish kulgili yoki qiziqarli narsalarni qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Qo'shiqchi juda yaxshi edi. U olomonni qiziqtirdi.

example: Coral is the hard, colorful material formed by the shells of animals.
type: The diver admired the beautiful coral under the water.
example_tr: Marjon hayvonlarning qobiqlaridan hosil bo'lgan qattiq, rangli materialdir.
column14: G'avvos suv ostidagi go'zal marjonga qoyil qoldi.

example: Cotton is a cloth made from the fibers of the cotton plant.
type: I like to wear clothes made from cotton in the summer.
example_tr: Paxta - paxta o'simligining tolalaridan tayyorlangan mato.
column14: Men yozda paxtadan tikilgan kiyim kiyishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: To crash means to hit and break something.
type: There was a loud noise when the car crashed into the tree.
example_tr: To'qnashuv - biror narsani urish va sindirish demakdir.
column14: Mashina daraxtga borib urilganda qattiq shovqin bo‘lgan.

example: A deck is a wooden floor built outside of a house or the floor of a ship.
type: A ship will store many supplies below its deck.
example_tr: Pastki - uyning tashqarisida yoki kemaning tagida qurilgan yog'och zamin.
column14: Kema o'z kemasi ostida ko'plab materiallarni saqlaydi.

example: To engage in something means to do it.
type: Dad was engaged in sawing a piece of wood in half.
example_tr: Biror narsa bilan shug'ullanish, uni qilish demakdir.
column14: Dadam yog'ochning yarmini arralash bilan shug'ullangan.

example: When something is firm, it is solid but not too hard.
type: He sleeps better on a firm bed.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qattiq bo'lsa, u qattiq, lekin juda qattiq emas.
column14: U qattiq yotoqda yaxshiroq uxlaydi.

example: Fuel is something that creates heat or energy.
type: Heat is the fuel that comes from fire.
example_tr: Yoqilg'i issiqlik yoki energiya hosil qiluvchi narsadir.
column14: Issiqlik - bu olovdan chiqadigan yoqilg'i.

example: When something is grand, it is big and liked by people.
type: The grand mountain rose high into the sky.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa buyuk bo'lsa, u katta va odamlarga yoqadi.
column14: Ulug‘ tog‘ osmonga ko‘tarildi.

example: A hurricane is a bad storm that happens over the ocean.
type: The wind from the hurricane bent the palm tree.
example_tr: Dovul - okean ustida sodir bo'ladigan yomon bo'ron.
column14: Dovuldan kelgan shamol palma daraxtini egdi.

example: A loss means the act or an instance of losing something.
type: I suffered a big loss while I was gambling.
example_tr: Yo'qotish harakat yoki biror narsani yo'qotish misolini anglatadi.
column14: Qimor o'ynab yurganimda katta yo'qotishga duchor bo'ldim.

example: If something is simple, it is plain and not decorated.
type: He bought a pair of plain white shoes over the weekend.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oddiy bo'lsa, u oddiy va bezatilgan emas.
column14: Dam olish kunlarida u bir juft oddiy oq tufli sotib oldi.

example: A reef is a group of rocks or coral that rise to or near the ocean.
type: He walked along the reef and looked at the water below.
example_tr: Rif - okeanga yoki okeanga yaqin joylashgan toshlar yoki marjonlar guruhi.
column14: U rif bo'ylab yurib, pastdagi suvga qaradi.

example: To shut something means to close it tightly.
type: Please shut the door; the air outside is cold.
example_tr: Biror narsani yopish uni mahkam yopish demakdir.
column14: Iltimos, eshikni yoping; tashqarida havo sovuq.

example: When someone is strict, they make sure others follow rules.
type: The teacher is strict. She does not let students talk in class.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qattiqqo'l bo'lsa, boshqalar qoidalarga rioya qilishiga ishonch hosil qiladi.
column14: O'qituvchi qattiqqo'l. U o'quvchilarning darsda gaplashishiga ruxsat bermaydi.

example: To surf means to use a special board to ride on waves in the ocean.
type: The students went to the beach to surf during their vacation.
example_tr: Sörf qilish - okeandagi to'lqinlarga minish uchun maxsus taxtadan foydalanishni anglatadi.
column14: Talabalar ta'til paytida dengiz sohiliga borishdi.

example: A task is a piece of work to be done that is usually difficult.
type: My task for the weekend was to clean the entire back yard.
example_tr: Vazifa - bu odatda qiyin bo'lgan bajarilishi kerak bo'lgan ish.
column14: Dam olish kunlaridagi vazifam butun orqa hovlini tozalash edi.

example: A zone is an area that has different qualities from the ones around it.
type: Firefighters often work in danger zones.
example_tr: Zona - bu atrofdagilardan farqli sifatlarga ega bo'lgan hudud.
column14: O't o'chiruvchilar ko'pincha xavfli zonalarda ishlaydi.

example: An apology is something someone says to show that they are sorry.
type: After arguing with her teacher, the girl wrote the teacher an apology.
example_tr: Kechirim so'rash, kimdir kechirim so'rashini ko'rsatish uchun aytadigan so'zdir.
column14: Qiz o'qituvchisi bilan janjallashgach, o'qituvchiga kechirim so'radi.

example: If someone or something is bold, they are not afraid of doing something.
type: The bold man climbed the high mountain.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa dadil bo'lsa, ular biror narsa qilishdan qo'rqmaydilar.
column14: Dadil odam baland toqqa chiqdi.

example: To capture someone or something is to catch them.
type: James tried to capture the bubbles in his hands.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani qo'lga olish - ularni qo'lga olish.
column14: Jeyms qo'llaridagi pufakchalarni ushlashga harakat qildi.

example: If a rule or quality is cardinal, then it is the most important one.
type: Raising your hand in the classroom before you speak is a cardinal rule.
example_tr: Agar qoida yoki sifat asosiy bo'lsa, u eng muhimi.
column14: Gapirishdan oldin sinfda qo'lingizni ko'tarish asosiy qoidadir.

example: A duke is a man of high social rank but below a king or queen.
type: The duke ruled over the land.
example_tr: Gertsog - yuqori ijtimoiy mavqega ega, ammo qirol yoki malikadan past bo'lgan odam.
column14: Gersog erni boshqargan.

example: To expose is to make known something that is hidden.
type: He took off his shirt exposing his costume.
example_tr: Oshkora qilish, yashiringan narsani oshkor qilishdir.
column14: U kostyumini ochib ko'ylagini yechdi.

example: If people feel guilty, they feel bad for what they did.
type: I felt guilty for taking my sister’s cookies.
example_tr: Agar odamlar o'zlarini aybdor his qilsalar, ular qilgan ishlaridan xafa bo'lishadi.
column14: Opamning pishiriqlarini olganim uchun o'zimni aybdor his qildim.

example: To hire someone is to pay them money to work for you.
type: We hired a man to paint our house.
example_tr: Biror kishini yollash - bu siz uchun ishlash uchun ularga pul to'lashdir.
column14: Uyimizni bo'yash uchun odam yolladik.

example: If someone is innocent, they are not guilty of a crime.
type: The judge said that the woman was innocent of the crime.
example_tr: Agar kimdir aybsiz bo'lsa, u jinoyatda aybdor emas.
column14: Sudya ayolning jinoyatda aybsizligini aytdi.

example: Jail is a place where criminals go to be punished.
type: The thief was caught and sent to jail for ten years.
example_tr: Qamoq bu jinoyatchilar jazolanish uchun boradigan joy.
column14: O‘g‘ri ushlanib, o‘n yilga qamoqqa tashlandi.

example: A minister is an important person in government with many duties.
type: The minister of education controls the country’s schools.
example_tr: Vazir hukumatdagi muhim shaxs bo'lib, ko'plab vazifalarni bajaradi.
column14: Ta'lim vaziri mamlakat maktablarini nazorat qiladi.

example: If someone or something is ordinary, they are not special in any way.
type: Today was just an ordinary day. Nothing unusual happened.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa oddiy bo'lsa, ular hech qanday tarzda alohida emas.
column14: Bugun oddiy kun edi. Hech qanday g'ayrioddiy narsa yuz bermadi.

example: If something is permanent, it lasts for a long time or forever.
type: We don’t know if Aunt Mildred’s visit will be a permanent one.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa doimiy bo'lsa, u uzoq vaqt yoki abadiy davom etadi.
column14: Mildred xolaning tashrifi doimiy bo'ladimi yoki yo'qligini bilmaymiz.

example: To preserve is to protect something from harm.
type: Dad sprayed a chemical on the house to help preserve its looks.
example_tr: Saqlash - biror narsani zarardan himoya qilish.
column14: Dadam uyning tashqi ko'rinishini saqlab qolish uchun unga kimyoviy dori sepdi.

example: To pronounce is to say the sounds of letters or words.
type: Young children often have trouble pronouncing words right.
example_tr: Talaffuz qilish - harflar yoki so'zlarning tovushlarini aytish.
column14: Yosh bolalar ko'pincha so'zlarni to'g'ri talaffuz qilishda qiyinchiliklarga duch kelishadi.

example: To resemble someone is to look like them.
type: The baby resembles his father a great deal.
example_tr: Birovga o'xshamoq - unga o'xshamoq.
column14: Chaqaloq otasiga juda o'xshaydi.

example: A symptom of a bad condition or illness is a sign that it is happening.
type: Sneezing and a high fever are symptoms of the common cold.
example_tr: Yomon holat yoki kasallikning alomati bu sodir bo'layotganining belgisidir.
column14: Hapşırma va yuqori isitma umumiy sovuqning belgilaridir.

example: Tobacco is a plant whose leaves are smoked, such as in cigarettes.
type: The tobacco in cigarettes is bad for your health.
example_tr: Tamaki - barglari dudlangan o'simlik, masalan, sigaretada.
column14: Sigaretdagi tamaki sog'liq uchun zararli.

example: Twins are two children born at the same time.
type: My sister and I are twins. We look exactly the same.
example_tr: Egizaklar bir vaqtning o'zida tug'ilgan ikkita boladir.
column14: Opam va men egizaklarmiz. Biz mutlaqo bir xil ko'rinishga egamiz.

example: A witch is a woman with magical powers.
type: People think that witches fly around on broomsticks.
example_tr: Jodugar - sehrli kuchga ega ayol.
column14: Odamlar jodugarlar supurgi ustida uchib ketishadi, deb o'ylashadi.

example: To accompany other fae means to join them or go with them.
type: My brothers accompanied me to the movie.
example_tr: Boshqa fayga hamrohlik qilish ularga qo'shilishni yoki ular bilan borishni anglatadi.
column14: Kinoga akalarim hamrohlik qilishdi.

example: When something is bare, it is plain. It has no covering.
type: He likes to walk around in his bare feet.
example_tr: Biror narsa yalang'och bo'lsa, u aniq. Uning qoplamasi yo'q.
column14: Yalang oyoqlarida yurishni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: A branch is the part of a tree with leaves.
type: The monkey was hanging from a branch on the tree.
example_tr: Shox - bu daraxtning barglari bo'lgan qismi.
column14: Maymun daraxtning shoxiga osilgan edi.

example: A breath is the air that goes into and out of one’s lungs.
type: You can’t take a breath under water.
example_tr: Nafas - bu o'pkaga kiradigan va undan chiqadigan havo.
column14: Siz suv ostida nafas ololmaysiz.

example: A bridge is something that is built over a river so people can cross it
type: The old bridge fell into the river.
example_tr: Ko'prik - odamlar daryodan o'tishi uchun qurilgan narsa
column14: Eski ko‘prik daryoga qulab tushdi.

example: To cast something means to throw it.
type: The fisherman cast his line into the water.
example_tr: Biror narsani tashlash, uni tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Baliqchi ipini suvga tashladi.

example: To dare means to be brave enough to try something.
type: He dared to jump out of the airplane and skydive.
example_tr: Jasorat qilish, biror narsani sinab ko'rish uchun jasur bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U samolyotdan sakrashga va parashyutdan sakrashga jur'at etdi.

example: When something is electronic, it uses electricity to do something.
type: I like having electronic devices such as an MP3 player.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa elektron bo'lsa, u biror narsa qilish uchun elektr energiyasidan foydalanadi.
column14: Menga MP3 pleer kabi elektron qurilmalar yoqadi.

example: An inn is a place where travelers can rest and eat.
type: The visitor got a room at the inn.
example_tr: Mehmonxona - sayohatchilar dam olishlari va ovqatlanishlari mumkin bo'lgan joy.
column14: Mehmon mehmonxonadan xona oldi.

example: A net is a bag made of strong thread. It is used to catch animals.
type: The boy caught butterflies in his net.
example_tr: To'r - mustahkam ipdan yasalgan sumka. U hayvonlarni tutish uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: Bola to'rida kapalaklarni tutdi.

example: A philosophy is a way to think about truth and life.
type: My philosophy is “live and let live.”
example_tr: Falsafa haqiqat va hayot haqida fikr yuritish usulidir.
column14: Mening falsafam “yasha va yasha”.

example: A pot is a deep, round metal container used for cooking.
type: Don't touch the pot on the stove. It’s hot.
example_tr: Qozon - pishirish uchun ishlatiladigan chuqur, dumaloq metall idish.
column14: Pechka ustidagi qozonga tegmang. Issiq.

example: A seed is the hard part of a plant or fruit that trees grow from.
type: I planted the seed in the dirt hoping that it would grow into a tree.
example_tr: Urug' - bu daraxtlar o'sadigan o'simlik yoki mevaning qattiq qismi.
column14: Daraxt bo‘lib qolar degan umidda urug‘ni tuproqqa ekdim.

example: When something is sharp, it has a thin edge that cuts things easily.
type: That knife is very sharp. Be careful not to hurt yourself.
example_tr: Biror narsa o'tkir bo'lsa, u narsalarni osongina kesib tashlaydigan nozik qirraga ega.
column14: Bu pichoq juda o'tkir. O'zingizga zarar yetkazmaslik uchun ehtiyot bo'ling.

example: A sort of something is a type of it.
type: What sort of instrument do you want to learn to play?
example_tr: Biror narsa uning bir turi.
column14: Qanday turdagi asbobni chalishni o'rganmoqchisiz?

example: To subtract means to take something away.
type: We learned how to subtract numbers from each other in class.
example_tr: Ayirish biror narsani olib qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Biz sinfda raqamlarni bir-biridan ayirishni o'rgandik.

example: When something is tight, it is fixed or fastened firmly in place.
type: The knots were too tight to untie.
example_tr: Biror narsa qattiq bo'lsa, u mahkamlanadi yoki joyiga mahkamlanadi.
column14: Tugunlar echish uchun juda qattiq edi.

example: If something is virtual, then it is very close to being true or accurate.
type: Because he's popular, Joe is the virtual leader of the group.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa virtual bo'lsa, u haqiqat yoki aniq bo'lishga juda yaqin.
column14: U mashhur bo'lgani uchun Djo guruhning virtual rahbari.

example: To weigh something means to see how heavy it is.
type: The little dog weighed exactly 3kgs.
example_tr: Biror narsani tortish uning qanchalik og'irligini ko'rishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkina itning vazni 3 kg edi.

example: To whisper means to say very quietly.
type: We have to whisper in the library so people can focus on reading.
example_tr: Pichirlash juda sekin gapirishni anglatadi.
column14: Odamlar diqqatini o‘qishga qaratishi uchun kutubxonada pichirlashimiz kerak.

example: If ideas are abstract, they are based on general ways of thinking.
type: The idea of beauty is abstract and changes over time.
example_tr: Agar g'oyalar mavhum bo'lsa, ular umumiy fikrlash usullariga asoslanadi.
column14: Go'zallik g'oyasi mavhum bo'lib, vaqt o'tishi bilan o'zgaradi.

example: If something is annual, it happens once a year.
type: The only time I see my aunts and uncles is at our annual family picnic.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yillik bo'lsa, bu yiliga bir marta sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Men xola va amakilarimni faqat yillik oilaviy sayrimizda ko‘raman.

example: Clay is a type of heavy, wet soil used to make pots.
type: She made a bowl out of the clay.
example_tr: Loy kostryulkalar tayyorlash uchun ishlatiladigan og'ir, nam tuproq turidir.
column14: U loydan kosa yasadi.

example: Cloth is material used to make clothes.
type: His shirt is made of a very soft type of cloth.
example_tr: Mato kiyim tikish uchun ishlatiladigan materialdir.
column14: Uning ko'ylagi juda yumshoq matodan qilingan.

example: A curtain is a cloth hung over a window or used to divide a room.
type: She opened the curtains to let light into the room.
example_tr: Parda - bu derazaga osilgan yoki xonani ajratish uchun ishlatiladigan mato.
column14: U xonaga yorug'lik kiritish uchun pardalarni ochdi.

example: To deserve is to be worthy of something as a result of one’s actions.
type: The dog deserved a bone for behaving very well.
example_tr: Loyiq bo'lmoq - bu o'z harakatlari natijasida biror narsaga loyiq bo'lish.
column14: It o'zini juda yaxshi tutgani uchun suyakka loyiq edi.

example: Feathers are the things covering birds’ bodies.
type: That bird has orange feathers on its chest.
example_tr: Tuklar qushlarning tanasini qoplaydigan narsadir.
column14: O'sha qushning ko'kragida to'q sariq rangli patlar bor.

example: If land is fertile, it is able to produce good crops and plants.
type: The farmer grew many vegetables in the fertile soil.
example_tr: Agar yer unumdor bo'lsa, unda yaxshi hosil va o'simliklar etishtirishga qodir.
column14: Fermer unumdor tuproqda ko‘plab sabzavot yetishtirdi.

example: A flood is an event in which water covers an area which is usually dry.
type: After three days of rain, there was a flood in the city.
example_tr: To'fon - bu odatda quruq bo'lgan hududni suv qoplaydigan hodisa.
column14: Uch kunlik yomg‘irdan keyin shaharda suv toshqini sodir bo‘ldi.

example: Furniture is the things used in a house such as tables and chairs.
type: His living room only had a few simple pieces of furniture.
example_tr: Mebel - bu uyda ishlatiladigan stol va stullar kabi narsalar.
column14: Uning yashash xonasida faqat bir nechta oddiy mebellar bor edi.

example: A grave is the place where a dead person is buried.
type: We visit our grandfather’s grave each year.
example_tr: Qabr - o'lgan odam dafn qilinadigan joy.
column14: Biz har yili bobomizning qabrini ziyorat qilamiz.

example: If something is ideal, it is the best that it can possibly be.
type: This house is an ideal place for my family. It has everything we need.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ideal bo'lsa, u bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan eng yaxshisidir.
column14: Bu uy mening oilam uchun ideal joy. Unda bizga kerak bo'lgan hamma narsa bor.

example: Intelligence is the ability to learn and understand things.
type: Because of his high intelligence, he finished school early.
example_tr: Aql - bu narsalarni o'rganish va tushunish qobiliyati.
column14: O‘zining yuksak aql-zakovati tufayli maktabni erta tugatdi.

example: If something happens nowadays, it happens at the present time.
type: In the past people walked everywhere. Nowadays, they use cars.
example_tr: Agar bugungi kunda biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, u hozirgi vaqtda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Ilgari odamlar hamma joyda yurishgan. Hozirgi kunda ular avtomobillardan foydalanishadi.

example: To obtain is to get something you want or need.
type: After I passed the test, I obtained my driver’s license.
example_tr: Olish - bu o'zingiz xohlagan yoki kerakli narsani olishdir.
column14: Sinovdan o'tganimdan so'ng, men haydovchilik guvohnomasini oldim.

example: When something is religious, it has to do with religion.
type: The holy man spoke about religious topics.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa diniy bo'lsa, bu din bilan bog'liq.
column14: Muqaddas odam diniy mavzular haqida gapirdi.

example: When something is romantic, it has to do with love.
type: The young couple went to see a romantic movie.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa romantik bo'lsa, bu sevgi bilan bog'liq.
column14: Yosh juftlik romantik film tomosha qilish uchun borishdi.

example: A shell is a hard covering that protects the body of some sea creatures.
type: There were many pretty shells on the beach.
example_tr: Chig'anoq - bu ba'zi dengiz jonzotlarining tanasini himoya qiladigan qattiq qoplama.
column14: Sohilda juda ko'p chiroyli qobiqlar bor edi.

example: A shore is the edge of a large body of water.
type: All of the boats were floating near the shore.
example_tr: Sohil - bu katta suv havzasining chekkasi.
column14: Barcha qayiqlar qirg‘oqqa yaqin suzib yurardi.

example: A wheel is a round thing on a vehicle that turns when it moves.
type: A car has four wheels.
example_tr: G'ildirak - bu harakatlanayotganda aylanadigan transport vositasidagi dumaloq narsa.
column14: Mashinaning to'rtta g'ildiragi bor.

example: To appeal to someone is to be interesting or attractive to them.
type: Sleeping all day appeals to me, but I have to go to school.
example_tr: Biror kishiga murojaat qilish - ular uchun qiziqarli yoki jozibali bo'lish.
column14: Kun bo'yi uxlash menga yoqadi, lekin men maktabga borishim kerak.

example: To assume something is to think that it is true, even with no proof.
type: I assume you are both familiar with this plan.
example_tr: Biror narsani taxmin qilish - bu haqiqat deb o'ylash, hatto hech qanday dalilsiz ham.
column14: O'ylaymanki, siz ikkalangiz ham bu reja bilan tanishsiz.

example: To borrow something is to take it and then give it back later.
type: Can I borrow a pencil to use today? I'll give it back to you tomorrow.
example_tr: Biror narsani qarzga olish - uni olib, keyin qaytarib berish.
column14: Bugun ishlatish uchun qalam olsam bo'ladimi? Ertaga qaytarib beraman.

example: A client is a person or business that pays another to do a service.
type: She has many clients who enjoy coming to her salon.
example_tr: Mijoz - bu xizmat ko'rsatish uchun boshqasiga pul to'laydigan shaxs yoki korxona.
column14: Uning saloniga kelishni yoqtiradigan ko'plab mijozlari bor.

example: The downtown is the center of most cities.
type: The downtown is filled with many tall buildings.
example_tr: Shahar markazi ko'pchilik shaharlarning markazidir.
column14: Shahar markazi ko'plab baland binolar bilan to'ldirilgan.

example: If something is dull, it is not exciting.
type: The movie was very dull. I fell asleep watching it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa zerikarli bo'lsa, bu hayajonli emas.
column14: Kino juda zerikarli edi. Uni tomosha qilib uxlab qoldim.

example: To embarrass someone is to make them feel ashamed or foolish.
type: He was embarrassed when he couldn't remember her name.
example_tr: Biror kishini sharmanda qilish, uni uyaltirish yoki ahmoq qilishdir.
column14: Uning ismini eslay olmay, xijolat tortdi.

example: A fare is an amount of money paid to use a bus, train, or taxi.
type: Since he is a senior, my grandfather pays a low fare for the bus.
example_tr: Yo'l haqi - bu avtobus, poezd yoki taksidan foydalanish uchun to'lanadigan pul miqdori.
column14: Katta o‘quvchi bo‘lgani uchun bobom avtobusga arzon yo‘lkira to‘laydi.

example: Former describes something that used to be but is not any more.
type: The hotel, a former castle, was built over 200 years ago.
example_tr: Former ilgari bo'lgan, ammo endi yo'q narsani tasvirlaydi.
column14: Sobiq qal'a bo'lgan mehmonxona 200 yil oldin qurilgan.

example: A formula is a set mathematical way or method of solving a problem.
type: I learned a new formula that may help us with our problem.
example_tr: Formula - bu masalani hal qilishning matematik usuli yoki usuli.
column14: Muammoni hal qilishda bizga yordam beradigan yangi formulani o'rgandim.

example: To found a company or organization means to start it.
type: The pilgrims founded one of the first colonies in the United States.
example_tr: Korxona yoki tashkilotni tashkil etish uni boshlash demakdir.
column14: Ziyoratchilar Qo'shma Shtatlardagi birinchi koloniyalardan biriga asos solgan.

example: To invest means to use money in a way that will bring a profit later.
type: I invested money in a new building that should bring me a profit.
example_tr: Investitsiya qilish, pulni keyinchalik foyda keltiradigan tarzda ishlatishni anglatadi.
column14: Menga foyda keltirishi kerak bo'lgan yangi binoga pul tikdim.

example: A loan is the act of lending something, usually money.
type: I got a loan from the bank.
example_tr: Qarz - bu biror narsani, odatda pulni qarzga berish harakati.
column14: Men bankdan kredit oldim.

example: If something is practical, it is useful in normal life.
type: Learning English is practical; you can use it in many places.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa amaliy bo'lsa, u oddiy hayotda foydalidir.
column14: Ingliz tilini o'rganish amaliydir; uni ko'p joylarda ishlatishingiz mumkin.

example: A quarter is 25 cents.
type: He paid a quarter for the candy.
example_tr: Chorak 25 sent.
column14: U konfet uchun chorak to‘ladi.

example: A salary is how much money a person makes at his or her job.
type: He got a new job with a better salary.
example_tr: Ish haqi - bu odamning o'z ishida qancha pul topishi.
column14: U yaxshi maosh bilan yangi ishga joylashdi.

example: A scholarship is money given to one so they can go to school.
type: I got a scholarship to help me pay for university.
example_tr: Stipendiya - bu maktabga borishi uchun beriladigan pul.
column14: Universitetga pul to‘lashim uchun stipendiya oldim.

example: If something is temporary, it exists for a short time.
type: This car is only temporary; I'll get a new one soon.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa vaqtinchalik bo'lsa, u qisqa vaqt davomida mavjud.
column14: Bu mashina vaqtinchalik; Tez orada yangisini olaman.

example: A treasure is a collection of valuable things, especially jewels or gold.
type: They became very rich when they found the buried treasure.
example_tr: Xazina - bu qimmatbaho narsalar, ayniqsa, qimmatbaho toshlar yoki oltinlar to'plami.
column14: Ko‘milgan xazinani topib, juda boyib ketishdi.

example: To urge someone is to try very hard to get them to do something.
type: He urged them to believe his story.
example_tr: Biror kishini undash, uni biror narsa qilishga undash uchun juda ko'p harakat qilishdir.
column14: U ularni uning hikoyasiga ishonishga undadi.

example: To arise is to happen.
type: Difficulties arose with his computer because it was old.
example_tr: Ko'tarilish - sodir bo'lish.
column14: Uning kompyuteri eski bo'lgani uchun qiyinchiliklar paydo bo'ldi.

example: A benefactor is a person who gives money to help someone.
type: The student’s benefactor gave him money to spend on his studies.
example_tr: Xayr-ehson qiluvchi - kimgadir yordam berish uchun pul beradigan kishi.
column14: Talabaning xayrixohi unga o'qishga sarflash uchun pul berdi.

example: A blacksmith is a person who makes things out of metal.
type: The blacksmith pounded the piece of metal until it was flat.
example_tr: Temirchi - metalldan buyumlar yasaydigan odam.
column14: Temirchi temir parchasini tekis bo‘lguncha urdi.

example: When someone is charitable, they help people who are in need.
type: My sister was charitable enough to help me buy my first house.
example_tr: Kimdir xayriya qilsa, muhtojlarga yordam beradi.
column14: Opam birinchi uyimni sotib olishimga yordam beradigan darajada xayrixoh edi.

example: A chimney is a tall pipe used to carry smoke out of a building.
type: The cat was on the roof sitting next to the chimney.
example_tr: Baca - bu binodan tutun chiqarish uchun ishlatiladigan baland quvur.
column14: Mushuk uyingizda, mo'ri yonida o'tirgan edi.

example: To compensate is to pay someone for the time they spent doing something.
type: Her boss compensated her for the extra work she did last week.
example_tr: Kompensatsiya - bu kimgadir biror narsa qilish uchun sarflagan vaqti uchun to'lashdir.
column14: Uning xo'jayini unga o'tgan hafta qilgan qo'shimcha ishi uchun kompensatsiya berdi.

example: If you encounter something, you meet or come close to it.
type: I encountered a sea turtle while I was swimming.
example_tr: Agar biror narsaga duch kelsangiz, u bilan uchrashasiz yoki yaqinlashasiz.
column14: Men suzayotganimda dengiz toshbaqasiga duch keldim.

example: To exceed is to be more than something.
type: Since I exceeded my limit, I decided to get rid of my credit cards.
example_tr: Oshib ketish - biror narsadan ko'proq bo'lish.
column14: Limitdan oshib ketganim sababli, kredit kartalarimdan xalos bo'lishga qaror qildim.

example: To forge is to make or produce, especially with difficulty.
type: Stacy and Heather forged their friendship when they were teenagers.
example_tr: Soxta qilish - yasash yoki ishlab chiqarish, ayniqsa qiyinchilik bilan.
column14: Steysi va Xezer o'smirlik chog'larida do'stlikni mustahkamlagan.

example: People who are humble do not believe that they are better than other people.
type: Even though Bob is the smartest boy in his class, he is humble.
example_tr: Kamtar odamlar o'zlarining boshqa odamlardan yaxshiroq ekanligiga ishonmaydilar.
column14: Bob o'z sinfidagi eng aqlli bola bo'lsa ham, u kamtar.

example: Iron is a strong metal that is used to make many objects.
type: The horse had shoes made of iron.
example_tr: Temir kuchli metall bo'lib, u ko'plab narsalarni yasashda ishlatiladi.
column14: Otning temirdan yasalgan tuflisi bor edi.

example: A ladder is an object that is used to climb up and down things.
type: He used a ladder to climb to the top of his tree house.
example_tr: Narvon - bu narsalarni yuqoriga va pastga tushirish uchun ishlatiladigan ob'ekt.
column14: U daraxt uyining tepasiga chiqish uchun narvondan foydalangan.

example: If people are modest, they do not think that they are too important.
type: Derek is very modest for someone who is so rich.
example_tr: Agar odamlar kamtar bo'lsa, ular o'zlarini juda muhim deb hisoblamaydilar.
column14: Derek juda boy odam uchun juda kamtar.

example: To occupy a place is to live, work, or be there.
type: Kevin and Alice occupied the chairs and had a long discussion.
example_tr: Biror joyni egallash - yashash, ishlash yoki u erda bo'lish.
column14: Kevin va Elis stullarni egallab, uzoq muhokama qilishdi.

example: A penny is a coin worth one cent.
type: U.S. President Abraham Lincoln is on the penny.
example_tr: Bir tiyin - bu bir sentga teng tanga.
column14: AQSh prezidenti Avraam Linkoln tiyin ustida.

example: To preach is to talk about and promote a religious idea.
type: Aaron often preached about living an honest life.
example_tr: Va'z qilish - diniy g'oya haqida gapirish va targ'ib qilish.
column14: Horun tez-tez halol hayot kechirish haqida va'z qilar edi.

example: To prosper is to be successful or make a lot of money.
type: Frank's new business finally prospered after many years of hard work.
example_tr: Rivojlanish - muvaffaqiyatga erishish yoki ko'p pul topish.
column14: Frankning yangi biznesi ko'p yillik mashaqqatli mehnatdan so'ng nihoyat gullab-yashnadi.

example: A province is a small area that is controlled by a country.
type: Canada is divided into several different provinces.
example_tr: Viloyat - bu mamlakat tomonidan nazorat qilinadigan kichik hudud.
column14: Kanada bir nechta turli viloyatlarga bo'lingan.

example: Satisfaction is a feeling you get when you do or receive something good.
type: Brad was filled with satisfaction when he saw what was for dinner.
example_tr: Qoniqish - bu yaxshi narsa qilganingizda yoki olganingizda paydo bo'ladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Bred kechki ovqat uchun nima borligini ko'rib, mamnun bo'ldi.

example: To sustain something is to keep it going.
type: Wind power is a clean way to sustain a city with energy.
example_tr: Biror narsani ushlab turish - uni davom ettirishdir.
column14: Shamol energiyasi shaharni energiya bilan ta'minlashning toza usulidir.

example: To acquire something is to gain possession of it.
type: Tina acquired a strange package yesterday.
example_tr: Biror narsaga ega bo'lish - unga egalik qilish.
column14: Kecha Tina g'alati paketga ega bo'ldi.

example: If something is awkward, it is embarrassing and uncomfortable.
type: After dropping his coffee cup, Robbie felt awkward.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noqulay bo'lsa, u noqulay va noqulaydir.
column14: Kofe piyolasini tashlagach, Robbi o'zini noqulay his qildi.

example: A caretaker is a person who takes care of very young, old, or sick people.
type: My grandmother’s caretaker helps her get around the house.
example_tr: Qarovchi - juda yosh, qari yoki kasal odamlarga g'amxo'rlik qiladigan kishi.
column14: Buvimning vasiysi unga uy atrofida yurishga yordam beradi.

example: To deceive someone is to make them believe something that is not true.
type: He tried to deceive his friends as they were playing a game.
example_tr: Biror kishini aldash, uni noto'g'ri narsaga ishontirishdir.
column14: Do‘stlari o‘yin o‘ynayotgan paytda aldamoqchi bo‘lgan.

example: To discourage someone is to make them feel less excited about something.
type: Mr. Perry discouraged the students from quitting school.
example_tr: Biror kishini tushkunlikka tushirish, uni biror narsadan kamroq hayajonlantirishdir.
column14: Janob Perri o'quvchilarni maktabni tark etishdan qaytardi.

example: If something is fake, it is made to look real in order to trick people.
type: The model was wearing fake eyelashes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa soxta bo'lsa, u odamlarni aldash uchun haqiqiy ko'rinishga keltiriladi.
column14: Model soxta kirpik taqqan edi.

example: Hatred is a strong feeling of not liking someone or something.
type: I have a hatred for the taste of medicine.
example_tr: Nafrat - bu kimnidir yoki biror narsani yoqtirmaslikning kuchli hissi.
column14: Dori ta'miga nafratim bor.

example: A hut is a house made of wood, grass, or mud that has only one or two rooms.
type: We all went into the hut to sleep.
example_tr: Kulba - yog'ochdan, o'tdan yoki loydan yasalgan, faqat bir yoki ikkita xonasi bo'lgan uy.
column14: Hammamiz uxlash uchun kulbaga kirdik.

example: If something is inferior, it is not as good as something else.
type: Cars built a hundred years ago are inferior to ones built today.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa pastroq bo'lsa, u boshqa narsa kabi yaxshi emas.
column14: Yuz yil oldin ishlab chiqarilgan mashinalar bugungi kunda ishlab chiqarilgan mashinalardan pastroq.

example: A lodge is a house in the mountains, used by people who ms.
type: During our ski trip, we stayed at a lodge.
example_tr: Lodge - tog'lardagi uy, ms.
column14: Chang'i sayrimiz davomida biz lojada qoldik.

example: To neglect someone or something is to not take care of it properly.
type: William neglected his room, so it is a complete mess.
example_tr: Birovni yoki biror narsani e'tiborsiz qoldirish, unga to'g'ri g'amxo'rlik qilmaslikdir.
column14: Uilyam o'z xonasini e'tiborsiz qoldirdi, shuning uchun bu butunlay tartibsizlik.

example: A newcomer is a person who has recently arrived at a place or a group.
type: The students happily welcomed the newcomer to the school.
example_tr: Yangi kelgan - yaqinda biror joyga yoki guruhga kelgan odam.
column14: O‘quvchilar maktabga yangi kelganni xursandchilik bilan kutib olishdi.

example: An offense is behavior that is wrong or breaks a law.
type: Stealing a car is a very serious offense.
example_tr: Huquqbuzarlik - bu noto'g'ri yoki qonunni buzadigan xatti-harakatlar.
column14: Mashinani o'g'irlash juda jiddiy jinoyatdir.

example: To overlook something is to not notice it, or to not realize that it is important.
type: Brenda overlooked the last step and had a bad fall.
example_tr: Biror narsaga e'tibor bermaslik - uni sezmaslik yoki uning muhimligini tushunmaslik.
column14: Brenda oxirgi qadamni e'tiborsiz qoldirdi va yomon yiqildi.

example: To repay is to pay back or to reward someone or something.
type: She repaid her friend for all of his hard work with a small gift.
example_tr: Qaytarmoq - qaytarib berish yoki kimnidir yoki biror narsani mukofotlash.
column14: U dugonasining barcha mehnatini kichik sovg‘a bilan qaytardi.

example: If something is ridiculous, it is silly or strange.
type: Steve looked ridiculous with those huge blue sunglasses.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kulgili bo'lsa, u ahmoq yoki g'alati.
column14: Stiv o'sha ulkan ko'k ko'zoynak bilan kulgili ko'rinardi.

example: If something is satisfactory, it is good enough.
type: Mina often received satisfactory grades since she studied so hard.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qoniqarli bo'lsa, u etarli darajada yaxshi.
column14: Mina juda qattiq o'qiganligi sababli ko'pincha qoniqarli baholar oldi.

example: A shepherd is a person who protects and cares for sheep.
type: The shepherd moved the sheep to another field.
example_tr: Cho'pon - qo'ylarni qo'riqlaydigan va boqadigan odam.
column14: Cho‘pon qo‘ylarni boshqa dalaga ko‘chirdi.

example: To venture is to go to a place that may be dangerous.
type: Even though it was dangerous, they ventured up the mountain.
example_tr: Rivojlanish - xavfli bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan joyga borish.
column14: Bu xavfli bo'lsa ham, ular toqqa chiqishdi.

example: Wheat is a plant which makes grain. Wheat grain is used to make bread.
type: The field of golden wheat was ready to be harvested.
example_tr: Bug'doy - don hosil qiluvchi o'simlik. Bug'doy donidan non tayyorlash uchun foydalaniladi.
column14: Oltin bug‘doy dalasi o‘rim-yig‘imga shay edi.

example: An alley is a narrow road behind houses or buildings.
type: The alley behind my house looks dirty.
example_tr: Xiyobon - uylar yoki binolar ortidagi tor yo'l.
column14: Uyim orqasidagi xiyobon iflos ko'rinadi.

example: An axis a tool used to cut wood.
type: She used an ax to cut some wood for the fire.
example_tr: Eksa - yog'ochni kesish uchun ishlatiladigan asbob.
column14: U bolta bilan olovga o‘tin kesib tashladi.

example: A bunch is a group of the same things.
type: She was hungry, so she ate the entire bunch of grapes.
example_tr: To'da - bir xil narsalar guruhi.
column14: U och edi, shuning uchun u butun uzumni yedi.

example: A chore is a job that you have to do but don’t like.
type: It’s Nikki’s chore to do the dishes every Tuesday and Wednesday night.
example_tr: Uy vazifasi - bu siz qilishingiz kerak bo'lgan, lekin yoqtirmaydigan ish.
column14: Har seshanba va chorshanba oqshomida idish-tovoq yuvish Nikkining ishi.

example: When something is decent, it is OK or good enough.
type: Eric did a decent job painting the fence.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yaxshi bo'lsa, u yaxshi yoki etarlicha yaxshi.
column14: Erik devorni bo'yashda munosib ish qildi.

example: Disgrace is a feeling of shame.
type: He felt a sense of disgrace after failing his big exam.
example_tr: Sharmandalik - sharmandalik hissi.
column14: U katta imtihondan o‘ta olmaganidan keyin sharmandalikni his qildi.

example: The elbow is the middle part of a person’s arm that lets you bend it.
type: She pointed to her elbow to show me where she hurt herself.
example_tr: Tirsak odam qo'lining o'rta qismi bo'lib, uni egish imkonini beradi.
column14: U qayerga ozor berganini ko‘rsatish uchun tirsagini ko‘rsatdi.

example: When you are grateful for something, you are happy that it happened.
type: The girls were grateful to have a chance to spend time with their grandfather.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa uchun minnatdor bo'lsangiz, u sodir bo'lganidan xursand bo'lasiz.
column14: Qizlar bobosi bilan vaqt o'tkazish imkoniga ega bo'lganidan minnatdor edilar.

example: To irritate means to annoy someone.
type: She was irritated when her brother told her that he had lost her camera.
example_tr: G'azablantirmoq, kimnidir bezovta qilmoq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Akasi kamerasini yo‘qotib qo‘yganini aytganida, u g‘azablandi.

example: To kid is to make a joke to make someone believe something which is not true.
type: I am not really mad. I was kidding when I said I was angry.
example_tr: Kichkintoy - bu kimnidir noto'g'ri narsaga ishontirish uchun hazil qilish.
column14: Men haqiqatan ham jinni emasman. Jahlim chiqdi, deb hazillashdim.

example: When something is loose, it is not held in place well.
type: The bolt was loose, so I tightened it with the wrench.
example_tr: Biror narsa bo'shashganda, u joyida yaxshi ushlab turilmaydi.
column14: Bolt bo'sh edi, shuning uchun men uni kalit bilan mahkamladim.

example: To offend someone means to make them angry or upset.
type: They were both offended by what they had said to each other.
example_tr: Biror kishini xafa qilish, uni g'azablantirish yoki xafa qilish demakdir.
column14: Ikkalasi ham bir-birlariga aytgan gaplaridan ranjidilar.

example: When something happens overnight, it happens during the night.
type: The campers stayed in the tent overnight.
example_tr: Bir kechada biror narsa sodir bo'lganda, bu kechada sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Lagerchilar chodirda tunab qolishdi.

example: To persist means to keep doing something even when it is hard.
type: Even though the lesson was difficult, he persisted until he understood.
example_tr: Qat'iylik, qiyin bo'lsa ham, biror narsani qilishda davom etishni anglatadi.
column14: Dars og'ir bo'lsa ham, tushunib yetguncha turib oldi.

example: A pine is a type of tree that is tall and thin.
type: There were many beautiful pine trees in the forest.
example_tr: Qarag'ay - baland va ingichka daraxt turi.
column14: O'rmonda juda ko'p chiroyli qarag'ay daraxtlari bor edi.

example: A scar is a mark on the skin after a wound heals.
type: The monster had horrible scars on his cheek and forehead.
example_tr: Chandiq - bu yara bitgandan keyin teridagi iz.
column14: Yirtqich hayvonning yonoqlari va peshonasida dahshatli izlar bor edi.

example: A sensation is a feeling a person gets from their senses.
type: Mom got a painful sensation in her head from the loud noise.
example_tr: Sensatsiya - bu odamning his-tuyg'ularidan oladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Qattiq shovqindan onam boshida og'riqli his bor edi.

example: A sled is a small vehicle that you use on snow.
type: Marvin likes to ride his sled down the hill in winter.
example_tr: Chana - bu siz qorda ishlatadigan kichik transport vositasi.
column14: Marvin qishda chanada tepadan pastga tushishni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: To tease someone means to laugh at or make fun of them.
type: Jake teased Charlie because he was the new student.
example_tr: Biror kishini masxara qilish uning ustidan kulish yoki masxara qilish demakdir.
column14: Jeyk Charlini masxara qildi, chunki u yangi talaba edi.

example: A valentine is someone you love or admire with great affection.
type: Harry wanted Molly to be his valentine.
example_tr: Valentin - bu siz yaxshi ko'radigan yoki katta mehr bilan hayratga soladigan odam.
column14: Garri Molli uning sevgilisi bo'lishini xohlardi.

example: When a plant blooms, it makes flowers.
type: Roses look so pretty when they bloom.
example_tr: O'simlik gullaganda, u gullaydi.
column14: Atirgullar gullaganda juda chiroyli ko'rinadi.

example: If something is compact, it is smaller than normal.
type: A laptop computer is much more compact than a desktop model.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ixcham bo'lsa, u odatdagidan kichikroq.
column14: Noutbuk kompyuteri ish stoli modeliga qaraganda ancha ixchamroq.

example: A curl is a small piece of something with a round shape.
type: The colorful ribbons were bent into curls.
example_tr: Jingalak - bu yumaloq shaklga ega bo'lgan narsaning kichik qismi.
column14: Rangli lentalar jingalaklarga egilgan.

example: To decay is to be destroyed naturally.
type: The old wooden house was slowly decaying.
example_tr: Chirish tabiiy ravishda yo'q qilishdir.
column14: Qadimgi yog'och uy asta-sekin chiriyotgan edi.

example: Dessert is a sweet food that you eat after a meal.
type: Kayla wants ice cream for dessert.
example_tr: Shirinlik - bu ovqatdan keyin iste'mol qilinadigan shirin taom.
column14: Kayla shirinlik uchun muzqaymoq istaydi.

example: To dip something is to put part of it into a liquid for a short time.
type: Laurel dipped her strawberry into the chocolate.
example_tr: Biror narsani cho'mdirish - uning bir qismini suyuqlikka qisqa vaqtga qo'yish.
column14: Lorel qulupnayini shokoladga botirdi.

example: If something is distant, it is far away.
type: Michael could barely see the distant island.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa uzoqda bo'lsa, u uzoqda.
column14: Maykl uzoqdagi orolni zo'rg'a ko'rdi.

example: An eclipse is an occasion when the moon moves in front of the sun.
type: A complete eclipse of the sun is a very rare occurrence.
example_tr: Tutilish - oyning quyosh oldida harakatlanishiga olib keladigan hodisa.
column14: Quyoshning to'liq tutilishi juda kam uchraydigan hodisa.

example: A fairy is a small, magic creature with wings.
type: There are usually fairies in fantasy stories.
example_tr: Peri - qanotli kichik, sehrli mavjudot.
column14: Fantastik hikoyalarda odatda peri bor.

example: Grace is a quality of moving in a smooth, relaxed and attractive way.
type: The ballerina danced with grace.
example_tr: Grace - bu silliq, bo'shashgan va jozibali tarzda harakat qilish sifati.
column14: Balerina nafis raqsga tushdi.

example: Leisure is time when you do not have to do work.
type: Eve likes to listen to music in her leisure time.
example_tr: Bo'sh vaqt - bu ish bilan mashg'ul bo'lmagan vaqt.
column14: Momo Havo bo'sh vaqtlarida musiqa tinglashni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: Mankind is all of the world’s people.
type: All of mankind has to work to make this a better world.
example_tr: Insoniyat butun dunyo xalqidir.
column14: Butun insoniyat bu dunyoni yaxshiroq qilish uchun harakat qilishi kerak.

example: Passion is a very strong feeling of wanting to do something.
type: She had a passion for dancing.
example_tr: Ehtiros - biror narsa qilishni xohlashning juda kuchli tuyg'usi.
column14: Uning raqsga tushish ishtiyoqi bor edi.

example: A pillow is something that you put your head on when you sleep.
type: When I travel, I usually take along my favorite pillow.
example_tr: Yostiq - uxlayotganingizda boshingizni qo'yadigan narsa.
column14: Men sayohat qilganimda, odatda, o'zimning sevimli yostig'imni olaman.

example: A pulse is the beat of the heart.
type: The doctor checked the patient's pulse by feeling his wrist.
example_tr: Puls - yurak urishi.
column14: Shifokor bemorning bilagini paypaslab, yurak urishini tekshirdi.

example: To refresh someone is to make them feel less hot or tired.
type: The baby was refreshed after taking a cool bath.
example_tr: Biror kishini tetiklash, uni kamroq issiq yoki charchash his qilishdir.
column14: Kichkintoy salqin vannadan so'ng tetiklandi.

example: To sneeze is to suddenly blow air out of your nose and mouth.
type: He sneezed after smelling the flower.
example_tr: Hapşırma - to'satdan burun va og'izdan havo chiqarish.
column14: U gulni hidlagandan keyin aksirdi.

example: A spice is a flavor for food and drinks.
type: Two common spices found in many homes are salt and pepper.
example_tr: Ziravorlar ovqat va ichimliklar uchun lazzatdir.
column14: Ko'pgina uylarda uchraydigan ikkita umumiy ziravorlar tuz va qalampirdir.

example: To whistle is to make a sound by putting your lips together and blowing.
type: As he was listening to music, Daryl whistled.
example_tr: Hushtak chalish - lablarni birlashtirib, puflab ovoz chiqarish.
column14: Musiqa tinglayotganida, Daril hushtak chaldi.

example: Wool is the hair that a sheep has.
type: Grandma wants to use the blue wool to knit me a sweater.
example_tr: Jun - bu qo'yning sochlari.
column14: Buvim menga ko'k jundan kozok to'qish uchun ishlatmoqchi.

example: To acquaint is to get to know something or someone.
type: Nancy acquainted herself with the new computer.
example_tr: Tanishmoq - biror narsa yoki kimnidir bilish.
column14: Nensi yangi kompyuter bilan tanishdi.

example: A cemetery is where people are buried when they die.
type: Some people are scared of cemeteries.
example_tr: Qabriston - bu odamlar vafot etganida dafn qilinadigan joy.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar qabristonlardan qo'rqishadi.

example: To curse someone or something is to hope that bad things happen to them.
type: The witch cursed the village.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani la'natlash, unga yomon narsalar sodir bo'lishiga umid qilishdir.
column14: Jodugar qishloqni la'natladi.

example: A disguise is something you wear so people cannot tell who you are.
type: Everyone knew that it was Dad in the Santa disguise.
example_tr: Niqob - bu siz kiyadigan narsa, shuning uchun odamlar sizning kimligingizni ayta olmaydi.
column14: Bu Qorbobo niqobidagi dadam ekanligini hamma bilar edi.

example: If something is fancy, it is nicer than normal.
type: Their table was all set for a fancy dinner.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa chiroyli bo'lsa, u odatdagidan ko'ra yoqimli.
column14: Ularning dasturxoni chiroyli kechki ovqat uchun tayyorlandi.

example: A flashlight is a small electric light that you carry in your hand.
type: We took a flashlight when we went camping.
example_tr: Chiroq - bu sizning qo'lingizda olib yuradigan kichik elektr chiroq.
column14: Biz lagerga borganimizda chiroq oldik.

example: A hood is part of a coat that goes over your head.
type: She put on her hood to keep her head warm.
example_tr: Kaput - bu sizning boshingizdan o'tadigan paltoning bir qismi.
column14: U boshini isitmoq uchun kaputini kiydi.

example: An inhabitant is a person who lives in a certain place.
type: The number of inhabitants in the countryside is increasing.
example_tr: Aholi - bu ma'lum bir joyda yashovchi shaxs.
column14: Qishloqlarda aholi soni ortib bormoqda.

example: To nourish something is to give it food that it needs to live.
type: A good mother will nourish her baby every day.
example_tr: Biror narsani oziqlantirish - unga yashash uchun zarur bo'lgan oziq-ovqat berishdir.
column14: Yaxshi ona har kuni bolasini boqadi.

example: A pirate is a sailor who steals things from other boats.
type: Pirates are very scary characters.
example_tr: Qaroqchi - boshqa qayiqlardan narsalarni o'g'irlaydigan dengizchi.
column14: Qaroqchilar juda qo'rqinchli belgilar.

example: A publication is something printed, like a newspaper or book.
type: She’s been a subscriber to that publication for over ten years.
example_tr: Nashr gazeta yoki kitob kabi bosma narsadir.
column14: U o'n yildan ortiq vaqtdan beri ushbu nashrga obuna bo'lgan.

example: A riddle is a question that is difficult to answer but meant to be funny.
type: I could not answer Wendy’s riddle, but it made me laugh.
example_tr: Topishmoq - bu javob berish qiyin, ammo kulgili savol.
column14: Men Vendining topishmoqiga javob bera olmadim, lekin bu meni kuldirdi.

example: When something rots, it slowly gets softer and is destroyed.
type: The old log began to rot in the forest.
example_tr: Biror narsa chiriganida, u asta-sekin yumshoq bo'ladi va yo'q qilinadi.
column14: Qadimgi yog'och o'rmonda chiriy boshladi.

example: To scare means to cause one to feel frightened.
type: I was scared by the sight of the monster.
example_tr: Qo'rqitish, qo'rqitish degani.
column14: Yirtqich hayvonni ko‘rib qo‘rqib ketdim.

example: If something will happen shortly, it will happen very soon.
type: My workday will end shortly.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tez orada sodir bo'lsa, bu juda tez sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Mening ish kunim tez orada tugaydi.

example: A skeleton is the bones of a body.
type: There is a skeleton in the science classroom.
example_tr: Skelet - bu tananing suyaklari.
column14: Tabiatshunoslik sinfida skelet bor.

example: If something spoils, it turns bad or rots.
type: We left the fruit out too long, and it spoiled.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa buzilsa, u yomonlashadi yoki chiriydi.
column14: Biz mevani juda uzoq vaqt qoldirdik va u buzilib ketdi.

example: If a person starves, they do not get enough to eat and sometimes die.
type: During the war, many people starved.
example_tr: Agar odam och qolsa, u to'yib ovqatlanmaydi va ba'zida o'ladi.
column14: Urush paytida ko'p odamlar ochlikdan o'lishdi.

example: A thrill is an exciting feeling.
type: The boys enjoy the thrill of surfing a big wave.
example_tr: Hayajon - hayajonli tuyg'u.
column14: O'g'il bolalar katta to'lqinda sayr qilishdan zavqlanishadi.

example: If something is wicked, it is very bad or evil.
type: My boss is a very wicked man.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomon bo'lsa, u juda yomon yoki yomondir.
column14: Mening xo'jayinim juda yomon odam.

example: To alert someone is to tell or warn them about something.
type: The fire alarm alerted us that there was a problem.
example_tr: Biror kishini ogohlantirish - unga biror narsa haqida aytish yoki ogohlantirishdir.
column14: Yong'in signalizatsiyasi bizni muammo borligi haqida ogohlantirdi.

example: A broadcast is a television or radio show.
type: We watched the broadcast of the local news on TV.
example_tr: Efir - bu teleko'rsatuv yoki radio ko'rsatuvi.
column14: Televizorda mahalliy yangiliklar ko'rsatilishini tomosha qildik.

example: A bulletin is a news report that talks about very recent and important events.
type: There was a live bulletin reporting on the economy of the city.
example_tr: Byulleten - bu eng so'nggi va muhim voqealar haqida gapiradigan yangiliklar.
column14: Shahar iqtisodiyoti haqida jonli xabar tarqatildi.

example: A bump is a small raised area on a surface.
type: The monkey got a bump on his head because he was hit by a rock.
example_tr: To'qmoq - bu sirtdagi kichik ko'tarilgan joy.
column14: Maymun toshga urilgani uchun boshiga zarba bo‘ldi.

example: To chop something means to cut it into pieces with a tool.
type: Mom chopped some vegetables to put into the stew.
example_tr: Biror narsani maydalash, uni asbob bilan bo'laklarga bo'lish demakdir.
column14: Onam go'shtga qo'yish uchun bir nechta sabzavotlarni kesib tashladi.

example: A closet is a small room used to store things.
type: Marie has many clothes inside of her closet.
example_tr: Shkaf - bu narsalarni saqlash uchun ishlatiladigan kichik xona.
column14: Marining shkafida ko'plab kiyimlar bor.

example: To console someone who is sad means to make them comforted.
type: When my dog ran away, my dad consoled me.
example_tr: Xafa bo'lgan odamga tasalli berish, uni taskinlash demakdir.
column14: Itim qochib ketganida, dadam meni yupatdi.

example: A district is a small part of a city, county, state, or country.
type: I live in a residential district of Seattle, Washington.
example_tr: Tuman - bu shahar, tuman, shtat yoki mamlakatning kichik bir qismi.
column14: Men Vashington shtatining Sietl shahridagi turar-joy okrugida yashayman.

example: A drawer is a small part in furniture that is used to store things.
type: I put my clothes into the empty drawers.
example_tr: Sandiq - bu narsalarni saqlash uchun ishlatiladigan mebelning kichik qismi.
column14: Men kiyimlarimni bo'sh tortmalarga qo'ydim.

example: To endure something tough means to do or go through it.
type: She had to endure her husband shouting all day long.
example_tr: Qiyin narsaga chidash, uni bajarish yoki o'tishni anglatadi.
column14: Erining kun bo‘yi baqirishiga chidashiga to‘g‘ri keldi.

example: To execute someone means to kill them as a legal punishment.
type: Some people are executed for serious crimes.
example_tr: Biror kishini qatl qilish uni qonuniy jazo sifatida o'ldirishni anglatadi.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar og'ir jinoyatlar uchun qatl qilinadi.

example: To grasp something means to hold it.
type: He grasped the bag of money tightly.
example_tr: Biror narsani ushlash uni ushlab turishni anglatadi.
column14: U pul solingan qopni mahkam ushladi.

example: When something is in the rear of something, it is in the back.
type: The man loaded the rear of his truck with boxes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa biror narsaning orqasida bo'lsa, u orqada.
column14: Erkak yuk mashinasining orqa tomoniga qutilarni yuklagan.

example: A senator is someone who makes laws for a state.
type: The young senator promised to make laws that would help the people.
example_tr: Senator - bu shtat uchun qonunlar ishlab chiqaruvchi shaxs.
column14: Yosh senator xalqqa yordam beradigan qonunlar ishlab chiqishga va’da berdi.

example: A skull is the hard part of your head. Your brain is inside of it.
type: The brain is protected by the skull.
example_tr: Bosh suyagi boshingizning qattiq qismidir. Sizning miyangiz uning ichida.
column14: Miya bosh suyagi bilan himoyalangan.

example: To stir something means to mix it using something small, like a spoon.
type: Mom stirred the batter until it was smooth.
example_tr: Biror narsani aralashtirish, uni qoshiq kabi mayda narsa yordamida aralashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Onam xamirni silliq bo'lguncha aralashtirdi.

example: To tap something is to hit it lightly.
type: He tapped the keys of the keyboard to write a short word.
example_tr: Biror narsaga tegish - uni engil urish.
column14: U qisqa so‘z yozish uchun klaviatura tugmalarini bosdi.

example: When something is tremendous, it is very large.
type: The Earth’s oceans are filled with a tremendous amount of water.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa juda katta bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Yer okeanlari juda ko'p miqdorda suv bilan to'ldirilgan.

example: When something is underneath something else, it is below or lower than it.
type: The roots of a tree are located underneath the ground.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsa ostida bo'lsa, u undan past yoki pastroq bo'ladi.
column14: Daraxtning ildizlari yer ostida joylashgan.

example: A worm is a small animal with a long, thin body.
type: Worms are often used to help catch fish.
example_tr: Qurt - uzun, ingichka tanasi bo'lgan kichik hayvon.
column14: Ko'pincha qurtlar baliq ovlashga yordam berish uchun ishlatiladi.

example: To abandon something is to leave it forever or for a long time.
type: The old room had been abandoned years before.
example_tr: Biror narsadan voz kechish - uni abadiy yoki uzoq vaqt tark etish.
column14: Eski xona bir necha yillar oldin tashlab ketilgan edi.

example: If someone is ambitious, they want to be rich or successful.
type: Kendra had to be ambitious to get into medical school.
example_tr: Agar kimdir shuhratparast bo'lsa, u boy yoki muvaffaqiyatli bo'lishni xohlaydi.
column14: Kendra tibbiyot maktabiga kirish uchun shuhratparast bo'lishi kerak edi.

example: When a dog barks, it makes a short, loud noise.
type: The dog barked loudly and frighteningly.
example_tr: It hurganda, u qisqa, baland ovoz chiqaradi.
column14: It baland ovozda va qo'rqinchli qichqirdi.

example: A bay is an area near the ocean where the land goes inward.
type: The Golden Gate Bridge crosses San Francisco Bay.
example_tr: Ko'rfaz - okean yaqinidagi quruqlik ichkariga kiradigan hudud.
column14: Oltin darvoza ko'prigi San-Fransisko ko'rfazini kesib o'tadi.

example: If someone is brilliant, they are very smart.
type: My younger sister is brilliant for someone her age.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ajoyib bo'lsa, u juda aqlli.
column14: Mening singlim o'z yoshidagi odam uchun ajoyib.

example: Your chin is the hard part at the bottom of your face.
type: Luke pointed to the hair on his chin.
example_tr: Sizning iyagingiz yuzingizning pastki qismidagi qattiq qismdir.
column14: Luqo iyagidagi sochlarga ishora qildi.

example: A complaint is something you say to tell people that you don’t like something.
type: Mom said she didn’t want to hear my brother's complaints.
example_tr: Shikoyat - bu odamlarga sizga biror narsa yoqmasligini aytish uchun aytadigan narsadir.
column14: Onam akamning shikoyatlarini eshitishni istamasligini aytdi.

example: When someone is deaf, they cannot hear.
type: Susan was born deaf.
example_tr: Agar kimdir kar bo'lsa, u eshitmaydi.
column14: Syuzan kar bo'lib tug'ilgan.

example: To be enthusiastic about something is to be excited by or interested in it.
type: The man was enthusiastic about his job.
example_tr: Biror narsaga ishtiyoq bilan munosabatda bo'lish - bu narsadan hayajonlanish yoki unga qiziqish.
column14: Erkak o'z ishiga ishtiyoq bilan yondashardi.

example: An expedition is a long trip, usually to a place very far away.
type: They got into their spaceship to begin their expedition.
example_tr: Ekspeditsiya - bu uzoq safar, odatda juda uzoq joyga.
column14: Ular ekspeditsiyani boshlash uchun o'zlarining kosmik kemasiga tushishdi.

example: The horizon is where the sky looks like it meets the ground.
type: The sun dipped below the horizon.
example_tr: Ufq - bu osmon yer bilan uchrashganday ko'rinadigan joy.
column14: Quyosh ufqdan pastga tushdi.

example: To be loyal to something or someone is to agree to always help them.
type: The three friends are very loyal to each other.
example_tr: Biror narsaga yoki kimgadir sodiq bo'lish, ularga doimo yordam berishga rozi bo'lishdir.
column14: Uch do'st bir-biriga juda sodiq.

example: The mayor is the person in charge of a city.
type: The mayor of my hometown is quite a powerful speaker.
example_tr: Shahar hokimi - bu shaharni boshqaradigan shaxs.
column14: Mening ona shahrimning meri juda kuchli notiq.

example: If something is mutual, it is felt in the same way by two or more people.
type: Robert likes Sarah. The feeling is mutual.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'zaro bo'lsa, uni ikki yoki undan ortiq kishi bir xil tarzda his qiladi.
column14: Robert Sarani yaxshi ko'radi. Tuyg'u o'zaro.

example: If someone is overweight, they are very fat.
type: Roger eats too much, so now he’s overweight.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ortiqcha vaznga ega bo'lsa, u juda semiz.
column14: Rojer juda ko'p ovqat eydi, shuning uchun endi u ortiqcha vaznga ega.

example: A refuge is a place where you go to be safe.
type: When it started to rain, she found refuge in the house.
example_tr: Boshpana - bu xavfsiz bo'lish uchun boradigan joy.
column14: Yomg'ir yog'a boshlaganda, u uyda panoh topdi.

example: To restore something is to put it back the way it was.
type: Victor restored the old car.
example_tr: Biror narsani qayta tiklash, uni avvalgi holatiga qaytarishdir.
column14: Viktor eski mashinani tikladi.

example: To rub something is to push on it and move your hand back and forth.
type: Mom’s feet were sore, so she rubbed them.
example_tr: Biror narsani ishqalash, uni surish va qo'lni oldinga va orqaga siljitishdir.
column14: Onamning oyoqlari og'riydi, shuning uchun u ularni ishqaladi.

example: Your senses are how you see, taste, hear, feel and smell.
type: lt would be hard to live without your five senses.
example_tr: Sizning his-tuyg'ularingiz - bu qanday ko'rish, ta'mlash, eshitish, his qilish va hidlash.
column14: Beshta sezgisiz yashash qiyin.

example: A veterinarian is a doctor that takes care of animals.
type: Wanda became a veterinarian because she loves dogs.
example_tr: Veterinar - bu hayvonlarga g'amxo'rlik qiladigan shifokor.
column14: Wanda veterinar bo'ldi, chunki u itlarni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: An anniversary is a day that celebrates something from the past.
type: My parents went out to eat for their wedding anniversary.
example_tr: Yubiley - bu o'tmishdagi narsalarni nishonlaydigan kun.
column14: Ota-onam to'ylarining yubileyiga ovqatlanish uchun ketishdi.

example: Arithmetic is math.
type: I like to study arithmetic at school.
example_tr: Arifmetika bu matematika.
column14: Men maktabda arifmetikani o'rganishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: To be ashamed is to feel upset because you did something wrong or bad.
type: He was ashamed when he found out that I knew about his past.
example_tr: Uyalish - noto'g'ri yoki yomon ish qilganingiz uchun xafa bo'lishdir.
column14: Uning o‘tmishi haqida bilishimni bilgach, uyalib ketdi.

example: To burst is to suddenly break open or apart.
type: The bomb burst over the city.
example_tr: Portlash - to'satdan ochilib ketish yoki parchalanish.
column14: Bomba shahar ustida portladi.

example: A carpenter is a person who builds things with wood.
type: We hired a carpenter to make a cupboard.
example_tr: Duradgor - yog'ochdan narsa yasaydigan odam.
column14: Shkaf yasash uchun duradgor yolladik.

example: Coal is a hard black rock that you burn for heat.
type: Many power stations burn coal to produce energy.
example_tr: Ko'mir - bu qattiq qora tosh, siz uni issiqlik uchun yoqasiz.
column14: Ko'pgina elektr stantsiyalari energiya ishlab chiqarish uchun ko'mir yoqadi.

example: A couch is a long, soft seat that many people can sit on.
type: Kim and Martin’s new couch was very expensive.
example_tr: Divan - ko'p odamlar o'tirishi mumkin bo'lgan uzun va yumshoq o'rindiq.
column14: Kim va Martinning yangi divanlari juda qimmat edi.

example: When a liquid drips, just a little bit falls at a time.
type: I heard water dripping from the faucet.
example_tr: Suyuqlik tomizganda, bir vaqtning o'zida ozgina tushadi.
column14: Men jo‘mrakdan suv oqayotganini eshitdim.

example: If something is elegant, it is very fancy and pleasing.
type: In Japan, women wear elegant kimonos on special occasions.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oqlangan bo'lsa, u juda chiroyli va yoqimli.
column14: Yaponiyada ayollar maxsus bayramlarda nafis kimono kiyishadi.

example: Fabric is cloth used to make clothes, furniture, etc.
type: The towels were made from a soft fabric.
example_tr: Mato - kiyim-kechak, mebel va boshqalarni tayyorlash uchun ishlatiladigan mato.
column14: Sochiqlar yumshoq matodan qilingan.

example: The highlands are high areas of land, usually with mountains.
type: The man had a small home in the highlands.
example_tr: Togʻlar baland erlar, odatda togʻlardir.
column14: Bu odamning baland tog'da kichkina uyi bor edi.

example: Ivory is a white, hard substance that comes from elephants.
type: The elephant’s long ivory tusks looked very impressive.
example_tr: Fil suyagi - fillardan olingan oq, qattiq modda.
column14: Filning uzun fil suyagi tishlari juda ta'sirli ko'rinardi.

example: A mill is a building where flour is made.
type: The farmer took his wheat to the mill to make it into flour.
example_tr: Tegirmon — un tayyorlanadigan bino.
column14: Dehqon bug‘doyini un qilish uchun tegirmonga olib bordi.

example: A needle is a small, sharp piece of metal that you use to make or fix clothes.
type: I used a needle to fix the hole in my pants.
example_tr: Igna - bu kiyim yasash yoki tuzatish uchun ishlatiladigan kichik, o'tkir metall buyum.
column14: Men shimimdagi teshikni igna bilan mahkamladim.

example: To polish something is to rub it in order to make it shiny.
type: Mark spent all morning polishing his shoes for the wedding.
example_tr: Biror narsani jilo qilish, uni porlashi uchun uni ishqalashdir.
column14: Mark ertalab to'y uchun poyabzalini silliqlash bilan o'tkazdi.

example: To sew means to put pieces of cloth together using string.
type: I learned to sew when I was a little girl.
example_tr: Tikish - mato bo'laklarini ip yordamida birlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkinaligimda tikuvchilikni o‘rganganman.

example: A shed is a small building where you store things like tools.
type: We have a small shed in the backyard for storage.
example_tr: Saroy - bu asboblar kabi narsalarni saqlaydigan kichik bino.
column14: Bizda saqlash uchun hovlida kichik shiypon bor.

example: A thread is a thin piece of string.
type: I have many different colors of thread at home.
example_tr: Ip - bu ingichka ip bo'lagi.
column14: Uyda turli rangdagi iplar bor.

example: To trim something is to cut it a little bit.
type: I had my hair trimmed this afternoon.
example_tr: Biror narsani kesish - uni biroz kesish.
column14: Bugun tushdan keyin sochimni qirqib oldim.

example: If something goes upwards, it moves vertically higher.
type: The kite went upwards further and further.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yuqoriga ko'tarilsa, u vertikal ravishda yuqoriga ko'tariladi.
column14: Uçurtma yana va yana yuqoriga ko'tarildi.

example: To ail a person or group is to cause difficulty or pain.
type: My brother went to the doctor to see what was ailing him.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki guruhni xastalash qiyinchilik yoki og'riq keltirishdir.
column14: Akam uni nima qiynalayotganini bilish uchun shifokorga bordi.

example: An ally is someone who agrees to help or support you.
type: I was happy to find many allies who shared the same opinion as me.
example_tr: Ittifoqchi - bu sizga yordam berishga yoki qo'llab-quvvatlashga rozi bo'lgan kishi.
column14: Men bilan bir xil fikrda bo'lgan ko'plab ittifoqchilarni topganimdan xursand bo'ldim.

example: To boast is to talk about how good you are.
type: We all became tired of listening to him boast about himself all day.
example_tr: Maqtanish - bu sizning qanchalik yaxshi ekanligingiz haqida gapirish.
column14: Biz hammamiz uning kun bo'yi o'zi haqida maqtanishini tinglashdan charchadik.

example: To bounce is to move something up and away from a surface after hitting it.
type: Owen bounced the ball on the ground.
example_tr: Sakrash - biror narsani urgandan keyin sirtdan yuqoriga va uzoqqa siljitish.
column14: Ouen to'pni yerga tepdi.

example: A bully is a person who is mean to others.
type: The two bullies always picked on the smaller, weaker kids.
example_tr: Bezori - bu boshqalarga yomon munosabatda bo'lgan odam.
column14: Ikki bezori har doim kichikroq, zaifroq bolalarni tanladi.

example: Carbohydrates are substances in foods like bread that give you energy.
type: Carbohydrates like rice are a good source of energy for active people.
example_tr: Uglevodlar - bu non kabi oziq-ovqat tarkibidagi moddalar bo'lib, sizga energiya beradi.
column14: Guruch kabi uglevodlar faol odamlar uchun yaxshi energiya manbai hisoblanadi.

example: To crawl is to move slowly on your hands and knees.
type: The baby crawled across the floor.
example_tr: Emaklash - qo'llar va tizzalar ustida sekin harakat qilishdir.
column14: Chaqaloq polga sudralib ketdi.

example: To defeat someone is to beat them in a game or battle.
type: The champion defeated the challenger in the boxing match.
