example_tr: Biror kishini mag'lub qilish - uni o'yin yoki jangda mag'lub etish.
column14: Chempion boks bahsida raqibni mag'lub etdi.

example: A dial is the front of a clock.
type: I looked at the dial to see what time it was.
example_tr: Terma soatning old qismidir.
column14: Men soat necha ekanligini bilish uchun siferblataga qaradim.

example: When someone or something is dominant, they are stronger than others.
type: The gorilla is one of the dominant animals in the jungle.
example_tr: Kimdir yoki biror narsa ustun bo'lsa, ular boshqalardan kuchliroqdir.
column14: Gorilla o'rmonda hukmron hayvonlardan biridir.

example: If you show mercy, you choose not to punish or harm someone.
type: He asked his boss for mercy and to not fire him.
example_tr: Agar siz rahm-shafqat ko'rsatsangiz, siz kimnidir jazolamaslik yoki zarar bermaslikni tanlaysiz.
column14: U xo'jayinidan rahm-shafqat so'radi va uni ishdan bo'shatmaslikni so'radi.

example: To nod is to move your head up and down.
type: I nodded my head as I listened to the song.
example_tr: Bosh qimirlatish - boshingizni yuqoriga va pastga siljitish.
column14: Qo‘shiqni tinglab boshimni qimirlatib qo‘ydim.

example: An opponent is someone who fights against you.
type: On the field, our opponents were too good for us.
example_tr: Raqib - bu sizga qarshi kurashadigan odam.
column14: Maydonda raqiblarimiz biz uchun juda yaxshi edi.

example: To quarrel is to argue or fight.
type: Billy quarreled with his wife about buying a new house.
example_tr: Janjallashish - bahslashish yoki urishish.
column14: Billi xotini bilan yangi uy sotib olish haqida janjallashdi.

example: A rival is someone that is trying to keep you from getting what you want.
type: The three rivals were all competing for the same job.
example_tr: Raqib - bu siz xohlagan narsangizga erishishingizga xalaqit beradigan odam.
column14: Uch raqib bir xil ish uchun kurashayotgan edi.

example: When a part of your body is sore, it hurts.
type: After lifting the heavy box, Mona’s back was sore.
example_tr: Agar tanangizning bir qismi og'rigan bo'lsa, u og'riyapti.
column14: Og'ir qutini ko'targandan so'ng, Monaning orqasi og'riydi.

example: To sting is to cause pain by pushing a sharp part into the skin.
type: The needle stung my arm and made me say, “Ouch!”
example_tr: Tishlash - teriga o'tkir qismni surish orqali og'riq keltirish.
column14: Igna qo‘limga sanchidi va “Ouh!” deyishga majbur qildi.

example: To strain is to try very hard.
type: Casey strained to lift the heavy box.
example_tr: Zo'rlash - juda qattiq harakat qilish.
column14: Keysi og'ir qutini ko'tarmoqchi bo'ldi.

example: Torture is something that causes you physical or mental pain.
type: Greg thought that writing the essay was torture.
example_tr: Qiynoqlar sizga jismoniy yoki ruhiy og'riq keltiradigan narsadir.
column14: Greg insho yozishni qiynoq deb o'yladi.

example: To wrestle is to play a game where you try to push someone to the floor.
type: My dad loved to wrestle when he was in high school.
example_tr: Kurash - bu kimnidir erga itarib yuborishga harakat qiladigan o'yin o'ynash.
column14: Dadam maktabda o‘qib yurganlarida kurashni yaxshi ko‘rardi.

example: Absence is the state of something being away.
type: There is an absence of sand in the hourglass.
example_tr: Yo'qlik - biror narsaning uzoqda bo'lgan holati.
column14: Qum soatida qum yo'q.

example: If you say something aloud, you say it so that others can hear you.
type: My father often reads stories aloud to me and my sister.
example_tr: Biror narsani baland ovozda aytsangiz, boshqalar sizni eshitishi uchun aytasiz.
column14: Dadam menga va singlimga tez-tez ovoz chiqarib hikoyalar o'qib beradi.

example: If someone is bald, they have no hair.
type: My oldest brother is bald.
example_tr: Agar kimdir kal bo'lsa, unda sochlari yo'q.
column14: Mening eng katta akam kal.

example: A blanket is a piece of cloth that you use to keep warm or to sit upon.
type: I laid a blanket on the ground so that we could have a picnic.
example_tr: Adyol - bu siz isinish yoki o'tirish uchun ishlatiladigan mato.
column14: Piknik qilaylik deb yerga ko‘rpacha yotqizdim.

example: To creep is to move quietly and slowly.
type: The cat slowly crept down the tree.
example_tr: O'rmalash - jim va sekin harakat qilish.
column14: Mushuk asta-sekin daraxtdan pastga tushdi.

example: Divorce is an event in which a marriage is ended.
type: Divorce rates have increased in the past twenty years.
example_tr: Ajralish - bu nikoh tugagan voqea.
column14: So'nggi yigirma yil ichida ajralishlar ko'paydi.

example: To imitate someone is to do exactly what they do.
type: He imitated his favorite superhero by putting on a costume.
example_tr: Biror kishiga taqlid qilish, ular qilgan ishni qilishdir.
column14: U kostyum kiyib, sevimli superqahramoniga taqlid qildi.

example: An infant is a baby.
type: The infant cried all night.
example_tr: Chaqaloq - bu chaqaloq.
column14: Kichkintoy tun bo'yi yig'ladi.

example: To kidnap someone is to take them illegally.
type: She was terrified to find out her son was kidnapped.
example_tr: Biror kishini o'g'irlash - uni noqonuniy ravishda olish.
column14: U o'g'lining o'g'irlab ketilganini bilib qo'rqib ketdi.

example: A nap is a short sleep, usually during the day.
type: I took a short nap because I stayed up late last night.
example_tr: Uyqu - bu qisqa uyqu, odatda kun davomida.
column14: Kecha kechgacha uxlab qolganim uchun qisqa uxladim.

example: You use nowhere to say that a place or thing does not exist.
type: Unfortunately, water was nowhere to be found.
example_tr: Siz biror joy yoki narsa mavjud emas deb aytish uchun hech qanday joydan foydalanmaysiz.
column14: Afsuski, suv hech qaerda yo'q edi.

example: To pat something is to hit it softly with your hand.
type: I patted some lotion onto my face.
example_tr: Biror narsani silash - uni qo'l bilan yumshoq urish.
column14: Men yuzimda loson kutdim.

example: Relief is a feeling you get when something bad or challenging ends.
type: I felt a sense of relief when I heard the good news.
example_tr: Yengillik - bu yomon yoki qiyin narsa tugaganda paydo bo'ladigan tuyg'u.
column14: Xushxabarni eshitib, o‘zimni yengil his qildim.

example: To reproduce is to make something exactly how someone else did it.
type: The children tried to reproduce their house using toy blocks.
example_tr: Qayta ishlab chiqarish - biror narsani boshqa birov qilganidek qilishdir.
column14: Bolalar o'yinchoq bloklari yordamida uylarini ko'paytirishga harakat qilishdi.

example: To rhyme is to have the same sounds at the end of a word.
type: Humpty Dumpty is an old rhyme that children learn in school.
example_tr: Qofiyalash - so‘z oxirida bir xil tovushlarning bo‘lishi.
column14: Humpty Dumpty - bu bolalar maktabda o'rganadigan eski qofiya.

example: To suck is to put something in your mouth and try to get flavor out of it.
type: The baby sucked milk from her bottle.
example_tr: So'rish - og'zingizga biror narsa solib, undan lazzat olishga harakat qilishdir.
column14: Chaqaloq shishasidan sut emdi.

example: If something is urgent, it is important and needs to be done now.
type: He had to leave now; it was urgent.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa shoshilinch bo'lsa, u muhim va hozir qilish kerak.
column14: U hozir ketishi kerak edi; shoshilinch edi.

example: To vanish is to go away suddenly.
type: All the passengers vanished from the train station.
example_tr: G'oyib bo'lish - to'satdan ketish.
column14: Barcha yo‘lovchilar vokzaldan g‘oyib bo‘lishdi.

example: A wagon is a cart you use to carry heavy things.
type: He used his wagon to carry some of his gifts.
example_tr: Vagon - bu og'ir narsalarni tashish uchun ishlatiladigan arava.
column14: Sovg'alarining bir qismini olib yurish uchun aravasidan foydalangan.

example: A wrinkle is a line on a person’s face that happens as they get old.
type: My grandfather has some wrinkles on his face.
example_tr: Ajin - bu odamning yuzidagi chiziq, u qariganda paydo bo'ladi.
column14: Bobomning yuzida ajinlar bor.

example: If something is abnormal, it is strange or not normal.
type: Her idea of art is a bit too abnormal for me.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'ayritabiiy bo'lsa, u g'alati yoki normal emas.
column14: Uning san'at haqidagi g'oyasi men uchun biroz g'ayritabiiy.

example: Bamboo is a hard plant with thin branches and leaves.
type: Outside his home, there is a lot of bamboo.
example_tr: Bambuk - ingichka shoxlari va barglari bo'lgan qattiq o'simlik.
column14: Uning uyi tashqarisida juda ko'p bambuk bor.

example: A blossom is a flower or group of flowers.
type: There were colorful blossoms in the yard.
example_tr: Gul - bu gul yoki gullar guruhi.
column14: Hovlida rang-barang gullar bor edi.

example: A compass is a device used to tell what direction one is going.
type: A compass is an important tool to have when you are traveling.
example_tr: Kompas - bu odam qaysi yo'nalishda ketayotganini aniqlash uchun ishlatiladigan qurilma.
column14: Kompas sayohat paytida bo'lishi kerak bo'lgan muhim vositadir.

example: A dialect is a regional variety of language showing where you are from.
type: People from the U.K. have a different dialect of English from those in the
example_tr: Dialekt - bu sizning qayerdan ekanligingizni ko'rsatadigan mintaqaviy tildir.
column14: Buyuk Britaniyadan kelgan odamlar ingliz tilidagi lahjalardan farq qiladi

example: If someone is dishonest, they do not tell the truth.
type: She was being dishonest when she copied the answers from his test.
example_tr: Agar kimdir insofsiz bo'lsa, u haqiqatni aytmaydi.
column14: Uning testidan javoblarni ko'chirib olganida, u insofsiz edi.

example: A dwarf is a creature from stories that often looks like a short, hairy man.
type: The dwarf had a pleasant look on his face.
example_tr: Mitti - bu ko'pincha qisqa, tukli odamga o'xshab ketadigan hikoyalardan jonzot.
column14: Mittining yuzida yoqimli ko'rinish bor edi.

example: An ecosystem is a group of plants and animals in an area.
type: The river's ecosystem not only includes fish but other insects and plants
example_tr: Ekotizim - bu hududdagi o'simliklar va hayvonlar guruhi.
column14: Daryoning ekotizimiga nafaqat baliq, balki boshqa hasharotlar va o'simliklar kiradi

example: If something is fatal, it causes death.
type: They passed away in a fatal car crash.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa halokatli bo'lsa, u o'limga olib keladi.
column14: Ular halokatli avtohalokatda vafot etdilar.

example: If someone is impatient, they are not able to wait for things.
type: Bob was so impatient that he could barely wait for the light turn green.
example_tr: Agar kimdir sabrsiz bo'lsa, u narsalarni kutishga qodir emas.
column14: Bob shunchalik sabrsiz ediki, u chiroqning yashil yonishini zo'rg'a kutardi.

example: A leaf is the flat green thing on trees or bushes.
type: In the fall, the leaves on the trees change colors.
example_tr: Barg - bu daraxtlar yoki butalar ustidagi tekis yashil narsa.
column14: Kuzda daraxtlardagi barglar ranglarini o'zgartiradi.

example: A manuscript is an old book or paper written by hand.
type: The manuscript was written over 150 years ago.
example_tr: Qo'lyozma - bu qo'lda yozilgan eski kitob yoki qog'oz.
column14: Qo'lyozma 150 yil oldin yozilgan.

example: A marsh is a type of wet land covered with grasses and short plants.
type: The marsh looked so lovely against the mountains.
example_tr: Botqoq - o'tlar va kalta o'simliklar bilan qoplangan nam erning bir turi.
column14: Botqoq tog'larga nisbatan juda yoqimli ko'rinardi.

example: Patience is the ability to wait for something without becoming upset.
type: Sue’s patience was rewarded by catching her very first fish.
example_tr: Sabr - biror narsani xafa qilmasdan kutish qobiliyatidir.
column14: Suening sabr-toqati birinchi baliqni tutish bilan taqdirlandi.

example: Perfume is a good-smelling liquid that girls wear.
type: When she wore her perfume, everyone said she smelled great.
example_tr: Parfyum - bu qizlar kiyadigan xushbo'y suyuqlik.
column14: U o'zining atirini surganida, hamma uning hidi ajoyib ekanini aytdi.

example: A pond is a very small area of water.
type: The ducks swam in the pond.
example_tr: Hovuz - bu juda kichik suv maydoni.
column14: O'rdaklar hovuzda suzishdi.

example: A proverb is a short saying that tells you something important.
type: The proverb “egg on your face” means you've done something embarrassing.
example_tr: Maqol - bu muhim narsani aytadigan qisqa so'z.
column14: “Yuzingda tuxum” degan maqol sen sharmandali ish qilganingni anglatadi.

example: A pursuit is a chase.
type: The dinosaur was in pursuit of the caveman.
example_tr: Ta'qib qilish - ta'qib qilish.
column14: Dinozavr g'or odamini ta'qib qilgan.

example: To recite something means to repeat or say aloud in front of a group.
type: Katie recited the Pledge of Allegiance in class.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'qish, bir guruh oldida takrorlash yoki ovoz chiqarib aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Keti sinfda “Sodiqlik qasamyodi”ni o‘qib berdi.

example: A wilderness is an area where no people live.
type: If you are not careful, you can get lost in the wilderness.
example_tr: Cho'l - bu odamlar yashamaydigan hudud.
column14: Ehtiyot bo'lmasangiz, cho'lda adashib qolishingiz mumkin.

example: To anticipate something is to think that it will happen.
type: Carrie anticipated the arrival of her baby.
example_tr: Biror narsani oldindan bilish - bu sodir bo'lishini o'ylash.
column14: Kerri chaqalog'ining kelishini kutdi.

example: A barrel is a round thing that you can keep liquids in.
type: There was an empty barrel outside the house.
example_tr: Bochka - bu suyuqliklarni saqlashingiz mumkin bo'lgan yumaloq narsa.
column14: Uyning tashqarisida bo'sh bochka bor edi.

example: A beam is a heavy bar.
type: Modern skyscrapers are made with several beams.
example_tr: Nur - bu og'ir bar.
column14: Zamonaviy osmono'par binolar bir nechta nurlardan iborat.

example: If something is casual, it is relaxed or simple.
type: You can wear casual clothes to the party like jeans.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tasodifiy bo'lsa, u xotirjam yoki oddiy.
column14: Bayramga jinsi shimlar kabi kundalik kiyim kiyishingiz mumkin.

example: Caution is care and attention in order to avoid danger.
type: Please use the power saw with caution. It is very dangerous.
example_tr: Ehtiyotkorlik - xavfni oldini olish uchun ehtiyotkorlik va e'tibor.
column14: Ehtiyotkorlik bilan elektr arra foydalaning. Bu juda xavfli.

example: If something is contrary to something else, it is the opposite.
type: It isn’t warm outside at all. On the contrary, it is quite cold.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsaga zid bo'lsa, buning aksi.
column14: Tashqarida umuman issiq emas. Aksincha, juda sovuq.

example: If you are deliberate, you do something on purpose.
type: Bernie made a deliberate attempt to injure Andy.
example_tr: Agar qasddan bo'lsangiz, ataylab biror narsa qilasiz.
column14: Berni qasddan Endiga jarohat yetkazishga urindi.

example: To dissolve something is to mix it into a liquid and disappear.
type: I dissolved the pill in a glass of water.
example_tr: Biror narsani eritish - uni suyuqlikka aralashtirib, yo'q bo'lib ketish.
column14: Men tabletkani bir stakan suvda eritib yubordim.

example: When something explodes, it blows up.
type: My new radio exploded when I plugged it in.
example_tr: Biror narsa portlasa, u portlaydi.
column14: Yangi radioim rozetkaga ulanganda portlab ketdi.

example: To fasten something is to close it or put it in the correct place.
type: Elizabeth fastened her seat belt.
example_tr: Biror narsani mahkamlash - uni yopish yoki to'g'ri joyga qo'yish.
column14: Elizabet xavfsizlik kamarini bog'ladi.

example: A germ is something that makes you sick.
type: Germs are on everything that you touch.
example_tr: Mikrob - bu sizni kasal qiladigan narsa.
column14: Mikroblar siz tegadigan hamma narsada.

example: A kit is a set of all the things needed to do something.
type: Is there a first aid kit in your office?
example_tr: To'plam - bu biror narsa qilish uchun zarur bo'lgan barcha narsalar to'plami.
column14: Ofisingizda birinchi yordam to'plami bormi?

example: A puff is a little bit of smoke or steam.
type: A puff of smoke came from the burnt match.
example_tr: Puf - bu ozgina tutun yoki bug '.
column14: Kuygan gugurtdan bir puflab tutun chiqdi.

example: A rag is a small towel.
type: Please use a rag to clean the dust off the table.
example_tr: Bir latta kichkina sochiqdir.
column14: Iltimos, stol ustidagi changni tozalash uchun lattadan foydalaning.

example: To scatter something is to make it go in many places.
type: I accidentally scattered all of my pills.
example_tr: Biror narsani sochish - uni ko'p joyga olib borish.
column14: Men tasodifan barcha tabletkalarimni sochdim.

example: A scent is a smell.
type: Julie enjoyed the scent of the flowers.
example_tr: Xushbo'y hid - bu hid.
column14: Julia gullarning hididan zavqlanardi.

example: Steel is a shiny gray metal.
type: The new apartment building was made with steel.
example_tr: Po'lat - yaltiroq kulrang metall.
column14: Yangi turar-joy binosi temirdan yasalgan.

example: If something is swift, it is fast.
type: The swift horse easily jumped over the hurdle.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tez bo'lsa, u tezdir.
column14: Tez ot to‘siqdan osongina sakrab o‘tdi.

example: If you toss something, you throw it softly.
type: He tossed a coin into the air.
example_tr: Agar biror narsani tashlasangiz, uni ohista tashlaysiz.
column14: U tangani havoga uloqtirdi.

example: Triumph is what you feel when you win or finish something.
type: He raised the award in triumph at the end of his speech.
example_tr: G'alaba - bu siz g'alaba qozonganingizda yoki biror narsani tugatganingizda his qiladigan narsadir.
column14: U o'z so'zining oxirida mukofotni tantanali ravishda ko'tardi.

example: When someone is aboard a ship or plane, they are on or in it.
type: They climbed aboard the kayak and paddled through the river.
example_tr: Kimdir kema yoki samolyot bortida bo'lsa, unda yoki uning ichida.
column14: Ular baydarkaga chiqib, daryo bo'ylab sayr qilishdi.

example: When a person is bitter, they are upset with someone or a situation.
type: He was extremely bitter when his computer crashed.
example_tr: Biror kishi achchiq bo'lsa, u kimdandir yoki vaziyatdan xafa bo'ladi.
column14: Kompyuteri ishdan chiqqanida u juda xafa edi.

example: A bullet is a small metal object that is shot out of guns.
type: Bullets come in different sizes for different guns.
example_tr: O'q - quroldan otilgan kichik metall buyum.
column14: O'qlar turli xil qurollar uchun turli o'lchamlarda bo'ladi.

example: The devil is a powerful evil spirit in some religions.
type: The church promised protection from the devil.
example_tr: Iblis ba'zi dinlarda kuchli yovuz ruhdir.
column14: Jamoat shaytondan himoya qilishni va'da qildi.

example: To drift means to be moved slowly by wind or water.
type: The large chunk of ice drifted in the water.
example_tr: Drift - shamol yoki suv bilan sekin harakatlanishni anglatadi.
column14: Katta muz bo'lagi suvda suzdi.

example: To enforce means to make a person follow a rule.
type: Police enforce traffic laws to keep everyone safe.
example_tr: Amalga oshirish, odamni qoidaga rioya qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Politsiya barchaning xavfsizligini ta'minlash uchun yo'l harakati qoidalariga rioya qiladi.

example: A fountain is a source of water made by people.
type: There was a beautiful fountain in the middle of the park.
example_tr: Favvora - bu odamlar tomonidan yaratilgan suv manbai.
column14: Bog'ning o'rtasida chiroyli favvora bor edi.

example: A harbor is an area of water along a shore where boats land.
type: There were a few small boats in the harbor.
example_tr: Port - bu qayiqlar qo'nadigan qirg'oq bo'ylab joylashgan suv maydoni.
column14: Portda bir nechta kichik qayiqlar bor edi.

example: To inhabit means to live in a certain place.
type: No one inhabits the ancient city.
example_tr: Yashash ma'lum bir joyda yashashni anglatadi.
column14: Qadimgi shaharda hech kim yashamaydi.

example: To march means to walk at a steady pace together with others.
type: The soldiers marched in straight rows.
example_tr: Yurish, boshqalar bilan birga bir maromda yurish demakdir.
column14: Askarlar to‘g‘ri saf tortdilar.

example: A millionaire is a person who has at least a million dollars.
type: He became a millionaire because he was smart with his money.
example_tr: Millioner - bu kamida million dollarga ega bo'lgan odam.
column14: U millionerga aylandi, chunki u pul bilan aqlli edi.

example: A port is a place where ships stop to load and unload things.
type: The ship was being loaded with materials at the port.
example_tr: Port - bu kemalar narsalarni yuklash va tushirish uchun to'xtaydigan joy.
column14: Portda kemaga materiallar yuklanayotgan edi.

example: A sheriff is a police officer who is in charge of a large area.
type: It was the sheriff's job to make the city safe.
example_tr: Sherif - bu katta hududni boshqaradigan politsiyachi.
column14: Shaharni xavfsiz holatga keltirish sherifning vazifasi edi.

example: To startle means to scare someone suddenly.
type: The loud crash startled the sleeping woman.
example_tr: Qo'rqitish, birdaniga birovni qo'rqitish demakdir.
column14: Qattiq zarba uxlab yotgan ayolni cho'chitib yubordi.

example: To sweat means to lose liquid from the body through the skin.
type: Whenever I workout, I sweat quite a bit.
example_tr: Terlash teri orqali tanadan suyuqlikni yo'qotish demakdir.
column14: Qachonki men mashq qilsam, men juda terlayman.

example: A trigger is the part of the gun that a person pulls to make it fire.
type: The man had his finger on the trigger of the gun.
example_tr: Tetik - bu qurolning odam o't ochish uchun tortib oladigan qismi.
column14: Erkak barmog'i bilan qurol tetigida edi.

example: To unify means to bring people or things together.
type: With their good deeds, the children tried to unify the world.
example_tr: Birlashtirish odamlarni yoki narsalarni birlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Bolalar o'zlarining xayrli ishlari bilan dunyoni birlashtirishga harakat qilishdi.

example: A vessel is a large ship or boat.
type: We toured the area aboard a luxury vessel.
example_tr: Kema - bu katta kema yoki qayiq.
column14: Biz hashamatli kemada hududni aylanib chiqdik.

example: A voyage is a long journey made on a boat or an aircraft.
type: The astronauts took off on a long voyage to the moon.
example_tr: Sayohat - qayiqda yoki samolyotda qilingan uzoq sayohat.
column14: Kosmonavtlar Oyga uzoq safarga chiqishdi.

example: To worship means to like and honor a person, thing, or religious figure.
type: Many people around the world worship in a church.
example_tr: Ibodat qilish inson, narsa yoki diniy shaxsni yoqtirish va hurmat qilish demakdir.
column14: Dunyo bo'ylab ko'p odamlar cherkovda ibodat qilishadi.

example: An apprentice is a person who learns how to do a job from a skilled person.
type: Mark is an apprentice chef at the restaurant.
example_tr: Shogird - bu ishni malakali odamdan o'rganadigan odam.
column14: Mark restoranda oshpaz shogirdi.

example: To assure someone is to tell them something is true to make them less worried.
type: He assured the boss that the building would be done on time.
example_tr: Biror kishini ishontirish - bu ularni kamroq tashvishga solishi uchun ularga haqiqat ekanligini aytishdir.
column14: U boshliqni binoning o‘z vaqtida bajarilishiga ishontirdi.

example: A bandage is a piece of cloth used to stop bleeding.
type: If you cut yourself, please get a bandage from the first-aid kit.
example_tr: Bandaj - qon ketishini to'xtatish uchun ishlatiladigan mato.
column14: Agar siz o'zingizni kessangiz, birinchi tibbiy yordam to'plamidan bandaj oling.

example: To bleed is to lose blood.
type: If you are not careful, you will cut your finger and bleed.
example_tr: Qon ketish - qon yo'qotish.
column14: Ehtiyot bo'lmasangiz, barmog'ingizni kesib, qon ketasiz.

example: To bond with someone is to become friends with them.
type: The women bonded after several hours of conversation.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan bog'lanish - u bilan do'stlashishdir.
column14: Ayollar bir necha soatlik suhbatdan so'ng bog'lanishdi.

example: A chef is a person who cooks in a restaurant.
type: Tom is a chef at the restaurant near my house.
example_tr: Oshpaz - bu restoranda ovqat pishiradigan odam.
column14: Tom mening uyim yaqinidagi restoranda oshpaz.

example: A crown is the hat worn by a king or queen.
type: The crown is made of gold.
example_tr: Toj - qirol yoki malika kiyadigan shlyapa.
column14: Toj oltindan yasalgan.

example: A departure is the act of leaving a place.
type: They were excited about their departure back home.
example_tr: Ketish - bu joyni tark etish harakati.
column14: Ular uyga qaytishlaridan hayajonlanishdi.

example: If someone is diligent, they work hard and are careful.
type: Craig has always been a very diligent person at work.
example_tr: Agar kimdir tirishqoq bo'lsa, u qattiq ishlaydi va ehtiyotkor bo'ladi.
column14: Kreyg har doim ishda juda tirishqoq odam bo'lgan.

example: An emperor is the leader of a group of countries.
type: The emperor Julius Caesar was in control of ancient Rome.
example_tr: Imperator - bir guruh mamlakatlarning rahbari.
column14: Qadimgi Rimni imperator Yuliy Tsezar boshqargan.

example: Fiber is a thread of a substance used to make clothes or rope.
type: The mat was made from tiny fibers.
example_tr: Elyaf - bu kiyim yoki arqon yasash uchun ishlatiladigan moddaning ipidir.
column14: Mato mayda tolalardan qilingan.

example: If something is horrible, it is very bad.
type: The assignment was horrible. I hated it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, bu juda yomon.
column14: Topshiriq dahshatli edi. Men buni yomon ko'rardim.

example: If someone is impolite, they are rude.
type: Roger is impolite to everyone he meets.
example_tr: Agar kimdir odobsiz bo'lsa, u qo'poldir.
column14: Rojer uchragan har bir kishiga nisbatan odobsiz.

example: To kneel is to put one or both knees on the ground.
type: Daryl got down on one knee and asked Nina to marry him.
example_tr: Tiz cho'kish - bir yoki ikkala tizzani erga qo'yish.
column14: Daril bir tiz cho'kib Ninadan unga turmushga chiqishni so'radi.

example: A luxury is an expensive thing that you do not need.
type: We stayed at a luxury resort for our honeymoon.
example_tr: Hashamat - bu sizga kerak bo'lmagan qimmat narsa.
column14: Biz asal oyimiz uchun hashamatli kurortda qoldik.

example: If something is massive, it is very big.
type: The wheels on his truck were massive.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa massiv bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Uning yuk mashinasining g'ildiraklari katta edi.

example: To panic is to feel so nervous or afraid that you cannot think clearly.
type: Everyone panicked when the house caught on fire.
example_tr: Vahima - bu shunchalik asabiylashish yoki qo'rqish, siz aniq o'ylay olmaysiz.
column14: Uy yonib ketganda hamma vahimaga tushdi.

example: A priority is something that is more important than other things.
type: My priority is to get good grades in school.
example_tr: Ustuvorlik - bu boshqa narsalarga qaraganda muhimroq narsa.
column14: Mening ustuvor vazifam maktabda yaxshi baho olishdir.

example: A robe is a long, loose piece of clothing.
type: Many people wear robes in the morning.
example_tr: Libos - uzun, bo'sh kiyim.
column14: Ko'p odamlar ertalab xalat kiyishadi.

example: To scold means to criticize one angrily because they have done wrong.
type: Jesse was scolded by the teacher for not paying attention.
example_tr: Tanashish, yomon ish qilgani uchun jahl bilan tanqid qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Jessi e'tibor bermagani uchun o'qituvchi tomonidan tanbeh qilindi.

example: An affair is an event or a thing that happened.
type: My wife and I attended a formal affair over the weekend.
example_tr: Ish - bu sodir bo'lgan voqea yoki narsa.
column14: Xotinim va men dam olish kunlari rasmiy uchrashuvda qatnashdik.

example: An assembly is a group that is together for the same reason.
type: The students had an assembly to talk about their interests.
example_tr: Assambleya - bu bir xil sababga ko'ra birga bo'lgan guruh.
column14: Talabalar o'zlarining qiziqishlari haqida suhbatlashdilar.

example: To bless is to ask God for protection or help.
type: The angel blessed the newborn baby to keep it safe.
example_tr: Baraka berish Xudodan himoya yoki yordam so'rashdir.
column14: Farishta yangi tug'ilgan chaqaloqni xavfsiz saqlash uchun duo qildi.

example: Cereal is a food that you mix with milk and eat for breakfast.
type: Cereal is a fast and common breakfast food enjoyed in the U.S.
example_tr: Don - bu sut bilan aralashtirib, nonushta qilish uchun iste'mol qilinadigan taom.
column14: Don AQShda tez va keng tarqalgan nonushta taomidir.

example: If someone is cheerful, they are happy or feel good.
type: The children were cheerful because they didn’t have to go to school.
example_tr: Agar kimdir quvnoq bo'lsa, u baxtli yoki o'zini yaxshi his qiladi.
column14: Bolalar quvnoq edilar, chunki ular maktabga borishlari shart emas edi.

example: The diameter of a round thing is the length across its center.
type: The diameter of the tree was about 22 centimeters.
example_tr: Dumaloq narsaning diametri uning markazidagi uzunlikdir.
column14: Daraxtning diametri taxminan 22 santimetr edi.

example: To exploit something is to use it for greedy reasons rather than good reasons.
type: The company exploits their workers and makes them stay 12 hours a day.
example_tr: Biror narsani ekspluatatsiya qilish, uni yaxshi sabablarga ko'ra emas, balki ochko'zlik uchun ishlatishdir.
column14: Kompaniya o'z ishchilarini ekspluatatsiya qiladi va ularni kuniga 12 soat qolishga majbur qiladi.

example: A famine is a long time with little or no food.
type: The farmers couldn’t grow any food on the dry soil, so there was a famine.
example_tr: Ochlik - bu oz yoki umuman oziq-ovqatsiz uzoq vaqt.
column14: Dehqonlar quruq tuproqda oziq-ovqat yetishtira olmadilar, shuning uchun ocharchilik boshlandi.

example: A harvest is the act of collecting food from farming.
type: They had a lot of wheat from the last harvest.
example_tr: Hosil - bu dehqonchilikdan oziq-ovqat yig'ish harakati.
column14: Ularda so‘nggi o‘rim-yig‘imdan ko‘p bug‘doy bor edi.

example: If someone is merry, they are very happy.
type: They felt merry because the weather was great.
example_tr: Agar kimdir quvnoq bo'lsa, u juda xursand bo'ladi.
column14: Ular quvnoq edilar, chunki ob-havo ajoyib edi.

example: A nut is a hard seed or fruit that comes from some trees and bushes.
type: To eat a nut, first you have to crack its shell.
example_tr: Yong'oq - bu ba'zi daraxtlar va butalardan olinadigan qattiq urug' yoki meva.
column14: Yong'oqni iste'mol qilish uchun avval uning qobig'ini sindirish kerak.

example: To pardon is a way to ask someone to repeat what was said before.
type: Pardon me teacher, but could you repeat what you just said?
example_tr: Kechirim - bu kimdandir ilgari aytilgan gaplarni takrorlashni so'rashning bir usuli.
column14: Kechirasiz, domla, lekin siz aytgan gaplaringizni takrorlay olasizmi?

example: A pharaoh was a king in ancient Egypt.
type: The pharaohs ruled Egypt for thousands of years.
example_tr: Fir'avn qadimgi Misrda shoh bo'lgan.
column14: Fir'avnlar Misrni ming yillar davomida boshqargan.

example: When a fruit is ripe, it is ready to be eaten.
type: The cherries were nice and ripe.
example_tr: Meva pishganida, u iste'mol qilishga tayyor bo'ladi.
column14: Gilos yaxshi va pishgan edi.

example: To roast something is to cook it in an oven or over a fire.
type: Mom roasted a turkey for the holiday dinner.
example_tr: Biror narsani qovurish - uni pechda yoki olovda pishirish.
column14: Onam bayramona kechki ovqat uchun kurka qovurdi.

example: A routine is a way of doing things that is the same every time.
type: My father’s daily routine includes shaving right before breakfast.
example_tr: Rutin - bu har doim bir xil bo'lgan narsalarni qilish usuli.
column14: Otamning kundalik tartibi nonushta oldidan soqol olishdan iborat.

example: A scheme is a plan or design.
type: Mickey and Minnie came up with a scheme to solve the problem.
example_tr: Sxema - bu reja yoki dizayn.
column14: Mikki va Minni muammoni hal qilish uchun sxemani o'ylab topishdi.

example: If something or someone is slim, they are thin.
type: Look at my new cell phone. It’s very slim.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir nozik bo'lsa, ular ingichka.
column14: Mening yangi mobil telefonimga qarang. Bu juda nozik.

example: A stove is a device used to cook food.
type: Our new stove helps us to cook food much faster than before.
example_tr: Pechka - ovqat pishirish uchun ishlatiladigan asbob.
column14: Bizning yangi pechimiz ovqatni avvalgidan ko'ra tezroq pishirishga yordam beradi.

example: A theft is a criminal act that involves someone stealing something.
type: The theft of his TV took place when he was at work.
example_tr: O'g'irlik - bu kimdir biror narsani o'g'irlash bilan bog'liq jinoiy harakat.
column14: Uning televizori o‘g‘irlanishi ishda bo‘lganida sodir bo‘lgan.

example: An adolescent is a young person or a teenager.
type: The adolescent was excited about getting a skateboard for his birthday.
example_tr: O'smir - bu yosh yoki o'smir.
column14: O'smir tug'ilgan kuni uchun skeytbord olishni juda hayajonga soldi.

example: Aptitude is a natural ability or skill.
type: He has a natural aptitude for water skiing.
example_tr: Qobiliyat - bu tabiiy qobiliyat yoki mahorat.
column14: Uning suv chang'isiga tabiiy qobiliyati bor.

example: To compliment is to say a nice thing about someone or something.
type: Her co-worker complimented her for doing a good job.
example_tr: Kompliment - bu kimgadir yoki biror narsaga yaxshi so'z aytish.
column14: Hamkasbi uni yaxshi ish qilgani uchun maqtadi.

example: To hinder is to keep someone or something from doing something.
type: All the traffic hindered me from getting to work on time.
example_tr: To‘sqinlik qilmoq, kimnidir yoki biror narsani biror narsa qilishdan qaytarishdir.
column14: Ishga o'z vaqtida borishimga barcha tirbandlik xalaqit berdi.

example: Journalism is the work of gathering the news to put in newspapers or on television.
type: Before becoming a teacher, she worked in journalism.
example_tr: Jurnalistika - bu gazeta yoki televideniega joylashtirish uchun yangiliklarni yig'ish ishi.
column14: O'qituvchi bo'lgunga qadar u jurnalistika sohasida ishlagan.

example: A jury is a group of people that listen to a trial and say if someone is guilty or not guilty.
type: The jury listened closely to the attorney before they made their decision.
example_tr: Hakamlar hay'ati - bu sud jarayonini tinglaydigan va kimdir aybdor yoki aybsizligini aytadigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Hakamlar hay'ati qaror qabul qilishdan oldin advokatni diqqat bilan tingladi.

example: Justice is faimess in the way that you treat other people.
type: People turn to the court system when they are seeking justice.
example_tr: Adolat - bu boshqalarga qanday munosabatda bo'lganingizda adolatdir.
column14: Odamlar adolat izlaganlarida sud tizimiga murojaat qilishadi.

example: Liberty is freedom to do what you want.
type: To many people, the Statue of Liberty is a symbol of freedom.
example_tr: Erkinlik - bu o'zingiz xohlagan narsani qilish erkinligi.
column14: Ko'pchilik uchun Ozodlik haykali ozodlik ramzidir.

example: If someone or something is literary, it is involved with literature in some way.
type: He worked hard fo create a successful literary career.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa adabiy bo'lsa, u qaysidir ma'noda adabiyot bilan bog'liq.
column14: Muvaffaqiyatli adabiy ijod yaratish uchun ko'p mehnat qildi.

example: A pharmacy is a place where medicine is sold.
type: My mother sells medicine to people at the pharmacy.
example_tr: Dorixona - dori sotiladigan joy.
column14: Onam dorixonada odamlarga dori sotadi.

example: A pill is a small object that has medicine inside.
type: She took a pill for her headache.
example_tr: Tabletka - bu ichida dori bo'lgan kichik narsa.
column14: U bosh og'rig'i uchun tabletka oldi.

example: To presume is to believe something is true without being certain.
type: Since he raised his hand, the teacher presumed he knew the answer.
example_tr: Taxmin qilish - biror narsaning to'g'riligiga ishonchsiz ishonishdir.
column14: U qo'lini ko'targani uchun o'qituvchi javobni biladi deb o'yladi.

example: To have privacy is to be away from other people.
type: Please hang the sign on the door so we can have some privacy.
example_tr: Shaxsiy hayotga ega bo'lish - bu boshqa odamlardan uzoqlashishdir.
column14: Iltimos, shaxsiy hayotimizni saqlab qolishimiz uchun belgini eshikka osib qo'ying.

example: A punishment is something that one must endure for any wrongdoing.
type: He was given a punishment for being rude to the teacher.
example_tr: Jazo - bu har qanday noto'g'ri ish uchun chidashi kerak bo'lgan narsa.
column14: U o'qituvchiga qo'pollik qilgani uchun jazolangan.

example: If someone is sensible, they make good decisions.
type: It was sensible for her to save some money each month.
example_tr: Agar kimdir aqlli bo'lsa, u to'g'ri qaror qabul qiladi.
column14: Uning uchun har oy bir oz pul tejash oqilona edi.

example: A slice is a piece from something larger, such as a cake.
type: The girl enjoyed a slice of cake at her birthday party.
example_tr: Dilim kattaroq narsaning bo'lagi, masalan, tort.
column14: Qiz o'zining tug'ilgan kunida bir bo'lak tortdan zavq oldi.

example: Sorrow is a very sad feeling.
type: The girl felt sorrow after her best friend moved away.
example_tr: Qayg'u - bu juda qayg'uli tuyg'u.
column14: Qiz eng yaqin do'sti ko'chib ketganidan keyin qayg'u chekdi.

example: A straw is a thin tube that is used to suck liquid into the mouth.
type: I drank the orange juice through a straw.
example_tr: Somon - suyuqlikni og'izga so'rish uchun ishlatiladigan ingichka naycha.
column14: Men apelsin sharbatini somon orqali ichdim.

example: To swell is to become larger and rounder.
type: My sister’s stomach began to swell after she got pregnant.
example_tr: Shishish - kattaroq va yumaloq bo'lish.
column14: Opamning qorni homilador bo'lganidan keyin shishib keta boshladi.

example: When something is tidy, it is clean and in order.
type: Leon has always been a very tidy boy.
example_tr: Biror narsa tartibli bo'lsa, u toza va tartibli bo'ladi.
column14: Leon har doim juda ozoda bola bo'lgan.

example: Affection is a feeling of liking someone or something.
type: Amanda has a lot of affection for her little sister Sarah.
example_tr: Mehribonlik - bu kimgadir yoki biror narsani yoqtirish hissi.
column14: Amanda singlisi Saraga juda mehr bilan qaraydi.

example: An agency is a business or service set up to act for others.
type: I went to a travel agency to help me arrange a flight home.
example_tr: Agentlik - bu boshqalar uchun harakat qilish uchun tashkil etilgan biznes yoki xizmat.
column14: Men uyga parvozni tashkil qilishda yordam berish uchun sayyohlik agentligiga bordim.

example: Ash is the grey or black powder created when something is burned.
type: The end of his cigar was full of ashes.
example_tr: Kul - biror narsa yondirilganda hosil bo'lgan kulrang yoki qora kukun.
column14: Sigaretining uchi kulga to‘la edi.

example: To confine something is to keep it in one place.
type: The elephant is confined to a cage in the zoo.
example_tr: Biror narsani cheklash - uni bir joyda saqlash.
column14: Fil hayvonot bog'idagi qafasga qamalgan.

example: To dismiss something is to say it is not important.
type: He quickly dismissed my idea about a new project.
example_tr: Biror narsani rad qilish - bu muhim emasligini aytish.
column14: U tezda yangi loyiha haqidagi fikrimni rad etdi.

example: To erupt is for a volcano or something to shoot a hot substance.
type: The volcano erupted for the first time in ten years.
example_tr: Otilish - bu vulqon yoki biror narsa issiq moddani otishdir.
column14: Vulqon o‘n yil ichida birinchi marta otildi.

example: Fate is a power that causes some things to happen.
type: Some people believe that a person’s hand can tell their fate.
example_tr: Taqdir - bu ba'zi narsalarni yuzaga keltiradigan kuch.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar, insonning qo'li taqdirini aytib berishi mumkinligiga ishonishadi.

example: Lava is the hot substance made of melted rock that shoots from volcanoes.
type: The red hot lava poured from the volcano.
example_tr: Lava - vulqonlardan otiladigan erigan toshdan yasalgan issiq modda.
column14: Vulqondan qizil issiq lava quyildi.

example: If someone is miserable, they are very unhappy.
type: He was miserable after his dog died.
example_tr: Agar kimdir baxtsiz bo'lsa, u juda baxtsizdir.
column14: Iti o'lganidan keyin u baxtsiz edi.

example: To navigate something is to control the way it moves or goes.
type: She navigated the ship across the ocean.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshqarish - uning harakatini yoki borishini boshqarish.
column14: U kemada okean bo'ylab harakat qildi.

example: To originate somewhere is to start there.
type: The idea of democracy originated in Ancient Greece.
example_tr: Biror joyda paydo bo'lish - u erdan boshlash.
column14: Demokratiya g'oyasi Qadimgi Yunonistonda paydo bo'lgan.

example: The remainder of something is what is left.
type: He took a bite of the apple, then gave me the remainder of it.
example_tr: Biror narsaning qolgan qismi qolgan narsadir.
column14: U olmadan bir tishlab oldi, keyin qolganini menga berdi.

example: To retrieve something is to find it and get it back.
type: She retrieved her mail from the mail box.
example_tr: Biror narsani olish - uni topish va qaytarib olish.
column14: U pochta qutisidan xatini oldi.

example: If something is shallow, it is not deep.
type: The kids were playing in the shallow water.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sayoz bo'lsa, u chuqur emas.
column14: Bolalar sayoz suvda o'ynashardi.

example: A slope is ground that is not flat.
type: The slope to the top of the mountain was very steep.
example_tr: Nishab - bu tekis bo'lmagan zamin.
column14: Tog‘ cho‘qqisiga qiyalik juda tik edi.

example: To span a length of time is to last that long.
type: His work began in 1999. It has spanned many years since then.
example_tr: Uzoq vaqt davom etish - bu uzoq davom etishdir.
column14: Uning ishi 1999 yilda boshlangan. O'shandan beri ko'p yillar davom etdi.

example: A superstition is something magical that people believe is real.
type: It is a superstition that Friday the 13th is an unlucky day.
example_tr: Xurofot - bu odamlar haqiqat deb ishonadigan sehrli narsa.
column14: 13-juma kuni omadsiz kun degan xurofot bor.

example: Sympathy is a feeling of being sad for another person.
type: I felt sympathy for my sister so I got her a balloon to cheer her up.
example_tr: Hamdardlik - bu boshqa odamga xafa bo'lish hissi.
column14: Men singlimga hamdard bo'lib, uning kayfiyatini ko'tarish uchun unga shar olib berdim.

example: To vibrate is to shake very hard.
type: The machine made his whole body vibrate as he broke up the ground.
example_tr: Tebranish - juda qattiq silkitish.
column14: Mashina uning butun vujudini titratdi, u yerni sindirdi.

example: To wander is to walk without going to a certain place.
type: The boys like to wander in the woods and look at birds.
example_tr: Sayohat qilish - ma'lum bir joyga bormasdan yurish.
column14: O'g'il bolalar o'rmonda sayr qilishni va qushlarga qarashni yaxshi ko'radilar.

example: Armor is metal worn by soldiers to protect the body.
type: The soldier wore armor to protect his body.
example_tr: Zirh - bu askarlar tanani himoya qilish uchun kiyiladigan metall.
column14: Askar tanasini himoya qilish uchun zirh kiygan.

example: To blaze means to burn brightly or powerfully.
type: The small fire soon blazed into a large dangerous one.
example_tr: Yonish, yorqin yoki kuchli yonishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkina olov tez orada katta xavfli olovga aylandi.

example: To boom means to make a loud, deep sound.
type: The firecrackers made a loud boom when they exploded.
example_tr: Bum - baland, chuqur ovoz chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Petardalar portlaganda kuchli shovqin chiqardi.

example: A cliff is a high and often flat wall of rock.
type: The wolf stood at the cliff and howled.
example_tr: Qoya - bu baland va ko'pincha tekis tosh devori.
column14: Bo'ri qoyaning yonida turib, qichqirdi.

example: A flame is part of fire.
type: The torch was filled with yellow and orange flames.
example_tr: Olov olovning bir qismidir.
column14: Mash'al sariq va to'q sariq olov bilan to'ldirilgan edi.

example: Independence is the state of being free from the control of others.
type: After leaving home, Sophia had a great feeling of independence.
example_tr: Mustaqillik - bu boshqalarning nazoratidan ozod bo'lish holati.
column14: Uydan chiqqandan so'ng, Sofiya ajoyib mustaqillik tuyg'usiga ega edi.

example: An invasion is an attack by a group from another country.
type: In Korea, walls were built around cities to protect them from invasions.
example_tr: Bosqinchilik - bu boshqa davlatdan kelgan guruhning hujumi.
column14: Koreyada shaharlarni bosqinlardan himoya qilish uchun atrofiga devorlar qurilgan.

example: A knight is a soldier of high rank and skill who usually serves a king.
type: He was the best soldier, so the king made him a knight.
example_tr: Ritsar - odatda qirolga xizmat qiladigan yuqori martaba va mahoratli askar.
column14: U eng yaxshi askar edi, shuning uchun podshoh uni ritsar qildi.

example: Lightning is the bright light seen during a storm.
type: The lightning flashed above the water.
example_tr: Chaqmoq - bu bo'ron paytida ko'rinadigan yorqin yorug'lik.
column14: Suv ustida chaqmoq chaqdi.

example: A rebel is a person who fights the government in order to change it.
type: The rebel had enough of the government’s unfair police.
example_tr: Isyonchi - hukumatni o'zgartirish uchun unga qarshi kurashadigan shaxs.
column14: Qo'zg'olonchi hukumatning adolatsiz politsiyasidan etarli edi.

example: To retreat means to run away because you have been beaten in a fight.
type: The army retreated because they were losing the battle.
example_tr: Orqaga chekinish, janjalda kaltaklanganingiz uchun qochib ketish demakdir.
column14: Armiya jangda yutqazayotgani uchun orqaga chekindi.

example: A revolution is a change to the political system by a group of people.
type: The revolution in Russia led to the creation of the Soviet Union.
example_tr: Inqilob - bu bir guruh odamlar tomonidan siyosiy tizimni o'zgartirish.
column14: Rossiyadagi inqilob Sovet Ittifoqining tuzilishiga olib keldi.

example: A spear is a long stick with a blade on one end that is used as a weapon.
type: The soldier was holding a spear in his hand.
example_tr: Nayza - qurol sifatida ishlatiladigan, bir uchida pichoqli uzun tayoq.
column14: Askar qo‘lida nayza tutib turardi.

example: If something is steep, then its slope or angle rises or falls sharply.
type: He rode his bike up the steep hill to reach the top.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tik bo'lsa, unda uning qiyaligi yoki burchagi keskin ko'tariladi yoki tushadi.
column14: U cho'qqiga chiqish uchun velosipedda tik tepalikka chiqdi.

example: A summit is the highest part of a hill or mountain.
type: Snow covered the summit of the mountain even during the summer.
example_tr: Cho'qqi - tepalik yoki tog'ning eng baland qismi.
column14: Yozda ham tog‘ cho‘qqisini qor qoplagan.

example: Thunder is the loud noise heard during a storm.
type: The sound of the thunder startled me.
example_tr: Momaqaldiroq - bo'ron paytida eshitiladigan kuchli shovqin.
column14: Momaqaldiroqning ovozi meni hayratga soldi.

example: Troops are soldiers that fight in groups in a battle.
type: The troops were all prepared to go into battle.
example_tr: Qo'shinlar - bu janglarda guruh bo'lib jang qiladigan askarlar.
column14: Barcha qo'shinlar jangga kirishishga tayyor edi.

example: A warrior is a brave soldier or fighter.
type: The samurai were some of the most skilled warriors in the ancient world.
example_tr: Jangchi - jasur askar yoki jangchi.
column14: Samuraylar qadimgi dunyoning eng mohir jangchilaridan biri edi.

example: To withdraw means to leave a place, usually during war.
type: After losing the battle, the enemy withdrew back to its own country.
example_tr: Chiqib ketish odatda urush paytida joyni tark etishni anglatadi.
column14: Jangda mag‘lubiyatga uchragan dushman o‘z yurtiga qaytib ketdi.

example: To yield something means to give up control of it or to give it away.
type: He had to yield his turn because he was in checkmate.
example_tr: Biror narsani berish, uni boshqarishdan voz kechishni yoki uni berishni anglatadi.
column14: U o'z navbatini berishga majbur bo'ldi, chunki u matda edi.

example: A bench is a long seat for two or more people.
type: Most parks have benches for citizens to relax upon.
example_tr: Skameyka - bu ikki yoki undan ortiq kishi uchun uzun o'rindiq.
column14: Aksariyat bog'larda fuqarolar dam olishlari uchun o'rindiqlar mavjud.

example: To confront a hard situation or person is to deal with it.
type: The couple has to confront each other about their problems.
example_tr: Og'ir vaziyatga yoki odamga qarshi turish - u bilan kurashish.
column14: Er-xotin o'zlarining muammolari haqida bir-birlariga qarshi turishlari kerak.

example: A daisy is a small flower with white petals and a yellow center.
type: There were a few daisies growing in the field.
example_tr: Daisy - oq gulbarglari va sariq markazli kichik gul.
column14: Dalada bir nechta papatyalar o'sib chiqdi.

example: A dispute is an argument or disagreement that people have.
type: Karen and Brian often have disputes about silly things.
example_tr: Munozara - bu odamlar o'rtasidagi tortishuv yoki kelishmovchilik.
column14: Karen va Brayan ko'pincha ahmoqona narsalar haqida bahslashishadi.

example: Horror is a feeling of being very afraid or shocked.
type: The audience screamed in horror when the ghost appeared in the movie
example_tr: Dahshat - bu juda qo'rquv yoki hayratda qolish hissi.
column14: Filmda sharpa paydo bo‘lganida tomoshabinlar dahshatdan baqirishdi

example: An incident is an event that is usually not pleasant.
type: Mr. Wilson had an incident where he became sick and had to leave.
example_tr: Hodisa odatda yoqimli bo'lmagan hodisadir.
column14: Janob Uilson kasal bo'lib, ketishga majbur bo'lgan voqeaga duch keldi.

example: Mist is water that you can see in the air or on a surface.
type: The forest was covered with mist.
example_tr: Tuman - havoda yoki sirtda ko'rish mumkin bo'lgan suv.
column14: O'rmonni tuman qoplagan edi.

example: An object is an inanimate thing that you can see or touch.
type: The shopping cart was filled with objects.
example_tr: Ob'ekt - bu siz ko'rishingiz yoki tegishingiz mumkin bo'lgan jonsiz narsa.
column14: Savatcha buyumlar bilan to'ldirilgan edi.

example: An orphan is a child who does not have parents.
type: The orphan frequently cried during the night.
example_tr: Yetim - ota-onasi bo'lmagan bola.
column14: Yetim kechalari tez-tez yig'lardi.

example: To plot is to make a secret plan to do something that is wrong.
type: The group was plotting to ruin the company’s business.
example_tr: Hiyla qilish - noto'g'ri ish qilish uchun yashirin reja tuzish.
column14: Guruh kompaniya biznesini barbod qilmoqchi bo'lgan.

example: When a female is pregnant, she is going to have a baby.
type: The pregnant woman was shopping for baby clothes.
example_tr: Ayol homilador bo'lsa, u bola tug'adi.
column14: Homilador ayol chaqaloq kiyimlari uchun xarid qilgan.

example: Rage is a very angry feeling.
type: The chef was filled with rage when his helpers ruined the meal.
example_tr: G'azab - bu juda g'azablangan tuyg'u.
column14: Oshpazning yordamchilari ovqatni buzib tashlashganida, g'azabga to'ldi.

example: Revenge is what you do to hurt or punish someone who hurts you.
type: He broke his sister’s doll as revenge after she lost his favorite book.
example_tr: Qasos bu sizni xafa qilgan odamni xafa qilish yoki jazolash uchun qiladigan narsadir.
column14: U o'zining sevimli kitobini yo'qotib qo'yganidan keyin qasos sifatida singlisining qo'g'irchog'ini sindirib tashladi.

example: Shame is a bad feeling about things you have done wrong.
type: The boy felt shame about misplacing his clothes.
example_tr: Uyat - bu noto'g'ri qilgan narsalaringiz uchun yomon tuyg'u.
column14: Bola kiyimini noto'g'ri joylashtirganidan uyaldi.

example: To sigh is to breathe out loudly and show that you are tired or sad.
type: Molly sighed when she looked at all the information she had to research.
example_tr: Xo'rsinish - baland ovozda nafas olish va charchaganingizni yoki g'amgin ekanligingizni ko'rsatishdir.
column14: Molli tadqiq qilishi kerak bo'lgan barcha ma'lumotlarni ko'rib, xo'rsinib qo'ydi.

example: To sneak is to move quietly so that no one hears or sees you.
type: The thief snuck out of the house without anyone noticing him.
example_tr: Yashirish - sizni hech kim eshitmasligi yoki ko'rmasligi uchun jimgina harakat qilishdir.
column14: O‘g‘ri hech kimga sezdirmay, uydan yashirinib chiqib ketdi.

example: To spare something is to give it because you have more than you need.
type: I wanted to help him but I couldn’t spare a tire.
example_tr: Biror narsani ayamaslik - uni berish, chunki sizda kerak bo'lgandan ko'proq narsa bor.
column14: Men unga yordam bermoqchi edim, lekin shinamni ayaolmadim.

example: The stem of a plant is the stick that grows leaves or flowers.
type: The rose had a long thin stem.
example_tr: O'simlikning poyasi - barg yoki gul o'sadigan tayoq.
column14: Atirgulning uzun ingichka poyasi bor edi.

example: Supper is a meal that is eaten in the evening.
type: We usually have supper around 6 o’clock at my house.
example_tr: Kechki ovqat - bu kechqurun iste'mol qilinadigan taom.
column14: Biz odatda kechki ovqatni soat 6 da uyimda qilamiz.

example: When something is tender, it is soft and easy to chew.
type: The meat was so tender they didn’t need knives to cut it with.
example_tr: Biror narsa yumshoq bo'lsa, u yumshoq va chaynash oson.
column14: Go'sht shunchalik yumshoq ediki, ularni kesish uchun pichoq kerak emas edi.

example: If something is beneath something else, it is under it.
type: The largest part of an iceberg lies beneath the waterline.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsa ostida bo'lsa, u uning ostidadir.
column14: Aysbergning eng katta qismi suv chizig'i ostida joylashgan.

example: A cub is a baby animal, such as a bear or lion.
type: The lion cub was crying for its mother.
example_tr: Kichkintoy - ayiq yoki sher kabi hayvonlarning bolasi.
column14: Arslon bolasi onasi uchun yig‘lardi.

example: Dawn is the time of day when the sun rises.
type: At dawn, the sun gently rose over the farm.
example_tr: Tong - kunning quyosh chiqishi vaqti.
column14: Tongda quyosh ferma ustidan ohista ko'tarildi.

example: If you are dissatisfied, you are not happy with something.
type: I was dissatisfied with their decision to work on Sunday.
example_tr: Agar siz norozi bo'lsangiz, biror narsadan mamnun emassiz.
column14: Ularning yakshanba kuni ishlash qaroridan norozi edim.

example: When something is done with ease, it is not hard to do.
type: The monkey climbed the tree with ease.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa osonlik bilan amalga oshirilsa, uni qilish qiyin emas.
column14: Maymun bemalol daraxtga chiqdi.

example: When something is evident, it is easy to see or understand.
type: It was evident from the look on his face that he was unhappy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, uni ko'rish yoki tushunish oson.
column14: Uning baxtsizligi yuz-ko‘zidan bilinib turardi.

example: Hail is ice that falls from the sky when rain freezes.
type: The hail from the storm was the size of golf balls.
example_tr: Do'l - yomg'ir muzlaganda osmondan tushadigan muz.
column14: Bo'rondan yog'adigan do'l golf to'plari hajmida edi.

example: To howl means to make a long, loud sound like a wolf or a dog.
type: The wolf howled at the moon.
example_tr: Voylash bo'ri yoki it kabi uzun va baland ovozda ovoz chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Bo‘ri oyga qarab qichqirdi.

example: To leap means to jump a long distance.
type: He had to leap over the gap to reach the other side of the hill.
example_tr: Sakrash uzoq masofaga sakrash demakdir.
column14: U tepalikning narigi tomoniga yetib borish uchun bo‘shliqdan sakrab o‘tishi kerak edi.

example: When something is magnificent, it is beautiful and grand.
type: The man gave his wife a pair of magnificent diamond earrings.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ajoyib bo'lsa, u go'zal va buyukdir.
column14: Erkak xotiniga bir juft ajoyib olmos sirg'a sovg'a qildi.

example: A necessity is something that is needed.
type: Fresh water is a necessity for life.
example_tr: Zarurat - bu zarur bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Toza suv hayot uchun zarurdir.

example: An outcome is the end of an action or event.
type: The outcome of his latest business plan was a complete failure.
example_tr: Natija - bu harakat yoki hodisaning yakuni.
column14: Uning so'nggi biznes-rejasining natijasi butunlay muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'ldi.

example: A pile is a large group of things on top of one another.
type: The pile of cups was beginning to tilt.
example_tr: Qoziq - bir-birining ustiga qo'yilgan narsalarning katta guruhi.
column14: Kosalar uyumi qiyshay boshladi.

example: When something is profound, it is very intelligent.
type: For a little boy, Jeremy has some profound thoughts.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa chuqur bo'lsa, u juda aqlli bo'ladi.
column14: Kichkina bola uchun Jeremi juda chuqur fikrlarga ega.

example: To seize something means to grab it quickly or strongly.
type: The man seized as much money as he could before anyone could see him.
example_tr: Biror narsani qo'lga olish, uni tez yoki kuchli ushlashni anglatadi.
column14: Erkak uni hech kim ko'rmaguncha imkon qadar ko'p pulni tortib oldi.

example: To squeeze something means to press it together and hold it tightly.
type: When Clara saw her cat, she gave it a big squeeze.
example_tr: Biror narsani siqish, uni bir-biriga bosib, mahkam ushlash demakdir.
column14: Klara mushukini ko'rgach, uni qattiq siqib qo'ydi.

example: When something is supreme, it is the highest or best.
type: The supreme officer was in charge of keeping the citizens calm.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oliy bo'lsa, u eng yuqori yoki eng yaxshisidir.
column14: Oliy zobit fuqarolarning tinchligini ta'minlash uchun mas'ul edi.

example: When something is terrific, it is very good.
type: My youngest daughter is a terrific painter.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, u juda yaxshi.
column14: Mening kenja qizim ajoyib rassom.

example: A trait is part of someone’s personality.
type: One trait of Salvador’s personality is his cheerfulness.
example_tr: Xususiyat birovning shaxsiyatining bir qismidir.
column14: Salvadorning o'ziga xos xususiyatlaridan biri bu uning quvnoqligi.

example: When something is vital, it is necessary for life.
type: The heart is a vital organ.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u hayot uchun zarurdir.
column14: Yurak muhim organdir.

example: When you become accustomed to something, you are in the habit of it.
type: Grandfather is accustomed to reading the newspaper every morning.
example_tr: Biror narsaga o'rganib qolganingizda, unga odatlanib qolasiz.
column14: Bobo har kuni ertalab gazeta o‘qishga odatlangan.

example: To affirm is to say that something is true.
type: Using a graph, Malcolm affirmed the success of the company.
example_tr: Tasdiqlash - biror narsaning haqiqat ekanligini aytish.
column14: Grafik yordamida Malkolm kompaniyaning muvaffaqiyatini tasdiqladi.

example: If someone is astonished, they are very surprised or shocked.
type: I was astonished when he pulled the live rabbit out of his hat.
example_tr: Agar kimdir hayron bo'lsa, u juda hayratda yoki hayratda.
column14: U shlyapasidan tirik quyonni sug‘urib olganida hayratda qoldim.

example: To bang is to hit something to make a noise.
type: The drummer banged on his drum as he marched in the parade.
example_tr: Portlash - shovqin qilish uchun biror narsaga urish.
column14: Barabanchi paradda ketayotganda barabanini chaldi.

example: A clan is a group of relatives or friends.
type: The Lee clan meets every year to celebrate the New Year.
example_tr: Klan - qarindoshlar yoki do'stlar guruhi.
column14: Li klani har yili Yangi yilni nishonlash uchun yig'iladi.

example: When something is dim, it does not give out much light.
type: Working in a dim room is bad for your eyes.
example_tr: Biror narsa xira bo'lsa, u ko'p yorug'lik bermaydi.
column14: Qorong'i xonada ishlash ko'zlar uchun yomon.

example: Emphasis is special attention or importance.
type: The students put special emphasis on chapter 4 because it will be on the test.
example_tr: Ta'kidlash alohida e'tibor yoki muhimlikdir.
column14: Talabalar 4-bobga alohida e'tibor berishadi, chunki u testda bo'ladi.

example: A fable is a short story that teaches a lesson.
type: In the fable about the tortoise and the hare, the lesson is consistency.
example_tr: Ertak - bu saboq beradigan qisqa hikoya.
column14: Toshbaqa va quyon haqidagi ertakda saboq izchillikdir.

example: A feast is a large meal for many people.
type: At Thanksgiving, I enjoy a wonderful feast with my family.
example_tr: Bayram ko'p odamlar uchun katta taomdir.
column14: Shukrona kunida men oilam bilan ajoyib ziyofatdan zavqlanaman.

example: To glow is to make a soft light.
type: The small flame glowed softly.
example_tr: Yorqinlik - yumshoq yorug'lik qilish.
column14: Kichkina olov ohista porladi.

example: When something is hollow, it has an empty space inside.
type: Straws are hollow, so liquid can flow through them.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ichi bo'sh bo'lsa, uning ichida bo'sh joy bo'ladi.
column14: Somonlar ichi bo'sh, shuning uchun ular orqali suyuqlik oqishi mumkin.

example: Instinct is the natural way that people behave without thinking about it.
type: Cats hunt mice because of instinct.
example_tr: Instinkt - bu odamlarning bu haqda o'ylamasdan o'zini tutishining tabiiy usuli.
column14: Mushuklar instinkt tufayli sichqonlarni ovlaydi.

example: A joint is a place of the body where the bones meet, such as the knee.
type: Two important bones in your leg meet at a joint in your knee.
example_tr: Bo'g'im - bu suyaklar birlashadigan tananing joyi, masalan, tizza.
column14: Oyog'ingizdagi ikkita muhim suyak tizzangizdagi bo'g'inda uchrashadi.

example: To leak is to let a liquid or gas pass through a flaw.
type: The pipe leaks from many places.
example_tr: Oqish - suyuqlik yoki gazni nuqsondan o'tkazish.
column14: Quvur ko'p joylardan oqadi.

example: A physician is a doctor.
type: The physician said I would feel better if I took my medicine.
example_tr: Shifokor - shifokor.
column14: Shifokor, agar dori ichsam, o'zimni yaxshi his qilishimni aytdi.

example: To sacrifice something valuable is to give it up to get something else.
type: Her parents sacrificed a lot of money in order for her to go to college.
example_tr: Qimmatli narsani qurbon qilish, boshqa narsani olish uchun undan voz kechishdir.
column14: Uning kollejga kirishi uchun ota-onasi ko'p pul qurbon qilishdi.

example: When something is stiff, it is hard to move.
type: The bird was standing on the tree’s stiff branch.
example_tr: Biror narsa qattiq bo'lsa, harakat qilish qiyin.
column14: Qush daraxtning qotib qolgan shoxida turardi.

example: To stroke is to move a hand over something or someone.
type: She stroked her cheek to see if there was something on it.
example_tr: Qo'l urish - biror narsa yoki kimdir ustidan qo'l siljitish.
column14: Biror narsa bor-yo‘qligini bilish uchun yuzini silab qo‘ydi.

example: When something is tragic, it is connected with death and suffering.
type: The airplane crashed in a tragic accident.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa fojiali bo'lsa, u o'lim va azob bilan bog'liq.
column14: Samolyot fojiali halokatga uchradi.

example: A tune is a song.
type: The students played a familiar tune for the audience.
example_tr: Ohang - bu qo'shiq.
column14: Talabalar tomoshabinlarga tanish kuy chalishdi.

example: To accommodate is to have enough room.
type: The meeting room can accommodate nine people.
example_tr: Joylashtirish - bu etarli joyga ega bo'lish.
column14: Uchrashuv xonasi to'qqiz kishini sig'dira oladi.

example: A circus is a traveling show with animals and people.
type: I like to go to the circus to see the animals do tricks.
example_tr: Sirk - bu hayvonlar va odamlar ishtirokidagi sayohat tomoshasi.
column14: Men hayvonlarning nayranglarini ko'rish uchun sirkga borishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: If two things coincide, they happen at the same time.
type: My birthday coincides with Chirstmas
example_tr: Agar ikkita narsa mos kelsa, ular bir vaqtning o'zida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Mening tug'ilgan kunim Rojdestvoga to'g'ri keladi

example: To commission someone to do something is to pay them to do it.
type: The artist was commissioned to create a picture.
example_tr: Biror kishiga biror narsa qilishni buyurmoq, buning uchun unga pul to'lashdir.
column14: Rassomga rasm yaratish topshirilgan.

example: A dose is a certain amount of medicine that you take at one time.
type: My mother gave me a dose of medicine before I went to bed.
example_tr: Doza - bu siz bir vaqtning o'zida qabul qiladigan ma'lum miqdordagi dori.
column14: Onam yotishdan oldin menga bir doza dori berdi.

example: To dye something is to make it a certain color by using a special chemical.
type: Valery got her hair dyed at the salon yesterday.
example_tr: Biror narsani bo'yash - bu maxsus kimyoviy vosita yordamida uni ma'lum bir rangga aylantirish.
column14: Kecha Valeriy salonda sochlarini bo'yadi.

example: The extent of something is how large, important, or serious it is.
type: He ate to such an extent that he became overweight.
example_tr: Biror narsaning qanchalik kattaligi, muhimligi yoki jiddiyligi.
column14: U shunchalik ovqatlandiki, u ortiqcha vaznga ega bo'ldi.

example: Gender is a category that describes being either a boy or a girl.
type: Do you know the gender of her new baby?
example_tr: Gender - bu o'g'il yoki qiz bo'lishni tavsiflovchi kategoriya.
column14: Uning yangi chaqalog'ining jinsini bilasizmi?

example: A headline is the title of a newspaper story.
type: The headline on the front page was about the economy.
example_tr: Sarlavha gazeta xabarining sarlavhasidir.
column14: Birinchi sahifadagi sarlavha iqtisodiyot haqida edi.

example: When something is informal, it is not official.
type: They had an informal meeting to talk about their experiences.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa norasmiy bo'lsa, u rasmiy emas.
column14: Ular norasmiy uchrashuv o‘tkazib, o‘z tajribalari haqida gapirib berishdi.

example: To inquire about something is to ask about it.
type: Dad called to inquire about the price of tickets for the show.
example_tr: Biror narsa haqida so'rash - bu haqda so'rash.
column14: Dadam spektakl uchun chiptalar narxini bilish uchun qo‘ng‘iroq qildi.

example: A messenger is one who carries information from one place to another.
type: The messenger delivered an important document to the office.
example_tr: Messenger - bu ma'lumotni bir joydan ikkinchi joyga o'tkazuvchi.
column14: Messenjer muhim hujjatni idoraga yetkazdi.

example: To peer at something is to watch it carefully.
type: She peered at people through the window.
example_tr: Biror narsaga diqqat bilan qarash - uni diqqat bilan kuzatish.
column14: U derazadan odamlarga qaradi.

example: A portrait is a painting or photograph of someone.
type: I saw many religious portraits when I went to the museum.
example_tr: Portret - bu kimningdir surati yoki surati.
column14: Muzeyga borganimda ko'plab diniy portretlarni ko'rdim.

example: To pose is to stay in one place without moving.
type: The kids and their dog posed for a picture.
example_tr: Poz qo'yish - harakat qilmasdan bir joyda turish.
column14: Bolalar va ularning itlari suratga tushishdi.

example: A ranch is a large farm where animals are kept.
type: My uncle has many horses on his ranch.
example_tr: Chorvachilik - bu hayvonlar boqiladigan yirik ferma.
column14: Amakimning fermasida ko‘p otlar bor.

example: To steer something is to control where it goes.
type: He steered the go-cart around the track.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshqarish - uning qayerga borishini boshqarish.
column14: U aravani yo‘l bo‘ylab boshqardi.

example: A stripe is a thick line.
type: The flag of the United States has red and white stripes.
example_tr: Chiziq - qalin chiziq.
column14: Qo'shma Shtatlar bayrog'ida qizil va oq chiziqlar mavjud.

example: When an animal is tame, it is not afraid to be near people.
type: The tame bird rested on his hand.
example_tr: Hayvon uylangan bo'lsa, u odamlarning yonida bo'lishdan qo'rqmaydi.
column14: Yumshoq qush uning qo‘liga suyanib qoldi.

example: To tempt people is offer them something they want but shoudn't have.
type: I wasn't hungry, but she temted me with a piece of my favorite cake.
example_tr: Odamlarni vasvasaga solish, ularga o'zlari xohlagan, lekin bo'lmasligi kerak bo'lgan narsani taklif qilishdir.
column14: Men och emasdim, lekin u meni sevimli tortimdan bir parcha bilan sinab ko'rdi.

example: An Aborigine is a native of Australia before Europeans lived there.
type: The Aborigines created beautiful artwork.
example_tr: Aborigen Avstraliyada yevropaliklar yashashidan oldin tug'ilgan.
column14: Aborigenlar chiroyli san'at asarlarini yaratdilar.

example: To ban something is to not let people do it.
type: Smoking is banned in this building.
example_tr: Biror narsani taqiqlash - bu odamlarga ruxsat bermaslikdir.
column14: Bu binoda chekish taqiqlangan.

example: If you are cautious, you are careful in a dangerous situation.
type: Be very cautious as you stack those boxes.
example_tr: Agar siz ehtiyotkor bo'lsangiz, xavfli vaziyatda ehtiyot bo'lasiz.
column14: Ushbu qutilarni yig'ishda juda ehtiyot bo'ling.

example: To confess something is to say that you did it.
type: He confessed that he was responsible for choosing the winning story.
example_tr: Biror narsani tan olish, buni qilganingizni aytishdir.
column14: U g'olib hikoyani tanlash uchun mas'ul ekanini tan oldi.

example: A cottage is a small, old house in the countryside.
type: My aunt lives in a pretty cottage in the mountains,
example_tr: Kottej - qishloqdagi kichik, eski uy.
column14: Mening xolam tog'lardagi go'zal dachada yashaydi,

example: Daytime is the time of the day when the sky is light.
type: I only allowed my kids to play outside in the daytime.
example_tr: Kunduz - osmon yorug' bo'lgan kunning vaqti.
column14: Men bolalarimga faqat kunduzi tashqarida o'ynashga ruxsat berdim.

example: If you are desperate, you will try anything to do or change something.
type: I'm desperate to find a new job.
example_tr: Agar umidsiz bo'lsangiz, biror narsani qilishga yoki biror narsani o'zgartirishga harakat qilasiz.
column14: Men yangi ish topmoqchiman.

example: If something fades, it gets quieter or darker.
type: The piece of cloth I found was old and faded.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'chib qolsa, u jimroq yoki qorong'i bo'ladi.
column14: Men topgan mato eskirgan va rangi o‘chib ketgan.

example: If a person or animal is fierce, they are angry or violent.
type: Wolves are fierce animals. Do not disturb them.
example_tr: Agar odam yoki hayvon shafqatsiz bo'lsa, ular g'azablangan yoki zo'ravondir.
column14: Bo'rilar shafqatsiz hayvonlardir. Ularni bezovta qilmang.

example: To gamble means to play a game that involves winning or losing.
type: Many people like to go to casinos to gamble.
example_tr: Qimor o'ynash, g'alaba qozonish yoki yutqazishni o'z ichiga olgan o'yinni o'ynashni anglatadi.
column14: Ko'p odamlar qimor o'ynash uchun kazinolarga borishni yaxshi ko'radilar.

example: A lawn is an area covered in grass.
type: My dad keeps the lawn in front of our house very neat.
example_tr: Maysazor - o't bilan qoplangan maydon.
column14: Dadam uyimiz oldidagi maysazorni juda toza saqlaydi.

example: To mow grass is to cut it to make it very short.
type: I mow our lawn every weekend.
example_tr: O'tni kesish - uni juda qisqa qilish uchun kesish.
column14: Men har hafta oxiri maysazorimizni o'rganaman.

example: An outlaw is a criminal who hides from the police.
type: The police passed out posters of the outlaw to all the people.
example_tr: Qonunbuzar - politsiyadan yashiringan jinoyatchi.
column14: Politsiya qonunbuzarning plakatlarini barcha odamlarga tarqatdi.

example: A prospect is a possibility that something will happen.
type: He wakes up every morning with the prospect of having a good day.
example_tr: Istiqbol - biror narsa sodir bo'lishi ehtimoli.
column14: U har kuni ertalab yaxshi kun o'tkazish umidi bilan uyg'onadi.

example: A purse is a bag where women keep money, makeup and keys.
type: My sister likes to buy designer purses.
example_tr: Hamyon - bu ayollar pul, bo'yanish va kalitlarni saqlaydigan sumka.
column14: Opam dizaynerlik hamyonlarini sotib olishni yaxshi ko'radi.

example: A rod is a thin stick made of wood or metal.
type: I bought a new fishing rod to use while on vacation.
example_tr: Tayoq - yog'och yoki metalldan yasalgan ingichka tayoq.
column14: Men ta'tilda foydalanish uchun yangi qarmoq sotib oldim.

example: If something seldom happens, it doesn’t happen very often.
type: It seldom rains in southern Arizona.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kamdan-kam sodir bo'lsa, u tez-tez sodir bo'lmaydi.
column14: Arizona janubida kamdan-kam yomg'ir yog'adi.

example: To shave means to cut the hairs on your face with a sharp tool.
type: My father shaves his face every day because he doesn’t want a beard.
example_tr: Soqol olish - yuzdagi tuklarni o'tkir asbob bilan kesish demakdir.
column14: Otam soqol qo'yishni istamagani uchun har kuni yuzini qirdiradi.

example: If you are terrified, you are extremely scared.
type: When I saw the ghost, I was absolutely terrified!
example_tr: Agar siz qo'rqsangiz, siz juda qo'rqasiz.
column14: Men sharpani ko'rganimda, men butunlay dahshatga tushdim!

example: A wizard is a man who can do magic.
type: The wizard made gold fall from the sky.
example_tr: Sehrgar - bu sehr qila oladigan odam.
column14: Sehrgar osmondan oltin tushirdi.

example: Baggage is the set of bags that people take with them when they travel.
type: I'm taking several pieces of baggage with me on vacation.
example_tr: Bagaj - bu odamlar sayohat qilishda o'zlari bilan olib ketadigan sumkalar to'plami.
column14: Men ta'tilda o'zim bilan bir nechta yuk olib ketyapman.

example: A bulb is the glass part of an electric light.
type: I had to change the light bulb in my bedroom.
example_tr: Lampochka - bu elektr chiroqning shisha qismi.
column14: Men yotoqxonamdagi lampochkani almashtirishim kerak edi.

example: A bundle is a number of things that are tied together.
type: I was shocked when he showed me a bundle of money.
example_tr: To'plam - bu bir-biriga bog'langan narsalar soni.
column14: U menga bir dasta pul ko‘rsatganida hayratda qoldim.

example: Cattle are cows and bulls, especially on a farm.
type: The rancher’s cattle were eating the grass in the field.
example_tr: Qoramol sigir va buqa, ayniqsa fermada.
column14: Chorvadorning mollari daladagi o'tni yeyayotgan edi.

example: To flee means to run away from trouble or danger.
type: The crowd of men tried to flee from the danger.
example_tr: Qochmoq muammo yoki xavfdan qochish demakdir.
column14: Olomon odamlar xavfdan qochishga harakat qilishdi.

example: To graze means to eat grass.
type: The cows grazed in the field.
example_tr: O‘tlamoq o‘t yemoq demakdir.
column14: Sigirlar dalada o‘tlab yurardi.

example: Greed is a desire to have more than the things that you need.
type: She ate all the cookies out of her greed.
example_tr: Ochko'zlik - bu sizga kerak bo'lgan narsalardan ko'proq narsaga ega bo'lish istagi.
column14: U ochko'zligidan barcha pechenyelarni yedi.

example: A herd is a large group of the same type of animals that live together.
type: The herd of cows moved slowly across the ranch.
example_tr: Poda - birga yashaydigan bir xil turdagi hayvonlarning katta guruhi.
column14: Sigirlar podasi rancho bo'ylab sekin harakatlandi.

example: To initiate something means to start it.
type: You have to turn the switch on to initiate the computer system.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshlash, uni boshlash demakdir.
column14: Kompyuter tizimini ishga tushirish uchun kalitni yoqishingiz kerak.

example: A lane is a small road.
type: The lane passes directly in front of our house.
example_tr: Bo'lak - bu kichik yo'l.
column14: Yo'lak to'g'ridan-to'g'ri uyimiz oldidan o'tadi.

example: Nerve is bravery or the belief that you can do something.
type: He has the nerve to think that he can actually wrestle with a lion.
example_tr: Asab - bu jasorat yoki biror narsa qilish mumkinligiga ishonish.
column14: U sher bilan kurasha oladi, deb o'ylash uchun asabi bor.

example: An optimist is somebody who sees the good parts of a situation.
type: Even though he has physical problems, my brother is an optimist.
example_tr: Optimist - bu vaziyatning yaxshi tomonlarini ko'radigan odam.
column14: Uning jismoniy muammolari bo'lsa ham, akam optimist.

example: A parade is a celebration when groups of people walk in the same direction.
type: There were many marching bands in the spring parade.
example_tr: Parad - bu odamlar guruhlari bir yo'nalishda yurishganda bayramdir.
column14: Bahorgi paradda ko'plab marshlar bor edi.

example: To pave the ground is to lay material on it to make it easier to walk or drive on.
type: The path was paved with yellow bricks.
example_tr: Erni asfaltlash - yurish yoki mashinada yurishni osonlashtirish uchun unga material yotqizishdir.
column14: So‘qmoq sarg‘ish g‘ishtlar bilan qoplangan.

example: A phantom is a ghost or spirit.
type: A scary phantom appeared from out of the darkness.
example_tr: Fantom - bu arvoh yoki ruh.
column14: Qorong'ulikdan qo'rqinchli hayol paydo bo'ldi.

example: Something that is portable is able to be moved or carried easily.
type: Since computers are portable, people can use them anywhere.
example_tr: Ko'chma narsa osongina ko'chirilishi yoki ko'chirilishi mumkin.
column14: Kompyuterlar ko'chma bo'lgani uchun odamlar ulardan istalgan joyda foydalanishlari mumkin.

example: A poster is a written announcement that is used to advertise something.
type: I saw a poster about a free concert in the park.
example_tr: Plakat - bu biror narsani reklama qilish uchun ishlatiladigan yozma e'lon.
column14: Men bog'da bepul konsert haqida plakat ko'rdim.

example: To scratch is to make small cuts with a claw or fingernail.
type: I used a stick to scratch my back.
example_tr: Chizish - tirnoq yoki tirnoq bilan kichik kesmalar qilishdir.
column14: Men belimni tirnash uchun tayoq ishlatdim.

example: A symphony is a long piece of music performed by many musicians.
type: Alex, a violin player, has always dreamt of playing a symphony.
example_tr: Simfoniya - bu ko'plab musiqachilar tomonidan ijro etiladigan uzun musiqa asari.
column14: Skripkachi Aleks har doim simfoniya chalishni orzu qilgan.

example: A widow is a woman whose husband has died.
type: The widow had no children and was very lonely.
example_tr: Beva ayol - eri vafot etgan ayol.
column14: Beva ayolning farzandi yo'q edi va juda yolg'iz edi.

example: To circulate something is to spread it quickly.
type: The fan helped to circulate cool air through the room.
example_tr: Biror narsani aylanma - uni tez tarqatish.
