column14: Fan xona bo'ylab salqin havo aylanishiga yordam berdi.

example: Consequent means happening because of a different situation.
type: Her consequent rash came after she touched the poison ivy.
example_tr: Natija boshqa vaziyat tufayli sodir bo'lishini anglatadi.
column14: Uning oqibati zaharli pechakka tegib ketganidan keyin paydo bo'ldi.

example: To derive something from another source means to get it from that thing.
type: Red’s nickname was derived from the color of her hair.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshqa manbadan olish, uni o'sha narsadan olishni anglatadi.
column14: Qizilning taxallusi uning sochlari rangidan olingan.

example: To drown is to die from not being able to breathe underwater.
type: He would have drowned if the sailors would not have rescued him.
example_tr: Cho'kish - suv ostida nafas ololmaslikdan o'lish.
column14: Agar dengizchilar uni qutqarmaganida, u cho'kib ketgan bo'lar edi.

example: A dynasty is a series of rulers who are all from the same family.
type: The ancient Egyptians had a dynasty that lasted for many years.
example_tr: Sulola - bu bir oiladan bo'lgan bir qator hukmdorlar.
column14: Qadimgi misrliklar uzoq yillar davom etgan sulolaga ega edilar.

example: A fraction is a small part of something.
type: Only a fraction of the cake was gone.
example_tr: Kasr - biror narsaning kichik qismi.
column14: Kekning faqat bir qismi g'oyib bo'ldi.

example: Frost is a white layer of ice that forms during very cold weather.
type: In the morning, the trees were all covered with frost.
example_tr: Ayoz - bu juda sovuq havoda hosil bo'lgan oq muz qatlami.
column14: Ertalab daraxtlarning hammasini sovuq qoplagan edi.

example: An illusion is something that looks real, but doesn’t actually exist.
type: Some pictures create an illusion for the eyes.
example_tr: Xayol - bu haqiqiy ko'rinadigan, lekin aslida mavjud bo'lmagan narsa.
column14: Ba'zi rasmlar ko'zlar uchun illyuziya yaratadi.

example: To invade is to take over a place by force.
type: The enemy forces tried to invade our country through the air.
example_tr: Bosqinchilik - bir joyni zo'rlik bilan egallash.
column14: Dushman kuchlari havo orqali yurtimizga bostirib kirishga urindi.

example: A lieutenant is a rank in the military or police, or a person with that rank.
type: The lieutenant was a good leader, and his soldiers respected him.
example_tr: Leytenant - bu harbiy yoki politsiyadagi unvon yoki bu unvonga ega bo'lgan shaxs.
column14: Leytenant yaxshi rahbar edi, askarlari uni hurmat qilishardi.

example: The word marine describes something related to the sea.
type: A healthy ocean is full of marine animals.
example_tr: Dengiz so'zi dengiz bilan bog'liq narsani tasvirlaydi.
column14: Sog'lom okean dengiz hayvonlariga to'la.

example: The merit of something or someone is their good qualities.
type: The actor received an award for his merits in the movie.
example_tr: Biror narsaning yoki kimningdir qadr-qimmati ularning yaxshi fazilatlaridir.
column14: Aktyor filmdagi xizmatlari uchun mukofot oldi.

example: A navy is the part of a country’s military that fights at sea.
type: Many countries are known for their strong navies.
example_tr: Dengiz floti - bu mamlakat armiyasining dengizda jang qiladigan qismi.
column14: Ko'pgina davlatlar kuchli dengiz floti bilan mashhur.

example: Polar relates to the cold places on Earth’s north and south ends.
type: Only a few people live in the Earth’s northern polar region.
example_tr: Polar Yerning shimoliy va janubiy uchlaridagi sovuq joylarga tegishli.
column14: Erning shimoliy qutb mintaqasida faqat bir nechta odam yashaydi.

example: A ray is a line of light that comes from a bright object.
type: The sun’s warm rays covered the beach.
example_tr: Nur - bu yorqin ob'ektdan keladigan yorug'lik chizig'i.
column14: Quyoshning iliq nurlari sohilni qopladi.

example: To resign means to quit a job.
type: After I officially resigned from work, I said goodbye to my boss.
example_tr: Iste'foga chiqish ishdan ketishni anglatadi.
column14: Rasmiy ravishda ishdan bo‘shagach, xo‘jayinim bilan xayrlashdim.

example: Suicide is the act of killing oneself.
type: Some people feel so sad that they think suicide is the only answer.
example_tr: O'z joniga qasd qilish - o'z joniga qasd qilish harakati.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar shunchalik g'amgin bo'lishadiki, ular o'z joniga qasd qilish yagona javob deb o'ylashadi.

example: To tremble is to shake as a result of cold weather.
type: Harry was not used to the cold, so he trembled most of the day.
example_tr: Titrash - sovuq havo natijasida titrash.
column14: Garri sovuqqa o'rganmagani uchun kunning ko'p qismini qaltirab o'tkazardi.

example: When something is underlying, it is a hidden cause of something else.
type: Her underlying fear of flying reduced her traveling options.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yashiringan bo'lsa, u boshqa narsaning yashirin sababidir.
column14: Uning uchishdan qo'rqishi uning sayohat qilish imkoniyatlarini qisqartirdi.

example: To travel via something means to travel through or using something.
type: We arrived in the city from the airport via the train.
example_tr: Biror narsa orqali sayohat qilish, biror narsa orqali sayohat qilish yoki undan foydalanishni anglatadi.
column14: Aeroportdan poyezd orqali shaharga yetib keldik.

example: To alter something means to make a small change to it.
type: I altered the color of my nails to match my hair.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'zgartirish, uni ozgina o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Sochlarimga mos keladigan tirnoqlarimning rangini o'zgartirdim.

example: If someone stands aside, they are on or to one side.
type: The man stood aside and opened the door for me.
example_tr: Agar kimdir chetda tursa, u bir tomonda yoki bir tomonda.
column14: U kishi chetga turdi va menga eshikni ochdi.

example: Autumn is the season of the year between summer and winter.
type: I love when the leaves fall in autumn because I can play in them.
example_tr: Kuz - yoz va qish o'rtasidagi yilning faslidir.
column14: Men barglar kuzda tushganini yaxshi ko'raman, chunki ularda o'ynashim mumkin.

example: To blend is to mix two or more things together so that they become one thing.
type: My wife blended together all of the ingredients to make a delicious stew.
example_tr: Aralashtirish - bu ikki yoki undan ortiq narsalarni bir-biriga aralashtirish, shunda ular bir narsaga aylanadi.
column14: Xotinim barcha masalliqlarni aralashtirib, mazali pishiriq tayyorladi.

example: To collapse is to fall down suddenly.
type: The tree collapsed right in front of our house.
example_tr: Yiqilish - to'satdan yiqilish.
column14: Daraxt uyimiz oldiga qulab tushdi.

example: To crush something is to press it together so its shape is destroyed.
type: Selena’s new car was crushed when something fell on top of it.
example_tr: Biror narsani maydalash - uni bir-biriga bosish, shunda uning shakli buziladi.
column14: Selenaning yangi mashinasi ustiga biror narsa tushganda ezilib qoldi.

example: To curve is to move in a line that bends and does not go straight.
type: The road curves to the left and to the right.
example_tr: Egrilik - bukilgan va to'g'ri ketmaydigan chiziq bo'ylab harakatlanish.
column14: Yo'l chapga va o'ngga egiladi.

example: If something is disgusting, it is very unpleasant.
type: After running all day, Greg's feet had a disgusting odor.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jirkanch bo'lsa, bu juda yoqimsiz.
column14: Kun bo'yi yugurgandan keyin Gregning oyoqlarida jirkanch hid paydo bo'ldi.

example: A drain is a pipe that carries away water from a building, such as in a kitchen.
type: The water in the sink goes down the drain as you wash your hands.
example_tr: Drenaj - bu suvni binodan, masalan, oshxonadan olib o'tadigan quvur.
column14: Qo'lingizni yuvayotganda lavabodagi suv drenajga tushadi.

example: To embrace is to hug.
type: When they saw each other again, the happy couple embraced.
example_tr: Quchoqlash - quchoqlash.
column14: Ular yana bir-birlarini ko'rishganda, baxtli er-xotin quchoqlashdi.

example: To envy someone is to wish that you had something that they have.
type: Sally envied the happy couple.
example_tr: Biror kishiga hasad qilish - sizda ularda bo'lgan narsa bo'lishini orzu qilish.
column14: Salli baxtli juftlikka havas qildi.

example: Fireworks are things that create colored lights when they are lit.
type: The display of fireworks was so beautiful.
example_tr: Fireworks - bu yoqilganda rangli chiroqlar yaratadigan narsalar.
column14: Pirotexnika namoyishi juda chiroyli edi.

example: Flour is a powder made from plants that is used to make foods like bread.
type: I wanted to bake a pie, but I needed flour.
example_tr: Un - non kabi oziq-ovqatlarni tayyorlash uchun ishlatiladigan o'simliklardan tayyorlangan kukun.
column14: Men pirog pishirmoqchi edim, lekin menga un kerak edi.

example: A fuse is a string that you light on fireworks to make them explode.
type: The boy lit the fuse on the rocket and waited for it to burst in the sky.
example_tr: Sug'urta - bu siz otashinlarni portlatish uchun yoqadigan simdir.
column14: Bola raketadagi sigortani yoqdi va uning osmonda otilishini kutdi.

example: Ginger is a spice from the root of a plant. It tastes spicy and sweet.
type: Ginger is a common ingredient in many dishes from India.
example_tr: Zanjabil o'simlik ildizidan olingan ziravordir. Uning ta'mi achchiq va shirin.
column14: Zanjabil Hindistondan ko'plab taomlarning umumiy tarkibiy qismidir.

example: If you are jealous, you think someone might take something from you.
type: Miriam was jealous because Sue was paying too much attention to Jim.
example_tr: Agar siz hasad qilsangiz, kimdir sizdan biror narsa olishi mumkin deb o'ylaysiz.
column14: Miriam rashkchi edi, chunki Syu Jimga haddan tashqari e'tibor berardi.

example: A paste is a thick and smooth substance.
type: My son needed some paste for a school project.
example_tr: Xamir qalin va silliq moddadir.
column14: O'g'limga maktab loyihasi uchun pasta kerak edi.

example: A receipt is a paper that proves that something was received or bought.
type: After looking at my receipt, I realized that I had spent too much money.
example_tr: Kvitansiya - biror narsa olingan yoki sotib olinganligini tasdiqlovchi qog'oz.
column14: Kvitansiyamga qarab, men juda ko'p pul sarflaganimni angladim.

example: To wipe something is to slide a piece of cloth over it to clean it.
type: She wiped the dust from the windows.
example_tr: Biror narsani artish, uni tozalash uchun uning ustiga mato bo'lagini siljitishdir.
column14: U derazalardagi changni artdi.

example: A wire is a thin string made out of metal.
type: The wires were connected to towers that brought electricity to the city.
example_tr: Tel - metalldan yasalgan ingichka ip.
column14: Simlar shaharga elektr energiyasi olib kiruvchi minoralarga ulangan.

example: If you acknowledge something, you accept that it is true or that it exists.
type: The teacher acknowledged that the young student was hungry.
example_tr: Agar biror narsani tan olsangiz, u haqiqat yoki uning mavjudligini qabul qilasiz.
column14: O‘qituvchi yosh talabaning och qolganini tan oldi.

example: An ambassador is a government worker who works in another country.
type: The ambassador from Korea was in charge of the conference.
example_tr: Elchi - boshqa davlatda ishlaydigan davlat xizmatchisi.
column14: Konferensiyaga Koreyadan kelgan elchi rahbarlik qildi.

example: If someone is a blonde, they have light-colored hair.
type: My cousin is different from me. She is a blonde with blue eyes.
example_tr: Agar kimdir sarg'ish bo'lsa, ular ochiq rangli sochlarga ega.
column14: Mening amakivachcham mendan farq qiladi. U ko'k ko'zli sarg'ish.

example: To conquer a country means to attack and take control of it.
type: The soldiers were trying to conquer the world.
example_tr: Bir mamlakatni zabt etish, unga hujum qilish va uni nazorat qilish demakdir.
column14: Askarlar dunyoni zabt etishga harakat qilishdi.

example: To drag something means to pull it across the ground.
type: The dog was dragging his owner down the street.
example_tr: Biror narsani sudrab olish uni yer bo'ylab tortib olishni anglatadi.
column14: It o‘z egasini ko‘chada sudrab borardi.

example: To exaggerate is to say that something is bigger or better than it really is.
type: Jimmy wasn’t exaggerating about the seriousness of his injury.
example_tr: Mubolag'a qilish - biror narsani haqiqatdan ham kattaroq yoki yaxshiroq deb aytish.
column14: Jimmi jarohatining jiddiyligi haqida bo'rttirib aytmadi.

example: Heritage is the collection of features of a society, such as language and religion.
type: Teepees are part of the heritage of the American Indians of the plains.
example_tr: Meros - bu jamiyatning til va din kabi xususiyatlarining yig'indisidir.
column14: Teepees tekislikdagi Amerika hindularining merosining bir qismidir.

example: To insult someone is to say things that will hurt their feelings.
type: The girls insulted each other all afternoon.
example_tr: Biror kishini haqorat qilish, uning his-tuyg'ularini ranjitadigan so'zlarni aytishdir.
column14: Qizlar tushdan keyin bir-birlarini haqorat qilishdi.

example: Meanwhile means until something happens or while something is happening.
type: He wants to be a doctor in the future, but meanwhile, he works a regular job.
example_tr: Ayni paytda, biror narsa sodir bo'lguncha yoki biror narsa sodir bo'lguncha degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: U kelajakda shifokor bo'lishni xohlaydi, lekin ayni paytda u oddiy ish bilan shug'ullanadi.

example: A necklace is a piece of jewelry that people wear around their necks.
type: Joyce receved a lovely pearl neckace for her wedding anniversayr.
example_tr: Marjon - odamlar bo'yniga taqib yuradigan zargarlik buyumlari.
column14: Joys nikoh yilligi munosabati bilan chiroyli marvarid marjonlarni oldi.

example: A noble is a rich and powerful person.
type: The Queen invited a noble from a nearby country to dinner.
example_tr: Zodagon - boy va qudratli odam.
column14: Qirolicha kechki ovqatga yaqin davlatdan zodagonni taklif qildi.

example: When something is precious, it is valuable and important.
type: In a desert, water can be more precious than money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qimmatli bo'lsa, u qimmatli va muhim bo'ladi.
column14: Cho'lda suv puldan qimmatroq bo'lishi mumkin.

example: A prejudice is an unfair opinion about someone before you get to know them.
type: The company’s rules against gender prejudice must be enforced.
example_tr: Noto'g'ri fikr - bu kimdir bilan tanishishdan oldin u haqida adolatsiz fikr.
column14: Kompaniyaning gender noto'g'ri qarashlariga qarshi qoidalari qo'llanilishi kerak.

example: A rumor is a story that may not be true.
type: Carla was spreading rumors around the office.
example_tr: Mish-mish - bu haqiqat bo'lmasligi mumkin bo'lgan voqea.
column14: Karla ofis atrofida mish-mishlar tarqatardi.

example: A sin is something that is wrong for religious reasons.
type: Taking something that doesn’t belong to you is a sin.
example_tr: Gunoh diniy sabablarga ko'ra noto'g'ri bo'lgan narsadir.
column14: Sizga tegishli bo'lmagan narsani olish gunohdir.

example: A spectacle is an amazing sight.
type: Niagara Falls is quite a spectacle.
example_tr: Tomosha - bu ajoyib manzara.
column14: Niagara sharsharasi juda ajoyib tomosha.

example: A stack is a pile of different things.
type: There was a stack of paperwork on his desk to complete.
example_tr: Stack - bu turli xil narsalar to'plami.
column14: Uning stolida to'ldirish uchun bir dasta qog'oz bor edi.

example: If someone is suspicious of someone else, they do not trust that person.
type: Dad was suspicious of the caller on the line.
example_tr: Agar kimdir boshqasidan shubhalansa, u odamga ishonmaydi.
column14: Dadam liniyada qo'ng'iroq qilgan odamdan shubhalanardi.

example: Tin is a cheap white metal.
type: Soup is a common food that is often sold in tin cans.
example_tr: Qalay arzon oq metalldir.
column14: Sho'rva ko'pincha qalay qutilarda sotiladigan keng tarqalgan taomdir.

example: If something is fiery, it is burning strongly.
type: The fiery blaze burned all night long.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa olovli bo'lsa, u kuchli yonmoqda.
column14: Olovli alanga tun bo'yi yondi.

example: Flesh is the skin, muscle and fat on your body.
type: The zebra’s flesh has black and white stripes.
example_tr: Go'sht tanangizdagi teri, mushak va yog'dir.
column14: Zebraning go'shti qora va oq chiziqlarga ega.

example: A grapefruit is a fruit similar to an orange, but bigger and not as sweet.
type: Would you like a grapefruit with your breakfast?
example_tr: Greypfrut apelsinga o'xshash meva, lekin kattaroq va unchalik shirin emas.
column14: Nonushta bilan greyfurt istaysizmi?

example: Hay is dry grass used to feed animals or used as a covering.
type: | need to buy some more hay for the horse to sleep on.
example_tr: Pichan - hayvonlarni boqish uchun ishlatiladigan yoki qoplama sifatida ishlatiladigan quruq o't.
column14: | ot uxlashi uchun yana bir oz pichan sotib olish kerak.

example: If you are horrified, you are very shocked and feel upset.
type: twas horrified when | read about the old lady who was attacked.
example_tr: Agar siz dahshatga tushsangiz, siz juda hayratdasiz va xafa bo'lasiz.
column14: twa dahshat qachon | hujumga uchragan kampir haqida o'qing.

example: Kerosene is a type of oil. Itis used in some lamps and stoves.
type: Many people in poor countries cook on kerosene stoves.
example_tr: Kerosin - neftning bir turi. U ba'zi lampalar va pechlarda ishlatiladi.
column14: Kambag'al mamlakatlardagi ko'p odamlar kerosin pechlarida pishiradi.

example: A loop is a line made into the shape of a circle.
type: He made a loop with the rope and placed it over the post.
example_tr: Loop - aylana shaklida qilingan chiziq.
column14: U arqon bilan halqa yasadi va uni ustun ustiga qo'ydi.

example: A paddle is a piece of wood or plastic that moves a boat across water.
type: We need a paddle to help us move across the water.
example_tr: Eshkak - qayiqni suv bo'ylab harakatlantiruvchi yog'och yoki plastmassa bo'lagi.
column14: Suv bo'ylab harakatlanishimizga yordam beradigan eshkak kerak.

example: A raft is a floating platform made from pieces of wood tied together.
type: The man made a raft out of bamboo and floated out to sea.
example_tr: Sal - bir-biriga bog'langan yog'och bo'laklaridan yasalgan suzib yuruvchi platforma.
column14: Odam bambukdan sal yasadi va dengizga suzib ketdi.

example: When something is sour, it has a sharp and unpleasant taste.
type: I don't like lemons because | think they are too sour.
example_tr: Biror narsa nordon bo'lsa, u o'tkir va yoqimsiz ta'mga ega.
column14: Men limonni yoqtirmayman, chunki | ular juda nordon deb o'ylayman.

example: A stake is a small, sharp piece of wood or metal that is put into the ground.
type: We marked our property by placing stakes into the ground.
example_tr: Qoziq - bu erga qo'yilgan kichik, o'tkir yog'och yoki metall bo'lak.
column14: Biz mulkimizni erga qoziq qo'yish orqali belgiladik.

example: A Steward is a person like a waiter who serves food on planes and ships.
type: The steward is bringing some tea.
example_tr: Styuard - bu samolyot va kemalarda ovqat beradigan ofitsiantga o'xshash odam.
column14: Styuard choy olib kelyapti.

example: String is a thin piece of fabric or rope.
type: | found a large ball of string.
example_tr: Ip - yupqa mato yoki arqon bo'lagi.
column14: | katta to'p ipni topdi.

example: A thorn is a sharp part of a plant.
type: Be careful of the thorns when you pick the roses!
example_tr: Tikan o'simlikning o'tkir qismidir.
column14: Atirgul terishda tikanlardan ehtiyot bo'ling!

example: To wreck something means to destroy or ruin it.
type: The teenagers wrecked the house for no reason at all.
example_tr: Biror narsani buzish, uni yo'q qilish yoki buzish demakdir.
column14: O'smirlar hech qanday sababsiz uyni vayron qilishdi.

example: To admonish someone is to tell them you disapprove of their behavior.
type: The teacher admonished Mark because he was chewing gum in class.
example_tr: Biror kishiga nasihat qilish, uning xatti-harakatidan norozi ekanligingizni aytishdir.
column14: O‘qituvchi Markni darsda saqich chaynagani uchun maslahat berdi.

example: If something is audible, then it is able to be heard.
type: The sound of the drums was audible from miles away.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa eshitilsa, u eshitilishi mumkin.
column14: Nog‘ora sadosi chaqirimlar uzoqdan ham eshitilardi.

example: If something or someone is awesome, they are impressive or frightening.
type: The huge military plane was an awesome sight.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir ajoyib bo'lsa, ular ta'sirli yoki qo'rqinchli.
column14: Ulkan harbiy samolyot ajoyib manzara edi.

example: To beware means to be careful of something or someone that is dangerous.
type: You should beware of driving fast on wet roads.
example_tr: Ehtiyot bo'lish, biror narsadan yoki xavfli narsadan ehtiyot bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Nam yo'llarda tez haydashdan ehtiyot bo'lishingiz kerak.

example: To brag means to talk of one’s abilities or achievements in a proud way.
type: He had strong muscles and bragged about it to the entire class.
example_tr: Maqtanish, o'z qobiliyatlari yoki yutuqlari haqida mag'rur tarzda gapirishni anglatadi.
column14: U kuchli mushaklarga ega edi va bu haqda butun sinfga maqtanardi.

example: If someone is conscious of something, then they are aware of it.
type: The new student was conscious of the other students staring at her.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsadan xabardor bo'lsa, demak u buni biladi.
column14: Yangi talaba boshqa talabalarning unga qarab turganini sezdi.

example: To disagree with someone means to have a different opinion from them.
type: The lawyers disagreed about the best way to settle the case.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan kelishmaslik, undan boshqacha fikrda bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Advokatlar ishni hal qilishning eng yaxshi yo'li bo'yicha kelisha olmadilar.

example: To echo means that a sound repeats itself because it bounced off an object.
type: The child yelled over the canyon, and the wall echoed the sound.
example_tr: Echo tovushning ob'ektdan sakrab o'tganligi sababli takrorlanishini anglatadi.
column14: Bola kanyon ustida qichqirdi va devor ovozini aks ettirdi.

example: If something is eventual, it will happen at the end of a series of events.
type: The constant training and planning led the team to an eventual victory.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yakuniy bo'lsa, u bir qator voqealar oxirida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Doimiy tayyorgarlik va rejalashtirish jamoani yakuniy g'alabaga olib keldi.

example: A hint is information that suggests something will happen or is true.
type: I quietly passed on a hint to my sister about the test.
example_tr: Maslahat - bu biror narsa sodir bo'lishini yoki haqiqat ekanligini ko'rsatadigan ma'lumot.
column14: Men sekingina singlimga test haqida bir maslahat berdim.

example: An idiot is a person who is not smart or who has done something silly.
type: Because he got lost in the forest, the man felt like an idiot.
example_tr: Ahmoq - aqlli bo'lmagan yoki ahmoqona ish qilgan odam.
column14: O'rmonda adashgani uchun odam o'zini ahmoqdek his qildi.

example: If something is immense, it is very large.
type: An immense amount of money was needed to buy such a large boat.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ulkan bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Bunday katta qayiqni sotib olish uchun juda katta pul kerak edi.

example: If something is indirect, then it is not the easiest or straightest way.
type: He chose to take the most indirect route to the coast.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa bilvosita bo'lsa, bu eng oson yoki eng to'g'ri yo'l emas.
column14: U qirg'oqqa eng bilvosita yo'lni tanladi.

example: An option is a choice between two or more things.
type: The children were given the option of three houses to pick from.
example_tr: Variant - bu ikki yoki undan ortiq narsa o'rtasidagi tanlov.
column14: Bolalarga uchta uydan tanlash imkoniyati berildi.

example: A pastime is an activity done for fun that you do often.
type: In the US, baseball is considered the national pastime.
example_tr: O'yin-kulgi - bu siz tez-tez qiladigan qiziqarli mashg'ulotdir.
column14: AQShda beysbol milliy o'yin-kulgi hisoblanadi.

example: If something is perfect, then it is without any mistakes.
type: She got all the questions right, so her score was perfect.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mukammal bo'lsa, u hech qanday xatosizdir.
column14: U barcha savollarni to'g'ri oldi, shuning uchun uning balli a'lo darajada edi.

example: To pinpoint something means to locate it exactly.
type: The navigation system in my car is able to pinpoint my exact location.
example_tr: Biror narsani aniq aniqlash, uni aniq aniqlashni anglatadi.
column14: Mashinamdagi navigatsiya tizimi mening aniq joylashuvimni aniqlay oladi.

example: To switch means to change something to something else.
type: Mom switched the TV station from the news to her favorite show.
example_tr: O'zgartirish, biror narsani boshqa narsaga o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Onam televizion stantsiyani yangiliklardan sevimli shousiga o'tkazdi.

example: If something or someone is thorough, then they are complete in every way.
type: Tina did a thorough job of cleaning the stains out of the carpet.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir puxta bo'lsa, unda ular har tomonlama to'liqdir.
column14: Tina gilamdagi dog‘larni yaxshilab tozaladi.

example: To torment someone means to cause them to suffer on purpose.
type: She tormented her little brother by taking his favorite toy.
example_tr: Birovni qiynash, uni ataylab qiynab qo'yish demakdir.
column14: U akasining sevimli o'yinchog'ini olib, uni qiynadi.

example: A beak is the hard curved part of a bird’s mouth.
type: The bird used her beak to dig a small hole in the ground.
example_tr: Gaga - qush og'zining qattiq kavisli qismi.
column14: Qush tumshug‘i bilan yerga kichik bir teshik qazdi.

example: If something is damp, it is somewhat wet.
type: My hair is still damp from my shower.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa nam bo'lsa, u biroz nam.
column14: Mening sochlarim hali ham dushdan nam.

example: To disapprove of something is to think that it is wrong.
type: Alex disapproved of his son’s behavior.
example_tr: Biror narsani rad etish - bu noto'g'ri deb o'ylash.
column14: Aleks o'g'lining xatti-harakatlarini ma'qullamadi.

example: You use except to talk about the only thing that a statement does not apply to.
type: Everyone had fun on the trip except Jim, who felt ill the whole time.
example_tr: Siz bayonotda qo'llanilmaydigan yagona narsa haqida gapirish uchun istisnadan foydalanasiz.
column14: Sayohatda hamma xursand bo'ldi, Jimdan tashqari, u doimo o'zini yomon his qildi.

example: A flight is an act of flying, often in an airplane.
type: The airplane made a flight around the world.
example_tr: Parvoz - bu ko'pincha samolyotda uchish harakati.
column14: Samolyot butun dunyo bo'ylab parvoz qildi.

example: When someone is fond of something, they like it.
type: I am very fond of chocolate cake.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi biror narsani yaxshi ko'rsa, unga yoqadi.
column14: Men shokoladli tortni juda yaxshi ko'raman.

example: When something or someone is immoral, they are evil or do bad things.
type: Stealing money from one's mother is an immoral act.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir axloqsiz bo'lsa, ular yomon yoki yomon ishlarni qiladilar.
column14: Onasidan pul o'g'irlash axloqsiz ishdir.

example: Ivy is a plant with long vines that grows upward typically on walls.
type: The walls of the castle are covered with ivy.
example_tr: Ivy - odatda devorlarda yuqoriga qarab o'sadigan uzun uzumli o'simlik.
column14: Qal'aning devorlari pechak bilan qoplangan.

example: To moan is to make a low sound when feeling pain or sadness.
type: The sick man moaned from his bed.
example_tr: Nola - og'riq yoki qayg'u his qilganda past ovoz chiqarish.
column14: Bemor to'shagidan nola qildi.

example: If someone is oblivious of something, they are unaware of it.
type: I was late to school because I was oblivious of the time.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsadan bexabar bo'lsa, u bundan bexabardir.
column14: Vaqtni unutganim uchun maktabga kechikdim.

example: To perish means to die, usually because of bad conditions or bad events.
type: Many people perish in wars.
example_tr: Halok bo'lish odatda yomon sharoitlar yoki yomon voqealar tufayli o'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Urushlarda ko'p odamlar halok bo'ladi.

example: A pit is a big hole in the ground.
type: Michael fell into the pit and needed some help to get out.
example_tr: Chuqur - bu erdagi katta teshik.
column14: Maykl chuqurga tushib ketdi va undan chiqish uchun yordam kerak edi.

example: The rim is the outside edge of a round thing, like a cup or bottle.
type: I put my lips to the rim of the bottle and took a drink.
example_tr: Jant - piyola yoki shisha kabi yumaloq narsaning tashqi qirrasi.
column14: Men lablarimni shishaning chetiga qo‘yib, ichimlik oldim.

example: A roost is a place where birds can land and rest or sleep.
type: The family of doves made a roost at the top of the tree.
example_tr: Roost - qushlar qo'nadigan va dam oladigan yoki uxlaydigan joy.
column14: Kabutarlar oilasi daraxt tepasida panoh yasadilar.

example: If something is slippery, it is wet or smooth and causes people to slip.
type: The repairman fell down on the floor because it was too slippery.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa silliq bo'lsa, u nam yoki silliq bo'lib, odamlarning sirpanishiga olib keladi.
column14: Ta'mirchi polga yiqilib tushdi, chunki u juda sirpanchiq edi.

example: To soar means to fly high in the air.
type: As the sun rose, two eagles soared through the sky.
example_tr: Parvoz qilish havoda baland uchishni anglatadi.
column14: Quyosh ko'tarilishi bilan osmonda ikkita burgut uchib ketdi.

example: If something is trivial, it is not important or meaningful.
type: Television is trivial, but learning to read is very important.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ahamiyatsiz bo'lsa, u muhim yoki mazmunli emas.
column14: Televizor arzimas narsa, lekin o'qishni o'rganish juda muhim.

example: If something is typical, it is normal for a certain type of thing.
type: Barking is typical behavior for dogs.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa odatiy bo'lsa, bu ma'lum bir turdagi narsa uchun normaldir.
column14: Hurish itlar uchun odatiy xatti-harakatlardir.

example: If something is utterly a way, it is completely that way.
type: When the sun was blocked by the moon, it was utterly dark outside.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa butunlay yo'l bo'lsa, u butunlay shunday.
column14: Quyoshni oy to‘sib qo‘yganida, tashqarida butunlay qorong‘i edi.

example: To weep means to cry.
type: My sister told me the dramatic movie would make me weep.
example_tr: Yig'lamoq yig'lamoq demakdir.
column14: Opam dramatik film meni yig'lab yuborishini aytdi.

example: If you do something awhile, you do it for a short time.
type: Wait here awhile, and I'll bring some tea.
example_tr: Agar siz biror narsa qilsangiz, uni qisqa vaqt ichida qilasiz.
column14: Shu yerda biroz kutib turing, men choy olib kelaman.

example: Cyberspace is the imaginary place of the Internet where activities occur.
type: I didn’t receive your email. It probably got lost in cyberspace.
example_tr: Kibermakon - bu faoliyat sodir bo'ladigan Internetning xayoliy joyi.
column14: Men sizning elektron pochtangizni olmadim. Ehtimol, u kiberkosmosda yo'qolgan.

example: To edit means to correct a piece of writing so that it is suitable to be published.
type: She asked her brother to edit her paper before she submitted it to her teacher.
example_tr: Tahrirlash yozuvni chop etishga yaroqli qilib tuzatish demakdir.
column14: U akasidan qog‘ozini o‘qituvchisiga topshirishdan oldin tahrir qilishni so‘radi.

example: An essay is a short piece of writing on a certain subject.
type: She had to write a two-page essay for her English class.
example_tr: Insho - bu ma'lum bir mavzu bo'yicha qisqacha yozma asar.
column14: U ingliz tili darsi uchun ikki sahifali insho yozishi kerak edi.

example: To evaluate something means to study it, so a decision can be made.
type: Joe and Ken evaluated the piano and agreed that it would work.
example_tr: Biror narsani baholash uni o'rganishni anglatadi, shuning uchun qaror qabul qilish mumkin.
column14: Jo va Ken pianinoni baholab, uning ishlashiga kelishib oldilar.

example: To faint means to go unconscious and fall down.
type: Carol fainted because she hadn’t eaten in over a day.
example_tr: Hushidan ketish hushidan ketish va yiqilish demakdir.
column14: Kerol hushidan ketdi, chunki u bir kundan ortiq ovqatlanmadi.

example: If something is global, it happens all around the world.
type: Pollution is a global problem.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa global bo'lsa, u butun dunyoda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Ifloslanish global muammodir.

example: A gymnasium is a building with equipment that you can use to get exercise.
type: When I go to the gymnasium, I use the treadmill for 20 minutes.
example_tr: Gimnaziya - bu mashq qilish uchun foydalanishingiz mumkin bo'lgan jihozlar bilan jihozlangan bino.
column14: Gimnaziyaga borganimda 20 daqiqa yugurish yo‘lakchasidan foydalanaman.

example: To highlight something means to mark it with a color so that it is easy to see
type: I read my vocabulary list and highlighted the most difficult words.
example_tr: Biror narsani ajratib ko'rsatish, uni ko'rish oson bo'lishi uchun uni rang bilan belgilashni anglatadi
column14: Men lug'at ro'yxatini o'qib chiqdim va eng qiyin so'zlarni ajratib ko'rsatdim.

example: If someone is ignorant about something, they have no knowledge about it.
type: I’m a bit ignorant about his theories. Can you explain them to me?
example_tr: Agar biror kishi biror narsadan bexabar bo'lsa, u haqida hech qanday ma'lumotga ega emas.
column14: Men uning nazariyalari haqida biroz bexabarman. Menga ularni tushuntirib bera olasizmi?

example: An index is a list of words at the end of a book that gives information.
type: If you look in the index, you’ll find the right page number.
example_tr: Indeks - bu kitob oxiridagi ma'lumot beruvchi so'zlar ro'yxati.
column14: Agar siz indeksga qarasangiz, to'g'ri sahifa raqamini topasiz.

example: A lecture is a long, educational speech.
type: His lecture on world hunger was very informative.
example_tr: Ma'ruza - bu uzoq, tarbiyaviy nutq.
column14: Uning dunyodagi ochlik haqidagi ma'ruzasi juda mazmunli edi.

example: A moral is a message at the end of a story that teaches you something.
type: At the end of the story, Mother explained the moral to the children.
example_tr: Axloq - bu sizga nimanidir o'rgatadigan hikoyaning oxiridagi xabar.
column14: Hikoyaning oxirida onasi bolalarga axloqni tushuntirdi.

example: To operate means to work or function.
type: I’m sorry, but the trains are not operating today.
example_tr: Ishlash, ishlash yoki ishlashni anglatadi.
column14: Kechirasiz, lekin bugun poyezdlar ishlamayapti.

example: If something is private, it is only used by one person or group.
type: Don’t look at my diary! It’s private!
example_tr: Agar biror narsa shaxsiy bo'lsa, u faqat bitta shaxs yoki guruh tomonidan ishlatiladi.
column14: Mening kundaligimga qaramang! Bu shaxsiy!

example: When something is recent, it happened a short time ago.
type: I did not know what caused his recent behavior.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yaqinda bo'lsa, u qisqa vaqt oldin sodir bo'lgan.
column14: Uning yaqindagi xatti-harakatlariga nima sabab bo'lganini bilmasdim.

example: A resolution is a personal decision.
type: At New Year, I made a list of resolutions to help me have a better year.
example_tr: Qaror - bu shaxsiy qaror.
column14: Yangi yilda men yilni yaxshiroq o'tkazishimga yordam beradigan qarorlar ro'yxatini tuzdim.

example: A semester is a portion of a school year.
type: Jack is in his second semester of college.
example_tr: Semestr - o'quv yilining bir qismi.
column14: Jek kollejning ikkinchi semestrida.

example: If something is typewritten, it is written on a computer or typewriter.
type: This is an important, formal project and must be typewritten.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yozuv mashinasida yozilgan bo'lsa, u kompyuter yoki yozuv mashinkasida yozilgan.
column14: Bu muhim, rasmiy loyiha bo'lib, yozuv mashinasida yozilishi kerak.

example: When something is weird, it is very strange.
type: My best friend’s dad is a bit weird.
example_tr: Biror narsa g'alati bo'lsa, u juda g'alati bo'ladi.
column14: Mening eng yaqin do'stimning dadasi biroz g'alati.

example: If something is absolute, it is total or complete.
type: My presentation was an absolute disaster! It was terrible!
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mutlaq bo'lsa, u to'liq yoki to'liqdir.
column14: Mening taqdimotim mutlaq falokat bo'ldi! Bu dahshatli edi!

example: Alas is a word that people say when something bad happens.
type: I looked everywhere for my purse, but alas, I couldn't find it.
example_tr: Voy, yomonlik yuz berganda aytadigan so'z.
column14: Hamma joyda hamyonimni qidirdim, afsuski, topolmadim.

example: If you are attentive, you are careful and you pay attention.
type: He is a good student because he is attentive to every detail on his work.
example_tr: Agar e'tiborli bo'lsangiz, siz ehtiyot bo'lasiz va diqqat qilasiz.
column14: U yaxshi talaba, chunki u o'z ishining har bir detaliga diqqat bilan qaraydi.

example: A cape is a large cloth that covers one’s back and is tied around the neck.
type: The superhero wore a long red cape.
example_tr: Qopqoq - bu odamning orqa qismini qoplaydigan va bo'yniga bog'langan katta mato.
column14: Superqahramon uzun qizil qalpoq kiygan.

example: To envision something means to imagine that it may happen.
type: I can envision my mom's face when I give her this present!
example_tr: Biror narsani tasavvur qilish - bu sodir bo'lishi mumkinligini tasavvur qilish demakdir.
column14: Men onamga sovg'ani berganimda uning yuzini tasavvur qila olaman!

example: When something happens evenly, it happens at the same rate or level.
type: The food was handed out evenly among the hungry people.
example_tr: Biror narsa bir tekis sodir bo'lganda, u bir xil tezlikda yoki darajada sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Ovqat och qolganlarga teng taqsimlangan.

example: Folk are common or average people.
type: I’ve invited all the folks from our street to a gathering at my place.
example_tr: Xalq oddiy yoki o'rtacha odamlardir.
column14: Men ko'chamizdagi barcha odamlarni o'z joyimdagi yig'ilishga taklif qildim.

example: To melt means to turn from a solid to a liquid.
type: The snowman that we made yesterday melted in the sun.
example_tr: Eritmoq qattiq holatdan suyuqlikka aylanmoq demakdir.
column14: Kecha biz yasagan qor odam quyoshda erib ketdi.

example: A patch is a part of a surface that is different in appearance from the rest.
type: There was one small patch of grass in the sand-covered desert.
example_tr: Yamoq - bu sirtning qolgan qismidan tashqi ko'rinishidan farq qiladigan qismi.
column14: Qum bilan qoplangan cho'lda kichik bir o't bo'lagi bor edi.

example: Pleasure is a feeling of happiness.
type: The student smiled with pleasure when she received the prize.
example_tr: Xursandchilik - bu baxt hissi.
column14: Talaba sovrinni olgach, zavq bilan jilmayib qo‘ydi.

example: A pop is a short, loud sound.
type: I heard a loud pop; then my computer screen shattered.
example_tr: Pop - bu qisqa, baland ovoz.
column14: Men baland ovozni eshitdim; keyin mening kompyuterim ekrani sinib ketdi.

example: A pudding is a sweet dessert.
type: Would you like some chocolate pudding and coffee for dessert?
example_tr: Puding - bu shirin desert.
column14: Shirinlik uchun shokoladli puding va kofe istaysizmi?

example: A rail is a horizontal bar made of metal or wood.
type: The cat was sitting on the rail of the fence.
example_tr: Rey - metall yoki yog'ochdan yasalgan gorizontal bar.
column14: Mushuk panjara panjarasida o'tirardi.

example: A recipe is a set of instructions to make food.
type: The apple cake that you made is really tasty. Can I have the recipe, please?
example_tr: Retsept - bu taom tayyorlash bo'yicha ko'rsatmalar to'plami.
column14: Siz tayyorlagan olma keki juda mazali. Iltimos, retseptni bera olamanmi?

example: A role is the normal purpose or function of a person or thing.
type: My role at work is to check the quality of the products.
example_tr: Rol - bu shaxs yoki narsaning normal maqsadi yoki funktsiyasi.
column14: Mening ishimdagi vazifam mahsulotlar sifatini tekshirishdan iborat.

example: To shrink means to get smaller.
type: If you stick to a healthy diet, your stomach will shrink!
example_tr: Kichraymoq, kichraymoq degani.
column14: Agar siz sog'lom ovqatlanishga rioya qilsangiz, oshqozoningiz qisqaradi!

example: To soak something means to make it very wet.
type: You need to soak these beans overnight before you cook them.
example_tr: Biror narsani ho'llash, uni juda nam qilish demakdir.
column14: Bu loviyalarni pishirishdan oldin bir kechada namlashingiz kerak.

example: A spark is a small, quick flash of fire.
type: As he welded the two pieces of metal together, sparks flew everywhere.
example_tr: Uchqun - bu yong'inning kichik, tez chaqnashi.
column14: U ikki bo‘lak metallni bir-biriga payvand qilar ekan, hamma joyda uchqunlar uchib ketdi.

example: A spirit is someone’s feelings and personality, but not a physical body part.
type: He has a very outgoing spirit. He can make friends with anyone.
example_tr: Ruh - bu kimningdir his-tuyg'ulari va shaxsiyati, ammo jismoniy tana qismi emas.
column14: U juda ochiq ruhga ega. U har kim bilan do'stlasha oladi.

example: A suit is a set of clothes. It usually includes a jacket with pants or a skirt.
type: I wore my new suit on my date with Melissa.
example_tr: Kostyum - bu kiyimlar to'plami. Odatda shim yoki yubka bilan ko'ylagi o'z ichiga oladi.
column14: Men Melissa bilan uchrashganimda yangi kostyumimni kiydim.

example: An account with a bank is an arrangement to keep one’s money there.
type: After I paid for the new car, my bank account was nearly empty.
example_tr: Bankdagi hisob - bu o'z pullarini u erda saqlash uchun kelishuv.
column14: Yangi mashina uchun pul to‘laganimdan so‘ng, bankdagi hisobim deyarli bo‘shab qoldi.

example: An architect is a person who designs buildings.
type: The plans for building the new home were drawn by a famous architect.
example_tr: Arxitektor - bu binolarni loyihalashtirgan shaxs.
column14: Yangi uy qurish rejalari mashhur me'mor tomonidan chizilgan.

example: To conceal something means to hide it.
type: You should conceal your money so no one can take it from you.
example_tr: Biror narsani yashirish uni yashirishni anglatadi.
column14: Pulingizni hech kim sizdan tortib ololmasligi uchun yashirishingiz kerak.

example: A crime is something bad that a person does that can be punished by law.
type: Police quickly arrived at the scene of the crime.
example_tr: Jinoyat - bu qonun bilan jazolanishi mumkin bo'lgan odam qilgan yomon narsa.
column14: Tez orada politsiya jinoyat joyiga yetib keldi.

example: A deed is a certificate that proves that someone owns something.
type: When she bought the car, she was given a deed to show the car was hers.
example_tr: Dalolatnoma - bu birovning biror narsaga egalik qilishini tasdiqlovchi guvohnoma.
column14: U mashinani sotib olgach, unga mashina uniki ekanligini ko'rsatish uchun hujjat berishgan.

example: Gratitude is a feeling of being thankful.
type: The kids showed Aunt Tess much gratitude for visiting them.
example_tr: Minnatdorchilik - bu minnatdorchilik hissi.
column14: Bolalar Tess xolaga tashrifi uchun minnatdorchilik bildirishdi.

example: A habitat is the natural home of animals or plants.
type: Frogs are often found in a wet habitat, such as near a lake, river, or pond.
example_tr: Yashash joyi - bu hayvonlar yoki o'simliklarning tabiiy uyi.
column14: Qurbaqalar ko'pincha nam muhitda, masalan, ko'l, daryo yoki hovuz yaqinida joylashgan.

example: To intervene means to help stop a problem between two people or groups.
type: The students argued until the teacher intervened.
example_tr: Aralashuv ikki kishi yoki guruh o'rtasidagi muammoni to'xtatishga yordam berishni anglatadi.
column14: O‘qituvchi gapga aralashguncha o‘quvchilar tortishib qolishdi.

example: A landmark is an object that helps people find or remember a location.
type: The tall tree was used as a landmark for people to find the road to the inn.
example_tr: Orientir - bu odamlarga joyni topish yoki eslab qolishga yordam beradigan ob'ekt.
column14: Uzun bo'yli daraxt odamlarning mehmonxonaga yo'l topishlari uchun nishon sifatida ishlatilgan.

example: If something is legal, it is related to the law or allowed by the law.
type: It was not legal for him to drive until he was eighteen years old.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qonuniy bo'lsa, u qonun bilan bog'liq yoki qonun bilan ruxsat etilgan.
column14: O‘n sakkiz yoshga to‘lguncha mashina haydashi qonuniy emas edi.

example: If something is memorable, then it is remembered for a special reason.
type: The party was memorable; people were still talking about it years later.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa esda qolarli bo'lsa, u alohida sababga ko'ra esda qoladi.
column14: Bayram esda qolarli bo'ldi; yillar o'tgandan keyin ham odamlar bu haqda gapirishdi.

example: To oblige someone means to require them to do something.
type: If I wanted to have playtime, I was obliged to clean my room once a week.
example_tr: Birovni majburlash, undan biror narsani talab qilish demakdir.
column14: Agar men o'yin vaqtini o'tkazmoqchi bo'lsam, haftada bir marta xonamni tozalashga majbur bo'ldim.

example: An offense is an action that breaks the law and requires punishment.
type: He was put in jail for two days for the offense.
example_tr: Huquqbuzarlik - bu qonunni buzadigan va jazoni talab qiladigan harakat.
column14: U jinoyat uchun ikki kunga qamoqqa tashlangan.

example: To proclaim something means to say it in public.
type: The army general proclaimed that the war was won.
example_tr: Biror narsani e'lon qilish, uni omma oldida aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Armiya generali urush g'alaba qozonganini e'lon qildi.

example: A rally is a large public meeting in order to support something.
type: The school had a rally in the gym to support the basketball team.
example_tr: Miting - bu biror narsani qo'llab-quvvatlash uchun ommaviy yig'ilish.
column14: Maktabning sport zalida basketbol jamoasini qo'llab-quvvatlash uchun miting bo'lib o'tdi.

example: To resolve something means to find a solution.
type: She resolved the problem with her children by giving them both a toy.
example_tr: Biror narsani hal qilish, yechim topishni anglatadi.
column14: Farzandlari bilan muammoni ikkalasiga ham o‘yinchoq berib hal qildi.

example: Resources are a person or country’s money and materials that they can use.
type: The poor man didn’t have the resources to feed himself.
example_tr: Resurslar - bu shaxs yoki mamlakatning pullari va ular foydalanishi mumkin bo'lgan materiallari.
column14: Kambag'alning o'zini boqish uchun mablag'i yo'q edi.

example: A sentence is punishment given to someone who didn’t follow the law.
type: The sentence for stealing a car is much worse than for stealing candy.
example_tr: Hukm - bu qonunga rioya qilmagan kishiga beriladigan jazo.
column14: Mashina o'g'irlash uchun jazo konfet o'g'irlashdan ko'ra yomonroqdir.

example: To volunteer means to offer to do something for free.
type: Many people volunteered to help the adults learn to read.
example_tr: Ko'ngilli bo'lish, biror narsani bepul qilishni taklif qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Ko'p odamlar kattalarga o'qishni o'rganishga yordam berish uchun ko'ngilli bo'lishdi.

example: A witness is someone who sees or hears a crime or accident happen.
type: The woman was the only witness of the horrible crime.
example_tr: Guvoh - jinoyat yoki baxtsiz hodisa sodir bo'lganini ko'rgan yoki eshitgan kishi.
column14: Ayol dahshatli jinoyatning yagona guvohi edi.

example: Access is the right to enter or use something.
type: The manager was the only person with access to the password.
example_tr: Kirish - biror narsaga kirish yoki undan foydalanish huquqi.
column14: Menejer parolga kirish huquqiga ega bo'lgan yagona shaxs edi.

example: Conduct is the way that someone acts.
type: She was punished for her bad conduct.
example_tr: Xulq-atvor - bu kimningdir harakat qilish usuli.
column14: U yomon xatti-harakati uchun jazolandi.

example: When an event or action is constant, it happens a lot or all the time.
type: The television at home is in constant use.
example_tr: Hodisa yoki harakat doimiy bo'lsa, u ko'p yoki doimo sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Uydagi televizor doimiy ravishda ishlatiladi.

example: A crack is a narrow space between the parts of something broken.
type: The old window was covered with cracks.
example_tr: Yoriq - singan narsaning qismlari orasidagi tor bo'shliq.
column14: Eski oyna yoriqlar bilan qoplangan.

example: A device is an object or a machine.
type: A thermometer is a device that tells temperature.
example_tr: Qurilma - bu ob'ekt yoki mashina.
column14: Termometr - bu haroratni ko'rsatadigan qurilma.

example: To enclose something is to contain it.
type: The cows in the field were enclosed by a fence.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rab olish - uni qamrab olish.
column14: Daladagi sigirlar panjara bilan o‘ralgan edi.

example: To grip something is to hold it very tightly.
type: I was scared, so I gripped my older sister's hand.
example_tr: Biror narsani ushlash - uni juda qattiq ushlab turish.
column14: Men qo‘rqib ketdim, shuning uchun katta opamning qo‘lidan ushlab oldim.

example: To halt is to stop moving.
type: The criminal halted when he saw the police coming.
example_tr: To'xtash - harakatni to'xtatish.
column14: Jinoyatchi politsiya kelayotganini ko‘rib, to‘xtab qoldi.

example: If something is impending, it is going to happen soon.
type: The student was nervous about his impending test.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yaqinlashayotgan bo'lsa, u tez orada sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Talaba yaqinlashib kelayotgan imtihonidan asabiy edi.

example: To influence someone or something is to have an effect over them.
type: My friend influenced my decision to attend Terrance University.
example_tr: Biror kishiga yoki biror narsaga ta'sir qilish, unga ta'sir qilishdir.
column14: Terrance universitetiga o'qishga kirishimga do'stim ta'sir ko'rsatdi.

example: A law is a rule made by the legislative body.
type: The students learned about different laws during social studies class.
example_tr: Qonun - bu qonun chiqaruvchi organ tomonidan ishlab chiqilgan qoida.
column14: Talabalar ijtimoiy fanlar darsi davomida turli qonunlar bilan tanishdilar.

example: A mode is a setting or condition on a machine.
type: Mother turned the TV to quiet mode while she talked on the phone.
example_tr: Rejim - bu mashinadagi sozlama yoki shart.
column14: Onam telefonda gaplashayotganda televizorni jim rejimga o'tkazdi.

example: To perspire means to sweat.
type: I usually perspire a lot when I am at practice.
example_tr: Terlash terlash demakdir.
column14: Men odatda mashg'ulot paytida juda ko'p terlayman.

example: To replace something is to put it in the place of something else.
type: I replaced the tire on my car because it was flat.
example_tr: Biror narsani almashtirish - uni boshqa narsaning o'rniga qo'yishdir.
column14: Men mashinamning shinasini almashtirdim, chunki u tekis edi.

example: To snap something means to break it suddenly, which causes a loud noise.
type: I took the stick and snapped it with my hands.
example_tr: Biror narsani sindirish uni to'satdan sindirishni anglatadi, bu esa baland shovqinga olib keladi.
column14: Men tayoqni olib, qo'llarim bilan urdim.

example: If a person or animal is sly, they are sneaky or good at tricking people.
type: The sly fox stole the eggs from the nest.
example_tr: Agar odam yoki hayvon ayyor bo'lsa, ular ayyor yoki odamlarni aldashda yaxshi.
column14: Ayyor tulki uyadagi tuxumlarni o‘g‘irlabdi.

example: To tend to do something is to be likely to do it or to do it often.
type: My mom tends to buy me the perfect gift each Christmas.
example_tr: Biror narsaga moyillik - bu ishni qilish yoki tez-tez qilishdir.
column14: Onam har Rojdestvoda menga eng zo'r sovg'a sotib olishga intiladi.

example: When something is valid, it is correct or based on good reasoning.
type: The expert's opinion on the subject was more valid than others.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ri bo'lsa, u to'g'ri yoki yaxshi fikrga asoslangan.
column14: Mutaxassisning bu boradagi fikri boshqalarga qaraganda ancha asosli edi.

example: A version is an account of something that differs slightly from the original.
type: She read the students British version of the Chinese fairy tale.
example_tr: Versiya - bu asl nusxadan biroz farq qiladigan narsaning hisobi.
column14: U talabalarga xitoy ertagining inglizcha versiyasini o'qidi.

example: You use whatsoever after a noun to emphasize that there is nothing of that thing.
type: The boy had no idea whatsoever how to solve the story problem.
example_tr: Siz bu narsaning hech narsasi yo'qligini ta'kidlash uchun otdan keyin nima bo'lsa ham ishlatasiz.
column14: Bola hikoya muammosini qanday hal qilishni bilmas edi.

example: If something is alongside another thing, then it is next to it.
type: We work alongside each other in the office.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsaning yonida bo'lsa, u uning yonida.
column14: Biz ofisda bir-birimiz bilan birga ishlaymiz.

example: Your appetite is your hunger for food.
type: Tom has a big appetite. He eats all the time.
example_tr: Sizning ishtahangiz ovqatga bo'lgan ochligingizdir.
column14: Tomning ishtahasi katta. U har doim ovqatlanadi.

example: To assist someone is to help them.
type: Andrew assisted me with my homework.
example_tr: Biror kishiga yordam berish, unga yordam berishdir.
column14: Endryu menga uy vazifasini bajarishda yordam berdi.

example: A breeze is a soft wind.
type: The breeze caused the leaves to fall off the tree.
example_tr: Shamol - bu yumshoq shamol.
column14: Shamol daraxtning barglarini to'kilishiga sabab bo'ldi.

example: To defy someone is to work against them or refuse to do what they say.
type: The students got into trouble for defying their teacher's rules.
example_tr: Biror kishiga qarshi chiqish, unga qarshi ishlash yoki uning aytganlarini qilishdan bosh tortishdir.
column14: Talabalar o'qituvchining qoidalarini buzgani uchun muammoga duch kelishdi.

example: To display something is to show it, especially by putting it in a certain place.
type: The museum displayed many wonderful paintings.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rsatish - uni ko'rsatish, ayniqsa uni ma'lum bir joyga qo'yish.
column14: Muzeyda ko'plab ajoyib rasmlar namoyish etildi.

example: If something or someone is efficient, they do not waste energy.
type: My car is very efficient. I rarely have to buy gas.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir samarali bo'lsa, ular energiyani behuda sarflamaydilar.
column14: Mening mashinam juda samarali. Men kamdan-kam hollarda benzin sotib olishim kerak.

example: If someone is feeble, they are small or weak.
type: The boy was too feeble to carry the object very far.
example_tr: Agar kimdir zaif bo'lsa, u kichik yoki zaifdir.
column14: Bola juda ojiz bo'lib, buyumni juda uzoqqa ko'tara olmadi.

example: To forgive someone is to stop being angry with them.
type: Sandra forgave Peter after he said he was sorry.
example_tr: Biror kishini kechirish, unga g'azablanishni to'xtatishdir.
column14: Sandra Butrusni kechirganini aytganidan keyin kechirdi.

example: If someone is lively, they have a lot of energy.
type: Jennifer is very lively: she’s always running and playing.
example_tr: Agar kimdir jonli bo'lsa, unda juda ko'p energiya bor.
column14: Jennifer juda jonli: u doimo yuguradi va o'ynaydi.

example: If something is majestic, it is large and beautiful.
type: The rich people lived in a big, majestic house.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ulug'vor bo'lsa, u katta va chiroyli.
column14: Katta, mahobatli uyda boylar yashar edi.

example: You use nor to connect two negative ideas.
type: I eat neither apples nor oranges. I don’t like either one.
example_tr: Siz ikkita salbiy fikrni bog'lash uchun yoki ishlatasiz.
column14: Men na olma, na apelsin yemayman. Men ikkalasini ham yoqtirmayman.

example: If someone is outraged, they are very angry.
type: My father was outraged when he saw that I had crashed his car.
example_tr: Agar kimdir g'azablansa, ular juda g'azablangan.
column14: Otam mashinasini urib yuborganimni ko‘rib, jahli chiqdi.

example: If someone is pessimistic, they believe that the worst will happen.
type: John is pessimistic. He always thinks something bad will happen.
example_tr: Agar kimdir pessimistik bo'lsa, u eng yomoni sodir bo'lishiga ishonadi.
column14: Jon pessimistik. U har doim yomon narsa bo'ladi deb o'ylaydi.

example: A rumor is a story that may not be true.
type: Carla was spreading rumors around the office.
example_tr: Mish-mish - bu haqiqat bo'lmasligi mumkin bo'lgan voqea.
column14: Karla ofis atrofida mish-mishlar tarqatardi.

example: To slap someone means to hit them with the palm of the hand.
type: Out of anger, Helen slapped Eunice on the face.
example_tr: Biror kishiga shapaloq urish, uni kaft bilan urish demakdir.
column14: Jahli chiqqan Xelen Yunisning yuziga shapaloq urdi.

example: To smash something is to break it into many small pieces.
type: Jacob smashed the window with a rock.
example_tr: Biror narsani sindirish - uni ko'p mayda bo'laklarga bo'lish.
column14: Yoqub derazani tosh bilan sindirdi.

example: A subject is the topic that is being discussed or taught.
type: The subject of Marco's speech was the economy.
example_tr: Mavzu - bu muhokama qilinadigan yoki o'qitiladigan mavzu.
column14: Marko nutqining mavzusi iqtisod edi.

example: A wage is the money that a person gets for doing a job.
type: The wages I receive from my job are really great!
example_tr: Ish haqi - bu odamning ishni bajarishi uchun oladigan pulidir.
column14: Ishimdan oladigan maoshim haqiqatan ham ajoyib!

example: You use whereas to show how two things are different.
type: My sister loves horror movies, whereas I prefer comedies.
example_tr: Ikki narsa bir-biridan qanday farq qilishini ko'rsatish uchun siz while dan foydalanasiz.
column14: Singlim dahshatli filmlarni yaxshi ko'radi, men esa komediyalarni afzal ko'raman.

example: When something is animate, it has life.
type: Rocks and machines are not animate things.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jonli bo'lsa, unda hayot bo'ladi.
column14: Toshlar va mashinalar jonli narsalar emas.

example: To classify things is to put them into groups based on their type.
type: The biologist classified the plant as a completely new species.
example_tr: Narsalarni tasniflash - ularni turiga qarab guruhlarga bo'lishdir.
column14: Biolog o'simlikni mutlaqo yangi tur sifatida tasnifladi.

example: To concede is to admit that something is true against your wish.
type: The student conceded that he had cheated on the test.
example_tr: Qabul qilish - bu sizning xohishingizga qarshi biror narsa haqiqat ekanligini tan olishdir.
column14: Talaba testda aldaganini tan oldi.

example: A concept is an idea about something.
type: I learned some concepts of molecules before working in the science lab.
example_tr: Kontseptsiya - bu biror narsa haqidagi fikr.
column14: Ilmiy laboratoriyada ishlashdan oldin molekulalar haqidagi ba'zi tushunchalarni o'rgandim.

example: To construct something means to make or build it.
type: The men used wood and metal to construct a house.
example_tr: Biror narsani qurish, uni yasash yoki qurish demakdir.
column14: Erkaklar uy qurish uchun yog'och va metalldan foydalanganlar.

example: A decade is a period of ten years.
type: She celebrated her three decades of work with the company.
example_tr: O'n yil - bu o'n yillik davr.
column14: U kompaniyadagi o'ttiz yillik ishini nishonladi.

example: A diagram is a simple drawing that explains what something is or how it works.
type: By following the diagram, I was able to put the desk together.
example_tr: Diagramma - bu nima ekanligini yoki qanday ishlashini tushuntirib beradigan oddiy chizma.
column14: Diagrammaga rioya qilib, men stolni bir joyga qo'yishga muvaffaq bo'ldim.

example: A ferry is a boat that carries passengers over short distances.
type: The ferry took the people across the lake.
example_tr: Parom - qisqa masofalarga yo'lovchilarni tashiydigan qayiq.
column14: Parom odamlarni ko‘l bo‘ylab olib ketdi.

example: If something is handy, it is useful.
type: An eraser is handy if you make a lot of mistakes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qulay bo'lsa, u foydalidir.
column14: Agar siz ko'p xato qilsangiz, o'chirgich qulay.

example: To isolate is to separate one person or thing from a group.
type: The teacher isolated the bad child from the class before talking with her.
example_tr: Izolyatsiya qilish - bir kishi yoki narsalarni guruhdan ajratish.
column14: O'qituvchi yomon bolani u bilan gaplashishdan oldin sinfdan ajratib qo'ydi.

example: A longing is a strong feeling of wanting.
type: Since he skipped breakfast, he had a longing for food all morning.
example_tr: Sog'inch - bu kuchli istak hissi.
column14: U nonushtani o'tkazib yuborgani uchun ertalabdan ovqatga intildi.

example: If something is numerous, there are many of those things.
type: It was hard to drive fast since there were numerous holes in the road.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ko'p bo'lsa, bunday narsalar juda ko'p.
column14: Tez haydash qiyin edi, chunki yo'lda ko'plab teshiklar bor edi.

example: A particle is a very small piece of something.
type: The bottles of wine were covered in a layer of dust particles.
example_tr: Zarracha - bu narsaning juda kichik qismi.
column14: Sharob shishalari chang zarralari qatlami bilan qoplangan.

example: A plea is a request that is urgent or emotional.
type: The poor, hungry man made a plea for food.
example_tr: Iltimos - bu shoshilinch yoki hissiy so'rov.
column14: Kambag'al, och odam ovqat uchun iltimos qildi.

example: To refrain from something is to avoid doing it.
type: The doctor asked Mary to refrain from eating fast food as part of her diet.
example_tr: Biror narsadan saqlanish, uni qilishdan qochishdir.
column14: Shifokor Meridan dietasining bir qismi sifatida tez ovqatlanishdan voz kechishni so'radi.

example: A review of something is a formal inspection of it by people in authority.
type: The government ordered a careful review of the economic situation.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rib chiqish - bu hokimiyatdagi odamlar tomonidan uni rasmiy tekshirish.
column14: Hukumat iqtisodiy vaziyatni diqqat bilan ko'rib chiqishni buyurdi.

example: If someone is sophisticated, they know many things about the world.
type: Jake is one of the most sophisticated persons I’ve ever met.
example_tr: Agar kimdir murakkab bo'lsa, u dunyo haqida ko'p narsalarni biladi.
column14: Jeyk men uchrashgan eng murakkab odamlardan biri.

example: To surrender something is to give it up.
type: The thief surrendered the money to the police when he was caught.
example_tr: Biror narsani taslim qilish - undan voz kechish.
column14: O‘g‘ri qo‘lga olinganda pulni politsiyaga topshirgan.

example: If something is upright, it is standing up straight.
type: Meerkats can’t walk like humans, but they can stand upright.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tik turgan bo'lsa, u tik turadi.
column14: Meerkats odamlar kabi yura olmaydi, lekin ular tik turishi mumkin.

example: If something is worthwhile, it is important or useful.
type: On his visit to Canada, he realized studying English was worthwhile.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa foydali bo'lsa, u muhim yoki foydalidir.
column14: Kanadaga tashrifi chog'ida u ingliz tilini o'rganish foydali ekanligini tushundi.

example: An alliance is a group of people who work together.
type: The junior executives formed an alliance with each other.
example_tr: Ittifoq - bu birgalikda ishlaydigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Kichik rahbarlar bir-biri bilan ittifoq tuzdilar.

example: Applause is the noise made when people clap hands to show approval.
type: At the end of his speech, everyone gave applause.
example_tr: Qarsaklar - bu odamlar ma'qullash uchun qo'l urishganda paydo bo'ladigan shovqin.
column14: Uning so‘zi so‘ngida hamma olqishlar qildi.

example: If you are armed, you are carrying a weapon.
type: The robber was armed with a gun.
example_tr: Agar siz qurollangan bo'lsangiz, siz qurol olib yurasiz.
column14: Qaroqchi qurol bilan qurollangan.

example: If something is authoritative, it uses the best information available.
type: This book is an authoritative source on Ancient Egypt’s Queen Nefertiti
example_tr: Agar biror narsa obro'li bo'lsa, u mavjud bo'lgan eng yaxshi ma'lumotdan foydalanadi.
column14: Bu kitob Qadimgi Misr malikasi Nefertiti haqidagi nufuzli manbadir

example: A ceremony is an event that happens on special occasions.
type: Tom and Amy’s marriage ceremony is in June.
example_tr: Marosim - bu alohida holatlarda sodir bo'ladigan voqea.
column14: Tom va Emining nikoh marosimi iyun oyida bo'lib o'tadi.

example: Culture is the music, art, and writings of a certain place or group of people.
type: Ancient Mexican culture is renowned for its architecture.
example_tr: Madaniyat - bu ma'lum bir joy yoki odamlar guruhining musiqasi, san'ati va yozuvlari.
column14: Qadimgi Meksika madaniyati o'zining me'morchiligi bilan mashhur.

example: A defense is something that is done to protect another thing.
type: The air force works in defense of its country.
example_tr: Himoya - bu boshqa narsani himoya qilish uchun qilingan narsa.
column14: Harbiy havo kuchlari o'z mamlakatini himoya qilish uchun ishlaydi.

example: A detail is a small piece of information.
type: Jane told Ben all the details of her trip to China
example_tr: Tafsilot - bu kichik ma'lumot.
column14: Jeyn Benga Xitoyga qilgan safarining barcha tafsilotlarini aytib berdi

example: When a group of things is diverse, it is made up of a wide variety of things.
type: Big cities have diverse populations with people of different races and ages.
example_tr: Bir guruh narsalar xilma-xil bo'lsa, u juda xilma-xil narsalardan iborat.
column14: Katta shaharlar turli irq va yoshdagi odamlardan iborat turli xil aholiga ega.

example: To enchant someone is to make them feel very interested or happy.
type: The beautiful woman enchanted everybody in the room.
example_tr: Biror kishini sehrlash, uni juda qiziqtirish yoki xursand qilishdir.
column14: Go'zal ayol xonadagi barchani sehrlab qo'ydi.

example: To equip someone is to give them the things needed to do something.
type: Steve was equipped with the tools needed to do the job.
example_tr: Biror kishini jihozlash, unga biror narsa qilish uchun zarur bo'lgan narsalarni berishdir.
column14: Stiv ishni bajarish uchun zarur vositalar bilan jihozlangan edi.

example: An exception is someone or something not conforming to a rule.
type: Most students thought the test was hard, but Tim was the exception.
example_tr: Istisno - bu qoidaga mos kelmaydigan kimdir yoki narsa.
column14: Aksariyat talabalar testni qiyin deb o'ylashgan, ammo Tim bundan mustasno edi.

example: A genre is a type of literature, art, or music characterized by its style.
type: She is considered a master in the comedy genre.
example_tr: Janr - bu o'z uslubi bilan ajralib turadigan adabiyot, san'at yoki musiqa turi.
column14: U komediya janrida usta sanaladi.

example: An impact is the effect someone or something has on another.
type: My grandmother had a great impact on my life.
example_tr: Ta'sir - bu kimdir yoki biror narsaning boshqasiga ta'siri.
column14: Mening buvim hayotimga katta ta'sir ko'rsatdi.

example: To lure someone is to convince them to do something, by using a trick.
type: The store lures people in with big signs that say “Sale!”
example_tr: Biror kishini o'ziga jalb qilish - hiyla ishlatib, uni biror narsa qilishga ishontirishdir.
column14: Do‘kon odamlarni “Sotish!” degan katta yozuvlar bilan o‘ziga tortadi.

example: An obstacle is an object or a problem that stops you from doing something.
type: Climbing over the giant rock was the biggest obstacle for the hikers.
example_tr: To'siq - bu sizni biror narsa qilishdan to'xtatadigan narsa yoki muammo.
column14: Sayyohlar uchun ulkan qoya ustiga chiqish eng katta to‘siq bo‘ldi.

example: A shelter is a place to go that is safe from danger or bad weather.
type: The frog took shelter from the storm in a nearby cave.
example_tr: Boshpana - bu xavfdan yoki yomon ob-havodan xavfsiz bo'lgan joy.
column14: Baqa bo'rondan yaqin atrofdagi g'orga panoh topdi.

example: To sort means to separate things into different groups or classes.
type: He sorted his clothes by colors and sizes.
example_tr: Saralash narsalarni turli guruhlarga yoki sinflarga ajratishni anglatadi.
column14: U kiyimlarini rangi va o'lchamiga qarab saralagan.

example: To supply something means to give people what they need or want.
type: The water heater supplied the house with warm water.
example_tr: Biror narsani etkazib berish, odamlarga kerakli yoki xohlagan narsani berishni anglatadi.
column14: Suv isitgichi uyni iliq suv bilan ta'minladi.

example: If people are vain, they are only concerned with how they look.
type: Rebecca is so vain that she looks at herself in every mirror.
example_tr: Agar odamlar behuda bo'lsa, ular faqat tashqi ko'rinishi bilan shug'ullanishadi.
column14: Rebekka shunchalik behudaki, u har oynada o'ziga qaraydi.

example: An alternative is something that you can choose instead of your first choice.
type: Her first plan to make extra money seemed weak, so she chose an alternative.
example_tr: Muqobil - bu sizning birinchi tanlovingiz o'rniga tanlashingiz mumkin bo'lgan narsadir.
column14: Uning qo'shimcha pul topish bo'yicha birinchi rejasi zaif bo'lib tuyuldi, shuning uchun u muqobilni tanladi.

example: An avenue is a road, often a large one with buildings on each side.
type: Drive down this avenue and then turn left to go to the park.
example_tr: Avenue - bu ko'pincha katta yo'l bo'lib, har ikki tomonida binolar mavjud.
column14: Ushbu xiyobondan pastga tushing va keyin parkga borish uchun chapga buriling.

example: The belly is the stomach of a person or animal.
type: His belly was full because he ate a lot of food.
example_tr: Qorin - bu odam yoki hayvonning oshqozoni.
column14: Ko‘p ovqat yegani uchun qorni to‘q edi.

example: A bid to do something is an attempt to do it.
type: He made a bid to become the university’s next president.
example_tr: Biror narsani qilish taklifi - bu ishni qilishga urinish.
column14: U universitetning keyingi prezidenti bo'lish uchun taklif qildi.

example: To blow means to move air or move something through the air, as in the wind.
type: The wind is blowing very hard today. We should stay inside.
example_tr: Puflash, shamolda bo'lgani kabi, havoni ko'chirish yoki havoda biror narsani harakatlantirishni anglatadi.
column14: Bugun shamol juda qattiq esmoqda. Biz ichkarida qolishimiz kerak.

example: A conflict is a fight between different people or groups.
type: The two nations had a conflict over which one could use the water in the river
example_tr: Mojaro - bu turli odamlar yoki guruhlar o'rtasidagi kurash.
column14: Ikki xalq o'rtasida daryodagi suvdan qaysi biri foydalanish mumkinligi haqida kelishmovchilik bor edi

example: A continent is one of the seven large areas of land on the Earth.
type: Asia is the largest continent.
example_tr: Qit'a - Yerdagi etti yirik quruqlikdan biri.
column14: Osiyo eng katta qit'adir.

example: A current is a steady and constant flow of air or water in a river or ocean.
type: The ocean currents took the ship far off into the sea,
example_tr: Oqim daryo yoki okeandagi havo yoki suvning barqaror va doimiy oqimidir.
column14: Okean oqimlari kemani dengizga olib ketdi,

example: Disrespect is rudeness or a behavior that shows a lack of respect.
type: He showed disrespect by arguing with his boss during a meeting.
example_tr: Hurmatsizlik - bu qo'pollik yoki hurmatsizlikni ko'rsatadigan xatti-harakatlar.
column14: Yig‘ilish vaqtida boshlig‘i bilan janjallashib, hurmatsizlik qilgan.

example: Enthusiasm is a very strong good feeling about something.
type: The crowd showed their enthusiasm for the soccer team by cheering loudly,
example_tr: G'ayrat - bu biror narsaga nisbatan juda kuchli yaxshi tuyg'u.
column14: Olomon baland ovozda olqishlab, futbol jamoasiga bo'lgan ishtiyoqini namoyish etdi,

example: When something is harsh, it is very unpleasant.
type: The desert can be a very harsh environment.
example_tr: Biror narsa qattiq bo'lsa, bu juda yoqimsiz.
column14: Cho'l juda qattiq muhit bo'lishi mumkin.

example: To lean is to bend the body in a particular direction.
type: The woman leaned against the counter because she was tired.
example_tr: Suyanmoq - tanani ma'lum bir yo'nalishda egishdir.
column14: Ayol charchaganidan peshtaxtaga suyandi.

example: The meantime is the time between two events.
type: Ted began setting the table. In the meantime, I began preparing the food.
example_tr: Bu ikki hodisa orasidagi vaqt.
column14: Ted dasturxon yoza boshladi. Bu orada men ovqat tayyorlashni boshladim.

example: Mischief is behavior that is meant to trick or cause trouble for people.
type: Ben was up to mischief when he persuaded Ken to paint his face.
example_tr: Buzg'unchilik - bu odamlarni aldash yoki muammo tug'dirish uchun qilingan xatti-harakatlardir.
column14: Ben Kenni yuzini bo'yashga ko'ndirganda, fitna uyushtirgan edi.

example: Muscle is a mass of tissue attached to bone that helps you move.
type: She went to the gym in order to make her muscles stronger.
example_tr: Mushak - bu suyakka biriktirilgan to'qimalarning massasi bo'lib, u harakatga yordam beradi.
column14: U mushaklarini kuchaytirish uchun sport zaliga bordi.

example: To rescue someone means to remove them from danger.
type: The firefighter rescued the man from the burning building.
example_tr: Biror kishini qutqarish, uni xavfdan olib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: O‘t o‘chiruvchi odamni yonayotgan binodan qutqarib oldi.

example: A succession is a number of things that follow one after the other.
type: The student said the letters of the alphabet in succession.
example_tr: Vorislik - bu birin-ketin keladigan narsalar soni.
column14: Talaba alifbodagi harflarni ketma-ket aytdi.

example: The terrain is the land and all of its physical features or parts.
type: The terrain below was rocky and full of hills.
example_tr: Relyef - quruqlik va uning barcha jismoniy xususiyatlari yoki qismlari.
column14: Pastdagi yer toshloq va tepaliklarga to'la edi.

example: If someone is timid, they are afraid, shy, or nervous.
type: The timid child hides behind her mother whenever she sees a stranger.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qo'rqoq bo'lsa, u qo'rqadi, uyatchan yoki asabiylashadi.
column14: Qo'rqoq bola har safar begona odamni ko'rsa, onasining orqasiga yashirinadi.

example: Violence is forceful action that is meant to injure or kill people.
type: The boy hit his brother in an act of violence.
example_tr: Zo'ravonlik - bu odamlarni jarohatlash yoki o'ldirishga qaratilgan zo'ravonlik harakati.
column14: Bola akasini zo‘ravonlik bilan urgan.

example: To affect someone or something is to have an influence over them.
type: The student’s poor attitude affected the other students in the class.
example_tr: Birovga yoki biror narsaga ta'sir qilish, unga ta'sir qilishdir.
column14: Talabaning yomon munosabati sinfdagi boshqa o'quvchilarga ta'sir qildi.

example: An autograph is the written name of a famous person.
type: Everybody wanted the movie star’s autograph.
example_tr: Avtograf - taniqli shaxsning yozma ismi.
column14: Hamma kino yulduzining avtografini olishni xohlardi.

example: A bead is a drop of liquid.
type: Beads of water collected outside the glass.
example_tr: Boncuk bir tomchi suyuqlikdir.
column14: Stakan tashqarisida to'plangan suv boncuklar.

example: To brew coffee or tea means to pour hat water over it.
type: Please brew a fresh pot of coffee.
example_tr: Qahva yoki choyni qaynatish uning ustiga shlyapa suvini quyishni anglatadi.
column14: Iltimos, yangi kofe qaynatib oling.

example: To charm someone is to please them with your personality.
type: Gail charmed everyone with her humorous stories.
example_tr: Biror kishini maftun etish, uni shaxsiyatingiz bilan xursand qilishdir.
column14: Geyl o'zining kulgili hikoyalari bilan barchani maftun etdi.

example: A destiny is all the things that happen or will happen to a person in their life,
type: It was his destiny to become a great singer.
example_tr: Taqdir - bu inson hayotida sodir bo'ladigan yoki sodir bo'ladigan barcha narsalar,
column14: Uning taqdiri buyuk qo‘shiqchi bo‘lish edi.

example: A horn is a device that makes a loud noise.
type: The boy honked his horn while he rode his bicycle past the house.
example_tr: Shox - bu baland ovoz chiqaradigan qurilma.
column14: Velosipedda uy yonidan o‘tayotganda bola shoxli signal berdi.

example: When someone is irritable, they become annoyed or angry very easily.
type: She is irritable when she doesn’t get enough sleep.
example_tr: Biror kishi asabiy bo'lsa, u juda tez g'azablanadi yoki g'azablanadi.
column14: U etarlicha uxlamasa, asabiylashadi.

example: To lag behind is to move slowly behind other moving objects.
type: The girl on rollerblades lagged behind the little girl on the bicycle.
example_tr: Orqada qolish - boshqa harakatlanuvchi jismlarning orqasida sekin harakat qilish.
column14: Rolikdagi qiz velosipeddagi kichkina qizdan orqada qoldi.

example: To maximize something means to make it the biggest in size or amount.
type: Businesses try to maximize their profits.
example_tr: Biror narsani maksimal darajada oshirish, uni hajmi yoki miqdori bo'yicha eng katta qilish demakdir.
column14: Korxonalar o'z daromadlarini maksimal darajada oshirishga harakat qilishadi.

example: A nightmare is a bad or scary dream.
type: The girl was scared to go back to sleep because she had a nightmare.
example_tr: Dahshatli tush - yomon yoki qo'rqinchli tush.
column14: Qiz dahshatli tush ko'rgani uchun uxlab qolishdan qo'rqib ketdi.

example: When something is nutritious, it helps the body stay healthy.
type: Mangoes are one of the most nutritious fruits in the world.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'yimli bo'lsa, u tananing sog'lom bo'lishiga yordam beradi.
column14: Mango dunyodagi eng to'yimli mevalardan biridir.

example: Protein is a substance that is necessary for the body to grow and be strong.
type: Fish and beef are good sources of protein.
example_tr: Protein - bu tananing o'sishi va kuchli bo'lishi uchun zarur bo'lgan moddadir.
column14: Baliq va mol go'shti yaxshi protein manbalaridir.

example: A signature is your name that you have written in your own way.
type: I put my signature at the end of the letter.
example_tr: Imzo - bu o'zingiz yozgan ismingiz.
column14: Xat oxiriga imzo qo‘ydim.

example: Stuff is a word used to refer to things without mentioning the things by name.
type: We gave a lot of stuff to the charity.
example_tr: Narsa - bu narsalarni nomi bilan zikr qilmasdan narsalarni ifodalash uchun ishlatiladigan so'z.
column14: Biz xayriyaga ko'p narsalarni berdik.

example: When something is subconscious, it is done without thinking about it.
type: Breathing is one of the subconscious things that the body does.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ongsiz bo'lsa, u bu haqda o'ylamasdan amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Nafas olish - bu tananing ongli ravishda qiladigan ishlaridan biridir.
