example: A van is a vehicle that is used for carrying things but is smaller than a truck.
type: The delivery company uses large vans to deliver packages.
example_tr: Furgon - bu narsalarni tashish uchun ishlatiladigan, ammo yuk mashinasidan kichikroq transport vositasi.
column14: Yetkazib berish kompaniyasi paketlarni yetkazib berish uchun katta furgonlardan foydalanadi.

example: To warn someone is to make them know of possible danger in the future.
type: The lifeguard warned people to stay away from the rough ocean.
example_tr: Biror kishini ogohlantirish, uni kelajakda yuzaga kelishi mumkin bo'lgan xavf haqida xabardor qilishdir.
column14: Qutqaruvchi odamlarni okeandan uzoqroq turish haqida ogohlantirgan.

example: A workout is an exercise routine that helps improve health.
type: She doesn’t do her workout on the weekends,
example_tr: Mashq - bu salomatlikni yaxshilashga yordam beradigan mashqlar tartibi.
column14: U dam olish kunlari mashq qilmaydi,

example: To zoom is to move quickly.
type: The cars zoomed along the road.
example_tr: Kattalashtirish - bu tez harakat qilish.
column14: Mashinalar yo'l bo'ylab kattalashib ketishdi.

example: A brick is a block of hard clay that is used for building things, such as walls.
type: There were several bricks scattered on the ground.
example_tr: G'isht - bu devorlar kabi narsalarni qurish uchun ishlatiladigan qattiq loy blokidir.
column14: Yerga bir nechta g‘isht sochilib yotibdi.

example: To crumble means to break or fall apart into small pieces.
type: The old house’s walls crumbled into a pile of rock and wood.
example_tr: Buzilish - mayda bo'laklarga bo'linish yoki parchalanish demakdir.
column14: Qadimgi uyning devorlari tosh va yog'och uyumiga qulab tushdi.

example: Dough is a mixture of flour and water that becomes bread when baked.
type: I made heart-shaped cookies from the dough.
example_tr: Xamir un va suv aralashmasi bo'lib, pishirilganda nonga aylanadi.
column14: Xamirdan yurak shaklidagi pechenye tayyorladim.

example: To express a feeling or idea means to show others how one thinks or feels.
type: The nurse expressed her sympathy for the sick patient.
example_tr: Tuyg'u yoki fikrni ifodalash, boshqalarga qanday fikrda ekanligini yoki his qilishini ko'rsatishni anglatadi.
column14: Hamshira kasal bemorga hamdardlik bildirdi.

example: A fist is a hand with fingers bent in toward the palm.
type: The bully made a fist and threatened to hit the small boy.
example_tr: Musht - barmoqlari kaftga egilgan qo'l.
column14: Bezori musht qilib, kichkina bolani urish bilan tahdid qildi.

example: If something is flexible, then it can bend easily without breaking.
type: The tree branch was so flexible it could be bent into a circle and not break.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa egiluvchan bo'lsa, u holda buzilmasdan osongina egilishi mumkin.
column14: Daraxt shoxlari shu qadar egiluvchan ediki, aylana shaklida egilib, sindirilmasdi.

example: To flush means the face becomes red due to heat, illness, or emotion.
type: After the long race, the runner’s face was flushed.
example_tr: Yuzning qizarishi issiqlik, kasallik yoki hissiyot tufayli qizarib ketishini anglatadi.
column14: Uzoq davom etgan poygadan keyin yuguruvchining yuzi qizarib ketdi.

example: To injure someone means to damage a part of their body.
type: The car crash injured two people.
example_tr: Biror kishiga shikast etkazish, uning tanasining bir qismiga zarar etkazish demakdir.
column14: Avtohalokat oqibatida ikki kishi jarohatlangan.

example: A lump is a small piece of something that is solid.
type: The artist took a lump of clay and turned it into a beautiful pot.
example_tr: Bo'lak - bu qattiq narsaning kichik bo'lagi.
column14: Rassom loydan bir parcha olib, uni chiroyli qozonga aylantirdi.

example: A mixture is something that is made by mixing other things together.
type: The walls were built using a mixture of water, rock, and dirt.
example_tr: Aralash - bu boshqa narsalarni bir-biriga aralashtirish orqali hosil bo'ladigan narsa.
column14: Devorlari suv, tosh va tuproq aralashmasi yordamida qurilgan.

example: To reconcile means to return to a friendly relationship.
type: After arguing, the two friends were reconciled with each other.
example_tr: Yarashtirish do'stona munosabatlarga qaytishni anglatadi.
column14: Ikki do‘st janjallashib, o‘zaro yarashishdi.

example: To ruin something means to harm or damage it greatly.
type: Our walk in the park was ruined by the sudden rain.
example_tr: Biror narsani buzish, unga katta zarar etkazish yoki zarar etkazish demakdir.
column14: Parkdagi sayrimizni to'satdan yomg'ir buzdi.

example: To shatter something means to break it suddenly into many tiny pieces.
type: When the ball hit the window, the glass shattered.
example_tr: Biror narsani sindirish, uni to'satdan juda ko'p mayda bo'laklarga bo'lish demakdir.
column14: To‘p derazaga tekkanida oyna sinib ketdi.

example: Shutters are wooden or metal covers in front of a window.
type: Mr. Smith closed the shutters every night to make his bedroom dark.
example_tr: Panjurlar deraza oldidagi yog'och yoki metall qoplamalardir.
column14: Janob Smit yotoqxonasini qorong'i qilish uchun har kecha panjurlarni yopardi.

example: To sift something means to remove all the large pieces.
type: The baker sifted the flour into a large bowl.
example_tr: Biror narsani elakdan o'tkazish barcha katta qismlarni olib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Nonvoy unni katta idishga elakdan o‘tkazdi.

example: If something is slight, then it is small or minor.
type: There was only a slight change in the little boy’s height.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa engil bo'lsa, u kichik yoki kichikdir.
column14: Kichkina bolaning bo'yida ozgina o'zgarish bor edi.

example: To sparkle means to shine brightly with quick flashes of light.
type: The stars sparkled in the winter night’s sky.
example_tr: Yorqinlik - bu yorug'likning tez chaqnashlari bilan porlashni anglatadi.
column14: Qishki tun osmonida yulduzlar porladi.

example: To sprinkle means to scatter something all over something else.
type: He sprinkled the pasta with salt and black pepper.
example_tr: Sepmoq, bir narsani boshqa narsaga sochmoq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: U makaronni tuz va qora murch bilan sepdi.

example: If food is stale, then it is not fresh but dry, hard, and not good to eat.
type: The cookies sat on the table so long that they became stale.
example_tr: Agar ovqat eskirgan bo'lsa, u yangi emas, balki quruq, qattiq va eyish yaxshi emas.
column14: Pechene stolda shunchalik uzoq o'tirdiki, ular eskirib qoldi.

example: To utter a word or a sound means to say it.
type: The lost boy was so scared that he could barely utter a single word.
example_tr: So‘z yoki tovushni aytish uni aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Yo‘qolgan bola shunchalik qo‘rqib ketdiki, bir og‘iz so‘z aytolmadi.

example: If something happens altogether, it happens completely.
type: The company stopped using sugar altogether in its food.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa butunlay sodir bo'lsa, u butunlay sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Kompaniya oziq-ovqatda shakardan foydalanishni butunlay to'xtatdi.

example: To bind is to bring people together.
type: The victims of the flood were bound by their need to help each other.
example_tr: Bog'lash - odamlarni birlashtirish.
column14: To'fon qurbonlari bir-biriga yordam berish zarurati bilan bog'liq edi.

example: A bruise is a dark mark caused by being hit by something.
type: She got a bruise on her knee from falling down.
example_tr: Ko'karish - bu biror narsa bilan urish natijasida paydo bo'lgan qorong'u belgi.
column14: Uning tizzasi yiqilib tushganidan jarohat olgan.

example: Accustom is a way of doing things that has been the same for a long time.
type: It is a custom that the bride and groom have the first dance.
example_tr: Ko'nikish - bu uzoq vaqt davomida bir xil bo'lgan narsalarni qilish usuli.
column14: Kelin va kuyovning birinchi raqsga tushishi odat tusiga kiradi.

example: When someone is disobedient, they do not follow the rules or instructions.
type: The disobedient children didn’t listen to their mother and had an accident.
example_tr: Biror kishi itoatsiz bo'lsa, u qoidalar yoki ko'rsatmalarga amal qilmaydi.
column14: Itoatsiz bolalar onalariga quloq solmadilar va baxtsiz hodisaga duch kelishdi.

example: To foresee something is to know about it before it happens.
type: The teacher didn’t foresee any problems with her large class.
example_tr: Biror narsani oldindan ko'rish - bu sodir bo'lishidan oldin uni bilishdir.
column14: O'qituvchi o'zining katta sinfida hech qanday muammo bo'lishini oldindan ko'ra olmadi.

example: To glimpse something is to see it for a short time.
type: She glimpsed outside the window as the plane was about to land.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rish - uni qisqa vaqt davomida ko'rish.
column14: Samolyot qo‘nmoqchi bo‘lganida, u derazadan tashqariga qaradi.

example: A hoop is a ring that is made of plastic, metal, or wood.
type: The boys tried to toss the ball through the basketball hoop.
example_tr: Halqa - bu plastik, metall yoki yog'ochdan yasalgan halqa.
column14: Yigitlar to'pni basketbol halqasi orqali uloqtirishga harakat qilishdi.

example: Misfortune is bad luck or an unlucky event.
type: His family helped him when he encountered misfortune.
example_tr: Baxtsizlik - omadsizlik yoki omadsiz hodisa.
column14: U baxtsizlikka duch kelganida, oilasi unga yordam berdi.

example: When something is negative, it is unpleasant or sad.
type: She doesn’t like to say negative things about her friends.
example_tr: Biror narsa salbiy bo'lsa, u yoqimsiz yoki qayg'ulidir.
column14: U do'stlari haqida salbiy gapirishni yoqtirmaydi.

example: Per is used to mean “each” when giving a price, size, or amount.
type: It costs $8 per person to watch the baseball game.
example_tr: Narx, o'lcham yoki miqdorni berishda Per "har biri" ma'nosida ishlatiladi.
column14: Beysbol o'yinini tomosha qilish uchun bir kishi uchun 8 dollar turadi.

example: To plead is to ask for something you want very badly.
type: He pleaded for his parents to let him go to the soccer game.
example_tr: Yalvarish - o'zingiz xohlagan narsani juda yomon so'rashdir.
column14: U ota-onasidan uni futbol o'yiniga qo'yib yuborishlarini iltimos qildi.

example: To rip something means to pull it apart.
type: She ripped the paper in half by accident.
example_tr: Biror narsani yirtib tashlash, uni tortib olish demakdir.
column14: U tasodifan qog‘ozning yarmini yirtib tashladi.

example: The sake of something is the reason for doing it.
type: The parents worked hard for their children’s sake.
example_tr: Biror narsaning manfaati uni qilishning sababidir.
column14: Ota-onalar farzandlari uchun ko'p mehnat qilishdi.

example: To scrape something is to rub it very hard with something sharp.
type: I accidentally scraped the paint off the side of the car.
example_tr: Biror narsani qirib tashlash - uni o'tkir narsa bilan juda qattiq ishqalash.
column14: Men tasodifan mashinaning yon tomonidagi bo'yoqni qirib tashladim.

example: A source of something is the place that it comes from.
type: The river was the source of drinking water for the village.
example_tr: Biror narsaning manbai - u kelib chiqqan joy.
column14: Daryo qishloqning ichimlik suvi manbai edi.

example: When somebody is stern, they are very serious.
type: The stern teacher didn't allow the students to speak during class.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qattiqqo'l bo'lsa, ular juda jiddiy.
column14: Qattiq o'qituvchi dars paytida talabalarga gapirishga ruxsat bermadi.

example: To stitch is to use a needle and thread to join pieces of cloth together.
type: My grandmother stitched the pieces together to make a big blanket.
example_tr: Tikish - mato bo'laklarini birlashtirish uchun igna va ipdan foydalanish.
column14: Buvim bo‘laklarni bir-biriga tikib, katta ko‘rpacha yasadi.

example: A thump is the sound of a heavy object falling.
type: They heard the thump when the bowling ball hit the floor.
example_tr: Yurish - og'ir narsaning tushishi ovozi.
column14: Bouling to'pi polga tekkanida ular zarbani eshitishdi.

example: When somebody is vehement, they are angry and emotional.
type: Gina was vehement when she found out that Liz was bad in school.
example_tr: Biror kishi g'azablangan bo'lsa, ular g'azablangan va hissiyotli bo'ladi.
column14: Liz maktabda yomon o'qiyotganini bilgach, Jina qattiq qattiqqo'l edi.

example: A civilization is an organized group of humans that have culture and government.
type: Most early civilizations in Central America didn’t use metal weapons.
example_tr: Sivilizatsiya - bu madaniyat va hukumatga ega bo'lgan odamlarning uyushgan guruhi.
column14: Markaziy Amerikadagi ilk tsivilizatsiyalarning aksariyati metall qurollardan foydalanmagan.

example: When something is convenient, it is easy to do and does not take a lot of work.
type: The bus is a convenient way to get to school.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qulay bo'lsa, uni qilish oson va ko'p mehnat talab qilmaydi.
column14: Avtobus - maktabga borishning qulay usuli.

example: A den is a living space for some types of animals, such as lions.
type: The mother lion left her babies in the den.
example_tr: Uy hayvonlari, masalan, sherlar uchun yashash joyidir.
column14: Ona sher chaqaloqlarini iniga tashlab ketdi.

example: Dew is the drops of water that form on the ground outside during the night.
type: When we woke up, we saw that the grass was covered in dew.
example_tr: Shudring - tunda tashqarida erda paydo bo'ladigan suv tomchilari.
column14: Uyg‘onganimizda ko‘rdikki, maysalar shudring bilan qoplangan.

example: When something is drastic, it is extreme or major.
type: She made a drastic decision to get her long hair cut short.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keskin bo'lsa, u ekstremal yoki asosiy hisoblanadi.
column14: U uzun sochlarini qisqartirishga qaror qildi.

example: To exit means to leave.
type: The students exited through the front door.
example_tr: Chiqish, ketishni anglatadi.
column14: Talabalar old eshikdan chiqishdi.

example: A flock is a group of animals, such as birds, sheep or goats.
type: There was one black sheep in the entire flock.
example_tr: Poda - bu qushlar, qo'ylar yoki echkilar kabi hayvonlar guruhi.
column14: Butun suruvda bitta qora qo‘y bor edi.

example: To fold is to bend something like paper or cloth so that it takes up less space.
type: I folded the paper and put it in my pocket.
example_tr: Qatlama - qog'oz yoki mato kabi narsalarni kamroq joy egallashi uchun bukish.
column14: Men qog‘ozni buklab, cho‘ntagimga solib qo‘ydim.

example: A lid is a top for a box or container that can be removed.
type: He lifted the lid of the box and revealed her present.
example_tr: Qopqoq - olib tashlash mumkin bo'lgan quti yoki idish uchun yuqori qism.
column14: U qutining qopqog'ini ko'tarib, sovg'asini ko'rsatdi.

example: To loom is to seem very large and often scary.
type: The ominous clouds loomed over the school.
example_tr: To'qish juda katta va ko'pincha qo'rqinchli ko'rinadi.
column14: Maktab ustidan dahshatli bulutlar qoplandi.

example: When something is mighty, it is strong and large.
type: The mighty wrestler scared all who faced him.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kuchli bo'lsa, u kuchli va katta bo'ladi.
column14: Qudratli polvon unga duch kelganlarning hammasini cho‘chitib yubordi.

example: A mushroom is a fungus with a round top. Some are used as food.
type: The soup had fresh mushrooms in it.
example_tr: Qo'ziqorin - dumaloq tepaga ega bo'lgan qo'ziqorin. Ba'zilari oziq-ovqat sifatida ishlatiladi.
column14: Sho'rvada yangi qo'ziqorinlar bor edi.

example: When something is native, it is originating in a certain place or area.
type: Avocadoes are native fruits of Mexico.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mahalliy bo'lsa, u ma'lum bir joy yoki hududdan kelib chiqadi.
column14: Avokadolar Meksikaning tabiiy mevalaridir.

example: Poison is a dangerous substance that causes illness or death.
type: They used poison to get rid of the rats in their home.
example_tr: Zahar kasallik yoki o'limga olib keladigan xavfli moddadir.
column14: Ular uyidagi kalamushlardan qutulish uchun zahardan foydalanishgan.

example: Reeds are tall and skinny plants that grow in groups near water.
type: The sun set behind the reeds of the lake’s shore.
example_tr: Qamish - suv yaqinida guruh bo'lib o'sadigan baland va oriq o'simliklar.
column14: Quyosh ko'l qirg'og'idagi qamish orqasida botdi.

example: To shield something is to protect it.
type: She shielded her eyes from the sun with sunglasses.
example_tr: Biror narsani himoya qilish - uni himoya qilish.
column14: U ko'zlarini quyoshdan himoya qiluvchi ko'zoynak bilan himoya qildi.

example: Stormy describes something affected or characterized by storms.
type: The golfers decided to go home because of the stormy weather.
example_tr: Stormy ta'sirlangan yoki bo'ronlar bilan tavsiflangan narsani tasvirlaydi.
column14: Bo'ronli ob-havo tufayli golfchilar uylariga ketishga qaror qilishdi.

example: To sway is to move slowly from side to side.
type: She swayed while she listened to the music.
example_tr: Chayqalish - sekin u yoqdan bu tomonga harakat qilish.
column14: U musiqa tinglagancha chayqalib ketdi.

example: When something is urban, it is related to the city.
type: Subways are an important form of urban transportation.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa shahar bo'lsa, u shahar bilan bog'liq.
column14: Metrolar shahar transportining muhim shakli hisoblanadi.

example: To wade is to walk in or pass through water.
type: The child waded in the water at the beach.
example_tr: O'tish - suvga kirish yoki suvdan o'tish.
column14: Bola plyajdagi suvda suzdi.

example: An accent is a certain way of speaking that shows where a person is from.
type: The new teacher's accent was clearly a German one.
example_tr: Urg'u - bu odamning qayerdan ekanligini ko'rsatadigan ma'lum bir nutq usuli.
column14: Yangi o‘qituvchining talaffuzi aniq nemischa edi.

example: A barber is a person whose job is to cut hair.
type: My hair is getting much too long. I'd better go to the barber's shop.
example_tr: Sartarosh - bu ishi soch kesish bo'lgan odam.
column14: Mening sochlarim juda uzun bo'lib ketmoqda. Yaxshisi, sartaroshxonaga borsam.

example: A basement of a house or building is a room that is built underground.
type: They turned their basement into a game room.
example_tr: Uy yoki binoning podvali yer ostida qurilgan xonadir.
column14: Ular yerto‘lasini o‘yin xonasiga aylantirishdi.

example: When something is blank, it does not have anything on it.
type: She got a blank paper to draw on.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa bo'sh bo'lsa, unda hech narsa yo'q.
column14: U chizish uchun bo'sh qog'oz oldi.

example: To blink means to shut the eyes and quickly open them again.
type: I blinked many times so that my eyes could adjust to the bright light.
example_tr: Miltillash ko'zlarni yumib, tezda yana ochishni anglatadi.
column14: Ko‘zlarim yorqin nurga moslasha olishi uchun ko‘p marta pirpiratdim.

example: A choir is a group of people who sing together.
type: He had choir practice every day after school.
example_tr: Xor - bu birgalikda kuylaydigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: U har kuni maktabdan keyin xor bilan shug'ullanardi.

example: When something is comic, it is funny.
type: The comic actor was famous for his jokes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kulgili bo'lsa, u kulgili bo'ladi.
column14: Komik aktyor o'zining hazillari bilan mashhur edi.

example: To complicate something means to make it harder than necessary.
type: The bad weather complicated finishing the job quickly.
example_tr: Biror narsani murakkablashtirish, uni zaruratdan ko'ra qiyinlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yomon ob-havo ishni tezda tugatishni qiyinlashtirdi.

example: To decline an offer or invitation means to say no to it.
type: She declined his offer to pay for her dinner.
example_tr: Taklif yoki taklifni rad etish, unga yo'q deyish demakdir.
column14: U kechki ovqat uchun pul to'lash taklifini rad etdi.

example: An errand is a trip taken to do a specific activity.
type: He couldn’t go to practice because he had several errands to do.
example_tr: Topshiriq - bu muayyan faoliyatni bajarish uchun qilingan sayohat.
column14: U mashg'ulotlarga bora olmadi, chunki uning bir nechta topshiriqlari bor edi.

example: A glove is a piece of clothing that covers your fingers and hand.
type: When it gets cold, I always put on a pair of gloves.
example_tr: Qo'lqop - bu barmoqlar va qo'llarni qoplaydigan kiyim.
column14: Sovuq tushganda, men har doim qo'lqop kiyaman.

example: A hermit is one who lives alone and does not spend time with others.
type: The hermit lived a simple life in a small cave in the forest.
example_tr: Zohid - yolg'iz yashaydigan va boshqalar bilan vaqt o'tkazmaydigan kishi.
column14: Zohid o'rmondagi kichik bir g'orda oddiy hayot kechirdi.

example: If something is done justly, then it is fair.
type: We justly decided to give the prize to him.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa adolatli qilingan bo'lsa, u adolatli bo'ladi.
column14: Biz haqli ravishda sovrinni unga berishga qaror qildik.

example: Leather is a material made from animal skin that is used to make clothing.
type: He got a new leather jacket for his birthday.
example_tr: Teri - hayvonlarning terisidan kiyim tikish uchun ishlatiladigan material.
column14: U tug'ilgan kuni uchun yangi charm kurtka oldi.

example: To ponder something is to think about it carefully.
type: She sat in the park and pondered her problem.
example_tr: Biror narsani mulohaza yuritish, bu haqda yaxshilab o'ylashdir.
column14: U parkda o'tirdi va o'z muammosini o'yladi.

example: To reserve something means to keep it for a certain person or time.
type: He reserved a table at the busy restaurant.
example_tr: Biror narsani zahiraga qo'yish, uni ma'lum bir shaxs yoki vaqt uchun saqlashni anglatadi.
column14: U gavjum restoranda stol band qildi.

example: A script is the words of a film or play.
type: He read the script of the play three times.
example_tr: Ssenariy - bu film yoki spektaklning so'zlari.
column14: U spektakl ssenariysini uch marta o‘qib chiqdi.

example: To search for something or someone means to look for them carefully.
type: I searched the newspaper for a new job.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoki kimnidir izlash ularni diqqat bilan izlashni anglatadi.
column14: Men gazetadan yangi ish qidirdim.

example: To slam is to close something hard.
type: She slammed the book shut after she finished reading it.
example_tr: Qattiq bir narsani yopishdir.
column14: U kitobni o‘qib bo‘lgach, uni qattiq yopib qo‘ydi.

example: A staircase is a set of stairs found inside a building.
type: The staircase leads directly into the kitchen.
example_tr: Zinapoya - bu bino ichida joylashgan zinapoyalar to'plami.
column14: Zinadan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri oshxonaga olib boradi.

example: Afflicted means to suffer physically or mentally.
type: He was afflicted by pain in his right arm.
example_tr: Jabrlanganlar jismoniy yoki ruhiy azoblanishni anglatadi.
column14: U o'ng qo'lidagi og'riqdan azob chekdi.

example: An aisle is a space between two things that people use to walk.
type: They were told to clear the aisle because the plane was about to land.
example_tr: Yo'lak - bu odamlar yurish uchun foydalanadigan ikki narsa orasidagi bo'shliq.
column14: Samolyot qo‘nmoqchi bo‘lgani uchun ularga yo‘lakni bo‘shatish kerakligi aytilgan.

example: The atmosphere is the air around the Earth where weather conditions form.
type: Scientists worry that harmful substances are hurting the atmosphere.
example_tr: Atmosfera - bu ob-havo sharoiti shakllanadigan Yer atrofidagi havo.
column14: Olimlar zararli moddalar atmosferaga zarar yetkazayotganidan xavotirda.

example: An author is a person who wrote a certain piece of writing.
type: The author was hard at work on his next novel.
example_tr: Muallif - bu ma'lum bir asar yozgan shaxs.
column14: Yozuvchi navbatdagi romani ustida qattiq mehnat qildi.

example: A breakdown is a failure to work correctly.
type: Her car had a breakdown, and she wasn’t sure how to fix it.
example_tr: Buzilish - bu to'g'ri ishlamaslik.
column14: Uning mashinasida nosozlik bor edi va u buni qanday tuzatishni bilmas edi.

example: Cargo is the items carried by a ship or airplane.
type: The cargo of the ship got wet when it started raining.
example_tr: Yuk - bu kema yoki samolyotda tashiladigan narsalar.
column14: Yomg'ir yog'a boshlaganda kemaning yuki ho'l bo'lib qoldi.

example: A chapter is a part of a book that usually has a number or a title.
type: The first chapter of a book usually introduces the main character of a story.
example_tr: Bo'lim - bu odatda raqam yoki nomga ega bo'lgan kitobning bir qismi.
column14: Kitobning birinchi bobida odatda hikoyaning bosh qahramoni tanishtiriladi.

example: To connect two things means to join them together.
type: I connected the mouse to my laptop computer.
example_tr: Ikki narsani bog'lash ularni birlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Men sichqonchani noutbuk kompyuterimga uladim.

example: ‘Etc. is short for “etcetera.” It is used to refer to other unspecified objects.
type: She was going to bring treats to the party: cookies, muffins, cake, etc.
example_tr: ‘Va hokazo. "va hokazo" so'zining qisqartmasi. U boshqa aniqlanmagan ob'ektlarga murojaat qilish uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: U ziyofatga shirinliklar olib kelmoqchi edi: pechenye, kekler, tort va boshqalar.

example: To flip means to press a switch quickly to turn it on or off.
type: To turn on the lights, just flip this switch.
example_tr: Oʻchirish degani, uni yoqish yoki oʻchirish uchun kalitni tez bosish demakdir.
column14: Chiroqni yoqish uchun faqat shu kalitni aylantiring.

example: If you are idle, you are not doing anything.
type: She read a book to keep from being idle.
example_tr: Agar siz bekorchi bo'lsangiz, hech narsa qilmaysiz.
column14: Bekor bo‘lib qolmaslik uchun kitob o‘qidi.

example: To notify someone of something is to tell them about it.
type: The teacher notified us about a change to our assignment.
example_tr: Biror kishiga biror narsa haqida xabar berish, bu haqda unga aytishdir.
column14: O'qituvchi bizga topshiriqni o'zgartirish haqida xabar berdi.

example: Peas are a vegetable that is small, round and green.
type: His favorite food was peas.
example_tr: No'xat mayda, yumaloq va yashil bo'lgan sabzavotdir.
column14: Uning sevimli taomi no'xat edi.

example: A raisin is a dried grape.
type: Raisins are one of my favorite snacks.
example_tr: Mayiz - quritilgan uzum.
column14: Mayiz mening eng sevimli gazaklarimdan biridir.

example: To retain something is to keep it.
type: Even by the afternoon, the day had retained the morning’s freshness.
example_tr: Biror narsani saqlab qolish - uni saqlab qolish.
column14: Hatto tushdan keyin ham kun ertalabki yangilikni saqlab qoldi.

example: To state something means to say it in a definite way.
type: The president stated his opinion about the world’s health concerns.
example_tr: Biror narsani bayon qilmoq, aniq bir tarzda aytishni bildiradi.
column14: Prezident dunyo salomatligi bilan bog‘liq muammolar haqida o‘z fikrini bildirdi.

example: A tray is a flat plate used to hold food.
type: The waiter brought our food on a tray.
example_tr: Tovoq - ovqatni saqlash uchun ishlatiladigan tekis plastinka.
column14: Ofitsiant laganda ovqatimizni olib keldi.

example: If something is unfortunate, it is bad or unlucky.
type: It was unfortunate that Dave's team lost, but he still had fun.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa baxtsiz bo'lsa, u yomon yoki omadsizdir.
column14: Deyv jamoasi mag‘lubiyatga uchragani achinarli bo‘ldi, lekin u baribir quvnoq edi.

example: When something is vivid, it is bright and colorful.
type: The figures in the painting were vivid.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jonli bo'lsa, u yorqin va rang-barang bo'ladi.
column14: Rasmdagi raqamlar jonli edi.

example: To vomit means to have food come up from one’s stomach.
type: It is common for women to vomit when they are pregnant.
example_tr: Qusish, oshqozondan oziq-ovqat chiqishini anglatadi.
column14: Homilador ayollarda qusish odatiy holdir.

example: To betray someone means to treat them in a dishonest way.
type: The man betrayed his country when he gave away national secrets.
example_tr: Biror kishiga xiyonat qilish, unga insofsiz munosabatda bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Bu odam milliy sirlarni berganda vataniga xiyonat qildi.

example: A blast is a loud noise made by something that explodes.
type: There was a loud blast when the police officer fired the gun.
example_tr: Portlash - bu portlash sodir bo'lgan narsaning kuchli shovqini.
column14: Politsiya xodimi quroldan o‘q uzganida kuchli portlash sodir bo‘lgan.

example: A bracelet is a piece of jewelry that you wear around your wrist.
type: My father gave me a pretty gold bracelet for my birthday.
example_tr: Bilaguzuk - bu bilagingizga taqib yuradigan zargarlik buyumlari.
column14: Tug'ilgan kunimda otam menga chiroyli oltin bilaguzuk sovg'a qildi.

example: To cease means to stop.
type: After about an hour, the rain ceased, and a rainbow appeared.
example_tr: To'xtatish to'xtash demakdir.
column14: Taxminan bir soat o'tgach, yomg'ir to'xtadi va kamalak paydo bo'ldi.

example: To choke means to cough because you have difficulty breathing.
type: There was a lot of smoke in the air, and it made me choke.
example_tr: Bo'g'ilish yo'talishni anglatadi, chunki nafas olish qiyin.
column14: Havoda juda ko'p tutun bor edi va bu meni bo'g'ib qo'ydi.

example: When an event is civil, it happens inside a country.
type: The country was torn apart by a terrible civil war.
example_tr: Agar hodisa fuqarolik bo'lsa, u mamlakat ichida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Mamlakat dahshatli fuqarolar urushi tufayli parchalanib ketdi.

example: To comment means to say something that shows your personal opinion.
type: Tom commented on the poor quality of the food.
example_tr: Fikr bildirish sizning shaxsiy fikringizni bildiradigan narsani aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Tom ovqatning sifatsizligi haqida fikr bildirdi.

example: To cross means to go from one side to the other side.
type: We used his boat to cross to the other side of the lake.
example_tr: Ketish - bir tomondan boshqa tomonga o'tishni anglatadi.
column14: Biz uning qayig‘i bilan ko‘lning narigi tomoniga o‘tdik.

example: A dent is damage caused by something heavy hitting something else.
type: That blue car hit my car, and now there is a small dent in my car door.
example_tr: Tish - bu og'ir narsaning boshqa narsaga urilishi natijasida etkazilgan zarar.
column14: O'sha ko'k mashina mening mashinamga urilgan, endi esa mashinamning eshigida kichik egilish bor.

example: To distrust someone means to believe that they are not honest.
type: Don’t lend money to someone if you distrust them!
example_tr: Biror kishiga ishonmaslik uning halol emasligiga ishonishni anglatadi.
column14: Kimgadir ishonmasangiz, unga qarz bermang!

example: A fort is a small building that is specially built to defend an area from attack.
type: When the army arrived, they built a big fort on the top of the hill.
example_tr: Qal'a - bu hududni hujumdan himoya qilish uchun maxsus qurilgan kichik bino.
column14: Qo‘shin yetib kelgach, tepalik tepasida katta qal’a qurdirdilar.

example: To found means to bring something into existence.
type: The pastor founded his church in the countryside.
example_tr: Topmoq, biror narsani vujudga keltirmoq demakdir.
column14: Pastor o'z cherkovini qishloqda qurgan.

example: Lining is a piece of cloth that covers the inside of clothes.
type: This jacket is very warm because it has a thick lining.
example_tr: Astar - kiyimning ichki qismini qoplaydigan mato.
column14: Bu ko'ylagi juda issiq, chunki u qalin astarga ega.

example: A mass is a large number of things of one type.
type: We received a mass of letters this morning.
example_tr: Massa - bu bir turdagi narsalarning ko'pligi.
column14: Bugun ertalab biz juda ko'p xat oldik.

example: To pray means to talk to God.
type: When people go to church, they pray for their families and friends.
example_tr: Ibodat qilish Xudo bilan gaplashishni anglatadi.
column14: Odamlar cherkovga borganlarida, ular oilalari va do'stlari uchun ibodat qilishadi.

example: If a place is rife with something bad, it is very common in that place.
type: This part of the country is rife with disease.
example_tr: Agar biror joyda yomon narsa bo'lsa, u erda bu juda keng tarqalgan.
column14: Mamlakatning bu qismi kasalliklarga boy.

example: When something is the sole thing, it is the only thing of a particular type.
type: His sole purpose in life was to help others.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yagona narsa bo'lsa, u ma'lum bir turdagi yagona narsadir.
column14: Uning hayotdagi yagona maqsadi boshqalarga yordam berish edi.

example: If you sweep the floor, you clean it with a tool like a broom or a brush.
type: There is a lot of dirt on the floor. Can you sweep it please?
example_tr: Agar siz polni supursangiz, uni supurgi yoki cho'tka kabi asbob bilan tozalaysiz.
column14: Zaminda juda ko'p axloqsizlik bor. Iltimos, supurib bera olasizmi?

example: Treachery is a behavior in which a person betrays a country or a person.
type: The man ran away to escape from the treachery of his wife.
example_tr: Xiyonat - bu odamning vatanga yoki shaxsga xiyonat qiladigan xatti-harakati.
column14: Erkak xotinining xiyonatidan qutulish uchun qochib ketdi.

example: To tuck something means to put it somewhere so that it is neat or safe.
type: He looked sloppy without his shirt being tucked into his pants.
example_tr: Biror narsani tiqish degani, uni toza yoki xavfsiz joyga qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Ko'ylagi shimiga tiqilib qolmagan holda, u bema'ni ko'rinardi.

example: A background is a person’s education, family, and experience.
type: The new teacher had a background in science and math.
example_tr: Orqa fon - bu insonning ta'limi, oilasi va tajribasi.
column14: Yangi o‘qituvchi fan va matematika bo‘yicha bilimga ega edi.

example: Bait is something used to trick a person or thing to do something.
type: The best bait for catching fish is a big, fat worm
example_tr: O'lja - bu odamni yoki narsalarni biror narsa qilish uchun aldash uchun ishlatiladigan narsa.
column14: Baliq ovlash uchun eng yaxshi o'lja katta, semiz qurtdir

example: To chronicle something means to record an event or speech.
type: The daily newspaper chronicles local and world events.
example_tr: Biror narsani xronika qilish voqea yoki nutqni yozib olishni anglatadi.
column14: Kundalik gazetada mahalliy va jahon voqealari xronika qilinadi.

example: Copper is a red-brown metal often used in electric wire and pipes.
type: Ancient hunters melted copper to make knives and spears.
example_tr: Mis ko'pincha elektr simlari va quvurlarda ishlatiladigan qizil-jigarrang metalldir.
column14: Qadimgi ovchilar misni eritib, pichoq va nayza yasashgan.

example: A disease is an illness that causes specific problems.
type: He had a disease that caused him to lose his hearing.
example_tr: Kasallik - bu muayyan muammolarni keltirib chiqaradigan kasallik.
column14: Uning eshitish qobiliyatini yo‘qotgan kasalligi bor edi.

example: Folklore is the collection of beliefs and stories of a culture.
type: India’s folklore has stories written in long poems about great warriors
example_tr: Xalq og'zaki ijodi - bu madaniyatning e'tiqodlari va hikoyalari to'plami.
column14: Hindiston folklorida buyuk jangchilar haqida uzun she'rlarda yozilgan hikoyalar mavjud

example: To infect someone means to give them an illness.
type: The common cold infects hundreds of millions of people each year.
example_tr: Biror kishini yuqtirish, unga kasallik berish demakdir.
column14: Sovuq har yili yuz millionlab odamlarni yuqtiradi.

example: To itch means to rub the skin with your fingernails.
type: The rough fabric in his shirt made the back of his neck itch.
example_tr: Qichishish terini tirnoqlari bilan ishqalashni anglatadi.
column14: Ko‘ylagidagi dag‘al matodan bo‘ynining orqa qismi qichishib ketdi.

example: Literature is books, plays, and poetry.
type: Early American literature covers the poetry and stories from 1500 to 1800.
example_tr: Adabiyot - bu kitoblar, spektakllar va she'rlar.
column14: Ilk Amerika adabiyoti 1500 dan 1800 gacha bo'lgan she'r va hikoyalarni qamrab oladi.

example: A millennium is one thousand years.
type: Stonehenge is believed to have been built about 5 millenniums ago.
example_tr: Ming yillik - ming yil.
column14: Stounhenj taxminan 5 ming yil oldin qurilgan deb ishoniladi.

example: A myth is a traditional story that explains a culture’s history and beliefs.
type: In Greece, there was a myth about a woman who had snakes for hair.
example_tr: Mif - bu madaniyat tarixi va e'tiqodlarini tushuntiruvchi an'anaviy hikoya.
column14: Yunonistonda soch uchun ilonlari bo'lgan ayol haqida afsona bor edi.

example: To promote someone means to raise them to a higher position or rank
type: After two years in the company, she was promoted to a manager.
example_tr: Biror kishini lavozimga ko'tarish, uni yuqori lavozimga yoki martabaga ko'tarishni anglatadi
column14: Kompaniyada ikki yil ishlagandan so'ng u menejer lavozimiga ko'tarildi.

example: To relate to something means to have a connection with it.
type: A company’s plan usually relates to how much profit it can make.
example_tr: Biror narsaga aloqador bo'lish, u bilan bog'lanishni anglatadi.
column14: Kompaniyaning rejasi odatda qancha foyda olishi mumkinligi bilan bog'liq.

example: Areligion is a belief in a god or gods.
type: Their religion taught that people should forgive their enemies.
example_tr: Areligion - bu xudo yoki xudolarga ishonish.
column14: Ularning dini odamlar o'z dushmanlarini kechirishlari kerakligini o'rgatgan.

example: A sum is a specific amount of money.
type: He calculated the numbers to see what the sum of his bills would be.
example_tr: So'm - bu ma'lum bir pul miqdori.
column14: Xarajatlarining summasi qancha bo'lishini bilish uchun u raqamlarni hisoblab chiqdi.

example: A teller is a person who works with a bank’s customers.
type: The teller at the bank helped Kelly put money into a savings account.
example_tr: Kassir - bu bank mijozlari bilan ishlaydigan shaxs.
column14: Bank kassasi Kelliga omonat hisobvarag'iga pul qo'yishda yordam berdi.

example: If someone is trustworthy, they are honest and truthful.
type: Mary is one of the most trustworthy people I’ve ever met.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ishonchli bo'lsa, u halol va rostgo'ydir.
column14: Meri men uchrashgan eng ishonchli odamlardan biri.

example: To update something means to make it more modern.
type: We need to update the programs on our computers.
example_tr: Biror narsani yangilash, uni yanada zamonaviy qilish demakdir.
column14: Biz kompyuterlarimizdagi dasturlarni yangilashimiz kerak.

example: Avein is a tube in the body that carries blood toward the heart.
type: The blue veins in my hand are just under my skin
example_tr: Avein - qonni yurakka olib boradigan tanadagi naycha.
column14: Qo‘limdagi ko‘k tomirlar xuddi terim ostida

example: Venom is a poisonous substance that comes from animals or plants.
type: A snake’s venom can be used to cure the illnesses it creates.
example_tr: Zahar hayvonlar yoki o'simliklardan olinadigan zaharli moddadir.
column14: Ilon zahari u yaratgan kasalliklarni davolash uchun ishlatilishi mumkin.

example: Charity is an act of giving help, usually money, to those who need it.
type: Thanks to his friends’ charity, he had enough money to pay the rent.
example_tr: Xayriya - yordamga muhtoj bo'lganlarga yordam, odatda pul berish harakati.
column14: Do'stlarining xayriya ishlari tufayli u ijara haqini to'lash uchun etarli pulga ega edi.

example: Commerce is the activity of buying and selling things.
type: The new shopping mall increased the commerce in that section of town.
example_tr: Tijorat - bu narsalarni sotib olish va sotish faoliyati.
column14: Yangi savdo majmuasi shaharning ushbu qismida savdoni oshirdi.

example: To condemn someone means to give them a specific punishment.
type: The judge condemned the criminal to five years in prison.
example_tr: Biror kishini qoralash, unga aniq jazo berishni anglatadi.
column14: Sudya jinoyatchini besh yillik qamoq jazosiga hukm qildi.

example: If something is cozy, then it is comfortable, warm, and relaxing.
type: The thick blanket made the bed very cozy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qulay bo'lsa, u qulay, iliq va tasalli.
column14: Qalin adyol karavotni juda qulay qildi.

example: To deplete an amount of something means to use up all of it.
type: All the driving he was doing was depleting his car’s fuel supply.
example_tr: Biror narsaning miqdorini yo'qotish uning hammasini ishlatishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning barcha haydashlari mashinasining yoqilg'i zaxirasini tugatgan.

example: An economy is the money and businesses of a country or region.
type: The factory was good for the economy because it brought jobs to the area.
example_tr: Iqtisodiyot - bu mamlakat yoki mintaqaning pul va biznesidir.
column14: Zavod iqtisodiyot uchun foydali edi, chunki u hududga ish o'rinlari olib keldi.

example: An empire is a large group of countries ruled by an emperor or empress.
type: The emperor built roads to make travel easier throughout the empire.
example_tr: Imperiya - imperator yoki imperator tomonidan boshqariladigan mamlakatlarning katta guruhi.
column14: Imperator butun imperiya bo'ylab sayohat qilishni osonlashtirish uchun yo'llar qurdi.

example: Goods are anything that can be bought or sold.
type: Shoes, hats, dresses and purses were the goods she wanted to buy.
example_tr: Tovarlar - bu sotib olinadigan yoki sotiladigan har qanday narsa.
column14: Poyafzal, shlyapa, ko'ylaklar va hamyonlar uning sotib olmoqchi bo'lgan tovarlari edi.

example: To heed something means to obey or follow it.
type: You should heed the advice on the sign and not drive so fast.
example_tr: Biror narsaga quloq solish, unga itoat qilish yoki unga ergashish demakdir.
column14: Belgidagi maslahatga quloq solishingiz va juda tez haydamasligingiz kerak.

image: yoʻlovchi mashinalar orqali tekin sayohat qilmoq
example: To hitchhike means to travel by asking for rides from passing vehicles.
type: She didn’t have a car, so she hitchhiked several miles to her brother’s home,
example_tr: Avtostopda sayohat qilish, o'tayotgan transport vositalaridan minishni so'rab sayohat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning mashinasi yo'q edi, shuning uchun u avtostopda akasining uyiga bir necha mil yo'l oldi,

example: To mock someone means to tease them in a cruel way.
type: The girls mocked Nancy because she was a new student.
example_tr: Birovni masxara qilish, uni shafqatsiz tarzda masxara qilish demakdir.
column14: Qizlar Nensini masxara qilishdi, chunki u yangi talaba edi.

example: If someone is neutral, then they do not help either of the two fighting sides.
type: The girl's friend remained neutral while the couple was arguing.
example_tr: Agar kimdir betaraf bo'lsa, u jang qilayotgan ikki tomonning hech biriga yordam bermaydi.
column14: Er-xotin janjallashganda qizning dugonasi betaraflikni saqlab qoldi.

example: To persecute means to treat someone badly.
type: Dan felt persecuted because he was smaller than the other boys at school.
example_tr: Quvg'in qilish - kimgadir yomon munosabatda bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Dan maktabdagi boshqa o'g'il bolalardan kichikroq bo'lgani uchun quvg'inga uchraganini his qildi.

example: Pity is the feeling of sadness and kindness for those who are suffering.
type: Because she had pity for the lost boy, she helped him find his parents.
example_tr: Rahm-shafqat - azob chekayotganlarga qayg'u va mehribonlik hissi.
column14: Adashgan bolaga rahmi kelgani uchun unga ota-onasini topishga yordam berdi.

example: To reduce something means to make it less in size or number.
type: When the store reduced its prices, people wanted to shop there.
example_tr: Biror narsani kamaytirish, uni hajmi yoki soni jihatidan kamroq qilish demakdir.
column14: Do'kon narxlarni pasaytirganida, odamlar u erdan xarid qilishni xohlashdi.

example: A scribe was a person whose job was to copy written works.
type: In Ancient Egypt, scribes recorded important events.
example_tr: Kotib - yozma asarlarni nusxalash vazifasi bo'lgan odam.
column14: Qadimgi Misrda ulamolar muhim voqealarni yozib olishgan.

example: A temper is someone's mood or a chance that they might get angry.
type: She has a temper. Even the slightest mistakes make her angry.
example_tr: Jahl - bu kimningdir kayfiyati yoki uning g'azablanishi ehtimoli.
column14: Uning jahli bor. Hatto eng kichik xatolar ham uni g'azablantiradi.

example: A throne is the special chair in which a ruler sits.
type: Nobody except the king and queen sat in the thrones in the great hall.
example_tr: Taxt - bu hukmdor o'tiradigan maxsus kursi.
column14: Katta zaldagi taxtlarda qirol va malikadan boshqa hech kim o‘tirmasdi.

example: Unity is the state of people working together for a certain purpose.
type: The project was finished early, thanks to the unity of the workers.
example_tr: Birlik - ma'lum bir maqsad yo'lida birgalikda harakat qiladigan odamlarning holati.
column14: Ishchilarning hamjihatligi tufayli loyiha erta yakunlandi.

example: A victor is a group or person that wins in a contest.
type: At the end of the game, the blue team was the victor.
example_tr: G'olib - bu musobaqada g'olib chiqqan guruh yoki shaxs.
column14: O'yin yakuniga ko'ra ko'k-ko'k jamoa g'alaba qozondi.

example: If something is accurate, it is completely correct.
type: The story in the newspaper wasn’t very accurate.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ri bo'lsa, u butunlay to'g'ri.
column14: Gazetadagi voqea unchalik aniq emas edi.

example: To analyze something is to study it.
type: The scientist will analyze the blood sample.
example_tr: Biror narsani tahlil qilish uni o'rganishdir.
column14: Olim qon namunasini tahlil qiladi.

example: An asteroid is a giant rock from outer space.
type: In 1908, a giant asteroid hit Siberia.
example_tr: Asteroid - bu koinotdan kelgan ulkan tosh.
column14: 1908 yilda Sibirga ulkan asteroid urilgan.

example: A controversy is a dispute about something that affects many people.
type: There has been a lot of controversy over the judge’s decision.
example_tr: Munozara - bu ko'p odamlarga ta'sir qiladigan narsa haqidagi bahs.
column14: Hakamning qarori bo'yicha ko'plab bahs-munozaralar bo'ldi.

example: To evolve is to change over time.
type: Many people think that humans evolved from animals.
example_tr: Rivojlanish - vaqt o'tishi bilan o'zgarish.
column14: Ko'pchilik odamlar hayvonlardan paydo bo'lgan deb o'ylashadi.

example: A factor is something that has an effect on the way another thing happens.
type: Smoking is the main factor that causes lung cancer.
example_tr: Omil boshqa narsa sodir bo'lishiga ta'sir qiladigan narsadir.
column14: Chekish o'pka saratonini keltirib chiqaradigan asosiy omil hisoblanadi.

example: If something is genetic, it is related to the genes in one’s body.
type: The color of one’s eyes is genetic.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa genetik bo'lsa, bu inson tanasidagi genlar bilan bog'liq.
column14: Ko'zlarning rangi genetikdir.

example: A genome is the collection of all the genes in a living thing.
type: Understanding the human genome may help cure many diseases.
example_tr: Genom - bu tirik mavjudotdagi barcha genlarning to'plami.
column14: Inson genomini tushunish ko'plab kasalliklarni davolashga yordam beradi.

example: To be identical is to be the same as someone or something else.
type: James and john are identical twins.
example_tr: Bir xil bo'lish - birov yoki boshqa narsa bilan bir xil bo'lish.
column14: Jeyms va Jon bir xil egizaklardir.

example: An intellectual is a very smart person.
type: We've always considered my Uncle Max the intellectual of the family.
example_tr: Ziyoli juda aqlli odam.
column14: Biz Maks amakimni har doim oilaning ziyolisi deb bilganmiz.

example: A majority of something is almost all of the people or things in that group.
type: A majority of the people voted for Tom Smith in the election.
example_tr: Biror narsaning aksariyati bu guruhdagi deyarli barcha odamlar yoki narsalardir.
column14: Saylovda ko'pchilik Tom Smitga ovoz berdi.

example: A mammal is an animal that usually has hair and is not born from an egg.
type: Even though it lives in the water, whales are actually mammals.
example_tr: Sutemizuvchilar odatda sochli va tuxumdan tug'ilmaydigan hayvondir.
column14: U suvda yashasa ham, kitlar aslida sutemizuvchilardir.

example: To multiply is to increase in number.
type: In the past year, the number of people at work multiplied by ten percent.
example_tr: Ko'paymoq - sonning ko'payishi.
column14: O'tgan yili ish joyidagilar soni o'n foizga ko'paydi.

example: Offspring are the children of a person or the babies of an animal.
type: The dog’s offspring had the same color of fur as she did.
example_tr: Nasl - bu odamning bolalari yoki hayvonlarning bolalari.
column14: Itning avlodi xuddi u kabi mo'yna rangiga ega edi.

example: A pesticide is a substance used to kill insects.
type: The farmer sprayed his crops with a pesticide to keep bugs away.
example_tr: Pestitsid - bu hasharotlarni o'ldirish uchun ishlatiladigan modda.
column14: Fermer hasharotlardan saqlanmoq uchun ekinlariga pestitsid sepdi.

example: To regulate something is to control how it happens.
type: The bank regulates how much money people can borrow from it.
example_tr: Biror narsani tartibga solish - bu qanday sodir bo'lishini nazorat qilish.
column14: Bank odamlar undan qancha pul qarz olishlarini tartibga soladi.

example: To reinforce something is to make it stronger.
type: Peter reinforced his opinion with information from a book.
example_tr: Biror narsani mustahkamlash - uni kuchaytirish.
column14: Butrus o'z fikrini kitobdagi ma'lumotlar bilan mustahkamladi.

example: If one is stricken by a disease or problem, they are badly affected by it.
type: Mike was stricken with a horrible illness.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi kasallik yoki muammoga duchor bo'lsa, u unga yomon ta'sir qiladi.
column14: Mayk dahshatli kasallikka chalindi.

example: If something is vast, it is very large.
type: The wealthy man bought a vast amount of land in the countryside.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa katta bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Boy qishloqdan katta miqdorda yer sotib oldi.

example: A vegetarian is someone who does not eat any meat products.
type: I became a vegetarian because I don’t like the taste of meat.
example_tr: Vegetarian - bu go'sht mahsulotlarini iste'mol qilmaydigan odam.
column14: Men vegetarian bo'ldim, chunki go'shtning ta'mini yoqtirmayman.

example: To cherish something means to hold it as very important.
type: I cherish this trophy I won.
example_tr: Biror narsani qadrlash, uni juda muhim deb bilishni anglatadi.
column14: Men yutgan bu sovrinni qadrlayman.

example: Compassion is a feeling of understanding for someone who is hurt or suffering.
type: The veterinarian had compassion for the sick little puppy.
example_tr: Rahmdillik - bu xafa bo'lgan yoki azob chekayotgan odamni tushunish hissi.
column14: Veterinariya shifokori kasal kuchukchaga rahm-shafqat ko'rsatdi.

example: Consent is permission to do something.
type: Their mother gave the children consent to go outside and play.
example_tr: Rozilik - biror narsa qilishga ruxsat.
column14: Ularning onasi bolalarga tashqariga chiqishga va o'ynashga rozilik berdi.

example: The core is the center of something.
type: The rings of a tree start forming at its core.
example_tr: Yadro biror narsaning markazidir.
column14: Daraxtning halqalari uning yadrosida shakllana boshlaydi.

example: If someone is cunning, they are good at tricking people.
type: The cunning child fooled his parents into thinking that he was kind.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ayyor bo'lsa, u odamlarni aldashni yaxshi biladi.
column14: Ayyor bola ota-onasini mehribon deb aldadi.

example: If someone is dizzy, then they feel off balance as if they will fall down.
type: The pregnant woman was dizzy after standing up too quickly.
example_tr: Agar kimdir boshi aylansa, u yiqilib tushadigandek muvozanatni his qiladi.
column14: Homilador ayol juda tez turgandan keyin boshi aylangan.

example: Equilibrium is the balance between different forces.
type: The sudden drop in prices upset the equilibrium of the economy.
example_tr: Muvozanat - bu turli kuchlar o'rtasidagi muvozanat.
column14: Narxlarning keskin pasayishi iqtisodiyotning muvozanatini buzdi.

example: To foster a feeling or a skill means to help it develop.
type: She helped foster a sense of calm in the little boy.
example_tr: Tuyg'u yoki mahoratni rivojlantirish, uni rivojlantirishga yordam berishni anglatadi.
column14: U bolada xotirjamlik hissini shakllantirishga yordam berdi.

example: To grind something means to break it into very small pieces or powder.
type: She wanted to grind the beans, so she could brew some coffee.
example_tr: Biror narsani maydalash, uni juda mayda bo'laklarga yoki kukunga bo'lish demakdir.
column14: U loviya maydalamoqchi edi, shuning uchun u kofe qaynatmoqchi edi.

example: To growl means to make a deep, angry sound.
type: The dog started to growl at the man walking by.
example_tr: Baqirmoq chuqur, g'azablangan ovoz chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: It o‘tib ketayotgan odamga qarab baqira boshladi.

example: Moderation is a state of being just enough but not too much.
type: It is important to eat in moderation so that you can have a healthy body.
example_tr: Moderatsiya - bu etarli bo'lish holati, lekin juda ko'p emas.
column14: Sog'lom tanaga ega bo'lish uchun me'yorida ovqatlanish muhimdir.

example: A predator is an animal that kills and eats other animals.
type: The peregrine falcon is a predator that eats fish.
example_tr: Yirtqich - bu boshqa hayvonlarni o'ldiradigan va yeyadigan hayvon.
column14: Peregrin lochin baliq iste'mol qiladigan yirtqich hisoblanadi.

example: If someone is sane, they can think in a normal way.
type: Oliver does not act like a sane person when he is angry.
example_tr: Agar kimdir aqli raso bo'lsa, u oddiy tarzda o'ylashi mumkin.
column14: Oliver jahli chiqqanda aqli raso odamdek harakat qilmaydi.

example: A saucer is a small round dish that you set a cup on.
type: He placed the spoon on the saucer.
example_tr: Tovoq - bu kichkina dumaloq idish bo'lib, unga stakan qo'yiladi.
column14: U qoshiqni likopchaga qo'ydi.

example: To snatch something means to take it away with a quick motion.
type: He was so hungry that he snatched an apple from a tree.
example_tr: Biror narsani tortib olish, uni tez harakat bilan olib qo'yishni anglatadi.
column14: U shunchalik och ediki, daraxtdan olma yulib oldi.

example: To stagger means to move in an unsteady way and almost fall over.
type: He staggered around after having too much to drink.
example_tr: Chayqalish - beqaror harakatlanish va deyarli yiqilish demakdir.
column14: Ko‘p ichganidan keyin gandiraklab ketdi.

example: To stumble means to put your foot down wrong so that you almost fall.
type: He stumbled as he ran through the puddle.
example_tr: Qoqilish, oyog'ingizni noto'g'ri qo'yishni anglatadi, shunda siz deyarli yiqilib qolasiz.
column14: Ko‘lmakdan yugurib o‘tayotganda qoqilib ketdi.

example: If someone is tense, they are worried something bad might happen.
type: After the phone call, Monica was very tense.
example_tr: Agar kimdir tarang bo'lsa, u yomon narsa yuz berishi mumkinligidan xavotirda.
column14: Telefon qo'ng'irog'idan keyin Monika juda tarang edi.

example: To tumble means to fall, often in a rolling way.
type: He lost his balance while snowboarding and tumbled to the ground.
example_tr: Yiqilish ko'pincha dumalab tushishni anglatadi.
column14: U snoubordda uchayotganda muvozanatni yo‘qotib, yerga quladi.

example: To withhold something is to not give it to someone.
type: They withheld all information until she paid her fine.
example_tr: Biror narsani ushlab qolish, uni birovga bermaslikdir.
column14: U jarimani to'lamaguncha, ular barcha ma'lumotlarni yashirishdi.

example: An aircraft is a vehicle that flies in the sky, such as an airplane or helicopter
type: At the museum in the airport, you can see a lot of old aircraft.
example_tr: Samolyot - bu samolyot yoki vertolyot kabi osmonda uchadigan transport vositasi
column14: Aeroportdagi muzeyda siz ko'plab eski samolyotlarni ko'rishingiz mumkin.

example: A celebrity is someone who is famous.
type: It was the highlight of the evening when the celebrities arrived.
example_tr: Mashhur - bu mashhur bo'lgan kishi.
column14: Bu mashhurlar kelgan oqshomning eng muhim voqeasi edi.

example: Concrete is a substance made from stones.
type: The man covered the ground with concrete.
example_tr: Beton toshlardan yasalgan moddadir.
column14: Erkak yerni beton bilan qoplagan.

example: If someone is decisive, they make decisions quickly.
type: Our boss is very decisive, so it did not take long to organize the project
example_tr: Agar kimdir hal qiluvchi bo'lsa, u tezda qaror qabul qiladi.
column14: Bizning xo'jayinimiz juda hal qiluvchi, shuning uchun loyihani tashkil qilish ko'p vaqt talab qilmadi

example: If someone is esteemed, many people like or respect them.
type: An esteemed scientist is coming to the university to talk about her discoveries.
example_tr: Agar kimdir hurmatga sazovor bo'lsa, ko'pchilik uni yaxshi ko'radi yoki hurmat qiladi.
column14: Hurmatli olim universitetga uning kashfiyotlari haqida gapirib berish uchun keladi.

example: If something is ethical, it is the right thing to do.
type: Many people believe that it is ethical to help others in need.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa axloqiy bo'lsa, buni qilish to'g'ri.
column14: Ko'p odamlar muhtoj bo'lganlarga yordam berishni axloqiy deb bilishadi.

example: If plants or animals are extinct, there are none left.
type: There used to be dinosaurs all over the world, but now they are extinct.
example_tr: Agar o'simliklar yoki hayvonlar yo'q bo'lib ketgan bo'lsa, ular qolmaydi.
column14: Ilgari butun dunyoda dinozavrlar bo'lgan, ammo hozir ular yo'q bo'lib ketgan.

example: If a person or plant is hardy, it is strong and can live through difficult conditions.
type: The farmer is a hardy man and doesn’t mind working outside.
example_tr: Agar odam yoki o'simlik chidamli bo'lsa, u kuchli va qiyin sharoitlarda yashashi mumkin.
column14: Fermer qattiqqo'l odam va tashqarida ishlashga qarshi emas.

example: An institute is an organization that is interested in research or teaching.
type: I am going to a lecture about ancient Rome at the Historical Institute.
example_tr: Institut tadqiqot yoki o'qitish bilan shug'ullanadigan tashkilotdir.
column14: Men Tarix institutida qadimgi Rim haqidagi ma'ruzaga boryapman.

example: Jealousy is a feeling of wanting something that somebody else has.
type: She felt a lot of jealousy when she saw Luke with two girls.
example_tr: Rashk - bu boshqa birovda bo'lgan narsani xohlash hissi.
column14: U Luqoni ikki qiz bilan ko'rganida juda hasad qildi.

example: To migrate means to move from one place to another.
type: Many birds migrate to warmer countries in the winter.
example_tr: Migratsiya bir joydan ikkinchi joyga ko‘chish demakdir.
column14: Qishda ko'plab qushlar issiq mamlakatlarga ko'chib o'tadi.

example: To nurture something means to care for it as it grows or develops.
type: Robert nurtured his plants, and that is why they grow so well.
example_tr: Biror narsani tarbiyalash, uning o'sishi yoki rivojlanishi davomida unga g'amxo'rlik qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Robert o'z o'simliklarini boqdi va shuning uchun ular juda yaxshi o'sadi.

example: If something is overhead, it is located above you.
type: As we sat on top of the hill, a plane flew overhead.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tepada bo'lsa, u sizning tepangizda joylashgan.
column14: Biz tepalikning tepasida o'tirganimizda, tepada bir samolyot uchib ketdi.

example: A principle is a belief about the correct way to behave.
type: To maintain principles, it's vital to watch, listen, and speak carefully.
example_tr: Printsip - bu o'zini tutishning to'g'ri yo'li haqidagi ishonch.
column14: Prinsiplarni saqlab qolish uchun diqqat bilan kuzatish, tinglash va gapirish juda muhimdir.

example: If a place is rural, it is in the countryside instead of the city.
type: I want to live in a small house in a rural area.
example_tr: Agar joy qishloq bo'lsa, u shahar o'rniga qishloqda.
column14: Men qishloqda kichkina uyda yashashni xohlayman.

example: If a place is secluded, it is far away from any other place.
type: There was a secluded bench in the park.
example_tr: Agar joy tanho bo'lsa, u boshqa joydan uzoqda.
column14: Parkda tanho skameyka bor edi.

example: A species is a type of plant or animal.
type: There are 21 different species of butterfly in this forest.
example_tr: Tur - bu o'simlik yoki hayvonning bir turi.
column14: Bu o'rmonda kapalakning 21 xil turi mavjud.

example: A swamp is a very wet area of land.
type: There are lots of wild animals living in the swamp.
example_tr: Botqoq erning juda nam maydonidir.
column14: Botqoqlikda ko'plab yovvoyi hayvonlar yashaydi.

example: To traverse means to move or travel through an area.
type: The explorer traversed the desert alone on a camel.
example_tr: Ketish, harakat qilish yoki hudud bo'ylab sayohat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Kashfiyotchi cho‘lni bir o‘zi tuyada bosib o‘tdi.

example: Zoology is a subject in which people study animals.
type: Helen wants to study zoology because she has always liked animals.
example_tr: Zoologiya - odamlar hayvonlarni o'rganadigan fan.
column14: Xelen zoologiyani o'rganishni xohlaydi, chunki u har doim hayvonlarni yaxshi ko'rgan.

example: An assumption is something that you believe is true but cannot prove.
type: I went to the cafeteria on the assumption that everyone would be there.
example_tr: Taxmin - bu siz haqiqat deb ishonadigan, ammo isbotlay olmaydigan narsadir.
column14: Hamma o‘sha yerda bo‘ladi, degan o‘yda choyxonaga bordim.

example: Barley is a grain that is used for animal feed, health food and beer.
type: The farmer grew barley to feed his cows in the winter.
example_tr: Arpa - bu hayvonlar uchun ozuqa, sog'lom oziq-ovqat va pivo uchun ishlatiladigan don.
column14: Dehqon qishda sigirlarini boqish uchun arpa yetishtirgan.

example: A beast is a large, dangerous animal.
type: A lion is one of the fiercest beasts on Earth.
example_tr: Yirtqich hayvon katta, xavfli hayvondir.
column14: Arslon er yuzidagi eng dahshatli hayvonlardan biridir.

example: A colonel is a military officer.
type: James has been given a promotion in the army. He is now a colonel.
example_tr: Polkovnik - harbiy ofitser.
column14: Jeymsga armiyada ko'tarilgan. Hozir u polkovnik.

example: If a disease is contagious, it is easily carried from one person to another.
type: You must wear protective clothing because the patient’s illness is contagious.
example_tr: Agar kasallik yuqumli bo'lsa, u bir odamdan boshqasiga osongina o'tadi.
column14: Siz himoya kiyimini kiyishingiz kerak, chunki bemorning kasalligi yuqumli.

example: A corpse is a dead body of a human.
type: After the accident, the corpse was taken to the hospital.
example_tr: Jasad - bu odamning o'lik tanasi.
column14: Baxtsiz hodisadan so‘ng jasad kasalxonaga yetkazilgan.

example: A crisis is a situation that is extremely stressful or dangerous.
type: The airport workers’ strike led to a crisis at the airport.
example_tr: Inqiroz - bu juda stressli yoki xavfli vaziyat.
column14: Aeroport ishchilarining ish tashlashi aeroportdagi inqirozga olib keldi.

example: To cure means to cause an illness or injury to end or disappear.
type: My dentist cured me of my toothache.
example_tr: Davolanish kasallik yoki jarohatni tugatish yoki yo'q qilish demakdir.
column14: Tish shifokorim tish og'rig'imni davoladi.

example: If something is deformed, it is not shaped normally and may appear ugly.
type: Even though the carrot was deformed, it was still safe to eat.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa deformatsiyalangan bo'lsa, u odatdagidek shakllanmagan va yomon ko'rinishi mumkin.
column14: Sabzi deformatsiyalangan bo'lsa ham, uni iste'mol qilish xavfsiz edi.

example: To discriminate means to judge people according to their looks.
type: They discriminated against her because she was different.
example_tr: Ajratish, odamlarni tashqi ko'rinishiga qarab hukm qilish demakdir.
column14: Ular uni kamsitishdi, chunki u boshqacha edi.

example: An embassy is where government officials work in a foreign country.
type: If you lose your passport, you should contact the embassy.
example_tr: Elchixona - bu davlat amaldorlari xorijiy davlatda ishlaydigan joy.
column14: Pasportingizni yo'qotib qo'ysangiz, elchixonaga murojaat qilishingiz kerak.

example: To extinguish a fire means to make it stop.
type: Michael extinguished the small fire with the hose.
example_tr: Yong'inni o'chirish uni to'xtatishni anglatadi.
column14: Maykl kichik olovni shlang bilan o'chirdi.

example: Flint is a hard stone that people used to make weapons for hunting.
type: There are a lot of flint tools in the museum.
example_tr: Flint - odamlar ov qilish uchun qurol yasagan qattiq tosh.
column14: Muzeyda chaqmoqtoshdan yasalgan asboblar juda ko‘p.

example: To harass someone means to annoy or trouble them.
type: The children harassed their mother because they wanted her attention.
example_tr: Biror kishini bezovta qilish, uni bezovta qilish yoki bezovta qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Bolalar onasining e'tiborini talab qilgani uchun ularni bezovta qilishdi.

example: To integrate means to join, communicate and socialize.
type: Governments want immigrants to integrate with the population.
example_tr: Integratsiya qo'shilish, muloqot qilish va ijtimoiylashishni anglatadi.
column14: Hukumatlar muhojirlarning aholi bilan integratsiyalashuvini xohlaydi.

example: If something is miniature, it is very small.
type: The boy enjoys playing with his miniature train set in his bedroom.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa miniatyura bo'lsa, u juda kichik.
column14: Bola yotoqxonasida o'zining miniatyura poezdi bilan o'ynashni yoqtiradi.

example: Nutrition is the process by which people use food to stay healthy.
type: It is important to pay attention to nutrition if you want to be an athlete.
example_tr: Oziqlanish - bu odamlar sog'lig'ini saqlash uchun oziq-ovqatdan foydalanadigan jarayon.
column14: Agar siz sportchi bo'lishni istasangiz, ovqatlanishga e'tibor berish muhimdir.

example: If something happens promptly, it happens quickly or on time.
type: Arrive promptly, or we won't have time to discuss everything.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tezda sodir bo'lsa, u tez yoki o'z vaqtida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Tezroq keling, aks holda hamma narsani muhokama qilishga vaqtimiz bo'lmaydi.

example: A technician is a person who is skilled in electronic or mechanical work.
type: I need to call the technician to help me with my computer.
example_tr: Texnik - bu elektron yoki mexanik ishda malakali shaxs.
column14: Menga kompyuterim bilan yordam berish uchun texnikni chaqirishim kerak.

example: The tropics are the areas of land and sea close to the equator.
type: People like to go to the tropics for vacation because it’s warm.
example_tr: Tropiklar - ekvatorga yaqin joylashgan quruqlik va dengiz hududlari.
column14: Odamlar dam olish uchun tropiklarga borishni yaxshi ko'radilar, chunki u issiq.

example: If something is beneficial, it is good for you.
type: Drinking milk everyday is beneficial to your bones.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa foydali bo'lsa, u siz uchun yaxshidir.
column14: Har kuni sut ichish suyaklar uchun foydalidir.

example: A birthplace is a place where a person is born or where something started.
type: China is the birthplace of chopsticks.
example_tr: Tug'ilgan joy - bu inson tug'ilgan yoki biror narsa boshlangan joy.
column14: Xitoy chopstiklarning vatani hisoblanadi.

example: The capacity of something is the amount of things that can be put in it.
type: The parking lot has reached its full capacity.
example_tr: Biror narsaning sig'imi - unga qo'yish mumkin bo'lgan narsalar miqdori.
column14: Avtoturargoh to‘liq quvvatiga yetdi.

example: If something is comparative, it is being judged based on something else.
type: The money that John has is comparative to most other adults.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qiyosiy bo'lsa, u boshqa narsaga asoslanib baholanadi.
column14: Jonning puli boshqa kattalar bilan solishtirganda.

example: If something is comprehensive, it has all the details about something else.
type: The teacher gave us a comprehensive review for the exam.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keng qamrovli bo'lsa, unda boshqa narsa haqida barcha tafsilotlar mavjud.
column14: O'qituvchi bizga imtihon uchun har tomonlama sharh berdi.

example: To conserve something is to protect it from being ruined or used completely.
type: The group worked to conserve the beauty of Europe’s national parks.
example_tr: Biror narsani saqlab qolish, uni buzish yoki butunlay ishlatishdan himoya qilishdir.
column14: Guruh Evropa milliy bog'larining go'zalligini saqlash uchun ishladi.

example: If something is crucial, it is extremely important to another thing.
type: Clean air is crucial to the survival of humans, plants, and animals.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u boshqa narsa uchun juda muhimdir.
column14: Toza havo odamlar, o'simliklar va hayvonlarning omon qolishi uchun juda muhimdir.

example: Cumulative describes an increase by adding one after another.
type: The cumulative snowfall in the area is 50 centimeters per year.
example_tr: Kumulyativ birin-ketin qo'shish orqali o'sishni tavsiflaydi.
column14: Bu hududda yiliga 50 santimetr qor yog'adi.

example: To deposit something is to put it into a place or another thing.
type: I deposited the money into my bank account.
example_tr: Biror narsani saqlash - uni biror joyga yoki boshqa narsaga qo'yishdir.
column14: Men pulni bankdagi hisob raqamimga kiritdim.

example: To distribute something is to give it to a number of people.
type: The teacher distributed crayons and markers to his students.
example_tr: Biror narsani tarqatish, uni bir qancha odamlarga berishdir.
column14: O‘qituvchi o‘quvchilariga rangli qalam va markerlar tarqatdi.

example: The equator is an imaginary line that splits the Earth into north and south.
type: The equator crosses the northern part of South America.
example_tr: Ekvator - bu Yerni shimol va janubga bo'ladigan xayoliy chiziq.
column14: Ekvator Janubiy Amerikaning shimoliy qismini kesib o'tadi.

example: Exotic describes something unusual because it is from far away.
type: Rebecca tried many exotic foods on her trip to Africa.
example_tr: Ekzotik g'ayrioddiy narsani tasvirlaydi, chunki u uzoqdan.
column14: Rebekka Afrikaga sayohatida ko'plab ekzotik taomlarni sinab ko'rdi.

example: If something is federal, it comes from the government of a country.
type: Sometimes federal laws are different from state laws.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa federal bo'lsa, u mamlakat hukumatidan keladi.
column14: Ba'zida federal qonunlar shtat qonunlaridan farq qiladi.

example: A formation is the way that something is made.
type: The formation of ice happens when water freezes.
example_tr: Shakllanish - bu biror narsaning yaratilish usuli.
column14: Muzning shakllanishi suv muzlaganda sodir bo'ladi.

example: The frequency of something is the number of times that it happens.
type: The frequency of rainstorms is very high, especially during the spring.
example_tr: Biror narsaning chastotasi - bu sodir bo'lish soni.
column14: Yomg'ir bo'ronlari chastotasi juda yuqori, ayniqsa bahorda.

example: An objective is a goal or plan that someone has.
type: My objective this week is to finish my homework by 7:30 every night.
example_tr: Maqsad - bu kimdir ega bo'lgan maqsad yoki rejadir.
column14: Mening bu haftadagi maqsadim har kuni kechqurun soat 7:30 da uy vazifamni bajarishdir.

example: Oxygen is a gas that all living things need to breathe.
type: My aunt believes that the oxygen in the country is cleaner than in the city.
example_tr: Kislorod barcha tirik mavjudotlar nafas olishi kerak bo'lgan gazdir.
column14: Xolam qishloqdagi kislorod shaharnikiga qaraganda tozaroq, deb hisoblaydi.

example: A rainforest is a forest that is in a place where it rains very often.
type: The rainforest is home to many animals.
example_tr: Yomg'ir o'rmoni - tez-tez yomg'ir yog'adigan joyda joylashgan o'rmon.
column14: Yomg'ir o'rmonlarida ko'plab hayvonlar yashaydi.

example: A strategy is a plan for how to do something.
type: The team came up with a strategy to win the game.
example_tr: Strategiya - bu qanday qilib biror narsani qilish rejasi.
column14: Jamoa o'yinda g'alaba qozonish strategiyasini ishlab chiqdi.

example: If an area is wooded, it is covered with trees.
type: Jim and Ben decided to go hiking in the wooded area by the river.
example_tr: Agar hudud o'rmonli bo'lsa, u daraxtlar bilan qoplangan.
column14: Jim va Ben daryo bo'yidagi o'rmonli hududda sayr qilishga qaror qilishdi.

example: Availis help. It is often used in the achievement of a goal.
type: His studying was to no avail because he failed the test.
example_tr: Yordam mavjud. U ko'pincha maqsadga erishishda qo'llaniladi.
column14: Uning o'qishi hech qanday natija bermadi, chunki u imtihondan o'ta olmadi.

example: To expand is to become bigger in size.
type: A balloon will expand as you blow air into it.
example_tr: Kengaytirish - kattaroq bo'lish.
column14: Balon ichiga havo puflaganingizda kengayadi.

example: To define means to clearly state, show, or explain what something is.
type: People define success in many different ways.
example_tr: Ta'riflash - bu nima ekanligini aniq aytish, ko'rsatish yoki tushuntirish demakdir.
column14: Odamlar muvaffaqiyatni turli yo'llar bilan belgilaydilar.

example: To dread is to be afraid of something that could, or is going to, happen.
type: I dread the idea that I will not get into college.
example_tr: Qo'rqish - sodir bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan yoki sodir bo'ladigan narsadan qo'rqish.
column14: Men kollejga kirmayman, degan fikrdan qo'rqaman.

example: If something is fundamental, it is a basic part of something.
type: The fundamental rules of basketball are easy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa asosiy bo'lsa, u biror narsaning asosiy qismidir.
column14: Basketbolning asosiy qoidalari oson.

example: If something is horrifying, it is frightening and very unpleasant.
type: There was a horrifying car accident today.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, u qo'rqinchli va juda yoqimsiz.
column14: Bugun dahshatli avtohalokat yuz berdi.

example: If someone is incredulous about something, they do not believe that it is true.
type: She was incredulous that monkeys could ever drive a car.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsaga ishonmasa, u haqiqat ekanligiga ishonmaydi.
column14: U maymunlarning mashina haydashiga ishonmasdi.

example: To linger is to last for a long time.
type: The smell of fresh cookies lingered in the bakery.
example_tr: Kechikmoq - uzoq davom etmoq.
column14: Nonvoyxonada yangi pishiriqlarning hidi anqib turardi.

example: An organism is a living thing, especially a very small one.
type: We studied the organism on the microscope.
example_tr: Organizm - bu tirik mavjudot, ayniqsa, juda kichik.
column14: Biz mikroskopda organizmni o'rgandik.

example: To paraphrase is to make someone else’s writing or speech shorter.
type: The students were asked to paraphrase the story they just heard.
example_tr: Tafsir qilish boshqa birovning yozishi yoki nutqini qisqartirishdir.
column14: Talabalardan eshitgan hikoyasini takrorlash so'ralgan.

example: A plague is a serious disease that quickly spreads to many people.
type: A plague in Europe killed millions of people.
example_tr: Vabo - bu juda ko'p odamlarga tez tarqaladigan jiddiy kasallik.
column14: Evropadagi vabo millionlab odamlarning hayotiga zomin bo'ldi.

example: If something happens presently, it is happening right now.
type: Presently, our profits are good, but by next year we can do even better.
example_tr: Agar hozir biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, u hozir sodir bo'lmoqda.
column14: Hozirda daromadimiz yaxshi, ammo keyingi yilga kelib bundan ham yaxshiroq ish qilishimiz mumkin.

example: If something is random, it happens without any pattern or reason.
type: Young children often ask random questions.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tasodifiy bo'lsa, u hech qanday naqsh yoki sababsiz sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Yosh bolalar ko'pincha tasodifiy savollarni berishadi.

example: A riot is a crowd that reacts to bad news by violently breaking laws.
type: A riot broke out after the candidate lost the election.
example_tr: To'polon - qonunlarni zo'ravonlik bilan buzish orqali yomon xabarlarga munosabat bildiradigan olomon.
column14: Nomzod saylovda mag‘lub bo‘lganidan keyin tartibsizliklar boshlandi.

example: To scribble is to write something quickly without caring about how it looks.
type: I scribbled a rough diagram of our plan and gave it to him.
example_tr: Yozish - bu qandaydir ko'rinishiga e'tibor bermasdan tez yozish.
column14: Men rejamizning taxminiy sxemasini yozdim va unga berdim.

example: A shrine is a religious building built to honor a person, event, or god.
type: He prayed at the shrine for an hour.
example_tr: Ziyoratgoh - bu shaxsni, hodisani yoki xudoni ulug'lash uchun qurilgan diniy bino.
column14: U ziyoratgohda bir soat ibodat qildi.

example: Solitude is the state of being totally alone.
type: John lives a life of solitude because he doesn’t get along well with people.
example_tr: Yolg'izlik - bu butunlay yolg'izlik holati.
column14: Jon odamlar bilan yaxshi munosabatda bo'lmagani uchun yolg'izlikda yashaydi.

example: If a contrast is stark, then the things being compared are utterly different.
type: There is a stark contrast between their test scores.
example_tr: Agar kontrast keskin bo'lsa, unda taqqoslanadigan narsalar butunlay boshqacha.
column14: Ularning test ballari o'rtasida keskin farq bor.

example: To summon a person is to ask them to come to you.
type: We summoned the doctor as soon as we noticed she was sick.
example_tr: Biror kishini chaqirish - bu sizning oldingizga kelishlarini so'rashdir.
column14: Uning kasal ekanligini sezganimizdan so'ng darhol shifokorni chaqirdik.

example: To worsen is to get worse.
type: The weather suddenly worsened, and we had to stay inside.
example_tr: Yomon bo'lish - yomonlash.
column14: Ob-havo birdan yomonlashdi va biz ichkarida qolishga majbur bo'ldik.

example: An automobile is a car.
type: The first automobiles were very different from the ones that exist today.
example_tr: Avtomobil - bu avtomobil.
column14: Birinchi avtomobillar bugungi kunda mavjud bo'lganlardan juda farq qiladi.

example: A candidate is a person who is competing to win something such as a job.
type: Alice is the best candidate for the job.
example_tr: Nomzod - bu ish kabi biror narsani yutish uchun kurashayotgan shaxs.
column14: Elis bu ish uchun eng yaxshi nomzod.

example: If something is confidential, it must be kept secret.
type: The information from the meeting is confidential.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa maxfiy bo'lsa, u sir saqlanishi kerak.
column14: Uchrashuvdan olingan ma'lumotlar maxfiydir.

example: If something is corporate, it is related to a large business.
type: Tom enjoys working in the corporate world.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa korporativ bo'lsa, u yirik biznes bilan bog'liq.
column14: Tom korporativ dunyoda ishlashni yoqtiradi.

example: To enhance something is to make it better.
type: Amy’s blue shirt really enhances the color of her eyes.
example_tr: Biror narsani yaxshilash - uni yaxshilash.
