column14: Emining ko'k ko'ylagi haqiqatan ham ko'z rangini yaxshilaydi.

example: An era is a period of time that has something special about it.
type: During the medieval era, knights wore protective armor.
example_tr: Davr - bu o'ziga xos narsaga ega bo'lgan vaqt davri.
column14: O'rta asrlarda ritsarlar himoya zirhlarini kiyib yurishgan.

example: A guideline is a rule about how to do something.
type: Before they began the project, the teacher gave them some guidelines.
example_tr: Yo'riqnoma - bu qanday qilib biror narsani qilish haqidagi qoida.
column14: Loyihani boshlashdan oldin o'qituvchi ularga ba'zi ko'rsatmalar berdi.

example: To incorporate is to add something to another thing.
type: I decided to incorporate a new ingredient into my cake recipe.
example_tr: Qo'shish - boshqa narsaga biror narsa qo'shish.
column14: Men tort retseptimga yangi ingredient qo'shishga qaror qildim.

example: To interact is to talk to or do something with another person.
type: The kids began to interact when the adults left the room.
example_tr: Muloqot - bu boshqa odam bilan gaplashish yoki biror narsa qilish.
column14: Kattalar xonani tark etgandan so'ng, bolalar muloqot qilishni boshladilar.

example: An interval is the time between two things happening.
type: Tony rested for brief intervals while he worked in the yard.
example_tr: Interval - bu sodir bo'layotgan ikki narsa orasidagi vaqt.
column14: Toni hovlida ishlaganda qisqa vaqt ichida dam oldi.

example: If something is mobile, it can be moved easily.
type: Mobile phones are popular because you can take them anywhere.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mobil bo'lsa, uni osongina ko'chirish mumkin.
column14: Mobil telefonlar mashhur, chunki ularni istalgan joyga olib ketishingiz mumkin.

example: To modify something is to change it a little bit.
type: I modified my outfit by adding a belt to it.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'zgartirish - uni biroz o'zgartirish.
column14: Men kiyimimni unga kamar qo'shib o'zgartirdim.

example: If two things are parallel, they are the same distance away from each other.
type: There are two yellow parallel lines dividing both sides of traffic.
example_tr: Agar ikkita narsa parallel bo'lsa, ular bir-biridan bir xil masofada joylashgan.
column14: Har ikki tomonni ajratuvchi ikkita sariq parallel chiziq mavjud.

example: A phenomenon is something that can be seen as it is happening.
type: I was amazed when I saw the phenomenon of shooting stars.
example_tr: Hodisa - bu sodir bo'layotgan paytda ko'rish mumkin bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Yulduzlarning uchish hodisasini ko'rib, hayratda qoldim.

example: To pollute means to make air, water, or land dirty, unclean, or foul.
type: The careless factory polluted the river with chemicals.
example_tr: Iflos qilish havo, suv yoki yerni iflos, harom yoki iflos qilish demakdir.
column14: Ehtiyotsiz zavod daryoni kimyoviy moddalar bilan ifloslantirdi.

example: To ridicule is to make fun of something in a mean way.
type: The other students ridiculed Peter's foreign accent.
example_tr: Masxara qilish - biror narsani yomon yo'l bilan masxara qilish.
column14: Boshqa talabalar Piterning ajnabiy talaffuzini masxara qilishdi.

example: If something is solar, it is related to the sun.
type: Using solar energy is good for the environment.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa quyosh bo'lsa, u quyosh bilan bog'liq.
column14: Quyosh energiyasidan foydalanish atrof-muhit uchun foydalidir.

example: A territory is a piece of land that belongs to a country but isn’t a state.
type: Gibraltar is a territory of Great Britain.
example_tr: Hudud - bu davlatga tegishli bo'lgan, ammo davlat bo'lmagan er qismi.
column14: Gibraltar - Buyuk Britaniya hududi.

example: A tournament is a competition, usually with many people participating.
type: My dad is playing in a golf tournament tomorrow.
example_tr: Turnir - bu odatda ko'p odamlar ishtirok etadigan musobaqa.
column14: Dadam ertaga golf turnirida o'ynaydi.

example: Transportation is any type of vehicle that can carry people or things.
type: I don’t have a car, so my normal transportation is the train.
example_tr: Transport - bu odamlar yoki narsalarni olib yurishi mumkin bo'lgan har qanday transport vositasi.
column14: Mening mashinam yo'q, shuning uchun mening oddiy transportim poezddir.

example: A bill is a statement of money owed for goods or a service.
type: I have so many bills that I do not know how to pay for them all.
example_tr: Veksel - bu tovar yoki xizmat uchun qarzdorlik to'g'risidagi hisobot.
column14: Menda shunchalik ko'p hisob-kitoblar borki, ularning hammasini qanday to'lashni bilmayman.

example: A boundary is the line where one area of land stops, and another begins.
type: This fence shows the boundary between our yard and yours.
example_tr: Chegara - bu erning bir maydoni to'xtab, boshqasi boshlanadigan chiziq.
column14: Bu panjara bizning hovlingiz bilan sizning hovlingiz orasidagi chegarani ko'rsatadi.

example: Chaos is a situation that is confusing and not ordered.
type: His presentation was in chaos. I couldn’t understand what he meant.
example_tr: Xaos - bu tartibsiz va tartibsiz holat.
column14: Uning taqdimoti tartibsizlikda edi. U nimani nazarda tutganini tushunolmadim.

example: If a person is consistent, they keep the same behavior or attitude.
type: Sara comes in every day and is our most consistent worker.
example_tr: Agar inson izchil bo'lsa, ular bir xil xatti-harakat yoki munosabatni saqlab qoladilar.
column14: Sara har kuni keladi va bizning eng doimiy ishchimiz.

example: A cyclone is a large storm with heavy rain and winds that spin in a circle.
type: Hundreds of homes were damaged by the cyclone.
example_tr: Tsiklon - kuchli yomg'ir va aylana bo'ylab aylanadigan shamollar bilan kuchli bo'ron.
column14: Tsiklon tufayli yuzlab uylar vayron bo'lgan.

example: If someone or something is doomed, they are going to fail or be destroyed.
type: Since I spent all my money, my date with Jane is doomed.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa halokatga uchrasa, ular muvaffaqiyatsizlikka uchraydi yoki yo'q qilinadi.
column14: Men butun pulimni sarflaganim sababli, Jeyn bilan uchrashuvim halokatga uchradi.

example: An heir is a person who receives money or property of someone who dies.
type: The princess was the heir to the king and queen's throne.
example_tr: Merosxo'r - vafot etgan kishining pulini yoki mulkini oladigan shaxs.
column14: Malika qirol va malika taxtining vorisi edi.

example: If something is martial, it is related to fighting or war.
type: Karate is a martial art that began many years ago in Japan.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jangovar bo'lsa, u jang yoki urush bilan bog'liq.
column14: Karate - bu ko'p yillar oldin Yaponiyada boshlangan jang san'ati.

example: If food is organic, it is grown without adding chemicals to it.
type: The organic carrots are more expensive, but they’re better for you.
example_tr: Agar oziq-ovqat organik bo'lsa, u kimyoviy moddalar qo'shmasdan o'stiriladi.
column14: Organik sabzi qimmatroq, lekin ular siz uchun yaxshiroqdir.

example: Poultry is a bird, such as a chicken, that is used for meat and eggs.
type: He raises poultry and sells their meat for extra money.
example_tr: Parranda go'sht va tuxum uchun ishlatiladigan tovuq kabi qushdir.
column14: Parranda boqib, go‘shtini qo‘shimcha pul evaziga sotadi.

example: To scramble is to move somewhere quickly and desperately.
type: The hikers scrambled down the side of the hill.
example_tr: Scramble - tez va umidsiz bir joyga ko'chib o'tishdir.
column14: Sayohatchilar tog‘ning yonbag‘ridan pastga tushishdi.

example: A sergeant is a soldier or police officer of middle rank.
type: He was promoted to sergeant after a year in the army.
example_tr: Serjant - o'rta darajadagi askar yoki politsiyachi.
column14: Harbiy xizmatda bir yil o‘tib, serjant unvonini oldi.

example: If you describe something as sheer, it is complete and very strong.
type: I was impressed by her sheer dedication to jogging.
example_tr: Agar biror narsani shaffof deb ta'riflasangiz, u to'liq va juda kuchli.
column14: Uning yugurishga bo'lgan sadoqati meni hayratda qoldirdi.

example: A stance is an attitude about an issue that someone states clearly.
type: My stance is that using oil and gas is bad for the environment.
example_tr: Pozitsiya - bu kimdir aniq bayon qilgan masalaga munosabat.
column14: Mening pozitsiyam shundaki, neft va gazdan foydalanish atrof-muhit uchun zararli.

example: A telegraph is a method of sending electric messages on wires.
type: In the 1900s, the telegraph was the fastest way to send a message.
example_tr: Telegraf - bu simlar orqali elektr xabarlarini yuborish usuli.
column14: 1900-yillarda telegraf xabar yuborishning eng tezkor usuli edi.

example: Textile is cloth that has been woven or knitted.
type: The blue textile was going to be used to make blouses.
example_tr: To'qimachilik - bu to'qilgan yoki trikotaj qilingan mato.
column14: Moviy to'qimachilik bluzkalar qilish uchun ishlatilishi kerak edi.

example: A tornado is a tube-shaped formation of air that spins very quickly.
type: During a tornado, the safest place to be is underground.
example_tr: Tornado - bu juda tez aylanadigan havoning quvur shaklidagi shakllanishi.
column14: Tornado paytida eng xavfsiz joy er osti hisoblanadi.

example: A typhoon is a large tropical storm that moves in circles.
type: Thousands of people lost electricity after a typhoon hit Australia.
example_tr: Tayfun - aylana bo'ylab harakatlanadigan yirik tropik bo'ron.
column14: Avstraliyada yuz bergan to‘fondan keyin minglab odamlar elektr energiyasidan mahrum bo‘ldi.

example: To wail is to show sadness by crying loudly.
type: The baby wailed because it was hungry.
example_tr: Yig'lamoq - baland ovozda yig'lash orqali qayg'u ko'rsatish.
column14: Chaqaloq och qolganidan yig‘lab yubordi.

example: A wardrobe is the collection of all of a person’s clothing.
type: She bought some new clothes to expand her wardrobe.
example_tr: Shkaf - bu insonning barcha kiyimlari to'plami.
column14: U garderobini kengaytirish uchun yangi kiyim sotib oldi.

example: You use although to say that one thing is contrasted by another.
type: Although she was late, her friends gave her a warm welcome.
example_tr: Siz bir narsani boshqasiga qarama-qarshi qo'yishni aytish uchun ham ishlatasiz.
column14: U kechikkan bo‘lsa-da, dugonalari uni iliq kutib olishdi.

example: To apply something means to put it on.
type: She always applies makeup to her face before going outside.
example_tr: Biror narsani qo'llash, uni qo'llashni anglatadi.
column14: U har doim ko'chaga chiqishdan oldin yuziga bo'yanish surtadi.

example: To await something means to wait for it.
type: The players awaited the judge’s decision.
example_tr: Biror narsani kutish uni kutishni anglatadi.
column14: Futbolchilar hakamning qarorini kutishdi.

example: When something is beloved, it is very special and you like it very much.
type: The boy took a nap next to his beloved cat.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sevimli bo'lsa, u juda o'ziga xos va sizga juda yoqadi.
column14: Bola sevimli mushukining yonida uxlab qoldi.

example: To bury someone or something means to put them in the ground.
type: They buried their grandfather under his favorite tree after he died.
example_tr: Birovni yoki biror narsani dafn etish, uni erga qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Ular bobosi vafotidan keyin uning sevimli daraxti tagiga dafn etishdi.

example: Climate is the usual weather in a place.
type: The climate in the desert is very hot.
example_tr: Iqlim - bu biron bir joyda odatiy ob-havo.
column14: Cho'lda iqlim juda issiq.

example: When you complain, you say that you are unhappy about something.
type: The workers complained that they were being treated unfairly.
example_tr: Shikoyat qilganingizda, biror narsadan norozi ekanligingizni aytasiz.
column14: Ishchilar o‘zlariga nisbatan adolatsizlik qilinayotganidan shikoyat qilishdi.

example: To confuse someone means to make them feel like they are unsure.
type: The sign confused the traveler because it pointed in two directions.
example_tr: Biror kishini chalkashtirib yuborish, uni ishonchsizligini his qilish demakdir.
column14: Belgi ikki tomonga ishora qilgani uchun sayohatchini chalkashtirib yubordi.

example: When something is due, it is expected to happen or be done at that time.
type: The papers were due on the 19th.
example_tr: Biror narsa kerak bo'lganda, u o'sha vaqtda sodir bo'lishi yoki bajarilishi kutiladi.
column14: Hujjatlarni topshirish 19-kuni kerak edi.

example: When you talk about an entire thing, you are talking about the whole thing.
type: He was so hungry that he ate the entire pizza by himself.
example_tr: Biror narsa haqida gapirganda, siz butun narsa haqida gapirasiz.
column14: U shunchalik och ediki, butun pitsani o'zi yedi.

example: To establish something means to create it.
type: He wanted to establish a club for people to help the Earth.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rnatish, uni yaratish demakdir.
column14: U Yerga yordam berish uchun odamlar uchun klub tashkil qilmoqchi edi.

example: A furnace is a place where heat is made.
type: Mr. Jones came to fix the furnace.
example_tr: Pech - bu issiqlik olinadigan joy.
column14: Janob Jons pechni tuzatish uchun keldi.

example: A leash is a rope or chain that is used to lead an animal.
type: A lot of dogs must wear a leash to keep them from running away.
example_tr: Tasma - hayvonni yetaklash uchun ishlatiladigan arqon yoki zanjir.
column14: Ko'pgina itlar qochib ketmasligi uchun tasma kiyishlari kerak.

example: To mature means to grow up to become an adult.
type: When they matured, they became as tall as their parents.
example_tr: Voyaga yetmoq, voyaga yetib, voyaga yetmoq demakdir.
column14: Ular kamolotga yetganlarida, ota-onalari kabi baland bo'yli bo'lishdi.

example: To measure something means to find out the quality, value, or effect of it.
type: The scientists carefully measured the amount of chemicals in the tubes.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'lchash - uning sifatini, qiymatini yoki ta'sirini aniqlash demakdir.
column14: Olimlar quvurlardagi kimyoviy moddalar miqdorini diqqat bilan o‘lchab ko‘rdilar.

example: The midst of something is the middle of it.
type: She was in the midst of cleaning when the telephone rang.
example_tr: Biror narsaning o'rtasi uning o'rtasidir.
column14: Telefon jiringlaganida u tozalash ishlarini olib borayotgan edi.

example: Misery is extreme suffering.
type: There was a lot of misery after Sam lost his dog.
example_tr: Baxtsizlik - bu haddan tashqari azob.
column14: Sem itini yo'qotganidan keyin juda ko'p baxtsizlik bor edi.

example: When something happened prior to something else, it happened earlier.
type: Ron had to wait since he arrived prior to the scheduled meeting time.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsadan oldin sodir bo'lsa, u oldinroq sodir bo'lgan.
column14: Ron rejalashtirilgan uchrashuv vaqtidan oldin kelgani uchun kutishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: Research is close and careful study to discover new things.
type: Scientists did a lot of research on the subject of blood type.
example_tr: Tadqiqot yangi narsalarni kashf qilish uchun yaqin va ehtiyotkorlik bilan o'rganishdir.
column14: Olimlar qon guruhi mavzusida juda ko'p tadqiqotlar o'tkazdilar.

example: A variety of something is a group of many different kinds of it.
type: There are a variety of flowers at the shop.
example_tr: Biror narsaning xilma-xilligi - uning turli xil turlaridan iborat guruh.
column14: Do'konda turli xil gullar mavjud.

example: To allot something means to give it to someone.
type: The coach allotted each team five minutes to prepare a strategy.
example_tr: Biror narsani ajratish, uni birovga berishni anglatadi.
column14: Murabbiy har bir jamoaga strategiya tayyorlash uchun besh daqiqa vaqt ajratdi.

example: To appall means to horrify, shock, or disgust someone.
type: The boy was appalled when he saw the accident.
example_tr: Dahshatga solish kimnidir dahshatga solish, hayratga solish yoki jirkanish demakdir.
column14: Bola baxtsiz hodisani ko‘rib, dahshatga tushdi.

example: A cache is a hiding place for valuable things.
type: The pirates kept their jewelry in a cache hidden in a cave.
example_tr: Kesh - bu qimmatbaho narsalarni yashirish joyi.
column14: Qaroqchilar o'zlarining taqinchoqlarini g'orda yashiringan keshda saqlashgan.

example: Convenience is a state of being able to do something with little effort.
type: The internet allows consumers to shop at their own convenience.
example_tr: Qulaylik - bu oz kuch sarflagan holda biror narsani qilishga qodirlik holati.
column14: Internet iste'molchilarga o'zlariga qulay tarzda xarid qilish imkonini beradi.

example: A dearth is an amount or supply which is not large enough.
type: There is a dearth of money in my bank account. I can’t afford a new car.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu etarlicha katta bo'lmagan miqdor yoki ta'minot.
column14: Bankdagi hisobimda pul yetishmayapti. Men yangi mashina sotib ololmayman.

example: If a thing you do is deliberate, you intend to do it.
type: She made a deliberate effort to save money each month.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qasddan qilingan bo'lsa, siz buni qilmoqchisiz.
column14: U har oy pulni tejashga harakat qildi.

example: When something is dire, it is terrible and very serious.
type: The tornado created a dire situation for the small town.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dahshatli bo'lsa, bu dahshatli va juda jiddiy.
column14: Tornado kichik shaharcha uchun dahshatli vaziyat yaratdi.

example: To elapse means to pass, as in seconds, minutes, or hours.
type: A few seconds must elapse before you can take another picture.
example_tr: O'tish degani soniyalar, daqiqalar yoki soatlar kabi o'tishni anglatadi.
column14: Boshqa suratga olishdan oldin bir necha soniya oʻtishi kerak.

example: Empathy is sharing or understanding another person’s feelings.
type: The caring nurse had empathy for her patients.
example_tr: Empatiya - bu boshqa odamning his-tuyg'ularini baham ko'rish yoki tushunish.
column14: G'amxo'r hamshira o'z bemorlariga hamdard edi.

example: When something is fanciful, it is unusual or unrealistic.
type: The girl had fanciful ideas about doing well in school without studying.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa xayoliy bo'lsa, u g'ayrioddiy yoki haqiqiy emas.
column14: Qizda o'qimay maktabda yaxshi o'qish haqida hayoliy g'oyalar bor edi.

example: To gripe means to complain constantly.
type: Lawrence always gripes when he has to do chores.
example_tr: Shikoyat qilish, doimiy shikoyat qilish demakdir.
column14: Lourens har doim uy ishlarini bajarishi kerak bo'lganda qiynaladi.

example: When something is grueling, it is very hard to do.
type: The climber faced the grueling task of reaching the top of the steep mountain.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mashaqqatli bo'lsa, buni qilish juda qiyin.
column14: Alpinist tik tog'ning cho'qqisiga chiqishdek mashaqqatli vazifani oldi.

example: When something is mundane, it is boring, common, or ordinary.
type: The man had the mundane chore of raking thousands of leaves into piles.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oddiy bo'lsa, u zerikarli, odatiy yoki oddiy.
column14: Bu odam minglab barglarni qoziqqa yig'ish bilan shug'ullangan.

example: To opt is to make a choice, especially when deciding in favor of something.
type: My brother likes chocolate ice cream, but I always opt for vanilla.
example_tr: Tanlash - bu tanlov qilish, ayniqsa biror narsa foydasiga qaror qilganda.
column14: Akam shokoladli muzqaymoqni yaxshi ko'radi, lekin men har doim vanilni tanlayman.

example: Outrage is a very strong emotion of anger or shock.
type: Tommy was feeling outrage when his parents said he couldn't go to the dance.
example_tr: G'azab - bu juda kuchli g'azab yoki zarba hissi.
column14: Ota-onasi uning raqsga bora olmasligini aytganida, Tommi g'azablangan edi.

example: When an amount of something is paltry, it is very small.
type: The poor man had a paltry sum of money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa arzimas bo'lsa, u juda oz bo'ladi.
column14: Bechoraning arzimagan puli bor edi.

example: To rectify something means to correct it.
type: I quickly rectified the spelling mistakes that I had on my essay.
example_tr: Biror narsani tuzatish, uni tuzatish degani.
column14: Inshodagi imlo xatolarimni tezda tuzatdim.

example: When someone is resourceful, they are good at dealing with hard situations.
type: After his boat sunk, Matt was resourceful enough to build a raft.
example_tr: Agar kimdir topqir bo'lsa, u qiyin vaziyatlarni engishga qodir.
column14: Qayiq cho'kib ketganidan so'ng, Mett sal yasash uchun etarlicha zukko edi.

example: Sustenance is food and water needed to keep a person, animal, or plant alive.
type: Without the proper sustenance, the man will starve.
example_tr: Rizq - bu odam, hayvon yoki o'simlikning hayotini saqlab qolish uchun zarur bo'lgan oziq-ovqat va suvdir.
column14: To'g'ri rizq bo'lmasa, odam och qoladi.

example: When something is tedious, it is long, frustrating, and boring.
type: His job involved a lot of tedious typing, filing, and organizing.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa zerikarli bo'lsa, u uzoq, umidsizlik va zerikarli bo'ladi.
column14: Uning ishi juda ko'p zerikarli matn terish, hujjatlarni topshirish va tartibga solishni o'z ichiga olgan.

example: An abbey is a house or group of houses where monks or nuns live.
type: When the monk returned to the abbey, he went immediately to his bedroom.
example_tr: Abbey - rohiblar yoki rohibalar yashaydigan uy yoki uylar guruhi.
column14: Rohib abbatlikka qaytib kelgach, u darhol yotoqxonasiga ketdi.

example: If something is abundant, then it is available in large quantities.
type: Cakes, cookies, and candy were so abundant that the child was very happy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ko'p bo'lsa, unda u ko'p miqdorda mavjud.
column14: Keklar, pechene va konfetlar shunchalik ko'p ediki, bola juda xursand edi.

example: To adjoin something means to be next to or attached to something else.
type: She can listen to her brother’s conversations because her room adjoins his.
example_tr: Biror narsaga qo'shilish, boshqa narsaning yonida yoki unga bog'liq bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U akasining suhbatlarini tinglashi mumkin, chunki uning xonasi unikiga tutashgan.

example: If something is ample, then it is enough or more than enough.
type: There was an ample supply of oats to feed the horses.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa etarli bo'lsa, u etarli yoki ko'proq.
column14: Otlarni boqish uchun jo‘xori yetarli edi.

example: If a place is arid, then it is hot and dry and gets very little or no rain.
type: Not many plants grow in the arid desert.
example_tr: Agar joy qurg'oqchil bo'lsa, u issiq va quruq bo'lib, yomg'ir juda kam yoki umuman yog'maydi.
column14: Qurg'oqchil cho'lda ko'p o'simliklar o'smaydi.

example: A cathedral is an important and often large and beautifully built church.
type: The large cathedral is full of people on Sunday mornings.
example_tr: Sobor muhim va ko'pincha katta va chiroyli qurilgan cherkovdir.
column14: Yakshanba kuni ertalab katta sobor odamlar bilan to'la.

example: To deprive someone of something means to not let them have it.
type: Because the child was bad, she was deprived of her dessert after dinner.
example_tr: Biror kishini biror narsadan mahrum qilish, unga ega bo'lishiga yo'l qo'ymaslikdir.
column14: Bola yomon bo'lgani uchun kechki ovqatdan keyin shirinligidan mahrum bo'ldi.

example: A drought is a long period of time in which little or no rain falls.
type: After three months of drought, the vegetation and trees started dying.
example_tr: Qurg'oqchilik - bu yog'ingarchilik kam yoki umuman yog'maydigan uzoq vaqt davri.
column14: Uch oylik qurg'oqchilikdan keyin o'simliklar va daraxtlar nobud bo'la boshladi.

example: If someone is eligible, then they are permitted to do or have something.
type: Only people who bought tickets were eligible to win a prize.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi munosib bo'lsa, unga biror narsa qilish yoki ega bo'lishga ruxsat beriladi.
column14: Faqat chipta sotib olganlar sovrin yutib olishlari mumkin edi.

example: To fast means to go without food or drink for a period of time.
type: In her religion, they fast for five days and then have a big feast.
example_tr: Ro‘za tutish degani, ma’lum muddat yemay, ichmay yurish demakdir.
column14: Uning dinida ular besh kun ro'za tutishadi va keyin katta ziyofat qilishadi.

example: To grumble means to complain.
type: He grumbled about having to work late on Friday.
example_tr: G'azablanish, shikoyat qilish demakdir.
column14: U juma kuni kech ishlash kerakligidan nolidi.

example: If someone goes inland, they travel into the center of a country or land.
type: The river curved inland near the campground.
example_tr: Agar kimdir quruqlikka kirsa, u mamlakat yoki quruqlik markaziga sayohat qiladi.
column14: Daryo lager yaqinida ichkariga qiyshayib ketgan.

example: Moisture is small drops of water in the air or on a surface.
type: If you breathe on a window, moisture from your breath collects on the glass.
example_tr: Namlik - havodagi yoki sirtdagi kichik suv tomchilari.
column14: Agar siz derazada nafas olsangiz, nafasingizdagi namlik oynada to'planadi.

example: If something happens nonetheless, then it occurs despite some other thing.
type: She tried to keep the dog out of the mud, but it got dirty nonetheless.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, u boshqa narsaga qaramay sodir bo'ladi.
column14: U itni loydan saqlamoqchi bo'ldi, lekin baribir u iflos bo'ldi.

example: An oath is a formal, often public, promise.
type: Judges must take an oath to be fair to everyone in court.
example_tr: Qasamyod - bu rasmiy, ko'pincha ommaviy va'da.
column14: Sudyalar sudda hammaga adolatli bo'lishga qasamyod qilishlari kerak.

example: A prairie is a large flat area of grassland.
type: The prairie was perfect for a farm because there were hills and trees.
example_tr: Dasht - yaylovlarning katta tekis maydoni.
column14: Dasht ferma uchun juda mos edi, chunki u erda tepaliklar va daraxtlar bor edi.

example: If something is ragged, then it is old, torn, and falling apart.
type: They could see his toes through the holes in his ragged shoes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yirtilgan bo'lsa, u eski, yirtilgan va parchalanib ketgan.
column14: Ular yirtiq tuflisining teshiklaridan uning oyoq barmoqlarini ko‘rishardi.

example: If an area of land is rugged, then it is rocky and difficult to travel through.
type: Their car couldn’t make it far along the rugged roads.
example_tr: Agar er maydoni qo'pol bo'lsa, u toshloq va u orqali borish qiyin.
column14: Ularning mashinasi og'ir yo'llar bo'ylab uzoqqa chiqa olmadi.

example: If something is scarce, then it is in a very small amount.
type: When gasoline was scarce, we rode our bikes, instead of driving, to school.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kam bo'lsa, u juda oz miqdorda.
column14: Benzin taqchil bo'lganida biz maktabga mashinada emas, velosipedda yurardik.

example: To speculate means to guess about something.
type: My sister looked at the sky and speculated that it would rain tomorrow.
example_tr: Taxmin qilish, biror narsa haqida taxmin qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Opam osmonga qarab, ertaga yomg'ir yog'adi, deb taxmin qildi.

example: IF something is analytic, it is related to logic and reasoning.
type: The analytic article criticized the new plan and presented one of its own.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa analitik bo'lsa, u mantiq va fikrlash bilan bog'liq.
column14: Tahliliy maqolada yangi reja tanqid qilindi va o‘ziga xos reja taqdim etildi.

example: To assert a fact or belief means to state it with confidence.
type: He asserted that his mother’s cooking was better than his best friend’s.
example_tr: Haqiqat yoki e'tiqodni tasdiqlash uni ishonch bilan aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning ta'kidlashicha, onasining ovqat pishirishi eng yaqin do'stinikidan yaxshiroq edi.

example: A bachelor is an unmarried man.
type: Since he was a bachelor, jason did his shopping by himself.
example_tr: Bakalavr - turmushga chiqmagan erkak.
column14: U bakalavr bo'lganligi sababli, Jeyson o'zi xarid qilgan.

example: Calculus is an advanced type of mathematics.
type: By using calculus, scientists determined small changes in the stars’ brightness.
example_tr: Hisoblash matematikaning ilg'or turidir.
column14: Hisoblashdan foydalanib, olimlar yulduzlarning yorqinligidagi kichik o'zgarishlarni aniqladilar.

example: If something is celestial, it is related to the sky or to outer space.
type: Comets are celestial objects that are rarely seen.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa samoviy bo'lsa, u osmon yoki kosmos bilan bog'liq.
column14: Kometalar kamdan-kam uchraydigan samoviy jismlardir.

example: If something is cognitive, it is related to learning and knowing things.
type: After her physical examination, her cognitive strengths were tested.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kognitiv bo'lsa, u narsalarni o'rganish va bilish bilan bog'liq.
column14: Jismoniy tekshiruvdan so'ng uning kognitiv qobiliyatlari sinovdan o'tkazildi.

example: A collision is the act of two things hitting into each another.
type: The collision between the two cars created a loud noise.
example_tr: To'qnashuv - bu ikki narsaning bir-biriga tegishi.
column14: Ikki mashinaning to‘qnashuvi natijasida kuchli shovqin paydo bo‘lgan.

example: IF someone is competent, they are able to think or act successfully.
type: Competent employees are much better than unknowledgeable ones.
example_tr: AGAR kimdir qobiliyatli bo'lsa, u muvaffaqiyatli fikr yuritishi yoki harakat qilishi mumkin.
column14: Vakolatli xodimlar bilmaganlarga qaraganda ancha yaxshi.

example: A diploma is a certificate proving that someone has completed their studies.
type: After four years of college, Mary finally had a diploma.
example_tr: Diplom - bu kimningdir o'qishni tugatganligini tasdiqlovchi sertifikat.
column14: To'rt yillik kollejdan so'ng, Meri nihoyat diplomga ega bo'ldi.

example: To excel at a subject or activity means to be very good at it.
type: Jenny excels at playing the piano.
example_tr: Mavzu yoki faoliyatda ustunlik qilish, bunda juda yaxshi bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Jenni pianino chalishni juda yaxshi biladi.

example: Geology is the study of the Earth’s natural structures and how they change.
type: Because he studied geology, he knew how the mountains were formed.
example_tr: Geologiya - bu Yerning tabiiy tuzilmalari va ularning qanday o'zgarishini o'rganadigan fan.
column14: U geologiya fanini o‘rgangani uchun tog‘larning qanday paydo bo‘lishini bilar edi.

example: To harness something means to control and use it, usually to make energy.
type: The sails harness the wind in order to move.
example_tr: Biror narsani ishlatish, uni boshqarish va ishlatish, odatda energiya ishlab chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Yelkanlar harakat qilish uchun shamoldan foydalanadi.

example: An intellect is a person’s ability to understand things easily.
type: She was known for her quick and strong intellect as well as her beauty.
example_tr: Aql - bu odamning narsalarni osongina tushunish qobiliyati.
column14: U o'zining tez va kuchli aqli, shuningdek, go'zalligi bilan mashhur edi.

example: If someone is keen, they are intelligent.
type: Only the keenest of students could have solved that math problem.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qiziquvchan bo'lsa, u aqlli.
column14: Bu matematik muammoni faqat eng zukko o'quvchilar hal qilishlari mumkin edi.

example: Mythology is a group of stories from a particular country or region.
type: Egyptian mythology was the basis for a religion.
example_tr: Mifologiya - bu ma'lum bir mamlakat yoki mintaqadagi hikoyalar guruhi.
column14: Misr mifologiyasi din uchun asos bo'lgan.

example: Physiology is the study of the various parts of living things.
type: His work in physiology helped him understand how the human body works.
example_tr: Fiziologiya tirik mavjudotlarning turli qismlarini o'rganadi.
column14: Uning fiziologiya sohasidagi faoliyati unga inson tanasi qanday ishlashini tushunishga yordam berdi.

example: If something is radioactive, then it lets out, or is related to, radiation.
type: Radioactive materials can be very bad for anyone’s health.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa radioaktiv bo'lsa, u radiatsiya chiqaradi yoki u bilan bog'liq.
column14: Radioaktiv moddalar har qanday odamning sog'lig'i uchun juda yomon bo'lishi mumkin.

example: Relativity is a set of ideas about time and space developed by Albert Einstein.
type: Relativity teaches that light travels at the same speed in the universe.
example_tr: Nisbiylik - bu Albert Eynshteyn tomonidan ishlab chiqilgan vaqt va makon haqidagi g'oyalar to'plami.
column14: Nisbiylik nazariyasi yorug'lik koinotda bir xil tezlikda harakatlanishini o'rgatadi.

example: Sociology is the study of human society, its organizations, and problems.
type: Sociology teaches that people’s problems are a result of their society.
example_tr: Sotsiologiya insoniyat jamiyati, uning tashkilotlari va muammolarini o‘rganadi.
column14: Sotsiologiya odamlarning muammolari ularning jamiyatining natijasi ekanligini o'rgatadi.

example: lf something is theoretical, it is based on theory rather than experience.
type: His conclusion was only theoretical and not meant to be publicized.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa nazariy bo'lsa, u tajribaga emas, balki nazariyaga asoslanadi.
column14: Uning xulosasi faqat nazariy edi va e'lon qilinishi kerak emas edi.

example: An administrator is a person who controls a business, company, or organization.
type: Everyone in the store did whatever the administrator asked them to do.
example_tr: Administrator - bu korxona, kompaniya yoki tashkilotni boshqaradigan shaxs.
column14: Do‘kondagilarning hammasi administrator nima desa, shuni qilishardi.

example: If someone is affluent, they are wealthy.
type: People in the city are usually more affluent than people in the country.
example_tr: Agar kimdir boy bo'lsa, u boydir.
column14: Shahar aholisi odatda mamlakatdagilarga qaraganda boyroqdir.

example: To audit means to inspect financial records from a person or business.
type: The government usually audits companies that report lower than usual incomes.
example_tr: Auditorlik - bu shaxs yoki korxonaning moliyaviy hisobotlarini tekshirishni anglatadi.
column14: Hukumat odatda odatdagidan pastroq daromad keltirgan kompaniyalarni tekshiradi.

example: To automate a company means to install machines or computers to do the work.
type: When the bank automated, it started installing ATM machines.
example_tr: Kompaniyani avtomatlashtirish - bu ishni bajarish uchun mashinalar yoki kompyuterlarni o'rnatishni anglatadi.
column14: Bank avtomatlashtirilgandan so'ng bankomatlarni o'rnatishni boshladi.

example: To bribe someone means to illegally persuade them for a favor with money.
type: The judge was bribed so that she would set the suspect free.
example_tr: Birovga pora berish, uni noqonuniy ravishda pul bilan yaxshilikka ko'ndirish demakdir.
column14: Gumonlanuvchini ozod qilish uchun sudyaga pora berilgan.

example: IF someone is corrupt, they break the law for money or fame.
type: The corrupt policemen didn’t arrest the man because he gave them money.
example_tr: AGAR kimdir poraxo'r bo'lsa, u pul yoki shon-shuhrat uchun qonunni buzadi.
column14: Poraxo'r politsiyachilar bu odamni hibsga olishmadi, chunki u ularga pul berdi.

example: To dispose of something means to get rid of it.
type: He disposed of the can by throwing it into the recycle bin.
example_tr: Biror narsani yo'q qilish, undan xalos bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U qutini axlat qutisiga tashlab tashladi.

example: A headquarters is a building where the bosses of a company work.
type: He drove the long route to headquarters because it was a nice day.
example_tr: Shtab - bu kompaniya boshliqlari ishlaydigan bino.
column14: U shtab-kvartiraga uzoq yo'lni bosib o'tdi, chunki bu yaxshi kun edi.

example: An incentive is what makes a person want to do something.
type: The chance of winning a prize was incentive to get people to play the game.
example_tr: Rag'bat - bu odamni biror narsa qilishni xohlaydigan narsa.
column14: Sovrin yutib olish imkoniyati odamlarni o'yin o'ynashga undash uchun turtki bo'ldi.

example: An infrastructure is a collection of services needed to run a society or business.
type: Power lines are important parts of a city’s infrastructure.
example_tr: Infratuzilma - bu jamiyat yoki biznesni boshqarish uchun zarur bo'lgan xizmatlar to'plami.
column14: Elektr tarmoqlari shahar infratuzilmasining muhim qismidir.

example: To legislate means to make laws.
type: Senators have to legislate fairly, so most people will enjoy the benefits.
example_tr: Qonun chiqarish qonunlar ishlab chiqish demakdir.
column14: Senatorlar adolatli qonun chiqarishlari kerak, shuning uchun ko'pchilik imtiyozlardan bahramand bo'ladi.

example: If something is legitimate, then it is acceptable according to the law.
type: She found a legitimate plan to raise extra funds for her vacation.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qonuniy bo'lsa, u qonun bo'yicha qabul qilinadi.
column14: U ta'til uchun qo'shimcha mablag' to'plashning qonuniy rejasini topdi.

example: To manipulate something means to skillfully or unfairly control or affect it.
type: The Dr. manipulated the data to make it look like the cure was working.
example_tr: Biror narsani manipulyatsiya qilish, uni mohirona yoki adolatsiz boshqarish yoki ta'sir qilish demakdir.
column14: Doktor ma'lumotlarni manipulyatsiya qilib, davolanish ishlayotgandek ko'rsatdi.

example: Merchandise is goods ready to be purchased or sold.
type: The store added more merchandise because there were more shoppers.
example_tr: Tovar - bu sotib olishga yoki sotishga tayyor tovarlar.
column14: Do'kon ko'proq tovarlar qo'shdi, chunki xaridorlar ko'p edi.

example: Retail is the activity of selling goods to the public, often for personal use.
type: Though cheap to make, once a t-shirt reaches retail, it costs ten times as much.
example_tr: Chakana savdo - bu ko'pincha shaxsiy foydalanish uchun tovarlarni aholiga sotish faoliyati.
column14: Tayyorlanishi arzon bo‘lsa-da, chakana sotuvga yetib borgach, uning narxi o‘n barobar qimmatga tushadi.

example: Revenue is the income made by a company.
type: The new products really increased the business’s monthly revenue.
example_tr: Daromad - bu kompaniya tomonidan olinadigan daromad.
column14: Yangi mahsulotlar haqiqatan ham biznesning oylik daromadini oshirdi.

example: Rubbish is trash or waste.
type: The floor around the garbage can was covered with all kinds of rubbish.
example_tr: Axlat - bu axlat yoki chiqindilar.
column14: Chiqindixona atrofidagi pol har xil axlat bilan qoplangan.

example: A subsidy is money given by the government to companies to assist them.
type: The official gave the company a subsidy, so it could open two new factories.
example_tr: Subsidiya - bu hukumat tomonidan kompaniyalarga ularga yordam berish uchun beriladigan pul.
column14: Rasmiy kompaniyaga subsidiya berdi, shuning uchun u ikkita yangi zavod ochishi mumkin edi.

example: A transaction is an act of buying or selling something.
type: Because the clerk was new at the job, the simple transaction took a long time.
example_tr: Bitim - bu biror narsani sotib olish yoki sotish harakati.
column14: Kotib ishda yangi bo'lgani uchun oddiy bitim uzoq vaqt talab qildi.

example: To violate a law, rule, or agreement means to break it.
type: I was given a ticket because the policeman said I violated the speed limit.
example_tr: Qonun, qoida yoki kelishuvni buzish uni buzishni anglatadi.
column14: Politsiyachi tezlikni buzganimni aytgani uchun menga chipta berishdi.

example: To assess something means to judge the structure, purpose, or quality of it.
type: She assessed the condition of the toy car before buying it.
example_tr: Biror narsani baholash uning tuzilishini, maqsadini yoki sifatini baholashni anglatadi.
column14: U o'yinchoq mashinani sotib olishdan oldin uning holatini baholagan.

example: To astonish someone means to greatly surprise them.
type: The amount of people that came to her party astonished her.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayratda qoldirish, uni hayratda qoldirishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning ziyofatiga kelgan odamlarning soni uni hayratda qoldirdi.

example: To commence something means to begin it.
type: His speech commenced with a “thank you” to all who had helped him succeed.
example_tr: Biror narsani boshlash, uni boshlash demakdir.
column14: Uning nutqi muvaffaqiyatga erishishda yordam bergan barchaga "rahmat" bilan boshlandi.

example: The essence of something is its important qualities or basic characteristics.
type: The essence of the argument was that both sides felt they had lost money.
example_tr: Biror narsaning mohiyati uning muhim sifatlari yoki asosiy belgilaridir.
column14: Bahsning mohiyati shundaki, har ikki tomon ham pul yo‘qotganini his qilgan.

example: To extract something means to remove it.
type: The dentist extracted the woman’s damaged tooth and put in a fake one.
example_tr: Biror narsani olib tashlash, uni olib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Tish shifokori ayolning shikastlangan tishini olib tashladi va soxta tish qo'ydi.

example: If something is fabulous, it is extremely good.
type: This strawberry is the best I’ve ever had. It’s fabulous.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ajoyib bo'lsa, u juda yaxshi.
column14: Bu qulupnay men ega bo'lgan eng yaxshisidir. Bu ajoyib.

example: Haste is speed in movement or action.
type: In order to get to the meeting in time, he proceeds with haste.
example_tr: Shoshqaloqlik - bu harakat yoki harakatdagi tezlik.
column14: Uchrashuvga vaqtida yetib borish uchun u shoshqaloqlik bilan davom etadi.

example: An impulse is a sudden thoughtless urge to do something.
type: Because of the scary noise, she had an impulse to run somewhere and hide.
example_tr: Impuls - bu to'satdan o'ylamasdan biror narsa qilishga intilish.
column14: Qo'rqinchli shovqin tufayli u qayoqqadir yugurib, yashirinish uchun turtki bor edi.

example: Latter describes something last in a series or the second choice of two things.
type: In the latter minutes of the game, the visitors scored the winning goal.
example_tr: Ikkinchisi ketma-ketlikdagi oxirgi narsani yoki ikkita narsaning ikkinchi tanlovini tasvirlaydi.
column14: O‘yinning so‘nggi daqiqalarida mehmonlar g‘alaba to‘pini kiritishdi.

example: A molecule is the smallest basic unit that makes up a physical substance.
type: A tiny drop of water is made up of thousands of molecules of water.
example_tr: Molekula jismoniy moddani tashkil etuvchi eng kichik asosiy birlikdir.
column14: Kichik bir tomchi suv minglab suv molekulalaridan iborat.

example: IF something is ongoing, then it is still happening or still growing.
type: The development of plants is ongoing because it takes time for them to mature.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa davom etayotgan bo'lsa, u hali ham sodir bo'ladi yoki o'sib bormoqda.
column14: O'simliklarning rivojlanishi davom etmoqda, chunki ularning etukligi uchun vaqt kerak.

example: If something is pharmaceutical, then it is related to the development of drugs.
type: Pharmaceutical companies discover new cures to illnesses all the time.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa farmatsevtika bo'lsa, unda bu dori vositalarining rivojlanishi bilan bog'liq.
column14: Farmatsevtika kompaniyalari har doim kasalliklarni davolashning yangi usullarini topadilar.

example: IF someone is precise, then they are exact and careful about their work.
type: The builder was very precise about where he placed the nails.
example_tr: Agar kimdir aniq bo'lsa, u o'z ishiga aniq va ehtiyotkorlik bilan munosabatda bo'ladi.
column14: Quruvchi tirnoqlarni qaerga qo'yishini juda aniq edi.

example: Proximity is closeness in time, space, or relationships.
type: All the trees in the proximity of the beach had been cut down.
example_tr: Yaqinlik - bu vaqt, makon yoki munosabatlardagi yaqinlik.
column14: Sohil yaqinidagi barcha daraxtlar kesilgan.

example: Publicity is public attention given to someone or something by the media.
type: She received a lot of publicity after her performance in the film.
example_tr: Ommaviylik - ommaviy axborot vositalari tomonidan kimgadir yoki biror narsaga e'tibor berish.
column14: Filmdagi rolidan keyin u juda ko'p e'tibor qozondi.

example: A remedy is a cure for a disease, argument, or problem.
type: A good remedy for a headache is an aspirin and a glass of water.
example_tr: Dori - bu kasallik, bahs yoki muammo uchun davo.
column14: Bosh og'rig'i uchun yaxshi vosita - aspirin va bir stakan suv.

example: The significance of something is the quality that makes it important.
type: The significance of the snowy weather was that we didn’t have to go to school.
example_tr: Biror narsaning ahamiyati uni muhim qiladigan sifatdir.
column14: Qorli ob-havoning ahamiyati shundaki, biz maktabga borishimiz shart emas edi.

example: IF something is subsequent, then it comes after something else in time.
type: The flood and the subsequent rescue of those caught in the flood were on TV.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keyingi bo'lsa, u vaqt o'tishi bilan boshqa narsadan keyin keladi.
column14: Suv toshqini va undan keyin suv toshqini ostida qolganlarni qutqarish televizorda ko'rsatilgan.

example: If something is synthetic, then it is made to be like something natural.
type: Clothing made out of synthetic fabrics is very effective at keeping people warm.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sintetik bo'lsa, u tabiiy narsaga o'xshaydi.
column14: Sintetik matolardan tikilgan kiyimlar odamlarni issiq tutishda juda samarali.

example: If something is terminal, then it causes or results in death.
type: Since his condition was not terminal, he felt a great sense of relief.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa terminal bo'lsa, u o'limga olib keladi yoki o'limga olib keladi.
column14: Uning ahvoli yakuniy emasligi sababli, u katta yengillik his qildi.

example: The altitude of a place is its height above sea level.
type: The air was thin at such a high altitude on the mountain.
example_tr: Joyning balandligi - bu uning dengiz sathidan balandligi.
column14: Tog'da shunday balandda havo yupqa edi.

example: A coastline is the outline of a country’s coast.
type: He noticed that most of the cities in Australia are on the coastline.
example_tr: Sohil chizig'i - bu mamlakat qirg'oqlarining konturi.
column14: U Avstraliyadagi shaharlarning ko'pchiligi qirg'oq bo'yida ekanligini payqadi.

example: To deter means to prevent or discourage someone from doing something.
type: Icy roads deter people from driving their cars.
example_tr: To'xtatish, kimnidir biror narsa qilishiga yo'l qo'ymaslik yoki qaytarishni anglatadi.
column14: Muzli yo'llar odamlarni mashinalarini haydashdan qaytaradi.

example: To devise something means to have an idea or plan about it in the mind.
type: The thieves devised a plan to steal the diamonds.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'ylab topish, u haqida fikr yoki rejaga ega bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: O'g'rilar olmoslarni o'g'irlash rejasini tuzdilar.

example: Expertise is the knowledge and skills to do something well.
type: John has a lot of advertising expertise. He can sell anything!
example_tr: Mutaxassislik - bu biror narsani yaxshi bajarish uchun bilim va ko'nikmalar.
column14: Jon juda ko'p reklama tajribasiga ega. U hamma narsani sotishi mumkin!

example: A fracture is a crack or break in something.
type: Don’t stand on that leg because there is a fracture. It might get worse.
example_tr: Sinish - biror narsaning yorilishi yoki sinishi.
column14: Oyoq ustida turmang, chunki sinish bor. Bu yomonlashishi mumkin.

example: To impair something means to damage it or make it worse.
type: Drinking coffee impairs my ability to go to sleep.
example_tr: Biror narsani buzish, uni buzish yoki yomonlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kofe ichish uyquga ketish qobiliyatimni buzadi.

example: To implement something means to ensure that what has been planned is done.
type: The school decided to implement a new teaching strategy.
example_tr: Biror narsani amalga oshirish, rejalashtirilgan narsaning bajarilishini ta'minlashni anglatadi.
column14: Maktab yangi o'qitish strategiyasini amalga oshirishga qaror qildi.

example: If something is indigenous, it is originally from, or native to, a place.
type: Tomatoes are indigenous to the Americas.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mahalliy bo'lsa, u asl joydan yoki mahalliy joydandir.
column14: Pomidorlar Amerika qit'asining tub aholisi hisoblanadi.

example: Insight is a deep and accurate understanding of something.
type: The physics textbook gave the student new insight about gravity.
example_tr: Insight - bu biror narsani chuqur va aniq tushunishdir.
column14: Fizika darsligi talabaga tortishish haqida yangi tushuncha berdi.

example: A limb is a large branch on a tree.
type: The monkey sat on the tree limb and enjoyed a piece of fruit.
example_tr: Oyoq - daraxtdagi katta shox.
column14: Maymun daraxt shoxiga o'tirdi va bir parcha mevadan zavqlandi.

example: A migraine is a painful headache that makes one feel sick.
type: My sister gets a migraine every time she has a lot of stress.
example_tr: O'chokli og'riqli bosh og'rig'i bo'lib, odam o'zini yomon his qiladi.
column14: Opam har safar juda ko'p stress bo'lganida migrenga duchor bo'ladi.

example: Optimism is the feeling of being hopeful about the future or success of something.
type: The mother had optimism about her children’s futures.
example_tr: Optimizm - bu kelajakka yoki biror narsaning muvaffaqiyatiga umid qilish hissi.
column14: Ona farzandlarining kelajagi haqida nekbin edi.

example: When something is peculiar, it is strange, sometimes in a bad way.
type: That peculiar smell coming from the kitchen reminds me of rotten eggs.
example_tr: Biror narsa o'ziga xos bo'lsa, u g'alati, ba'zan yomon tarzda.
column14: Oshxonadan kelayotgan o'ziga xos hid menga chirigan tuxumni eslatadi.

example: When a person is proficient at something, they can do it well.
type: Secretaries are proficient at typing quickly.
example_tr: Biror kishi biror narsada malakali bo'lsa, u buni yaxshi qila oladi.
column14: Kotiblar tez yozishni yaxshi bilishadi.

example: A quest is a long and difficult search for something.
type: The treasure hunter went on a quest to find an ancient gold necklace.
example_tr: Kvest - bu biror narsani uzoq va qiyin izlash.
column14: Xazina ovchisi qadimiy tilla marjonni topish uchun izlanishga chiqdi.

example: A ridge is a long, narrow piece of raised land.
type: The brown bear walked along the edge of the mountain ridge.
example_tr: Togʻ tizmasi — baland erning uzun, tor qismi.
column14: Qo‘ng‘ir ayiq tog‘ tizmasi bo‘ylab yurdi.

example: A spouse is the person to whom someone is married.
type: I live in a home with my spouse and our two children.
example_tr: Turmush o'rtog'i - bu kimdir turmush qurgan shaxs.
column14: Men turmush o'rtog'im va ikki farzandimiz bilan uyda yashayman.

example: To thrust means to push or move something quickly with a lot of force.
type: The boxer thrust his fist into the punching bag.
example_tr: Surish - biror narsani katta kuch bilan tez surtish yoki harakatga keltirish demakdir.
column14: Bokschi musht qopiga musht tushirdi.

example: To tolerate something means to be able to accept it even when it is unpleasant.
type: When you are in a hurry, it can be hard to tolerate traffic signals.
example_tr: Biror narsaga chidash, uni yoqimsiz bo'lsa ham qabul qila olish demakdir.
column14: Shoshayotganingizda, svetoforlarga toqat qilish qiyin bo'lishi mumkin.

example: Ifa plant or animal is aquatic, it lives or grows in water.
type: The dolphin is an aquatic mammal.
example_tr: Agar o'simlik yoki hayvon suvda yashovchi bo'lsa, u suvda yashaydi yoki o'sadi.
column14: Delfin suvda yashovchi sutemizuvchidir.

example: The biosphere is the earth’s surface and atmosphere where there are living things.
type: Birds, trees, and worms all thrive in the biosphere.
example_tr: Biosfera - bu tirik mavjudotlar mavjud bo'lgan yer yuzasi va atmosfera.
column14: Qushlar, daraxtlar va qurtlar biosferada ko'payadi.

example: When something is bizarre, it is very strange.
type: My bizarre dreams make no sense to me when I am awake.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'alati bo'lsa, u juda g'alati bo'ladi.
column14: Uyg'onganimda mening g'alati tushlarimning ma'nosi yo'q.

example: Celsius is a scale for measuring temperature.
type: Water freezes at zero degrees Celsius.
example_tr: Selsiy - haroratni o'lchash uchun shkala.
column14: Suv nol daraja Selsiyda muzlaydi.

example: If something is coarse, that means it has a rough texture.
type: The coarse sweater made my skin itch.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qo'pol bo'lsa, bu uning qo'pol tuzilishga ega ekanligini anglatadi.
column14: Dag'al kozok terimni qichitdi.

example: A companion is a person that someone spends a lot of time with.
type: I always walk to school with my companion Frank.
example_tr: Hamroh - bu kimdir ko'p vaqt o'tkazadigan odam.
column14: Men doim hamrohim Frenk bilan maktabga boraman.

example: To digest means to swallow food and pass it through the body.
type: Allow some time for food to be digested before going swimming.
example_tr: Ovqat hazm qilish deganda ovqatni yutish va uni tanadan o'tkazish tushuniladi.
column14: Suzishga borishdan oldin ovqat hazm bo'lishi uchun biroz vaqt ajrating.

example: The duration of an event is the time during which it happens.
type: The girls watched television for the duration of the evening.
example_tr: Voqea davomiyligi - bu sodir bo'ladigan vaqt.
column14: Kechqurun qizlar televizor tomosha qilishdi.

example: Ecology is the study of the environment and living things.
type: We study ecology to learn how to help improve the Earth.
example_tr: Ekologiya atrof-muhit va tirik mavjudotlarni o'rganadi.
column14: Biz Yerni yaxshilashga qanday yordam berishni o'rganish uchun ekologiyani o'rganamiz.

example: A feat is an impressive or difficult achievement or action.
type: The elephant’s standing up on one leg was a feat.
example_tr: Jasorat - bu ta'sirli yoki qiyin yutuq yoki harakat.
column14: Filning bir oyog'ida turishi jasorat edi.

example: IF something is infinite, it has no limit or end.
type: Many scientists believe that the universe is infinite.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa cheksiz bo'lsa, uning chegarasi ham, oxiri ham yo'q.
column14: Ko'pgina olimlar koinotning cheksiz ekanligiga ishonishadi.

example: The nucleus is the central part of an atom or cell.
type: The nucleus is made up of many tiny particles.
example_tr: Yadro atom yoki hujayraning markaziy qismidir.
column14: Yadro ko'plab mayda zarralardan iborat.

example: A parasite is a tiny animal or plant that attaches to another animal to get food.
type: The sick dog was covered in parasites.
example_tr: Parazit - oziq-ovqat olish uchun boshqa hayvonga yopishib oladigan mayda hayvon yoki o'simlik.
column14: Kasal it parazitlar bilan qoplangan.

example: When something is prominent, it is important and well known.
type: Queen Victoria was a prominent person in history.
example_tr: Biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u muhim va yaxshi ma'lum.
column14: Qirolicha Viktoriya tarixdagi taniqli shaxs edi.

example: When something is repetitive, it is repeated many times and becomes boring.
type: Working on an assembly line making cars every day is a repetitive job.
example_tr: Biror narsa takrorlansa, u ko'p marta takrorlanadi va zerikarli bo'ladi.
column14: Har kuni avtomobil ishlab chiqaradigan konveyerda ishlash takrorlanadigan ishdir.

example: If something is reproductive, it has to do with a living thing producing young.
type: The reproductive system of a plant is simple.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa reproduktiv bo'lsa, bu tirik mavjudotning yosh tug'ilishi bilan bog'liq.
column14: O'simlikning reproduktiv tizimi oddiy.

example: When a place is temperate, it never gets too hot or cold.
type: In Peru, the weather is temperate and rarely gets too hot or cold.
example_tr: Agar joy mo''tadil bo'lsa, u hech qachon juda issiq yoki sovuq bo'lmaydi.
column14: Peruda ob-havo mo''tadil va kamdan-kam hollarda juda issiq yoki sovuq bo'ladi.

example: Tolerance is the ability to accept something painful or unpleasant.
type: Boxers have a high tolerance for pain.
example_tr: Tolerantlik - og'riqli yoki yoqimsiz narsani qabul qilish qobiliyati.
column14: Bokschilar og'riqqa chidamliligi yuqori.

example: To undergo an action means to have it happen to you.
type: The cancer patient undergoes treatments twice a week.
example_tr: Harakatni boshdan kechirish, bu siz bilan sodir bo'lishini anglatadi.
column14: Saraton kasalligi haftasiga ikki marta davolanadi.

example: When someone is vulnerable, they are weak and without protection.
type: He felt very vulnerable when he was stranded in the desert.
example_tr: Biror kishi zaif bo'lsa, u zaif va himoyasizdir.
column14: U sahroda qolib ketganida o'zini juda zaif his qilgan.

example: If someone is adept at something, they are very good at doing it.
type: The carpenter is very adept at building houses.
example_tr: Agar kimdir biror narsaga mohir bo'lsa, u buni juda yaxshi bajaradi.
column14: Duradgor uy qurishda juda mohir.

example: If land is barren, it has no plants growing on it.
type: People cannot farm in barren lands.
example_tr: Agar yer unumdor bo'lsa, unda o'simliklar o'smaydi.
column14: Odamlar taqir yerlarda dehqonchilik qila olmaydi.

example: If something is ceramic, it is made of baked clay.
type: The house’s roof was made of ceramic tiles.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa keramika bo'lsa, u pishirilgan loydan qilingan.
column14: Uyning tomi keramik plitkalardan qilingan.

example: If something is culinary, it is related to cooking.
type: I gained culinary skills after working in a restaurant for many years.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oshpazlik bo'lsa, u pishirish bilan bog'liq.
column14: Men uzoq yillar restoranda ishlaganimdan keyin oshpazlik mahoratiga ega bo‘ldim.

example: If something is dense, it has a lot of things close together.
type: I easily became lost in the dense forest.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa zich bo'lsa, unda bir-biriga yaqin bo'lgan juda ko'p narsalar mavjud.
column14: Men zich o'rmonda osongina adashib qoldim.

example: Dignity is the ability to be calm and worthy of respect.
type: When his company went out of business, he faced it with dignity.
example_tr: Qadr-qimmat - bu xotirjam va hurmatga loyiq bo'lish qobiliyati.
column14: Uning kompaniyasi ishlamay qolganda, u buni hurmat bilan qarshi oldi.

example: To dominate someone or something is to control them.
type: The loud man dominated the conversation.
example_tr: Birovga yoki biror narsaga hukmronlik qilish - ularni boshqarish.
column14: Baland ovozli odam suhbatda hukmronlik qildi.

example: If something is edible, you can eat it.
type: We learn about edible plants when we go camping.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yeyish mumkin bo'lsa, uni eyishingiz mumkin.
column14: Biz lagerga borganimizda qutulish mumkin bo'lgan o'simliklar haqida bilib olamiz.

example: If someone is hostile, they are angry and unfriendly.
type: We were happy to move away from our hostile neighbor.
example_tr: Agar kimdir dushman bo'lsa, u g'azablangan va do'stona emas.
column14: Biz dushman qo‘shnimizdan uzoqlashganimizdan xursand edik.

example: Your intake of food is the amount of food you take into your body.
type: The doctor said I needed to increase my intake of fruits and vegetables.
example_tr: Oziq-ovqat iste'mol qilish - bu tanangizga kiradigan oziq-ovqat miqdori.
column14: Shifokor meva va sabzavotlarni ko'paytirishim kerakligini aytdi.

example: If someone does something likewise, they do the same thing as someone else.
type: If Joe is staying away from school to go swimming, I want to do likewise.
example_tr: Agar kimdir xuddi shunday ish qilsa, u ham boshqa birov bilan bir xil narsani qiladi.
column14: Agar Jo suzish uchun maktabdan uzoqda qolsa, men ham xuddi shunday qilishni xohlayman.

example: Malnutrition is the condition of not getting enough nutrients.
type: After eating only a meager amount of food, she suffered from malnutrition.
example_tr: Noto'g'ri ovqatlanish - bu etarli miqdorda ozuqa moddalarini olmaslik sharti.
column14: Ozgina ovqat iste'mol qilgach, u to'yib ovqatlanmaslikdan aziyat chekdi.

example: Medication is medicine or drugs given to people who are sick.
type: The doctor gave me medication to treat my illness.
example_tr: Dori - bu kasal odamlarga beriladigan dori yoki dorilar.
column14: Shifokor menga kasallikni davolash uchun dori berdi.

example: A misconception is a wrong idea about something.
type: People once believed the misconception that the Earth is flat.
example_tr: Noto'g'ri tushuncha - bu biror narsa haqida noto'g'ri fikr.
column14: Bir paytlar odamlar Yer tekisligi haqidagi noto'g'ri tushunchaga ishonishgan.

example: If something is obscure, it is not well-known.
type: The old man travels the world in search of obscure books.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noaniq bo'lsa, u hammaga ma'lum emas.
column14: Chol noaniq kitoblarni izlab dunyo kezadi.

example: To oppress someone means to rule over them in a cruel and unfair way.
type: Free speech had been oppressed in his country.
example_tr: Birovga zulm qilish, uni shafqatsiz va nohaq tarzda hukmronlik qilish demakdir.
column14: Uning mamlakatida so'z erkinligi tazyiq ostida edi.

example: To peel fruits and vegetables is to remove their skin.
type: We peeled the apple before eating it.
example_tr: Meva va sabzavotlarni tozalash ularning terisini olib tashlashdir.
column14: Biz olmani eyishdan oldin tozalab oldik.

example: A prescription is permission from a doctor to get medicine.
type: The doctor gave me a prescription for my medication.
example_tr: Retsept - bu dori olish uchun shifokorning ruxsati.
column14: Shifokor menga dori-darmonlarim uchun retsept berdi.

example: A respirator is a machine that helps weak or sick people breathe.
type: The man needed a respirator to breathe.
example_tr: Nafas olish apparati - bu zaif yoki kasal odamlarning nafas olishiga yordam beradigan mashina.
column14: Nafas olish uchun odamga respirator kerak edi.

example: To strive is to struggle to achieve something.
type: People who strive to succeed often do.
example_tr: Intilish - biror narsaga erishish uchun kurashish.
column14: Ko'pincha muvaffaqiyatga erishmoqchi bo'lgan odamlar buni qilishadi.

example: If something is archaic, it is very old or outdated.
type: To be competitive, we must update our archaic equipment.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa arxaik bo'lsa, u juda eski yoki eskirgan.
column14: Raqobatbardosh bo'lish uchun biz eski jihozlarimizni yangilashimiz kerak.

example: If someone is benevolent, they are kind and generous.
type: My father was a benevolent man and gave lots of money to charity.
example_tr: Agar kimdir xayrixoh bo'lsa, u mehribon va saxiydir.
column14: Dadam mehribon odam bo'lib, xayriya ishlariga ko'p pul ajratardi.

example: Brass is a metal that is used to make musical instruments and ornaments.
type: Brass is used to make musical instruments like trumpets.
example_tr: Guruch - musiqa asboblari va bezaklar yasash uchun ishlatiladigan metall.
column14: Guruchdan karnay kabi musiqa asboblari yasaladi.

example: Capitalism is an economic system where private companies make goods for profit.
type: Most industries in the world today are based on capitalism.
example_tr: Kapitalizm - bu xususiy kompaniyalar foyda olish uchun mahsulot ishlab chiqaradigan iqtisodiy tizim.
column14: Bugungi kunda dunyodagi aksariyat sanoatlar kapitalizmga asoslangan.

example: A component is a part of a larger machine.
type: Computers have many different components, so they are complicated to build.
example_tr: Komponent kattaroq mashinaning bir qismidir.
column14: Kompyuterlar juda ko'p turli xil komponentlarga ega, shuning uchun ularni qurish juda murakkab.

example: Dependence is a situation in which somebody relies on something else.
type: Young children have a dependence on their parents.
example_tr: Qaramlik - bu kimdir boshqa narsaga tayanadigan vaziyat.
column14: Yosh bolalar ota-onalariga qaram bo'lishadi.

example: To diminish means to reduce or get smaller.
type: As the economy got worse, my savings diminished.
example_tr: Kichraytirmoq, kamaymoq yoki kichraymoq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Iqtisodiyot yomonlashgani sari jamg'armalarim kamayib ketdi.

example: A drawback is a disadvantage.
type: The drawback of having a car is that it is very expensive to maintain.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu kamchilik.
column14: Avtomobilga ega bo'lishning kamchiliklari shundaki, uni saqlash juda qimmat.

example: A fad is something that is popular for a short time.
type: The hula hoop was a fad for a few years, but it soon lost its popularity.
example_tr: Moda - bu qisqa vaqt ichida mashhur bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Hula-halqa bir necha yillar davomida moda edi, lekin tez orada u mashhurligini yo'qotdi.

example: To impose means to interrupt or force your ideas on other people.
type: He imposes on his wife every morning by expecting her to make breakfast.
example_tr: Tajriba qilish o'z g'oyalaringizni boshqa odamlarga to'xtatish yoki majburlash demakdir.
column14: U har kuni ertalab xotiniga nonushta qilishini kutadi.

example: Managerial describes something related to a manager or management.
type: She has managerial experience in the tech industry.
example_tr: Menejment menejer yoki boshqaruv bilan bog'liq narsalarni tavsiflaydi.
column14: U texnologiya sohasida boshqaruv tajribasiga ega.

example: If something is medieval, it comes from the period between 650 and 1500 CE.
type: We visited a castle that was built during medieval times.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'rta asrlarga tegishli bo'lsa, u miloddan avvalgi 650 va 1500 yillar oralig'ida keladi.
column14: Biz o'rta asrlarda qurilgan qal'ani ziyorat qildik.

example: If something is obsolete, it is not used anymore because something better exists.
type: Since computers became inexpensive, typewriters have become obsolete.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa eskirgan bo'lsa, u endi ishlatilmaydi, chunki yaxshiroq narsa mavjud.
column14: Kompyuterlar arzonlashgandan beri yozuv mashinkalari yaroqsiz holga keldi.

example: A peninsula is a large piece of land that is surrounded by the sea on three sides.
type: The state of Florida is an example of a peninsula.
example_tr: Yarim orol uch tomondan dengiz bilan o'ralgan katta quruqlik qismidir.
column14: Florida shtati yarim orolga misoldir.

example: If a person has prestige, people admire or respect them.
type: The young actress gained much prestige after she won an award.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi obro'ga ega bo'lsa, odamlar uni qadrlashadi yoki hurmat qilishadi.
column14: Yosh aktrisa mukofotni qo'lga kiritganidan keyin katta obro'-e'tibor qozondi.

example: A proportion is an amount that shows the link between the parts and the whole.
type: Only a small proportion of the people in this town actually work here.
example_tr: Proporsiya - bu qismlar va butun o'rtasidagi bog'liqlikni ko'rsatadigan miqdor.
column14: Bu shaharcha aholisining faqat kichik bir qismi ishlaydi.

example: If something is radical, it is very new or different.
type: The president is planning to make some radical changes to the law.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa radikal bo'lsa, u juda yangi yoki boshqacha.
column14: Prezident qonunga tubdan o‘zgartirish kiritishni rejalashtirmoqda.

example: To refute something means to prove that it is false or incorrect.
type: The bank manager has refuted the claims that he lied to his customers.
example_tr: Biror narsani inkor etish uning yolg‘on yoki noto‘g‘ri ekanligini isbotlash demakdir.
column14: Bank menejeri o'z mijozlariga yolg'on gapirgani haqidagi da'volarni rad etdi.

example: If something is spectacular, it looks or sounds very impressive.
type: There was a spectacular fireworks display in the park at New Year.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ajoyib bo'lsa, u juda ta'sirli ko'rinadi yoki eshitiladi.
column14: Yangi yil bayrami munosabati bilan bog'da ajoyib otashinlar namoyish etildi.

example: To weave means to make cloth using horizontal and vertical threads.
type: We saw a woman weave a blanket on our vacation to South America.
example_tr: Toʻqish deganda gorizontal va vertikal iplar yordamida mato yasash tushuniladi.
column14: Biz Janubiy Amerikaga ta'tilda bir ayolning adyol to'qiganini ko'rdik.

example: An accountant is a person whose job is to keep financial accounts.
type: The accountant helped me keep track of my money.
example_tr: Buxgalter - bu moliyaviy hisobni yuritish bo'lgan shaxs.
column14: Buxgalter menga pullarimni hisobga olishda yordam berdi.

example: A capitalist is a business person who invests in trade and industry for profit.
type: The capitalist invested in a factory that made wheat into cereal.
example_tr: Kapitalist - foyda olish uchun savdo va sanoatga sarmoya kiritadigan tadbirkor.
column14: Kapitalist bug'doydan don ishlab chiqaradigan zavodga sarmoya kiritdi.

example: Contempt is the feeling of having no respect for something.
type: The judge had contempt for the wicked criminal.
example_tr: Nafrat - biror narsani hurmat qilmaslik hissi.
column14: Sudya yovuz jinoyatchiga nafrat bilan qaradi.

example: To dedicate oneself to something means to put a lot of time and effort into it.
type: The nun dedicated herself to helping people in need.
example_tr: O'zini biror narsaga bag'ishlash, unga ko'p vaqt va kuch sarflashni anglatadi.
column14: Rohiba o'zini muhtojlarga yordam berishga bag'ishladi.

example: A ditch is a narrow hole cut into the ground by a road or a field.
type: When the car slid off of the road, it fell into the ditch.
example_tr: Xandaq - yo'l yoki dala tomonidan erga o'yilgan tor teshik.
column14: Mashina yo‘ldan sirg‘alib ketganida ariqga tushib ketgan.

example: An enterprise is a company or business.
type: My father owns an advertising enterprise.
example_tr: Korxona - bu kompaniya yoki korxona.
column14: Dadamning reklama korxonasi bor.

example: When something is exquisite, it is very beautiful or pleasant.
type: The artist made exquisite watercolor paintings.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa nafis bo'lsa, u juda chiroyli yoki yoqimli.
column14: Rassom akvarel bo'ylab nafis rasmlar yaratdi.

example: To finance someone or something means to provide money for them.
type: The government financed the scientist’s experiments with new weapons.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani moliyalashtirish, ularni pul bilan ta'minlashni anglatadi.
column14: Hukumat olimning yangi qurollar bilan tajribalarini moliyalashtirdi.

example: When someone is indifferent toward something, they have a lack of interest in it.
type: Lisa is indifferent toward school. She doesn’t care what her final grades are.
example_tr: Biror kishi biror narsaga befarq bo'lsa, unda unga qiziqish yo'q.
column14: Liza maktabga befarq. U yakuniy baholari qanday ekanligiga ahamiyat bermaydi.

example: To irrigate means to supply water to land so that crops can grow.
type: In dry climates, it is important to irrigate fields of crops.
example_tr: Sug'orish - ekinlar o'sishi uchun yerga suv berish demakdir.
column14: Quruq iqlim sharoitida ekin maydonlarini sug'orish muhim ahamiyatga ega.

example: To maximize something is to make it as great in amount, size, or importance.
type: You should exercise regularly to maximize a healthy lifestyle.
example_tr: Biror narsani maksimal darajada oshirish - uni miqdori, hajmi yoki ahamiyati bo'yicha katta qilishdir.
column14: Sog'lom turmush tarzini maksimal darajada oshirish uchun siz muntazam ravishda mashq qilishingiz kerak.

example: When something is monetary, it relates to money.
type: A strong monetary policy is important for a country to be successful.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa pul bo'lsa, u pul bilan bog'liq.
column14: Kuchli pul-kredit siyosati mamlakat muvaffaqiyatli bo'lishi uchun muhimdir.

example: A precaution is an action that is meant to stop something bad from happening.
type: As a precaution, you should put on a heavy coat before going out in cold weather.
example_tr: Ehtiyot chorasi - biror yomon narsa sodir bo'lishini to'xtatish uchun qilingan harakat.
column14: Ehtiyot chorasi sifatida sovuq havoda ko'chaga chiqishdan oldin siz og'ir palto kiyishingiz kerak.

example: Preliminary describes something that happens before a more important event.
type: The runners must do well in the preliminary races to qualify for the final race.
example_tr: Oldinroq muhimroq voqea oldidan sodir bo'lgan narsani tasvirlaydi.
column14: Yuguruvchilar final poygasiga chiqish uchun dastlabki poygalarda yaxshi natija ko'rsatishlari kerak.

example: To saturate something means to completely soak it with a liquid.
type: The sponge was saturated with soapy water and dripped all over the floor.
example_tr: Biror narsani to'yintirish, uni suyuqlik bilan to'liq ho'llash demakdir.
column14: Shimgich sovunli suv bilan to'yingan va butun erga tomizilgan.

example: The simplicity of something is the fact that it is easy to do or understand.
type: We were able to find the house thanks to the simplicity of the directions.
example_tr: Biror narsaning soddaligi - buni qilish yoki tushunish oson bo'lgan haqiqatdir.
column14: Yo'nalishlarning soddaligi tufayli biz uyni topa oldik.

example: To sow seeds means to plant them in the ground.
type: He always sows his garden seeds in the springtime.
example_tr: Urug'larni ekish - ularni erga ekish demakdir.
column14: U har doim bahorda bog'iga urug'larni ekadi.

example: Soy is a food made from soybeans, such as flour or butter.
type: Soy can be made into tofu, sauce, and also milk.
example_tr: Soya - un yoki sariyog 'kabi soyadan tayyorlangan taom.
column14: Soyadan tofu, sous, shuningdek sut tayyorlanishi mumkin.

example: A spade is a tool used for digging.
type: The gardener used her spade to make a hole for the seed.
example_tr: Kurak - qazish uchun ishlatiladigan asbob.
column14: Bog‘bon belkurakdan foydalanib, urug‘ uchun teshik ochdi.

example: When something is upcoming, that means it will happen in the near future.
type: The kids were worried about their upcoming exam.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yaqinlashayotgan bo'lsa, bu yaqin kelajakda sodir bo'lishini anglatadi.
column14: Bolalar yaqinlashib kelayotgan imtihondan xavotirda edilar.

example: When a bad thing is acute, it is very severe and intense.
type: When she fell out of the tree, the girl felt an acute pain in her arm.
example_tr: Yomon narsa o'tkir bo'lsa, u juda og'ir va kuchli.
column14: U daraxtdan yiqilganida, qiz qo'lida o'tkir og'riqni his qildi.

example: Aggression is behavior that is mean or violent to others.
type: The problem was only made worse by Mark’s aggression.
example_tr: Agressiya - bu boshqalar uchun shafqatsiz yoki zo'ravonlik.
column14: Markning tajovuzkorligi muammoni yanada kuchaytirdi.

example: A banquet is a grand formal dinner.
type: Both families brought a lot of food for the wedding banquet.
example_tr: Ziyofat - bu katta rasmiy kechki ovqat.
column14: Ikkala oila ham to'y ziyofatiga juda ko'p ovqat olib kelishdi.

example: A biography is an account of someone's life that is written by someone else.
type: We read a biography about Charles Darwin in science class.
example_tr: Biografiya - bu boshqa birov tomonidan yozilgan birovning hayoti haqidagi hikoya.
column14: Biz fan darsida Charlz Darvin haqidagi biografiyani o'qidik.

example: To boost something means to increase or improve it.
type: Lowering prices boosts customers’ interest in shopping.
example_tr: Biror narsani kuchaytirish, uni oshirish yoki yaxshilash demakdir.
column14: Narxlarni pasaytirish mijozlarning xarid qilishga qiziqishini oshiradi.

example: To clap means to hit one’s hands together to express pleasure or get attention.
type: After the speech, everyone in the crowd clapped their hands for the speaker.
example_tr: Qarsak chalish, zavqlanish yoki e'tiborni jalb qilish uchun qo'llarni bir-biriga urish demakdir.
column14: Nutqdan so‘ng olomondagilarning barchasi ma’ruzachi uchun qo‘l urishdi.

example: To compel someone to do something means to force them to do it.
type: Traffic signs compel drivers to drive safely.
example_tr: Biror kishini biror narsa qilishga majburlash, uni majburlash demakdir.
column14: Yo'l belgilari haydovchilarni xavfsiz haydashga majbur qiladi.

example: The dominance of a person is their state of being more powerful than others.
type: Large gorillas hit their chests to express their dominance over others.
example_tr: Shaxsning hukmronligi uning boshqalardan ko'ra kuchliroq bo'lgan holatidir.
column14: Katta gorillalar boshqalar ustidan hukmronlik qilish uchun ko'kragiga urishdi.

example: When something is gorgeous, it is very pleasing and attractive.
type: The girl picked out a gorgeous dress to wear to the dance.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ajoyib bo'lsa, u juda yoqimli va jozibali bo'ladi.
column14: Qiz raqsga kiyish uchun ajoyib libos tanladi.

example: When something is inevitable, it is certain to happen or cannot be avoided.
type: It is inevitable that the days will get longer in the summer.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muqarrar bo'lsa, u albatta sodir bo'ladi yoki undan qochib bo'lmaydi.
column14: Yozda kunlar uzoqlashishi muqarrar.

example: A legacy is an effect that exists because of a person or thing in the past.
type: The legacy of the ancient Egyptians can be seen in their monuments.
example_tr: Meros - bu o'tmishdagi shaxs yoki narsa tufayli mavjud bo'lgan ta'sir.
column14: Qadimgi misrliklarning merosini ularning yodgorliklarida ko'rish mumkin.

example: A masterpiece is a very good painting, novel, movie, or other work of art.
type: The Arc de Triomphe is considered a masterpiece in the world of architecture.
example_tr: Asar - bu juda yaxshi rasm, roman, kino yoki boshqa san'at asari.
column14: Arc de Triomphe arxitektura olamining durdona asari hisoblanadi.

example: If there are multiple things, there are many of them.
type: When the stunt went wrong, the man suffered multiple injuries.
example_tr: Agar bir nechta narsa bo'lsa, ularning ko'pi bor.
column14: Kaskadyor noto'g'ri bo'lganida, erkak ko'plab jarohatlar oldi.

example: To narrate a story means to write about it or read it aloud.
type: This story was written by john, but Aaron is narrating it to the crowd.
example_tr: Hikoyani hikoya qilish u haqida yozish yoki uni ovoz chiqarib o'qish demakdir.
column14: Bu hikoyani Jon yozgan, ammo Horun buni olomonga aytib beryapti.

image: yomon nom chiqargan, yomon otliq boʻlgan
example: When something is notorious, it is well-known because of something bad.
type: This area of town is notorious for gang activity.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mashhur bo'lsa, u yomon narsa tufayli taniqli bo'ladi.
column14: Shaharning bu hududi jinoiy guruhlar faoliyati bilan mashhur.

example: When something is outdated, it is old and no longer useful in modern time.
type: Tape players are becoming outdated because of digital music.
example_tr: Qachonki biror narsa eskirgan bo'lsa, u eski bo'lib, zamonaviy davrda endi foydali emas.
column14: Raqamli musiqa tufayli lenta pleyerlari eskirib bormoqda.

example: When a thing is talked about overall, the whole thing is considered.
type: Overall, the party was a huge success.
example_tr: Biror narsa haqida umumiy gap ketganda, hamma narsa ko'rib chiqiladi.
column14: Umuman olganda, partiya katta muvaffaqiyatga erishdi.

example: A partiality is a tendency to prefer one thing to another.
type: She has a partiality for watking to school instead of driving.
example_tr: Tarafsizlik - bir narsani boshqasidan afzal ko'rish tendentsiyasi.
column14: U mashinani haydash o'rniga maktabga qarashni yoqtiradi.
