example: When an act is spontaneous, it is not planned. It happens suddenly.
type: My wife made a spontaneous decision to buy a new sofa while | was at work.
example_tr: Harakat o'z-o'zidan bo'lsa, u rejalashtirilmaydi. Bu birdan sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Xotinim o'z-o'zidan yangi divan sotib olishga qaror qildi | ishda edi.

example: A virtue is a good quality or way of behaving.
type: My best virtue is forgiveness.
example_tr: Fazilat - bu yaxshi sifat yoki o'zini tutish usuli.
column14: Mening eng yaxshi fazilatim kechirimdir.

example: Anthropology is the study of people, society, and culture.
type: In anthropology class, I learned about simple tools that ancient cultures used.
example_tr: Antropologiya odamlar, jamiyat va madaniyatni o'rganadi.
column14: Antropologiya darsida men qadimgi madaniyatlar qo‘llagan oddiy vositalar bilan tanishdim.

example: To applaud means to clap in order to show approval.
type: Everyone cheered and applauded Manny's efforts.
example_tr: Qarsak chalish ma’qullash uchun qarsak chalish demakdir.
column14: Menni harakatlarini hamma olqishladi va olqishladi.

example: To appoint someone to a job means to give the job to them.
type: Two students were appointed to help the scientists with their research.
example_tr: Biror kishini ishga tayinlash, unga ishni berish demakdir.
column14: Olimlarga tadqiqot ishlarida yordam berish uchun ikkita talaba tayinlandi.

example: When things are compatible, they work well or exist together successfully.
type: Jan and Fred are too different. They will never be compatible.
example_tr: Agar narsalar mos bo'lsa, ular yaxshi ishlaydi yoki birgalikda muvaffaqiyatli mavjud.
column14: Jan va Fred juda boshqacha. Ular hech qachon mos kelmaydi.

example: Competence is the ability to do something well or effectively.
type: The job was easy because the group had enough competence to do it well.
example_tr: Kompetensiya - biror narsani yaxshi yoki samarali bajarish qobiliyati.
column14: Ish oson edi, chunki guruh buni yaxshi bajarish uchun etarli malakaga ega edi.

example: To confer with someone means to discuss something with them to make a decision.
type: I will have to confer with my wife before I can purchase a new car.
example_tr: Biror kishi bilan maslahatlashish, qaror qabul qilish uchun u bilan biror narsani muhokama qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Yangi mashina sotib olishdan oldin xotinim bilan maslahatlashishim kerak.

example: When things are consecutive, they happen one after another without interruption.
type: The king ruled for ten consecutive years.
example_tr: Ishlar ketma-ket bo'lsa, ular uzluksiz birin-ketin sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Podshoh ketma-ket o'n yil hukmronlik qildi.

example: When something is crude, it is not exact or detailed, but it can still be useful.
type: She drew crude hearts on the ground to show how much she loved him.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qo'pol bo'lsa, u aniq yoki batafsil emas, lekin u hali ham foydali bo'lishi mumkin.
column14: U uni qanchalik sevishini ko'rsatish uchun erga qo'pol yuraklarni chizdi.

example: A cube is a solid object with six square surfaces that are all the same size.
type: Please get me some ice cubes to put in my soda.
example_tr: Kub - bu bir xil o'lchamdagi oltita kvadrat yuzasi bo'lgan qattiq jismdir.
column14: Iltimos, soda qo'yishim uchun menga muz kublarini olib keling.

example: Feedback is comments to a person about how they are doing something.
type: I asked my boss for feedback on my work.
example_tr: Fikr-mulohaza - bu odamga qanday qilib biror narsa qilayotgani haqida sharh.
column14: Men xo'jayinimdan ishim haqida fikr so'radim.

example: Ignorance of something is lack of knowledge about it.
type: When he failed the test, his ignorance of math was obvious.
example_tr: Biror narsadan bexabarlik - bu haqdagi bilimning etishmasligi.
column14: Sinovdan o‘ta olmaganida, matematikani bilmasligi yaqqol ko‘rinib turardi.

example: When something is masculine, it is a quality or thing related to men.
type: American football is usually considered a masculine sport.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa erkakka xos bo'lsa, bu sifat yoki erkaklarga tegishli narsadir.
column14: Amerika futboli odatda erkaklar sporti hisoblanadi.

example: A monument is a structure that is built to remind people of a person or event.
type: A large monument was built to honor the brave soldiers.
example_tr: Yodgorlik - bu inson yoki voqeani eslatish uchun qurilgan inshoot.
column14: Jasur askarlar sharafiga katta yodgorlik qurildi.

example: When someone is muscular, they are very fit and strong.
type: He exercised regularly so that his body could become muscular.
example_tr: Biror kishi muskulli bo'lsa, u juda mos va kuchli.
column14: U muntazam ravishda jismoniy mashqlar bilan shug'ullangan, shunda uning tanasi mushak bo'lishi mumkin edi.

example: A person’s posture is the position in which they stand or sit.
type: Your back will feel better if you improve your posture.
example_tr: Biror kishining pozitsiyasi - bu uning turgan yoki o'tirgan holati.
column14: Sizning holatingizni yaxshilasangiz, orqangiz yaxshilanadi.

example: To situate something means to place or build it in a certain place.
type: The road was situated between the forest and the lake.
example_tr: Biror narsani joylashtirish, uni ma'lum bir joyga joylashtirish yoki qurish demakdir.
column14: Yo'l o'rmon va ko'l o'rtasida joylashgan edi.

example: To supervise something means to make sure that it is done correctly.
type: Allen supervised the construction workers to ensure everyone’s safety.
example_tr: Biror narsani nazorat qilish uning to'g'ri bajarilishiga ishonch hosil qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Allen barchaning xavfsizligini ta'minlash uchun qurilish ishchilarini nazorat qildi.

example: Symmetry is the state of having two halves that are exactly the same.
type: The artist made sure to use perfect symmetry when painting the butterfly.
example_tr: Simmetriya - bu bir xil bo'lgan ikkita yarmiga ega bo'lish holati.
column14: Rassom kapalakni chizishda mukammal simmetriyadan foydalanishga ishonch hosil qilgan.

example: A tattoo is a design that is drawn permanently on the skin with needles.
type: The surfer had tattoos on both his arms.
example_tr: Tatuirovka - bu ignalar bilan teriga doimiy ravishda chizilgan dizayn.
column14: Syorferning ikkala qo'lida tatuirovka bor edi.

example: An undergraduate is a student at a college who is studying for a bachelor’s degree.
type: She was excited to finish high school and enroll as an undergraduate in the fall.
example_tr: Bakalavr - bu bakalavr bosqichida tahsil olayotgan kollej talabasi.
column14: U o'rta maktabni tugatib, kuzda bakalavrga o'qishga kirishidan hayajonlandi.

example: A brook is a small stream.
type: Water flows down several brooks on the mountain.
example_tr: Daryo - bu kichik oqim.
column14: Tog'dagi bir nechta ariqlardan suv oqadi.

example: To cater to someone means to provide them with all the things needed or wanted.
type: Bill was too sick to get out of bed, so his nurse catered to his needs.
example_tr: Biror kishiga xizmat qilish, uni barcha kerakli yoki xohlagan narsalar bilan ta'minlashni anglatadi.
column14: Bill to'shakdan turolmaydigan darajada kasal edi, shuning uchun hamshirasi uning ehtiyojlarini qondirdi.

example: When someone is considerate, they pay attention to the needs of others.
type: The considerate boy gave a present to his girlfriend on Valentine's Day.
example_tr: Biror kishi e'tiborli bo'lsa, u boshqalarning ehtiyojlariga e'tibor beradi.
column14: Ehtiyotkor bola sevishganlar kunida sevgilisiga sovg'a berdi.

example: The consumption of food or drink is the act of eating or drinking it.
type: These apples are too rotten for consumption.
example_tr: Oziq-ovqat yoki ichimlik iste'mol qilish - uni eyish yoki ichish harakati.
column14: Bu olma iste'mol qilish uchun juda chirigan.

example: Criteria are factors on which a person judges or decides something.
type: Before she got the job, she had to meet all the necessary criteria.
example_tr: Mezon - bu inson biror narsani hukm qiladigan yoki qaror qiladigan omillar.
column14: Ishga kirishdan oldin u barcha kerakli mezonlarga javob berishi kerak edi.

example: Crust is the tough outer part of a loaf of bread.
type: The little boy never ate the crust of his pizza.
example_tr: Qobiq nonning qattiq tashqi qismidir.
column14: Kichkina bola hech qachon pitssaning qobig'ini yemagan.

example: To degrade someone means to cause people to have shame.
type: The teacher degraded Bob when she announced his poor performance to the class
example_tr: Birovni kamsitish, odamlarni sharmanda qilish demakdir.
column14: O'qituvchi Bobning yomon ishlashini sinfga e'lon qilganda, uni kamsitdi

example: To entitle someone means to give them the rights to have or do something.
type: His golden ticket entitled him to sit in the front row at the concert.
example_tr: Biror kishiga huquq berish, unga biror narsaga ega bo'lish yoki qilish huquqini berishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning oltin chiptasi unga kontsertda birinchi qatorda o'tirish huquqini berdi.

example: To escort people means to safely accompany them to a place.
type: Her bodyguards escorted her to the movie theater.
example_tr: Odamlarni kuzatib borish, ularni xavfsiz joyga kuzatib borishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning tansoqchilari uni kinoteatrgacha kuzatib borishdi.

example: When something is external, it is connected to an outer part.
type: It is warm inside my house, but the external temperature is freezing.
example_tr: Biror narsa tashqi bo'lsa, u tashqi qismga ulanadi.
column14: Uyim ichida havo issiq, lekin tashqi harorat sovuq.

example: A facility is a building that exists for a particular purpose.
type: There are many educational facilities
example_tr: Ob'ekt - bu ma'lum bir maqsad uchun mavjud bo'lgan bino.
column14: Ko'plab ta'lim muassasalari mavjud

example: A faculty is a mental or physical ability.
type: The boy’s mental faculties impressed all of his teachers.
example_tr: Fakultet - bu aqliy yoki jismoniy qobiliyat.
column14: Bolaning aqliy qobiliyatlari uning barcha o'qituvchilarini hayratda qoldirdi.

example: A heap of things is a large pile of them.
type: After the building was torn down, all that was left was a heap of bricks.
example_tr: Bir to'p narsa - bu ularning katta uyasi.
column14: Bino buzib tashlanganidan keyin bir uyum g‘isht qolgan xolos.

example: A hemisphere is one half of the earth.
type: In the northern hemisphere, the weather is usually warmest in July and August.
example_tr: Yarim shar erning yarmini tashkil qiladi.
column14: Shimoliy yarim sharda ob-havo odatda iyul va avgust oylarida eng issiq bo'ladi.

example: A hound is a type of dog that is often used for racing or hunting.
type: The men took their hounds with them when they went on the hunting trip.
example_tr: It ko'pincha poyga yoki ov uchun ishlatiladigan it turidir.
column14: Erkaklar ovga chiqqanda itlarini o‘zlari bilan olib ketishgan.

example: If something is impersonal, it is not friendly and makes people feel unimportant.
type: The boy felt scared on his first day at the big, impersonal high school.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa shaxsiy bo'lmasa, u do'stona emas va odamlarni ahamiyatsiz his qiladi.
column14: Bola katta, shaxssiz o'rta maktabdagi birinchi kunida qo'rquvni his qildi.

example: An ornament is an attractive object that people display in their homes.
type: The woman kept some colorful ornaments on the shelves.
example_tr: Ornament - bu odamlar o'z uylarida ko'rsatadigan jozibali narsadir.
column14: Ayol javonlarda bir nechta rang-barang bezaklarni saqladi.

example: A pedestrian is a person who is walking on a street.
type: Cars should be careful when pedestrians are walking around.
example_tr: Piyoda - bu ko'chada ketayotgan odam.
column14: Piyodalar aylanib o'tayotganda mashinalar ehtiyot bo'lishlari kerak.

example: A sanctuary is a place where people in danger can go to be safe.
type: The church was made into a sanctuary for homeless people in the winter.
example_tr: Qo'riqxona - bu xavf ostida bo'lgan odamlar xavfsiz bo'lish uchun boradigan joy.
column14: Cherkov qishda uysizlar uchun ziyoratgohga aylantirilgan.

example: A spectator is someone who watches something, especially a sports event.
type: There were thousands of spectators at the big game.
example_tr: Tomoshabin - biror narsani, ayniqsa, sport musobaqasini tomosha qiladigan kishi.
column14: Katta o'yinda minglab tomoshabinlar bor edi.

example: An asset is a skill or quality that is useful or valuable.
type: The coach realized the boy’s speed was an asset to the team.
example_tr: Aktiv - bu foydali yoki qimmatli mahorat yoki sifat.
column14: Murabbiy bolaning tezligi jamoa uchun foydali ekanligini tushundi.

example: An aspect is one part or feature of something.
type: I thought about the different aspects of owning two dogs.
example_tr: Aspekt - biror narsaning bir qismi yoki xususiyati.
column14: Men ikkita itga ega bo'lishning turli jihatlari haqida o'yladim.

example: Braille is a system of raised patterns on paper that allows the blind to read.
type: The boy enjoyed reading his favorite books written in Braille.
example_tr: Brayl - bu ko'rlarga o'qish imkonini beruvchi qog'ozdagi baland naqshlar tizimi.
column14: Bola Brayl alifbosida yozilgan sevimli kitoblarini zavq bilan o'qidi.

example: A bud is a part of a plant that turns into a flower or a leaf.
type: Two weeks after planting the seed, a small bud appeared.
example_tr: Kurtak - o'simlikning gul yoki bargga aylanadigan qismi.
column14: Urug'ni ekishdan ikki hafta o'tgach, kichik kurtak paydo bo'ldi.

example: To coordinate things is to make different parts work together.
type: Each skating team had to coordinate their movements for the show.
example_tr: Ishlarni muvofiqlashtirish - bu turli qismlarning birgalikda ishlashini ta'minlashdir.
column14: Har bir konkida uchish jamoasi shou uchun harakatlarini muvofiqlashtirishi kerak edi.

example: To disprove something means to show that it is not true.
type: The scientist disproved the theory that the sun moved around the Earth.
example_tr: Biror narsani inkor qilish uning to'g'ri emasligini ko'rsatishni anglatadi.
column14: Olim Quyoshning Yer atrofida harakatlanishi haqidagi nazariyani rad etdi.

example: If something is humanitarian, it is connected to helping people’s lives.
type: After the flood, several humanitarian organizations offered help.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa insonparvarlik bo'lsa, u odamlar hayotiga yordam berish bilan bog'liq.
column14: To'fondan keyin bir qancha gumanitar tashkilotlar yordam taklif qildi.

example: A hypothesis is an idea for something that has not been proved yet.
type: The teacher did an experiment to prove whether his hypothesis was right.
example_tr: Gipoteza - bu hali isbotlanmagan narsaning g'oyasi.
column14: O'qituvchi o'z farazining to'g'riligini isbotlash uchun tajriba o'tkazdi.

example: An imprint is an effect or lesson from an experience that is hard to forget.
type: The experience of war left an imprint on his mind that troubled him.
example_tr: Imprint - unutish qiyin bo'lgan tajribaning ta'siri yoki saboqidir.
column14: Urush tajribasi uning ongida iz qoldirib, uni tashvishga soldi.

example: When something is informative, it provides a lot of information.
type: The travel guide had a lot of informative facts about the region.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa informatsion bo'lsa, u juda ko'p ma'lumot beradi.
column14: Sayohat qo'llanmasida mintaqa haqida juda ko'p ma'lumot beruvchi faktlar mavjud edi.

example: When something is optic, it relates to the eyes or light.
type: Her blindness was caused by a problem with her optic nerve.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa optik bo'lsa, u ko'zlar yoki yorug'lik bilan bog'liq.
column14: Uning ko‘rligi ko‘rish nervidagi muammo sabab bo‘lgan.

example: A premise is an idea on which something is based.
type: The premise of the movie that Bobbi and I watched was unrealistic.
example_tr: Oldindan biror narsa asos bo‘ladigan fikr.
column14: Bobbi va men tomosha qilgan filmning asosi haqiqatga to'g'ri kelmaydi.

example: A rack is an object with shelves that holds things.
type: He stored his tools on a rack.
example_tr: Rack - bu narsalarni ushlab turadigan javonli ob'ekt.
column14: U asboblarini tokchada saqlagan.

example: The Renaissance was a period between the 14th and 17th centuries.
type: Leonardo Da Vinci was a popular artist of the Renaissance.
example_tr: Uygʻonish davri 14—17-asrlar oraligʻidagi davr edi.
column14: Leonardo da Vinchi Uyg'onish davrining mashhur rassomi edi.

example: To revere something is to admire it greatly.
type: The students revere their teacher, who has taught them a lot.
example_tr: Biror narsani hurmat qilish, uni juda hayratda qoldirishdir.
column14: Talabalar o‘zlariga ko‘p narsalarni o‘rgatgan ustozini hurmat qilishadi.

example: When something is simultaneous, it occurs at the same time as something else.
type: The movement of the gears inside the watch was simultaneous.
example_tr: Biror narsa bir vaqtda bo'lsa, u boshqa narsa bilan bir vaqtda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Soat ichidagi viteslarning harakati bir vaqtning o'zida edi.

example: A skeptic is a person who does not believe something.
type: The scientist showed the skeptic that dinosaurs did exist by providing evidence.
example_tr: Skeptik - bu biror narsaga ishonmaydigan odam.
column14: Olim skeptiklarga dinozavrlarning haqiqatan ham borligiga dalil keltirish orqali ko‘rsatdi.

example: When something is spatial, it relates to the position and size of things.
type: He was asked where the books were located to test his spatial ability.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa fazoviy bo'lsa, u narsalarning holati va hajmiga bog'liq.
column14: Uning fazoviy qobiliyatini sinab ko'rish uchun undan kitoblar qayerda joylashganligi so'ralgan.

example: To specify is to describe something clearly.
type: The poster didn’t specify where the concert was taking place.
example_tr: Aniqlash - biror narsani aniq tasvirlash.
column14: Plakatda kontsert qayerda bo'lib o'tayotganiga aniqlik kiritilmagan.

example: Wax is a substance that is slightly shiny and melts when heated.
type: The candles are made of wax.
example_tr: Mum bir oz porloq va qizdirilganda eriydigan moddadir.
column14: Shamlar mumdan qilingan.

example: An accessory is a thing that is added to another thing to make it look better.
type: The store sold colorful accessories like bags, sunglasses, and makeup.
example_tr: Aksessuar - bu boshqa narsaga yaxshi ko'rinish uchun qo'shiladigan narsa.
column14: Do'konda sumkalar, quyoshdan saqlaydigan ko'zoynaklar va bo'yanish kabi rangli aksessuarlar sotilgan.

example: An acquisition is something that a person buys or gets in some way.
type: Marty was happy with his new acquisition: a very fast bicycle.
example_tr: Sotib olish - bu odam qandaydir tarzda sotib oladigan yoki oladigan narsadir.
column14: Marti o'zining yangi xarididan xursand edi: juda tez velosiped.

example: When something is adequate, it is good enough for something else.
type: Without adequate notice of the road block, they will have to turn around.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa etarli bo'lsa, u boshqa narsa uchun etarli.
column14: Yo'l to'sig'i to'g'risida tegishli ogohlantirishsiz, ular burilishga majbur bo'ladi.

example: Cardboard is a material made out of stiff paper. It is often used to make boxes.
type: We packed our things into cardboard boxes and moved to our new home.
example_tr: Karton qattiq qog'ozdan tayyorlangan materialdir. Ko'pincha qutilarni tayyorlash uchun ishlatiladi.
column14: Biz narsalarimizni karton qutilarga solib, yangi uyimizga ko'chib o'tdik.

example: A dilemma is a difficult situation in which a choice has to be made.
type: Choosing either the tastier or healthier drink proved to be quite a dilemma.
example_tr: Dilemma - bu tanlov qilish kerak bo'lgan qiyin vaziyat.
column14: Mazali yoki foydali ichimlikni tanlash juda qiyin bo'ldi.

example: When something is elaborate, it contains a lot of details.
type: She gave the teacher an elaborate explanation of her project.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ishlab chiqilgan bo'lsa, unda juda ko'p tafsilotlar mavjud.
column14: U o'qituvchiga o'z loyihasini batafsil tushuntirib berdi.

example: To facilitate something is to make it easier.
type: To facilitate the meeting, Melissa used a simple computer program.
example_tr: Biror narsani osonlashtirish, uni osonlashtirishdir.
column14: Uchrashuvni osonlashtirish uchun Melissa oddiy kompyuter dasturidan foydalangan.

example: A fleet is a group of ships.
type: The fleet of ships spent a few days at the dock.
example_tr: Filo - bu kemalar guruhi.
column14: Kemalar floti dokda bir necha kun o'tkazdi.

example: A grid is a pattern of squares with numbers and letters to find places on a map.
type: We located our town using the grid.
example_tr: To'r - bu xaritadagi joylarni topish uchun raqamlar va harflardan iborat kvadratchalar naqshidir.
column14: Biz shaharchamizni tarmoq yordamida aniqladik.

example: To import means to bring in a product from another country.
type: Foods that have been imported are usually more expensive.
example_tr: Import degani mahsulot boshqa davlatdan olib kirish demakdir.
column14: Import qilingan oziq-ovqatlar odatda qimmatroq.

example: To infer something is to decide it is true based on other information one has.
type: By the position of the sun in the sky, she inferred that it was noon.
example_tr: Biror narsani xulosa qilish - bu mavjud bo'lgan boshqa ma'lumotlarga asoslanib, uning haqiqat ekanligini aniqlash.
column14: Quyoshning osmondagi holatiga ko'ra, u kunduzi deb xulosa qildi.

example: To inflate something means to fill it up with air.
type: I helped him inflate the balloons.
example_tr: Biror narsani puflash, uni havo bilan to'ldirishni anglatadi.
column14: Men unga sharlarni shishirishiga yordam berdim.

example: When something is innate, it is something that one is born with, it is not learned.
type: He had the innate desire to please his teachers.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tug'ma bo'lsa, u tug'ilgan narsadir, u o'rganilmaydi.
column14: U ustozlarini rozi qilish uchun tug'ma ishtiyoqga ega edi.

example: Marble is a type of rock that feels cold and is smooth when cut.
type: The large house had floors made of marble.
example_tr: Marmar - sovuqni his qiladigan va kesilganda silliq bo'lgan tosh turi.
column14: Katta uyning pollari marmardan yasalgan edi.

example: A mast is a long pole on a ship that holds the sail.
type: The mast held both sails of the ship upright.
example_tr: Mast - yelkanni ushlab turadigan kemadagi uzun qutb.
column14: Mast kemaning ikkala yelkanini tik ushlab turardi.

example: Nausea is the feeling of being sick to your stomach.
type: The doctor said the medicine would help get rid of her nausea.
example_tr: Ko'ngil aynish - bu sizning oshqozoningiz kasal bo'lish hissi.
column14: Shifokorning aytishicha, dori uning ko'ngil aynishidan xalos bo'lishga yordam beradi.

example: When something is naval, it relates to a country’s navy or military ships.
type: The country sent all of its naval forces to protect them.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa dengiz bo'lsa, u mamlakatning dengiz floti yoki harbiy kemalariga tegishli.
column14: Mamlakat ularni himoya qilish uchun barcha dengiz kuchlarini yubordi.

example: A pouch is a small, flexible bag that is usually made of cloth.
type: I keep my money in a small pouch.
example_tr: Xalta - odatda matodan qilingan kichik, egiluvchan sumka.
column14: Men pulimni kichik sumkada saqlayman.

example: If something is saturated, it is completely wet.
type: Leigh’s hair became saturated in the rain storm.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'yingan bo'lsa, u butunlay nam.
column14: Leyning sochlari yomg'ir bo'ronida to'yingan edi.

example: To update something means to make it more modern.
type: We need to update the programs on our computers.
example_tr: Biror narsani yangilash, uni yanada zamonaviy qilish demakdir.
column14: Biz kompyuterlarimizdagi dasturlarni yangilashimiz kerak.

example: An addict is a person who cannot stop doing or having something.
type: She was a coffee addict. She had more than three cups each day.
example_tr: Giyohvand - biror narsa qilish yoki ega bo'lishni to'xtata olmaydigan odam.
column14: U qahvaga qaram edi. U har kuni uchta stakandan ko'proq ichdi.

example: When something is archeological, it relates to archeology.
type: They found archeological evidence that proved an ancient species of man.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa arxeologik bo'lsa, u arxeologiyaga tegishli.
column14: Ular insonning qadimgi turini isbotlovchi arxeologik dalillarni topdilar.

example: Archeology is the study of ancient people through their artifacts.
type: He studied archeology to learn more about ancient Egyptian culture.
example_tr: Arxeologiya qadimiy odamlarni ularning artefaktlari orqali o'rganadi.
column14: U qadimgi Misr madaniyati haqida ko'proq ma'lumot olish uchun arxeologiyani o'rgangan.

example: To brainstorm is to have a lot of ideas about a certain topic.
type: The students met after school to brainstorm ideas for their assignment.
example_tr: Aqliy hujum - bu ma'lum bir mavzu bo'yicha juda ko'p g'oyalarga ega bo'lish.
column14: Talabalar maktabdan so'ng o'z topshiriqlari bo'yicha fikr almashish uchun uchrashdilar.

example: A budget is the amount of money available to spend on something.
type: His budget for food was very tight.
example_tr: Byudjet - bu biror narsaga sarflash mumkin bo'lgan pul miqdori.
column14: Uning oziq-ovqat uchun byudjeti juda qattiq edi.

example: When something is chaotic, it is crazy, confused, and hectic.
type: The first day of school can be chaotic for a new student.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa xaotik bo'lsa, u aqldan ozgan, chalkash va notinch bo'ladi.
column14: Maktabning birinchi kuni yangi o'quvchi uchun xaotik bo'lishi mumkin.

example: To cite something is to mention it as an example or as proof of something.
type: She cited six reasons that the school needed to build new classrooms.
example_tr: Biror narsani keltirish, uni biror narsaga misol yoki dalil sifatida keltirishdir.
column14: U maktabda yangi sinfxonalar qurish zarurligining oltita sababini keltirdi.

example: To correspond is to match or to be similar to something.
type: The boy’s story didn’t correspond with his mother’s version.
example_tr: Mos kelmoq - biror narsaga mos kelmoq yoki o'xshash bo'lmoq.
column14: Bolaning hikoyasi onasining versiyasiga mos kelmadi.

example: A courtyard is an outdoor area that is surrounded by the walls of a building.
type: During the summer, the courtyard is a nice place to have lunch.
example_tr: Hovli - bu binoning devorlari bilan o'ralgan tashqi maydon.
column14: Yozda hovli tushlik qilish uchun yaxshi joy.

example: An estate is a large area of land owned by a family or organization.
type: He lived on his father’s estate in the country.
example_tr: Mulk - bu oila yoki tashkilotga tegishli bo'lgan katta er maydoni.
column14: U mamlakatdagi otasining mulkida yashagan.

example: Fraud is the crime of gaining money by lying or by tricking people.
type: Experts say that credit card fraud increases around the holidays.
example_tr: Firibgarlik - yolg'on gapirish yoki odamlarni aldab pul topish jinoyatidir.
column14: Mutaxassislarning ta'kidlashicha, bayram kunlari kredit kartalaridagi firibgarliklar ko'payadi.

example: Hydrogen is a gas that has no taste, color, or smell.
type: Balloons filled with hydrogen can easily float away if you aren’t careful.
example_tr: Vodorod ta'mi, rangi va hidiga ega bo'lmagan gazdir.
column14: Vodorod bilan to'ldirilgan sharlar, agar ehtiyot bo'lmasangiz, osongina suzib ketishi mumkin.

example: Integrity is honesty and good morals.
type: The principal had a lot of integrity.
example_tr: Insof bu halollik va yaxshi axloqdir.
column14: Direktor juda sofdillikka ega edi.

example: To knit is to make fabric by connecting strings together.
type: My grandmother knitted me a sweater.
example_tr: Trikotaj - bu iplarni bir-biriga bog'lab, mato yasash.
column14: Buvim menga kozok to'qdi.

example: An outlook is a person’s opinion or way of thinking about something.
type: He changed his outlook about rats after he read a book about them.
example_tr: Dunyoqarash - bu insonning biror narsa haqida fikri yoki fikrlash usuli.
column14: U kalamushlar haqidagi kitobni o‘qiganidan so‘ng ular haqidagi dunyoqarashini o‘zgartirdi.

example: A parachute is a device that helps people and things fall to the ground safely.
type: They used parachutes dropped from airplanes to send supplies to the civilians.
example_tr: Parashyut - bu odamlar va narsalarning erga xavfsiz tushishiga yordam beradigan qurilma.
column14: Ular tinch aholiga yuklarni yuborish uchun samolyotlardan tushirilgan parashyutlardan foydalanganlar.

example: When something is prehistoric, it is from a time when there was no written history.
type: The scientists found prehistoric pots used by the peaple in the area.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tarixdan oldingi bo'lsa, u yozma tarix bo'lmagan davrga tegishli.
column14: Olimlar ushbu hududda peple ishlatadigan tarixdan oldingi idishlarni topdilar.

example: A proponent is a person who supports an idea or a plan.
type: He was a proponent of using environmentally friendly products.
example_tr: Taqdimotchi - bu g'oya yoki rejani qo'llab-quvvatlovchi shaxs.
column14: U ekologik toza mahsulotlardan foydalanish tarafdori edi.

example: To refine something is to make it better by making changes.
type: The principal refined his method of controlling students over the years.
example_tr: Biror narsani takomillashtirish - o'zgartirishlar kiritish orqali uni yaxshilashdir.
column14: Direktor yillar davomida talabalarni nazorat qilish uslubini takomillashtirdi.

example: To restrict is to limit something and prevent it from getting bigger.
type: The club restricted the amount of members.
example_tr: Cheklash - biror narsani cheklash va uning kattalashishiga yo'l qo'ymaslikdir.
column14: Klub a'zolar sonini cheklab qo'ydi.

example: An attorney is one who gives others advice about the law.
type: The attorney appeared in front of the judge for me.
example_tr: Advokat - bu qonun bo'yicha boshqalarga maslahat beradigan kishi.
column14: Men uchun advokat sudyaning qarshisida paydo bo'ldi.

example: When something is chronic, it happens over and over again over time.
type: He had chronic pain in his chest and needed to see a doctor.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa surunkali bo'lsa, vaqt o'tishi bilan u qayta-qayta sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Uning ko'kragida surunkali og'riq bor edi va shifokorga murojaat qilish kerak edi.

example: Discipline is training that helps people follow the rules.
type: One of the teacher’s jobs is to teach her students discipline.
example_tr: Intizom - bu odamlarga qoidalarga rioya qilishga yordam beradigan ta'lim.
column14: O'qituvchining vazifalaridan biri shogirdlariga tartib-intizomni o'rgatishdir.

example: A donor is somebody who gives something to an organization.
type: He was proud to be a blood donor.
example_tr: Donor - bu tashkilotga biror narsa beradigan kishi.
column14: U qon donori ekanidan faxrlanardi.

example: A fellow is someone who shares a job or quality with someone else.
type: All of my fellow patients at the hospital have also complained about the food.
example_tr: Hamkor - bu boshqa birov bilan ish yoki sifatni baham ko'radigan kishi.
column14: Kasalxonadagi barcha bemorlarim ham ovqatdan shikoyat qilishdi.

example: Gossip is information that might be untrue but is still discussed anyway.
type: The friends exchanged gossip about the people they knew in school.
example_tr: G'iybat - bu noto'g'ri bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan, ammo baribir muhokama qilinadigan ma'lumotlar.
column14: Do'stlar maktabda tanishgan odamlari haqida g'iybat bilan almashishdi.

example: To graduate from a school means to complete and pass all courses of study there.
type: At the end of the spring, my friends and I will graduate from high school.
example_tr: Maktabni tugatish degani, u erda o'qishning barcha kurslarini tugatish va o'tish.
column14: Bahor oxirida men va do‘stlarim maktabni bitiramiz.

example: Graffiti is words or drawings in public places.
type: The wall was covered with colorful graffiti.
example_tr: Graffiti - bu jamoat joylaridagi so'zlar yoki chizmalar.
column14: Devor rang-barang graffiti bilan qoplangan.

example: A guardian is someone who protects somebody or something.
type: The librarians are the guardians of the books.
example_tr: Qo'riqchi - bu kimnidir yoki biror narsani himoya qiladigan kishi.
column14: Kutubxonachilar kitoblarning qo'riqchilaridir.

example: To implicate someone is to show that they have done a crime or something bad.
type: The man was implicated in the theft at the store.
example_tr: Kimnidir ayblash, uning jinoyat yoki yomon ish qilganligini ko'rsatishdir.
column14: Erkak do‘kondagi o‘g‘irlikda ishtirok etgan.

example: Kin is a one's family and relatives.
type: His kin were all farmers.
example_tr: Qarindosh - bu oila va qarindoshlar.
column14: Uning qarindoshlarining hammasi dehqon edi.

example: A referee is a person who makes sure that the rules are followed in sports.
type: The soccer player didn’t agree with the referee.
example_tr: Hakam - sportda qoidalarga rioya qilinishini nazorat qiluvchi shaxs.
column14: Futbolchi hakamning fikriga qo'shilmadi.

example: To sever something is to cut through it completely.
type: He severed the string using scissors.
example_tr: Biror narsani uzish, uni butunlay kesib tashlashdir.
column14: U qaychi yordamida ipni uzdi.

example: A shaft is a handle of a tool or weapon.
type: The golf club had a long wooden shaft that he held in his hands.
example_tr: Mil - bu asbob yoki qurolning dastasi.
column14: Golf klubida uning qo'lida ushlab turgan uzun yog'och mil bor edi.

example: To stab means to cut someone or something with a sharp object like a knife.
type: He stabbed the fork into the potato and passed it to his daughter.
example_tr: Pichoq kabi birovni yoki biror narsani o'tkir narsa bilan kesishni anglatadi.
column14: U sanchqini kartoshkaga sanchib, qiziga uzatdi.

example: A stimulus is something that causes growth or activity.
type: Having a lot of money is a stimulus for people to buy more things.
example_tr: Rag'bat - bu o'sish yoki faollikni keltirib chiqaradigan narsa.
column14: Ko'p pulga ega bo'lish odamlarning ko'proq narsalarni sotib olishiga turtki bo'ladi.

example: A suspicion is a feeling that something is possible or true in a crime.
type: The police had a suspicion that the driver had stolen the purse.
example_tr: Gumon - jinoyatda biror narsaning mumkin yoki haqiqat ekanligini his qilish.
column14: Politsiya haydovchining hamyonni o‘g‘irlaganiga shubha qilgan.

example: To terminate something means to stop or end it.
type: The trip was terminated after the car broke down.
example_tr: Biror narsani tugatish, uni to'xtatish yoki tugatish demakdir.
column14: Mashina buzilganidan keyin sayohat to'xtatildi.

example: A theme is the main subject of a book, movie, or painting.
type: The students discussed the book’s theme in class.
example_tr: Mavzu kitob, film yoki rasmning asosiy mavzusidir.
column14: Talabalar darsda kitob mavzusini muhokama qildilar.

example: Tuition is the amount of money paid to go to a school.
type: University tuitions have increased by fifty percent in the last five years.
example_tr: O'qish - bu maktabga borish uchun to'lanadigan pul miqdori.
column14: Oxirgi besh yil ichida universitetlarda o‘qish to‘lovlari ellik foizga oshdi.

example: If someone is aggressive, then they constantly want to fight.
type: Nobody liked to play games with him because he was always too aggressive.
example_tr: Agar kimdir tajovuzkor bo'lsa, u doimo jang qilishni xohlaydi.
column14: Hech kim u bilan o'ynashni yoqtirmasdi, chunki u har doim juda tajovuzkor edi.

example: Amnesty is a pardon given to prisoners of war.
type: She was denied amnesty for her involvement in the war.
example_tr: Amnistiya - bu harbiy asirlarga berilgan afv.
column14: U urushda qatnashgani uchun amnistiyadan bosh tortdi.

example: An arena is a building where people can watch sports and concerts.
type: The new arena was all set to hold the championship match.
example_tr: Arena - bu odamlar sport va konsert tomosha qilishlari mumkin bo'lgan bino.
column14: Yangi arena chempionlik o'yinini o'tkazishga tayyor edi.

example: An auditorium is a large building used for public events.
type: People have gathered at the school auditorium to watch the play.
example_tr: Auditoriya - ommaviy tadbirlar uchun foydalaniladigan katta bino.
column14: Xalq spektaklni tomosha qilish uchun maktab auditoriyasiga yig‘ilgan.

example: A captive is a prisoner.
type: The guards told the captive that there was no way he could escape the prison.
example_tr: Asir - mahbus.
column14: Soqchilar asirga qamoqxonadan qochishning iloji yo‘qligini aytishdi.

example: Combat is fighting between two people or groups.
type: The two warriors were locked in combat.
example_tr: Jang - bu ikki kishi yoki guruh o'rtasidagi jang.
column14: Ikki jangchi jangda qulflangan edi.

example: If something is commonplace, then it is ordinary.
type: There is nothing commonplace about the way Morris dresses.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa odatiy bo'lsa, u odatiy.
column14: Morrisning kiyinish uslubida oddiy narsa yo'q.

example: A compound is an enclosed area such as a prison or factory.
type: The workers waited outside the compound for the gates to the factory to open.
example_tr: Murakkab qamoqxona yoki fabrika kabi yopiq hududdir.
column14: Ishchilar majmua tashqarisida zavod darvozalari ochilishini kutishdi.

example: A corps is a division of a military force.
type: The army had a corps of archers who trained apart from the regular soldiers.
example_tr: Korpus - harbiy kuchlarning bo'linmasi.
column14: Armiyada oddiy askarlardan tashqari kamonchilar korpusi ham bor edi.

example: To distract someone means to stop them from concentrating on something.
type: The phone call distracted him so much that he forgot all about his homework.
example_tr: Biror kishining e'tiborini chalg'itish, uning diqqatini biror narsaga qaratishga to'sqinlik qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Telefon qo'ng'irog'i uni shunchalik chalg'itib yubordiki, u uy vazifasini unutdi.

example: If someone is dumb, they are unable to speak.
type: She did not share the secret. She remained silent as if she were dumb.
example_tr: Agar kimdir soqov bo'lsa, u gapira olmaydi.
column14: U sirni oshkor qilmadi. U xuddi soqovday jim qoldi.

example: A foe is an enemy or opponent.
type: It was hard to believe that anyone could be his foe.
example_tr: Dushman - dushman yoki raqib.
column14: Kimdir uning dushmani bo'lishi mumkinligiga ishonish qiyin edi.

example: To hack something means to cut it into uneven pieces.
type: My uncle used the ax to hack the tree into many logs.
example_tr: Biror narsani buzish, uni notekis bo'laklarga bo'lish demakdir.
column14: Amakim bolta bilan daraxtni ko‘p yog‘ochlarga buzib tashladi.

example: To meditate means to focus or think deeply in silence.
type: She liked to meditate for several hours of each day.
example_tr: Meditatsiya qilish, diqqatni jamlash yoki sukutda chuqur o'ylashni anglatadi.
column14: U har kuni bir necha soat meditatsiya qilishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: To nick someone means to cut them slightly with a sharp object.
type: While cutting the carrots, the cook nicked his finger with the edge of his knife.
example_tr: Biror kishini laqillatish, uni o'tkir narsa bilan ozgina kesish demakdir.
column14: Sabzini kesayotganda oshpaz pichoqning qirrasi bilan barmog'ini tishladi.

example: To provoke someone means to annoy them on purpose to cause violence.
type: The older boy provoked Paul by calling him mean names.
example_tr: Biror kishini g'azablantirish, zo'ravonlik qilish uchun uni qasddan bezovta qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Katta bola Pavlusni yomon ismlar bilan chaqirib, uni g'azablantirdi.

example: A realm is any area of activity or interest.
type: He was not very active in the realm of business.
example_tr: Hudud - bu har qanday faoliyat yoki qiziqish sohasi.
column14: U biznes sohasida unchalik faol emas edi.

example: A reign is the period of time in which a ruler rules.
type: The emperor’s reign lasted for only two years.
example_tr: Hukmronlik - bu hukmdor hukmronlik qiladigan vaqt davri.
column14: Imperatorning hukmronligi atigi ikki yil davom etdi.

example: Rust is a red and brown coating on iron objects caused by water and air.
type: The old metal gate would not swing because the hinges were covered in rust.
example_tr: Zang - suv va havo ta'siridan kelib chiqqan temir buyumlar ustidagi qizil va jigarrang qoplama.
column14: Eski temir darvoza tebranib qolmasdi, chunki ilmoqlar zang bosgan edi.

example: If something is sacred, then it is worshipped and respected.
type: One religion in India will not harm cows because it believes that they are sacred.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muqaddas bo'lsa, unga sig'inish va hurmat qilish.
column14: Hindistondagi bir din sigirlarga zarar etkazmaydi, chunki u ularni muqaddas deb biladi.

example: If someone acts accordingly, they act in a way that is suitable.
type: He feels like he did a good job, and his boss should pay him accordingly.
example_tr: Agar kimdir shunga muvofiq harakat qilsa, ular mos keladigan tarzda harakat qilishadi.
column14: U o'zini yaxshi ish qilgandek his qiladi va xo'jayin unga mos ravishda maosh to'lashi kerak.

example: An anchor is a heavy object dropped from a boat to make it stay in one place.
type: When the ship reached its destination, the crew dropped the anchor.
example_tr: Langar - qayiqdan bir joyda turishi uchun tushirilgan og'ir narsa.
column14: Kema belgilangan manzilga yetib borgach, ekipaj langarni tushirib yubordi.

example: A buoy is a floating sign that warns boats of dangerous areas.
type: Don’t steer the boat near those buoys. There are rocks underneath the water.
example_tr: Buy - qayiqlarni xavfli joylardan ogohlantiruvchi suzuvchi belgi.
column14: Qayiqni o'sha kemalar yonida boshqarmang. Suv ostida toshlar bor.

example: A catastrophe is an unexpected event that causes great suffering or damage.
type: It was a catastrophe for my family when my dad lost his job.
example_tr: Falokat - bu katta azob-uqubat yoki zarar keltiradigan kutilmagan hodisa.
column14: Otam ishdan ayrilganida bu mening oilam uchun falokat edi.

example: Context is the situations that form the background of an event.
type: They studied the context of the battle before giving their presentation.
example_tr: Kontekst - bu hodisaning fonini tashkil etuvchi vaziyatlar.
column14: Ular taqdimot qilishdan oldin jang kontekstini o'rganishdi.

example: To designate someone or something means to give them a particular description.
type: The famous lighthouse was designated a historical monument.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani belgilash, unga ma'lum bir tavsif berishni anglatadi.
column14: Mashhur mayoq tarixiy yodgorlik sifatida belgilandi.

example: To distort something means to lie about it.
type: His lawyer distorted the facts so that he would be set free.
example_tr: Biror narsani buzish, bu haqda yolg'on gapirishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning advokati ozod bo'lishi uchun faktlarni buzib ko'rsatdi.

example: A dock is an enclosed area where ships go to be loaded, unloaded, and repaired.
type: The huge ship pulled into the dock, and the crew unloaded the cargo.
example_tr: Dock - bu kemalar yuklash, tushirish va ta'mirlash uchun ketadigan yopiq maydon.
column14: Ulkan kema dokga chiqdi va ekipaj yukni tushirdi.

example: The fore of something is the front part of it.
type: The teacher's desk is at the fore of the classroom.
example_tr: Biror narsaning oldingi qismi uning old qismidir.
column14: O'qituvchining stoli sinfning oldingi qismida joylashgan.

example: If something is frequent, then it happens or is done often.
type: While Dad was sick, the doctor made frequent visits to his house.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tez-tez bo'lsa, u tez-tez sodir bo'ladi yoki amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Dadam kasal bo'lganida, shifokor uning uyiga tez-tez tashrif buyurdi.

example: When something is genuine, it is true or real.
type: After the painting was determined to be genuine, it sold for a million dollars.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa haqiqiy bo'lsa, u haqiqat yoki haqiqiydir.
column14: Rasm haqiqiy ekanligi aniqlangach, u million dollarga sotildi.

example: Grease is an oily substance put on moving parts, so they work smoothly.
type: When I was done working on the car, I had grease all over my hands.
example_tr: Yog 'bu harakatlanuvchi qismlarga qo'yiladigan yog'li moddadir, shuning uchun ular muammosiz ishlaydi.
column14: Mashinada ishlashni tugatganimdan so'ng, qo'llarimga yog' bor edi.

example: When something is intricate, it has many small parts or details.
type: The intricate painting on the quilt was very lovely.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa murakkab bo'lsa, unda juda ko'p kichik qismlar yoki tafsilotlar mavjud.
column14: Yorgandagi murakkab rasm juda yoqimli edi.

example: To offset means to use one thing to cancel out the effect of another thing.
type: Increased wages are offset by higher prices for goods.
example_tr: Kompensatsiya qilish, boshqa narsaning ta'sirini bekor qilish uchun bir narsadan foydalanishni anglatadi.
column14: Oshgan ish haqi tovarlarning yuqori narxlari bilan qoplanadi.

example: To overlap something means to cover a piece of it.
type: The gift on top overlaps the other gift on the bottom.
example_tr: Biror narsani ustma-ust yopish, uning bir qismini qoplash demakdir.
column14: Yuqoridagi sovg'a pastdagi boshqa sovg'a bilan bir-biriga mos keladi.

example: To precipitate an event means to cause it to happen sooner than normal.
type: The violent attack precipitated an all-out war.
example_tr: Hodisani tezlashtirish, uni odatdagidan tezroq sodir bo'lishini anglatadi.
column14: Shiddatli hujum keng qamrovli urushni keltirib chiqardi.

example: When something is secondhand, it has been owned by someone else.
type: Her secondhand jeans were a bit faded in the front.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ikkinchi qo'l bo'lsa, u boshqa birovga tegishli.
column14: Uning ikkinchi qo‘l jinsi shimining old tomoni biroz xiralashgan edi.

example: A slot is a narrow opening in a machine or container.
type: To operate the machine, put your coins into the slot.
example_tr: Slot - bu mashina yoki idishdagi tor teshik.
column14: Mashinani ishlatish uchun tangalaringizni uyaga soling.

example: To submerge something means to put it below the surface of a liquid.
type: The whale submerged its huge body into the ocean.
example_tr: Biror narsani suvga botirish, uni suyuqlik yuzasiga tushirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kit ulkan tanasini okeanga botirdi.

example: A tactic is a careful plan to achieve something.
type: Sam thought of a good tactic in order to attract more business.
example_tr: Taktika - biror narsaga erishish uchun puxta reja.
column14: Sem ko'proq biznesni jalb qilish uchun yaxshi taktikani o'ylab topdi.

example: When a number is aggregate, it is made up of smaller amounts added together.
type: The company totaled its aggregate sales for the entire year.
example_tr: Agar raqam jamlangan bo'lsa, u bir-biriga qo'shilgan kichikroq miqdorlardan iborat.
column14: Kompaniya butun yil davomida o'zining umumiy sotuvlarini jamladi.

example: An antibiotic is a medical drug used to kill bacteria and treat infections.
type: The doctor gave me a shot of an antibiotic when I got the flu.
example_tr: Antibiotik - bu bakteriyalarni o'ldirish va infektsiyalarni davolash uchun ishlatiladigan tibbiy dori.
column14: Grippga chalinganimda shifokor menga antibiotik urdi.

example: A circuit is a piece of an electronic device that allows electricity to flow.
type: Be very careful not to shock yourself when fixing an electrical circuit.
example_tr: O'chirish - bu elektr tokining oqishini ta'minlaydigan elektron qurilmaning bir qismi.
column14: Elektr zanjirini tuzatayotganda o'zingizni zarba bermaslik uchun juda ehtiyot bo'ling.

example: To complement something or someone is to make them better.
type: The wool scarf complemented her lovely eyes.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoki kimnidir to'ldirish - ularni yaxshiroq qilish.
column14: Jun sharf uning yoqimli ko'zlarini to'ldirdi.

example: To compress something means to press or squeeze it so that it takes up less space.
type: I compressed my clothes to fit into a single suitcase.
example_tr: Biror narsani siqish, uni kamroq joy egallashi uchun uni bosish yoki siqish demakdir.
column14: Men kiyimlarimni bitta chamadonga sig'dirish uchun siqdim.

example: A database is a collection of data that is stored in a computer.
type: The company has a database of all the names and accounts of their customers.
example_tr: Ma'lumotlar bazasi - bu kompyuterda saqlanadigan ma'lumotlar to'plami.
column14: Kompaniya o'z mijozlarining barcha ismlari va hisoblari haqida ma'lumotlar bazasiga ega.

example: An equivalent is an amount or value that is the same as another amount or value.
type: I worked the equivalent of sixty hours this week.
example_tr: Ekvivalent - bu boshqa miqdor yoki qiymat bilan bir xil bo'lgan miqdor yoki qiymat.
column14: Men bu hafta oltmish soatga teng ishladim.

example: When someone is immune to a disease, they cannot be affected by it.
type: Children usually get shots to make them immune to certain diseases.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi kasallikka qarshi immunitetga ega bo'lsa, u unga ta'sir qila olmaydi.
column14: Bolalar odatda ma'lum kasalliklarga qarshi immunitet hosil qilish uchun uriladi.

example: Input is information that is put into a computer.
type: Type the input into the computer program.
example_tr: Kirish - bu kompyuterga kiritilgan ma'lumotlar.
column14: Kirishni kompyuter dasturiga kiriting.

example: When a relationship is intimate, the two things are very closely connected.
type: I only tell my secrets to my most intimate friends.
example_tr: Agar munosabatlar yaqin bo'lsa, bu ikki narsa bir-biri bilan chambarchas bog'liq.
column14: Men faqat eng yaqin do'stlarimga sirlarimni aytaman.

example: A magnet is a piece of iron or other material which attracts iron toward it.
type: I used a magnet to pick up the nails that were scattered on the floor.
example_tr: Magnit - bu temir bo'lagi yoki temirni o'ziga tortadigan boshqa material.
column14: Men magnit yordamida yerga sochilib qolgan mixlarni oldim.

example: A person’s metabolism is the way chemical processes in their body use energy.
type: If you exercise every day, your metabolism speeds up.
example_tr: Insonning metabolizmi - bu uning tanasidagi kimyoviy jarayonlar energiyadan foydalanish usuli.
column14: Har kuni mashq qilsangiz, metabolizm tezlashadi.

example: A microchip is a small device inside a computer that holds information.
type: I can put more data on my computer if I buy a more powerful microchip.
example_tr: Mikrochip - bu kompyuter ichidagi ma'lumotni saqlaydigan kichik qurilma.
column14: Agar kuchliroq mikrochip sotib olsam, kompyuterimga ko'proq ma'lumot qo'yishim mumkin.

example: A phase is a stage in a process or the gradual development of something.
type: The first phase in the recycling project involves finding volunteers to help out.
example_tr: Faza - bu jarayondagi bosqich yoki biror narsaning bosqichma-bosqich rivojlanishi.
column14: Qayta ishlash loyihasining birinchi bosqichi yordam berish uchun ko'ngillilarni topishni o'z ichiga oladi.

example: To pinch means to take a piece of skin between one’s fingers and squeeze.
type: I pinched my nose, so I couldn’t smell the odor from the garbage.
example_tr: Chimchilash barmoqlar orasiga teri bo'lagini olib, siqish demakdir.
column14: Men burnimni chimchiladim, shuning uchun axlatdan hidni sezmadim.

example: When something is prevalent, it is common.
type: Growing a beard is more prevalent behavior in men than women.
example_tr: Biror narsa keng tarqalgan bo'lsa, u keng tarqalgan.
column14: Soqol o'stirish ayollarga qaraganda erkaklarda ko'proq uchraydi.

example: When something is quantum, it relates to the behavior of atomic particles.
type: The physics student studied quantum mechanics.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa kvant bo'lsa, u atom zarralarining harakati bilan bog'liq.
column14: Fizika talabasi kvant mexanikasini o‘rgangan.

example: A ratio is a relationship between two things expressed in numbers or amounts.
type: The boy to girl ratio is one to three.
example_tr: Nisbat - bu raqamlar yoki miqdorlarda ifodalangan ikki narsa o'rtasidagi munosabat.
column14: O'g'il va qiz nisbati birdan uchga teng.

example: A spiral is a shape which winds round and round in a larger and larger circle.
type: A strand of DNA looks like two interlocking spirals.
example_tr: Spiral - bu kattaroq va kattaroq doirada aylana va aylana bo'ylab aylanadigan shakl.
column14: DNK zanjiri bir-biriga bog'langan ikkita spiralga o'xshaydi.

example: When something is viral, it is a disease or infection that is caused by a virus.
type: The girl was in bed for a week when she had a viral infection.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa virusli bo'lsa, bu virus sabab bo'lgan kasallik yoki infektsiya.
column14: Qiz virusli infektsiyaga chalinganida bir hafta davomida yotoqda yotdi.

example: If you are astounded, you are very surprised.
type: I was astounded that Monica won the art competition.
example_tr: Agar hayron bo'lsangiz, siz juda hayratdasiz.
column14: Monika san'at tanlovida g'olib chiqqanidan hayratda qoldim.

example: An attribute is a characteristic of a person or thing.
type: He isn’t very clever, but he does have some other positive attributes.
example_tr: Atribut - bu shaxs yoki narsaning o'ziga xos xususiyati.
column14: U juda aqlli emas, lekin uning boshqa ijobiy fazilatlari ham bor.

example: If someone is bilingual, then they can speak two languages.
type: Since you already know English, after learning French you'll be bilingual.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ikki tilli bo'lsa, u ikki tilda gaplasha oladi.
column14: Siz allaqachon ingliz tilini bilganingiz uchun, frantsuz tilini o'rganganingizdan so'ng siz ikki tilli bo'lasiz.

example: A clone is an identical copy of a living creature.
type: Scientists recently made a clone of a sheep.
example_tr: Klon tirik mavjudotning bir xil nusxasi.
column14: Olimlar yaqinda qo‘yning klonini yasashdi.

example: Colloquial describes informal words that are more suitable for speech than writing.
type: I find it difficult to understand people if they use colloquial language.
example_tr: So'zlashuv so'zlari yozishdan ko'ra nutq uchun ko'proq mos keladigan norasmiy so'zlarni tavsiflaydi.
column14: Agar odamlar so'zlashuv tilidan foydalansa, ularni tushunish qiyin.

example: Cosmetics are substances that make the face and skin more beautiful.
type: Girls often look nicer when they don’t use so many cosmetics.
example_tr: Kosmetika - bu yuz va terini yanada chiroyli qiladigan moddalar.
column14: Qizlar ko'pincha juda ko'p kosmetikadan foydalanmasa, chiroyli ko'rinadi.

example: To dash means to run or move quickly.
type: Helen dashed up the stairs, so she wouldn’t be late for her appointment.
example_tr: Chiziq yugurish yoki tez harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Xelen uchrashuvga kechikmaslik uchun zinadan yuqoriga otildi.

example: Disgust is a feeling of distaste and anger caused by something rude or unpleasant.
type: He felt disgust toward his date because she had such terrible eating habits.
example_tr: Jirkanish - qo'pol yoki yoqimsiz narsadan kelib chiqadigan norozilik va g'azab hissi.
column14: U uchrashuvidan nafratlanardi, chunki u shunday dahshatli ovqatlanish odatlariga ega edi.

example: If something is fluorescent, it is such a bright color that it seems to give off light.
type: She highlighted the key words in the document with a fluorescent yellow pen.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa lyuminestsent bo'lsa, u shunchalik yorqin rangki, u yorug'lik chiqaradiganga o'xshaydi.
column14: U hujjatdagi kalit so'zlarni lyuminestsent sariq qalam bilan ta'kidladi.

example: If you are furious, you are extremely angry.
type: My father was furious when he read my bad school report.
example_tr: Agar siz g'azablansangiz, siz juda g'azablanasiz.
column14: Otam mening yomon maktab hisobotimni o'qib, g'azablandi.

example: A gulf is a gap between people who do not understand each other.
type: There has been a gulf between James and Tony since their parents died.
example_tr: Ko'rfaz - bu bir-birini tushunmaydigan odamlar orasidagi bo'shliq.
column14: Ota-onalari vafot etganidan beri Jeyms va Toni o'rtasida kelishmovchilik bor edi.

example: Humanities are subjects which analyze human ideas, such as history and literature.
type: Jennifer has always been more interested in humanities than science.
example_tr: Gumanitar fanlar tarix va adabiyot kabi insoniy g'oyalarni tahlil qiladigan fanlardir.
column14: Jennifer har doim fandan ko'ra gumanitar fanlarga qiziqqan.

example: A knot is made when you tie the ends of rope or cord together.
type: He tied a knot in his shoelaces, so they wouldn’t come off during the race.
example_tr: Arqon yoki shnurning uchlarini bir-biriga bog'laganingizda tugun hosil bo'ladi.
column14: U poyga paytida echilib ketmasligi uchun poyabzal bog'ichlariga tugun bog'ladi.

example: A linguist is someone who studies languages.
type: Tony is a good linguist and speaks four different languages.
example_tr: Tilshunos - bu tillarni o'rganadigan kishi.
column14: Toni yaxshi tilshunos va to'rt xil tilda gapiradi.

example: A participant is someone who joins in a social event or competition.
type: There were thousands of participants in this year’s marathon.
example_tr: Ishtirokchi - bu ijtimoiy tadbir yoki musobaqada ishtirok etuvchi shaxs.
column14: Bu yilgi marafonda minglab ishtirokchilar bor edi.

example: If something is plausible, it is reasonable or possible.
type: It is plausible that Jack isn’t here today because he is sick.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa mantiqiy bo'lsa, bu oqilona yoki mumkin.
column14: Jek kasal bo'lgani uchun bugun bu erda emasligi aniq.

example: A ritual is a formal custom that people do regularly.
type: Ken was very interested to learn about the religious rituals of the natives.
example_tr: Marosim - bu odamlar muntazam ravishda bajaradigan rasmiy odat.
column14: Ken mahalliy aholining diniy marosimlarini o'rganishga juda qiziqdi.

example: A sibling is a brother or sister.
type: Jane has two siblings, an older brother and a younger sister.
example_tr: Aka-uka - bu aka yoki opa-singil.
column14: Jeynning ikkita ukasi, katta akasi va singlisi bor.

example: If someone is skinny, they are extremely thin.
type: Polly is very skinny. I think she needs to eat more.
example_tr: Agar kimdir oriq bo'lsa, u juda nozik.
column14: Polli juda oriq. Menimcha, u ko'proq ovqatlanishi kerak.

example: If something is vague, it is not clear, and it gives very few details.
type: I asked him about his mother’s health, but he was very vague about it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noaniq bo'lsa, u aniq emas va u juda kam ma'lumot beradi.
column14: Men undan onasining sog'lig'i haqida so'radim, lekin u bu haqda juda noaniq edi.

example: An acid is a chemical that can burn or dissolve other substances.
type: In chemistry class, we mixed two acids together and watched the reaction.
example_tr: Kislota boshqa moddalarni yoqishi yoki eritishi mumkin bo'lgan kimyoviy moddadir.
column14: Kimyo darsida biz ikkita kislotani aralashtirib, reaksiyani kuzatdik.

example: An administration is the group of people who manage a company or organization.
type: She hoped she could be promoted to a job in the administration.
example_tr: Ma'muriyat - bu kompaniya yoki tashkilotni boshqaradigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: U ma'muriyatdagi ishga ko'tarilishi mumkinligiga umid qildi.

example: Administrative describes anything related to managing a company or organization.
type: I work as an administrative assistant to the owner of the company.
example_tr: Ma'muriyat kompaniya yoki tashkilotni boshqarish bilan bog'liq barcha narsalarni tavsiflaydi.
column14: Men kompaniya egasining ma'muriy yordamchisi bo'lib ishlayman.

example: Biotechnology is the use of living parts, such as cells, in industry and technology.
type: Researchers at the biotechnology company use bacteria to make medicine.
example_tr: Biotexnologiya - sanoat va texnologiyada hujayralar kabi tirik qismlardan foydalanish.
column14: Biotexnologiya kompaniyasi tadqiqotchilari dori tayyorlash uchun bakteriyalardan foydalanadilar.

example: Cholesterol is a substance in fat, tissues, and blood of all animals.
type: When people have too much cholesterol, they are at a high risk for heart problems.
example_tr: Xolesterin barcha hayvonlarning yog'lari, to'qimalari va qonidagi moddadir.
column14: Odamlarda juda ko'p xolesterin bo'lsa, ular yurak muammolari uchun yuqori xavfga ega.

example: A coalition is a group of people or organizations working for a common purpose.
type: The companies formed a coalition to make trade less expensive.
example_tr: Koalitsiya - bu umumiy maqsadda ishlaydigan odamlar yoki tashkilotlar guruhi.
column14: Kompaniyalar savdoni arzonlashtirish uchun koalitsiya tuzdilar.

example: When something is deceptive, it encourages one to believe something that is false.
type: The scary-looking man’s appearance is deceptive, but he is actually very nice.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aldamchi bo'lsa, u yolg'on narsaga ishonishga undaydi.
column14: Qo'rqinchli ko'rinishdagi odamning ko'rinishi aldamchi, lekin u aslida juda yoqimli.

example: Diabetes is a medical condition where a person has too much sugar in their blood.
type: Overweight people are more likely to suffer from diabetes than slimmer ones.
example_tr: Qandli diabet - bu odamning qonida juda ko'p shakar bo'lgan tibbiy holat.
column14: Ortiqcha vaznli odamlar ingichka odamlarga qaraganda diabetdan ko'proq aziyat chekishadi.

example: To eliminate something that is unwanted means to completely remove it.
type: Wearing a seatbelt eliminates some of the dangers of driving a car.
example_tr: Keraksiz narsani yo'q qilish uni butunlay olib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Xavfsizlik kamarini taqish avtomobil haydashdagi ba'zi xavflarni bartaraf etadi.

example: Erosion is the destruction of rock or soil due to flowing water or weather.
type: Canyons are formed because rivers of fast-moving water caused erosion.
example_tr: Eroziya - suv oqimi yoki ob-havo ta'sirida tosh yoki tuproqning vayron bo'lishi.
column14: Kanyonlar tez harakatlanuvchi suv daryolari eroziyaga olib kelganligi sababli hosil bo'lgan.

example: Ethics are moral beliefs or rules about right or wrong.
type: The act of stealing certainly doesn’t go against some people’s ethics.
example_tr: Etika - bu to'g'ri yoki noto'g'ri haqidagi axloqiy e'tiqodlar yoki qoidalar.
column14: O'g'irlik harakati, albatta, ba'zi odamlarning axloqiga zid kelmaydi.

example: If something is explicit, it is very clear, open, and truthful.
type: The man gave a very explicit account of the car accident.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u juda aniq, ochiq va haqiqatdir.
column14: Erkak avtohalokat haqida juda aniq ma'lumot berdi.

example: A framework is a set of rules or ideas that people use to solve problems.
type: His ideas fit into the framework of a successful business plan.
example_tr: Ramka - bu odamlar muammolarni hal qilish uchun foydalanadigan qoidalar yoki g'oyalar to'plami.
column14: Uning g'oyalari muvaffaqiyatli biznes-rejaga mos keladi.

example: To manufacture something means to make it in a factory.
type: My father’s company manufactures steel building materials.
example_tr: Biror narsa ishlab chiqarish, uni zavodda yasashni anglatadi.
column14: Otamning kompaniyasi temir qurilish materiallari ishlab chiqaradi.

example: A mechanism is a part of a machine that performs a certain function.
type: I can’t open my car door because the locking mechanism is broke.
example_tr: Mexanizm - bu ma'lum bir funktsiyani bajaradigan mashinaning bir qismi.
column14: Men mashinamning eshigini ocholmayman, chunki qulflash mexanizmi buzilgan.

example: To minimize means to reduce something to the lowest possible level.
type: I checked my homework twice to minimize errors I might have made.
example_tr: Minimallashtirish biror narsani mumkin bo'lgan eng past darajaga tushirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yoʻl qoʻygan xatolarimni kamaytirish uchun uy vazifamni ikki marta tekshirdim.

example: Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by flowers that bees and other insects collect.
type: Bees use nectar to make their honey.
example_tr: Nektar - asalarilar va boshqa hasharotlar yig'adigan gullar tomonidan ishlab chiqarilgan shirin suyuqlik.
column14: Asalarilar asal tayyorlash uchun nektardan foydalanadilar.

example: A notion is an idea or belief about something.
type: I have a notion that this route would get us to the beach.
example_tr: Tushuncha - bu biror narsa haqidagi g'oya yoki e'tiqod.
column14: Menda bu marshrut bizni plyajga olib boradi degan fikr bor.

example: When things are prone to some bad thing, they are likely affected by it.
type: Some people are more prone to catching colds than others.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomon narsaga moyil bo'lsa, ular buning ta'siriga tushishi mumkin.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar boshqalarga qaraganda sovuqqa moyil.

example: When something is straightforward, it is good because it is easy to understand.
type: The teacher’s grading system was straightforward and fair.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ri bo'lsa, u yaxshi, chunki uni tushunish oson.
column14: O'qituvchining baholash tizimi to'g'ri va adolatli edi.

example: If something is astronomical, then itis extremely large.
type: It’s an astronomical distance between the Milky Way galaxy and the nearest galaxy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa astronomik bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Bu Somon yo'li galaktikasi va eng yaqin galaktika o'rtasidagi astronomik masofa.

example: An atom is the smallest unit of a substance.
type: A molecule consists of a combination of two or more atoms.
example_tr: Atom moddaning eng kichik birligidir.
column14: Molekula ikki yoki undan ortiq atomlarning birikmasidan iborat.

example: Breadth is the distance from one side to the other side of something.
type: The breadth of the northern wall of the house is twenty meters.
example_tr: Kenglik - biror narsaning bir tomonidan boshqa tomoniga bo'lgan masofa.
column14: Uyning shimoliy devorining kengligi yigirma metr.

example: A circumference is the distance completely around a circular object.
type: The circumference of the Earth is obviously much larger than a baseball's.
example_tr: Aylana - bu dumaloq jismning to'liq atrofidagi masofa.
column14: Yerning aylanasi beysbolnikidan ancha katta ekanligi aniq.

example: A comet is an object in space made of ice and rock with a tail of glowing dust.
type: Comets take many decades to complete an orbit around a star.
example_tr: Kometa - bu kosmosdagi muz va toshdan yasalgan, dumi porlab turgan chang.
column14: Kometalar yulduz atrofida aylanib chiqishlari uchun o'nlab yillar kerak bo'ladi.

example: A crater is a large hole in a planet's or moon’s surface.
type: They could clearly see the big crater on the moon through the telescope.
example_tr: Krater - bu sayyora yoki oy yuzasida joylashgan katta teshik.
column14: Ular teleskop orqali Oydagi katta kraterni aniq ko'rishgan.

example: A crescent is the curved shape lit on the moon’s face during its early and late stages.
type: Ten days ago the entire moon was bright, but now only a small crescent is shining.
example_tr: Yarim oy - bu erta va kech bosqichlarida oyning yuzida yoritilgan egri shakl.
column14: O'n kun oldin butun oy yorqin edi, lekin hozir faqat kichik yarim oy porlamoqda.

example: Debris is the small pieces scattered from something wrecked or destroyed.
type: The debris from the cube scattered on the floor.
example_tr: Chiqindi - bu vayron bo'lgan yoki vayron bo'lgan narsadan sochilgan mayda bo'laklar.
column14: Kubning qoldiqlari polga sochilib ketdi.

example: Despair is the complete loss of hope.
type: After the other company won the account, our salespeople were filled with despair.
example_tr: Umidsizlik - umidning butunlay yo'qolishi.
column14: Boshqa kompaniya hisobni qo'lga kiritgandan so'ng, bizning sotuvchilarimiz umidsizlikka to'lib ketishdi.

example: To embed something means to place it firmly within a surrounding thing.
type: The logger embedded the ax into the wood after chopping several lags.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rnatish, uni atrofdagi narsa ichiga mahkam joylashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Daraxtchi bir nechta laglarni maydalagandan so'ng, boltani yog'ochga solib qo'ydi.

example: A fragment is a small part of something.
type: After the light broke, there were fragments of glass fo clean up.
example_tr: Fragment - biror narsaning kichik qismi.
column14: Chiroq singanidan keyin tozalash uchun shisha parchalari bor edi.

example: A galaxy is any extremely large collection of star systems.
type: Our solar system is located in the outer area of our galaxy.
example_tr: Galaktika yulduz tizimlarining har qanday juda katta to'plamidir.
column14: Bizning quyosh sistemamiz galaktikamizning tashqi hududida joylashgan.

example: If something is gigantic, then it is extremely large.
type: Some dinosaurs were so gigantic that they were the size of buildings.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ulkan bo'lsa, u juda katta.
column14: Ba'zi dinozavrlar shunchalik ulkan ediki, ular binolarning kattaligida edi.

example: Gloom is a state of being almost completely dark.
type: In the gloom of the morning, it was difficult to see the boat on the lake.
example_tr: Tushkunlik - bu deyarli butunlay qorong'ilik holati.
column14: Tong qorong‘usida ko‘lda qayiqni ko‘rish qiyin edi.

example: To radiate means to send out energy or heat.
type: The heat from the fireplace radiated throughout the room.
example_tr: Nurlanish energiya yoki issiqlikni yuborishni anglatadi.
column14: Kaminning issiqligi butun xonaga tarqaldi.

example: To roam means to move around without a plan or purpose.
type: All day the cows roamed around the field eating grass.
example_tr: Rouming, rejasiz yoki maqsadsiz harakatlanishni anglatadi.
column14: Sigirlar kun bo'yi dala bo'ylab o't yeyishdi.

example: If something is solitary, then it is lonely or the only one.
type: The only thing in the room was a solitary chair.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yolg'iz bo'lsa, u yolg'iz yoki yagonadir.
column14: Xonadagi yagona narsa yolg'iz o'rindiq edi.

example: The spectrum is the full range of color ranging from red to violet.
type: You can see the entire spectrum in a rainbow.
example_tr: Spektr - qizildan binafsha ranggacha bo'lgan ranglarning to'liq diapazoni.
column14: Kamalakda siz butun spektrni ko'rishingiz mumkin.

example: A sphere is a three-dimensional round shape, like a ball.
type: The balloons were inflated into a variety of colorful spheres.
example_tr: Shar - to'p kabi uch o'lchamli dumaloq shakl.
column14: Pufaklar turli xil rang-barang sharlarga puflangan.

example: Status is the position of something or Someone in relation to others.
type: She had achieved the status of being the smartest girl in the class.
example_tr: Status - bu biror narsaning yoki kimdirning boshqalarga nisbatan pozitsiyasi.
column14: U sinfdagi eng aqlli qiz degan maqomga erishgan edi.

example: IF someone is bankrupt, then they are unable to pay their debts.
type: The store had few customers and soon went bankrupt.
example_tr: Agar kimdir bankrot bo'lsa, u o'z qarzlarini to'lay olmaydi.
column14: Do'konning xaridorlari kam edi va tez orada bankrot bo'ldi.

example: To conform to rules or laws is to obey them.
type: The new student had to conform to the school’s dress code.
example_tr: Qoidalarga yoki qonunlarga rioya qilish ularga bo'ysunishdir.
column14: Yangi talaba maktabning kiyinish qoidalariga mos kelishi kerak edi.

example: To employ someone means to give work to them.
type: The bookstore employed two full-time clerks.
example_tr: Birovni ishga olish, unga ish berish demakdir.
column14: Kitob do‘konida ikki nafar doimiy xodim ishlagan.

example: To expel someone means to force them to leave a place.
type: Since he would not follow the rules, the principal had to expel the student.
example_tr: Biror kishini haydab chiqarish, uni joyni tark etishga majburlash demakdir.
column14: U qoidalarga rioya qilmagani uchun direktor talabani o'qishdan chiqarishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: An extension is a part added to something to give it more time or space.
type: My parents decided to add an extension to our house for the new baby.
example_tr: Kengaytma - bu narsaga ko'proq vaqt yoki joy berish uchun qo'shilgan qism.
column14: Ota-onam yangi chaqaloq uchun uyimizga kengaytma qo'shishga qaror qilishdi.

example: If something is forthcoming, then it is about to happen in the future.
type: Some economists predicted that the forthcoming world economy would be severe.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oldinda bo'lsa, u kelajakda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Ba'zi iqtisodchilar bo'lajak jahon iqtisodiyoti og'ir bo'lishini bashorat qilishdi.

example: To furnish means to put furniture in a house or room.
type: Most homes are furnished with tables, chairs, and beds.
example_tr: Uyga yoki xonaga mebel qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Aksariyat uylar stol, stullar va ko'rpa-to'shaklar bilan jihozlangan.

example: Hygiene is the conditions or methods needed for health and cleanliness.
type: People who brush their teeth at least twice a day are practicing good hygiene.
example_tr: Gigiena - bu salomatlik va tozalik uchun zarur bo'lgan shartlar yoki usullar.
column14: Tishlarini kuniga kamida ikki marta yuvadigan odamlar yaxshi gigiena qoidalariga rioya qilishadi.

example: If something is hygienic, then it is clean and unlikely to cause disease.
type: My sister works very hard to keep her entire home as hygienic as possible.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa gigienik bo'lsa, u toza va kasallikka olib kelishi mumkin emas.
column14: Singlim butun uyini iloji boricha gigienik saqlash uchun juda ko'p ishlaydi.

example: A landlord is a man who rents property to a person.
type: The landlord collected everyone’s rent money on the first day of every month.
example_tr: Uy egasi - bir kishiga mulkni ijaraga beradigan odam.
column14: Uy egasi har oyning birinchi kunida hammaning ijara pulini yig'ib oldi.

example: To lease means to rent property, usually an apartment or land.
type: When the family first leased the apartment, the rent was very low.
example_tr: Ijaraga olish mulkni, odatda kvartirani yoki erni ijaraga olishni anglatadi.
column14: Oila birinchi marta kvartirani ijaraga olganida, ijara haqi juda past edi.

example: If something is mandatory, then it is required by law.
type: It's mandatory that everyone be at least sixteen to drive a car in the US.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa majburiy bo'lsa, u qonun bilan talab qilinadi.
column14: AQShda mashina haydash uchun har bir kishi kamida o'n olti yoshga to'lishi shart.

example: To mend something means to fix it when it is broken or damaged.
type: Mother mended the rip in my pants with a piece of cloth.
example_tr: Biror narsani ta'mirlash, uni singan yoki shikastlanganda tuzatishni anglatadi.
column14: Onam shimimdagi yirtiqni mato bilan tuzatdi.

image: uy sotib olish uchun olingan qarz
example: A mortgage is a loan for property, especially homes and businesses.
type: When they bought their new home, the married couple had to sign a mortgage.
example_tr: Ipoteka - bu mulk, ayniqsa uylar va korxonalar uchun kredit.
column14: Yangi uyni sotib olishganda, er-xotin ipoteka shartnomasini imzolashlari kerak edi.

example: Personnel are employees in a business.
type: When business increased, we had to hire more personnel.
example_tr: Xodimlar biznesdagi xodimlardir.
column14: Biznes ko'paygach, biz ko'proq xodimlarni yollashga majbur bo'ldik.

example: Plumbing is the system of pipes used in a home to supply water.
type: When the plumbing stopped working, no one was allowed to use the toilets.
example_tr: Santexnika - bu uyda suv ta'minoti uchun ishlatiladigan quvurlar tizimi.
column14: Santexnika ishlamay qolganda, hech kim hojatxonadan foydalanishga ruxsat berilmagan.

example: A tenant is a person who rents property from a landlord.
type: The new tenants moved into the house across the street.
example_tr: Ijarachi - uy egasidan mulkni ijaraga olgan shaxs.
column14: Yangi ijarachilar ko'chaning narigi tomonidagi uyga ko'chib o'tishdi.

example: If something is trendy, then it is very popular and new.
type: Carlo bought a trendy new car.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa moda bo'lsa, u juda mashhur va yangi.
column14: Karlo zamonaviy yangi mashina sotib oldi.

example: A utility is a business that supplies services such as water or electricity.
type: If you don't pay the utilities, you may have your electricity turned off.
example_tr: Kommunal xizmat - bu suv yoki elektr energiyasi kabi xizmatlarni etkazib beradigan biznes.
column14: Agar siz kommunal to'lovlarni to'lamasangiz, elektr energiyasi o'chirilishi mumkin.

example: Whereby means by which or through which.
type: The mayor had a new bridge built whereby the citizens could cross the river.
example_tr: Qaysi orqali yoki qaysi orqali.
column14: Shahar hokimi fuqarolarning daryodan o'tishi mumkin bo'lgan yangi ko'prik qurdirdi.

example: If something is aesthetic, then it is concerned with a love of beauty.
type: The dresses were noteworthy for their aesthetic design.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa estetik bo'lsa, u go'zallikka bo'lgan muhabbat bilan bog'liq.
column14: Ko'ylaklar estetik dizayni bilan e'tiborga loyiq edi.

example: If someone is arrogant, they think that they are more important than others.
type: He is very arrogant. Even though he’s not the boss, he tells everyone what to do.
example_tr: Agar kimdir mag'rur bo'lsa, u o'zini boshqalardan ustunroq deb hisoblaydi.
column14: U juda takabbur. U xo'jayin bo'lmasa ham, u hammaga nima qilish kerakligini aytadi.

example: A bias is a person’s likelihood to like one thing more than another thing.
type: The mothers had a natural bias for their own child’s picture.
example_tr: Tarafsizlik - bu odamning bir narsani boshqa narsadan ko'ra ko'proq yoqtirish ehtimoli.
column14: Onalar o'z farzandlarining rasmiga tabiiy yondashdilar.

example: A canyon is a narrow valley with steep walls through which a river often flows.
type: The canyon was so deep that the ground inside was covered in shadow.
example_tr: Kanyon ko'pincha daryo oqib o'tadigan tik devorlarga ega tor vodiydir.
column14: Kanyon shu qadar chuqur ediki, ichkaridagi yer soya bilan qoplangan edi.

example: A creek is a stream or small river.
type: Only small fish lived in the shallow waters of the creek.
example_tr: Daryo - bu oqim yoki kichik daryo.
column14: Daryoning sayoz suvlarida faqat kichik baliqlar yashagan.

example: A drill is a tool with a point that spins in order to make a hole.
type: The carpenter used the drill to make several holes in the wood.
example_tr: Matkap - bu teshik ochish uchun aylanadigan nuqtasi bo'lgan asbob.
column14: Duradgor burg‘u yordamida yog‘ochda bir nechta teshik ochgan.

example: An executive is the top manager of a business.
type: After twenty years at the company, he finally became the executive.
example_tr: Ijrochi - bu biznesning top menejeri.
column14: Kompaniyada yigirma yil ishlagandan so'ng, u nihoyat boshqaruvchi bo'ldi.

example: Fatigue is a feeling of extreme tiredness.
type: After three days with little sleep, she was feeling a lot of fatigue.
example_tr: Charchoq - bu haddan tashqari charchoq hissi.
