column14: Uch kunlik uyqudan keyin u juda charchoqni his qildi.

example: An incline is a sharp rise in something, especially a hill or mountain.
type: This mountain has one of the steepest inclines in the world.
example_tr: Nishab - biror narsaning, ayniqsa tepalik yoki tog'ning keskin ko'tarilishi.
column14: Bu tog' dunyodagi eng tik qiyaliklardan biriga ega.

example: If something is nasty, then it is not nice or pleasant.
type: The rotten apple left a nasty taste inside her mouth.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomon bo'lsa, u yoqimli yoki yoqimli emas.
column14: Chirigan olma og'zida yoqimsiz ta'm qoldirdi.

example: To perceive something means to be aware of it.
type: He was talking loudly, so he did not perceive that the music had stopped.
example_tr: Biror narsani idrok etish, undan xabardor bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U baland ovozda gapirar edi, shuning uchun u musiqa to'xtaganini sezmadi.

example: A primate is a type of mammal that includes monkeys, apes, and humans.
type: Primates use their hands for such tasks as swinging from branches.
example_tr: Primat - maymunlar, maymunlar va odamlarni o'z ichiga olgan sutemizuvchilarning bir turi.
column14: Primatlar shoxlardan tebranish kabi vazifalar uchun qo'llaridan foydalanadilar.

example: If something is primitive, then it is simple, basic, and not very developed.
type: The computers of the 1980s are primitive compared to those of today’s.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ibtidoiy bo'lsa, u oddiy, asosiy va unchalik rivojlanmagan.
column14: 1980-yillardagi kompyuterlar bugungi kunlarga nisbatan ibtidoiy.

example: A stereotype is a general but often incorrect idea about a person or thing.
type: There’s a stereotype that pigs are dirty animals. But they are rather clean.
example_tr: Stereotip - bu odam yoki narsa haqida umumiy, lekin ko'pincha noto'g'ri fikr.
column14: Cho'chqalar iflos hayvonlar degan stereotip mavjud. Ammo ular ancha toza.

example: If something is sticky, then it is covered with a substance that things stick to.
type: Place the sticky part of the tape against the paper, so it will cling to the wall.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yopishqoq bo'lsa, u holda narsalar yopishib oladigan modda bilan qoplangan.
column14: Lentaning yopishqoq qismini qog'ozga qo'ying, shunda u devorga yopishadi.

example: A termite is an insect that lives in groups and feeds on wood.
type: The wood we found was full of termites.
example_tr: Termit - guruh bo'lib yashaydigan va yog'och bilan oziqlanadigan hasharotlar.
column14: Biz topgan yog‘och termitlarga to‘la edi.

example: If something happens thereby an action, then it is the result of that action.
type: He didn’t score a goal, thereby ending his chance at setting a record.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, bu harakatning natijasidir.
column14: U gol urmadi va shu bilan rekord o'rnatish imkoniyatini tugatdi.

example: A trail is a path through a wild area.
type: A narrow trail cut through the field and over the hills.
example_tr: So'qmoq - bu yovvoyi hududdan o'tadigan yo'l.
column14: Dala va tepaliklarni kesib o'tgan tor iz.

example: A twig is a short and thin branch from a tree or bush.
type: They started the fire with a handful of dry twigs.
example_tr: Shox - daraxt yoki butadan olingan qisqa va ingichka shox.
column14: Bir hovuch quruq novdalar bilan olov yoqishdi.

example: Welfare is the health and happiness of a person or group.
type: Having plenty of clean water is necessary for the welfare of people.
example_tr: Farovonlik - bu inson yoki guruhning salomatligi va baxtidir.
column14: Ko'p miqdorda toza suvga ega bo'lish odamlarning farovonligi uchun zarurdir.

example: If something is done on one’s behalf, it is done for that person by another.
type: The original speaker was sick, so his son gave the speech on his behalf.
example_tr: Biror kishining nomidan biror narsa qilingan bo'lsa, u uchun boshqasi tomonidan amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Asl ma'ruzachi kasal edi, shuning uchun o'g'li uning nomidan nutq so'zladi.

example: To flap means to move quickly up and down or from side to side.
type: The tiny bird flapped its wings and ate from the flowers.
example_tr: Qopqoqlash tez yuqoriga-pastga yoki u yoqdan bu yoqqa siljishni anglatadi.
column14: Kichkina qush qanotlarini qoqib, gullardan yedi.

example: A glacier is a large piece of ice that moves very slowly.
type: The North Pole is covered by a huge glacier.
example_tr: Muzlik - bu juda sekin harakatlanadigan katta muz bo'lagi.
column14: Shimoliy qutb katta muzlik bilan qoplangan.

example: The globe refers to the Earth.
type: Water covers most of the globe.
example_tr: Globus Yerni nazarda tutadi.
column14: Suv yer sharining katta qismini egallaydi.

example: When something is horizontal, it is flat and level with the ground.
type: The Russian flag has three horizontal stripes of white, blue, and red.
example_tr: Biror narsa gorizontal bo'lsa, u tekis va erga tekis bo'ladi.
column14: Rossiya bayrog'ida oq, ko'k va qizil rangli uchta gorizontal chiziq mavjud.

example: To hum means to make a low, continuous noise.
type: The man hummed his favorite song.
example_tr: G'o'ng'irlash - past, doimiy shovqin qilish demakdir.
column14: Erkak o'zining sevimli qo'shig'ini xirilladi.

example: An inventory is a supply of something.
type: Gwen was checking the inventory to make sure we had what we needed.
example_tr: Inventar - bu biror narsaning ta'minoti.
column14: Gven bizda kerakli narsa borligiga ishonch hosil qilish uchun inventarni tekshirayotgan edi.

example: If a thought or feeling is inward, it is not expressed or shown to others.
type: She had an inward feeling of guilt when she lied to her mother.
example_tr: Agar fikr yoki tuyg'u ichki bo'lsa, u boshqalarga aytilmaydi yoki ko'rsatilmaydi.
column14: Onasiga yolg‘on gapirganda, ichida aybdorlik hissi bor edi.

example: A loaf of bread is bread shaped and baked in one piece.
type: Could you please buy a loaf of bread for sandwiches?
example_tr: Non - bu bir bo'lak shaklida pishirilgan non.
column14: Iltimos, sendvich uchun bir bo'lak non sotib olasizmi?

example: An oracle is person who speaks with gods and gives advice about the future.
type: The king went to the oracle to ask if going to war was a good idea.
example_tr: Orakul - bu xudolar bilan gaplashadigan va kelajak haqida maslahat beradigan odam.
column14: Podshoh urushga borish yaxshi fikrmi, deb so‘ramoqchi bo‘ldi.

example: To orbit something means to move around it in a continuous, curving path.
type: The moon orbits the Earth.
example_tr: Biror narsani orbita qilish uning atrofida uzluksiz, egri yo'lda harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Oy Yer atrofida aylanadi.

example: An overview is a general description of a situation.
type: My brother gave me an overview of the important parts of the book.
example_tr: Umumiy ko'rinish - bu vaziyatning umumiy tavsifi.
column14: Akam menga kitobning muhim qismlari haqida umumiy ma’lumot berdi.

image: film, konsertni aholi orasida namoyish etilishidan oldin koʻrish
example: A preview is an opportunity to see something before it is available to the public.
type: The band played us a preview of their new song.
example_tr: Oldindan ko'rish - bu ommaga taqdim etilishidan oldin biror narsani ko'rish imkoniyati.
column14: Guruh bizga yangi qo'shig'ining prevyusini namoyish etdi.

example: If something is previous, then it happened earlier in time or order.
type: He turned back to the previous page to read the paragraph again.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oldingi bo'lsa, u vaqt yoki tartibda oldin sodir bo'lgan.
column14: U xatboshini qayta o‘qish uchun oldingi sahifaga qaytdi.

example: To provide something means to supply it.
type: Each student was provided with a test and three sharp pencils.
example_tr: Biror narsani ta'minlash, uni etkazib berishni anglatadi.
column14: Har bir talaba test va uchta o'tkir qalam bilan ta'minlandi.

example: Jo recur means to happen more than once.
type: Burglaries seem to recur over and over in our neighborhood.
example_tr: Jo recur bir necha marta sodir bo'lishini anglatadi.
column14: Mahallamizda o‘g‘irliklar qayta-qayta sodir bo‘layotgandek.

example: When something is relevant, it is important to a certain person or situation.
type: The thirty-year-old book about politics is still relevant to our society today.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tegishli bo'lsa, u ma'lum bir shaxs yoki vaziyat uchun muhimdir.
column14: O‘ttiz yillik siyosat haqidagi kitob bugungi kunda ham jamiyatimiz uchun dolzarbdir.

example: Arite is a traditional ceremony carried out by a particular group or society.
type: Special masks are worn during the rite when a new baby is born.
example_tr: Arite - ma'lum bir guruh yoki jamiyat tomonidan o'tkaziladigan an'anaviy marosim.
column14: Yangi chaqaloq tug'ilganda marosim paytida maxsus niqoblar kiyiladi.

example: To stall means to stop a process and continue it at a later time.
type: If you give the car a push, it won’t stall.
example_tr: To'xtash jarayonni to'xtatib, keyinroq davom ettirishni anglatadi.
column14: Agar siz mashinaga turtki bersangiz, u to'xtab qolmaydi.

example: If something is supernatural, it is not real or explainable by natural law.
type: The dragon had supernatural powers such as flying and breathing fire.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'ayritabiiy bo'lsa, u haqiqiy emas yoki tabiiy qonun bilan tushuntirib bo'lmaydi.
column14: Ajdaho uchish va olovdan nafas olish kabi g'ayritabiiy kuchlarga ega edi.

example: To adapt means to change in order to deal with a new situation or addition.
type: When he went to the new town, he had to adapt to all the weather changes.
example_tr: Moslashish yangi vaziyat yoki qo'shimcha bilan shug'ullanish uchun o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yangi shaharga borganida, u barcha ob-havo o'zgarishlariga moslashishi kerak edi.

example: Biological describes the process of life and living things.
type: In science, we learned about the biological process of bacterial growth.
example_tr: Biologik hayot va tirik mavjudotlar jarayonini tavsiflaydi.
column14: Fanda biz bakteriyalar o'sishining biologik jarayoni haqida bilib oldik.

example: When something is cellular, it relates to the cells of animals or plants.
type: She used a microscope to see the activity at a cellular level.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa hujayrali bo'lsa, u hayvonlar yoki o'simliklar hujayralariga tegishli.
column14: U hujayra darajasidagi faoliyatni ko'rish uchun mikroskopdan foydalangan.

example: When people are dynamic, they are lively and have creative ideas.
type: The new, dynamic employee came up with a good way to juggle his work load.
example_tr: Odamlar dinamik bo'lsa, ular jonli va ijodiy g'oyalarga ega.
column14: Yangi, dinamik xodim o'z ish yukini o'ynashning yaxshi usulini o'ylab topdi.

example: A fantasy is a pleasant situation that people think about but is unlikely to happen.
type: Becoming an astronaut is a fantasy shared by many children.
example_tr: Fantaziya - bu odamlar o'ylaydigan, lekin sodir bo'lishi dargumon yoqimli holat.
column14: Kosmonavt bo'lish ko'plab bolalarning hayolidir.

example: Heredity is the process of passing on features from parents to children.
type: The boy’s face is similar to his father’s because of heredity.
example_tr: Irsiyat - bu xususiyatlarning ota-onalardan bolalarga o'tish jarayoni.
column14: Bolaning yuzi irsiyat tufayli otasinikiga o'xshaydi.

example: When something is internal, it exists or happens inside a person, object, or place.
type: We removed the outer case to reveal the computer's internal wires.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ichki bo'lsa, u odam, narsa yoki joy ichida mavjud yoki sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Biz kompyuterning ichki simlarini aniqlash uchun tashqi korpusni olib tashladik.

example: When something is minimal, it is very small.
type: My lazy husband does a minimal amount of work around the house.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa minimal bo'lsa, u juda kichikdir.
column14: Mening dangasa erim uy atrofida minimal miqdordagi ishlarni bajaradi.

example: A pioneer is a person who is the first to discover or be involved in something.
type: He was a pioneer of computer programming.
example_tr: Kashshof - bu nimanidir birinchi bo'lib kashf etgan yoki ishtirok etgan odam.
column14: U kompyuter dasturlashning kashshofi edi.

example: To prescribe medicine means to tell someone to take it.
type: When I was sick, the doctor prescribed me flu medicine.
example_tr: Dori yozib berish, birovga uni qabul qilishni aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Kasal bo'lganimda shifokor grippga qarshi dori yozib berdi.

example: When things are respective, they relate separately to each person just mentioned.
type: The boxers were told to return to their respective corners.
example_tr: Agar narsalar tegishli bo'lsa, ular yuqorida aytib o'tilgan har bir kishiga alohida bog'liq.
column14: Bokschilarga o'z burchaklariga qaytishlari aytildi.

example: To revive someone or something means to restore health or life to them.
type: She revived the feeling of warmth in her leg by rubbing it softly.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani jonlantirish, ularning sog'lig'ini yoki hayotini tiklashni anglatadi.
column14: Oyog‘idagi iliqlik tuyg‘usini ohista ishqalab jonlantirdi.

example: When rules or systems are rigid, they are severe because they cannot be changed.
type: Societies often have rigid rules about the way that people are supposed to act.
example_tr: Qoidalar yoki tizimlar qattiq bo'lsa, ular qattiq, chunki ularni o'zgartirish mumkin emas.
column14: Jamiyatlarda ko'pincha odamlar qanday harakat qilishlari kerakligi haqida qat'iy qoidalar mavjud.

example: A sequence is a number of events or things that come one after another.
type: The dominos fell in a sequence of one after another.
example_tr: Ketma-ket ketma-ket keladigan hodisalar yoki narsalar soni.
column14: Dominoslar ketma-ket tushib ketdi.

example: To substitute something or someone means to have them take the place of another.
type: When I ran out of juice, I had to substitute water to drink in the morning.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoki kimnidir almashtirish ularning boshqasining o'rnini egallashini anglatadi.
column14: Sharbat tugagach, ertalab ichish uchun suvni almashtirishim kerak edi.

example: A surgeon is a doctor who is trained to do surgery.
type: The surgeon operated on the old man’s heart.
example_tr: Jarroh - bu operatsiya qilish uchun o'qitilgan shifokor.
column14: Jarroh cholning yuragini operatsiya qildi.

example: Therapy is treatment for a particular physical or mental illness or condition.
type: After she broke her legs, she used physical therapy to learn how to walk again.
example_tr: Terapiya muayyan jismoniy yoki ruhiy kasallik yoki holatni davolashdir.
column14: U oyoqlarini sindirganidan so'ng, u yana yurishni o'rganish uchun fizika terapiyasidan foydalangan.

example: To transfer something means to move it from one place to another.
type: The family transferred the groceries from the shopping cart to the car.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'chirish, uni bir joydan ikkinchi joyga ko'chirishni anglatadi.
column14: Oila aravadagi oziq-ovqatlarni mashinaga o'tkazishdi.

example: A transition is a process where there is a change from one form to another.
type: The weather gets colder during the transition from summer to autumn.
example_tr: O'tish - bu bir shakldan ikkinchisiga o'tish jarayoni.
column14: Yozdan kuzga o'tish davrida havo sovuqroq bo'ladi.

example: A transplant is an operation in which a damaged part of one’s body is replaced.
type: The sick child needed a heart transplant to live.
example_tr: Transplantatsiya - bu tananing shikastlangan qismini almashtirish operatsiyasi.
column14: Kasal bolaning yashashi uchun yurak transplantatsiyasi kerak edi.

example: An aquarium is a building where fish and underwater animals are kept.
type: We took a trip to the aquarium and saw a scary shark.
example_tr: Akvarium - bu baliq va suv osti hayvonlari saqlanadigan bino.
column14: Biz akvariumga sayohat qildik va qo'rqinchli akulani ko'rdik.

example: If something is arbitrary, it is not based on any plan or system, so it seems random.
type: The classroom had many arbitrary rules that made me confused.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'zboshimchalik bilan bo'lsa, u hech qanday reja yoki tizimga asoslanmagan, shuning uchun u tasodifiy ko'rinadi.
column14: Sinf xonasida ko'plab o'zboshimchalik qoidalari bor edi, bu meni chalkashtirib yubordi.

example: An autobiography is a true story of a person’s life written by that person.
type: I read an autobiography about my favorite entertainer.
example_tr: Avtobiografiya - bu shaxs tomonidan yozilgan inson hayotining haqiqiy hikoyasi.
column14: Men sevimli tomoshabin haqida avtobiografiyani o'qidim.

example: A convention is behavior that is considered to be common or polite.
type: In the US, a popular convention is to shake hands when you meet someone.
example_tr: Konventsiya - bu odatiy yoki muloyim deb hisoblanadigan xatti-harakatlar.
column14: Qo'shma Shtatlarda, kimdir bilan uchrashganda qo'l berib ko'rishish mashhur konventsiyadir.

example: If someone is gracious, then they are kind and helpful to those who need it.
type: The operator was gracious enough to help me find his number.
example_tr: Agar kimdir mehribon bo'lsa, u muhtojlarga mehribon va yordam beradi.
column14: Operator menga uning raqamini topishga yordam berdi.

example: To improve something means to make it better.
type: He studied hard to improve his test scores from the previous year.
example_tr: Biror narsani yaxshilash, uni yaxshilash demakdir.
column14: U o'tgan yilgi test ballarini yaxshilash uchun qattiq o'qidi.

example: To insulate something means to protect it from heat, cold, or noise.
type: People can conserve energy by insulating their houses.
example_tr: Biror narsani izolyatsiya qilish uni issiqlikdan, sovuqdan yoki shovqindan himoya qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Odamlar uylarini izolyatsiya qilish orqali energiyani tejashlari mumkin.

example: To intrigue means to cause an interest in something or someone.
type: Her mysterious past intrigued her new friend.
example_tr: Intriga, biror narsaga yoki kimgadir qiziqish uyg'otishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning sirli o'tmishi yangi do'stini qiziqtirdi.

example: Longevity is the ability to live for a long time.
type: Sea turtles have an amazing longevity.
example_tr: Uzoq umr ko'rish - uzoq vaqt yashash qobiliyati.
column14: Dengiz toshbaqalari ajoyib uzoq umr ko'rishadi.

example: To misplace something means to lose it.
type: I misplaced my wallet, and I didn’t find it until a week later.
example_tr: Biror narsani noto'g'ri joylashtirish, uni yo'qotish demakdir.
column14: Men hamyonimni noto'g'ri joylashtirdim va bir hafta o'tgach, uni topa olmadim.

example: When children are naughty, they behave badly or do not do what they are told.
type: The boy had to go to his room because he was being naughty.
example_tr: Bolalar yaramas bo‘lsa, o‘zini yomon tutadi yoki aytganini qilmaydi.
column14: Bola yaramasligi uchun xonasiga ketishi kerak edi.

example: A norm is a way of behaving that is considered normal in a particular society.
type: Wearing a heavy coat all summer is not considered a norm in the desert.
example_tr: Norm - bu muayyan jamiyatda odatiy deb hisoblangan o'zini tutish usuli.
column14: Butun yoz davomida og'ir palto kiyish cho'lda norma hisoblanmaydi.

example: An orangutan is a large ape with red and brown hair and long arms.
type: Orangutans use their long arms to swing from trees.
example_tr: Orangutan - qizil va jigarrang sochli, uzun qo'llari bo'lgan katta maymun.
column14: Orangutanlar daraxtlardan tebranish uchun uzun qo'llaridan foydalanadilar.

example: To overload something means to put more things into it than it is meant to hold.
type: If you overload the truck, it might crash.
example_tr: Biror narsani haddan tashqari yuklash, unga ushlab turishdan ko'ra ko'proq narsalarni qo'yishni anglatadi.
column14: Agar siz yuk mashinasini ortiqcha yuklasangiz, u halokatga uchrashi mumkin.

example: Philanthropy is the act of helping others, without wanting anything in return.
type: The wealthy business owner is well known for his acts of philanthropy.
example_tr: Xayriya - bu evaziga hech narsa istamasdan, boshqalarga yordam berish harakati.
column14: Boy biznes egasi o'zining xayriya ishlari bilan mashhur.

example: To probe into something means to ask questions to discover facts about it.
type: The bank probed into his financial history to see if he qualified for a loan.
example_tr: Biror narsani tekshirish, u haqida faktlarni aniqlash uchun savollar berishni anglatadi.
column14: Bank uning kredit olish huquqiga ega yoki yo'qligini bilish uchun uning moliyaviy tarixini o'rganib chiqdi.

example: A recipient of something is the person who receives it.
type: I was the recipient of four phone calls today.
example_tr: Biror narsani oluvchi - uni qabul qiluvchi shaxs.
column14: Bugun men to'rtta qo'ng'iroqni qabul qildim.

example: A reptile is a cold-blooded animal that lays eggs and has skin covered with scales.
type: Lizards are my favorite type of reptile.
example_tr: Sudralib yuruvchi - sovuq qonli hayvon, tuxum qo'yadigan va terisi tarozi bilan qoplangan.
column14: Kaltakesaklar mening sevimli sudralib yuruvchilarimdir.

example: To thrive means to do well and be successful, healthy, or strong.
type: He may be an old man, but he continues to thrive.
example_tr: Rivojlanish - yaxshi ish qilish va muvaffaqiyatli, sog'lom yoki kuchli bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U keksa odam bo'lishi mumkin, lekin u rivojlanishda davom etmoqda.

example: When something is ultimate, it is the final result or aim of a long series of events.
type: By trying hard in school, I will reach my ultimate goal of becoming a doctor.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yakuniy bo'lsa, bu uzoq davom etadigan voqealar seriyasining yakuniy natijasi yoki maqsadidir.
column14: Maktabda qattiq harakat qilsam, shifokor bo'lishdek yakuniy maqsadimga erishaman.

example: If something is antique, it is very old and rare, and therefore valuable.
type: My grandmother's antique rocking chair is worth a lot of money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa antiqa bo'lsa, u juda qadimgi va kamdan-kam uchraydi va shuning uchun qimmatlidir.
column14: Buvimning qadimiy tebranadigan kursisi katta pulga arziydi.

example: An applicant is someone who writes a request to be considered for a job or prize.
type: Lots of applicants came into the store when the job position became available.
example_tr: Ariza beruvchi - bu ish yoki mukofot uchun ko'rib chiqilishi uchun so'rov yozadigan shaxs.
column14: Ish joyi mavjud bo'lganda do'konga ko'plab abituriyentlar kirishdi.

example: An artifact is an old object made by humans that is historically interesting.
type: We studied artifacts from an ancient Chinese settlement.
example_tr: Artefakt - bu tarixiy jihatdan qiziqarli bo'lgan odamlar tomonidan yaratilgan eski ob'ekt.
column14: Biz qadimiy Xitoy manzilgohidagi artefaktlarni o‘rgandik.

example: When something is authentic, it is not false or a copy of the original.
type: We ate authentic Italian food on our vacation to Rome.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa haqiqiy bo'lsa, u yolg'on yoki asl nusxaning nusxasi emas.
column14: Biz Rimga ta'tilda asl italyan taomlarini yedik.

example: The chronology of a series of past events is when they happened.
type: We learned the chronology of World War I in history class.
example_tr: O'tmishdagi bir qator voqealarning xronologiyasi ular sodir bo'lgan paytdir.
column14: Birinchi jahon urushi xronologiyasini tarix darsida bilib oldik.

example: A diplomat is a representative of a country who works with another country.
type: The Spanish diplomat discussed trade issues with officials in Peru.
example_tr: Diplomat - bu boshqa davlat bilan ishlaydigan davlat vakili.
column14: Ispaniyalik diplomat Peru rasmiylari bilan savdo masalalarini muhokama qildi.

example: An epic is a long book, poem, or movie about a period of time or a great event.
type: The poet wrote an epic about the great discoveries of the past thousand years.
example_tr: Doston - bu ma'lum bir davr yoki buyuk voqea haqidagi uzun kitob, she'r yoki film.
column14: Shoir o‘tgan ming yillikning buyuk kashfiyotlari haqida doston yozgan.

example: An excerpt is a short piece of writing or music taken from a larger piece.
type: I didn’t listen to the entire symphony online, but I did play an excerpt.
example_tr: Ko'chirma - bu kattaroq qismdan olingan qisqa yozuv yoki musiqa.
column14: Men butun simfoniyani onlayn tinglamadim, lekin parcha ijro etdim.

example: A fossil is the hard remains of a prehistoric animal or plant.
type: The expert arranged the fossils to build the skeleton of the dinosaur.
example_tr: Qazilma - bu tarixdan oldingi hayvon yoki o'simlikning qattiq qoldiqlari.
column14: Mutaxassis qazilmalarni dinozavr skeletini qurish uchun joylashtirdi.

example: To humiliate someone means to make them feel ashamed and embarrassed.
type: I was humiliated when I tripped and fell down in front of the whole school.
example_tr: Kimnidir kamsitish, uni uyaltirish va xijolat qilish demakdir.
column14: Butun maktab oldida qoqilib yiqilganimda xor bo'ldim.

example: When a poem is considered lyric, it is written in a simple and direct style.
type: I enjoy reading and creating my own lyric poetry.
example_tr: She’r lirik deb hisoblansa, u sodda va to‘g‘ridan-to‘g‘ri uslubda yoziladi.
column14: Men o'qishni va o'z lirik she'rlarimni yaratishni yoqtiraman.

example: Majesty is supreme greatness or authority.
type: You should address the king and queen as your majesty.
example_tr: Ulug'vorlik - oliy ulug'vorlik yoki hokimiyat.
column14: Siz shoh va malikaga o'z oliyjanobligingiz sifatida murojaat qilishingiz kerak.

example: The monarch of a country is the king, queen, emperor, or empress.
type: The monarch lived in a beautiful palace with a grand gate.
example_tr: Mamlakat monarxi qirol, malika, imperator yoki imperatordir.
column14: Monarx katta darvozali go'zal saroyda yashagan.

example: To precede something means to come before it.
type: The hurricane was preceded by a moment of still wind and clear sky.
example_tr: Biror narsadan oldin kelmoq, undan oldin kelmoq degani.
column14: Dovuldan oldin bir lahza tinch shamol va musaffo osmon bor edi.

example: When someone is punctual, they do something or arrive at the right time.
type: My mother hates being late. She is the most punctual person I know.
example_tr: Agar kimdir o'z vaqtida bo'lsa, u biror narsa qiladi yoki kerakli vaqtda keladi.
column14: Onam kechikishni yomon ko'radi. U men bilgan eng punktual odam.

example: To recruit people means to select them to join or work for an organization.
type: We successfully recruited someone to be the new manager.
example_tr: Odamlarni yollash ularni tashkilotga qo'shilish yoki ishlash uchun tanlashni anglatadi.
column14: Biz yangi menejer bo'lish uchun birovni muvaffaqiyatli ishga oldik.

example: A refund is money given back to a person when an item is returned to a store.
type: I asked for a refund because the shoes I bought were too tight.
example_tr: Qaytarilgan pul buyum do'konga qaytarilganda shaxsga qaytariladigan puldir.
column14: Men sotib olgan poyafzal juda qattiq bo‘lgani uchun pulni qaytarishni so‘radim.

example: A register is an official list or record of people or things.
type: At a wedding there is a register for all of the guests to sign.
example_tr: Reestr - bu odamlar yoki narsalarning rasmiy ro'yxati yoki yozuvi.
column14: To'yda barcha mehmonlar imzo chekishi uchun ro'yxatga olish kitobi mavjud.

example: Renown is the quality of being well known due to having done good things.
type: Michael is a singer of great renown in New Zealand.
example_tr: Shon-shuhrat - bu yaxshi ishlar qilganligi sababli taniqli bo'lish sifati.
column14: Maykl Yangi Zelandiyada mashhur qo'shiqchi.

example: A tusk is a long, curved, pointed tooth of an elephant, boar, or walrus.
type: Sadly, some people hunt elephants and remove their tusks to sell them.
example_tr: Tush - fil, cho'chqa yoki morjning uzun, kavisli, uchli tishi.
column14: Afsuski, ba'zi odamlar fillarni ovlaydi va ularni sotish uchun tishlarini olib tashlaydi.

example: A burden is a serious or difficult responsibility.
type: Children who do not behave are a burden to their parents.
example_tr: Yuk - bu jiddiy yoki qiyin mas'uliyat.
column14: O'zini tutmagan bolalar ota-onalariga yuk bo'ladi.

example: To compromise is to agree to something that is not exactly what you want.
type: We both compromised about the game we decided to play.
example_tr: Murosaga kelish - bu siz xohlagan narsaga mutlaqo rozi bo'lmaslikdir.
column14: Ikkalamiz o'ynashga qaror qilgan o'yin haqida murosaga keldik.

example: To craft something is to make it using skill.
type: She crafted the bookcase out of solid pine wood and then painted it.
example_tr: Biror narsani hunarmandchilik qilish, uni mahorat yordamida qilishdir.
column14: U qattiq qarag'ay yog'ochidan kitob javonini yasadi va keyin uni bo'yadi.

example: A crook is someone who is not honest or who commits crimes.
type: The manager was arrested by the police for being a crook.
example_tr: Firibgar - halol bo'lmagan yoki jinoyat sodir etgan odam.
column14: Menejer firibgar ekani uchun politsiya tomonidan hibsga olingan.

example: Currency is the form of money used in a certain place.
type: Elizabeth had to exchange her dollars for foreign currency.
example_tr: Pul birligi - ma'lum bir joyda ishlatiladigan pul shakli.
column14: Elizabet dollarlarini chet el valyutasiga almashtirishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: An enigma is someone or something that is mysterious or hard to understand.
type: The theft of the paintings is an enigma to the investigators.
example_tr: Jumboq - bu sirli yoki tushunish qiyin bo'lgan kimdir yoki narsadir.
column14: Rasmlarning o'g'irlanishi tergovchilar uchun jumboqdir.

example: When people or things are fragile, they are not strong and can be damaged easily.
type: The fragile glassware was carefully packed into boxes.
example_tr: Odamlar yoki narsalar mo'rt bo'lsa, ular kuchli emas va osonlikcha shikastlanadi.
column14: Nozik shisha idishlar ehtiyotkorlik bilan qutilarga qadoqlangan.

example: A hybrid is a mixture of different things or styles.
type: In Greek mythology, a centaur is a hybrid of a man and a horse.
example_tr: Gibrid - bu turli xil narsalar yoki uslublarning aralashmasi.
column14: Yunon mifologiyasida kentavr - bu odam va otning gibrididir.

example: Innocence is a lack of experience of difficult or complex things in life.
type: Everyone who met her found her innocence to be charming.
example_tr: Aybsizlik - bu hayotdagi qiyin yoki murakkab narsalar tajribasining etishmasligi.
column14: Uni uchratganlarning barchasi uning beg'uborligini maftunkor deb bilishardi.

example: To merge two things is to combine them into one whole thing.
type: The storm clouds merged into one large menacing cloud that filled the sky.
example_tr: Ikki narsani birlashtirish, ularni bir butun narsaga birlashtirishdir.
column14: Bo'ronli bulutlar osmonni to'ldirgan katta qo'rqinchli bulutga birlashdi.

example: When something is moderate, it is not too big or too small in size or amount.
type: It takes a moderate amount of patience to be around small children all day.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'rtacha bo'lsa, u juda katta yoki juda kichik emas.
column14: Kun bo'yi kichik bolalar atrofida bo'lish uchun o'rtacha sabr-toqat kerak.

example: To overwhelm is to exist in such a large amount that someone cannot deal with it.
type: The amount of homework her teacher assigned has overwhelmed her.
example_tr: Haddan tashqari ko'p miqdorda mavjud bo'lish, kimdir u bilan shug'ullana olmaydi.
column14: O'qituvchisi bergan uy vazifalari uni haddan tashqari oshirib yubordi.

example: A perception of a situation is a way of thinking about it or understanding it.
type: Since he couldn’t see, his perception of life was much different than mine.
example_tr: Vaziyatni idrok etish - bu haqda o'ylash yoki uni tushunish usuli.
column14: U ko'ra olmagani uchun uning hayot haqidagi tasavvuri menikidan ancha farq qilar edi.

example: A reunion is the meeting of people or things that have been separated.
type: Every summer we have a family reunion at the lake.
example_tr: Uchrashuv - bu ajratilgan odamlar yoki narsalarning uchrashuvi.
column14: Har yozda biz ko'lda oilaviy yig'ilish o'tkazamiz.

example: To rig something means to dishonestly arrange it.
type: The bad politician rigged the election so that he would win.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'rnatish, uni insofsiz tartibga solishni anglatadi.
column14: Yomon siyosatchi g‘alaba qozonish uchun saylovni soxtalashtirdi.

example: A shiver is a shaking movement the body makes when someone is cold or scared.
type: I got shivers on my way home because it was so cold.
example_tr: Titrash - bu odam sovuq yoki qo'rqib ketganda tananing titrash harakati.
column14: Uyga ketayotib, havo juda sovuq bo'lgani uchun titrab ketdim.

example: When someone is sociable, they are friendly.
type: Many of my good friends are sociable, but I am shy.
example_tr: Agar kimdir do'stona bo'lsa, ular do'stona munosabatda bo'lishadi.
column14: Mening yaxshi do'stlarimning ko'pchiligi ochiqko'ngil, lekin men uyatchanman.

example: When someone is talkative, they talk a lot.
type: My aunt is very talkative whenever she is on the phone.
example_tr: Biror kishi gapirsa, ko'p gapiradi.
column14: Xolam har safar telefonda gaplashsa, judayam gapiradi.

example: To tow something is to pull it.
type: The truck was towing a trailer behind it.
example_tr: Biror narsani tortib olish - uni tortib olish.
column14: Yuk mashinasi orqasida tirkamani tortib kelayotgan edi.

example: To tramp is to put your feet down in a loud, heavy way as you walk.
type: The baby tramped across the floor as he was learning to walk.
example_tr: Sezmoq - yurish paytida oyoqlaringizni baland ovozda, og'ir tarzda pastga tushirish.
column14: Kichkintoy yurishni o'rganayotganda polni oyoq osti qildi.

example: To alleviate pain or suffering means to make it less intense or severe.
type: She needed something to alleviate the pain in her back.
example_tr: Og'riq yoki azob-uqubatlarni engillashtirish, uni kamroq kuchliroq yoki og'irroq qilish demakdir.
column14: Unga belidagi og'riqni engillashtiradigan narsa kerak edi.

example: Astrology is the study of the stars in the belief that they influence people’s lives.
type: Jack, who studies astrology, believes that the stars can predict the future.
example_tr: Astrologiya - bu yulduzlarni odamlarning hayotiga ta'sir qilishiga ishonadigan fan.
column14: Astrologiyani o'rganuvchi Jek, yulduzlar kelajakni bashorat qila olishiga ishonadi.

example: To differentiate things or people is to show the difference between them.
type: It was hard to differentiate between the identical twins.
example_tr: Narsalarni yoki odamlarni farqlash ular orasidagi farqni ko'rsatishdir.
column14: Bir xil egizaklarni farqlash qiyin edi.

example: To disrupt something or someone is to prevent them from working.
type: The loud crash disrupted the class lecture.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoki kimnidir buzish, ularning ishlashiga to'sqinlik qilishdir.
column14: Kuchli shovqin sinf ma'ruzasini buzdi.

example: An equation is a math operation to determine the value of something.
type: I used the Pythagorean theorem to solve the equation,
example_tr: Tenglama - bu biror narsaning qiymatini aniqlash uchun matematik operatsiya.
column14: Tenglamani yechish uchun Pifagor teoremasidan foydalandim,

example: To err means to make a mistake.
type: The pilot erred in his estimate of the time it would take to make the trip.
example_tr: Xato qilish xato qilish demakdir.
column14: Uchuvchi safarga qancha vaqt ketishini taxmin qilishda xato qilgan.

example: When something is erroneous, it is incorrect or only partly correct.
type: The child held the erroneous belief that time machines were real.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noto'g'ri bo'lsa, u noto'g'ri yoki qisman to'g'ri bo'ladi.
column14: Bola vaqt mashinalari haqiqiy ekanligiga noto'g'ri e'tiqodga ega edi.

example: If people or things are frantic, they behave in a wild way because they are frightened
type: The cat became frantic when I tried to give it a bath.
example_tr: Agar odamlar yoki narsalar g'azablansa, ular qo'rqib ketganligi sababli o'zlarini yovvoyi tutadilar
column14: Mushukni cho‘miltirmoqchi bo‘lganimda g‘azablanib ketdi.

example: The hull of a boat or tank is the main body of it.
type: After the wreck at sea, the ship’s hull was the last part to sink.
example_tr: Qayiq yoki tankning korpusi uning asosiy qismidir.
column14: Dengizdagi halokatdan so'ng, kemaning korpusi cho'kib ketgan oxirgi qism edi.

example: When an action is inadvertent, it is done without realizing what you are doing.
type: She made an inadvertent error when she knocked over the nail polish.
example_tr: Harakat beixtiyor bo'lsa, u nima qilayotganingizni tushunmasdan amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Tirnoq bo‘yog‘ini ag‘darib tashlaganida, u beixtiyor xatoga yo‘l qo‘ydi.

example: To improvise something is to do it with whatever is available or without planning.
type: There was no meat for the pizza, so we improvised with what was in the fridge.
example_tr: Biror narsani improvizatsiya qilish, uni mavjud bo'lgan narsa bilan yoki rejalashtirmasdan qilishdir.
column14: Pitsa uchun go'sht yo'q edi, shuning uchun biz muzlatgichda bo'lgan narsalarni improvizatsiya qildik.

example: The latitude of a place is its distance from the equator.
type: The device was able to tell the traveler his exact latitude.
example_tr: Joyning kengligi uning ekvatordan uzoqligidir.
column14: Qurilma sayohatchiga uning aniq kengligini aytib bera oldi.

example: A mariner is a sailor.
type: The old mariner used his telescope to find the shore.
example_tr: Dengizchi - dengizchi.
column14: Keksa dengizchi qirg‘oqni topish uchun teleskopidan foydalangan.

example: A multitude of things or people is a very large number of them.
type: A multitude of people were waiting at the airport.
example_tr: Ko'p narsa yoki odamlar - ularning juda katta soni.
column14: Aeroportda ko'plab odamlar kutib turardi.

example: A nuisance is a person or thing that is annoying or causes a lot of problems.
type: The teenager considered her noisy little brothers to be quite a nuisance.
example_tr: Noqulaylik - bezovta qiluvchi yoki juda ko'p muammolarni keltirib chiqaradigan odam yoki narsa.
column14: O'smir shovqinli ukalarini juda bezovta deb hisobladi.

example: The permanence of something is its ability to last forever.
type: Poor results will threaten the permanence of the new teaching system.
example_tr: Biror narsaning doimiyligi uning abadiy qolishi qobiliyatidir.
column14: Yomon natijalar yangi o'qitish tizimining doimiyligiga tahdid soladi.

example: To revolve around something is to keep it as the main feature or focus.
type: My life revolves around sports.
example_tr: Biror narsa atrofida aylanish - uni asosiy xususiyat yoki diqqat markazida saqlashdir.
column14: Mening hayotim sport bilan bog'liq.

example: To soothe means to calm someone who is angry or upset.
type: The mother soothed her crying baby by rocking him in her arms.
example_tr: Tinchlantirish, g'azablangan yoki xafa bo'lgan odamni tinchlantirishni anglatadi.
column14: Ona yig‘layotgan chaqalog‘ini bag‘riga bosib, tinchlantirdi.

example: If someone is stranded, they are prevented from leaving a place.
type: When the plane left, my sister and I were stranded in China.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yo'lda qolgan bo'lsa, u joydan chiqib ketishiga to'sqinlik qiladi.
column14: Samolyot jo‘nab ketgach, singlim bilan Xitoyda qolib ketdik.

example: When something is volatile, it is likely to change suddenly and unexpectedly.
type: The volatile volcano might explode at any moment.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'zgaruvchan bo'lsa, u to'satdan va kutilmaganda o'zgarishi mumkin.
column14: Uchuvchi vulqon har qanday vaqtda portlashi mumkin.

example: When are is ates; it demands great effort or labor.
type: The explorers began their arduous hike up the steep mountain.
example_tr: Qachon bo'ladi; katta kuch yoki mehnat talab qiladi.
column14: Tadqiqotchilar tik tog'da mashaqqatli yurishni boshladilar.

example: To attain something means to gain or achieve it, often after a lot of effort.
type: In two more years, | will attain my high school diploma.
example_tr: Biror narsaga erishish ko'pincha ko'p harakatlardan keyin unga erishish yoki erishishni anglatadi.
column14: Yana ikki yildan keyin, | o'rta maktab diplomimga erishaman.

example: To coexist with something means to exist with it in the same time and place.
type: Our pets coexist at our home with little or no problems.
example_tr: Biror narsa bilan birga yashash, u bilan bir vaqtda va bir joyda mavjud bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Uy hayvonlari bizning uyimizda juda kam yoki hech qanday muammosiz yashaydi.

example: To conceive something means to be able to imagine or believe it.
type: The child could not conceive the actual size of the Earth.
example_tr: Biror narsani tasavvur qilish, tasavvur qilish yoki unga ishonishni anglatadi.
column14: Bola Yerning haqiqiy hajmini tasavvur qila olmadi.

example: When something or someone is dubious, they are not considered honest.
type: The police thought that the man’s description of the crime was dubious.
example_tr: Biror narsa yoki kimdir shubhali bo'lsa, ular halol hisoblanmaydi.
column14: Politsiya erkakning jinoyat tavsifi shubhali deb hisobladi.

example: An ego is a person’s sense of their own worth.
type: Kelly’s ego made her think that she was some kind of a superhero.
example_tr: Ego - bu insonning o'z qadr-qimmatini his qilishidir.
column14: Kellining nafsi uni qandaydir super qahramon deb o'ylashga majbur qildi.

example: Elastic is a rubber that stretches when itis pulled.
type: He attached the elastic bungee to his legs before he jumped off the platform.
example_tr: Elastik - bu tortilganda cho'zilib ketadigan kauchuk.
column14: U platformadan sakrashdan oldin oyoqlariga elastik bunge bog'ladi.

example: An endeavor is an attempt to do something, especially something new or original.
type: The company’s new advertising endeavor ended in a horrible failure.
example_tr: Harakat - bu biror narsa, ayniqsa, yangi yoki o'ziga xos narsa qilishga urinish.
column14: Kompaniyaning yangi reklama urinishi dahshatli muvaffaqiyatsizlik bilan yakunlandi.

example: To engrave means to cut a design or words into the surface of something.
type: The couple engraved their names onto the old pine tree.
example_tr: Gravür qilish, biror narsa yuzasiga naqsh yoki so'zlarni kesib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Er-xotin o'z ismlarini eski qarag'ay daraxtiga o'yib qo'yishdi.

example: To excavate means to dig on land and remove dirt to look for something.
type: The team wishes to excavate the site in hopes of finding fossils.
example_tr: Qazish, biror narsani izlash uchun quruqlikda qazish va tuproqni tozalash demakdir.
column14: Jamoa qazilma qoldiqlarini topish umidida saytni qazishni xohlaydi.

example: When something is jagged, it has a tough, uneven shape or edge.
type: The swimmer was hurt when he fell on the jagged rocks.
example_tr: Biror narsa tishli bo'lsa, u qattiq, notekis shaklga yoki qirraga ega bo'ladi.
column14: Suzuvchi qirrali toshlarga yiqilib, jarohat olgan.

example: A locale is a small area or place where something specific happens.
type: The spa was the perfect locate for my mother to relax and enjoy her vacation.
example_tr: Mahalliy til - bu aniq bir narsa sodir bo'ladigan kichik hudud yoki joy.
column14: Kurort onam uchun dam olish va ta'tildan zavq olish uchun eng zo'r joy edi.

example: Amold is a hollow container that is used to make certain shapes.
type: Using a cupcake mold will ensure that they come out just right.
example_tr: Amold - bu ma'lum shakllarni tayyorlash uchun ishlatiladigan ichi bo'sh idish.
column14: Kek qolipidan foydalanish ularning to'g'ri chiqishini ta'minlaydi.

example: When something is outright, itis open and direct.
type: Everyone knew that the boy's story was an outright lie.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ochiq bo'lsa, u ochiq va to'g'ridan-to'g'ri.
column14: Bolaning hikoyasi yolg‘on ekanini hamma bilardi.

example: The periphery of an area, place, or thing is the edge of it.
type: A beautiful floral pattern is on the periphery of the stationery.
example_tr: Hudud, joy yoki narsaning cheti uning chetidir.
column14: Chiroyli gul naqshlari ish yuritish buyumlarining chetida joylashgan.

example: Plaster is a smooth paste that gets hard when it dries.
type: He used plaster to fill in the cracks in the old walls.
example_tr: Gips silliq pastadir, u quriganida qattiqlashadi.
column14: Qadimgi devorlardagi yoriqlarni gips ishlatgan.

example: A shovel is a tool with a long handle that is used for digging.
type: The boy grabbed his shovel and got all of the snow off of the sidewalk.
example_tr: Belkurak - qazish uchun ishlatiladigan uzun tutqichli asbob.
column14: Bola belkurakni olib, yo‘lakdagi qorning hammasini olib tashladi.

example: When something is skeletal, it relates to bones in the body.
type: We studied the skeletal system in anatomy class.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa skelet bo'lsa, u tanadagi suyaklarga tegishli.
column14: Biz anatomiya darsida suyak tizimini o'rgandik.

example: lf something is terrestrial, it relates to Earth.
type: There are billions of terrestrial life forms.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa er yuzida bo'lsa, u Yerga tegishli.
column14: Er yuzidagi milliardlab hayot shakllari mavjud.

example: When something or someone is vicious, they are violent and cruel.
type: The vicious dog tried to bite the small child.
example_tr: Biror narsa yoki kimdir shafqatsiz bo'lsa, ular zo'ravon va shafqatsiz.
column14: Yovuz it kichkina bolani tishlamoqchi bo'ldi.

example: If something or someone is absurd, they are ridiculous.
type: That group of people making animal noises sounds completely absurd.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir bema'ni bo'lsa, ular kulgili.
column14: Hayvonlarning shovqini qiladigan odamlar guruhi mutlaqo bema'ni tuyuladi.

example: Anemia is a blood condition that causes a person to be pale and tired.
type: When she first developed anemia, she became tired often.
example_tr: Anemiya - bu odamning rangi oqarib, charchashga olib keladigan qon kasalligi.
column14: Birinchi marta kamqonlik paydo bo'lganida, u tez-tez charchagan.

example: The aristocracy is the highest class of people in certain societies.
type: Most members of the aristocracy were very well-fed.
example_tr: Aristokratiya - bu ma'lum jamiyatlarda odamlarning eng yuqori qatlami.
column14: Aristokratiya vakillarining ko'pchiligi juda yaxshi ovqatlangan.

example: An aristocrat is a person who is of the highest class in certain societies.
type: The aristocrat did not need a job because his family was wealthy.
example_tr: Aristokrat - bu muayyan jamiyatlarda eng yuqori tabaqaga mansub shaxs.
column14: Aristokratga ish kerak emas edi, chunki uning oilasi badavlat edi.

example: Attire is nice or special clothing.
type: Everyone wore their best attire to the president’s daughter’s wedding.
example_tr: Kiyim - bu chiroyli yoki maxsus kiyim.
column14: Prezident qizining to'yida hamma o'zining eng yaxshi libosini kiydi.

example: Acraze is a brief and popular activity or object.
type: Wearing bright red socks was a craze when | was in high school.
example_tr: Akraze - bu qisqa va mashhur faoliyat yoki ob'ekt.
column14: Yorqin qizil paypoq kiyish jinni edi qachon | o'rta maktabda edi.

example: To enlarge something means to make it bigger.
type: The classrooms were enlarged over the summer to make room for more students.
example_tr: Biror narsani kattalashtirish, uni kattalashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yozda ko'proq o'quvchilar uchun joy ochish uchun sinf xonalari kengaytirildi.

example: An excess is an amount of something that is more than needed or wanted.
type: Because it never got cold that winter, many stores had an excess of coats.
example_tr: Ortiqcha narsa - kerakli yoki xohlaganidan ko'proq narsaning miqdori.
column14: O'sha qishda hech qachon sovuq bo'lmagani uchun ko'plab do'konlarda paltolar ortiqcha bo'lgan.

example: If something is feminine, then it has qualities that are commonly related to women.
type: Many of the older people thought his long hair made him look too feminine.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ayollik bo'lsa, unda u odatda ayollarga tegishli bo'lgan fazilatlarga ega.
column14: Ko'pgina keksa odamlar uning uzun sochlari uni juda nazokatli qiladi deb o'ylashgan.

example: A hallmark is a unique characteristic of something.
type: Different types of pasta and tomato sauces are hallmarks of Italian food.
example_tr: Belgi - bu narsaning o'ziga xos xususiyati.
column14: Har xil turdagi makaron va pomidor soslari italyan taomlarining o'ziga xos belgilaridir.

example: A pad is a thick piece of soft material used to protect or clean things.
type: Football players wear shoulder pads to keep them safe.
example_tr: Yostiqcha - bu narsalarni himoya qilish yoki tozalash uchun ishlatiladigan qalin yumshoq material.
column14: Futbolchilar xavfsizligini ta'minlash uchun elkalariga yostiqlar kiyishadi.

example: If something is predominant, then it is the most important, common or strongest.
type: Before cars were invented, horses were the predominant method of travel.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ustun bo'lsa, u eng muhim, keng tarqalgan yoki kuchli.
column14: Avtomobillar ixtiro qilinishidan oldin, otlar sayohat qilishning asosiy usuli edi.

example: If someone or something is reputable, then they have a good reputation.
type: The service from the less than reputable company made her angry.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa obro'li bo'lsa, unda ular yaxshi obro'ga ega.
column14: Kamroq nufuzli kompaniyaning xizmati uni g'azablantirdi.

example: Rouge is a red powder or cream used as makeup on the cheeks or lips.
type: Even when she didn’t wear rouge, her cheeks appeared red,
example_tr: Rouge - yonoqlarda yoki lablarda bo'yanish sifatida ishlatiladigan qizil kukun yoki krem.
column14: U rouge kiymagan bo'lsa ham, uning yonoqlari qizarib ketdi,

example: To signify means to be a symbol of something.
type: Ared octagon is used to signify to stop.
example_tr: Ishora qilish, biror narsaning ramzi bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Ared sakkizburchak to'xtashni bildirish uchun ishlatiladi.

example: A strap is a thin long piece of fabric used to fasten, carry, or hold something.
type: She put the strap of her purse over her shoulder and walked out of the door.
example_tr: Tasma - biror narsani mahkamlash, tashish yoki ushlab turish uchun ishlatiladigan ingichka uzun mato.
column14: U hamyonining kamarini yelkasiga qo‘yib, eshikdan chiqdi.

example: Atangle is something or many things twisted together.
type: The laces of his shoes were in such a tangle that he could not untie them.
example_tr: Atangle - bu bir-biriga o'ralgan narsa yoki ko'p narsalar.
column14: Oyoq kiyimining iplari shu qadar chigal ediki, uni yecha olmasdi.

example: Vanity is excessive pride or love of one’s own appearance or things one has done.
type: Her vanity won't allow her to pass a mirror without looking at herself.
example_tr: Bekorchilik - bu haddan tashqari mag'rurlik yoki o'z tashqi ko'rinishiga yoki qilgan ishlariga bo'lgan muhabbat.
column14: Uning bema'niligi unga o'ziga qaramasdan ko'zgudan o'tishga imkon bermaydi.

example: To vie for something means to compete against others for it.
type: The three boys vied for the prize in the chemistry contest.
example_tr: Biror narsa uchun kurashish, buning uchun boshqalar bilan raqobatlashishni anglatadi.
column14: Uch nafar o‘g‘il kimyo fanidan sovrinli o‘rin uchun kurashdi.

example: If something or someone is vulgar, then they are rude or lacking in style.
type: Her vulgar behavior got her into trouble with her parents.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir qo'pol bo'lsa, unda ular qo'pol yoki uslubga ega emas.
column14: Uning qo'pol xatti-harakati uni ota-onasi bilan muammoga aylantirdi.

example: An attic is a room just below a house's roof.
type: There were two windows in their attic.
example_tr: Chordoq - bu uyning tomi ostidagi xona.
column14: Ularning chodirida ikkita deraza bor edi.

example: A chunk is a thick, solid piece of something.
type: When they broke open the rock, they saw it was filled with chunks of gold.
example_tr: Bo‘lak – biror narsaning qalin, qattiq bo‘lagi.
column14: Ular toshni sindirib ochib, uning oltin bo‘laklari bilan to‘ldirilganini ko‘rdilar.

example: If something is civic, then it is related to a town or city, especially its government.
type: Most of the important civic buildings are located downtown.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa fuqarolik bo'lsa, u shahar yoki shahar, ayniqsa uning hukumati bilan bog'liq.
column14: Muhim fuqarolik binolarining aksariyati shahar markazida joylashgan.

example: A descent is a movement downwards.
type: During the space shuttle's descent, the Earth became larger and larger.
example_tr: Pastga tushish - bu pastga qarab harakat qilish.
column14: Kosmik kemaning tushishi paytida Yer tobora kattalashib bordi.

example: A din is loud, unpleasant, and extended noise.
type: The din of the rusty machinery made the factory a horrible place to work.
example_tr: Din - baland, yoqimsiz va cho'zilgan shovqin.
column14: Zanglagan mexanizmlarning shovqini zavodni dahshatli ish joyiga aylantirdi.

example: To dissatisfy someone means to fail to please them.
type: He was dissatisfied with his meal.
example_tr: Birovni qoniqtirmaslik, uni rozi qilmaslik demakdir.
column14: U ovqatdan norozi edi.

example: A fuss is excited or annoyed behavior that is not useful in any way.
type: The child made an awful fuss because she didn't want to go to bed.
example_tr: Shovqin - bu hech qanday foydali bo'lmagan hayajonli yoki bezovta qiluvchi xatti-harakatlar.
column14: Bola yotishni istamagani uchun dahshatli shov-shuv ko'tardi.

example: If food is gourmet, then it is nicer and more expensive than regular food.
type: In order to get a gourmet meal, you have to eat at an expensive restaurant.
example_tr: Agar oziq-ovqat gurme bo'lsa, u oddiy ovqatdan ko'ra yoqimli va qimmatroq.
column14: Gurme taomini olish uchun siz qimmat restoranda ovqatlanishingiz kerak.

example: If something happens hence, then it happens as a result of something.
type: John forgot the key. Hence, we couldn't open the door.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, u biror narsa natijasida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Jon kalitni unutdi. Shuning uchun biz eshikni ocholmadik.

example: If something is intrinsic, then it is related to the basic nature of that thing.
type: Paper money has no intrinsic value; it is useful simply because society says it is.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'ziga xos bo'lsa, u o'sha narsaning asosiy tabiati bilan bog'liq.
column14: Qog'oz pulning o'ziga xos qiymati yo'q; bu shunchaki foydalidir, chunki jamiyat buni aytadi.

example: A kettle is a large metal pot used for boiling liquids or cooking food.
type: The soup was being cooked in a large kettle.
example_tr: Choynak - suyuqlikni qaynatish yoki ovqat pishirish uchun ishlatiladigan katta metall qozon.
column14: Katta choynakda sho‘rva pishirilayotgan edi.

example: A ministry is a government department.
type: The Ministry of Trade is responsible for taxing imports and exports.
example_tr: Vazirlik - bu davlat idorasi.
column14: Savdo vazirligi import va eksportga soliq solish uchun javobgardir.

example: An ordeal is a bad experience.
type: Driving in the snowstorm was an ordeal she'd never forget.
example_tr: Sinov - bu yomon tajriba.
column14: Qor bo'ronida haydash u hech qachon unutolmaydigan sinov edi.

example: If someone is outspoken, then they are not afraid to say what they think.
type: She was an outspoken critic about the new banking laws.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ochiqchasiga gapirsa, u o'z fikrini aytishdan qo'rqmaydi.
column14: U yangi bank qonunlari haqida ochiq tanqidchi edi.

example: To overwork someone means to make them tired with too much work.
type: After working for three weeks with only one day of rest, Judy was overworked.
example_tr: Biror kishini ortiqcha ishlash, uni ortiqcha ish bilan charchatishni anglatadi.
column14: Faqat bir kunlik dam olish bilan uch hafta ishlagandan so'ng, Judi juda ko'p ishladi.

example: If something is particular, then it is a single, important part of a group of things.
type: The dress shop didn't have the particular dress she was looking for.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'ziga xos bo'lsa, demak u narsalar guruhining yagona, muhim qismidir.
column14: Liboslar do'konida u qidirgan ko'ylak yo'q edi.

example: If something is pungent, then it tastes or smells strong and sharp.
type: The garlic made the soup taste so pungent that the chef wouldn't serve it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'tkir bo'lsa, u kuchli va o'tkir ta'mi yoki hidini sezadi.
column14: Sarimsoq sho'rvaning ta'mini shunchalik o'tkir qildiki, oshpaz unga xizmat qilmadi.

example: To snore means to make a loud noise each time a sleeping person breathes.
type: It was impossible to get to sleep because my husband snored.
example_tr: Horlama, uxlab yotgan odam har safar nafas olayotganda baland ovozda ovoz chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Erim xo'rlagani uchun uxlab qolishning iloji bo'lmadi.

example: If something is done soundly, then it is done in the best or most complete way.
type: The nearest opponent was ten meters behind. She won the race soundly.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'g'ri bajarilgan bo'lsa, u eng yaxshi yoki eng to'liq tarzda amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Eng yaqin raqib o'n metr orqada edi. U musobaqada ishonchli g'alaba qozondi.

example: A superintendent is a person who runs a certain department or building.
type: The superintendent decided to close the schools because of the weather.
example_tr: Nazoratchi - bu ma'lum bir bo'lim yoki binoni boshqaradigan shaxs.
column14: Nazoratchi ob-havo tufayli maktablarni yopishga qaror qildi.

example: To alternate means to switch back and forth between two things.
type: The best exercise alternates muscle and heart strengthening.
example_tr: Almashtirish ikki narsani oldinga va orqaga almashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Eng yaxshi mashq mushak va yurakni mustahkamlashni almashtiradi.

example: If someone is apologetic, they are sorry about something.
type: The boy felt apologetic after losing his sister’s favorite toy.
example_tr: Agar kimdir kechirim so'rasa, u biror narsadan afsuslanadi.
column14: Bola singlisining sevimli o'yinchog'ini yo'qotib qo'yganidan keyin kechirim so'radi.

example: If something or someone is benign, they do not hurt anyone.
type: Many spiders look scary, but most are actually benign.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir yaxshi bo'lsa, ular hech kimga zarar etkazmaydi.
column14: Ko'pgina o'rgimchaklar qo'rqinchli ko'rinadi, lekin ko'pchilik aslida yaxshi.

example: To char means to burn something so that it turns black.
type: While Frank went inside to get the mustard, he accidentally charred the hotdogs.
example_tr: Char degani, biror narsaning qora rangga aylanishi uchun kuydirish demakdir.
column14: Frenk xantal olish uchun ichkariga kirganda, u tasodifan hotdoglarni kuydirib yubordi.

example: To clarify means to make something easier to understand by explaining it.
type: Drew tried to clarify all the functions of Michelle's new computer.
example_tr: Aniqlash, biror narsani tushuntirish orqali tushunishni osonlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Dryu Mishelning yangi kompyuterining barcha funksiyalariga aniqlik kiritishga harakat qildi.

example: Distress is the feeling of being upset or worried.
type: Failing a class caused the student a lot of distress.
example_tr: Qiyinchilik - bu xafa bo'lish yoki tashvishlanish hissi.
column14: Sinfdagi muvaffaqiyatsizlik talabani juda ko'p qayg'uga soldi.

example: When someone's actions are dogged, they try hard to continue something.
type: Her dad bought her a new jacket after her dogged requests for one.
example_tr: Biror kishining xatti-harakati tajovuzkor bo'lsa, u nimanidir davom ettirishga harakat qiladi.
column14: Dadasi uning qattiq iltimoslaridan keyin unga yangi kurtka sotib oldi.

example: To ensue means to happen after something.
type: After a few minutes of lightening, thunder ensued.
example_tr: Oqibat, biror narsadan keyin sodir bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Bir necha daqiqa chaqmoq chaqqandan keyin momaqaldiroq gumburladi.

example: To gasp means to make a noise by quickly breathing in when surprised.
type: John always gasps when watching a scary movie.
example_tr: Nafas olish hayratda qolganda tez nafas olish orqali shovqin chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: Jon qo'rqinchli filmni tomosha qilganda doimo nafas oladi.

example: To negotiate means to try to make an agreement through discussion.
type: Mario and Joe took a long time negotiating the contract between the companies.
example_tr: Muzokara qilish, muhokama qilish orqali kelishuvga erishishga harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Mario va Jo kompaniyalar o'rtasidagi shartnoma bo'yicha muzokaralar olib borish uchun uzoq vaqt talab qilishdi.

example: An overdose is an instance of taking or having too much of something.
type: John’s skin was burned from an overdose of sunshine.
example_tr: Dozani oshirib yuborish - bu biror narsaning haddan tashqari ko'p bo'lishi yoki qabul qilinishi.
column14: Jonning terisi quyosh nurining haddan tashqari dozasidan kuygan.

example: Persuasion is the act of making someone do or believe something.
type: The persuasion of his argument convinced the customer to buy the flaptap.
example_tr: Ishontirish - bu kimnidir biror narsa qilishga yoki ishonishga majbur qilish harakati.
column14: Uning argumentini ishontirish mijozni flaptap sotib olishga ishontirdi.

example: A relay is a race in which teams of runners or swimmers race against each other.
type: Ferry was the fastest on his team, so he ran the last part of the relay.
example_tr: Estafeta - bu yuguruvchilar yoki suzuvchilar jamoalari bir-biriga qarshi poyga.
column14: Ferri o'z jamoasida eng tezkor edi, shuning uchun u estafetaning oxirgi qismini yugurdi.

example: Reluctance is a feeling of not wanting to do something.
type: Jesse took out the trash with great reluctance.
example_tr: Istaksizlik - biror narsa qilishni xohlamaslik hissi.
column14: Jessi katta istamay axlatni olib chiqdi.

example: To restate something means to say it again or in a different way.
type: Mrs. Jones restated the test question to the class.
example_tr: Biror narsani takrorlash, uni qayta yoki boshqacha tarzda aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Missis Jons test savolini sinfga qaytardi.

example: Sesame is an herb that is grown for its small seeds and its oil.
type: fused the buns with the sesame seeds on them.
example_tr: Susan mayda urugʻlari va yogʻi uchun yetishtiriladigan oʻtdir.
column14: kunjut bilan bulochkalarni birlashtirdi.

example: To sip something means to drink a small amount at a time.
type: Liza relaxed on the beach, sipping fruit juice through a straw.
example_tr: Biror narsani ho'plab ichish, bir vaqtning o'zida oz miqdorda ichishni anglatadi.
column14: Liza sohilda somondan meva sharbatini ho'plab, dam oldi.

example: The verge is the point at which something is about to happen.
type: Joan was on the verge of leaving her house when the phone rang.
example_tr: Chegara - biror narsa sodir bo'ladigan nuqta.
column14: Joan uyidan chiqish arafasida edi, telefon jiringladi.

example: If someone is wary, they are cautious or mistrusting.
type: She was wary of going to school because she hadn't done her homework.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ehtiyotkor bo'lsa, u ehtiyotkor yoki ishonmaydi.
column14: U uy vazifasini bajarmagani uchun maktabga borishdan qo‘rqardi.

example: To waver is to be unable to decide between two choices.
type: I wavered between eating the apple or the cake for a snack.
example_tr: Tebranish ikki tanlov o'rtasida qaror qabul qila olmaslikdir.
column14: Men olma yoki tortni yeb yeyish o‘rtasida ikkilanib qoldim.

example: If something goes ashore, it goes from water to the land.
type: After a long day of fishing, Glen pulled his boat ashore, so it wouldn't float away.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qirg'oqqa chiqsa, u suvdan quruqlikka ketadi.
column14: Uzoq kunlik baliq ovidan so‘ng Glen suzmasligi uchun qayig‘ini qirg‘oqqa tortdi.

example: To contradict means to state the opposite of what someone else has.
type: Ken was always fighting with his little sister because she kept contradicting him.
example_tr: Qarama-qarshilik boshqa birovda mavjud bo'lgan narsaning aksini aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Ken doimo singlisi bilan janjallashardi, chunki u doimo unga qarshi edi.

example: A counterpart is something that is very similar to something else in what it does.
type: Our manager will meet our rival company’s counterpart later today.
example_tr: Qarshdosh - bu o'z ishida boshqa narsaga juda o'xshash narsa.
column14: Menejerimiz bugun kechroq raqib kompaniyamizning hamkasbi bilan uchrashadi.

example: When something or someone is devoid of a thing, they are missing it.
type: The movie was devoid of any violence, so it was a perfect movie for the family.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir biror narsadan mahrum bo'lsa, ular uni etishmaydi.
column14: Filmda hech qanday zo'ravonlik yo'q edi, shuning uchun u oila uchun mukammal film edi.

example: To diverge is to become different or to follow a different direction.
type: The road diverged into two paths that led to our houses.
example_tr: Ajralish - boshqacha bo'lish yoki boshqa yo'nalishga ergashish.
column14: Yo'l ikkiga bo'linib, uylarimizga olib bordi.

example: To elude means to avoid being caught by something.
type: The rabbit eluded the wolf by hiding in a bush.
example_tr: Qochish, biror narsaga ilinmaslikni anglatadi.
column14: Quyon butaga yashirinib, bo‘ridan qochib qutuldi.

example: An embryo is a human or animal that is still growing inside its mother.
type: Some doctors say that what a mother eats has a big effect on her embryo.
example_tr: Embrion - bu onasining ichida hali ham o'sib borayotgan odam yoki hayvon.
column14: Ba'zi shifokorlarning ta'kidlashicha, onaning ovqati uning embrioniga katta ta'sir qiladi.

example: To fend off something means to push it away and avoid it.
type: Dave spent all night fending off bugs instead of sleeping.
example_tr: Biror narsadan qutulish, uni itarish va undan qochish demakdir.
column14: Deyv tun bo'yi uxlash o'rniga hasharotlarga qarshi kurashdi.

example: When something is fictitious, it is made up and not real.
type: The author said that the characters in her book were completely fictitious.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa xayoliy bo'lsa, u o'ylab topiladi va haqiqiy emas.
column14: Muallifning aytishicha, uning kitobidagi qahramonlar butunlay uydirma.

example: A gazette is a newspaper.
type: Alice wants to write for a gazette when she’s older.
example_tr: Gazeta - bu gazeta.
column14: Elis qariganida gazetaga yozishni xohlaydi.

example: If something is homogeneous, it is made up of things which are all the same.
type: All of the houses on Victor’s block were boring and homogeneous.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa bir hil bo'lsa, u hammasi bir xil bo'lgan narsalardan iborat.
column14: Viktor blokidagi barcha uylar zerikarli va bir hil edi.

example: To obstruct something means to get in its way.
type: The car broke down on the road and obstructed traffic for hours.
example_tr: Biror narsaga to'sqinlik qilish, uning yo'liga kirishni anglatadi.
column14: Mashina yo‘lda buzilib, soatlab harakatga to‘sqinlik qilgan.

example: To plunge means to move down into something very quickly.
type: The water in the pool was very cold, but the boy plunged in anyway.
example_tr: Sho'ng'in qilish - tezda biror narsaga tushishni anglatadi.
column14: Hovuzdagi suv juda sovuq edi, lekin bola baribir cho'kib ketdi.

example: To prolong means to make something last for a longer time.
type: Sandy walked slowly across the beach, trying to prolong her lunch break.
example_tr: Uzaytirish, biror narsani uzoqroq muddatga qoldirish demakdir.
column14: Sandy tushlik tanaffusini uzaytirmoqchi bo'lib, sohil bo'ylab sekin yurdi.

example: To publicize is to make something get a lot of attention.
type: The company publicized the job positions in the newspaper.
example_tr: Ommaviy e'lon qilish - biror narsaning diqqatini jalb qilishdir.
column14: Kompaniya ish o'rinlarini gazetada e'lon qildi.

example: If something is sparse, there is not very much of it in a big area.
type: Rob spent Saturday in his garden, clearing out the sparse weeds.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa siyrak bo'lsa, u katta maydonda unchalik ko'p emas.
column14: Rob shanba kunini o'z bog'ida siyrak begona o'tlarni tozalash bilan o'tkazdi.

example: A surplus is an extra amount of something.
type: The store sold their surplus items on sale.
example_tr: Ortiqcha narsa - bu narsaning qo'shimcha miqdori.
column14: Do'kon ularning ortiqcha narsalarni sotuvga sotdi.

example: To theorize means to develop ideas about something.
type: They enjoyed theorizing about how things worked.
example_tr: Nazariylashtirish - biror narsa haqida g'oyalarni ishlab chiqish demakdir.
column14: Ular narsalar qanday ishlashi haqida nazariya qilishni yoqtirardi.

example: To verify means to find out if something is true.
type: Julian called the movie theater to verify that the movie started at nine.
example_tr: Tekshirish, biror narsaning haqiqat yoki yo'qligini aniqlashni anglatadi.
column14: Julian kinoteatrga qo'ng'iroq qilib, film to'qqizda boshlanganini tekshirishdi.

example: If something or someone is vigorous, they use a lot of energy.
type: Henry uses vigorous exercise to keep himself in shape.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir kuchli bo'lsa, ular juda ko'p energiya sarflaydi.
column14: Genri o'zini formada ushlab turish uchun kuchli mashqlardan foydalanadi.

example: An altar is a table used in churches.
type: The altar had many lit candles on it.
example_tr: Qurbongoh - cherkovlarda ishlatiladigan stol.
column14: Qurbongohda ko'plab shamlar yondirilgan edi.

example: Arthritis is an illness causing pain and swelling in a person’s joints.
type: Agatha couldn't play the piano anymore because of her arthritis.
example_tr: Artrit - bu odamning bo'g'imlarida og'riq va shish paydo bo'lishiga olib keladigan kasallik.
column14: Agata artriti tufayli pianino chala olmadi.

example: Botany is the study of plants.
type: Gardens are the best places for botany.
example_tr: Botanika o'simliklarni o'rganadi.
column14: Bog'lar botanika uchun eng yaxshi joylardir.

example: IF something or someone is credible, they can be believed or trusted.
type: Dick gave a credible reason for being late and didn’t get in any trouble.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir ishonchli bo'lsa, ularga ishonish yoki ishonish mumkin.
column14: Dik kechikishning ishonchli sababini aytdi va hech qanday muammoga duch kelmadi.

example: If someone is deceased, they are dead.
type: We visited the graves of our deceased grandparents.
example_tr: Agar kimdir o'lgan bo'lsa, u o'lgan.
column14: Marhum bobo va buvilarimiz qabrlarini ziyorat qildik.

example: Deception is the act of lying or tricking someone.
type: The magic looked very real, but it was only deception.
example_tr: Aldash - yolg'on gapirish yoki kimnidir aldash harakati.
column14: Sehr juda haqiqiy ko'rinardi, lekin bu faqat yolg'on edi.

example: To decipher writing is to figure out what it says.
type: My teacher complained that she couldn’t decipher my essay.
example_tr: Yozishni dekodlash, unda nima deyilganini aniqlashdir.
column14: O'qituvchim inshoni tushuna olmaganidan shikoyat qildi.

example: Dung is solid waste material produced by animals.
type: There was cow dung all over the field.
example_tr: Go'ng - bu hayvonlar tomonidan ishlab chiqarilgan qattiq chiqindilar.
column14: Dala bo‘ylab sigir tezaklari bor edi.

example: Dusk is the time in the evening when it begins to get dark.
type: After dusk, Hannah would catch fireflies in the park.
example_tr: Kechqurun - qorong'i tusha boshlagan vaqt.
column14: Qorong'i tushgandan keyin Xanna parkda o't chirog'ini tutdi.

example: To gratify someone means to please them.
type: Bonnie was gratified after receiving her gift from her parents.
example_tr: Biror kishini xursand qilish, uni rozi qilish demakdir.
column14: Bonni ota-onasidan sovg'a olganidan keyin xursand bo'ldi.

example: To hone something is to improve it and make it very good.
type: Lisa honed her chess skills by hours and hours of practice.
example_tr: Biror narsani yaxshilash, uni yaxshilash va uni juda yaxshi qilishdir.
column14: Liza shaxmat bo'yicha mahoratini soatlab va soatlab mashg'ulotlar orqali oshirdi.

example: To mash something is to crush it so that it is soft.
type: We mashed the hard potatoes and served them for dinner.
example_tr: Biror narsani ezish - uni yumshoq qilib maydalash.
column14: Biz qattiq kartoshkani maydalab, kechki ovqatga xizmat qildik.

example: If something is ornate, it is decorated with a lot of fancy things.
type: Kim’s prom dress was very expensive since it was so ornate.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa bezakli bo'lsa, u juda ko'p chiroyli narsalar bilan bezatilgan.
column14: Kimning bitiruv libosi juda bezakli bo'lgani uchun juda qimmat edi.

example: Pneumonia is a dangerous illness causing the lungs to fill with liquid.
type: Elaine got pneumonia after playing outside in the rain without a coat.
example_tr: Pnevmoniya o'pkaning suyuqlik bilan to'lib ketishiga olib keladigan xavfli kasallikdir.
column14: Elaine paltosiz yomg'ir ostida o'ynagani uchun pnevmoniyaga chalingan.

example: When someone is psychic, they know what will happen or what people think.
type: I think my grandmother has psychic abilities because she can predict anything.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ruhiy bo'lsa, u nima bo'lishini yoki odamlar nima deb o'ylashini biladi.
column14: Menimcha, buvimning ruhiy qobiliyati bor, chunki u hamma narsani bashorat qila oladi.

example: If someone is psychotic, they have a very serious mental illness.
type: The psychotic patient believed he saw things that weren’t real.
example_tr: Agar kimdir psixotik bo'lsa, unda juda jiddiy ruhiy kasallik bor.
column14: Psixotik bemor haqiqiy bo'lmagan narsalarni ko'rganiga ishondi.

example: The scope of something is how many people or things it relates to.
type: Modern history has a wide scope.
example_tr: Biror narsaning ko'lami - bu qancha odam yoki narsalar bilan bog'liqligi.
column14: Zamonaviy tarix keng qamrovga ega.

example: If something or someone is sinister, they are evil.
type: Bad guys in most movies have sinister laughs.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir yomon bo'lsa, ular yovuzdir.
column14: Aksariyat filmlardagi yomon odamlarning kulgisi bor.

example: Strife is disagreement or fighting between people or groups.
type: There was a lot of strife between Jim and Lisa about what TV show to watch.
example_tr: Nizo - bu odamlar yoki guruhlar o'rtasidagi kelishmovchilik yoki janjal.
column14: Jim va Liza o'rtasida qanday teleko'rsatuv ko'rish haqida juda ko'p janjal bor edi.

example: IF something is therapeutic, it helps to cure a disease or makes you healthier.
type: After a stressful day of working, Phoebe would take a therapeutic bath.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa terapevtik bo'lsa, u kasallikni davolashga yordam beradi yoki sizni sog'lom qiladi.
column14: Stressli ish kunidan keyin Fibi terapevtik vanna qabul qilardi.

example: If something is congested, it is full or blocked.
type: Tom didn’t get home until after dark because the road was so congested.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tiqilib qolsa, u to'lgan yoki bloklangan.
column14: Tom qorong'i tushguncha uyga qaytmadi, chunki yo'l juda tirband edi.

example: A courier is someone who takes and delivers mail or packages.
type: Before trains, most couriers used horses to travel.
example_tr: Kuryer - bu pochta yoki paketlarni qabul qiluvchi va etkazib beradigan shaxs.
column14: Poezdlardan oldin ko'pchilik kurerlar sayohat qilish uchun otlardan foydalanganlar.

example: To deform something means to change it from its correct or original shape.
type: The computer program deformed the building’s picture into an unreal sight.
example_tr: Biror narsani deformatsiya qilish, uni to'g'ri yoki asl shaklidan o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kompyuter dasturi binoning rasmini haqiqiy bo'lmagan ko'rinishga aylantirdi.

example: Etiquette is the group of rules about how to be polite.
type: When in Asian countries, bowing is a form of etiquette.
example_tr: Odob - bu qanday qilib xushmuomala bo'lish haqida qoidalar guruhi.
column14: Osiyo mamlakatlarida ta'zim qilish odob-axloq qoidalarining bir turi hisoblanadi.

example: If something is exclusive, it is expensive and only for rich people.
type: The golf course was so exclusive that most people hadn’t even heard of it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa eksklyuziv bo'lsa, u qimmat va faqat boy odamlar uchun.
column14: Golf maydoni shu qadar eksklyuziv ediki, ko'pchilik bu haqda hatto eshitmagan.

example: Freight is a set of items carried on a train, boat, or airplane.
type: Trade ships only carried valuable freight like silk and spices.
example_tr: Yuk tashish - bu poezd, qayiq yoki samolyotda tashiladigan narsalar to'plami.
column14: Savdo kemalari faqat ipak va ziravorlar kabi qimmatbaho yuklarni tashigan.

example: A garment is a piece of clothing.
type: The business man had all of his garments cleaned before the important meeting.
example_tr: Kiyim - bu kiyimning bir qismi.
column14: Ishbilarmon muhim uchrashuv oldidan barcha kiyimlarini tozalagan.

example: Insomnia is a condition in which a person has difficulty sleeping.
type: Nate’s insomnia prevented him from getting enough rest.
example_tr: Uyqusizlik - bu odamning uxlashi qiyin bo'lgan holat.
column14: Neytning uyqusizligi uning etarlicha dam olishiga to'sqinlik qildi.

example: Intuitive is knowing about something without naturally having support or proof.
type: Rhonda had an intuitive feeling that Shane wasn't coming to school today.
example_tr: Intuitiv - biror narsa haqida tabiiy ravishda qo'llab-quvvatlash yoki isbotsiz bilish.
column14: Ronda Sheyn bugun maktabga kelmayotganini intuitiv his qildi.

example: If something is liable to happen, it is very likely that it will happen.
type: During the summer months, hikers in the forest are liable to see deer and elk.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sodir bo'lishi mumkin bo'lsa, bu sodir bo'lishi ehtimoli katta.
column14: Yoz oylarida o'rmon bo'ylab sayyohlar kiyik va elkalarni ko'rishlari mumkin.

example: To obsess about something means to think about it all of the time.
type: After watching the Star Wars movies, Ike obsessed about becoming a Jedi.
example_tr: Biror narsa haqida o'ylash har doim bu haqda o'ylashni anglatadi.
column14: "Yulduzli urushlar" filmlarini tomosha qilgandan so'ng, Ayk Jedi bo'lishni orzu qildi.

example: When something is overboard, it is over the side of a boat and in the water.
type: Tom and Gary slipped on the wet floor and fell overboard.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa bortga tushib qolsa, u qayiqning chetida va suvda bo'ladi.
column14: Tom va Gari ho'l polda sirpanib ketishdi va bortga qulashdi.

example: A premium is a payment that is higher than average.
type: Tony paid for premium gas because it made his car run the best.
example_tr: Mukofot - bu o'rtacha qiymatdan yuqori bo'lgan to'lov.
column14: Toni premium gaz uchun pul to'ladi, chunki bu uning mashinasini eng yaxshi ishlashiga olib keldi.
