example: A privilege is a special right given to only a certain person or group of people.
type: Only the best employee had the privilege of parking in that spot.
example_tr: Imtiyoz - bu faqat ma'lum bir shaxs yoki odamlar guruhiga beriladigan maxsus huquqdir.
column14: Faqat eng yaxshi xodim o'sha joyda to'xtash huquqiga ega edi.

example: To propel something means to push or move it somewhere.
type: The strong wind propelled the leaf through the air and across the street.
example_tr: Biror narsani harakatga keltirish, uni biron joyga surish yoki ko'chirishni anglatadi.
column14: Kuchli shamol bargni havoda va ko'cha bo'ylab harakatlantirdi.

example: To socialize is to have a good time with people.
type: I like to socialize with my classmates after school.
example_tr: Ijtimoiy aloqa - bu odamlar bilan yaxshi vaqt o'tkazish.
column14: Men maktabdan keyin sinfdoshlarim bilan muloqot qilishni yaxshi ko'raman.

example: To suppress something means to prevent it from happening.
type: She suppressed her urge to scream because she didn’t want to be noticed.
example_tr: Biror narsani bostirish uning sodir bo'lishining oldini olishni anglatadi.
column14: U baqirish istagini bosdi, chunki unga e'tibor berishni xohlamadi.

example: A tram is a vehicle like a streetcar that runs on electricity above ground.
type: I took the tram to Eighth Avenue.
example_tr: Tramvay yer ustidagi elektr energiyasi bilan ishlaydigan tramvay kabi transport vositasidir.
column14: Men tramvayda Sakkizinchi avenyugacha bordim.

example: To unsettle someone means to make them anxious or worried.
type: The dark clouds in the sky unsettled Beth.
example_tr: Biror kishini bezovta qilish, uni tashvishga solish yoki tashvishga solishni anglatadi.
column14: Osmondagi qora bulutlar Betni bezovta qildi.

example: To warp means to become bent into the wrong shape.
type: The woman put the clock above the fireplace, and the heat warped it.
example_tr: Bukish noto'g'ri shaklga egilish demakdir.
column14: Ayol soatni kamin ustiga qo'ydi va issiqlik uni buzib tashladi.

example: An artery is a tube that takes blood from the heart to the rest of the body.
type: Eating healthily keeps your arteries clean, so biocd can flow with ease.
example_tr: Arteriya qonni yurakdan tananing qolgan qismiga olib boradigan naychadir.
column14: Sog'lom ovqatlanish arteriyalaringizni toza tutadi, shuning uchun biocd osonlik bilan oqishi mumkin.

example: Deterioration is the act of becoming worse.
type: The lack of care led to the deterioration of the house.
example_tr: Buzilish - bu yomonlashish harakati.
column14: G'amxo'rlikning etishmasligi uyning yomonlashishiga olib keldi.

example: If something or someone is elusive, they are hard to find.
type: The elusive fish only came out at night.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir qiyin bo'lsa, ularni topish qiyin.
column14: Tushunmaydigan baliq faqat tunda chiqdi.

example: To forage means to look around for food.
type: Many animals hide food in the fall since little can be foraged in winter.
example_tr: Oziq-ovqat izlash, atrofdan oziq-ovqat izlashni anglatadi.
column14: Ko'pgina hayvonlar kuzda ovqatni yashirishadi, chunki qishda ozgina ozuqa olish mumkin.

example: To impede something means to keep it from moving or going forward.
type: The barrier impeded our ability to get closer to the building.
example_tr: Biror narsaga xalaqit berish, uning harakatlanishidan yoki oldinga siljishidan to'xtatish demakdir.
column14: To'siq bizning binoga yaqinlashishimizga to'sqinlik qildi.

example: To induce something means to make it happen.
type: Running without good shoes may induce leg pain.
example_tr: Biror narsani rag'batlantirish, uni amalga oshirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yaxshi poyabzalsiz yugurish oyoq og'rig'iga olib kelishi mumkin.

example: If two things are inseparable, they can’t be separated.
type: Denise and Diana have been inseparable since they first met.
example_tr: Agar ikkita narsa ajralmas bo'lsa, ularni ajratib bo'lmaydi.
column14: Denis va Diana birinchi uchrashganlaridan beri ajralmas edi.

example: If something is invalid, it is not correct.
type: The way to winning debates is to avoid invalid arguments.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noto'g'ri bo'lsa, u to'g'ri emas.
column14: Munozaralarda g'alaba qozonishning yo'li noto'g'ri bahslardan qochishdir.

example: To magnify something means to make it look bigger than it really is.
type: Astronomers use telescopes to magnify far-away stars.
example_tr: Biror narsani kattalashtirish, uni avvalgisidan kattaroq qilish demakdir.
column14: Astronomlar uzoqdagi yulduzlarni kattalashtirish uchun teleskoplardan foydalanadilar.

example: The mainstream is a group of ideas that are considered normal and accepted.
type: Before punk rock music became part of the mainstream, only a few people liked it.
example_tr: Asosiy oqim - bu normal hisoblangan va qabul qilingan g'oyalar guruhi.
column14: Pank-rok musiqasi asosiy oqimning bir qismi bo'lishidan oldin, uni faqat bir nechta odam yoqtirardi.

example: A microbe is a very small living thing that often makes people sick.
type: The first step in curing a disease is finding the microbe that causes the disease.
example_tr: Mikrob - bu odamlarni tez-tez kasal qiladigan juda kichik tirik mavjudot.
column14: Kasallikni davolashda birinchi qadam kasallikni keltirib chiqaradigan mikrobni topishdir.

example: If something is negligible, it is extremely small and not important.
type: The amount she owed was negligible. It was less than ten cents.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ahamiyatsiz bo'lsa, u juda kichik va muhim emas.
column14: Uning qarzi arzimas edi. Bu o'n sentdan kam edi.

example: Paralysis is the loss of the ability to move all or part of your body.
type: His paralysis meant that he had to use a wheelchair to get around.
example_tr: Falaj - bu tanangizning butun yoki bir qismini harakatlantirish qobiliyatini yo'qotish.
column14: Uning falaj bo'lishi u aylanib o'tish uchun nogironlar aravachasidan foydalanishi kerakligini anglatardi.

example: A pest is an animal or insect that hurts plants or food.
type: Many farmers put up scarecrows to keep pests off of their corn.
example_tr: Zararkunanda o'simliklar yoki oziq-ovqatlarga zarar etkazadigan hayvon yoki hasharotdir.
column14: Ko'pgina fermerlar makkajo'xori zararkunandalaridan himoya qilish uchun qo'rquv qo'yishadi.

example: To prevail means to be accepted or very common.
type: Unfortunately, injustice still prevails in the country’s court system.
example_tr: G'alaba qozonish, qabul qilinish yoki juda keng tarqalgan degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Afsuski, mamlakat sud tizimida hamon adolatsizlik hukm surmoqda.

example: Respiration is the act of breathing.
type: Artificial respiration is the best thing to do if someone stops breathing.
example_tr: Nafas olish - bu nafas olish harakati.
column14: Agar kimdir nafas olishni to'xtatsa, sun'iy nafas olish eng yaxshisidir.

example: To rupture means to tear or burst open.
type: Sarah put too much water into the balloon, and it ruptured.
example_tr: Yirtilish, yirtib tashlash yoki yorilish degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Sara sharga juda ko'p suv quydi va u yorilib ketdi.

example: If something or someone is savage, they are very violent or cruel.
type: Wild animals are very savage when defending their babies.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir vahshiy bo'lsa, ular juda zo'ravon yoki shafqatsiz.
column14: Yovvoyi hayvonlar o'z chaqaloqlarini himoya qilishda juda vahshiy.

example: To stun someone means to make them unable to speak due to surprise or shock.
type: Tim fell off the swing and was too stunned to cry.
example_tr: Biror kishini hayratda qoldirish, hayrat yoki zarba tufayli uni gapira olmasligini anglatadi.
column14: Tim belanchakdan yiqilib, hayratda qoldi va yig'lay olmadi.

example: If one is susceptible to something like disease, they are easily harmed by it.
type: Not eating enough vegetables makes you more susceptible to getting sick.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi kasallik kabi biror narsaga moyil bo'lsa, u osonlikcha zarar ko'radi.
column14: Sabzavotlarni etarli darajada iste'mol qilmaslik sizni kasallanishga ko'proq moyil qiladi.

example: To accumulate something is to collect a lot of it over time.
type: The mail accumulated in their mailbox while they were on vacation.
example_tr: Biror narsani to'plash - vaqt o'tishi bilan ko'p yig'ish.
column14: Ular ta'tilda bo'lganlarida pochta qutilarida to'plangan.

example: When something is aerial, it relates to being in the air or flying.
type: The aerial photographer took pictures from the air balloon.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa havoda bo'lsa, bu havoda bo'lish yoki uchish bilan bog'liq.
column14: Aerofotosuratchi havo sharidan suratga oldi.

example: An apparatus is a device used for a particular purpose.
type: The campers had an apparatus that showed them their exact location.
example_tr: Uskuna - bu ma'lum bir maqsadda ishlatiladigan qurilma.
column14: Lagerchilarda ularning aniq joylashuvini ko'rsatadigan apparat bor edi.

example: An avalanche is a large amount of snow, ice, and rock falling off a mountain.
type: The avalanche destroyed the mountain village.
example_tr: Ko'chki - tog'dan ko'p miqdorda qor, muz va toshlarning tushishi.
column14: Ko‘chki tog‘li qishloqni vayron qilgan.

example: Consistency is the state of always behaving in the same way.
type: Her consistency in archery meant that our team had a chance to win.
example_tr: Mustahkamlik - bu har doim bir xil yo'l tutish holati.
column14: Uning kamondan otishdagi barqarorligi jamoamizda g‘alaba qozonish imkoniyatini ko‘rsatdi.

example: Convection is the flow of hot air through gas or liquid.
type: The weather changed because of convection in the atmosphere.
example_tr: Konvektsiya - bu gaz yoki suyuqlik orqali issiq havo oqimi.
column14: Atmosferadagi konvektsiya tufayli ob-havo o'zgardi.

example: To discharge someone is to allow them to leave from a place, usually a hospital.
type: He was discharged from the hospital after three days.
example_tr: Biror kishini bo'shatish - bu unga joydan, odatda kasalxonadan chiqib ketishga ruxsat berishdir.
column14: U uch kundan keyin kasalxonadan chiqdi.

example: When something is intact, it is complete and not damaged.
type: Despite being over ten years old, my father’s model ship is still intact.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa buzilmagan bo'lsa, u to'liq va shikastlanmagan.
column14: O'n yoshdan oshganiga qaramay, otamning kema modeli hali ham buzilmagan.

example: When a person is mortal, they cannot live forever.
type: All people are mortal.
example_tr: Inson o'lgan bo'lsa, u abadiy yashay olmaydi.
column14: Hamma odamlar o'likdir.

example: An omen is a sign of what will happen in the future.
type: He thought that seeing a black cat in the street was an omen of bad luck.
example_tr: Omen - kelajakda nima sodir bo'lishining belgisi.
column14: U ko'chada qora mushukni ko'rish - omadsizlik belgisi, deb o'yladi.

example: When the sky is overcast, it is full of clouds and is not sunny.
type: The sky was overcast in the morning, but by noon it was bright again.
example_tr: Osmon bulutli bo'lsa, u bulutlarga to'la va quyoshli emas.
column14: Ertalab osmon bulutli edi, lekin tushga yaqin yana yorishib ketdi.

example: When something is poignant, it causes a very strong feeling of sadness.
type: The girls cried at the end of the poignant movie.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'tkir bo'lsa, u juda kuchli qayg'u tuyg'usini keltirib chiqaradi.
column14: Qizlar achchiq film oxirida yig'lashdi.

example: A ranger is a person who protects the forest or parks.
type: Peter wanted to be a ranger because he liked spending time outside.
example_tr: Qo'riqchi - o'rmon yoki bog'larni qo'riqlovchi shaxs.
column14: Piter inspektor bo'lishni xohladi, chunki u tashqarida vaqt o'tkazishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: Rubble is piles of broken stone and wood created after a building is destroyed.
type: There was rubble all over the city after the earthquake.
example_tr: Moloz - bu bino vayron bo'lganidan keyin hosil bo'lgan singan tosh va yog'och qoziqlari.
column14: Zilziladan keyin butun shaharda vayronalar bor edi.

example: To seclude someone means to keep them away from other people.
type: She was secluded on an island for over a year.
example_tr: Biror kishini yolg'izlash uni boshqa odamlardan uzoqlashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: U bir yildan ortiq vaqt davomida orolda tanho edi.

example: lf something moves sideways, then it moves to or from the side.
type: Jim turned sideways in order to slow down and stop his snowboard.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yon tomonga harakat qilsa, u yon tomonga yoki yon tomonga harakat qiladi.
column14: Jim snoubordni sekinlashtirish va to'xtatish uchun yon tomonga o'girildi.

example: To sob is to cry loudly.
type: I sobbed when my youngest daughter got married.
example_tr: Yig'lash - baland ovozda yig'lash.
column14: Kichik qizim turmushga chiqqanida yig‘lab yubordim.

example: When something or someone is sober, they are serious and calm.
type: After the funeral, everybody felt very sober.
example_tr: Biror narsa yoki kimdir hushyor bo'lsa, ular jiddiy va xotirjam bo'lishadi.
column14: Dafn marosimidan keyin hamma o'zini juda hushyor his qildi.

example: A speck is a very small mark or amount.
type: A speck of blood appeared where the mosquito bit him.
example_tr: Doza - bu juda kichik belgi yoki miqdor.
column14: Chivin tishlagan joyida qon parchasi paydo bo'ldi.

example: An upbringing is the way that someone is taught to behave by their parents.
type: He had a strict upbringing and was never allowed to watch television.
example_tr: Tarbiya - bu ota-onasi tomonidan o'zini tutishga o'rgatish usuli.
column14: U qattiq tarbiya olgan va televizor ko'rishga ruxsat berilmagan.

example: To advocate a plan or idea is to support or suggest it in public.
type: The group advocated increased spending on education and schools.
example_tr: Reja yoki g'oyani qo'llab-quvvatlash, uni omma oldida qo'llab-quvvatlash yoki taklif qilishdir.
column14: Guruh ta'lim va maktablarga sarflanadigan xarajatlarni oshirish tarafdori edi.

example: To authorize something means to give permission for it.
type: The mayor authorized the construction of a new statue in the park.
example_tr: Biror narsaga ruxsat berish, unga ruxsat berish demakdir.
column14: Shahar hokimi bog‘da yangi haykal o‘rnatishga ruxsat berdi.

example: A civilian is someone who is not in the military.
type: It was Todd's job to keep civilians from entering the army facility.
example_tr: Fuqaro - bu harbiy xizmatda bo'lmagan kishi.
column14: Toddning vazifasi tinch aholining armiya inshootiga kirishiga yo‘l qo‘ymaslik edi.

example: A commodity is something that can be bought or sold.
type: Fran’s uncle made most of his money trading commodities.
example_tr: Tovar - bu sotib olinadigan yoki sotiladigan narsa.
column14: Franning amakisi ko'p pul savdosi bilan shug'ullangan.

example: A conquest is an event by which one country takes over another country.
type: After the conquest, the people of the small city had no freedom.
example_tr: Bosqinchilik - bu bir davlatning boshqa davlatni egallashi bilan bog'liq hodisa.
column14: Bosqindan keyin kichik shahar aholisi erkinlikka ega emas edi.

example: To disclose something means to tell it to someone else.
type: John came home late, so he had to disclose his activities to his wife.
example_tr: Biror narsani oshkor qilish uni boshqa birovga aytishni anglatadi.
column14: Jon uyga kech keldi, shuning uchun u o'z faoliyatini xotiniga oshkor qilishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: The dynamics of a situation are the way that parts of it affect each other.
type: A good psychologist needs to know a lot about the dynamics of brain disorders.
example_tr: Vaziyatning dinamikasi - uning qismlari bir-biriga ta'sir qilish usuli.
column14: Yaxshi psixolog miya buzilishlarining dinamikasi haqida ko'p narsalarni bilishi kerak.

example: To enroll in something is to put one’s name on a list as a member of a group.
type: The students had to enroll in the class one semester in advance.
example_tr: Biror narsaga ro'yxatdan o'tish - bu o'z ismini guruh a'zosi sifatida ro'yxatga kiritish.
column14: Talabalar sinfga bir semestr oldin yozilishi kerak edi.

example: When someone is envious, they want something that another person has.
type: They were envious of their neighbor’s front yard.
example_tr: Biror kishi hasad qilsa, u boshqa odamda bo'lgan narsani xohlaydi.
column14: Ular qo'shnisining old hovlisiga havas qilishdi.

example: Euphoria is a feeling of extreme happiness.
type: The athlete felt euphoria after he won the important game.
example_tr: Eyforiya - bu haddan tashqari baxt hissi.
column14: Sportchi muhim o'yinda g'alaba qozonganidan keyin eyforiyani his qildi.

example: When something is festive, it is happy and related to a party or celebration.
type: Dean's favorite part of Christmas is the festive clothing that people wear.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tantanali bo'lsa, u baxtli va ziyofat yoki bayram bilan bog'liq.
column14: Dinning Rojdestvo bayramining eng sevimli qismi bu odamlar kiyadigan bayram kiyimidir.

example: When someone is jolly, they are cheerful and happy.
type: My grandmother's jolly attitude always made me smile.
example_tr: Biror kishi quvnoq bo'lsa, u quvnoq va baxtli bo'ladi.
column14: Buvimning xushchaqchaq munosabati meni doim tabassum qilib turardi.

example: Lentils are very small beans that people cook and eat.
type: Danni made her special soup with lentils when her husband was sick.
example_tr: Yasmiq - odamlar pishiradigan va iste'mol qiladigan juda kichik loviya.
column14: Danni eri kasal bo'lganida yasmiq bilan maxsus sho'rva tayyorladi.

example: To marshal a group means to assemble them in order.
type: The students were marshaled outside and put into groups.
example_tr: Guruhni marshal qilish ularni tartibda yig'ishni anglatadi.
column14: Talabalar tashqariga chiqarildi va guruhlarga bo'lindi.

example: Morale is the amount of hope that people have during a difficult situation.
type: To improve our family’s morale, mom suggested going on a picnic.
example_tr: Ma'naviyat - bu qiyin vaziyatda odamlarning umidlari miqdori.
column14: Oilamizning ruhiy holatini yaxshilash uchun onam piknikga borishni taklif qildi.

example: A prophecy is a prediction about what will happen in the future.
type: Some people believe that prophecies are actually true.
example_tr: Bashorat - bu kelajakda nima bo'lishini bashorat qilish.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar bashoratlarning haqiqat ekanligiga ishonishadi.

example: A sage is someone who is very wise.
type: Hal always visited the local sage for help with love.
example_tr: Donishmand - bu juda dono odam.
column14: Hal har doim sevgi bilan yordam so'rab mahalliy adibga tashrif buyurgan.

example: A senate is a part of the government in some countries.
type: Everybody liked Caroline and chose her to speak for them in the senate.
example_tr: Senat ayrim mamlakatlarda hukumat tarkibiga kiradi.
column14: Hamma Karolinni yaxshi ko'rardi va uni senatda o'zlari uchun gapirish uchun tanladilar.

example: A sentiment is an opinion based on your feelings.
type: Tess told everyone at the table her sentiments about eating meat.
example_tr: Tuyg'u - bu sizning his-tuyg'ularingizga asoslangan fikr.
column14: Tess stolda o'tirganlarning barchasiga go'sht iste'mol qilish haqidagi his-tuyg'ularini aytdi.

example: Unrest is a state of anger about something among the people in a place.
type: High taxes caused much of the unrest that led to the Revolutionary War.
example_tr: Noto'g'rilik - biror joyda odamlarning biror narsadan g'azablanish holati.
column14: Yuqori soliqlar inqilobiy urushga olib kelgan ko'plab tartibsizliklarga sabab bo'ldi.

example: To adorn something means to make it more beautiful by decorating it.
type: Small glass beads adorned the vase.
example_tr: Biror narsani bezash, uni bezash orqali yanada chiroyli qilish demakdir.
column14: Kichkina shisha boncuklar vaza bilan bezatilgan.

example: Bliss is a state of complete happiness.
type: Every time he sees his girlfriend, he feels a sense of bliss.
example_tr: Baxt - bu to'liq baxt holati.
column14: Har safar qiz do'stini ko'rganida, u baxt hissini his qiladi.

example: An A butler is the most important male servant in a wealthy house.
type: Whenever he needed something, he rang a bell, and the butler appeared.
example_tr: Butler - badavlat xonadondagi eng muhim erkak xizmatkor.
column14: Qachonki unga biror narsa kerak bo‘lsa, qo‘ng‘iroq chalar, uy sotuvchisi paydo bo‘lardi.

example: Acramp is a strong pain caused by a muscle after a lot of physical use.
type: After the marathon, Jenny got a terrible cramp in her calf muscle.
example_tr: Akramp - bu ko'p jismoniy foydalanishdan keyin mushakdan kelib chiqqan kuchli og'riq.
column14: Marafondan keyin Jenni buzoq mushaklarida dahshatli kramp paydo bo'ldi.

example: When a building is dilapidated, it is old and in bad condition.
type: Paint peeled off of the old dilapidated apartment building.
example_tr: Bino vayron bo'lsa, u eski va yomon ahvolda bo'ladi.
column14: Eski vayronaga aylangan turar-joy binosining bo'yog'i tozalangan.

example: To evoke a memory or emotion means to make it occur.
type: The picture evoked memories of when grandmother was a girl.
example_tr: Xotira yoki his-tuyg'uni uyg'otish uni amalga oshirishni anglatadi.
column14: Rasm buvining qiz bo'lgan paytlari haqidagi xotiralarni uyg'otdi.

example: A farewell is an instance of saying goodbye or a way to say it.
type: She got on the plane after we said our farewells.
example_tr: Vidolashuv - bu xayrlashish misoli yoki uni aytish usuli.
column14: Biz xayrlashganimizdan keyin u samolyotga chiqdi.

example: A faucet is a device that controls the flow of a liquid or gas.
type: Turn off the faucet when you are done brushing your teeth.
example_tr: Kran - bu suyuqlik yoki gaz oqimini boshqaradigan qurilma.
column14: Tishlaringizni yuvib bo'lgach, kranni o'chiring.

example: Filth is a large amount of dirt or dirty things that disgust you.
type: There was tons of filth and trash on the shore of the river.
example_tr: Nopoklik - sizni jirkanch qiladigan katta miqdordagi axloqsizlik yoki iflos narsalar.
column14: Daryo qirg'og'ida tonnalab iflos va axlat bor edi.

example: A flaw is a mistake in something that causes it to be less effective or correct.
type: We discovered a major flaw in the metal chain.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu uning samarasiz yoki to'g'ri bo'lishiga olib keladigan narsadagi xato.
column14: Biz metall zanjirda katta kamchilikni topdik.

example: To grin means to smile broadly.
type: That joke makes me grin every time | hear it.
example_tr: Jilmayish keng tabassum qilish demakdir.
column14: O'sha hazil meni har safar kulimsiradi | eshit.

example: Housekeeping is the maintenance of a house or an establishment like a hotel.
type: Housekeeping is not much fun, but it has to be done.
example_tr: Uy xo'jaligi - bu uy yoki mehmonxona kabi muassasani saqlash.
column14: Uyni tozalash unchalik qiziq emas, lekin buni qilish kerak.

example: Amound of something is a large pile of it.
type: There was a mound of clothes on the messy teenager's floor.
example_tr: Biror narsaning miqdori uning katta uyumidir.
column14: Betartib o‘smirning polida to‘plangan kiyimlar bor edi.

example: When a body part is numb, it does not have any feeling.
type: After holding my hand under the icy water, my fingers went numb.
example_tr: Agar tana a'zosi xiralashgan bo'lsa, unda hech qanday tuyg'u bo'lmaydi.
column14: Qo‘limni muzdek suv ostida tutganimdan so‘ng barmoqlarim qotib qoldi.

example: When people are reckless, they act in an unsafe way.
type: The reckless driver posed a threat to everyone else on the road.
example_tr: Odamlar ehtiyotsiz bo'lsa, ular xavfli yo'l bilan harakat qilishadi.
column14: Ehtiyotsiz haydovchi yo'lda qolgan barchaga xavf tug'dirdi.

example: Slate is a dark grey rock that can easily be split into layers.
type: The roof of the church was made of slate.
example_tr: Slate - qatlamlarga osongina bo'linadigan quyuq kulrang tosh.
column14: Cherkovning tomi shiferdan qilingan.

example: Astool is a seat with legs but no support for a person’s arms and back.
type: I don't find stools very comfortable to sit on.
example_tr: Astool - oyoqlari bo'lgan o'rindiq, lekin odamning qo'llari va orqasi uchun hech qanday yordam yo'q.
column14: Menga o‘tirish uchun taburelar unchalik qulay emas.

example: Atestament to something shows that it exists or is true.
type: The beautiful performance was a testament to the singer’s natural talents.
example_tr: Biror narsaga guvohlik uning mavjudligini yoki haqiqatligini ko'rsatadi.
column14: Chiroyli ijro xonandaning tabiiy iste'dodidan dalolat berdi.

example: Timber is wood that is used for building houses and making furniture.
type: Trees in this area are grown specifically to be used for timber.
example_tr: Yog'och - bu uy qurish va mebel ishlab chiqarish uchun ishlatiladigan yog'och.
column14: Bu hududdagi daraxtlar yog'och uchun maxsus o'stiriladi.

example: Avalve is a device attached to a pipe that controls the flow of liquid or air.
type: The mechanic removed the dirt to clear the engine valve.
example_tr: Avalve - suyuqlik yoki havo oqimini boshqaradigan quvurga biriktirilgan qurilma.
column14: Mexanik dvigatel klapanini tozalash uchun kirni olib tashladi.

example: To certify something means to confirm that its results are true.
type: The photograph on her passport certified that she was indeed jolene Sawyer.
example_tr: Biror narsani tasdiqlash, uning natijalari haqiqat ekanligini tasdiqlash demakdir.
column14: Uning pasportidagi fotosurat uning haqiqatan ham Jolen Soyer ekanligini tasdiqlaydi.

example: To collaborate means to work together on something.
type: When they collaborated, they managed to finish their chores early.
example_tr: Hamkorlik biror narsa ustida birgalikda ishlashni anglatadi.
column14: Hamkorlik qilganlarida, ular uy ishlarini erta tugatishga muvaffaq bo'lishdi.

example: To compile things means to collect a variety of them into a group.
type: She compiled a list of people who she wanted to attend her birthday party.
example_tr: Narsalarni jamlash, ularning xilma-xilligini guruhga yig'ishni anglatadi.
column14: U tug'ilgan kunida qatnashmoqchi bo'lgan odamlar ro'yxatini tuzdi.

example: To counteract something means to act against it in order to reduce or stop it.
type: Medicine is supposed to counteract illnesses.
example_tr: Biror narsaga qarshi turish, uni kamaytirish yoki to'xtatish uchun unga qarshi harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Tibbiyot kasalliklarga qarshi turishi kerak.

example: To curb something means to prevent it from happening or increasing.
type: She curbed her anger by listening to a relaxing song.
example_tr: Biror narsani jilovlash, uning sodir bo'lishi yoki ko'payishining oldini olishni anglatadi.
column14: U g‘azabini tinchlantiruvchi qo‘shiq tinglab bosdi.

example: To diagnose someone means to identify the medical condition they have.
type: Several of the children were diagnosed with the flu.
example_tr: Biror kishiga tashxis qo'yish, uning tibbiy holatini aniqlashni anglatadi.
column14: Bir qancha bolalarda gripp aniqlangan.

example: To enact something means to make it into a law.
type: The council enacted a law that would only allow buses to drive downtown.
example_tr: Biror narsani qabul qilish, uni qonunga aylantirish demakdir.
column14: Kengash avtobuslarning faqat shahar markazida harakatlanishiga ruxsat beruvchi qonunni qabul qildi.

example: A federation is a group of states or businesses working for a common cause.
type: The United Nations is a federation designed to prevent war, disease, and famine.
example_tr: Federatsiya - bu umumiy maqsad uchun ishlaydigan davlatlar yoki korxonalar guruhi.
column14: Birlashgan Millatlar Tashkiloti urush, kasallik va ocharchilikning oldini olish uchun tuzilgan federatsiyadir.

example: If something is gross, then it is disgusting.
type: The food was so gross that the dog couldn’t eat it without feeling sick.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa qo'pol bo'lsa, u jirkanchdir.
column14: Oziq-ovqat shunchalik qo'pol ediki, it kasal bo'lmasdan ovqatlana olmadi.

example: If something is humane, then it is good and kind.
type: Helping build homes for poor people is very humane.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa insoniy bo'lsa, u yaxshi va mehribondir.
column14: Kambag'allar uchun uy qurishga yordam berish juda insonparvarlikdir.

example: If something is intolerable, then it is so bad that people cannot bear it.
type: The weather was so intolerable that I had to put on my warmest clothes.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa chidab bo'lmas bo'lsa, u shunchalik yomonki, odamlar bunga chiday olmaydi.
column14: Ob-havo shu qadar chidab bo'lmas ediki, men eng issiq kiyimlarimni kiyishga majbur bo'ldim.

example: If someone is needy, they are very poor.
type: After he lost his job, he became very needy.
example_tr: Agar kimdir muhtoj bo'lsa, u juda kambag'aldir.
column14: Ishdan ayrilgach, u juda muhtoj bo'lib qoldi.

example: The onset of something unpleasant is the beginning of it.
type: At the onset of the battle, the enemy wasn’t prepared for such a large attack.
example_tr: Noxush narsaning boshlanishi uning boshlanishidir.
column14: Jang boshida dushman bunday katta hujumga tayyor emas edi.

example: To pledge means to make a promise to do something.
type: Her mother pledged that she would find her daughter’s lost kitten.
example_tr: Garov qilish - biror narsa qilishga va'da berishni anglatadi.
column14: Onasi qizining yo'qolgan mushukchasini topishga va'da berdi.

example: To prohibit something means to not allow it.
type: She prohibited the students from speaking until their work was done.
example_tr: Biror narsani taqiqlash, unga ruxsat bermaslik demakdir.
column14: U talabalarga ish tugaguniga qadar gapirishni taqiqladi.

example: A rash is an infected area of the skin with redness, bumps, itching, or dryness.
type: The new perfume left a horrible rash on my skin.
example_tr: Toshma - terining qizarishi, shishishi, qichishi yoki quruqligi bilan kasallangan hududi.
column14: Yangi parfyum terimda dahshatli toshma qoldirdi.

example: To render something means to make it become something else.
type: His report was rendered unimportant by the release of new information.
example_tr: Biror narsani ko'rsatish, uni boshqa narsaga aylantirish demakdir.
column14: Uning hisoboti yangi ma'lumotlarning e'lon qilinishi bilan ahamiyatsiz bo'lib qoldi.

example: Smallpox is a disease that causes tiny bumps on the skin and high fevers.
type: When she saw the tiny bumps, she thought her son might have smallpox.
example_tr: Chechak - terida mayda shishlar va yuqori isitmani keltirib chiqaradigan kasallik.
column14: Kichkina shishlarni ko'rib, u o'g'li chechak bilan kasallangan bo'lishi mumkin deb o'yladi.

example: To transmit something means to pass it from one person or place to another.
type: The radio tower transmits a signal to all the radios in a 20-kilometer radius.
example_tr: Biror narsani uzatish, uni bir kishidan yoki joydan boshqasiga o'tkazishni anglatadi.
column14: Radiominora 20 kilometr radiusdagi barcha radiolarga signal uzatadi.

example: To vow means to make a promise to do something.
type: Before they are allowed to work, all senators must vow to never accept bribes.
example_tr: Nazr qilish, biror narsa qilishga va'da berishni anglatadi.
column14: Ishga ruxsat berishdan oldin barcha senatorlar hech qachon pora olmaslikka va'da berishlari kerak.

example: Camouflage is something used to hide people and things.
type: The green and brown camouflage was best used for hiding in forests and jungles.
example_tr: Kamuflyaj - odamlar va narsalarni yashirish uchun ishlatiladigan narsa.
column14: Yashil va jigarrang kamuflyaj o'rmonlar va o'rmonlarda yashirinish uchun eng yaxshi ishlatilgan.

example: To contemplate something means to think about it.
type: Mark took a moment to contemplate the math problem before solving it.
example_tr: Biror narsa haqida o'ylash, u haqida o'ylashni anglatadi.
column14: Mark matematika muammosini hal qilishdan oldin uning ustida o'ylashga vaqt ajratdi.

example: To contend with something means to struggle to overcome it.
type: Stacy had to contend with a learning disability throughout high school.
example_tr: Biror narsa bilan kurashish, uni engish uchun kurashish demakdir.
column14: Steysi o'rta maktab davomida o'rganishdagi nogironlik bilan kurashishga majbur bo'ldi.

example: A cot is a small portable bed.
type: At the camp, the boys’ cabin was lined with cots.
example_tr: Karyola - bu kichik ko'chma to'shak.
column14: Lagerda o'g'il bolalar kabinasi karyolalar bilan qoplangan.

example: To enlist means to join the military.
type: In their final year at school, the students were asked to enlist in the military.
example_tr: Ro'yxatga olish harbiy xizmatga kirishni anglatadi.
column14: Maktabning so‘nggi yilida o‘quvchilarni harbiy xizmatga chaqirishdi.

example: A frontier is a border between two regions or countries.
type: A fence was built along the frontier where the river curved.
example_tr: Chegara - bu ikki mintaqa yoki davlat o'rtasidagi chegara.
column14: Daryoning qiyshaygan joyida chegara bo'ylab panjara qurilgan.

example: A handbook is an item that gives specific information or instructions.
type: If you look at the handbook, it will tell you which wires to connect to the TV.
example_tr: Qo'llanma - bu aniq ma'lumot yoki ko'rsatmalar beradigan element.
column14: Agar siz qo'llanmani ko'rib chiqsangiz, u televizorga qaysi simlarni ulash kerakligini aytadi.

example: If someone is hesitant, then they are not sure or slow in acting or speaking.
type: Though he knew the answer, he was hesitant to say it because he might be wrong.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ikkilanayotgan bo'lsa, u harakat yoki gapirishda ishonchsiz yoki sekin emas.
column14: U javobni bilsa-da, aytishga ikkilanib qoldi, chunki u noto'g'ri bo'lishi mumkin edi.

example: If something is lush, then it is full of a variety of large, healthy plants.
type: The lush jungle was filled with plants, trees, and vines.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yam-yashil bo'lsa, unda u turli xil katta, sog'lom o'simliklar bilan to'la.
column14: Yam-yashil o'rmon o'simliklar, daraxtlar va toklarga to'la edi.

example: Marrow is the soft substance in the center of bones.
type: Dissolved marrow is a common ingredient in soups.
example_tr: Ilik suyaklar markazidagi yumshoq moddadir.
column14: Eritilgan ilik sho'rvalarning umumiy tarkibiy qismidir.

example: An outfit is a set of clothes worn together, often for a certain job or event.
type: Kelly’s new outfit made her look so glamourous.
example_tr: Kiyim - bu ko'pincha ma'lum bir ish yoki tadbir uchun birgalikda kiyiladigan kiyimlar to'plami.
column14: Kellining yangi kiyimi uni juda jozibali ko'rsatdi.

example: A paw is an animal's foot that has claws or soft bottoms.
type: The kitten cleaned its paws with its tongue.
example_tr: Panja - bu hayvonning panjasi yoki pastki qismi yumshoq.
column14: Mushukcha tili bilan panjalarini tozaladi.

example: To quiver means to tremble or shake.
type: The flame on the candle quivered whenever someone opened or closed a door.
example_tr: Tittirmoq, titroq, titroq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Sham ustidagi alanga kimdir eshikni ochsa yoki yopsa, titrar edi.

example: If something or someone is splendid, then they are very good.
type: From his head down to his shoes, his clothes looked splendid.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir ajoyib bo'lsa, ular juda yaxshi.
column14: Boshidan tortib tuflisiga qadar kiyimlari ajoyib ko'rinardi.

example: To stray means to go in a wrong direction and often become lost.
type: He found himself lost because he had strayed from the tour group.
example_tr: Adashish noto'g'ri yo'nalishga borishni va ko'pincha adashib qolishni anglatadi.
column14: U sayyohlik guruhidan uzoqlashgani uchun o'zini yo'qotib qo'ydi.

example: If something is substantial, then it is of great importance, size, or value.
type: The bank said that he owed it a substantial amount of money.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u katta ahamiyatga ega, o'lcham yoki qiymatga ega.
column14: Bank uning katta miqdorda qarzi borligini aytdi.

example: A torch is a stick with one end on fire that can be carried in order to give light.
type: He grabbed a piece of wood and stuck it in the fire in order to make a torch.
example_tr: Mash'al - bu yorug'lik berish uchun ko'tarilishi mumkin bo'lgan bir uchi olovli tayoq.
column14: U mash'al qilish uchun bir parcha yog'ochni olib, olovga qo'ydi.

example: A tract is a large area of land.
type: On the other side of the mountains was a long tract of forest.
example_tr: Trakt - bu katta er maydoni.
column14: Tog'larning narigi tomonida uzun o'rmon yo'llari bor edi.

example: A vigil is a period of watchful attention at night for a specific purpose.
type: He had a vigil in front of the tomb for three days.
example_tr: Hushyorlik - bu ma'lum bir maqsad uchun tunda hushyorlik davri.
column14: U qabr oldida uch kun hushyorlik qildi.

example: If someone is weary, then they are tired.
type: Jane was weary after a long day of work.
example_tr: Agar kimdir charchagan bo'lsa, demak u charchagan.
column14: Jeyn uzoq ish kunidan keyin charchagan edi.

example: To adhere means to act in the way that a rule or agreement says is right.
type: If the new employees wish to succeed, they must adhere to the boss’s rules.
example_tr: Qabul qilish, qoida yoki kelishuv to'g'ri deb aytilgan tarzda harakat qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Agar yangi xodimlar muvaffaqiyatga erishmoqchi bo'lsalar, ular boshliqning qoidalariga rioya qilishlari kerak.

example: To administer means to take responsibility for organizing something.
type: The teacher’s assistant will administer the test.
example_tr: Boshqaruv biror narsani tashkil qilish uchun mas'uliyatni o'z zimmasiga olishni anglatadi.
column14: Sinovni o'qituvchining yordamchisi boshqaradi.

example: When people are compassionate, they feel pity and sympathy for others.
type: The compassionate nurse tried to make the sick man feel comfortable.
example_tr: Odamlar rahm-shafqatli bo'lsa, ular boshqalarga rahm-shafqat va hamdardlik his qiladilar.
column14: Rahmdil hamshira kasal odamni qulay his qilishga harakat qildi.

example: To contaminate something means to put dirty or harmful chemicals into it.
type: The lake was contaminated when pollutants entered into the water.
example_tr: Biror narsani ifloslantirish, unga iflos yoki zararli kimyoviy moddalar qo'yish demakdir.
column14: Suvga ifloslantiruvchi moddalar tushganda ko'l ifloslangan.

example: A deficiency is a lack of something, especially something that is needed.
type: Your snack has a deficiency of any real nutrients.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu biror narsaning, ayniqsa zarur bo'lgan narsaning etishmasligi.
column14: Sizning gazakingiz har qanday haqiqiy ozuqa moddalarining etishmasligiga ega.

example: An epidemic is an outbreak of a disease that spreads quickly.
type: It was difficult to stop the flu epidemic.
example_tr: Epidemiya - tez tarqaladigan kasallikning tarqalishi.
column14: Gripp epidemiyasini to'xtatish qiyin edi.

example: A hazard is something that could be dangerous to a person’s health or safety.
type: Smoking cigarettes poses many health hazards.
example_tr: Xavf - bu inson salomatligi yoki xavfsizligi uchun xavfli bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan narsa.
column14: Chekish ko'plab sog'liq uchun xavf tug'diradi.

example: When something is imperative, it is extremely important and must be done.
type: It was imperative for him to find a job.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa majburiy bo'lsa, u juda muhim va bajarilishi kerak.
column14: Uning uchun ish topish juda muhim edi.

example: Intestines are tubes through which food passes after it leaves the stomach.
type: Whatever you eat goes into your intestines.
example_tr: Ichaklar - bu oshqozondan chiqqandan keyin ovqat o'tadigan naychalar.
column14: Siz nima iste'mol qilsangiz, ichaklaringizga kiradi.

example: To manifest means to make something visible or obvious.
type: The holiday season manifested joy in the children.
example_tr: Namoyon bo'lmoq nimanidir ko'rinadigan yoki ravshan qilish demakdir.
column14: Bayram bayrami bolalarda quvonchni namoyon etdi.

example: When something is metabolic, it relates to a person’s or animal’s metabolism.
type: People who have a low metabolic rate will gain weight.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa metabolik bo'lsa, u odam yoki hayvonning metabolizmiga bog'liq.
column14: Metabolizm darajasi past bo'lgan odamlar kilogramm berishadi.

example: When a place is overcrowded, it has too many people or things in it.
type: The lobby was overcrowded with people.
example_tr: Agar joy gavjum bo'lsa, unda juda ko'p odamlar yoki narsalar bo'ladi.
column14: Qabulxona odamlar bilan gavjum edi.

example: When something is paramount, it is more important than anything else.
type: The safety of passengers must be paramount when designing a car.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muhim bo'lsa, u hamma narsadan muhimroqdir.
column14: Avtomobilni loyihalashda yo'lovchilarning xavfsizligi birinchi o'rinda turishi kerak.

example: A practitioner is a doctor.
type: She made an appointment with the practitioner to treat her cough.
example_tr: Amaliyotchi - shifokor.
column14: U yo'talni davolash uchun amaliyotchi bilan uchrashdi.

example: The provision of something is the act of giving it to people in need or want.
type: That department is responsible for the provision of emergency supplies.
example_tr: Biror narsani ta'minlash - bu muhtoj yoki muhtoj odamlarga berish harakati.
column14: O'sha bo'lim favqulodda vaziyatlarni ta'minlash uchun javobgardir.

example: To replenish something means to make it full or complete again.
type: We planted nearly one hundred seeds to replenish the garden after the fire.
example_tr: Biror narsani to'ldirish, uni to'liq yoki to'ldirishni anglatadi.
column14: Olovdan keyin bog‘ni to‘ldirish uchun yuzga yaqin urug‘ ekdik.

example: When something is sterile, it is completely clean and free from germs.
type: The hospital room looked quite sterile.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa steril bo'lsa, u butunlay toza va mikroblardan xoli bo'ladi.
column14: Kasalxona xonasi juda steril ko'rinardi.

example: To upgrade something means to improve it or make it more efficient.
type: He upgraded to a real fancy car.
example_tr: Biror narsani yangilash, uni yaxshilash yoki samaraliroq qilish demakdir.
column14: U haqiqiy hashamatli mashinaga ko'tarildi.

example: When something is viable, it is capable of doing what it is intended to do.
type: Her method of solving the math problem seemed viable.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa hayotiy bo'lsa, u o'zi xohlagan narsani qilishga qodir.
column14: Uning matematika muammosini hal qilish usuli hayotiy tuyuldi.

example: When something is voluntary, it is done by choice but is not required.
type: Many people attended the voluntary boat safety class.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ixtiyoriy bo'lsa, u ixtiyoriy ravishda amalga oshiriladi, lekin talab qilinmaydi.
column14: Ko'p odamlar qayiq xavfsizligi bo'yicha ixtiyoriy darsda qatnashdilar.

example: If something is amid something else, then it is in the middle of it.
type: The bee was busily flying amid the flowers in the garden.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsaning o'rtasida bo'lsa, demak u uning o'rtasida.
column14: Asalari bog'dagi gullar orasidan ovora uchib yurardi.

example: If something happens backstage, it occurs behind a theater's stage.
type: After the show, the director went backstage and thanked the actors.
example_tr: Agar sahna orqasida biror narsa sodir bo'lsa, u teatr sahnasining orqasida sodir bo'ladi.
column14: Spektakldan so‘ng rejissyor sahna ortiga o‘tib, aktyorlarga minnatdorchilik bildirdi.

example: A billionaire is someone who has at least one billion dollars.
type: The sale of his inventions made the inventor a billionaire.
example_tr: Milliarder - bu kamida bir milliard dollarga ega bo'lgan odam.
column14: Uning ixtirolarini sotish ixtirochini milliarderga aylantirdi.

example: A brute is someone who behaves or looks like a violent animal.
type: My older brother can act like a brute when he doesn’t get his way.
example_tr: Shafqatsiz - zo'ravon hayvonga o'xshagan yoki o'zini tutadigan odam.
column14: Katta akam o'z yo'lini topmasa, shafqatsizlardek harakat qilishi mumkin.

example: If someone is clumsy, then they are awkward in handling things.
type: The businessman was clumsy and dropped his work files.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qo'pol bo'lsa, u narsalarni boshqarishda noqulay.
column14: Tadbirkor qo‘pol bo‘lib, ish fayllarini tashlab yubordi.

example: To collide with something means to hit into it while moving.
type: The two cars collided with each other because their drivers were not careful.
example_tr: Biror narsa bilan to'qnashuv harakatlanayotganda unga urish demakdir.
column14: Ikki mashina haydovchilari ehtiyot bo‘lmagani uchun o‘zaro to‘qnashib ketgan.

example: A culprit is someone who did a crime or other bad deed.
type: The police were still searching for the culprit from the robbery.
example_tr: Jinoyatchi - jinoyat yoki boshqa yomon ish qilgan shaxs.
column14: Politsiya hamon talonchilikda aybdorni qidirmoqda.

example: To evacuate means to leave a place of danger to a place of safety.
type: During the flood, many families were evacuated to higher ground.
example_tr: Evakuatsiya qilish xavfli joyni xavfsiz joyga qoldirishni anglatadi.
column14: Toshqin paytida ko'plab oilalar balandroq joylarga evakuatsiya qilingan.

example: If something is flammable, then it is able to catch on fire.
type: Be careful with that blanket near the candle. It is extremely flammable.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yonuvchan bo'lsa, u yonib ketishi mumkin.
column14: Sham yaqinidagi adyol bilan ehtiyot bo'ling. U nihoyatda yonuvchan.

example: A mob is a large crowd of people that often wants to cause violence.
type: The copier was destroyed by a mob of angry workers.
example_tr: Olomon - bu ko'pincha zo'ravonlik qilishni xohlaydigan katta olomon.
column14: Nusxa ko'chirish mashinasi g'azablangan ishchilar tomonidan vayron qilingan.

example: If something is premature, then it is done too early or before the proper time.
type: Mark's celebration was premature because the ball hadn't fallen in the hole.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa erta bo'lsa, u juda erta yoki to'g'ri vaqtdan oldin amalga oshiriladi.
column14: Markning bayrami erta edi, chunki to'p teshikka tushmagan edi.

example: To resent something means to have bad feelings about it.
type: She resented the fact that she had never been able to play an instrument.
example_tr: Biror narsadan xafa bo'lish, unga nisbatan yomon his-tuyg'ularga ega bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: U hech qachon cholg‘u chala olmaganidan ranjidi.

example: A satire is a work of art that uses humor and irony to make fun of something.
type: This book is a satire of what life was like in the army.
example_tr: Satira - biror narsani masxara qilish uchun hazil va kinoyadan foydalanadigan san'at asari.
column14: Bu kitob armiyadagi hayot qanday kechganligi haqidagi satiradir.

example: Scrutiny is the careful examination of something.
type: A scientist should always practice scrutiny with their work.
example_tr: Tekshirish - biror narsani sinchiklab tekshirish.
column14: Olim har doim o'z ishini tekshirishi kerak.

example: To segregate something means to place it in a group apart from other things.
type: In gym class, the children were segregated into two groups: boys and girls.
example_tr: Biror narsani ajratish, uni boshqa narsalardan alohida guruhga joylashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Sport zalida bolalar ikki guruhga bo'lingan: o'g'il bolalar va qizlar.

example: To subject someone to something means to force them to do or experience it.
type: The officers subjected everyone to a careful search before they left the plane.
example_tr: Biror kishini biror narsaga bo'ysundirish, uni majburlash yoki boshdan kechirishni anglatadi.
column14: Ofitserlar samolyotni tark etishdan oldin barchani sinchkovlik bilan tekshirishdi.

example: A tumult is a loud and confused noise made by a large crowd of people.
type: She couldn’t hear her friend over the tumult of the other excited guests.
example_tr: G‘ala-g‘ovur - bu katta olomon tomonidan chiqarilgan baland va chalkash shovqin.
column14: U boshqa hayajonlangan mehmonlarning shovqinidan do'stini eshita olmadi.

example: To underestimate something or someone means to think they are not important.
type: We lost the game because we underestimated the other team’s skill.
example_tr: Biror narsani yoki kimnidir kamsitish, ularni muhim emas deb o'ylashni anglatadi.
column14: Boshqa jamoaning mahoratini past baholaganimiz uchun o'yinni yutqazdik.

example: Uproar is loud noise caused by people who are very angry or upset.
type: The fans made a great uproar when their team lost the game.
example_tr: G'alayon - bu juda g'azablangan yoki xafa bo'lgan odamlar tomonidan paydo bo'ladigan baland shovqin.
column14: Jamoasi o‘yinda mag‘lub bo‘lgach, muxlislar katta shov-shuv ko‘tarishdi.

example: To accelerate means to increase in speed.
type: When he stepped on the gas pedal, the motorcycle accelerated.
example_tr: Tezlashtirish tezligini oshirishni anglatadi.
column14: U gaz pedalini bosganida, mototsikl tezlashdi.

example: If you do something anew, you do it again and in a different way.
type: Though he had failed his driving test, he decided to try it anew.
example_tr: Agar biror narsani yangidan qilsangiz, uni yana va boshqa yo'l bilan qilasiz.
column14: U haydash imtihonidan o'ta olmagan bo'lsa-da, u yana sinab ko'rishga qaror qildi.

example: A defect is a part of something that is wrong or missing.
type: All these bottles have a defect and must be sent back to the warehouse.
example_tr: Kamchilik - bu noto'g'ri yoki etishmayotgan narsaning bir qismi.
column14: Bu idishlarning barchasida nuqson bor va ularni omborga qaytarish kerak.

example: If something is dreary, then it is dull, dark, and lifeless.
type: After the fire, this section of forest is rather dreary.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa g'amgin bo'lsa, u zerikarli, qorong'i va jonsizdir.
column14: Yong'indan keyin o'rmonning bu qismi juda qo'rqinchli.

example: To duplicate something means to copy it.
type: She duplicated her friend's movements like she was in front of a mirror.
example_tr: Biror narsani takrorlash, uni nusxalash demakdir.
column14: U xuddi ko‘zgu oldida turgandek dugonasining harakatlarini takrorladi.

example: If something is electromagnetic, it is related to electricity and magnetic fields.
type: Different colors of light come from different levels of electromagnetic energy.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa elektromagnit bo'lsa, u elektr va magnit maydonlar bilan bog'liq.
column14: Yorug'likning turli xil ranglari turli darajadagi elektromagnit energiyadan kelib chiqadi.

example: An electron is a particle in all atoms that has a negative electric charge.
type: The number of electrons in an atom determines the substance the atoms make.
example_tr: Elektron barcha atomlardagi manfiy elektr zaryadiga ega bo'lgan zarrachadir.
column14: Atomdagi elektronlar soni atomlar hosil qiladigan moddani aniqlaydi.

example: To glide means to fly on extended wings with little or no effort.
type: When the wind is blowing, birds can glide easily through the sky.
example_tr: Sirpanish - cho'zilgan qanotlarda kam yoki hech qanday kuch sarflamasdan uchish demakdir.
column14: Shamol esganda, qushlar osmonda osongina sirpanishlari mumkin.

example: If someone is ingenious, then they are very smart.
type: Charles was the only person ingenious enough to repair the plane’s engines.
example_tr: Agar kimdir zukko bo'lsa, u juda aqlli.
column14: Charlz samolyot dvigatellarini ta'mirlashga qodir bo'lgan yagona odam edi.

example: An innovation is a product or an idea that is new or very original.
type: Mrs. Johnson made a great innovation to the company’s business plan.
example_tr: Innovatsiya - bu yangi yoki juda original mahsulot yoki g'oya.
column14: Jonson xonim kompaniyaning biznes rejasiga ajoyib yangilik kiritdi.

example: If something or someone is innovative, they can think in creative ways.
type: Since Peter was so innovative, he was chosen to lead the science team.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yoki kimdir innovatsion bo'lsa, ular ijodiy yo'llar bilan o'ylashlari mumkin.
column14: Butrus juda innovatsion bo'lganligi sababli, u ilmiy jamoaga rahbarlik qilish uchun tanlangan.

example: To launch something means to make it go into motion.
type: The boat launched from the dock and floated down the river.
example_tr: Biror narsani ishga tushirish, uni harakatga keltirishni anglatadi.
column14: Qayiq dokdan suzib, daryo bo'ylab suzib ketdi.

example: If something is meteorological, it is concerned with the science of weather.
type: The thunderstorm was so large that it became a great meteorological event.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa meteorologik bo'lsa, u ob-havo fani bilan bog'liq.
column14: Momaqaldiroq shunchalik katta ediki, u ajoyib meteorologik hodisaga aylandi.

example: Meteorology is the science that studies the weather.
type: In order to understand the weather, you have to study meteorology.
example_tr: Meteorologiya - ob-havoni o'rganadigan fan.
column14: Ob-havoni tushunish uchun siz meteorologiyani o'rganishingiz kerak.

example: To penetrate something means to enter into it.
type: The knife easily penetrated the surface of the orange.
example_tr: Biror narsaga kirish, unga kirish demakdir.
column14: Pichoq apelsin yuzasiga osongina kirib bordi.

example: Propulsion is the force that moves something forward.
type: The propulsion lifted the rocket into the sky.
example_tr: Harakat - bu biror narsani oldinga siljitadigan kuch.
column14: Harakat raketani osmonga ko'tardi.

example: To simulate something means to copy its actions or characteristics.
type: The French language teacher could simulate the accent of a French citizen.
example_tr: Biror narsani taqlid qilish uning harakatlarini yoki xususiyatlarini nusxalashni anglatadi.
column14: Frantsuz tili o'qituvchisi frantsuz fuqarosining aksentini taqlid qilishi mumkin edi.

example: To spur someone means to urge them into action.
type: The coach’s speech spurred her team into playing the best game of their lives.
example_tr: Biror kishini rag'batlantirish, uni harakatga undash demakdir.
column14: Murabbiyning nutqi uning jamoasini hayotidagi eng yaxshi o'yinni o'tkazishga undadi.

example: To stimulate something means to cause or to increase activity in it.
type: Doctors sometimes use electric shock to stimulate a patient's heartbeat.
example_tr: Biror narsani rag'batlantirish, unda faollikni oshirish yoki kuchaytirishni anglatadi.
column14: Shifokorlar ba'zida bemorning yurak urishini rag'batlantirish uchun elektr toki urishidan foydalanadilar.

example: If someone is tenacious, then they do not easily give up.
type: I'm sure that he'll finish that difficult sale. He is very tenacious.
example_tr: Agar kimdir qat'iyatli bo'lsa, u osonlikcha taslim bo'lmaydi.
column14: Ishonchim komilki, u bu qiyin savdoni tugatadi. U juda qat'iyatli.

example: If something is done beforehand, then it is done in advance.
type: He packed his luggage beforehand, so he was able to leave right away.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oldindan qilingan bo'lsa, u oldindan amalga oshiriladi.
column14: U yukini oldindan yig'di, shuning uchun u darhol ketishga muvaffaq bo'ldi.

example: If a temperature is centigrade, it is scaled, so water freezes at 0° and boils at 100°.
type: During the spring time, the temperature gets as warm as 26 degrees centigrade.
example_tr: Agar harorat santigrad bo'lsa, u o'lchovli bo'ladi, shuning uchun suv 0 ° da muzlaydi va 100 ° da qaynaydi.
column14: Bahor faslida havo harorati 26 darajagacha qiziydi.

example: To chatter means to talk quickly about unimportant things.
type: The children chattered in the back of the classroom.
example_tr: Suhbatlashish, ahamiyatsiz narsalar haqida tez gapirishni anglatadi.
column14: Bolalar sinfning orqa tomonida gaplashishdi.

example: A concerto is music for a solo instrument and played with an orchestra.
type: The piano concerto has a section in which only the piano plays,
example_tr: Konsert - bu yakkaxon cholg'u uchun musiqa bo'lib, orkestr bilan ijro etiladi.
column14: Pianino kontsertida faqat pianino ijro etiladigan bo'lim mavjud.

example: To condense a gas means to make it a liquid.
type: The cool air made tiny drops of water condense on the tops of the grass.
example_tr: Gazni kondensatsiya qilish uni suyuqlikka aylantirishni anglatadi.
column14: Salqin havo maysalar tepasida mayda suv tomchilarini quyuqlashtirdi.

example: A cove is a part of land where it curves inward around the sea.
type: They hid the boat in a small cove on the south side of the island.
example_tr: Ko'y - dengiz atrofida ichkariga egilgan quruqlikning bir qismi.
column14: Ular qayiqni orolning janubiy tomonidagi kichik qo‘yga yashirishdi.

example: To deteriorate means to become steadily worse.
type: The nation’s economy continued to deteriorate despite the politicians’ efforts.
example_tr: Buzilish - bu tobora yomonlashishni anglatadi.
column14: Siyosatchilarning sa'y-harakatlariga qaramay, mamlakat iqtisodiyoti yomonlashishda davom etdi.

example: An exterior is the outside surface of something.
type: The exterior of the nut was hard and woody, but the inside was soft and delicious.
example_tr: Eksteryer - biror narsaning tashqi yuzasi.
column14: Yong'oqning tashqi ko'rinishi qattiq va yog'och edi, lekin ichki qismi yumshoq va mazali edi.

example: A freeway is a road with no stops where cars travel at high speeds.
type: Once you get on the freeway, it only takes an hour to drive to my parent’s farm.
example_tr: Magistral yo'l - bu mashinalar yuqori tezlikda harakatlanadigan to'xtash joyi bo'lmagan yo'l.
column14: Magistral yo'lga chiqqaningizdan so'ng, ota-onamning fermasigacha borish uchun bor-yo'g'i bir soat vaqt ketadi.

example: If someone or something is hearty, then they are loud and happy.
type: The grandmother ended her story with a hearty laugh that pleased her grandchild.
example_tr: Agar kimdir yoki biror narsa samimiy bo'lsa, ular baland ovozda va baxtlidir.
column14: Buvi o‘z hikoyasini nabirasini xursand qilgan quvnoq kulgi bilan yakunladi.

example: If someone is hospitable, they are friendly to strangers.
type: At dinner, Dad was very hospitable to my friends.
example_tr: Agar kimdir mehmondo'st bo'lsa, u begonalarga do'stona munosabatda bo'ladi.
column14: Kechki ovqat paytida dadam do'stlarimga juda mehmondo'st edi.

example: A manor is a large house with many rooms.
type: The manor had over forty rooms in addition to beautiful gardens.
example_tr: Manor - bu ko'p xonali katta uy.
column14: Manorning go'zal bog'lardan tashqari qirqdan ortiq xonalari bor edi.

example: A monastery is a building in which monks live.
type: The monks at this monastery are famous for their bread and music,
example_tr: Monastir - bu rohiblar yashaydigan bino.
column14: Ushbu monastirdagi rohiblar non va musiqa bilan mashhur.

example: A nursery is a room where babies and children sleep, play, or are cared for.
type: The children kissed their parents goodnight and went upstairs to the nursery.
example_tr: Bolalar bog'chasi - bu chaqaloqlar va bolalar uxlaydigan, o'ynaydigan yoki ularga g'amxo'rlik qiladigan xona.
column14: Bolalar ota-onalari bilan xayrli tun o'pishib, bolalar bog'chasiga ko'tarilishdi.

example: If something is outstretched, then it is extended to its full length.
type: The cat stood on its back legs with its front legs outstretched.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa cho'zilgan bo'lsa, u to'liq uzunligiga uzaytiriladi.
column14: Mushuk old oyoqlarini yoyib, orqa oyoqlarida turdi.

example: A parcel is a package of things to be carried or mailed somewhere.
type: The parcel looked like it had been stepped on by someone.
example_tr: Posilka - bu biror joyga olib o'tiladigan yoki pochta orqali yuboriladigan narsalar to'plami.
column14: Posilka uni kimdir bosganga o'xshardi.

example: A profile is an outline of a face, usually as seen from the side.
type: The drawing of Olivia’s profile came out very well.
example_tr: Profil odatda yon tomondan ko'rinadigan yuzning konturidir.
column14: Oliviya profilining chizilgani juda yaxshi chiqdi.

example: If someone is vivacious, they are talkative and cheerful.
type: Everyone at the party was very vivacious and having a good time.
example_tr: Agar kimdir quvnoq bo'lsa, u suhbatdosh va quvnoq.
column14: Bayramda hamma juda quvnoq va maroqli dam olishdi.

example: If something is winding, then it follows a twisting course.
type: The winding river turned and looped around the bases of the hills.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa o'ralgan bo'lsa, u burilish yo'li bilan boradi.
column14: Aylanib yurgan daryo aylanib, tepaliklar etagini aylanib chiqdi.

example: To zip something means to close it with a zipper.
type: She zipped her backpack closed after putting her books inside it.
example_tr: Biror narsani fermuar bilan yopish degani.
column14: U kitoblarini ichiga qo'ygandan so'ng ryukzakni fermuar bilan yopdi.

example: An airway is the passage by which air reaches a person’s lungs.
type: Since he was sick, mucus would occasionally get stuck in his airway.
example_tr: Havo yo'li - bu havo odamning o'pkasiga etib boradigan o'tish joyi.
column14: U kasal bo'lganligi sababli, nafas olish yo'liga vaqti-vaqti bilan shilimshiq tiqilib qolardi.

example: The Almighty is a name for a god ina religion.
type: Before eating, they thanked the Almighty for their food.
example_tr: Qudratli dinda xudoning nomi.
column14: Ovqatlanishdan oldin, ular taomlari uchun Qodirga shukr qilishdi.

example: An advent is the arrival or beginning of an important person, thing, or event.
type: During the advent of radio, very few programs actually played music.
example_tr: Advent - muhim shaxs, narsa yoki hodisaning kelishi yoki boshlanishi.
column14: Radioning paydo bo'lishi davrida juda kam sonli dasturlar aslida musiqa ijro etgan.

example: A constellation is a group of stars with a recognizable shape.
type: That constellation in the shape of a square is named after a flying horse.
example_tr: Yulduz turkumi - bu taniqli shaklga ega bo'lgan yulduzlar guruhi.
column14: Kvadrat shaklidagi bu yulduz turkumi uchayotgan ot sharafiga nomlangan.

example: If something is definitive, then it is the most official.
type: This library has the definitive collection of books on ancient Egypt.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa aniq bo'lsa, u eng rasmiy hisoblanadi.
column14: Ushbu kutubxonada qadimgi Misrga oid kitoblarning aniq to'plami mavjud.

example: To equate one thing with another is to compare them and consider them very similar.
type: She equated the man’s messy appearance with a lack of responsibility.
example_tr: Bir narsani boshqasiga tenglashtirish, ularni solishtirish va juda o'xshash deb hisoblashdir.
column14: U erkakning tartibsiz ko'rinishini mas'uliyatning etishmasligi bilan tenglashtirdi.

example: To inhale means to take air or a smell into the lungs.
type: The camper inhaled the cool and fresh mountain air and felt relaxed.
example_tr: Nafas olish o'pkaga havo yoki hidni olish demakdir.
column14: Kampir tog‘ning salqin va musaffo havosidan nafas oldi va o‘zini erkin his qildi.

example: To invoke something is to mention it to support an argument or ask for help.
type: Before going into battle, the soldier invoked the name of his god for protection.
example_tr: Biror narsani chaqirish - bu bahsni qo'llab-quvvatlash yoki yordam so'rash uchun uni eslatishdir.
column14: Jangga kirishdan oldin askar himoya qilish uchun xudosining ismini chaqirdi.

example: If something is lunar, then it is related to the moon.
type: During a lunar eclipse, Earth’s shadow darkens the moon’s surface.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oy bo'lsa, u oy bilan bog'liq.
column14: Oy tutilishi paytida Yerning soyasi oy yuzasini qoraytiradi.

example: A novelty is something that is new, original, or strange.
type: Ice cream was a novelty for him since he rarely had any.
example_tr: Yangilik - bu yangi, o'ziga xos yoki g'alati narsa.
column14: Muzqaymoq uning uchun yangilik edi, chunki u kamdan-kam bo'lgan.

example: If something is outmoded, then it is no longer in fashion or use.
type: Black and white television sets are outmoded.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa eskirgan bo'lsa, u endi modada yoki foydalanishda emas.
column14: Qora va oq televizorlar eskirgan.

example: To personalize something means to design it to meet a person’s unique needs.
type: He personalized the woman's exercises to give her a better workout.
example_tr: Biror narsani shaxsiylashtirish, uni insonning o'ziga xos ehtiyojlarini qondirish uchun loyihalashni anglatadi.
column14: U ayolga yaxshiroq mashq qilish uchun mashqlarni shaxsiylashtirdi.

example: To pertain to something means to be related or connected to it.
type: All of the lawyer's questions pertained to events around the night of the crime.
example_tr: Biror narsaga tegishli bo'lmoq, unga aloqador bo'lmoq yoki bog'langan bo'lmoq degan ma'noni anglatadi.
column14: Advokatning barcha savollari jinoyat kechasi atrofidagi voqealarga tegishli.

example: If something is primal, then it is very basic or related to the origin of something.
type: Cooking the food over the camp fire felt like a primal way of making a meal.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ibtidoiy bo'lsa, u juda asosiy yoki biror narsaning kelib chiqishi bilan bog'liq.
column14: Lager olovida ovqat pishirish taom tayyorlashning asosiy usulidek tuyuldi.

example: If something is psychiatric, then it is related to mental illness or its treatment.
type: The doctor said the patient might have a psychiatric problem.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa psixiatrik bo'lsa, unda bu ruhiy kasallik yoki uni davolash bilan bog'liq.
column14: Shifokor bemorda psixiatrik muammo bo'lishi mumkinligini aytdi.

example: Psychiatry is the study and treatment of mental illness.
type: Studying psychiatry has taught me a lot about mental illness.
example_tr: Psixiatriya ruhiy kasalliklarni o'rganish va davolashdir.
column14: Psixiatriyani o'rganish menga ruhiy kasalliklar haqida ko'p narsalarni o'rgatdi.

example: A reflex is an unconscious action in which a body part responds to an event.
type: There was a reflex when the doctor hit his knee with a rubber hammer.
example_tr: Refleks - bu ongsiz harakat bo'lib, unda tana a'zosi biron bir hodisaga javob beradi.
column14: Shifokor tizzasini rezina bolg'a bilan urganida refleks bor edi.

example: A seizure is sudden illness in which the body loses control and shakes.
type: Bright flashing lights can cause seizures in children.
example_tr: Tutqich - bu to'satdan kasallik bo'lib, unda tana nazoratni yo'qotadi va titraydi.
column14: Yorqin miltillovchi chiroqlar bolalarda soqchilikni keltirib chiqarishi mumkin.

example: Asession is a meeting at a regular time in order to discuss and solve an issue.
type: Every three months the managers met in a session to discuss regional sales.
example_tr: Baholash - bu masalani muhokama qilish va hal qilish uchun muntazam ravishda yig'ilish.
column14: Har uch oyda menejerlar mintaqaviy savdoni muhokama qilish uchun sessiyada uchrashishdi.

example: A utensil is a common tool or container.
type: It seemed that a fork was the wrong utensil for trying to eat the soup.
example_tr: Idish - bu umumiy asbob yoki idish.
column14: Aftidan, vilka sho'rva yeyish uchun noto'g'ri idish bo'lib tuyuldi.

example: An adhesive is a substance used for sticking things together.
type: The carpenter used an adhesive to hold the two pieces of wood together.
example_tr: Yelim - bu narsalarni bir-biriga yopishtirish uchun ishlatiladigan moddadir.
column14: Duradgor ikki bo‘lakni bir-biriga yopishtiruvchi yopishtiruvchi vositadan foydalangan.

example: If something is adverse, then it is harmful.
type: Not eating healthy foods can have an adverse effect on your health.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomon bo'lsa, u zararli.
column14: Sog'lom ovqat iste'mol qilmaslik sog'lig'ingizga salbiy ta'sir ko'rsatishi mumkin.

example: A dependency is a strong need for someone or something.
type: The child still has a dependency on her mother.
example_tr: Tobelik - bu kimgadir yoki biror narsaga kuchli ehtiyoj.
column14: Bola hali ham onasiga qaram bo'lib qoladi.

example: To dump something means to throw it away or get rid of it.
type: She dumped the garbage into the trash can.
example_tr: Biror narsani tashlab yuborish, uni tashlash yoki undan qutulish demakdir.
column14: U axlatni axlat qutisiga tashladi.

example: If something is eternal, then it lasts forever.
type: She said that her love for him was eternal.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa abadiy bo'lsa, u abadiy davom etadi.
column14: U unga bo'lgan sevgisi abadiy ekanligini aytdi.

example: To fluctuate means to rise and fall in number or amount.
type: Prices for gasoline have been fluctuating all month.
example_tr: Tebranish, son yoki miqdorning ko'tarilishi va kamayishini anglatadi.
column14: Benzin narxi oy davomida o'zgarib turdi.

example: If something moves to and fro, it moves backward and forward or side to side.
type: Her long hair went to and fro as she swung on the swing.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oldinga va orqaga harakat qilsa, u orqaga va oldinga yoki yonma-yon harakatlanadi.
column14: Uning uzun sochlari belanchakda tebrangancha u yoqdan-bu yoqqa yurardi.

example: Inclusion is the act of including someone or something in a group.
type: Her inclusion into the photo club was well received.
example_tr: Inklyuzivlik - bu kimnidir yoki biror narsani guruhga kiritish harakati.
column14: Uning fotoklubga kiritilishi yaxshi kutib olindi.

example: If something is intermediate, then it is in the middle of two levels, places, or times.
type: He selected the intermediate ski hill to begin his afternoon of skiing.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa oraliq bo'lsa, u ikki daraja, joy yoki vaqtning o'rtasida bo'ladi.
column14: U tushdan keyin chang'i sportini boshlash uchun oraliq chang'i tepaligini tanladi.

example: If something is intermittent, then it happens in a way that is not constant.
type: It was hard to focus because intermittent noises came from the workers outside.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa vaqti-vaqti bilan bo'lsa, u doimiy bo'lmagan tarzda sodir bo'ladi.
column14: E'tiborni qaratish qiyin edi, chunki tashqarida ishchilardan vaqti-vaqti bilan shovqin eshitildi.

example: A mentor is a person with experience or knowledge who advises someone.
type: The students each chose a mentor to help them with the experiment.
example_tr: Mentor - bu kimgadir maslahat beradigan tajriba yoki bilimga ega shaxs.
column14: Talabalarning har biri tajribada yordam berish uchun murabbiy tanladi.

example: A phoenix is an imaginary bird that burned to ashes and was reborn.
type: Some believe the phoenix is a symbol for rebirth and a new beginning.
example_tr: Feniks - hayoliy qush, u yonib kul bo'lib, qayta tug'iladi.
column14: Ba'zilar Feniksni qayta tug'ilish va yangi boshlanish ramzi deb hisoblashadi.

example: Photosynthesis is the process in which plants change sunlight and air.
type: The chemical in plants that makes them green is used in photosynthesis.
example_tr: Fotosintez - bu o'simliklarning quyosh nuri va havoni o'zgartirish jarayoni.
column14: O'simliklarni yashil rangga aylantiradigan kimyoviy moddalar fotosintezda ishlatiladi.

example: Pollen is the tiny yellow powder made in the flowers of plants.
type: During the spring, the pollen in the air makes some people become sick.
example_tr: Polen o'simliklar gullarida hosil bo'lgan mayda sariq kukundir.
column14: Bahor faslida havodagi gulchanglar ba'zi odamlarni kasal qiladi.

example: To regain something means to get it back.
type: The battery regained its power after being recharged.
example_tr: Biror narsani qaytarib olish, uni qaytarib olishni anglatadi.
column14: Batareya qayta zaryadlangandan so'ng o'z kuchini tikladi.

example: To reverse means to change to the opposite direction.
type: They reversed their direction after seeing the sign.
example_tr: Orqaga teskari tomonga o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Ular belgini ko'rib, yo'nalishini o'zgartirdilar.

example: A swarm is a group of flying insects.
type: A beautiful swarm of butterflies filled the summer sky.
example_tr: Toʻda — uchuvchi hasharotlar guruhi.
column14: Yozgi osmonni chiroyli kapalaklar to'dasi to'ldirdi.

example: Texture is the quality of something that can be known by its touch.
type: The texture of her skin was very soft and smooth.
example_tr: Tekstura - bu teginish orqali bilish mumkin bo'lgan narsaning sifati.
column14: Uning terisi juda yumshoq va silliq edi.

example: To tickle someone is to touch them in a way that causes laughter.
type: The mother tickled the little boy’s foot, and he screamed with laughter.
example_tr: Biror kishini qitiqlash - unga kulgiga sabab bo'ladigan tarzda teginish.
column14: Onasi bolaning oyog'ini qitiqladi va u kulib baqirdi.

example: If something is vibrant, then it is bright and full of color.
type: Their new shirts were a vibrant shade of red.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa jonli bo'lsa, u yorqin va rangga to'la.
column14: Ularning yangi ko'ylaklari qizilning yorqin soyasida edi.

example: To abolish something means to put an end to it, such as a system or law.
type: President Lincoln abolished slavery in the US.
example_tr: Biror narsani bekor qilish, unga chek qo'yish demakdir, masalan, tizim yoki qonun.
column14: Prezident Linkoln AQShda qullikni bekor qildi.

example: To amend something means to change it to improve or make it accurate.
type: The countries were in agreement that the treaty needed to be amended.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'zgartirish, uni yaxshilash yoki aniq qilish uchun o'zgartirishni anglatadi.
column14: Mamlakatlar shartnomaga o'zgartirishlar kiritish zarurligi haqida kelishib oldilar.

example: To aspire means to have a strong desire to achieve or do something.
type: George aspired to be a doctor from a young age.
example_tr: Intilish, biror narsaga erishish yoki qilish istagi kuchli bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Jorj yoshligidan shifokor bo'lishni orzu qilgan.

example: To censor information means to remove it if it is rude or rebellious.
type: To protect innocent people, the location of the bomb was censored.
example_tr: Ma'lumotni tsenzura qilish, agar u qo'pol yoki isyonkor bo'lsa, uni olib tashlashni anglatadi.
column14: Begunoh odamlarni himoya qilish uchun bomba joylashuvi tsenzura qilingan.

example: A charter is a document that describes the rights of an organization or group.
type: The company charter explained that all employees had to pay a tax.
example_tr: Nizom - bu tashkilot yoki guruhning huquqlarini tavsiflovchi hujjat.
column14: Kompaniya nizomida barcha xodimlar soliq to'lashlari kerakligi tushuntirilgan.

example: A constitution is a document of principles for a government.
type: The country’s constitution said a prime minister could only serve three terms.
example_tr: Konstitutsiya hukumatning tamoyillari hujjatidir.
column14: Mamlakat konstitutsiyasiga ko'ra, bosh vazir faqat uch muddatga saylanishi mumkin.

example: When a place is cosmopolitan, it is full of people from many different places.
type: There are dozens of different types of restaurants in a cosmopolitan city.
example_tr: Agar joy kosmopolit bo'lsa, u turli joylardan kelgan odamlar bilan to'la.
column14: Kosmopolit shaharda o'nlab turli xil restoranlar mavjud.

example: To disseminate information or knowledge means to distribute it.
type: The organization disseminates information about the dangers of smoking.
example_tr: Axborot yoki bilimni tarqatish uni tarqatish demakdir.
column14: Tashkilot chekishning zarari haqida ma'lumot tarqatadi.

example: To flatter people means to praise them in an effort to please them.
type: He was just flattering me when he said that my new dress looked gorgeous.
example_tr: Odamlarga xushomad qilish, ularni rozi qilish uchun ularni maqtash demakdir.
column14: U yangi ko'ylagim ajoyib ko'rinishini aytganida, shunchaki xushomad qilardi.

example: When someone is infamous, they are well known for something bad.
type: That news channel is infamous for presenting biased information.
example_tr: Biror kishi obro'li bo'lsa, u yomon narsa bilan tanilgan.
column14: O'sha yangiliklar kanali xolis ma'lumotlarni taqdim etishi bilan mashhur.

example: If one is lame, they cannot walk properly due to an injury to the leg or foot.
type: The terrible accident left many people dead and several others lame.
example_tr: Agar kimdir cho'loq bo'lsa, oyog'i yoki oyog'i jarohati tufayli to'g'ri yura olmaydi.
column14: Dahshatli baxtsiz hodisa ko'plab odamlarning hayotiga zomin bo'ldi va yana bir qancha odamlar cho'loq bo'ldi.

example: To limp means to walk with difficulty because someone’s leg or foot is hurt.
type: After the injury, the player limped off of the field.
example_tr: Oqsoqlanish, birovning oyog'i yoki oyog'i shikastlangani uchun qiyinchilik bilan yurishni anglatadi.
column14: Jarohatdan keyin futbolchi oqsoqlanib maydonni tark etdi.

example: An outburst is a sudden, strong expression of an emotion.
type: There was an outburst of cheers when the comedian took the stage.
example_tr: Portlash hissiyotning to'satdan kuchli ifodasidir.
column14: Komediyachi sahnaga chiqqanida shov-shuv ko‘tarildi.

example: When a behavior is pathological, it is extreme, unacceptable, and uncontrollable.
type: The pathological liar could not even tell the truth about unimportant matters.
example_tr: Agar xatti-harakatlar patologik bo'lsa, u ekstremal, qabul qilib bo'lmaydigan va nazorat qilib bo'lmaydigandir.
column14: Patologik yolg'onchi hatto ahamiyatsiz narsalar haqida haqiqatni ayta olmadi.

example: When something is phenomenal, it is unusually great.
type: The child's ability to play the piano is nothing short of phenomenal.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa fenomenal bo'lsa, u g'ayrioddiy ajoyibdir.
column14: Bolaning pianino chalish qobiliyati ajoyib narsa emas.

example: A poll is a survey in which people give their opinions about important things.
type: The poll showed that many people support the plan to stop gang violence.
example_tr: So'rov - bu odamlar muhim narsalar haqida o'z fikrlarini bildiradigan so'rov.
column14: So‘rov shuni ko‘rsatdiki, ko‘pchilik guruh zo‘ravonligini to‘xtatish rejasini qo‘llab-quvvatlamoqda.

example: Remorse is a strong feeling of sadness and regret.
type: When I realized what I did, I felt remorse for my actions.
example_tr: Tavba - kuchli qayg'u va pushaymonlik hissi.
column14: Men nima qilganimni anglab etgach, qilgan ishlarimdan pushaymon bo'ldim.

example: Secrecy is the behavior of keeping things secret.
type: The secrecy of the big organization made the government nervous.
example_tr: Maxfiylik - bu narsalarni sir saqlash harakati.
column14: Katta tashkilotning maxfiyligi hukumatni asabiylashtirdi.

example: To tackle something means to deal with it in a determined and efficient way.
type: Such social problems need to be tackled right away.
example_tr: Biror narsani hal qilish, uni qat'iy va samarali tarzda hal qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Bunday ijtimoiy muammolarni zudlik bilan hal qilish kerak.

example: A trance is a state where people seem asleep and have no control of themselves.
type: The woman’s powerful eyes often put men in a trance.
example_tr: Trans - bu odamlar uxlab yotgandek tuyuladigan va o'zlarini nazorat qila olmaydigan holat.
column14: Ayolning kuchli ko'zlari ko'pincha erkaklarni transga tushiradi.
