example: A coward is a person who lacks courage to do risky or dangerous things.
type: A firefighter cannot be a coward. They have to be able to act quickly.
example_tr: Qo'rqoq - bu xavfli yoki xavfli ishlarni qilish uchun jasoratga ega bo'lmagan odam.
column14: O't o'chiruvchi qo'rqoq bo'la olmaydi. Ular tezda harakat qila olishlari kerak.

example: To delete something means to remove or erase written material.
type: Several lines had been deleted from her speech.
example_tr: Biror narsani o'chirish yozma materialni olib tashlash yoki o'chirishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning nutqidan bir qancha satrlar o‘chirib tashlangan edi.

example: If something is firsthand, then it is from an original source.
type: If you want firsthand knowledge, ask someone who saw it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa birinchi qo'l bo'lsa, u asl manbadan.
column14: Agar siz birinchi qo'l bilim olishni istasangiz, uni ko'rgan odamdan so'rang.

example: If someone is earnest, then they are honest.
type: The child was very earnest when she told her mother how she broke the dish.
example_tr: Agar kimdir samimiy bo'lsa, u haloldir.
column14: Bola onasiga idishni qanday sindirganini aytib, juda jiddiy edi.

example: If something is ethnic, then it is related to a group with a similar culture.
type: Many sections of the city are home to different ethnic communities.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa etnik bo'lsa, u o'xshash madaniyatga ega bo'lgan guruh bilan bog'liq.
column14: Shaharning ko'p qismlarida turli etnik jamoalar yashaydi.

example: To exclude someone means to not accept them into a group.
type: Carol was excluded from the contest because her friend was a judge.
example_tr: Biror kishini istisno qilish, uni guruhga qabul qilmaslikni anglatadi.
column14: Kerol tanlovdan chetlashtirildi, chunki uning do'sti hakam bo'lgan.

example: If someone is fluent in a language, then they are able to speak it very well.
type: She was so fluent in German that you'd have thought she was from Germany.
example_tr: Agar biror kishi biron bir tilni yaxshi bilsa, u juda yaxshi gapira oladi.
column14: U nemis tilini shu qadar yaxshi bilardiki, uni Germaniyadan deb o‘ylagan bo‘lardingiz.

example: If something is imperial, then it is of, or related to an empire.
type: These old imperial coins were once used in the Roman Empire.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa imperiya bo'lsa, u imperiyaga tegishli yoki u bilan bog'liq.
column14: Ushbu eski imperator tangalari bir vaqtlar Rim imperiyasida ishlatilgan.

example: If something is inclusive, then it is open to all groups and people in society.
type: A more inclusive event would have allowed children to attend.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa inklyuziv bo'lsa, u jamiyatdagi barcha guruhlar va odamlar uchun ochiqdir.
column14: Ko'proq inklyuziv tadbir bolalarning ishtirok etishiga imkon bergan bo'lardi.

example: A legislature is the section of a government that makes laws.
type: The senator had served ten years in the national legislature.
example_tr: Qonun chiqaruvchi organ - bu hukumatning qonunlar ishlab chiqaruvchi bo'limi.
column14: Senator milliy qonun chiqaruvchi organda o'n yil ishlagan.

example: If something is linguistic, then it is concerned with language.
type: A linguistic way of studying culture focuses on words within that culture.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa lingvistik bo'lsa, u til bilan bog'liq.
column14: Madaniyatni o'rganishning lingvistik usuli ushbu madaniyat ichidagi so'zlarga qaratilgan.

example: If someone is monolingual, then they speak only one language.
type: In today’s global economy, being monolingual limits your opportunities.
example_tr: Agar kimdir bir tilli bo'lsa, u faqat bitta tilda gaplashadi.
column14: Bugungi global iqtisodiyotda bir tilda bo'lish imkoniyatlaringizni cheklaydi.

example: Nationality is an identity based on the nation from which you come.
type: His nationality is German, but he speaks French, Spanish, and Korean.
example_tr: Millat - bu siz kelgan millatga asoslangan o'ziga xoslik.
column14: Uning millati nemis, lekin u frantsuz, ispan va koreys tillarini biladi.

example: A patriot is someone who loves, supports, and defends their country.
type: Every year young patriots join their countries’ militaries.
example_tr: Vatanparvar - bu o'z vatanini sevadigan, qo'llab-quvvatlaydigan va himoya qiladigan odam.
column14: Har yili yosh vatanparvarlar o'z mamlakatlari harbiylariga qo'shilishadi.

example: To prosecute someone means to take legal action against them.
type: They were prosecuted for fishing in the river without a permit.
example_tr: Biror kishini jinoiy javobgarlikka tortish, unga nisbatan qonuniy choralar ko'rish demakdir.
column14: Ular daryoda ruxsatsiz baliq ovlaganliklari uchun javobgarlikka tortilgan.

example: If something is racial, then it is related to a race or races.
type: The differences between racial groups are physical characteristics and culture.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa irqiy bo'lsa, u irq yoki irq bilan bog'liq.
column14: Irqiy guruhlar o'rtasidagi farqlar jismoniy xususiyatlar va madaniyatdir.

example: If something is solemn, then it is serious and honest.
type: The professor preferred a solemn relationship between him and his students.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tantanali bo'lsa, u jiddiy va haloldir.
column14: Professor o'zi va talabalari o'rtasidagi tantanali munosabatni afzal ko'rdi.

example: Solidarity is a union formed from common responsibilities or interests.
type: All the citizens came together in a show of solidarity to create change.
example_tr: Birdamlik - bu umumiy mas'uliyat yoki manfaatlardan tashkil topgan ittifoq.
column14: Barcha fuqarolar o'zgarishlarni yaratish uchun birdamlik namoyishida birlashdilar.

example: Tact is the ability to avoid offending people when dealing with problems.
type: Since both sides would not agree, it required someone with tact to make peace.
example_tr: Xushmuomalalik - muammolarni hal qilishda odamlarni xafa qilmaslik qobiliyatidir.
column14: Ikkala tomon ham rozi bo'lmagani uchun tinchlik o'rnatish uchun xushmuomala odam kerak edi.

example: To undermine someone means to betray or weaken their efforts or authority.
type: The documents helped to undermine the workers’ trust in their bosses’ honesty.
example_tr: Biror kishiga putur etkazish, uning harakatlariga yoki hokimiyatiga xiyonat qilish yoki zaiflashtirish demakdir.
column14: Hujjatlar ishchilarning o'z xo'jayinlarining halolligiga ishonchini yo'qotishga yordam berdi.

example: To allocate something means to put it aside for a certain purpose or person.
type: The government allocated $100 million to aid the disaster relief effort.
example_tr: Biror narsani ajratish, uni ma'lum bir maqsad yoki shaxs uchun chetga surish demakdir.
column14: Hukumat tabiiy ofat oqibatlarini bartaraf etish uchun 100 million dollar ajratdi.

example: When food is appetizing, it looks and smells very good.
type: The appetizing plate of cookies was gone in half an hou.
example_tr: Ovqat ishtahani ochganda, u juda yaxshi ko'rinadi va hidlaydi.
column14: Ishtahani ochuvchi pechenye tarelkasi yarim soatda g‘oyib bo‘ldi.

example: A blizzard is a severe snow storm with strong winds.
type: We did not dare to go outside during the terrible blizzard.
example_tr: Qor bo'roni - kuchli shamollar bilan kuchli qor bo'roni.
column14: Dahshatli bo'ron paytida ko'chaga chiqishga jur'at eta olmadik.

example: A cavity is a hole or space in something.
type: There was a small cavity in the wall of the cave where an animal lived.
example_tr: Bo'shliq - bu biror narsadagi teshik yoki bo'shliq.
column14: G‘or devorida hayvon yashaydigan kichik bo‘shliq bor edi.

example: If samething moves clockwise, it moves in a circle in the same direction as a clock.
type: Turn the screw clockwise to tighten it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa soat yo'nalishi bo'yicha harakatlansa, u soat bilan bir xil yo'nalishda aylana bo'ylab harakatlanadi.
column14: Vintni mahkamlash uchun soat yo'nalishi bo'yicha aylantiring.

example: When circles or rings are concentric, they have the same center.
type: The target was a Series of concentric circles.
example_tr: Agar doiralar yoki halqalar konsentrik bo'lsa, ular bir xil markazga ega.
column14: Maqsad konsentrik doiralar seriyasi edi.

example: Courtesy is the excellence of manners or social conduct.
type: Jenna always behaves with great courtesy when people visit her home.
example_tr: Xushmuomalalik - bu odob-axloq yoki ijtimoiy xulq-atvorning mukammalligi.
column14: Odamlar uning uyiga tashrif buyurishganda Jenna doimo o'zini juda xushmuomalalik bilan tutadi.

example: When food is crisp, it is hard or has a hard surface in a way that is pleasant.
type: My favorite snack is a bag of crisp, delicious potato chips.
example_tr: Ovqat tiniq bo'lsa, u qattiq yoki yoqimli tarzda qattiq yuzaga ega.
column14: Mening sevimli gazak - bu tiniq, mazali kartoshka chiplari.

example: Discord is disagreement or fighting between people.
type: There was much discord between the experts on the talk show.
example_tr: Nizo - bu odamlar o'rtasidagi kelishmovchilik yoki janjal.
column14: Tok-shouda mutaxassislar o'rtasida juda ko'p kelishmovchilik bo'lgan.

example: If something is frigid, it is extremely cold.
type: We decided not to go on the hike because the weather was too frigid.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sovuq bo'lsa, u juda sovuq.
column14: Biz sayohatga chiqmaslikka qaror qildik, chunki havo juda sovuq edi.

example: To generate something means to cause it to develop or begin.
type: The mayor promised to generate new jobs and programs to help the poor.
example_tr: Biror narsani yaratish, uning rivojlanishiga yoki boshlanishiga sabab bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Shahar hokimi yangi ish o‘rinlari yaratishga va kam ta’minlanganlarga yordam berishga va’da berdi.

example: When something is glacial, it relates to large masses of ice that move slowly.
type: Penguins thrive in the glacial regions of Antarctica.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa muzlik bo'lsa, u sekin harakatlanadigan katta muz massalariga tegishli.
column14: Pingvinlar Antarktidaning muzlik hududlarida ko'payadi.

example: An interchange of ideas between people is a discussion of each person’s idea.
type: There was an interchange of ideas between the groups.
example_tr: Odamlar o'rtasidagi fikr almashish - bu har bir shaxsning g'oyasini muhokama qilish.
column14: Guruhlar o‘rtasida fikr almashuvi bo‘ldi.

example: A locker is a small cabinet with a lock where people store their possessions.
type: I keep my school books in my locker,
example_tr: Shkaf - bu odamlar o'z narsalarini saqlaydigan qulfli kichik shkaf.
column14: Men maktab kitoblarimni shkafimda saqlayman,

example: When something is multicultural, it relates to many different cultures.
type: Everyone was welcomed to attend the multicultural celebration.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ko'p madaniyatli bo'lsa, u turli madaniyatlarga tegishli.
column14: Ko'p madaniyatli bayramda barchani kutib olishdi.

example: An omission is something that has been left out or not done.
type: Mike was upset because of the omission of his name during the ceremony.
example_tr: E'tiborsizlik - tashlab qo'yilgan yoki bajarilmagan narsadir.
column14: Mayk marosim paytida uning ismi ko'rsatilmagani uchun xafa bo'ldi.

example: To oversee something means to make sure that it is being done properly.
type: His job was to oversee the progress of the construction project.
example_tr: Biror narsani nazorat qilish uning to'g'ri bajarilganligiga ishonch hosil qilishni anglatadi.
column14: Uning vazifasi qurilish loyihasining borishini nazorat qilish edi.

example: To pierce something means to make a hole in it using a sharp object.
type: The arrow pierced the target in the very center.
example_tr: Biror narsani teshish, o'tkir narsa yordamida teshik qilish demakdir.
column14: O'q nishonni o'rtasiga teshdi.

example: To replicate something is to do it in the exact same way as someone before.
type: I would love to replicate my father’s achievements in school.
example_tr: Biror narsani takrorlash - bu avvalgi odamga o'xshash tarzda qilish.
column14: Men otamning maktabdagi yutuqlarini takrorlashni istardim.

example: When something is wavy, itis not straight but has a series of curves.
type: The child drew wavy lines all over the piece of paper.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa to'lqinli bo'lsa, u tekis emas, balki bir qator egri chiziqlarga ega.
column14: Bola qog'oz parchasi bo'ylab to'lqinli chiziqlar chizdi.

example: To abide by something, like a rule, means to obey it.
type: If you want to play the game with us, you must be willing to abide by our rules.
example_tr: Biror narsaga rioya qilish, xuddi qoida kabi, unga bo'ysunishni anglatadi.
column14: Agar siz biz bilan o'ynashni istasangiz, bizning qoidalarimizga rioya qilishga tayyor bo'lishingiz kerak.

example: Conversion is the act of changing something into a different state or form.
type: The city discussed the conversion of the parking lot into a skateboard park.
example_tr: Konversiya - bu biror narsani boshqa holat yoki shaklga o'zgartirish harakati.
column14: Shahar avtoturargohni skeytbord parkiga aylantirish masalasini muhokama qildi.

example: To cram things means to put them into a place that can barely contain them.
type: He crammed all of his shirts into the top drawer of the dresser.
example_tr: Narsalarni siqish, ularni zo'rg'a sig'dira oladigan joyga qo'yish demakdir.
column14: U barcha ko'ylaklarini shkafning yuqori tortmasiga tiqdi.

example: To defer means to arrange for an action to happen at a later time.
type: The girl was very sleepy, so she chose to defer her bath until morning.
example_tr: Kechiktirish, keyinroq sodir bo'ladigan harakatni tartibga solishni anglatadi.
column14: Qiz juda uyqusirab edi, shuning uchun u ertalabgacha hammomni kechiktirishni tanladi.

example: To export products means to sell them to other countries.
type: The United States exports many cereals and grains.
example_tr: Mahsulotlarni eksport qilish, ularni boshqa mamlakatlarga sotish demakdir.
column14: Qo'shma Shtatlar ko'plab don va donlarni eksport qiladi.

example: Fumes are unhealthy smoke and gases that are made by fires or chemicals.
type: The engine put unpleasant, black fumes into the air.
example_tr: Tutunlar - bu yong'in yoki kimyoviy moddalar natijasida hosil bo'lgan nosog'lom tutun va gazlar.
column14: Dvigatel havoga yoqimsiz, qora tutun chiqaradi.

example: When something is habitual, it is a behavior that a person usually does or has.
type: The man was a habitual liar who was incapable of being honest with the police.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa odatiy bo'lsa, bu odamning odatda qiladigan yoki ega bo'lgan xatti-harakatidir.
column14: Bu odam odatdagi yolg'onchi bo'lib, politsiya bilan halol bo'lishga qodir emas edi.

example: To justify something means to show or prove that it is necessary.
type: The government tried to justify its decision to bring the country into a war.
example_tr: Biror narsani oqlash, uning zarurligini ko'rsatish yoki isbotlash demakdir.
column14: Hukumat mamlakatni urushga olib kirish haqidagi qarorini oqlashga harakat qildi.

example: Output is the amount of something that a person or thing produces.
type: The boss hired more workers to increase the factory’s output of products.
example_tr: Chiqarish - bu shaxs yoki narsa ishlab chiqaradigan narsaning miqdori.
column14: Boss zavodning mahsulot ishlab chiqarishini oshirish uchun ko'proq ishchilarni yolladi.

example: Overpopulation is the state of having too many people in an area.
type: The organization is concerned with overpopulation of the world.
example_tr: Aholining haddan tashqari ko'payishi - bu hududda juda ko'p odamlarning mavjudligi holati.
column14: Tashkilot dunyo aholisining haddan tashqari ko'payishi bilan shug'ullanadi.

example: A patent is a right to be the only person allowed to make or sell a new product.
type: He quickly established a patent for his brilliant invention.
example_tr: Patent - bu yangi mahsulotni ishlab chiqarish yoki sotish huquqiga ega bo'lgan yagona shaxs bo'lish huquqi.
column14: U tezda o'zining ajoyib ixtirosi uchun patent yaratdi.

example: To penalize someone means to punish him or her.
type: The team was penalized when they broke the rules.
example_tr: Biror kishini jazolash, uni jazolashni anglatadi.
column14: Jamoa qoidalarni buzgani uchun jarimaga tortildi.

example: Petroleum is a liquid natural resource from which many fuels are made.
type: The petroleum at that factory is used to make gasoline.
example_tr: Neft suyuq tabiiy resurs bo'lib, undan ko'plab yoqilg'ilar tayyorlanadi.
column14: O'sha zavoddagi neft benzin ishlab chiqarish uchun ishlatiladi.

example: A prototype is a new machine that is not ready to be made in large quantities.
type: He introduced his prototype to the motorcycle company.
example_tr: Prototip - bu katta miqdorda ishlab chiqarishga tayyor bo'lmagan yangi mashina.
column14: U o'zining prototipini mototsikl kompaniyasiga taqdim etdi.

example: A scrap of something is a small amount of it.
type: Chris liked to use many scraps of paper when thinking up ideas.
example_tr: Biror narsaning parchasi - bu uning kichik miqdori.
column14: Kris g'oyalarni o'ylashda ko'plab qog'oz parchalaridan foydalanishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: A sector is a part of a country’s economy in a specific type of industry.
type: We learned about just a few of the factories within the manufacturing sector.
example_tr: Sektor - sanoatning muayyan turidagi mamlakat iqtisodiyotining bir qismi.
column14: Biz ishlab chiqarish sektoridagi zavodlarning bir nechtasi haqida bilib oldik.

example: To subscribe to something is to agree or to concur with it.
type: She subscribed to the view that musical education should be kept in schools.
example_tr: Biror narsaga obuna bo'lish - unga rozi bo'lish yoki rozi bo'lish.
column14: U maktablarda musiqa ta'limini saqlab qolish kerak degan fikrga qo'shildi.

example: To subsist means to have the food, water, and money needed to stay alive.
type: Some people are forced to subsist on only a few dollars a month.
example_tr: Yashash yashash uchun zarur bo'lgan oziq-ovqat, suv va pulga ega bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar oyiga bir necha dollarga kun kechirishga majbur.

example: To suspend something means to delay or stop it from happening for a while.
type: The oil company suspended production until it was sure the factory was safe.
example_tr: Biror narsani to'xtatib qo'yish, uni biroz vaqtga kechiktirish yoki to'xtatish demakdir.
column14: Neft kompaniyasi zavod xavfsizligiga ishonch hosil qilmaguncha ishlab chiqarishni to'xtatdi.

example: A synthesis is a combination of different ideas or styles.
type: The band’s music was a synthesis of many different musical genres.
example_tr: Sintez - bu turli g'oyalar yoki uslublarning kombinatsiyasi.
column14: Guruh musiqasi turli xil musiqiy janrlarning sintezi edi.

example: An acrobat is a person who entertains people by doing amazing physical things.
type: There were acrobats at the circus that did impressive and complicated jumps.
example_tr: Akrobat - bu ajoyib jismoniy narsalarni qilish orqali odamlarni xursand qiladigan odam.
column14: Sirkda ta'sirchan va murakkab sakrashlarni amalga oshiruvchi akrobatlar bor edi.

example: Advocacy is the act of supporting or recommending something.
type: janine’s strong advocacy for the event made people want to attend.
example_tr: Advokatlik - biror narsani qo'llab-quvvatlash yoki tavsiya qilish harakati.
column14: Janinening ushbu tadbirga kuchli targ'iboti odamlarni ishtirok etish istagini uyg'otdi.

example: If something is communal, it involves a group of people.
type: On the weekends, Theo and his son picked up trash in the communal park.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa umumiy bo'lsa, u bir guruh odamlarni o'z ichiga oladi.
column14: Dam olish kunlari Teo va uning o'g'li kommunal bog'da axlat yig'ishdi.

example: If something is fluid, it is smooth and moves gracefully.
type: Boris was a famous ballet dancer because people admired his fluid movements
example_tr: Agar biror narsa suyuq bo'lsa, u silliq va nozik harakat qiladi.
column14: Boris mashhur balet raqqosi edi, chunki odamlar uning suyuq harakatlariga qoyil qolishdi

example: To harmonize means to make different things go well together.
type: The sweet and sour flavors of the dish harmonized well and tasted great.
example_tr: Uyg'unlashtirish turli xil narsalarni bir-biriga moslashtirishni anglatadi.
column14: Taomning shirin va nordon ta'mi yaxshi uyg'unlashdi va ajoyib ta'mga ega edi.

example: If someone is industrious, they work hard.
type: Dennis was very industrious, so he never had problems finding a job.
example_tr: Agar kimdir mehnatsevar bo'lsa, u qattiq ishlaydi.
column14: Dennis juda mehnatkash edi, shuning uchun u hech qachon ish topishda muammoga duch kelmadi.

example: When someone is inventive, they are good at creating new things.
type: The inventive student built a robot to help her with her chores.
example_tr: Agar kimdir ixtirochi bo'lsa, u yangi narsalarni yaratishda yaxshi.
column14: Ixtirochi talaba unga uy ishlarida yordam berish uchun robot yasadi.

example: If something is judicial, it is related to judges or courts of law.
type: The laws changed the way the judicial system was structured.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa sud bo'lsa, u sudyalar yoki sudlar bilan bog'liq.
column14: Qonunlar sud tizimining tuzilishini o'zgartirdi.

example: Mandarin is one of the two main Chinese languages.
type: Although John’s parents both spoke Mandarin, he could only speak English,
example_tr: Mandarin ikki asosiy xitoy tillaridan biridir.
column14: Jonning ota-onasi ikkalasi ham mandarin tilida gaplashsa ham, u faqat ingliz tilida gapira olardi,

example: If something is metropolitan, it relates to a large city.
type: All of the metropolitan excitement of New York City made Rufus nervous.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa metropoliten bo'lsa, u katta shaharga tegishli.
column14: Nyu-Yorkdagi barcha poytaxt hayajonlari Rufusni asabiylashtirdi.

example: To mimic something means to copy the way it sounds or moves.
type: The hunter mimicked a duck’s call and shot the two ducks that called back.
example_tr: Biror narsaga taqlid qilish uning tovushini yoki harakatini nusxalashni anglatadi.
column14: Ovchi o'rdakning chaqirig'iga taqlid qildi va orqaga chaqirgan ikkita o'rdakni otdi.

example: When something is misguided, it is based on bad judgment or wrong beliefs.
type: The snake bit Molly during her misguided attempt to grab it.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa noto'g'ri bo'lsa, u noto'g'ri hukm yoki noto'g'ri e'tiqodga asoslanadi.
column14: Ilon Mollini ushlashga urinayotganda tishlab oldi.

example: To rehearse means to practice and prepare for a performance in front of people.
type: Vick’s band rehearsed all week before their first show.
example_tr: Repetitsiya deganda odamlar oldida mashq qilish va chiqishga tayyorgarlik ko'rish tushuniladi.
column14: Vik guruhi birinchi namoyishidan oldin butun hafta davomida mashq qilishdi.

example: To scorn someone means to behave without respect toward them.
type: The criminal was scorned by everyone in the community.
example_tr: Biror kishini kamsitish, unga nisbatan hurmatsiz munosabatda bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Jinoyatchi jamiyatda hamma tomonidan nafratlandi.

example: If something is sensory, it is related to the senses.
type: Iris and Eric preferred the sensory thrill of watching movies in the theater.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa hissiy bo'lsa, u hislar bilan bog'liq.
column14: Iris va Erik teatrda filmlarni tomosha qilish hissiy hayajonni afzal ko'rishdi.

example: If something is staple, it is standard or basic.
type: Hamburgers, steaks and hotdogs are staple foods to cook on a grill.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa asosiy bo'lsa, u standart yoki asosiy hisoblanadi.
column14: Gamburgerlar, biftek va hotdoglar grilda pishirish uchun asosiy taomlardir.

example: A statute is a law that is official and has been written down.
type: The new statute made it illegal to walk dogs in the park.
example_tr: Nizom - bu rasmiy bo'lgan va yozib olingan qonun.
column14: Yangi nizom parkda itlar bilan yurishni noqonuniy qildi.

example: A veteran is someone who has a lot of experience doing something.
type: Hank was the team veteran and had played in more games than anyone else.
example_tr: Veteran - bu biror narsa qilishda katta tajribaga ega bo'lgan kishi.
column14: Xenk jamoa faxriysi edi va boshqalardan ko'ra ko'proq o'yinlarda o'ynagan.

example: A villain is an evil person who breaks the law or hurts others.
type: The villain escaped with half of my family’s valuables.
example_tr: Yovuz odam qonunni buzadigan yoki boshqalarni xafa qiladigan yovuz odamdir.
column14: Yovuz odam oilamning qimmatbaho buyumlarining yarmini olib qochib ketdi.

example: A vine is a plant that has long, twisting stems and climbs upward.
type: The branches of the trees were covered with vines.
example_tr: Tok - uzun, burama poyaga ega va yuqoriga ko'tariladigan o'simlik.
column14: Daraxtlarning shoxlari uzum bilan qoplangan.

example: To constrain something means to limit its development.
type: Jim cannot join us because he is constrained by previous plans.
example_tr: Biror narsani cheklash uning rivojlanishini cheklash demakdir.
column14: Jim bizga qo'shila olmaydi, chunki u avvalgi rejalari bilan cheklangan.

example: A depot is a bus or train station.
type: He waited for his mother to arrive at the depot.
example_tr: Depo - bu avtobus yoki poezd stantsiyasi.
column14: Depoga onasining kelishini kutdi.

example: To emulate people means to imitate them because they are greatly admired.
type: As a small boy, he always tried to emulate his big brother.
example_tr: Odamlarga taqlid qilish ularga taqlid qilishni anglatadi, chunki ular juda hayratda.
column14: Kichkina bolaligida u doimo katta akasiga taqlid qilishga harakat qildi.

example: The forefinger is the finger between one’s thumb and middle finger.
type: He shouted, “There it is!” and pointed with his forefinger.
example_tr: Ko'rsatkich barmog'i - bosh va o'rta barmoqlar orasidagi barmoq.
column14: U baqirdi: "Mana bu!" va ko'rsatkich barmog'i bilan ishora qildi.

example: The guts are all the organs inside a person or animal.
type: The doctor can tell you every process that happens in one’s guts.
example_tr: Ichaklar odam yoki hayvon ichidagi barcha organlardir.
column14: Shifokor sizga insonning ichaklarida sodir bo'ladigan har bir jarayonni aytib berishi mumkin.

example: When something is inherent, it is a natural part of something else.
type: Sweating is an inherent bodily function when exercising.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa tabiatan bo'lsa, u boshqa narsaning tabiiy qismidir.
column14: Jismoniy mashqlar paytida terlash tananing o'ziga xos funktsiyasidir.

example: To intimidate means to frighten others.
type: My dad intimidates my friends whenever they visit.
example_tr: Qo'rqitish, boshqalarni qo'rqitish demakdir.
column14: Dadam do'stlarimga tashrif buyurishganda ularni qo'rqitadi.

example: A janitor is a person who makes repairs and takes care of a building.
type: The school janitor cleaned up the messy cafeteria.
example_tr: Farrosh - binoni ta'mirlash va parvarish qilish bilan shug'ullanadigan shaxs.
column14: Maktab farroshi tartibsiz choyxonani yig‘ishtirib qo‘ydi.

example: When something is moist, it is slightly wet.
type: The ground is still moist from the rain last night.
example_tr: Biror narsa nam bo'lsa, u bir oz nam bo'ladi.
column14: Kecha yomg‘irdan yer hali ham nam.

example: Nope is an informal way of saying “no.”
type: He asked if I had any money, and I had to say, “Nope.”
example_tr: Yo'q - bu "yo'q" deyishning norasmiy usuli.
column14: U menda pul bor-yo'qligini so'radi va men "Yo'q" deyishga majbur bo'ldim.

example: To prod means to push someone or something with a finger or pointed object.
type: The bully prodded me in the chest with his finger.
example_tr: Prod - barmog'i yoki uchi uchli narsa bilan kimnidir yoki biror narsani surish demakdir.
column14: Bezori barmog‘i bilan ko‘ksimga turtib qo‘ydi.

example: A ransom is a sum of money paid to a kidnapper to set the person free.
type: He kidnapped the prince and demanded $1 million as ransom.
example_tr: To'lov bu odamni ozod qilish uchun o'g'irlaganga to'langan pul summasidir.
column14: U shahzodani o'g'irlab ketgan va to'lov sifatida 1 million dollar talab qilgan.

example: To restrain someone or something means to use physical strength to stop them.
type: Mike restrained Allen from reaching the door.
example_tr: Biror kishini yoki biror narsani ushlab turish, uni to'xtatish uchun jismoniy kuch ishlatishni anglatadi.
column14: Mayk Allenni eshikka yetib borishini to'xtatdi.

example: Saliva is the watery liquid in people’s mouths that helps in digestion.
type: The baby could not keep the saliva from dripping out of its mouth.
example_tr: Tuprik odamlarning og'zidagi suvli suyuqlik bo'lib, ovqat hazm qilishga yordam beradi.
column14: Chaqaloq og'zidan tupurik oqib chiqmasligini uddalay olmadi.

example: To spit means to force liquid from one’s mouth.
type: He emerged from the pool and spit water from his mouth.
example_tr: Tupurish og'zidan suyuqlik chiqarishni anglatadi.
column14: U hovuzdan chiqdi va og'zidan suv tupurdi.

example: To sprint means to run very fast over a short distance.
type: The kids didn’t want to be late to class, so they sprinted to the bus stop.
example_tr: Sprint qisqa masofaga juda tez yugurishni anglatadi.
column14: Bolalar darsga kechikishni xohlamadilar, shuning uchun ular avtobus bekatiga yugurishdi.

example: A stunt is something that is done in order to get attention or publicity.
type: The man jumped over the cars as a promotional stunt.
example_tr: Kaskadyor - bu e'tiborni jalb qilish yoki reklama qilish uchun qilingan narsa.
column14: Erkak reklama maqsadida mashinalar ustidan sakrab o‘tgan.

example: When people are tolerant, they are approved of because they accept others.
type: The tolerant leader thought that everyone was equal regardless of race.
example_tr: Odamlar bag'rikeng bo'lsa, ular boshqalarni qabul qilgani uchun ma'qullanadi.
column14: Tolerant rahbar irqidan qat’iy nazar hamma teng deb hisoblardi.

example: A vampire is a fictional monster that sleeps in a coffin and sucks people’s blood.
type: The vampire snuck up on the woman and bit her in the neck.
example_tr: Vampir - bu tobutda uxlab yotgan va odamlarning qonini so'radigan xayoliy yirtqich hayvon.
column14: Vampir ayolga yashirinib kelib, uning bo'ynidan tishlab oldi.

example: To yawn means to open one’s mouth wide and breathe in air.
type: The child yawned and stretched her arms before bed for the night.
example_tr: Esnash og'zini keng ochib, havodan nafas olishni anglatadi.
column14: Bola esnadi va kechasi uchun yotishdan oldin qo'llarini cho'zdi.

example: An analogy is a connection made between things to show that they are similar.
type: The doctor made an analogy between the human heart and a water pump.
example_tr: Oʻxshatish - bu narsalarning oʻxshashligini koʻrsatish uchun oʻzaro bogʻlanish.
column14: Doktor inson yuragi va suv nasosi o'rtasida o'xshashlik yaratdi.

example: A person's ancestry is the series of people from whom a person descended.
type: We studied our ancestry and found out that we are related to royalty.
example_tr: Insonning nasl-nasabi - bu insonning nasl-nasabi bo'lgan odamlar qatori.
column14: Biz nasl-nasabimizni o‘rganib, shohlarga qarindosh ekanimizni bilib oldik.

example: An archer is a person who uses a bow and arrows.
type: The expert archer hit the target every time.
example_tr: Kamonchi - kamon va o'qlarni ishlatadigan odam.
column14: Mutaxassis kamonchi har safar nishonga tegdi.

example: A conspiracy is a secret plan made by a group of people to do something illegal.
type: Some people think that there was a conspiracy to kill American president John Kennedy.
example_tr: Fitna - bu bir guruh odamlar tomonidan noqonuniy biror narsa qilish uchun tuzilgan yashirin rejadir.
column14: Ba'zi odamlar Amerika prezidenti Jon Kennedini o'ldirish uchun fitna bo'lgan deb o'ylashadi.

example: A deputy is the second-highest-ranking person in a business or government.
type: While the sheriff was ill, the deputy took over his duties.
example_tr: Deputat biznes yoki hukumatdagi ikkinchi eng yuqori martabali shaxsdir.
column14: Sherif kasal bo'lganida, o'rinbosar uning vazifalarini o'z zimmasiga oldi.

example: An earl is a nobleman from Britain.
type: The Earl of Canterbury lived in a huge mansion.
example_tr: Earl - Britaniyalik zodagon.
column14: Kenterberi grafi ulkan qasrda yashagan.

example: When something is fragrant, it has a pleasant smell.
type: The girl picked delicious berries and fragrant flowers.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa xushbo'y bo'lsa, u yoqimli hidga ega.
column14: Qiz mazali rezavorlar va xushbo'y gullarni terdi.

example: A funnel is an object with a wide top and a narrow bottom for pouring liquids.
type: The worker used a funnel when he poured the oil into the engine.
example_tr: Voronka - suyuqliklarni quyish uchun tepasi keng va pastki qismi tor bo'lgan ob'ekt.
column14: Ishchi moyni dvigatelga quyayotganda huni ishlatgan.

example: If something is hereditary, it is a trait passed onto children from their parents.
type: The hereditary disease affected three generations of children.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa irsiy bo'lsa, bu ota-onadan bolalarga o'tadigan xususiyatdir.
column14: Irsiy kasallik bolalarning uch avlodiga ta'sir ko'rsatdi.

example: A hymn is a religious song that often praises a god.
type: The book was filled with hymns that the worshippers sang.
example_tr: Madhiya ko'pincha xudoni ulug'laydigan diniy qo'shiqdir.
column14: Kitob namozxonlar kuylagan madhiyalar bilan to'ldirildi.

example: To invert something means to turn it upside down.
type: He inverted the bicycle to make repairs on the wheels.
example_tr: Biror narsani teskari aylantirish, uni teskari aylantirish demakdir.
column14: U g'ildiraklarini ta'mirlash uchun velosipedni teskari aylantirdi.

example: Prey is the animals that are hunted and eaten by another creature.
type: The lion ran as fast as he could to catch his prey.
example_tr: O'lja - bu boshqa jonzot tomonidan ovlanadigan va yeyiladigan hayvonlar.
column14: Arslon o‘ljasini qo‘lga olish uchun bor kuchi bilan yugurdi.

example: A procession is a group of people who walk or drive in a line during a public event.
type: The procession all celebrated when they reached the end.
example_tr: Kortej - ommaviy tadbir paytida bir qatorda yuradigan yoki mashinada yuradigan odamlar guruhi.
column14: Marosim oxiriga yetganda hamma bayramni nishonladi.

example: A prophet is a person chosen by a god to give the god’s message to people.
type: Harold believed that he was one of the prophets of his god.
example_tr: Payg'ambar - bu xudoning xabarini odamlarga etkazish uchun xudo tomonidan tanlangan shaxs.
column14: Garold o'z xudosining payg'ambarlaridan biri ekanligiga ishongan.

example: When something is sarcastic, it is the opposite of what is actually meant.
type: She hurt her mother’s feelings with her constant sarcastic remarks.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa istehzoli bo'lsa, u aslida nazarda tutilgan narsaning aksi bo'ladi.
column14: U doimiy istehzoli gaplari bilan onasining ko'nglini og'ritdi.

example: Seasoning is a mix of salt, herbs, and spices that improves the taste of food.
type: This steak tastes bland. Maybe I'll add some seasoning to it.
example_tr: Ziravorlar - bu taomning ta'mini yaxshilaydigan tuz, o'tlar va ziravorlar aralashmasi.
column14: Bu bifshteksning ta'mi yumshoq. Ehtimol, men unga ziravorlar qo'shaman.

example: Sodium is an element that can be used to make substances such as salt.
type: Sodium and chloride combine to make table salt.
example_tr: Natriy - tuz kabi moddalarni olish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin bo'lgan element.
column14: Natriy va xlorid birlashib, osh tuzini hosil qiladi.

example: A tyranny is a cruel and unfair government in which one person has power.
type: His tyranny was impossible to live under.
example_tr: Zulm - bu bir kishi hokimiyatga ega bo'lgan shafqatsiz va adolatsiz hukumat.
column14: Uning zulmi ostida yashash mumkin emas edi.

example: A tyrant is someone who treats people in a cruel, harsh, and unfair way.
type: Our boss is a tyrant. He makes us work long hours for little pay.
example_tr: Zolim - odamlarga shafqatsiz, qo'pol va adolatsiz munosabatda bo'lgan odam.
column14: Bizning xo'jayinimiz zolim. U bizni oz maosh evaziga uzoq soat ishlashga majbur qiladi.

example: Vinegar is a strong liquid made from sour wine that is used in cooking.
type: Be careful because too much vinegar will ruin the recipe.
example_tr: Sirka - pishirishda ishlatiladigan nordon sharobdan tayyorlangan kuchli suyuqlik.
column14: Ehtiyot bo'ling, chunki juda ko'p sirka retseptni buzadi.

example: If something is adjoining, it is next to or joined with a building, or room.
type: I couldn’t sleep because the people in the adjoining room were loud.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ulashgan bo'lsa, u bino yoki xonaning yonida yoki u bilan birlashtirilgan.
column14: Men uxlay olmadim, chunki qo'shni xonadagi odamlar baland ovozda edi.

example: To allege something is to say that it is true without offering proof.
type: The little girl had alleged that her older brother hid her favorite doll.
example_tr: Biror narsani da'vo qilish - bu dalil keltirmasdan haqiqat deb aytish.
column14: Kichkina qiz akasi sevimli qo'g'irchog'ini yashirganini da'vo qilgan.

example: An arch is a curved opening formed under a structure such as a bridge or doorway.
type: The arch of the bridge was not high enough for the tall boat to pass underneath.
example_tr: Ark - ko'prik yoki eshik teshigi kabi inshoot ostida hosil bo'lgan kavisli teshik.
column14: Ko‘prik arki baland qayiqning ostidan o‘tishi uchun unchalik baland emas edi.

example: To assemble means to get together in one place.
type: The parents assembled to discuss ways to improve their children’s education.
example_tr: Yig‘ilish, bir joyda yig‘ilish demakdir.
column14: Ota-onalar farzandlarining ta'limini yaxshilash yo'llarini muhokama qilish uchun yig'ilishdi.

example: A casualty is a person killed or injured in a war or an accident.
type: The only casualty in the car accident was a woman who broke her arm.
example_tr: Qurbon - urush yoki baxtsiz hodisada halok bo'lgan yoki yaralangan shaxs.
column14: Avtohalokatda jabrlangan yagona ayol qo‘lini sindirib olgan.

example: To erect something means to build it.
type: The king erected two towers on the north and south sides of his castle.
example_tr: Biror narsani qurish, uni qurish demakdir.
column14: Podshoh o‘z qasrining shimoliy va janubiy tomoniga ikkita minora qurdirdi.

example: IF something is foul, then it is not pleasant or enjoyable.
type: He wouldn't let his dog drink from the water because it had a foul smell.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa yomon bo'lsa, u yoqimli yoki yoqimli emas.
column14: Itiga suv ichishga ruxsat bermadi, chunki uning hidi yomon edi.

example: A hectare is a unit of measure equal to 10, 000 square meters.
type: His family farm covered many hectares.
example_tr: Gektar - 10 000 kvadrat metrga teng o'lchov birligi.
column14: Uning oilaviy xo‘jaligi ko‘p gektar maydonni egallagan.

example: To heighten an emotion means to increase the intensity of it.
type: The pleasant music heightened their enjoyment of the wonderful dinner.
example_tr: Tuyg'uni kuchaytirish, uning intensivligini oshirishni anglatadi.
column14: Yoqimli musiqa ularning ajoyib kechki ovqatdan zavqini oshirdi.

example: Hospitality is friendly behavior and entertainment given to guests or strangers.
type: The travelers were amazed at the hospitality given them by the hotel’s staff.
example_tr: Mehmondo'stlik - bu mehmonlarga yoki notanishlarga do'stona xatti-harakatlar va o'yin-kulgi.
column14: Sayohatchilar mehmonxona xodimlarining mehmondo'stligidan hayratda qolishdi.

example: A mansion is a large and expensive home.
type: The mansion had thirty bedrooms, two kitchens, and a pool.
example_tr: Saroy katta va qimmat uydir.
column14: Saroyda o'ttizta yotoq xonasi, ikkita oshxona va basseyn bor edi.

example: To outnumber a group means to have a greater number than it.
type: The girls outnumbered the boys at the school by four to one.
example_tr: Guruhdan oshib ketish, undan ko'p songa ega bo'lishni anglatadi.
column14: Qizlar maktabdagi o'g'il bolalardan to'rt baravar ko'p edi.

example: If someone is overjoyed, then they are extremely happy.
type: He was overjoyed by the news of his promotion.
example_tr: Agar kimdir juda xursand bo'lsa, u juda baxtlidir.
column14: Uning lavozimga ko‘tarilishi haqidagi xabardan u juda xursand bo‘ldi.

example: A pasture is an area of land covered with grass for animals to use as food.
type: The sheep were taken to a pasture where there was more grass.
example_tr: Yaylov - hayvonlarning ozuqa sifatida foydalanishi uchun o't bilan qoplangan yer maydoni.
column14: Qo‘ylarni o‘t ko‘proq yaylovga olib ketishdi.

example: A petition is a written request asking an authority to do something.
type: The citizens all signed a petition asking the mayor to repair the sidewalks.
example_tr: Ariza - bu hokimiyatdan biror narsa qilishni so'rab yozma ariza.
column14: Fuqarolarning barchasi shahar hokimidan yo‘laklarni ta’mirlashni so‘rab arizaga imzo chekishdi.

example: To renovate a building means to repair it or build new structures on it.
type: The old fire station was renovated into an apartment building.
example_tr: Binoni ta'mirlash, uni ta'mirlash yoki uning ustiga yangi inshootlar qurish demakdir.
column14: Eski o‘t o‘chirish stantsiyasi ko‘p qavatli uyga aylantirildi.

example: To revise something means to change or update it to make it better.
type: When the editor discovered certain facts were wrong, he revised the book.
example_tr: Biror narsani qayta ko'rib chiqish, uni yaxshilash uchun uni o'zgartirish yoki yangilashni anglatadi.
column14: Muharrir ba'zi faktlar noto'g'ri ekanligini bilib, kitobni qayta ko'rib chiqdi.

example: A slab is a large, thick, flat piece of stone, concrete, metal, or wood.
type: I looked at various slabs of stone to decorate my house.
example_tr: Plita - tosh, beton, metall yoki yog'ochdan yasalgan katta, qalin, tekis bo'lak.
column14: Uyimni bezash uchun turli tosh plitalarga qaradim.

example: A terrace is an open area that is connected to a house or an apartment.
type: In the afternoons, she liked to sit on the terrace and check her email.
example_tr: Teras - bu uy yoki kvartira bilan bog'langan ochiq maydon.
column14: Peshindan keyin u terastada o'tirishni va elektron pochtasini tekshirishni yaxshi ko'rardi.

example: Turf is a section of grass and the dirt in which it grows.
type: After the game, the turf looked ragged.
example_tr: Maysa - bu o't va u o'sadigan axloqsizlikning bir qismi.
column14: O'yindan so'ng chim yirtiq ko'rindi.

example: If something is analogous to another thing, then it is like it in certain ways.
type: The relationship with his teacher was analogous to that of a son and mother.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsaga o'xshash bo'lsa, u ma'lum jihatdan unga o'xshaydi.
column14: Uning ustozi bilan munosabatlari o'g'il va onaning munosabatiga o'xshardi.

example: Binoculars are a device used for seeing things that are far away.
type: He could see the ship on the horizon only if he used his binoculars.
example_tr: Dürbün uzoqdagi narsalarni ko'rish uchun ishlatiladigan qurilma.
column14: U ufqda turgan kemani faqat durbin yordamida ko‘ra olardi.

example: The bulk of something is its great size.
type: The large elephant moved its bulk with legs as strong as tree trunks.
example_tr: Biror narsaning asosiy qismi uning katta hajmidir.
column14: Katta fil daraxt tanasi kabi kuchli oyoqlari bilan asosiy qismini harakatga keltirdi.

example: If something comprises something else, it consists of or is made up of it.
type: Our school’s football team is mostly comprised with seniors.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa boshqa narsani o'z ichiga olsa, u undan iborat yoki undan iborat.
column14: Maktabimiz futbol jamoasi asosan katta yoshdagilardan iborat.

example: To depict something means to show or portray it, often using art.
type: The statue’s face depicted the general's determination and courage.
example_tr: Biror narsani tasvirlash, ko'pincha san'atdan foydalanib, uni ko'rsatish yoki tasvirlashni anglatadi.
column14: Haykalning yuzida generalning qat'iyati va jasorati tasvirlangan.

example: If something is dual, then it is made up of two parts.
type: The room had a dual function. It was a living room, but at night it was a bedroom.
example_tr: Agar biror narsa ikki tomonlama bo'lsa, u ikki qismdan iborat.
column14: Xona ikki tomonlama funktsiyaga ega edi. Bu yashash xonasi edi, lekin kechalari yotoqxona edi.

example: Fahrenheit temperature is a scale where water freezes at 32° and boils at 212°.
type: When the temperature dropped to 32° Fahrenheit, it started snowing.
example_tr: Farengeyt harorati - suv 32 ° da muzlab, 212 ° qaynaydigan shkala.
column14: Harorat Farangeyt 32 ° ga tushganda, qor yog'a boshladi.

example: To fulfill something means to achieve or finish it.
type: The professor did not fulfill his promise not to miss a single class.
example_tr: Biror narsani bajarish, unga erishish yoki tugatish demakdir.
column14: Professor bitta darsni qoldirmaslik haqidagi va'dasini bajarmadi.

example: A grove is a small group of trees.
type: All the trees in this grove are apple trees.
example_tr: Toʻqay — bu daraxtlarning kichik guruhi.
column14: Bu bog‘dagi barcha daraxtlar olma daraxtlari.

example: Ore is the raw form of rock or material from which a valuable metal is taken.
type: The factory melted the ore and used it to make iron products.
example_tr: Ruda - qimmatbaho metal olinadigan tosh yoki materialning xom shakli.
column14: Zavod rudani eritib, undan temir buyumlar ishlab chiqarish uchun foydalanardi.

example: The outback is the wild inland region of Australia where very few people live.
type: Many Australian farmers use the outback to raise cattle.
example_tr: Outback Avstraliyaning yovvoyi ichki hududi bo'lib, u erda juda kam odam yashaydi.
column14: Ko'pgina avstraliyalik fermerlar chorva mollarini boqish uchun chetdan foydalanadilar.

example: To outweigh something means to exceed it in value, amount, or importance.
type: Finding a warm place to sleep outweighed the need to find something to eat.
example_tr: Biror narsadan ustun bo'lish, uning qiymati, miqdori yoki ahamiyati bo'yicha oshib ketishni anglatadi.
column14: Uxlash uchun issiq joy topish, ovqatlanish uchun biror narsa topish zaruratidan ustun keldi.

example: A paradox is a true statement or real event that seems illogical.
type: The paradox of her work was that the less she worked, the more she got done.
example_tr: Paradoks - bu mantiqsiz ko'rinadigan haqiqiy bayonot yoki haqiqiy voqea.
column14: Uning ishining paradoksi shundaki, u qanchalik kam ishlasa, shunchalik ko'p ish qilgan.

example: A pier is a structure that extends into a body of water.
type: If you want to catch bigger fish, then go to the far end of the pier.
example_tr: Pirs - bu suv havzasiga cho'zilgan inshoot.
column14: Agar siz kattaroq baliq tutmoqchi bo'lsangiz, iskala chetiga boring.

example: A shortcut is a route that is shorter than the main route.
type: We got to the house first because we took a shortcut through the forest.
example_tr: Yorliq asosiy marshrutdan qisqaroq marshrutdir.
column14: Biz uyga birinchi bo'lib keldik, chunki biz o'rmon bo'ylab yorliq oldik.

example: A tariff is a tax or fee paid on certain imports or exports.
type: Our tariff on imported wool makes foreign wool more expensive.
example_tr: Tarif - muayyan import yoki eksport uchun to'lanadigan soliq yoki yig'im.
column14: Import qilingan junga tarifimiz xorijiy junni qimmatroq qiladi.

example: A thermometer is a device that measures temperature.
type: The thermometer outside the window indicated that it was a hot day today.
example_tr: Termometr - bu haroratni o'lchaydigan qurilma.
column14: Deraza tashqarisidagi termometr bugun issiq kun ekanligini ko‘rsatdi.

example: To tilt something means to tip it into a sloping position.
type: She tilted her glass and almost spilled some of the wine inside.
example_tr: Biror narsani egish, uni eğimli holatga keltirishni anglatadi.
column14: U qadahni egib, ichkaridagi sharobni to‘kib yuborishiga sal qoldi.

example: If a statement is vice versa, then its two main ideas are switched with one another.
type: Students learn from their teachers, and vice versa.
example_tr: Agar bayonot aksincha bo'lsa, unda uning ikkita asosiy g'oyasi bir-biri bilan almashtiriladi.
column14: Talabalar o'z o'qituvchilaridan o'rganadilar va aksincha.

example: The whereabouts of someone or something is the place where they are.
type: The police looked for the lost dog, but its whereabouts were still unknown.
example_tr: Biror kishining yoki biror narsaning joylashgan joyi - ular joylashgan joy.
column14: Politsiya yo'qolgan itni qidirdi, ammo uning qayerda ekanligi hali ham noma'lum.

example: Amber is a hard, yellowish material that comes from trees.
type: The necklace was made from pieces of amber.
example_tr: Amber - bu daraxtlardan keladigan qattiq, sarg'ish material.
column14: Marjon kehribar parchalaridan yasalgan.

example: Charcoal is a black material that is used as fuel for fire.
type: There was burnt charcoal left on the ground from an old fire.
example_tr: Ko'mir - olov uchun yoqilg'i sifatida ishlatiladigan qora material.
column14: Qadimgi olovdan yerda kuygan ko‘mir qolgan edi.

example: A columnist is a writer who creates articles about a particular subject.
type: The columnist won praise for his articles about life on the farm.
example_tr: Kolonist - bu ma'lum bir mavzu bo'yicha maqolalar yaratadigan yozuvchi.
column14: Kolumnist fermadagi hayot haqidagi maqolalari uchun maqtovga sazovor bo'ldi.

example: When someone is courteous, they are polite and respectful.
type: The mother asked her family to be courteous to their guests.
example_tr: Biror kishi xushmuomala bo'lsa, u muloyim va hurmatli bo'ladi.
column14: Ona oilasidan mehmonlarga xushmuomala bo'lishni so'radi.

example: Credentials are the proof of someone’s experience or ability to do something.
type: The mechanic hung his credentials on his office wall.
example_tr: Hisob ma'lumotlari kimningdir tajribasi yoki biror narsa qilish qobiliyatining isbotidir.
column14: Mexanik ishonchnomalarini ishxonasi devoriga osib qo‘ydi.

example: A cricket is an insect that makes loud noises, usually at night.
type: In the country, we could see the stars and hear the crickets at night.
example_tr: Kriket - bu odatda tunda baland tovushlarni chiqaradigan hasharotlar.
column14: Mamlakatda biz kechalari yulduzlarni ko'rishimiz va kriketlarni eshitishimiz mumkin edi.

example: A delta is a flat area where a river splits into smaller rivers that flow into the sea.
type: The archeologists found many ancient materials in the delta of the Nile River.
example_tr: Delta - daryoning dengizga quyiladigan kichikroq daryolarga bo'linadigan tekis hudud.
column14: Arxeologlar Nil daryosining deltasidan ko'plab qadimiy materiallarni topdilar.

example: Detergent is soap that is used to clean clothes or dishes.
type: My brother added too much detergent to the wash, and bubbles got all over the floor.
example_tr: Yuvish vositasi - bu kiyim yoki idishlarni tozalash uchun ishlatiladigan sovun.
column14: Akam yuvish uchun juda ko'p detarjan qo'shib qo'ydi va pufakchalar hamma joyda paydo bo'ldi.

example: A euphemism is a term that is used in place of a mean or unpleasant word.
type: "Window maintenance officer" is a euphemism for a window washer.
example_tr: Evfemizm - bu o'rtacha yoki yoqimsiz so'z o'rnida ishlatiladigan atama.
column14: "Derazalarga texnik xizmat ko'rsatuvchi ofitser" - bu deraza yuvish uchun evfemizm.

example: To expire is to no longer be effective because its use has come to an end.
type: The man’s driver's license was going to expire in two days.
example_tr: Yaroqlilik muddati tugashi endi samarali bo'lmaydi, chunki undan foydalanish tugadi.
column14: Erkakning haydovchilik guvohnomasi ikki kundan keyin tugashi kerak edi.

example: Granite is a very hard type of rock that is often black or pink.
type: The kitchen counter was made of granite.
example_tr: Granit ko'pincha qora yoki pushti rangga ega bo'lgan juda qattiq jinsdir.
column14: Oshxona peshtaxtasi granitdan qilingan.

example: Gravel is a combination of small stones mixed with sand.
type: The ground around the swing set was covered with gravel.
example_tr: Shag'al - qum bilan aralashtirilgan kichik toshlarning kombinatsiyasi.
column14: Belanchak majmuasi atrofidagi yer shag'al bilan qoplangan.

example: To haunt is to cause problems or negative thoughts over a long period of time.
type: His thoughts about his scary dream haunted him for weeks.
example_tr: Ta'qib qilish - uzoq vaqt davomida muammolar yoki salbiy fikrlarni keltirib chiqarishdir.
column14: Uning qo'rqinchli tushi haqidagi fikrlari uni haftalar davomida ta'qib qildi.

example: When someone is liberal, they accept different ideas and people.
type: My grandparents aren’t as liberal as my parents.
example_tr: Kimdir liberal bo'lsa, u turli g'oyalar va odamlarni qabul qiladi.
column14: Mening bobom va buvim ota-onam kabi erkin emaslar.

example: A maze is a system of paths that is complicated and easy to get lost in.
type: We got lost in the maze in the garden.
example_tr: Labirint - bu murakkab va adashib qolish oson bo'lgan yo'llar tizimi.
column14: Biz bog‘dagi labirintda adashib qoldik.

example: Moss is a small green or yellow plant that grows on wet dirt, rocks, or tree trunks.
type: Be careful not to slip on the moss that’s covering those rocks.
example_tr: Moss - ho'l tuproqlarda, toshlarda yoki daraxt tanasida o'sadigan kichik yashil yoki sariq o'simlik.
column14: O'sha toshlarni qoplagan moxga sirpanib tushmaslik uchun ehtiyot bo'ling.

example: When a bird pecks, it bites or hits something with its beak.
type: The birds pecked at the seeds on the ground.
example_tr: Qush cho‘ksa, tumshug‘i bilan biror narsani tishlaydi yoki uradi.
column14: Qushlar yerdagi urug‘larni paypasladi.

example: A reservoir is a place for storing water for a town to use.
type: If it doesn’t rain soon, the reservoir is going to dry up completely.
example_tr: Suv ombori - bu shaharning foydalanishi uchun suvni saqlash joyi.
column14: Tez orada yomg'ir yog'masa, suv ombori butunlay quriydi.

example: A streak is a long, thin mark that is easy to see.
type: Her hair was brown except for a streak which she dyed blonde.
example_tr: Chiziq - bu ko'rish oson bo'lgan uzun, ingichka belgi.
column14: Uning sochlari jigarrang edi, lekin u sariq rangga bo'yalgan.

example: A pebble is a small, round stone.
type: We threw pebbles into the lake to make the water splash.
example_tr: Shag'al - kichik, yumaloq tosh.
column14: Suvni chayqash uchun ko'lga toshlarni tashladik.

example: To testify means to give evidence as a witness.
type: The judge listened while the victim testified about the robbery.
example_tr: Guvohlik qilish, guvoh sifatida ko'rsatma berish demakdir.
column14: Jabrlanuvchi o'g'irlik haqida ko'rsatma berayotganda sudya tingladi.
